Name: 16”/50 caliber Mark 7 gun
Summary: The 16"/50 (40.6 cm) caliber gun Mark 7 was the main armament of the Iowa-class battleships. This was possibly the best battleship gun ever put into service. Originally intended to fire the relatively light 2240 pound (1016 kg) AP Mark 5 projectile, the shell handling system for these guns was redesigned to use the "super-heavy" 2700 pound (1224.7 kg) AP Mark 8 before any of the USS Iowa class (BB-61) battleships were laid down.

Name: 5”/38 caliber Mark 12 gun
Summary: The 5"/38 (12.7 cm) caliber gun Mark 12 was a US naval gun. It was unquestionably the finest dual purpose gun of World War II. Originally designed to arm new destroyers being built in the 1930s, the 5"/38 (12.7 cm) wound up being used on nearly every major US warship built between 1934 and 1945 and was still being used on new construction as late as the 1960s.

Name: 6"/47 caliber Mark 16 gun
Summary: The 6"/47 (15.2 cm) caliber gun Mark 16 was a feature of many US Navy light cruisers during World War II. These guns were used to arm the Brooklyn- and Cleveland-class light cruisers, the latter being the most numerous class of cruisers ever built. The 6"/47 caliber gun was one of several weapons developed by the United States Navy in the 1930s to fire "super-heavy" armor-piercing projectiles, thus increasing warships' destructive power while complying with the limits on bore diameter set by the London Naval Treaty. Compared with the previous 6"/53 caliber guns, the 6"/47 Mark 16 fired a 59 kilogram (130 pounds) projectile instead of a 48 kilogram (105 pounds) projectile. These new projectiles had almost double the penetration performance when compared against the older 6"/53 (15.2 cm) AP projectiles used for the Omaha class (CL-4) light cruisers.

Name: 8”/55 caliber Mark 15 gun
Summary: The 8"/55 (20.8 cm) caliber gun Mark 15 formed the main batteries of United States Navy Baltimore, Oregon City, Boston, and Albanyclass cruisers. This gun is similar in construction to the previous 8"/55 caliber Mark 12, and related to the 8"/55 caliber Mark 9, 10, 11, 13, and 14 (but of much lighter construction) which served as the main guns for several earlier heavy cruisers as well as the self-defense guns on the only two Lexington-class aircraft carrier, the first operational aircraft carriers in the US Navy, until their removal at Pearl Harbor in 1942 to be used as coastal artillery It was superseded by the improved 8"/55RF caliber gun Mark 16 by 1948, which were only installed on three Des Moines-class heavy cruisers.

Name: Aarakocra
Summary: Aarakocra are denizens of the Elemental Plane of Air that serve the Wind Dukes of Aaqa. They stand as constantly vigilant scouts and warriors protecting against both invaders of the Elemental Plane of Earth (most notably against gargoyles) and worshippers of Elemental Evil (in their case, Yan-C-Bin). They are duty-bound to eternally attempt to restore the Wind Dukes of Aaqa to their previous state of power as vaati, which was lost when fighting against the Queen of Chaos, the former ruler of the Abyss.

Name: Aaron Tide (The Boxer)
Summary: Aaron Tide was the previous World Heavyweight Boxing Champion, and seemingly the strongest boxer in history. Having never lost a single match due to his monstrous strength and reason defying power, Aaron lived a life of luxury and fame.

Name: Aballin
Summary: While inert one can't tell an Aballin apart from a pool of water, also they often contain treasure from previous victims inside them. But if one is foolish enough to try and drink from the supposed pool of water or take the tressure in it they'll meet an unpleasent surpise of the Aballin morphing into a gelatinous form which tries to suffocate the person.

Name: Aboleth
Summary: Aboleths are ancient, primordial entities that have existed since the creation of the multiverse, supposedly being spontaneously created when the empty void of reality was touched by an alien entity in the Far Realm, allowing the Aboleths to bleed into the multiverse. They formed an empire throughout the void through sheer psionic might, being the gods before gods came to be- though the dawn of these creatures, the gods as we know them, caused the Abolethic Sovereignity to crumble.

Name: AC-130
Summary: The AC-130 is a gunship modification of the C-130 Hercules and is a heavily armed, long endurance ground attack aircraft which carries a variety of various ground attack weapons ranging from machine guns to howitzers. Due to its large profile, low operating altitude, and slow speed making it an easy target, it usually flies close air support missions at night. During an attack, the gunship performs a pylon run, flying a circle around the target.

Name: Accablement & Abattement
Summary: Accablement & Abattement is a pair of sadnesses in the game In Stars and Time, acting as the game’s second floor boss in Dormont’s House of Change.

Name: Achaierai
Summary: Achaierai were evil birds of prey, enormous and flightless, that roamed the pleanes of existence that dedicated themselves wholly to war and despair. Achaierai are known throughout the planes for their vicious nature, lethal torture effects, and their powerful poison.

Name: Addled Frog
Summary: The Addled Frog is a swamp-dwelling creature found in the wetlands surrounding the lair of Auntie Ethel, and is apparently corrupted by her presence. If spoken to by someone who can communicate with animals, its dialogue is unfocused and confused, and can become outright hostile if engaged with for too long. Yet, when Ethel's presence has been cleansed, the frog regains clarity and offers a reward to whomever may have destroyed the hag (or, at least, forced her from her home).

Name: AH-64 Apache
Summary: The Boeing AH-64 Apache is an American twin-turboshaft attack helicopter with a tailwheel-type landing gear arrangement and a tandem cockpit for a crew of two. It features a nose-mounted sensor suite for target acquisition and night vision systems. It is armed with a 30 mm (1.18 in) M230 chain gun carried between the main landing gear, under the aircraft's forward fuselage, and four hard points mounted on stub-wing pylons for carrying armament and stores, typically a mixture of AGM-114 Hellfire missiles and Hydra 70 rocket pods. The AH-64 has a large amount of systems redundancy to improve combat survivability.

Name: Alaghi
Summary: A distant cousin of the Yeti, the Alaghi are a peaceful race of hunters which only kill those they hunt.

Name: Alcatraz (Crysis)
Summary: James "Alcatraz" Rodriquez is the protagonist in Crysis 2 and the novel Crysis: Legion, which contains additional personal background about him. He is a Force Recon Marine originally sent to New York City to (unknowingly) combat the Ceph, before receiving the Crynet Nanosuit 2.0 from Prophet, and ultimately becomes a "reincarnation" of Laurence Barnes, as shown in Crysis 3, having merged with the original's personality and conscious being stored within the nanosuit.

Name: Alder
Summary: Alder (アデク Adeku) is the Champion of the Unova region's Pokémon League in Pokémon Black and White.

Name: Aldo the Cleric
Summary: Aldo the Cleric is one of King of Dragons' selectable characters and protagonists, being one of the heroes that goes against Gildiss, the mighty Red Dragon.

Name: Alfred Pennyworth (Post-Crisis)
Summary: Alfred Pennyworth is the butler of the Wayne Family and the guardian of Bruce Wayne. He served in the military as a field medic, before becoming an actor, retiring, and becoming a butler for the Wayne Family. Following the deaths of Thomas and Martha Wayne, he became Bruce Wayne's legal guardian and raised him to become Batman.

Name: Allip
Summary: An Allip is a powerful undead created from the restless spirit of a being that killed itself. It was driven mad in life and now seeks only revenge on the living, attempting to get vengeance on those who pushed them over the edge.

Name: Almiraj
Summary: The Almiraj at a first glance appears simply as a rabbit with the horn of a unicorn, and while that asessment is true they can still be quite dangerous due to their unpredictable nature and their inante teleportation ability which earned them the nickname Blink Rabbit. An even more dangerous variant of the Almiraj is the Psionic one which has a 10% to appear when ever an Almiraj gives birth, this Almiraj has various abilities such as Detonate and Molecular Agitation which makes it a formidable foe.

Name: Altaïr Ibn-La'Ahad
Summary: Altaïr Ibn-La'Ahad (Arabic: الطائر ابن لا أحد‎, The Bird, Son of None; 1165 – 1257) was a Syrian member of the Levantine Brotherhood of Assassins who served as their Mentor from 1191 until his death in 1257. During his tenure as Mentor, through the knowledge of an Apple of Eden, Altaïr made several discoveries and inventions that greatly helped the Order's progression. His leadership saw to the spread of the Assassins' influence throughout the Old World.

Name: Ambush Drake
Summary: The Ambush Drake is a draconic group predator which uses telepathy to communicate with its own kind, and in combat they use stealth tactics alongside their poisonous breath to defeat opponets. Like dragons they have a natural desire to hoard but a group of Ambush Drakes does not have a concept of private ownership and they share all their belongings.

Name: Anabel (Pokémon)
Summary: Anabel is a Frontier Brain from the Battle Frontier in Pokémon Emerald. While that is the end of her role in Emerald, she plays a bigger part in Pokémon Sun and Moon in the post-game, where it is revealed that she was sucked through an Ultra Wormhole into the Sun/Moon universe, where she becomes part of the International Police and their UB Task Force.

Name: Anarky (Post-Crisis)
Summary: A possible child of the Joker and Linda Penman, Lonnie Machin was a prodigal high school student until influence from anarchist philosophy turned him into the aptly-named vigilante Anarky. Though he was taken down by Batman and sent to a juvenile detention center, he soon escaped to become a consistent adversary to both the Batman and the criminals of Gotham City.

Name: Angajuk
Summary: An old sperm whale, Angajuk is a whale granted human like intelligence by a druid. They are over 200 years old and have been serving as underwater transport system for people for many years. On their back there is a boat which is enchanted to create an air bubble when Angajuk goes underwater in order to let those who ride on him to breath underwater.

Name: Angel of Valor
Summary: The Angel of Valor are the weakest and most numerous of the angels that serve the gods, they are used as foot soldiers of their deities. while following the orders of higher ranking angels or even clerics of their gods.

Name: Ankheg
Summary: Ankhegs are enormous burrowing insects that hunt smaller prey via detecting tremors through the ground. Among the earliest monsters added to Dungeons and Dragons, they have persisted through every edition, providing a solid example of an iconic low-level creature. Invariably an Ankheg is larger than a cattle and tends to weigh just under 400 kilos.

Name: Annis Hag
Summary: Vast talons, foul with human flesh, there grew In place of hands, and her features livid blue, Glared in her visage; whilst her obscene waist Warm skins of human victims embraced.

Name: Ant-Man (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Scott Edward Harris Lang is a former professional criminal who was convinced by Hank Pym to take on the mantle of Ant-Man. He fought against Pym's former protégé Darren Cross, who had gone insane while trying to recreate the Pym Particles, leading to Lang defending his friends, family and the world as the Ant-Man.

Name: Aranea
Summary: Aranea were a species of artificial demi-lycanthropes that maintained the ability to shapeshift from humanoid form to that of an enormous monstrous spider. Long ago they were cast out of their cities once their use in the Night Wars had been completed, and since then have spread and traded through illusions and secret means. Long ago they were purged from their homes in genocide, and took to worshiping demons to get revenge on their attackers.

Name: Archie (Pokémon)
Key: '''By Himself''' | '''Pokémon Team (Mt. Chimney)''' | '''Pokémon Team (Seafloor Cavern)''' | '''Pokémon Team (Battle Maison)''' | '''Pokémon (Team Gen 7)'''
Summary: Archie is the boss of Team Aqua. The player only battles him in Seafloor Cavern in Emerald and Mt. Chimney and Seafloor Cavern in Sapphire. In Ruby, he is an ally to the player on his/her mission to stop Team Magma from expanding the land mass and in Sapphire, he is the main antagonist of the game.

Name: Ardos
Summary: Ardos (Japanese: アルドス Ardos) is one of the five Cipher Admins from Pokémon XD: Gale of Darkness. Ardos is one of Grand Master Greevil's two bodyguards, and is revealed at the end of the game to also be one of Greevil's sons (the other bodyguard/son being his twin brother Eldes).

Name: Arrowhawk
Summary: Arrowhawks were four-winged birds of prey from the Elemental Plane of Air, and were well-known for their ability to fly and levitate indefinitely from the second they were born. Their striking blue plumage was in fact scales developed for protection.

Name: Ascomoid
Summary: The Ascomoid is a big ball of fungus which rolls around the world trying to crush whatever crosses it in order to eat them.

Name: Ashe (League of Legends)
Summary: Iceborn warmother of the Avarosan tribe, Ashe commands the most populous horde in the north. Stoic, intelligent, and idealistic, yet uncomfortable with her role as leader, she taps into the ancestral magics of her lineage to wield a bow of True Ice. With her people’s belief that she is the mythological hero Avarosa reincarnated, Ashe hopes to unify the Freljord once more by retaking their ancient, tribal lands.

Name: Assassin Vine
Summary: Assassin Vines are a typical breed of low-level encounter for any Dungeons and Dragons campaign setting. The concept is one of a simple plant typically found attached to steep walls that reaches out and grabs prey, strangling them and ultimately using their decomposing corpses as fertilizer. Its berries were delicious (presumably as bait) and were known to make a unique sort of wine.

Name: Attuma (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Attuma is a fierce Talokanil warrior and one of Namor's advisors.

Name: Auntie Ethel
Summary: Why are you so cruel? Please. It's you lot who come to me. All you do is want - to be prettier, to be richer, to be loved. People are their own worst enemies, petal. I just let them see it.

Name: Avengers (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Iron Man: How were you guys planning on beating that? Captain America: Together. Iron Man: We'll lose. Captain America: Then we'll do that together, too.

Name: AZ (Pokémon)
Summary: AZ is an important backstory character of Pokémon X & Y. 3,000 years prior, AZ was the King of the Kalos region, at the same time as the war. His Floette was forcibly introduced in the conflict, causing its death. In grief, and in an attempt to revive his lost companion, he built the Ultimate Weapon, which ultimately ended the war, and made him immortal.

Name: Azbara Jos
Summary: Azbara Jos is a Red Wizard of Thay, an organization of magic users attempting to overthrow the rule of the lich Szass Tam. Azbara, in particular, is an associate of Rath Modar, leader of the Red Wizards. The two were once working with the Cult of the Dragon to free Tiamat from the Nine Hells. The Red Wizards are undertaking this endeavor in the hope that the goddess will assist them in the destruction of the Lich. Azbara is arrogant and actively works towards several goals- particularly investigating the portals used by the cult and working alongside their local leader, a dragon named Rezmir.

Name: Azer
Summary: An Azer is a bronze-skinned dwarf forged by the fire giants. Azers serve as warriors for many pantheons of gods, most notably Moradin- though they are not many, as each Azer is forged by his ancestors with excruciating detail. Azers live largely confined to their volcanic kingdom in the Plane of Fire.

Name: B-1 Lancer
Summary: The Rockwell (Now part of Boeing) B-1 Lancer is a four engine, supersonic variable sweep swing strategic bomber developed in the 1960s originally to replace the aging B-52 Stratofortress. The bomber's original design has evolved into the current B-1B Lancer, a low-level penetration bomber with a long range while retaining supersonic capability.

Name: B-17 Flying Fortress
Summary: The B-17 Flying Fortress is a four engine heavy bomber designed by Boeing, primarily employed by the US Army Air Corps in the European theatre as a strategic bomber against German targets, but also saw service albeit in lesser quantities against the Japanese in the Pacific Theatre. The long range, durability, heavy defensive armament, and speed of the aircraft lent it it's reputation as a strategic bomber. Over 10,000 were built over the course of World War II.

Name: B-2 Spirit
Summary: The B-2 Spirit is a 2-seat stealth bomber developed by Northrop-Grumman. It is a heavy penetration strategic bomber sporting low observable stealth technology for piercing into high density air defenses. It is capable of carrying both conventional and nuclear payloads. There are currently 21 built.

Name: Babau
Summary: Babau are the assassins of the Abyss, and will only engage in combat with enemies that it has an advantage over. While not cowardly, the Babau is far from courageous, and carefully analyzes every encounter before engaging. Most lieutenants of the Abyss have a small army of Babau in their pay, to ensure quickly accessible killers for hire.

Name: Bakuto (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Bakuto is a leader of a Hand faction who spent his entire life training under many different masters to become a skilled martial artist. During his training, Bakuto would be told the legend of K'un-Lun and the Immortal Iron Fist who was said to be the Hand's most dangerous enemy. After learning of the Iron Fist's existence, Bakuto would attempt to learn as much as he could on the subject. When Danny Rand was revealed to be alive after being missing for fifteen years, Bakuto, believing Rand to be the new Iron Fist, would travel to New York City to investigate himself.

Name: Baltimore-class Heavy Cruiser
Summary: The Baltimore-class Heavy Cruiser was a large class of heavy cruisers in the United States Navy commissioned during or shortly after World War II. Fourteen Baltimores were completed, more than any other class of heavy cruiser, along with three ships of the Oregon City-class sub-class. Fast and heavily armed, the Baltimore cruisers were mainly used in World War II to protect the fast aircraft carriers in battle groups from air attack. Additionally, their 8"/55 (203mm) main guns and secondary 5"/38 (127mm) guns were regularly used to bombard land targets in support of amphibious landings. After the war, only six Baltimores and two Oregon City-class ships remained in service, while the rest were moved to the reserve fleet.

Name: Bane (Post-Crisis)
Summary: This man was born in the prison of Peña Duro, where he would have to serve a life sentence in the place of his father. He grew up in the prison, and killing one of his fellow prisoners, the guards bestowed a name upon him: Bane. The prison guards locked Bane in a pit for ten years as penance, expecting him to die, but he survived and became a legend to the other inmates. Bane trained his mind and his body and was eventually chosen as a test subject for a drug called Venom. Bane was the only subject who survived the test, and he was subsequently given surgery so the drug could be injected directly into his brain. After faking his own death to escape Peña Duro, Bane returned to free the inmates, kill the warden and steal a helicopter so he could travel to Gotham City, home of the man that Bane wanted to destroy: the Batman.

Name: Barghest
Summary: Barghests are fiendish shapechangers hailing from the plane of Gehenna, though they are often sighted on the Prime Material due to their growth rituals. In essence, they are often sent to the Prime Material to devour powerful mortals so that they may grow in power.

Name: Basilisk (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: Basilisks are reptilian magical creatures bestowed with the capability to turn enemies to stone. Their abilities are renowned enough that a seasoned adventurer will recognize the threat of remaining in the area when they begin seeing remarkably life-like statues of frightened wildlife.

Name: Batman (One Million)
Summary: In 853rd century, it was on the prison planet of Pluto that the seeds would be sowed for this Batman. The planet was home to tens of thousands of the worst criminals from across the galaxy, kept under strict control. However, one day, a virus infected members of the prison guard, driving them utterly insane. In their madness, they released the prisoners. The worst scum of the galaxy routed the remaining guards in hours and took control. They dragged guards and their families to exercise area. It was there that the sadistic prisoners made fifteen thousand children watch as their parents were gunned down over a period of days. The resulting trauma drove hundreds to commit suicide with hundreds more driven mad from the experience. But one child did not succumb. Instead, he took a vow to never allow such an atrocity to occur again. He vowed to become the Batman.

Name: Batman (Thomas Wayne)
Summary: Batman (Thomas Wayne) is a fictional character appearing in American comic books published by DC Comics. Created by Geoff Johns (writer) and Andy Kubert (artist), he made his first appearance in Flashpoint #1 (July 2011). He is a hardened version of Thomas Wayne seen in Geoff Johns's alternate timeline comic Flashpoint (2011) whose son was killed instead of Martha Wayne and himself. His character returned to the main DC Universe in DC Rebirth as a revived amalgamation of his original self that was killed by Joe Chill and the Flashpoint Batman that was killed by Eobard Thawne in a storyline revolving around the "Smiley-face" button from Watchmen.

Name: Batwoman (Post-Crisis)
Summary: Kate Kane is Batwoman, one of many vigilantes who protect Gotham City using the imagery of a Bat. She is both Jewish and an open lesbian, playing a socialite during the day and working with her cousin Bette as vigilantes by night.

Name: Bea (Pokémon)
Key: '''By Herself''' | '''Pokèmon Team (Stow-on-Side Stadium)''' | '''Pokèmon Team (Champion Cup Finals)''' | '''Pokèmon Team (Champion tournament)'''
Summary: Bea (Japanese: サイトウ Saitō) is the Gym Leader of Stow-on-Side's Gym, known officially as Stow-on-Side Stadium. She specializes in Fighting-type Pokémon. She gives the Fighting Badge to Trainers who defeat her. She is also an exclusive Gym Leader on Pokémon Sword.

Name: Bearded Devil
Summary: Bearded Devils (also referred to as Barbazu in the Infernal tongue) are the front line soldiers of the Blood War, and the shock troopers of the Hells. Often seen directly battling the demonic threat along the Styx, Bearded Devils are also known to lead other low-ranking devils in combat. They are most known abroad for their striking beards, which serve as a sort of secondary weapon, and their glaives, which leave horrific wounds that can kill just as easily as the weapons that made them.

Name: Belker
Summary: Belkers are beings made of smoke residing in the Elemental Plane of Air. Such creatures are invariably evil but also reclusive, hiding away from any they might inflict their evil upon. Though their shape changes with the wind, they always present themselves with large bat wings and vile faces, giving them a certain demonic visage.

Name: Bernard (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: New sounds through damp and dark oppression break Is it the foe, that foul, contemptuous heel? Or art thou friend, a rescue from my lonely wake? Come out of love for me, not love for blood and steel.

Name: Betelgeuse (Musical)
Summary: Betelgeuse is an eccentric and crude self-proclaimed bio-exorcist who seeks to obtain his goal of becoming alive again by any means necessary.

Name: Bison (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: A large herb animal, the Bison is one of the many mammals that roams the lands of Dungeons and Dragons.

Name: Black Bear (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: One of the various bears in Dungeons and Dragons, the Black Bear is one of the smaller variants. They only attack those who try to steal their food or threaten them and their family.

Name: Black Canary (Post-Crisis)
Summary: Dinah Laurel Lance, better known as Black Canary, is a super heroine and a member of the Justice League of America. The daughter of the original Black Canary, a charter member of the Justice Society of America, Dinah was inspired by her mother and detective father to fight crime and corruption wherever possible. However, after her father's passing and her subsequent rejection from the police force, she turned to vigilantism as a means of fighting the growing threats to the peace she so loves.

Name: Black Mask (Post-Crisis)
Summary: Raised in a wealthy home by neglectful parents, Roman Sionis exhibited psychopathic tendencies since childhood, however they emerged in full force when he murdered his own parents and took on the persona of "Black Mask". Now a ruthless crime boss most recognized by the black skull mask burned onto his head and his penchant for sadistic torture, Black Mask has proven himself to be one of Batman's most dangerous foes over years of encounters.

Name: Black Panther (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: T'Challa, also known by the moniker of Black Panther, is the protector of the nation of Wakanda. Following the untimely death of his father T'Chaka, he inherited his father's position as king. In his rush to avenge his father, he became involved in the internal conflict among the Avengers, siding with Iron Man. However, upon seeing how vengeance drove Helmut Zemo's actions and subsequently Iron Man's as well, he saw the error of his judgement and became an ally to Captain America.

Name: Black Pudding
Summary: Black Puddings are quasi-sentient globs of viscous black goop, most often found in poorly-lit dungeon halls where it might be dismissed as nothing more than a blot of shadow. In truth, it is a malevolent carnivore that strips and dissolves even the most durable materials, leaving behind only stone. It is a painful and not altogether quick way to perish.

Name: Black Widow (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Thaddeus Ross: You've got some nerve, I'll give you that. Natasha: You could use some of that right now.

Name: Blaze (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: An elemental that lives in the Nether, the Blaze spends its days floating above the ground. The Blaze's rods can be used as ingredients for potion making, which makes Blaze hunting alluring for adventurers.

Name: Blight
Summary: Blights are the ill-bred results of a bloodied stake being driven through the heart of one Gulthias the Vampire, killing him. However, the evil of this undead was so great that the stake was given his life, and grew into a mighty tree. The roots of the tree birthed horrendous creatures, now known as Blights, who have transformed huge swathes of land into corrupted places where only the flora may tread.

Name: Blink Dog
Summary: Blink Dogs are the mortal enemies of Displacer Beasts, and are canine-appearing magical beasts with the ability to teleport at will. Unlike most beasts present in most Dungeons and Dragons settings, Blink Dogs are known to be good so while they will not interact with humans, they do defend their lands.

Name: Blizzard (Gregor Shapanka)
Summary: Dr. Gregor Shapanka, Ph.D., an employee of Stark Industries, was conducting private research into a means for achieving physical immortality, who got fired for attempting to steal from Anthony Stark's vault.

Name: Bloodmote Cloud
Summary: Bloodmote Clouds are groups of undead mosquitoes intent on drawing blood from all living creatures. They are wildly more dangerous than their living counterparts, being capable of draining a human in mere seconds.

Name: Bloodthorn
Summary: Growing in deserts and plains of evil and chaotic realms, the Bloodthorn is a deadly plant. This plant gets its name from its eating habits, with it ensnaring and draining the blood of living creatures.

Name: Blue Slaad
Summary: The second lowest of the Slaadi race, the Blue Slaad is also a fearsome enemy. Their claw attacks inflict a terrible disease that turns creatures into Red Slaad, with it being unironic as the two Slaad types both loath each other.

Name: Boar (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: A wild cousin of the domesticated pig, the Boar is a medium-sized omnivore mammal. They are fierce fighters, being able to fight even past the point of fatal harm, charging at foes with their tusks.

Name: Bone Naga
Summary: Bone Nagas are a member of the immortal species known as nagas. They were created by the mighty Creator Race Sarrukh, though they are ultimately an incomplete perversion of true nagas. During the ritual made to cement the naga's immortality, yuan-ti necromantic rituals rendered the creature undead, twisting them into servants of the yuan-ti instead, and with merely a fraction of the power their siblings possessed.

Name: Bone Rat Swarm
Summary: Bone Rat Swarms are hordes of skeletal, undead rats created for some nefarious necromantic purpose. They gather in great masses and rampage through urban environments, stripping anything they find to the bone.

Name: Bonegnasher
Summary: Seeking power, the ogre named Bonegnasher alongside his men attacked King Damara in order to obtain the Orb of Dragonkind, in the porcess slaying the king's men and forcing Drama as a last ditch effort to hide the orb. If the adventurers tasked to stop Bonegnasher from finding the orb inside the castle fail he will use the orb to call forth a red dragon and lay destruction upon the land.

Name: Bonnie (In Stars and Time)
Summary: Bonnie, full name Boniface Sohane Aglae Zabor, is a major character in the game In Stars and Time and START AGAIN: a prologue, traveling with Mirabelle, Isabeau, Odile, and Siffrin on a quest to defeat the King and save Vaugarde from the fate of being frozen in time. Bonnie is described as a loud and brave kid from the coastal town of Bambouche. Throughout the game, they help out randomly in battles and are on snack duty.

Name: Boromir
Summary: ‘Beneath Amon Hen I heard his cry. There many foes he fought, His cloven shield, his broken sword, they to the water brought. His head so proud, his face so fair, his limbs they laid to rest, And Rauros, golden Rauros-falls, bore him upon its breast. ‘O Boromir! The Tower of Guard shall ever northward gaze, To Rauros, golden Rauros-falls, until the end of days.

Name: Bourdon
Summary: Very nice of those hands to not attack us. But none of our attacks are hurting that big one...

Name: Bradley Fighting Vehicle
Summary: The Bradley Fighting Vehicle (BFV) is a fighting vehicle platform of the United States manufactured by BAE Systems Land & Armaments, formerly United Defense. It was named after U.S. General Omar Bradley.

Name: Brain in a Jar
Summary: Brains in Jars are masterpieces of technology and necromancy merged into a single being. They are undead, brains kept alive by preservative fluid and given reign to focus on their psionic power rather than supporting their physical body. The ritual for creating such a creature is relatively unknown- merely placing the brain in the correct fluids will not produce any of the same effects. Only those with enough control over the brain commit such rituals, as the brain is adept at taking control of the thoughts of others.

Name: Bralani
Summary: The Brelani were a species of wild Eladrin, good-aligned celestials hailing from the Plane of Arborea. These eladrin in particular refused to outright serve any particular god, instead agreeing to ally with them. They embody the snow, wind, and sand, and were considered lesser to their Ghaele brothers.

Name: Braum
Summary: Blessed with massive muscles, and an even bigger heart, Braum is a beloved hero of the Freljord. Every child born to the ice knows of his legendary strength, capable of felling entire forests of frost-oaks in a single night or rending the very mountains asunder. With a colossal vault door borne across his back as a shield, Braum roams the land as a friend to those in need and a terrible foe of evildoers.

Name: Braun Strowman (WWE)
Summary: Braun Strowman also known as The Monster Among Men started out as a successful strongman when eventually he met Mark Henry who introduced him to the WWE. There he became a member of the Wyatt Family while wearing the mask of the Black sheep. Once he broke away from the group, he eventually started a successful solo-run that has resulted in him being a one time WWE Champion and accomplishing very powerful feats of destroying vehicles and breaking objects. Braun is 2.03 m tall and weighs over 385 lb.

Name: Breachgnome
Summary: Specialized in fighting within cramped spaces, a well-positioned Breachgnome can hold off superior enemy forces for a long duration. They are trained to fight alone, although sometimes they work in small units that coordinate to block off several paths at once. They are seldom seen outside Gnome communities, though when are found outside they are often looking for Gnomes to help.

Name: Brown Bear (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: One of the many bears in Dungeons and Dragons, the Brown Bear is the larger cousin of the Black Bear. They are around 9 feet long, and are far stronger than black bears. Like other bears, they are omnivores, and they are noted to be rather aggressive.

Name: Bruno (Pokémon)
Summary: Bruno (シバ Siba) is a Fighting-type Trainer and member of the Elite Four of Kanto and Johto.

Name: Bugbear
Summary: One of the stronger Goblinoids, the Bugbear bullies and hunts whatever it wishes to. Unlike their Goblin brothers, they aren't weak to light and stand at around 7 feet tall with strong physique.

Name: Bulette
Summary: Bulettes, or as they are famously known, Land Sharks, are massive shelled-creatures that live solely to eat and will in fact eat anything, with their powerful digestive systems quickly working through even arcane and metal objects. They hunt via sensing tremors above them.

Name: Bullseye (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Benjamin Leonard "Dex" Poindexter is a veteran of the United States Army and a former FBI agent who possesses a remarkable talent for accuracy. Struggling with a mental illness throughout his life, Poindexter relied on structure and rules to maintain his sanity with the counseling of Eileen Mercer, whose death affected Poindexter, leading him to stalk his former co-worker Julie Barnes. When he used his skills to save Wilson Fisk's life as a member of his federal escort, Poindexter was manipulated into becoming Fisk's personal assassin. He was tasked with impersonating Daredevil in order to turn the public against him while ensuring Ray Nadeem and Karen Page did not expose Fisk. Upon the real Daredevil's revelation to Poindexter that Fisk had been playing him and had orchestrated Barnes' murder, Poindexter turned against his superior and went on a rampage at Fisk's wedding in an attempt to kill him. While fighting Daredevil, Poindexter was defeated by Fisk, who broke his spine.

Name: BX-series droid commando
Summary: BX-series droid commandos, also known as commando droids, were a type of advanced battle droid used by the Confederacy of Independent Systems during the Clone Wars. They were created as an improvement over the standard B1 battle droids and had great agility and far superior computer processing power. They were feared for their accuracy with blasters and fighting skill as well as the fact that they did not go down easily.

Name: Calamité
Summary: Something appeared for a second on the big ball head!!! That was... A [Rock/Paper/Scissors] sign?

Name: Cambion
Summary: Cambions are the spawn of demons mating with humans, generally between a succubus (or an incubus) as well as a mortal being. The result is a demi-fiend, something not wholly one or the other. Many such Cambions result from demon lords themselves, especially Graz'zt, who commonly partakes of earthly flesh.

Name: Camel (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: The camel is the best mundane mount one can use if they wish to travel through the desert. They are able to endure the desert heat far better then most animals and require little food and water. Some camels are breed for strength and aggression and are used for desert warfare.

Name: Captain Atom (Post-Crisis)
Summary: During the Vietnam War, Nathaniel Christopher Adam served in the United States Air Force. Under the watchful eye of Col. Wade Eiling, he was framed for a crime he didn't commit and condemned to death in 1968. He was offered the option to engage in a military experiment with a slim chance of surviving in exchange for a presidential pardon if he survived. The experiment entailed blasting a huge nuclear bomb beneath the hull of a wrecked extra-terrestrial ship while Adam was inside it to evaluate its resilience. Against all chances, Adam lived, with the alien metal merging with his flesh and the surplus energy propelling him twenty years forward in time.

Name: Captain Boomerang Jr. (Post-Crisis)
Summary: Owen Mercer also known as Captain Boomerang Jr. is the son of George Harkness, the original Captain Boomerang and his idol, taking up his mantle after a mission to assassinate the father of Tim Drake went south. He decides to choose to become a different man, to change the outlook of the legacy his father left behind, walking the thin line between hero and villain.

Name: Captain Marvel (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Captain Carol Susan Jane Danvers, also known as Captain Marvel, is a former United States Air Force pilot who, upon being exposed to the energy of the Tesseract, obtained cosmic powers. She was made into a Kree-Human hybrid via a blood transfusion from Yon-Rogg, while having her memories removed, turning her into the Kree's weapon and a member of Starforce. During the Kree's war with the Skrulls, Danvers returned to Earth and began recalling her past, with help from Nick Fury and Maria Rambeau. Danvers also discovered that Yon-Rogg had been manipulating her for years, learning from Talos that the Skrulls were merely seeking to find a new home. With this information, Danvers unlocked her true powers and defeated the Kree invasion onto Earth that was being led by Ronan the Accuser, before setting off out to the far reaches of the galaxy to finish what her late mentor Mar-Vell had once started.

Name: Captain Othelstan
Summary: Captain Othelstan is the leader of the Parnast Cult of the Dragon and direct liaison with Blagothkus. He is a large, powerfully-built figure, and trained in unique means of warfare- specifically, the captain rides wyverns into combat. In terms of the Cult, he is a Dragonsoul- one of the highest ranks below the reformed Cult's leadership, the Wyrmspeakers.

Name: Carnivorous Ape
Summary: A larger, stronger, and more violent variant of a regular gorilla, the Carnivorous Ape is a menace for anyone in the jungle. They are extremely smart for an animal, reaching IQ scores over 70, with them also being rather cunning. They prefer to stalk their prey, following them for miles before jumping them. In combat they can either use their claws or their sharp teeth to rip victims to shreds.

Name: Carrion Crawler
Summary: Carrion Crawlers are the ultimate parasite, feeding on all decomposing parts of rotten corpses- even the bones. It prefers not to compete with other scavengers, but will instead remain patiently in places of death and wait for the sign of coming prey- light. A carrion crawler will follow a torch for hours or longer, awaiting the bearer's death.

Name: Catman (Post-Crisis)
Summary: Thomas Blake is Catman, a former super-criminal and enemy of Batman, who had somewhat reformed and turned his efforts for good instead of evil. Despite still upholding poor regard for the law, Catman has become an anti-hero for his intermittent code of honor.

Name: Catoblepas
Summary: A head of a a bufflo, legs of a hippopotamus, and a tail with a mace on the end alongside an extremely long neck, the Catoblepas is a terrible beast which no adventurer wants to meet.

Name: Catwoman (Post-Crisis)
Summary: Selina Kyle, also known by her alias, Catwoman, is a costumed thief of Gotham City. Her criminal activities are often tempered by a reluctant altruism, making her an inconsistent villain and occasional heroine. She regularly eludes capture by the Dark Knight, and maintains a complicated, adversarial relationship with Batman that frequently turns flirtatious and occasionally romantic. Over the years, their relationship has developed to the point where they each have both become increasingly reliable allies. She is also the daughter of crime boss Rex “The Lion” Calabrese, and heiress to his crime family.

Name: Cave Fisher
Summary: The Cave Fisher is a spider like creature which primarily lives underground. It produces a sticky filament in order to trap prey and allow it to easily drag it to itself, in case where it's successful it'll use its big claws to cut the prey into various chunks.

Name: CBU-97 Sensor Fuzed Weapon
Summary: The CBU-97 Sensor Fuzed Weapon is a United States Air Force Cluster Bomb developed by Textron Defense Systems. The weapon is designed for destroying vehicles using an explosively fromed penetrator. Unlike standard Cluster Bombs, a CBU-97 detect the target using laser sensors and infrared sensors.

Name: Centaur (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: Centaurs are a species of half-horse half-humanoid creatures that often wander the planes in tribal communities. Typically Centaurs will avoid conflicts though are known to fight fiercely and to the death if pressed. It is the nature of centaurs to make enormous treks across entire continents, and might take decades to return. Often a conflict will start due to settlements appearing in their nomadic pathways.

Name: Changeling (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: A race with the ability to freely shapeshift their body, their origins are shrouded in mystery. Some sources say they are fey, while others have them as descendants of Doppelgangers. No matter which origin you believe, the Changelings are unrivaled when it comes to disguising their form and using that to their advantage.

Name: Cheetah (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: Found in tropical plains and grasslands, the Cheetah is the only cat with non retractable claws. If taken young they can be domesticated. They are skilled hunters, and are incredibly fast as well.

Name: Chimera (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: Chimeras are creations of the Demon Lord Demogorgon, and famous creatures of legend- the result of fusing a goat, a lion, and a dragon together. Each head maintains a different personality trait latent to that creature- lions to hunt and protect their lands, dragons to seek treasure and slay, and the goat head to simply fight to the absolute death. A chimera is a relatively simple creature and can be lured into service of more powerful creatures easily.

Name: Chitauri (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: The Chitauri are a race of cybernetically enhanced aliens who serve under the leadership of Thanos, who gave them over to Loki for use in his invasion of Earth in an attempt to acquire the Tesseract. Though they successfully invaded the planet through a wormhole created by the Tesseract, they were ultimately defeated by the Avengers.

Name: Choker
Summary: Chokers lurk underground and in urban areas, lashing out at whatever prey happens to wander by. It is capable of extending its limbs massively due to limited structure in them- merely cartilage joints.

Name: Cinderspawn
Summary: Cinderspawn are undead elementals of flame. They have burnt out, and have their lifespan extended supernaturally. Now, in undeath, they seek to eliminate the heat of the living.

Name: Cioccolata
Summary: Cioccolata is a minor antagonist in JoJo's Bizarre Adventure Part V: Vento Aureo. A former doctor who was fired for "accidentally" killing a patient during surgery, he joins Passione alongside his "pet", Secco, as one of the Boss' Guard Squad members. Due to his malevolent nature, he is rarely called upon, but the Boss had no other choice but to call him to fight Bruno Bucciarati and his gang in Rome.

Name: Cleveland-class Light Cruiser
Summary: The Cleveland-class light cruisers were built for the U.S. Navy during World War II, and were the most numerous class of light cruisers ever built. The ships were designed with the goal of increased cruising range, anti-aircraft armament, torpedo protection, etc., compared with earlier U.S. cruisers. Fifty-two ships of this class were originally planned, but nine of them were completed as the light aircraft carriers of the Independence class, and two of them were completed to a somewhat different design, called the Fargo class. The Fargo-class cruisers were a modified version of the previous Cleveland-class cruiser design; the main difference was a more compact pyramidal superstructure with single trunked funnel, intended to improve the arcs of fire of the anti-aircraft guns. In all, 13 Fargo-class ships were planned but only Fargo and Huntington were ever completed, the rest being cancelled at varying states of completion with the de-escalation of World War II. Of the 27 Cleveland-class cruisers that were commissioned, one (Galveston) was completed as a guided missile cruiser and five were later modified as Galveston and Providence-class guided missile cruisers. Following the naming convention at the time, all the ships completed as cruisers were named for US cities and towns.

Name: Clock King (William Tockman)
Summary: William Tockman was a criminal who was said to only have 7 months to live, causing him to become obsessed with time keeping. Even though he outlived his expected life-expectancy by decades, he never outgrew his love for time. Though he briefly became a hero and even a member of the Justice League, he soon fell into the grasps of villainy once again.

Name: Cockatrice (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: The Cockatrice is a combination of chicken, reptile, and bat- and is renowned for its capability of turning foes to stone, making it a feared creature in the lower echelons of magical threats. They are predatory and will eat anything from berries to creatures smaller than itself.

Name: Coldlight Walker
Summary: People die in many places and due to various reasons, and those who die due to extreme cold can have the misfortune of becoming a Coldlight Walker.

Name: Colleen Wing (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Colleen Wing is a skilled martial artist who was trained by the mysterious Bakuto. She would later open up her own dojo in New York City. Colleen would eventually meet Danny Rand and help him adjust to the changes that had occurred in the city since his disappearance 15 years prior.

Name: Colonel Radec
Summary: Colonel Mael Radec was the leader of the Helghast forces defending the Helghan capital of Pyrrhus City. He is the founder of Radec Academy and Scolar Visari's personal bodyguard. He is the secondary antagonist of Killzone 2 and is known to be one of the most ruthless enemies there.

Name: Corki
Summary: The yordle pilot Corki loves two things above all others: flying, and his glamorous mustache... though not necessarily in that order. After leaving Bandle City, he settled in Piltover and fell in love with the wondrous machines he found there. He dedicated himself to the development of flying contraptions, leading an aerial defense force of seasoned veterans known as the Screaming Yipsnakes. Calm under fire, Corki patrols the skies around his adopted home, and has never encountered a problem that a good missile barrage couldn’t solve.

Name: Corpse Rat Swarm
Summary: Corpse Rats are undead rats that swarm in countless multitudes to devour the flesh of the living. They essentially serve the same purpose as zombies in terms of undead classification.

Name: Crawling Claw
Summary: Crawling Claws are the dismembered hands of murderous humanoids, animated by evil spellcasters to continue the slaughter they wrought in life. Essentially, a ritual is done to place the soul of a creature in the severed hand, allowing it to work as a laborer for evil casters. Notably, these evil beings are immune to the powers of others concerning undead- and indeed, since their soul is totally under the supervision of their caster, they cannot be affected by such powers, making them ideal servants.

Name: Crazy Quilt (Post-Crisis)
Summary: Paul Dekker was a criminal artist, who left hidden messages in his paintings leading to the hiding places of his ill-gotten goods. His career came to an end, however, when he was betrayed by a henchman, suffering a gunshot wound that robbed him of his sight. Desperate to regain his vision, he accepted an experimental procedure. While the surgery did restore his ability to see, it was entirely in bright, disorienting colors. Dekker was driven mad, and took up the new identity of Crazy Quilt.

Name: Creeper (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: Creepers are green, explosive creatures found prowling the Overworld at night. They are evil creatures that seek to explode and destroy anything else, destroying themselves and their targets in one destructive blast. They are known to become even more powerful when struck with lightning, making them an even greater threat.

Name: Crimson Dynamo I
Summary: Anton Vanko was born in Armenia and went on to becoming one of Russia's top inventors, and supposedly the world's greatest expert in electricity. One of his inventions was an armor that could control electromagnetism. With its red covering, he named it the Crimson Dynamo. After a demonstration in which he used the armor to destroy a dummy robot modeled after Iron Man and controlled a tank, he was sent to the United States to sabotage Stark Industries, the main supplier of armament technology for the American government. Vanko regretted being set on this course as he admired the young Tony Stark's work, and during his fight with Iron Man, he was convinced to serve the United States, leaving his dastardly ways.

Name: Crocodile (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: A large reptile, the Crocodile is one of the many animals that roam the land. They are skilled hunters that employ stealth, usually hiding underwater to let them bite their prey. The crocodile is even found in places such as the Feywilds, with the Feymire Crocodile being larger and stronger then its regular counterpart.

Name: Crossbones (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Brock Rumlow was a HYDRA infiltrator who had been posing as a S.H.I.E.L.D. agent, and STRIKE's team field commander. Due to his training from S.H.I.E.L.D. and HYDRA, Rumlow had become a world-class combatant, with extensive experience in street fighting, martial arts, and military combat techniques.

Name: Cube Monsters (Fortnite)
Summary: The Cube Monsters are a recurring enemy from Fortnite: Battle Royale, named for their affinity and relation to The Cube. The Monsters are spawned by Cube Fragments, which can quickly create hordes of the Monsters. Later in the story, the Ice King was able to create similar Winter themed Monsters with striking resemblance to the Cube Monsters.

Name: CV90
Summary: The Combat Vehicle 90 (CV90) (Swedish: stridsfordon 90ⓘ, strf 90 or Stridsfordon 90) is a family of Swedish tracked armoured combat vehicles designed by the Swedish Defence Materiel Administration (FMV), Hägglund & Söner and Bofors during the mid-1980s to early 1990s, before entering service in Sweden in the mid-1990s. The CV90 platform design has continuously evolved from the Mk 0 to the current Mk IV with technological advances and changing battlefield requirements.

Name: Cyclops (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: Cyclopes are savage giants that have forsaken the gods. Though not unintelligent, they prefer simple lifestyles tending to livestock for food, and generally remain reclusive. Cyclops are only sociable among their kin, meeting to trade and find mates occasionally. They bear a strong distaste for humans and other sentient species, though will normally never attack unless they are extremely vulnerable.

Name: Cyclops (Marvel Comics)
Key: '''Base''' | '''1/5 of the Phoenix Force''' | '''1/2 of the Phoenix Force''' | '''Dark Phoenix'''
Summary: Cyclops, also known as Scott Summers, is the leader of the X-Men and one of Professor Xavier's first students - he and Jean Grey have been a couple for many years and although not always getting along with some of the X-Men (such as Wolverine) Scott always tries to do his job professionally and with consideration for others, though this can make him come across as bossy at times to people that don't understand or appreciate his style of leadership.

Name: Daredevil (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Leapfrog: So, the devil ninja guy, he's a lawyer? Daredevil: No. I'm just a big fan of legal dramas.

Name: Darius (League of Legends)
Summary: There is no greater symbol of Noxian might than

Name: Darren Cross (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Doctor Darren Cross was the protégé of Hank Pym, who usurped his mentor as CEO of Pym Technologies and rebranded it as Cross Technologies. Cross became obssessed with the Pym Particles and using Pym's technologies to achieve success, but the constant exposure to the particles negatively affected his mind. Cross had developed the Yellowjacket Suit and intended to sell it to HYDRA and the Ten Rings, but Pym and Hope Van Dyne joined forces with Ant-Man, who destroyed his entire research. Driven mad after losing everything he built, Cross wore the suit himself and became Yellowjacket, to get revenge by killing Ant-Man and his family. As Yellowjacket threatened Cassie Lang, he was confronted by Ant-Man, who neutralized him by shrinking him down to a sub-atomic level and destroying his suit.

Name: Deadshot (Floyd Lawton)
Summary: Floyd Lawton and his brother Ed both grew up wealthy, but despite their money, the boys did not grow up happy. Both of their parents were sociopathic monsters, constantly fighting and using the boys as ammo. Eventually, their mother convinced Ed to shoot his father. Desperate to keep his beloved brother from going through the guilt of killing someone, Floyd tried to stop his brother by shooting him in the arm with a rifle. But sadly, the branch he was perched on broke, and Floyd accidentally shot his brother in the head, killing him. After this Floyd spiraled into mental instability, honing his marksmanship skills and eventually becoming the masked assassin, Deadshot, and became reputed as the Man Who Never Misses.

Name: Death Dog
Summary: Looking like a black dog with two heads and about the size of a wolf, the Death Dog is a canine that roams primarily the deserts. It holds incredible hate within its heart, and it also has a taste for human flesh which leads it to attack adventures and explorers alike.

Name: Deep Gnome
Summary: Deep Gnomes, also known as Svirfneblin, are Gnomes primarily found underground in the Underdark. Their time in the underground has made so they naturally blend in and understand stone. They possess both great fighting skills and innate magical abilities, which they use greatly in combat.

Name: Defenders (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: The Defenders were a team of four street-based superheroes who banded together to save New York City from the Hand.

Name: Demonhive
Summary: Demonhives are massive colonies of millions of tiny, diabolical insects that swarm the Lower Planes, though were first seen on the Infinite layers of the Abyss (hence their name), though were later found elsewhere. By right of sheer numbers they lay waste to entire planar locales, ripping through and absorbing all resources. It is only thanks to their destruction by Planeswalkers and warriors of the Blood War that they don't spread beyond the Lower Planes, bring ruin to all other places of existence. The single greatest sign of a Demonhive infestation outside of direct confrontation is the constant, dizzying drone of its millions of Demonets.

Name: Derro
Summary: Derro are small, pale creatures hailing from the Underdark, with burrows of their kind in almost every major Drow or Mind Flayer city. Despite being generally accepted among such societies, they are largely considered among the lower class. The species as a whole maintains a sort of innate cleverness and sadism towards others, likely owing to their creation story- twisted and tormented beasts from dwarf and human stock, likely made by some lost deity of darkness and madness.

Name: Desiccator
Summary: Desiccators are small undead remains of water elementals. Now dried of their life source (water), they long eternally to quench their undying thirst. These creatures are often mistaken for mummies due to their extremely dry appearance.

Name: Dimetrodon (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: While looking like one, the Dimetrodon is in fact not a dinosaur and is closer to mammals than to reptiles They occupy a niche similar to crocodiles but instead of good water mobility the Dimetrodon has excellent sprinting ability which allows it to get to its prey in order to deliver a powerful bite.

Name: Dire Ape
Summary: A Dire Ape is a far larger and deadlier version of a Gorilla. They are extremely territorial and will try to maul anyone entering their turf.

Name: Dire Boar
Summary: The Dire Boar is a giant variant of the regular boar, it's a rather vicious animal who when engages in combat attempts to tear its enemies into shreds with its tusks. The Dire Boar has 2 variants, the Thunderfury Boar which is a Fey Dire Boar and the Fhorge which is a variant found in the Outlands.

Name: Dire Maggot
Summary: An enlarged version of a regular maggot, the Dire Maggot is a larva of a massive flying vermin. Unlike their smaller counterpart which feed only on decaying matter Dire Maggots are capable enough to try and hunt their own food.

Name: Dire Wolf (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: The Dire Wolf is a prehistoric version of the regular wolf, it's bigger and deadlier then its regular counterpart. The Dire Wolf is also one of the most popular animals for Druids to assume the form of via their Wild Shape ability in early levels.

Name: Displacer Beast
Summary: Displacer Beasts were the mortal enemies of Blink Dogs, feral feline monstrosities most commonly encountered in the Feywild. They are noted as being huge, and possess heavily mutated genes, which leads to mutant offspring appearing every once in a while. Such mutants will generally lead enormous packs of Displacer Beasts in their hunts for blink dog packs.

Name: Doric
Summary: Doric is an tiefiling who lives in the Neverwinter Wood after being abandoned there as a child and created among an community of wood elves. Even thought she keeps herself emotionally distant she has great affection for her land and her fellow comrades.

Name: Dottie Underwood
Summary: Dottie Underwood was a Russian spy, who was trained from a young age in the red room, a Soviet training program. She ended up working with Leviathan, to bring down the SSR, and kill Howard Stark. She is defeated by Peggy Carter, and captured by the SSR, and she later helped them out, but then escaped.

Name: Dragonne
Summary: Dragonnes are apparent hybrids of bronze dragons and lions, with fur replaced by a scaly hide. They are renowned as remorseless hunters of wanderers and travelers- a fact more based on fear than fact. In truth, the Dragonne only attacks those directly threatening its lair.

Name: Dragonnel
Summary: Distant relatives of dragons, the Dragonnel is a decently intelligent creature which can serve as a good mount for those who get their hands on its eggs.

Name: Dralmorrer Borngray
Summary: Once a member of Evermeet, an Elf territory, Dralmorrer Borngray was an elf supremacist who left his homeland in disgust at the open arms offered to non-elves. He was a member of Eldreth Veluuthra, an organization dedicated to wiping out humankind, among others. However, he saw no means of destroying them and lamented, now wandering the world in search of answers. Eventually, he found Rezmir, a Half-Dragon who convinced him that Tiamat would destroy all non-elves in her coming. Thus, Dralmorrer joined the Cult of the Dragon to serve Rezmir.

Name: Draven
Summary: In Noxus, warriors known as reckoners face one another in arenas where blood is spilled and strength tested—but none has ever been as celebrated as

Name: Dretch
Summary: A Dretch is nearly the lowest form of life in the Infinite Layers of the Abyss. A dretch's life is one of torture and slavery, servitude over any other class of demon. It is said a single Balor may own thousands, or even millions of dretches. Every pitiful soul that ends up in hell, every chaotic evil death that doesn't have some divine purpose, becomes a dretch or merely withers away. Thus the armies of the damned are fueled. The only escape is to attain a better form, a difficult process that often takes centuries. Few dretches survive for that long.

Name: Dror Ragzlin
Summary: Dror Ragzlin is a barbarian chieftain of a large goblinoid tribe that resides in the Shattered Sanctum, a former Selunite temple located in the Western Heartlands near the Emerald Grove. As the tribe's de facto leader (and sole hobgoblin member), Dror is one of three leaders of the Absolute Cult in the area, along with Priestess Gut and Minthara. In particular, Dror is interested in discovering an artifact that threatens the Absolute's existence that was rumored to be in the area- to this end, he seeks to investigate a nautiloid crash located not far from his location. Dror is an ambitious individual who sees himself as being better than his fellow True Souls, such that he aims to be the right hand of the Absolute some day.

Name: Dryad (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: Dryads are forest spirits and guardians of the plants within them, generally residing within the trees. Dryads are peaceful by nature (though not unwilling to fight), and are often considered to be exemplary messengers of the gods- including the likes of Corellon Larethian and Erevan Ilesere.

Name: Dust Mephit
Summary: One of the many Mephit types, the Dust Mephit is an impish looking elemental. They are composed of earth and air, with them having great control over dust.

Name: Echo (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Maya Lopez is a deaf member of the Choctaw tribe who moved out of her hometown as a child with her father William Lopez, and became the protégé of Wilson Fisk, growing up under his care. Losing his father due to Ronin's hunt for criminals, Lopez became the Tracksuit Mafia's commander, vowing revenge on Ronin. Lopez worked for Fisk alongside Kazi Kazimierczak. However, Lopez learned that Ronin had seemingly returned, she fell into conflict with Kate Bishop and Clint Barton, who were searching for Ronin's Suit, with Lopez believed that they could be her chance to find Ronin; however, Barton revealed himself to be Ronin.

Name: Edgin Darvis
Summary: Edgin Darvis is an human bard from Icewind Dale and was in the past a member of the Harpers, a spy organization dedicated to protecting Faerûn’s common folk, this changed after the death of his wife, when Edgin has forsworn his oath and turned to thievery to support his family. His strong moral compass whoever compels him to steal only from people he believes deserve will not suffer from it.

Name: Eldes
Summary: Eldes (Japanese: エルデス Eldes) is the younger brother of Ardos and one of the five Cipher Admins of Pokémon XD: Gale of Darkness.

Name: Elektra (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Elektra Natchios is an assassin who was trained under Stick to join the Chaste. She fell in love with Matt Murdock during a mission for Stick to bring Murdock into the organization. She returned to his life after years of absence, putting her beliefs and methods at conflict with his own. Later, she was revealed to potentially be the Black Sky, the one who is supposed to lead the Hand. However, Elektra chose to help Murdock defeat the malevolent organization, and was killed in the final confrontation with Nobu Yoshioka. The Hand then retrieved Elektra's corpse from the grave and placed it in a stone chamber to be exposed to the Resurrection Elixir.

Name: Enderman (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: Mysterious and dangerous, the Enderman is a tall entity with thin limbs, purple eyes and black body. They mainly reside at the End, but have been spotted in other dimensions. The Enderman shun water and sunlight, and if a human gazes at their eyes it will attack them with all its might.

Name: Entomber
Summary: Entombers are thralls of necromancers and serve both as acquirers and disposers of corpses. Thus, they wait silently in tombs and graveyards, treating all intruders as targets. They all have their mouths shut at their creation, sewn tight to prevent them from speaking.

Name: Erik Killmonger (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Erik Stevens (born N'Jadaka) was a former American black-ops soldier of Wakandan origin through his father, Prince N'Jobu. His savagery while serving in the US black-ops earned him the nickname Erik Killmonger. Years after T'Chaka killed his father for betraying Wakanda, Killmonger then planned to forcibly dethrone T'Challa in order to accomplish his father's plan to use Wakanda's technology to conquer the world via imperialistic, supremacist, world-spanning, and likely genocidal warfare, to stop what he perceived to be the oppression of people of African descent by the world. Manipulating and then killing Ulysses Klaue to gain access to their city, Killmonger seemingly killed T'Challa during ritual combat and took the throne, but just before Killmonger unleashed his plan, the Black Panther had returned and challenged Killmonger, eventually killing him in their final battle.

Name: Ethereal Filcher
Summary: Ethereal Filchers are bizarre pickpockets who excel at moving between planes to escape capture. Whatever they take, they store in their lairs, which they line with treasures in the most inaccessible places imaginable- oftentimes at the bottom of ruined mines, in forgotten cellars, or merely immensely deep caverns.

Name: Ethereal Marauder
Summary: Ethereal Marauders are predatory animals from, as their name might suggest, the Ethereal Plane, and are known to be kept as pets and guardians of the magic users hailing from that plane. Despite their magical nature they lack intelligence beyond an animalistic level, and are quite savage hunters.

Name: Etrigan (Post-Flashpoint)
Summary: Etrigan was once a rhyming demon of low standing, belittled by Lucifer, the lord of Hell. Fed up with his treatment, he decided to start a revolt, managing to get many demons to serve him due to his sheer battle prowess, but he couldn't hope to stand up to Lucifer, and was cast down to Earth, where the wizard Merlin fused him with his own unruly apprentice, Jason of Norwich, which would later go on to be known as Jason Blood.

Name: Ettercap
Summary: Ettercaps are solitary creatures that act as guardians to writhing hordes of spiders, shepherding them as a human might do to sheep. Ettercaps tend to create massive webs to kill wanderers who find their lairs, so that they might feast upon their remains alongside their flock. The presence of an Ettercap attracts monstrous vermin to their forests, twisting the once peaceful landscape into a horrible, dark place.

Name: Ettin
Summary: Ettins are immense, brutish giant-like creatures known for their hatred of all other things to the point of violent isolationism. While they were recognized by the giant community as one of their own, they were called runt- in a literal sense, "ettin" now means "runt" in Jotun, tongue of the giants. Each head has its own personality and quirks, and each head generally hates the other due to constant exposure to the other's slights.

Name: Ezmerelda d'Avenir
Summary: Ezmerelda d'Avenir is the warrior protoge of Rudolph van Richten, a renowned vampire hunter. As a child, her family kidnapped Richten's son, Erasmus, and delivered him to a vampire. His screams, begging for mercy, haunt her. Richten tracked down her family and interrogated them on the location of his son- and spared them. This act of mercy inspired Ezmerelda.

Name: Ezra Bridger
Summary: Ezra Bridger was a human male Jedi Padawan who, as an orphan on the Outer Rim planet of Lothal, became a rebel fighter and revolutionary leader in the early rebellion against the Galactic Empire. He was born to Ephraim and Mira Bridger, two outspoken opponents of the Imperial regime on Lothal. As a boy, his parents were taken prisoner by the Empire, leaving Bridger to fend for himself on the streets of Lothal. He joined the rebel crew of the Ghost five years before the Battle of Yavin and, with his Force-sensitivity having been discovered, became the apprentice of Kanan Jarrus, a Jedi who survived Order 66. Bridger's abilities with the Force grew quickly, which aided in many of the crew's efforts against the Empire.

Name: F-117 Nighthawk
Summary: The F-117 Nighthawk is a single seat, twin engine attack aircraft developed by the secretive Skunk Works division of Lockheed and operated chiefly by the USAF. The aircraft is based on the earlier Have Blue technology demonstrator and was the first operational aircraft to be designed around stealth technology.

Name: F-14 Tomcat
Summary: The F-14 Tomcat is a supersonic, twin-engine, variable sweep wing, two-place fighter designed to attack and destroy enemy aircraft at night and in all weather conditions. Although now retired in the U.S. Navy, it remains in use, seeing service with the Iranian Air Force.

Name: F-22 Raptor
Summary: The F-22 Raptor is an advanced, all-weather twin engine single seat stealth 5th generation fighter developed by Lockheed Martin. It is the end result of the USAF's Advanced Tactical Fighter program, and although it was designed first and foremost for air superiority, it also has other roles in the form of ground attack, electronic warfare, and signal intelligence.

Name: M109 Paladin
Summary: The M109 Paladin is an American 155 mm turreted self-propelled howitzer, first introduced in the early 1960s to replace the M44 and M52. It has been upgraded a number of times, most recently to the M109A7. The M109 family is the most common Western indirect-fire support weapon of maneuver brigades of armored and mechanized infantry divisions. It has a crew of four: the section chief/commander, the driver, the gunner, and the ammunition handler/loader.

Name: Faerie Dragon
Summary: Faerie Dragons are fey-touched dragons closely related to pseudodragons. They are roughly the size of a cat and bear vibrant butterfly-like wings. Unlike other dragons, their scales change as they grow older, which indicates how strong that particular faerie dragon is. They are also much smaller than their great dragon cousins, being only the size of a housecat.

Name: Falcon (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Samuel Thomas "Sam" Wilson, better known as the Falcon, was a former United States Air Force pararescue airman who left active duty when his wing-man Riley died in combat, choosing instead to begin helping any of his fellow veterans who were suffering from post-traumatic stress disorder at Veterans Affairs. During this time, Wilson met and soon became an ally of Captain America during the beginning of the HYDRA Uprising, assisting him in bringing down Alexander Pierce's schemes for Project Insight before then choosing to remain with Captain America. Falcon later joined the Avengers, and has been an active member ever since.

Name: Faramir
Summary: Faramir is a soldier of Gondor the Lord of the Rings series, he first appears in the book The Two Towers. Faramir was the second son of Denethor II and the younger brother of Boromir. He was the Captain of the Rangers of Ithilien and Captain of the White Tower upon his brother's death.

Name: Fire Bat
Summary: Hailing from the Elemental Plane of Fire, Fire Bats for casual observers appears simply as a flaming bat but one should not underestimate it in combat for they're quite cunning and can't be truly killed unless proper precautions are taken.

Name: Firefly (Garfield Lynns) (Post-Crisis)
Summary: Garfield Lynns was a professional pyrotechnic effects expert who was eventually driven insane by his obsession with flames, eventually leading Lynns to adopt a hi-tech suit of armour and the name: Firefly and became a crazed arsonist terrorising Gotham. Initially being the partner of Killer Moth he eventually took off to do his own crimes after their relationship became problematic.

Name: Firestorm (Pre-Crisis)
Summary: The original Firestorm was distinguished by his integrated dual identity. High school student Ronnie Raymond and Nobel Prize-winning physicist Martin Stein were caught in a nuclear accident that allowed them to fuse into the "nuclear man" Firestorm. Due to Stein's being unconscious during the accident, Raymond was prominently in command of the Firestorm form with Stein as a voice of reason inside his mind. The banter between the two was a hallmark of their adventures.

Name: Flameskull
Summary: Flameskulls are undead guardians crafted from the remains of deceased wizards. When created, they begin cackling in a disturbing manner, and fly about the lair of their new master, patrolling for intruders. It maintains very little recollection of its former life, and is instead totally devoted to its new master. They are exceptionally hard to destroy, as they simply reform unless doused in holy water, making them an exceptional threat to the underprepared adventurer.

Name: Flaming Fist Marcus
Summary: Flaming Fist Marcus is a member of the mercenary and police organization known as the Flaming Fist, himself holding a high-ranking title within the group. During the Absolute Crisis, he can be found at the Last Light Inn, a sanctuary against the creeping shadow curse that has tainted a large swathe of land surrounding the Moonrise Towers. Unknown to his allies in the Flaming Fist, or to the Harpers who maintain the Last Light Inn, Marcus has long since betrayed them in favor of the Absolute, going to their base of operations at Moonrise and receiving an illithid tadpole in his head and granted supernatural powers.

Name: Flesh Golem (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: Created by various evil spellcasters across D&D, a Flesh Golem is various bodies sown together and animated through magic in order to create a minion for one's bidding. Flesh Golems can be created from various creatures ranging from humans, Scale Ones, and all the way to demons. No matter what a Flesh Golem is a fierce enemy to face in combat.

Name: Fleshraker
Summary: A relative of the velociraptor, the Fleshraker is one Dungeon and Dragons's unique dinosaurs not found in our world. They hunt as pacts, preferring lone targets, though if hungry will attack groups. They are skilled at hiding and jumping which they use to great effect for ambushes during hunts, with them appearing out of nowhere to their prey. Against prey they can't take in one surprise attack they have their poisonous bite, which worsens the victim's dexterity which the Fleshraker uses as a chance to attack later.

Name: Flying Fingers
Summary: A variant of the Crawling Claw, the Flying Finger as the name suggests is a flying construct made from the hands of various evil people. Each hand has an eye sown into it in order to give it potent sensory ability, which aids it in its main duty of guarding locations for evil casters.

Name: Flying Snake
Summary: A colorful snake with wings, the Flying Snake is a small venomous snake that is also able to spit acid. They can be used as familiars for spellcasers and be turned into an undead creature, one that is called Deathfang.

Name: Fomorian
Summary: Fomorians are wretched, malformed giants of once previous good breeding. They live in the Feywild, once alongside the elves, pixies, and other fey of that plane- until their inner malice wrent their forms into the horrible disfigured creatures they are now. Angered by their change, they fled to the Feydark, that plane's counterpart to the Underdark of the Prime Material. No fomorian looks alike, though each bears certain consistent features: pale white to dark purple skin, hairless forms, and two differently shaped eyes, the larger of which is known as their "Evil Eye", which they can use to pass on their race's intrinsic curse.

Name: Forest Gnome
Summary: Shy and reclusive, Forest Gnomes are the rarest of the Gnome types. They seldom get out of their woods, so their impact on the world at large is often minor. They are deeply connected to nature, being able to communicate with animals while also easily hiding in a forest environment.

Name: Formian
Summary: Formians are ant-like outsiders hellbent on meticulous keeping of order, to the point that their views often align with that of the Modron civilization. They resided in Mechanus, always keeping perfect order in their strict hierarchy of society. Formians create a hivemind based around their queen at a vast radius of fifty miles, thus ensuring their civilizations may never falter.

Name: Frost Folk
Summary: Many people seek power, Frost Folk are the descents of humans who sold their souls to winter Gods in exchange for power. Frost Folk at a first glance appear like a regular blond, pale skinned people with blue eyes but anyone who stands even 30 feet of them can tell they're no regular humans due to the chill that follows them around. They often hunted animals to use their fur to craft an armor.

Name: Frulam Mondath
Summary: Frulam Mondrath is a division leader of the Cult of the Dragon, an organization whose most recent goal has been summoning Tiamat, Queen of Dragons to the Prime Material Plane, and freeing the goddess from her prison in the Nine Hells. Frulam has been a longstanding member of this cult, generally taking on tasks of raiding towns and villages for plunder for their dragon overlords. She considers Langdedrosa Cyanwrath her right-hand man and trusts the half-dragon to watch over the dragon hatchery.

Name: G'iah (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: G'iah is the daughter of Talos and Soren, as well as one of the Skrull refugees who were rescued from the Kree Empire by Captain Marvel and Nick Fury. Losing her faith in Fury and her father, G'iah joined Gravik and the Skrull Resistance to take over Earth. However, upon learning of her mother's demise, G'iah's loyalty started wavering and she started secretly working with Talos. She was eventually caught by Gravik, who tried executing her, but she survived by infusing herself with the Extremis. Turning against Gravik completely, she impersonated Fury and confronted him at the New Skrullos, as she turned into the Super Skrulls using the Harvest. G'iah managed to kill Gravik and liberate all the abducted humans, after which she was recruited by Sonya Falsworth in a mutually beneficial agreement to protect Skrulls in return for their services to Falsworth.

Name: Galeb Duhr
Summary: Galeb Duhr is an intelligent elemental from the Plane of Earth, bearing the ability to invoke life in rocks and dirt.
