After WW2 she continued to work for SSR, until she left, and founded S.H.I.E.L.D, with Howard Stark, and Chester Philips. She is the aunt of Sharon Carter, and eventually dies from old age.

Name: Peryton
Summary: Perytons are large, stag-vulture chimeric creatures originating from another world than our own. Much like Githyanki or Mind Flayerss, they are predatorial beings who wandered to this plane for raiding and colonization purposes (among others) after subjugating their own planet. However, due to the chaotic nature of these beings, their empire quickly fell apart and those that remained here lost the ability to return, stranding them here and reducing them to outcasts.

Name: Phaerlin Giant
Summary: The Phaerlin Giant are descendant of the Stone Giant, born from the latter being warped by powerful magic. The Phaerlin Giant is far more bestial then other Giants, not even using boulders in combat and instead relying purely on their claws and teeth.

Name: Pharblex Splattergoo
Summary: Pharblex Splattergoo was the leader of a Bullywug tribe based around Castle Naerytar, who enjoyed tormenting the Lizardfolk vicariously through Dralmorrer Borngray. Thanks to the elf's help, he managed to slay one of the former Lizardfolk chiefs, and planned to kill the next- however, in return for this help, his bullywug acted as servants for the local Dragon Cult leader, Rezmir.

Name: Phase Spider
Summary: The Phase Spider is a horse sized blue and white spider which has the unique ability of shifting between the Prime Material world and the Ethereal Plane. Said ability makes it appear as if the Phase Spider teleports.

Name: Phase Spider Matriarch
Summary: I recall my life upon the surface with more than regret. I weep for the decades spent treading the murky waters of profanity while my true Queen waited in the shadows. Even my name, ‘Eliette’, feels foreign and foul upon my tongue. A high elf exalted by Lolth herself - my drow captors cannot fathom it. But I see their house's downfall in visions granted by the Spider Queen herself. When that day comes, when some unnamed whelp from an insignificant house cuts the matron mother's throat, I will escape. I will find solitude, and I will worship Lolth with my very soul.

Name: Poison Ivy (Post-Crisis)
Summary: Poison Ivy is an enemy of Batman. She is depicted as one of the world's most prominent eco-terrorists. She is obsessed with plants, botany, and environmentalism. She uses toxins from plants and her own bloodstream for her criminal activities, which are usually aimed at protecting the natural environment. Fellow villain Harley Quinn is her recurring partner-in-crime and possibly her only human friend.

Name: Polar Bear (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: One of the many bears that roam the lands, Polar Bears are found in colder climates. They are larger than the Brown Bear and sport a white coat of fur, allowing them to far in snowy plains.

Name: Poppy
Summary: Tier: 9-A | 4-B

Name: Portal Drake
Summary: Dwelling in the Underdark, the Portal Drake is a type of drake that has a variety with various magical abilities.

Name: Priestess Gut
Summary: Priestess Gut is the spiritual leader of the Absolute cult of goblinoids growing in the Shattered Sanctum, a former Selune temple-fort located in the Western Heartlands near the Emerald Grove. A spellcaster of some talent, and a gifted enough leader in the goblinoid sense (that is to say, a wretched bully and deceiver), Gut is a True Soul, one of the chosen few of the Absolute gifted with an Illithid tadpole that connects them to their "god".

Name: Prince Xizor
Summary: Xizor is a prominent antagonist in the Star Wars expanded universe. He was a Falleen Prince of House Sizhran and the leader of the powerful criminal organization Black Sun. Xizor was a ruthless competitor and charismatic public figure in high society with his headquarters in the city-planet Coruscant. Close to the Imperial Palace, but less splendid, was Xizor's Palace: his home outside Falleen. Following the Battle of Hoth, Xizor was considered one of the most influential beings in the galaxy, on par with Emperor Palpatine and Darth Vader, due to his exceptional wealth and influence through his criminal activities.

Name: Prisoner 13
Summary: Korda Gilntstone, better known as Prisoner 13 is one of the oldest criminals housed within the prison they're at. They are there for trying to take over a clan by force. Now in prison, they form a spy network where none of those who work for her know how she looks.

Name: Prometheus (Post-Crisis)
Summary: Prometheus is a twisted mirror version of Batman. His parents were hippies inspired by the Bonnie and Clyde movie to become criminals. Eventually, they got cornered by the police and gunned down in front of their son. On that night, he swore he would take his revenge on the system and kill as many forces of justice as he could. He traveled around the world, training and studying, preparing himself to the day he would emerge as Prometheus. On his adult years, he met a group of Tibetan monks who worshipped evil. After gaining their trust, they gave him a Cosmic Key, a gateway to the dimension formally known as the Phantom Zone. There, he built his base and crafted the tools he needed to fight the Justice League.

Name: Punisher (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Francis "Frank" David Castle Sr. is a violent vigilante and former member of the United States Marine Corps, who had joined Cerberus Squad while he was serving in Afghanistan. Fearing he was slowly losing his honor under the command of Agent Orange, Castle returned to his family, only to lose them all during a brutal shooting. Castle became the Punisher, as he aimed to clean up New York City of crime by any means necessary. While seeking to avenge his own family's deaths, Castle came into conflict with Daredevil. Castle was soon arrested and, despite the efforts of Nelson and Murdock, was sentenced to life within prison. However, Castle was freed with the help of Wilson Fisk, and discovered the Blacksmith was the one who was responsible for his family's murder.

Name: Purple (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: One of the many residents of the city of Harmony, Purple is an acolyte wizard that worships the God of Knowledge Oghma. They are one of several adventurers that ultimately solve the city's energy crisis.

Name: Purple Worm
Summary: A powerful beast, the Purple Worm is a massive worm which tunnels in the ground in constant search of food, the tunnels it leaves behind are often used by other underground races as living places. In combat a Purple Worm simply tries to sting, bite and swallow its prey until it's dead.

Name: Quaggoth
Summary: One of many races which inhabit the underdark, the Quaggoth is a savage creature which tears enemies apart with their claws and weapons. They often become Drow slaves in order to fight surface world elves.

Name: Quake (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Quake aka Daisy Johnson, formerly known as Skye (Born July 2, 1988), was a hacker working with the Rising Tide who was recruited by Phil Coulson to join his SHIELD team as a consultant before becoming an agent. After being exposed to Terrigen Mist, her dormant Inhuman abilities were activated and she was granted the power of vibration manipulation. She is the daughter of Calvin Zabo, a medical doctor who after losing his family became a violent and unstable villain, and Jiaying, an Inhuman with the power of life force absorption. Daisy was the first recruit and leader of the Secret Warriors, a SHIELD team comprised of superpowered (namely Inhuman) individuals. Daisy Johnson for a short time period assumed the role of the SHIELD Director before the mantle and title of Director was given to Alphonso Mackenzie.

Name: Quasit
Summary: Quasits are miniscule demons from the Abyss, and are known to be particularly insidious due to their lack of impressive physical might. Their small stature and cowardly nature makes them perfectly suited as familiars of malevolent spellcasters, or perhaps contacts with the agents of the Abyss. Though they hunger for power and influence as all demons do, they are unable to achieve it. Quasits are known to adapt guerrilla tactics when they do have to take up combat, preferring to assault an enemy from an invisible state and then run before they're aware of what happened.

Name: Question (Renee Montoya) (Post-Crisis)
Summary: Renee Montoya was a longtime detective for the GCPD. Events surrounding the murder of her partner, Crispus Allen, led her to quit the GCPD, and she began spiraling downwards. However, the original Question, who was dying of lung cancer, chose to make Renee his successor. So, after he died, Renee picked up the mantle of The Question.

Name: Quth-Maren
Summary: Quth-Maren are foul undead created by clerics of Kiaransalee, the Drow godess of murder[1]. They are the result of multiple necromantic rituals performed on a body flayed of all flesh it once possessed. It is composed solely of muscles attached to bone. They serve in the armies of Irae T'sarran as fodder infantry.

Name: Ra's Al Ghul (Post-Crisis)
Summary: Ra's Al Ghul was born to a nomadic tribe hundreds of years ago in Arabia. Always being interested in science, he left his tribe and worked for many years as a physician, marrying the daughter of the man he apprenticed under. When the prince of the city fell sick, the king asked Ra's for his aid in curing him. Using his knowledge of science and mysticism Ra's invented the first Lazarus Pit, using it to cure the prince. However, when the prince came out of the pit he was overtaken in a vengeful rage, killing Ra's wife. The King was unable to believe his son would kill someone and sentenced Ra's for the crime. Ra's would escape, rejoin his old tribe and proceed to lay waste to the city, beginning his reign as the Demon's Head.

Name: Rahab
Summary: One of Kain's seven lieutenants, Rahab ruled over the Rahabim clan, serving Kain for centuries until his departure from that time. Eventually, they managed to overcome the vampiric weakness to water, but degenerated across the following centuries, and were ultimately slain by Raziel in his quest for revenge.

Name: Rakshasa (Dungeons and Dragons)
Key: '''Rakshasa''' | '''Greater Rakshasa''' | '''Ak'chazar''' | '''Naztharune''' | '''Dread Knight''' | '''Lord of Dust''' | '''Zakya''' | '''Half-Dragon Rakshasa''' | '''Naityan Rakshasa''' | '''Overlord'''
Summary: Rakshasa are fiendish creatures born from the Lower Planes with the appearance of humanoid tigers of proud stature, distinguishable from similar creatures such as Weretigers by their hands, which can bend both backwards and forwards. Extravagant and conniving by nature, Rakshasa plague all the Planes with their manipulations, constantly enacting plots to achieve greater power. They serve countless masters- their own Rajahs, demon lords[1], yugoloths, night hags, and even the mightiest of devils. As manipulators and masterminds, the Rakshasa ply their trade from their luxuriously decorated palaces, subtly tipping the scales in planar and political conflicts as it suited their wants.

Name: Red Dragon (Dungeons and Dragons)
Key: '''Wyrmling to Young''' | '''Juvenile to Mature Adult''' | '''Old to Ancient''' | '''Wyrms and Great Wyrms'''
Summary: And belching fire, and began to lunge down

Name: Red Hood (Post-Crisis)
Key: '''Pre-Death in the Family''' | '''Post-Death in the Family'''
Summary: Robin: Batman, stop…! Stop! You’ll kill him! Batman: He took her from me, Robin… every woman I love, something always takes her from me… Robin: You lost the Catwoman, yeah… but you caught the Joker… and you saved the Bensons… saved their lives… that’s something.[2]

Name: Red Noob and Blue Noob
Summary: Blue: And we'll crush you!

Name: Red Robin (Post-Crisis)
Summary: Tim Drake (also known as Tim Wayne) is a fictional comic book superhero from the DC Comics universe. As the third Robin in the Batman comics, he served as Batman's sidekick, and he is a superhero in his own right. He currently uses the superhero identity of Red Robin.

Name: Red Slaad
Summary: The most common and weakest of the Slaad kind, the Red Slaad is none the less a fearsome foe to face. They are naturally resistant to magic and various damage types, and each claw swipe of theirs is able to infect a creature with its offspring. If a person dies to the disease a Blue Slaad will born from it.

Name: Remorhaz
Summary: Native to frozen lands, the Remorhaz spends all its days hunting prey. They are a millipede like creature that emits incredible heat from its body, using it burrow through ice without any issue.

Name: Rheinmetall 120mm Main Gun
Summary: The Rheinmetall 120mm gun is a smoothbore tank gun designed and produced by the West German Rheinmetall-DeTec AG company, developed in response to Soviet advances in armor technology and development of new armored threats. Production began in 1974, with the first version of the gun, known as the L/44 as it was 44 calibers long, used on the German Leopard 2 tank and soon produced under license for the American M1A1 Abrams and other tanks. The 120-millimeter gun has a length of 5.28 meters, and the gun system weighs approximately 3,317 kilograms. A variety of ammunition has been developed for use by tanks with guns based on Rheinmetall's original L/44 design. This includes a series of kinetic energy penetrators, such as the American M829 series, and high explosive anti-tank warhead warheads. Recent ammunition includes a wide range of new anti-personnel rounds and demolition munitions, giving tanks armed with the L/44 and its derivatives greater versatility on the modern battlefield. The LAHAT, developed in Israel, is a gun-launched missile which has received interest from Germany and other Leopard 2 users, and is designed to defeat both land armor and combat helicopters. The Israelis also introduced a new anti-personnel munition which limits collateral damage by controlling the fragmentation of the projectile.

Name: Riddler (Post-Crisis)
Summary: One of the Dark Knight's most infamous villains, Edward Nygma enjoys flaunting his intellectual superiority by conducting crimes and leaving clues for Batman to piece together. While this habit constantly leads to the aptly named Riddler failing in his criminal endeavors, his puzzle-problem actually stems not only from his own narcissism and ego, but also from a deep-seeded psychological compulsion. Because of this, the Riddler often finds himself a resident of Arkham Asylum following his inevitable capture.

Name: Riven
Summary: Once a swordmaster in the warhosts of Noxus, Riven is an expatriate in a land she previously tried to conquer. She rose through the ranks on the strength of her conviction and her brutal efficiency, and was rewarded with a legendary runic blade—however, on the Ionian front, Riven’s faith in her homeland was tested and ultimately broken. Having severed all ties to the empire, she now wanders with her shattered sword, seeking to atone for a past she cannot fully recall.

Name: Robin (Damian Wayne)
Summary: Damian Wayne is the biological son of Bruce Wayne and Talia al Ghul. His existence was hidden from his father up to when he was about ten years old, during which time he was trained by the League of Assassins in a variety of disciplines to make him an extremely efficient killer. Damian was then sent to his father to disrupt his work as a vigilante (a task he completed with ease thanks to his blood relations and lack of social skills), but later grew to prefer his role as the son of Bruce Wayne and his time as Robin over his position as the al Ghul heir.

Name: Rock Gnome
Summary: The most common of the Gnomes, the Rock Gnomes are found all across the surface world. They are inventive and rather intelligent, using it to construct various devices for fun. They are also considered superb gunsmiths.

Name: Roper
Summary: The larva form, also known as a Piercer is an ambush predator in underground places that uses it camouflage in order to let itself drop upon prey whenever it senses someone below it. The adult form, also known as a Roper meanwhile is a far more active hunter, which while still using stealth, also employs tentacles it tosses at enemies in order to pull them to its maw.

Name: Rot Grub
Summary: The Rot Grub is a parasite that will burrow into any sort of organic material in order to eat it, with a blood warm target they'll go to their heart in order to lay their eggs there.

Name: Rothé
Summary: A large mammal, the Rothé is a sturdy beast which can be found in the mountains, it also has more magical variants like the Deep Rothé which can emit magical lights or the Ghost Rothé which can cast Silence and Jump in order to aid itself.

Name: RPG-7
Summary: The RPG-7 (Russian: РПГ-7) is a portable, reusable, unguided, shoulder-launched, anti-tank rocket-propelled grenade launcher. Originally the RPG-7 (Ручной Противотанковый Гранатомёт – Ruchnoy Protivotankovyi Granatomyot – Hand-held anti-tank grenade launcher) and its predecessor, the RPG-2, were designed by the Soviet Union; it is now manufactured by the Russian company Bazalt. The weapon has the GRAU index (Russian armed forces index) 6G3.

Name: Rumble
Summary: Rumble is a young inventor with a temper. Using nothing more than his own two hands and a heap of scrap, the feisty yordle constructed a colossal mech suit outfitted with an arsenal of electrified harpoons and incendiary rockets. Though others may scoff and sneer at his junkyard creations, Rumble doesn't mind—after all, he's the one with the flamespitter.

Name: Rust Monster
Summary: Rust Monsters are iconic creatures of the Dungeons and Dragons universe, and are the renowned antithesis to most fighter classes due to their ability to destroy metal on contact. Despite their fairly large size (being the size of a pony), they rarely deal in combat aside from their hunger for metal.

Name: Rylkar
Summary: Rylkar are rats that have evolved during heir time in the Underdark. They are known to enter an area, consume everything within it, and reproduce using all resources exponentially- thus leaving a rat-infested barrens. Rylkars bear a strong tie to flame, and view it as raw energy, something they can use to reproduce their thousands of young.

Name: Ryouga
Summary: Ryouga (Japanese: リョウガ) is the main character of the Pokémon RéBURST manga. Hot-blooded, naive, and not particularly worldly, he is able to gain the powers of a Pokémon with the aid of a Burst Heart. The one thing he hates most is the word "impossible", mentioning it riles him up into accomplishing what he was deemed incapable of doing.

Name: Saber-Toothed Tiger (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: Smilodon, or better known as Saber-Toothed Tiger is a large prehistoric cat which lived in icy plains and hills.They favor ambushes as their main way to get food, with their long fangs being especially deadly.

Name: Sabrina (Pokémon)
Summary: Sabrina is one of the eight gym leaders of Kanto, and the first psychic gym leader. She is the gym leader of Saffron City. Unlike many humans in the Pokemon universe, she has actual powers.

Name: Sahuagin
Summary: Utterly vile and ruthless, the Sahuagin, also known as Sea Devils, terrorize the sea and beaches alike. They hold incredible hate for sea elves, going of their way to destroy nearby communities of them.

Name: Sailsnake
Summary: The Sailsnake is a mutated form of the viper snake which has fins it uses to glide from place to place. Their size varies from 4 to 6 feet long and they can weigh up to 50 pound, but larger specimens can be bred if one desires so.

Name: Salamander (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: Native to the Realm of Fire, the Salamander are a hierarchical race which roams the land. The weaker Salamanders are often enslaved by other races, while the Noble are among some of the strongest inhabitants of the realm.

Name: Satyr (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: Half man and half goat in appearance, the Satyr is an all male fey creature that roams the Forgotten Lands. They are more concerned with courting women than anything else, with them most of the time not even having weapons on.

Name: Scarecrow (Post-Crisis)
Summary: Jonathan Crane was abused by both peers and family alike as a child due to his unusually slender appearance. With this making him grow resentful to all around him, he soon developed an obsession with fear and phobias, getting revenge on everyone who ridiculed him through lethal frights. As an adult, Jonathan becomes a psychologist for Arkham Asylum, where he performs fear-inducing experiments onto the inmates, and he eventually combines a scarecrow suit based off of an incident in his childhood with a special chemical gas he developed to become the criminal Scarecrow.

Name: Sea Hag (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: Sea Hags are horrific appearing fey creatures often found around shorelines (as their name implies). Twisted and changed by the oceans they live in, they are considered the ugliest of all hags, even by other hags with whom they share sisterhood. As such, she is spiteful, and easily enraged- if something beautiful causes hope, she intends to counter it with fear. If something beautiful can improve life, she would instead unleash death.

Name: Sejuani
Summary: Sejuani is the brutal, unforgiving Warmother of the Winter’s Claw, one of the most feared tribes of the Freljord. Her people’s survival is a constant, desperate battle against the elements, forcing them to raid Noxians, Demacians, and Avarosans alike to survive the harsh winters. Sejuani herself spearheads the most dangerous of these attacks from the saddle of her drüvask boar Bristle, using her True Ice flail to freeze and shatter her enemies.

Name: Serag Kull
Summary: Cruel and sly, captain Serag Kull is a prime example of all that is wrong with the Red Plumes. A well connected man, he uses his position to get away with beating people senseless and extorting local merchants.

Name: Sewerm
Summary: The Sewerm is a relatively big aquatic snake that measures up to 2.4 m, this snake has also adapted to live in swamps and sewers hence its name but its most noteworthy ability is the oil it secrets which can numb one's sense of touch. Due to this oil the Sewerm is sought up by doctors in order to use the oil as a pain killer.

Name: Shadow (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: An enemy of the living that lurks in the darkness, the Shadow is a menacing foe to face in combat. As their name implies, they're animated shadows of dead people. Their origins are shrouded in mystery however one thing is for certain, that being that their touch is deadly. Their touch siphons life and strength from those unlucky enough to be hit by it, and if one dies from this their shadow becomes a new Shadow monster.

Name: Shambling Mound
Summary: A Shambling Mound (also referred to as a Shambler) is a large plant beast that is composed of a mass of dead vegetation and corpses the Shambler has clung onto itself throughout its life. A predator, the Shambling Mound lives in the swamps and forests, using its appearance to blend in with its surroundings before ambushing its prey and engulfing it into its body, proceeding to crush the prey until it can be absorbed.

Name: Shang-Chi (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Xu Shang-Chi (Chinese: 徐尚氣) is the son of Xu Wenwu, the founder of the Ten Rings. Having been trained by the organization since childhood, he has become a master martial artist with skills that are unsurpassed by many.

Name: Sharon Carter (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Sharon Carter is the great-niece of S.H.I.E.L.D. co-founder Peggy Carter, and became a member of the agency herself. Sharon would be assigned by Nick Fury to monitor Steve Rogers in the apartment he lived in, going by the alias Kate. When the infiltration of HYDRA within S.H.I.E.L.D. was revealed, Sharon participated in the resulting shootout. After S.H.I.E.L.D fell, Sharon would join the CIA, where she would be involved in the investigation of the bombing of the Vienna International Center while secretly helping Steve Rogers and Sam Wilson protect Bucky Barnes, who had been framed for the bombing.

Name: Shield Guardian
Summary: Created by wizards to serve as personal bodyguards, the Shield Guardian is a fearsome foe for those trying to attack its master.

Name: Shocker (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Herman Schultz is a former salvage worker who had become a professional criminal and one of the key members of Adrian Toomes' Crew who had sold alien-human hybrid weaponry created by the Tinkerer. As Toomes had murdered his former crewmate Jackson Brice, who had used a modified gauntlet occasionally under the alias of Shocker, Toomes passed the gauntlet down to Schultz and then appointed him as the new Shocker. With his new title and power of the gauntlet, Schultz continued to aid Toomes with fighting Spider-Man's attempts to stop all their black market arms deals, eventually resulting in the Shocker being defeated during a fight and arrested. (Marvel Cinematic Universe Wiki)

Name: Shocker Lizard
Summary: The Shocker Lizard is small reptile while is able to produce none lethal shocks on its own but in groups their electricty becomes quite dangerous.

Name: Shuri (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Shuri is the princess of Wakanda and sister of its king, T'Challa, the Black Panther. Leader of the Wakandan Design Group, she is responsible for the invention of Wakanda's most recent technology and her brother's costume, later helping him retake the Wakandan throne from Erik Killmonger.

Name: Siffrin
Summary: This profile contains major spoilers for the entirety of In Stars And Time. It is highly suggested that you fully complete the game before reading this profile.

Name: Sion (League of Legends)
Summary: Tier: 9-A | High 6-A

Name: Skin Kite
Summary: Made from stolen skin and needing to absorb new skin in order to repair their rotting body, a Skin Kite is a terrible sight to behold. They possess the ability to fly which they use alongside their stealth ability to latch onto creatures and absorb their skin in order to both repair the skin Kite's body and produce new Skin Kites.

Name: Skum
Summary: The Skum is a monster created by the Aboleth, it's made from human stock but unlike a human it must stay in water or else its skin may start errupting which harms them.

Name: SMAW
Summary: The SMAW (Shoulder-launched Multipurpose Assault Weapon) is a shoulder launched rocket weapon with the primary function of being an assault weapon, and secondary purpose being an anti armor rocket launcher.

Name: Smiler
Summary: Once just an elf adventurer, Smiler was abandoned in Avernus by his companions. He has spent over 70 years there, using his charisma and intelligence to survive.

Name: Snow Cloak
Summary: Appearing like a 2 headed mantis ray, the Snow Cloak is a cunning hunter of the frozen lands using its natural colouring alongside great stealth abilities to ambush prey and then attack it with varuious spells.

Name: Snow Goblin
Summary: Standing between 3 to 4 feet tall, Snow Goblins are a Goblinoid creature that inhabits cold lands. Their voices can be heard from miles away and are used as hunting signals. The females are usually larger and more aggressive then males.

Name: Snowflake Ooze
Summary: One of the most visually stunning Oozes, the Snowflake Ooze lives in various cold caves or tunnels, seeking to freeze any warm blooded creature it can get its hands on.

Name: Sovereign Glut
Summary: Sovereign Glut is a deposed myconid regent, his circle destroyed by duergars who left him as the sole survivor. Now hiding out in another myconid circle, Glut seeks aid in destroying the duergar who slaughtered his people and silenced their song. Once his people are avenged, he then prepares to take down his benefactor, Sovereign Spaw, another myconid ruler who did nothing as Glut's people perished around him- in swearing his revenge, Glut swears to initiate the "Age of Glut" in the Underdark, where he will lead his people with a new song- a song of war and bloodshed.

Name: Spectral Panther
Summary: Mysterious creatures, the Spectral Panther is a panther warped by the Shadowfell to the point where it has became far larger and gained various magical abilities.

Name: Sperm Whale (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: A massive behemoth, the Sperm Whale is a carnivorous whale which roams cold waters. They are massive enough to be able to swallow boats, with it leading to their stomachs containing various treasures.

Name: Spider-Mobile (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Corona Motors, in an effort to promote their new non-polluting car engine, hired the advertising firm of Carter & Lombardo to approach Spider-Man about building a Spider-Mobile. Initially turning down the offer as a dumb idea, Spider-Man reconsidered when he realized how badly he needed the money for rent and expenses. With the aid of the Human Torch, they completed the construction of the Spider-Mobile. After a crash course in driving, Spidey's first capture was of Hammerhead's thugs. Mysterio tricked Spider-Man into dumping the car into the river.

Name: Spirit Naga
Summary: Spirit Nagas are witch-like nagas hailing from the time of the sarrukh. Irrevocably evil, these creatures are typically found in solitude, guarding some long-forgotten ruin of an ancient civilization, or ruling over a cult of lesser beings who worship the naga like a goddess. These creatures can be found in numerous locales, and are even found in the Orient as spirits. Their appearance varies heavily, with many simply bearing a human head on a serpentine body. It is said to be easy to identify a spirit naga by scent, as their favorite meals include rotten flesh, giving them a terrible odor.

Name: Spitfire
Summary: The Spitfire is a single seat, single engine fighter aircraft designed and manufactured by Supersubmarine before World War II, making its first flight in 1936 and entering service a year before the start of the second world war. The fighter was built in many different variants, and more Spitfires have been produced than any other British aircraft, with over 20000 built by the end of the war.

Name: Stature (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Cassandra Eleanor "Cassie" Lang is the daughter of Scott Lang and Maggie Lang. Fascinated by the Quantum Realm, Lang invented the Quantum Satellite, which resulted in her, her father and the van Dyne family being shrunken deep into the Realm, being trapped in Axia. Wishing to aid the Freedom Fighters in spite of Ant-Man's denies, she donned the Stature suit to battle against Kang's Empire. However, Stature and Ant-Man were captured by M.O.D.O.K. and questioned by Kang the Conqueror, who used her life as leverage for Ant-Man to retrieve the Multiversal Engine Core. Once she escaped, Stature made a speech across Axia to motivate the oppressed citizens to revolve against Kang and his army before facing off M.O.D.O.K. and returning home with her family.

Name: Stature (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Daughter of Scott Lang, Cassie Lang developed growth powers as a result of repeated exposure to Pym Particles, which were interlinked to her emotional state. After the demise of her father, Cassie carried his legacy by becoming a member of the Young Avengers under the alias of Stature.

Name: Stealth (Image Comics)
Summary: Stealth is a superhero who has battled crime in Detroit for decades with an advanced suit of armor. However, his worsening mental problems begin causing him to mistake federal officers and even his own family for criminals, with increasingly disastrous results.

Name: Stick (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Stick is a member of the Chaste, an ancient, powerful organisation that was created to fight the Hand and stop them from the mysterious Black Sky upon the world. Stick was born blind, but learned to hone his other senses to superhuman degrees. He became an extremely skilled martial artist who would go on to train Matt Murdock and Elektra Natchios, and later aid them in fighting the Hand.

Name: Stone Giant
Key: '''Regular''' | '''Elder''' | '''Dreamwalker''' | '''Cairwight''' | '''Stalker of Baphomet''' | '''Evil Earth''' | '''Runecarver''' | '''Earth Titan''' | '''Rockspeaker''' | '''Scion of Skoraeus'''
Summary: One of the main giant races, the Stone Giant is a mighty foe for anyone to face. They are hulking, gray-skinned humanoid-looking creatures that stand 18 feet tall. They can live up to 800 years, and while they're not the smartest of the Giant kin, they are usually far smarter than the likes of Hill Giants.

Name: Succubus (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: Succubi (or, as their male presentation is known, Incubi), are demons prone to corruption and subterfuge. They are known throughout the planes to make a very specific trade with mortals- physical love, in return for their soul. A succubus will try to take the souls of more powerful mortal, to gain the souls of their underlings as well. As such, while generally only low-level demons roam the material planes, succubi are exceedingly common.

Name: Super Shotgun
Summary: Essentially this weapon is a traditional (some might say outright old) double barrel shotgun that found its way to Mars and was used to fight off the demon invasion by none other than Doomguy himself. This shotgun is potentially three times more powerful than the typical shots fired from the Combat Shotgun.

Name: Tasthania Silvershade
Summary: Tasthania Silvershade was a young girl when her entire village was slaughtered by orcish raiders. She had been in the woods, and when she returned, she saw a unicorn searching for survivors amongst the smoldering wreckage. The young elf joined it, and the pair found only one survivor- an orc. To Tasthania's astonishment, the unicorn healed it- the elf was enraged as the orc fled. Years later, she had been ambushed by orcs in the same forest- however, she was spared, as the chieftain of the warband was the same orc the unicorn had spared in her village. This caused Tasthania to have an epiphany, and led to her completely changing her worldview- now, she is totally devoted to the redemption of the orcish people, and counts many of those redeemed amongst her closest friends.

Name: Teemo
Summary: Undeterred by even the most dangerous and threatening of obstacles, Teemo scouts the world with boundless enthusiasm and a cheerful spirit. A yordle with an unwavering sense of morality, he takes pride in following the Bandle Scout's Code, sometimes with such eagerness that he is unaware of the broader consequences of his actions. Though some say the existence of the Scouts is questionable, one thing is for certain: Teemo's conviction is nothing to be trifled with.

Name: Tenchi Masaki
Key: '''Base Form''' | '''With the Juraian armor and the Tenchi-ken''' | '''Awakened Power''' | '''New Timeline''' | '''Ascended self'''
Summary: Tenchi Masaki (柾木 天地, Masaki Tenchi) is the main protagonist of the Tenchi Muyo! series. Tenchi was a normal boy until he unsealed Ryoko Hakubi, and became the center of events surrounding the highest authority of the galaxy, Jurai. In the Ryo-Ohki continuity, he's actually the grandson of Yosho, the crown prince of Jurai as well as one of the only beings who's able to create Light Hawk Wings as a result of Tokimi's disruption of space-time in the hope of creating a being stronger than her and her sisters.

Name: The Inspector
Summary: From the 1965 cartoon series, stars the inspector. The Inspector is a police detective from France who is always trying to bring justice, thus getting into situations where he must find out a way to solve the problem.

Name: The Joker (Post-Crisis)
Summary: --and his crew goes native on him!

Name: The King (In Stars and Time)
Summary: The King is the main antagonist of the game In Stars and Time and START AGAIN: a prologue, opposing the saviors by freezing Vaugarde in time in an effort to preserve it and save it from the fate that his own country, the island north of Vaugarde, met: being erased from people’s memories.

Name: The Penguin (Post-Crisis)
Summary: Oswald Cobblepot, a.k.a The Penguin is a fictional DC supervillain and one of Batman's most notorious adversaries. Oswald was bullied as a child for his bird-like appearance and the fact that he was always forced to carry an umbrella due to an overprotective and insistent mother. Cobblepot, born into a life of wealth, grew to become one of Gotham's most collected and eccentric villains, many times leading a charming public life as the forerunner of the Iceberg Lounge, a high society nightclub.

Name: The Player (Block Tales)
Summary: The Player is an unofficial name belonging to the playable character in Block Tales. They're a Robloxian from the future that was sent back to the past after hitting a device with the ability to mess with time in an effort to stop the main antagonist from kidnapping Builderman. After being sent back to 2010, they encounter Shedletsky, who is heavily injured from fighting Red and Blue. Upon defeating red and blue, Shedletsky sends them on a quest to find the seven sword fight on the heights swords (Sfoth swords/Sfoths) in order to both stop mysterious individuals who had fought Shedletsky beforehand from misusing their power and rescue Builderman

Name: The Question (Vic Sage) (Post-Crisis)
Summary: Charlie Szasz was abandoned on an orphanage's steps in Hub City, and grew up as a ruffian who would eventually pursue a career path in investigative journalism as the hard-headed Vic Sage. One of his cases led him to reconnect with his old professor, Dr. Aristotle Rodor, who gave him a pseudoderm mask to better hide his identity when pursuing the case. Thus the Question was born, a vigilante using his fists to solve crimes and get answers much needed.

Name: The Saviors (In Stars and Time)
Summary: This profile contains major spoilers for In Stars And Time. It is highly suggested that you fully complete the game before reading this profile.

Name: Thor (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Thor Odinson is the God of Thunder, prince of Asgard and a former member of the Avengers. When his irresponsible behavior threatened his homeland, he was stripped of his power and banished by his father Odin to Earth. While exiled on Earth, Thor learned humility, found love in Jane Foster, and helped to save his new friends from a destructive threat sent by his jealous adoptive brother Loki. In the process, Thor redeemed himself in the eyes of his father and was granted access to his power once more.

Name: Thunderbolts (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: The New Avengers, previously named the Thunderbolts by Alexei Shostakov, are a team of extraordinary individuals, with either superpowers or other special characteristics. They were assembled in 2027 as a result of being targeted by Valentina Allegra de Fontaine and working together to stop the Void from taking over New York City. Following their victory, de Fontaine manipulated the situation to declare the team as the newly formed iteration of the Avengers, which was met with a mixed reception from the public.

Name: Titania (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Mary MacPherran is a superpowered social media influencer and entrepreneur under the pseudonym Titania.

Name: Titanothere (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: An ancient ancestor of the rhinoceri, the Titanothere is a massive herd animal which once roamed the lands. Easily irritable, if they feel threatened the largest of the herd charges foes with their horn, dealing massive damage and launching man-sized creatures into the air.

Name: Tixie Tockworth
Summary: Once a Svirfneblin, Tixie Tockworth was a bright tinkerer in the town of Little Lockford. However one day she decided she wants to become a machine, which lead to her losing her compassion for others. Her town's militia tried stopping her but was pushed back by her automatons. Afterwards she unleashed them on the rest of the town and driving all the Svirfneblins from Little Lockford. Now left to her own devices she strives to fully change into a machine.

Name: Tomb Mote
Summary: Tomb Motes are animated pieces of corpses that come to life after some time in undisturbed tombs. They are born from matted hair, bone chips, the odd tooth, pieces of tombstones, and the dirt itself. They serve no particular purpose but are invariably evil, attacking any intruders in the domain of the dead.

Name: Treant (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: Living tree; the "'Treant"' serves as the forest's guardian. They are generally peaceful but will attack any evil creature or those who carelessly use fire. Treants come in many varieties, with some having creatures like Rot Grub on their bodies to combat pests.

Name: Trebuchet
Summary: The Trebuchet, also known as the Counterweight Trebuchet, is a type of catapult that utilizes a counterweight to launch a powerful stone projectile over great distances. It became increasingly more common than catapults and were preferred over said weapons due to being far more accurate and powerful.

Name: Triceratops (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: A large herbivore, the Triceratops is a dinosaur within Dungeons and Dragons. They mainly live in herds, using those to defend themselves from powerful predators like the Tyrannosaurus Rex.

Name: Tristana
Summary: While many other yordles channel their energy into discovery, invention, or just plain mischief-making, Tristana was always inspired by the adventures of great warriors. She had heard much about Runeterra, its factions, and its wars, and believed her kind could become worthy of legend too. Setting foot in the world for the first time, she took up her trusty cannon Boomer, and now leaps into battle with steadfast courage and optimism.

Name: Tristesse
Summary: Remnants of the people that were defeated by the King... Their grief and sadness is all that remains. They cannot tell friend from foe anymore. Defeating them is all we can do... Every sadness has a different resistance and weakness. Maybe there's a way to figure it out from their appearance...

Name: Troglodyte
Summary: The Troglodyte is a bit shorter then an average human but is far more deadlier due to their sharp claws, teeth and expertise with using spears in combat. Troglodytes also release a foul stench when ever they're angry, said smell is so horrid most creatures get repulsed by it, but the Troglodyte uses it both as an offensive tool and a communication device, as their sense of smell is rather potent.

Name: Troll (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: Trolls are giants outside of the Ordining, largely due to their predatorial and uncivilized ways of life. In fact, they are not believed to be direct relatives of giants at all, and are only classified as such due to their large stature and ability to mate with true giants. They could be found almost anywhere, with multitudes of sub-species forming as a result of their extremely varied environment choices. Some could be found in the boiling hot jungle, while others function perfectly fine in the bone-chilling arctic wastelands, while yet others could survive in active volcanoes.

Name: True Soul Nere
Summary: Nere is a True Soul of the Absolute cult, making him one of its leaders. He is in charge of their base of operations at Grymforge, an abandoned Sharite complex located in the deep Underdark and trnasformed into a legendary forge capable of molding adamantine into powerful weapons and armor. A cruel and arrogant bully, Nere lords over his duergar underlings and deep gnome slaves as a tyrant, going so far as to beat or even kill them for inconveniencing him.

Name: Trundle
Summary: Trundle is a hulking and devious troll with a mischievous streak. There is nothing he can't beat into submission and bend to his will, not even the ice itself. With his massive, frozen club, he chills his enemies to the core and runs them through with jagged shards of ice. Fiercely territorial, Trundle chases down anyone foolish enough to enter his domain and laughs as they bleed into the tundra.

Name: Tryndamere
Summary: Fueled by unbridled fury and rage, Tryndamere once carved his way through the Freljord, openly challenging the greatest warriors of the north to prepare himself for even darker days ahead.

Name: Two-Face (Post-Crisis)
Summary: Harvey Dent was abused in childhood by his father Harry, who would decide whether or not to beat him at the flip of a coin, resulting in him developing mental illnesses at a young age. Despite this, he grew up to become the district attorney of Gotham City, until during the trial of Salvatore "Sal" Maroni, the crime boss threw acid in Harvey's face.

Name: Type 72 Anti-Tank Mine
Summary: The Type 72 Anti-Tank Mine is a circular anti-tank blast mine designed by China. It is similar to the Russian TM-46 mine. A metal-cased version and a plastic-cased version of the mine are produced. The mine has a central plastic cased blast resistant fuze.

Name: Tyrannosaurus Rex (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: The Tyrannosaurus Rex is one of the most iconic creatures in fiction and while in the grand scheme of Dungeons and Dragons it's an irrelevant creature, in 5e it's the strongest form a Druid can assume as a Wild Shape assuming they're not from the Moon Circle.

Name: U.S. Agent (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Jonathan F. "John" Walker is a former Captain of the United States Army's 75th Ranger Regiment and a founding member of the New Avengers. Due to his successful operations around the world, Walker was chosen to succeed Steve Rogers as the second Captain America. However, his aspirations of living up to Rogers' legacy attracted the ire of Sam Wilson and Bucky Barnes in their pursuit of the Flag Smashers, during which he took the Super Soldier Serum after failing to apprehend Karli Morgenthau. When his partner and best friend Lemar Hoskins was killed in action, Walker brutally murdered a surrendering foreign national in public, leading to him being stripped of his mantle and discharged from the United States Army with total loss of rank. Walker confronted Morgenthau again in New York City but chose to abandon his revenge to join Wilson and Barnes in thwarting her attack on the GRC. Despite his discharge, Walker was recruited by government agent Valentina Allegra de Fontaine to continue serving America in secret as U.S. Agent.

Name: Umber Hulk
Key: '''Umber Hulk''' | '''Truly Horrid Umber Hulk''' | '''Vodyanoi''' | '''Shadow Hulk''' | '''Umber Ravager''' | '''Abyssal Hulk''' | '''Astral Hulk'''
Summary: Umber Hulks are ancient mutant creatures born countless eons ago, possibly before the onset of the Dawn War[1]. Hulking bug-eyed monstrosities, the Umber Hulks lurk in the Underdark, tunneling from cavern to cavern in search of food (and little else), often causing wars and conflicts over territory as they move. They are feared on a nearly mythological level to some due to their peculiar ability to incapacitate hostiles with a glance- and leave survivors with nary a memory of what occurred.

Name: V-1 Flying Bomb
Summary: The V-1 flying bomb was an early cruise missile and the only production aircraft to use a pulsejet for power. It was the first of the so-called "Vengeance weapons" series (V-weapons or Vergeltungswaffen), developed at Peenemünde Army Research Center in 1939 by the Nazi German Luftwaffe at the beginning of the Second World War, and was deployed at bombarding England. The thousands of V-1 missiles launched into England were fired from launch facilities along the French (Pas-de-Calais) and Dutch coasts. The existence of such a concept as cruise missile inspired the British to operate an arrangement of air defenses, including anti-aircraft guns and fighter aircraft, to intercept the bombs before they reached their targets, while the launch sites and underground storage depots became targets for Allied attacks including strategic bombing.

Name: Varag
Summary: Standing at 7 feet tall, the Varag is a Goblinoid like Goblins or Hobgoblins. The average Varag knows the Goblin language but is barely able to talk in it, and outside combat they are not the brightest creatures. However pact leaders are capable fighters, with them leading entire brigades.

Name: Veigar
Summary: An enthusiastic master of dark sorcery, Veigar has embraced powers that few mortals dare approach. As a free-spirited inhabitant of Bandle City, he longed to push beyond the limitations of yordle magic, and turned instead to arcane texts that had been hidden away for thousands of years. Now a stubborn creature with an endless fascination for the mysteries of the universe, Veigar is often underestimated by others—but even though he believes himself truly evil, he possesses an inner morality that leads some to question his deeper motivations.

Name: Violet Fungus
Summary: Violet Fungi are specimens of toxic mushroom that grow in certain areas of Faerun, Greyhawk, and many other multiverses. They rely on symbiotic relationships with Shriekers to lure in and, for their part, poison prey. After killing such wanderers in all of their folly, the fungi will scavenge nutrients off of their corpses. Remarkably, this plant has developed the ability to move somewhat.

Name: Volothamp Geddarm
Summary: No less a peerless font of sagacity as Elminater of Shadowdale has attested that more worlds than this one teem with monsters. As a result, that "Here there be monsters" line has appeared on maps of worlds far from this one, and hidden from your modest scribe. And who am I, you ask?

Name: Walrus (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: Found in arctic climates such as Icewind Dale, the Walrus is a bulky and massive mammal. They are often hunted for their meat and tusks.

Name: Wasp (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Hope Van Dyne is the daughter of Hank Pym and Janet Van Dyne who takes on her mother's mantle of the Wasp. Training Scott Lang against Darren Cross, Hope herself fought Ava Starr alongside Lang in order to save her mother from the Quantum Realm.

Name: Werebear
Summary: Werebears are a species of benevolent lycnathropes, creatures infected with diseases that transform them from their usual shape into that of some animal. While the affliction itself is considered a curse, werebears are seen as beings of immense good, and generally work to keep their less well-meaning cousins in check (oftentimes fighting the likes of werewolves and wereboars on a regular basis). Unlike others of its kind, the werebear actively works against spreading their curse. When in combat, these enormous ursine creatures avoid biting so as to not infect any others.

Name: Wereboar
Summary: Wereboars are among the most common forms of lycanthropes in the lands of Faerun and beyond and, much like other lycanthropes, are afflicted with a curse that causes them to transform into animals and go on rampages of uncontrollable rage.

Name: Wererat
Summary: Wererats are among the most common and most despicable of all lycanthropes, and can generally be found in gangs inhabiting sewer systems and similar constructs. They are noted for their nervous and suspicious behaviors and, much like all other lycanthropes, they tend to take on traits of their animal even in human form- short, matted hair and quickly darting eyes are often signs of a wererat.

Name: Weretiger
Summary: Regal and graceful, Weretigers are, even in human form, beings of pedigree and class. Afflicted with the lycanthropy curse, weretigers make ideal hunters thanks to their sleek dexterity in all environments. They tend to live alone on the outskirts of humanity, only interacting with humanity to trade when needed. Weretigers are commonly found in warm jungles, where their true animal counterparts reside with them.

Name: Werewolf (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: Werewolves are canine lycanthropes and are generally regarded as beings of incredible evil (though this is not always the case). In their human forms, werewolves merely seem agitated, easily angered by the slightest inconvenience. Both good and evil werewolves alike flee from civilized society- those that fear the curse fear too for their fellow man, and wish to refrain from killing them. Those that embrace the curse seek to save their own hides, and do not wish to be held responsible for their murderous acts.

Name: Werner Werman (Cuphead Show)
Summary: https://vsbattles.fandom.com/wiki/File:WernerWermanIntro.ogg

Name: Whirlwind (Marvel Comics)
Summary: David Cannon was a mutant born with the ability to spin at inhuman speeds, allowing him to create tornadoes as he went along. Turning to a life of crime, Cannon took on the alias of the Human Top, and then Whirlwind, and has been a frequent foe to the Wasp ever since.

Name: White Canary
Summary: The White Canary is a powerful martial artist, the only sister to the Twelve Brothers in Silk, and an opponent of Dinah Lance, the Black Canary.

Name: White Tiger (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Hector Ayala is a vigilante operating in New York City as White Tiger. He became a client of Matt Murdock when he was arrested under false charges of killing a police officer. During the trial, Ayala's identity as White Tiger was revealed to the public, which aided in his acquittal. Upon resuming his activity as White Tiger, he was assassinated by Cole North.

Name: Winter Wolf
Summary: White and larger then their regular counterpart the Winter Wolf is a fearsome predator whose well adepted to hunting in snowy areas.

Name: Wolverine (Deadpool & Wolverine)
Summary: Logan: Scott used to beg me to wear it. So did Jean, Storm, Beast... All of them. They wanted me to be part of the team, but I wouldn't. Told them they all looked fuckin' ridiculous. I mean, I couldn't have 'em thinking I wanted to be there. And then one day while I was off on my own, the humans came. They went mutant hunting. Laura: I can guess the rest. Logan: No, no, let me say it, I... I need to say it. By the time I stumbled home, shit-faced from the bar, it was too late. They were dead.

Name: Wood Elf
Summary: One of the major sub races of elves, the Wood Elves who are also known as Sylvan Elves live deep in the forests. They are so attuned with nature that they are able to make use of any small cover to hide away, and they are naturally faster on their feet.

Name: Worg (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: A variant of the Dire Wolf, the Worg is an evil wolf.

Name: Wyvern (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: 15 feet long and standing on two legs, the Wyvern shares the general apperance of a dragon but lacks the intelligence of one. It's an aggressive predator which dive bombs from the sky on its prey and tries to whisk it away, using its poisonous stinger on them if necessary, some Wyverns also have magic in them due to influnce from the Shadowfell, and they use said magic to cause necrotic damage to their targets.

Name: Yelena Belova (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: This article contains plot details about an upcoming or recently released episode/chapter/movie/book/game/etc.

Name: Yellowjacket (Darren Cross)
Summary: Self-made billionaire Darren Cross was diagnosed with a rare heart condition, and was further mutated in the attempts to cure it, but to no avail. Desperate, he kidnapped heart surgeon Dr. Erica Sondheim to replace his damaged heart, but was stopped by Ant-Man, who was trying to rescue Dr. Sondheim so she could operate on his daughter in time.

Name: Yeti (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: The Yeti is a distant relative of both primates and bears that lives in the high mountain peaks. Unlike their cousins the Yeti possesses the ability to absorb the heat of their area and have a gaze that can induce terror into those that are unprepared for it, but the former ability comes with a weakness to any great source of it as they'd absorb it too which would raise their internal body tempature to dangerous levels.

Name: Yuumi
Summary: A magical cat from Bandle City, Yuumi was once the familiar of a yordle enchantress, Norra. When her master mysteriously disappeared, Yuumi became the Keeper of Norra's sentient Book of Thresholds, traveling through portals in its pages to search for her. Yearning for affection, Yuumi seeks friendly companions to partner with on her journey, protecting them with luminous shields and fierce resolve. While Book strives to keep her on task, Yuumi is often drawn to worldly comforts, such as naps and fish. In the end, however, she always returns to her quest to find her friend.

Name: Zark
Summary: Zark is a dwarven delinquent living in the city of Loudwater, who in recent years has turned to a life of crime (including slavery and smuggling) to support his lazy lifestyle. He has been in cahoots with the Zelbross Bandits since they spared his life in return for his services.

Name: Zhou Cheng (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Zhou Cheng is a deadly servant of the Hand who was trained by the martial artist Ch'i-Lin to become a powerful combatant by consuming large amounts of alcoholic beverages in order to "tame his inner dragon". Cheng was assigned to guard one of Madame Gao's compounds in China, but was approached by the Iron Fist, who was searching for Gao, leading to a showdown between the two martial artists. Cheng ultimately lost the fight, but was left alive.

Name: Zuggtmoy
Summary: In Zuggtmoy's Cradle your body shall sleep,

Name: Zulkir
Summary: A Dire Badger, Zulkir is a specimen who was granted intelligence far beyond animals by an Awakening spell.

Name: .950 JDJ Rifle
Summary: The .950 JDJ Rifle is known as being "the largest sporting rifle made." It was developed by J.D. Jones, president of SSK Industries. It normally would be classified as a "destructive device" due to the rifle's groove diameter of .950 inches. However SSK was given a "Sporting Use Exception" in order to deregulate the rifle. Due to its heavy weight and massive recoil, it can only be shot from a bench rest or heavy bipod, which even then runs risk of injury. As such, the gun is more of a novelty than any combat or sporting weapon.

Name: 3”/50 caliber Mark 22 gun
Summary: The 3″/50 (7.62 cm) caliber gun Mark 22 was a US naval gun of a simpler construction than the previous class of 3" guns, and successive versions were improved designs. This gun was widely used up to the 1930s, but were then gradually replaced on larger ships by 5"/25 (12.7 cm) single mountings and later by Bofors 40mm guns in twin and quad mountings. During World War II, this weapon was extensively used on smaller warships such as destroyer escorts, submarines and auxiliaries along with many merchant ships, with about 14,000 guns being produced between 1940 and 1945.

Name: 5”/38 caliber Mark 12 gun
Summary: The 5"/38 (12.7 cm) caliber gun Mark 12 was a US naval gun. It was unquestionably the finest dual purpose gun of World War II. Originally designed to arm new destroyers being built in the 1930s, the 5"/38 (12.7 cm) wound up being used on nearly every major US warship built between 1934 and 1945 and was still being used on new construction as late as the 1960s.

Name: 6"/47 caliber Mark 16 gun
Summary: The 6"/47 (15.2 cm) caliber gun Mark 16 was a feature of many US Navy light cruisers during World War II. These guns were used to arm the Brooklyn- and Cleveland-class light cruisers, the latter being the most numerous class of cruisers ever built. The 6"/47 caliber gun was one of several weapons developed by the United States Navy in the 1930s to fire "super-heavy" armor-piercing projectiles, thus increasing warships' destructive power while complying with the limits on bore diameter set by the London Naval Treaty. Compared with the previous 6"/53 caliber guns, the 6"/47 Mark 16 fired a 59 kilogram (130 pounds) projectile instead of a 48 kilogram (105 pounds) projectile. These new projectiles had almost double the penetration performance when compared against the older 6"/53 (15.2 cm) AP projectiles used for the Omaha class (CL-4) light cruisers.

Name: A-10 Thunderbolt II
Summary: The A-10 Thunderbolt II is a close-air support and forward air control aircraft designed to tank hits from high-explosive and armor piercing rounds up to at least 23 mm. It was designed by the company known as Fairchild Republic. It is primarily used by the US military.

Name: Aarakocra
Summary: Aarakocra are denizens of the Elemental Plane of Air that serve the Wind Dukes of Aaqa. They stand as constantly vigilant scouts and warriors protecting against both invaders of the Elemental Plane of Earth (most notably against gargoyles) and worshippers of Elemental Evil (in their case, Yan-C-Bin). They are duty-bound to eternally attempt to restore the Wind Dukes of Aaqa to their previous state of power as vaati, which was lost when fighting against the Queen of Chaos, the former ruler of the Abyss.

Name: Aballin
Summary: While inert one can't tell an Aballin apart from a pool of water, also they often contain treasure from previous victims inside them. But if one is foolish enough to try and drink from the supposed pool of water or take the tressure in it they'll meet an unpleasent surpise of the Aballin morphing into a gelatinous form which tries to suffocate the person.

Name: Abrian
Summary: Strongly resembling an ostrich, the Abrian is a flightless bird which are common in the lower planes and are smart enough to talk the common language of Abyssal. In combat Abrians prefer to fight in groups due to their sonic abilities being enhanced by numbers and if they lose the numeric advantage in combat they're not above escaping the fight.

Name: Abyssal Chicken
Summary: The Abyssal Chicken is a small fiend which to an extent resembles a chicken, mainly sharing the fact that both creatures can only fly at short bursts of time but unlike a regular chicken this creature is a carnivore and is a rather murderous beast.

Name: AC-130
Summary: The AC-130 is a gunship modification of the C-130 Hercules and is a heavily armed, long endurance ground attack aircraft which carries a variety of various ground attack weapons ranging from machine guns to howitzers. Due to its large profile, low operating altitude, and slow speed making it an easy target, it usually flies close air support missions at night. During an attack, the gunship performs a pylon run, flying a circle around the target.

Name: Accablement & Abattement
Summary: Accablement & Abattement is a pair of sadnesses in the game In Stars and Time, acting as the game’s second floor boss in Dormont’s House of Change.

Name: Accuracy International Arctic Warfare
Summary: The Accuracy International Arctic Warfare rifle is a bolt-action sniper rifle designed and manufactured by the British company Accuracy International. It has proved popular as a civilian, police, and military rifle since its introduction in the 1980s. The rifles have some features that improve performance in very cold conditions (which gave the rifle its name), without impairing operation in less extreme conditions. Arctic Warfare rifles are generally fitted with a Schmidt & Bender PM II telescopic sight with fixed or variable magnification. Variable telescopic sights can be used if the operator wants more flexibility to shoot at varying ranges, or when a wide field of view is required. Accuracy International actively promotes fitting the German-made Schmidt & Bender MILITARY MK II product line as sighting components on their rifles, which is rare for a rifle manufacturer. The German and Russian forces preferred a telescopic sight made by Zeiss over Accuracy International's recommendation.

Name: Acrocanthosaurus (Real World)
Summary: Acrocanthosaurus is a genus of theropod dinosaur that lived in what is now North America.

Name: Addled Frog
Summary: The Addled Frog is a swamp-dwelling creature found in the wetlands surrounding the lair of Auntie Ethel, and is apparently corrupted by her presence. If spoken to by someone who can communicate with animals, its dialogue is unfocused and confused, and can become outright hostile if engaged with for too long. Yet, when Ethel's presence has been cleansed, the frog regains clarity and offers a reward to whomever may have destroyed the hag (or, at least, forced her from her home).

Name: AeroVeedramon
Summary: A small, blue-colored, Dragon Digimon child. Although it is small and powerless, it has the potential to evolve to every Dragon Digimon. For that reason, it is a Digimon that is considered exceedingly valuable by tamers and researchers of Dragon Digimon. It is cherished due to its personality of friendliness and overflowing curiosity, characteristic of Baby Digimon. Just like other Baby Digimon, it spits acidic bubbles to attack, but as usual, their power is nonexistent.

Name: African Buffalo
Summary: nan

Name: Agatha (Pokémon)
Summary: Agatha (キクコ Kikuko) is a member of the Kanto Elite 4. She is the third member as well as the oldest. She specializes in Ghost-types and other menacing looking pokemon.

Name: Agatha Harkness (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Agatha Harkness is a witch who was a member of the Salem Witch Coven, and daughter to its leader, Evanora Harkness. After being put on trial for execution in 1693 for practicing dark magic and betraying her coven, Agatha killed her clan and her mother through the use of her dark magic, after they attempted to execute her for her crimes. Agatha absorbed their magic in the process and took the brooch off of her mother's rotten corpse before flying off. Hundreds of years later in the modern day, Agatha resurfaced and took on the name 'Agnes' and entered the town of Westview, New Jersey to investigate the odd Pocket Reality created by Wanda Maximoff, encasing the town. Agatha then meets Wanda herself and observes her under the suspicion that Wanda may be the Scarlet Witch, a powerful mythical being referenced in the Darkhold, desiring to take her chaotic powers for herself.

Name: AH-64 Apache
Summary: The Boeing AH-64 Apache is an American twin-turboshaft attack helicopter with a tailwheel-type landing gear arrangement and a tandem cockpit for a crew of two. It features a nose-mounted sensor suite for target acquisition and night vision systems. It is armed with a 30 mm (1.18 in) M230 chain gun carried between the main landing gear, under the aircraft's forward fuselage, and four hard points mounted on stub-wing pylons for carrying armament and stores, typically a mixture of AGM-114 Hellfire missiles and Hydra 70 rocket pods. The AH-64 has a large amount of systems redundancy to improve combat survivability.

Name: Alaghi
Summary: A distant cousin of the Yeti, the Alaghi are a peaceful race of hunters which only kill those they hunt.

Name: Alain (Pokémon)
Summary: Alain is a character appearing in Pokémon the Series: XYZ and the Mega Evolution Acts. He is Ash's main rival in the Kalos region, and the eventual Kalos League Champion after defeating Ash in the finals.

Name: Albertosaurus
Summary: Albertosaurus is a genus of theropod dinosaur that lived during the Late Cretaceous period, approximately 70 to 73 million years ago. It belongs to the same family as Tyrannosaurus rex and is closely related to it. The name "Albertosaurus" translates to "Alberta lizard," as the fossils of this dinosaur were first discovered in Alberta, Canada.

Name: Aldo the Cleric
Summary: Aldo the Cleric is one of King of Dragons' selectable characters and protagonists, being one of the heroes that goes against Gildiss, the mighty Red Dragon.

Name: Algomon
Summary: Tier: Unknown | 9-B | High 8-C | 6-C | At least 4-C, Possibly Low 1-C | At least Low 1-C, up to 1-C

Name: Alligator Loki
Summary: Alligator Loki is the pseudonym assigned to a counterpart of Earth-616 Loki, accidentally displaced from his universe during a fight between the latter and Thor. The God of Thunder took him in as his pet, regardless of the protests of the Alligator himself. After an initial quarrel with his "human" version, the two realized they have much in common and became partners in crime. Alligator Loki eventually settled down in the new universe, living in the rivers of Asgard or in Thor and Loki's apartment in Midgard.

Name: Allip
Summary: An Allip is a powerful undead created from the restless spirit of a being that killed itself. It was driven mad in life and now seeks only revenge on the living, attempting to get vengeance on those who pushed them over the edge.

Name: Allister
Key: '''By Himself''' | '''Pokémon Team (Stow-on-Side Stadium)''' | '''Pokémon Team (Champion Cup Finals)''' | '''Pokémon Team (Champion Tournament)'''
Summary: Allister (Japanese: オニオン Onion) is the Gym Leader of Stow-on-Side's Gym, known officially as Stow-on-Side Stadium. He specializes in Ghost-type Pokémon. He gives the Ghost Badge to Trainers who defeat him. He is also an exclusive Gym Leader on Pokémon Shield. In Pokémon Sword, Bea takes his place as Stow-on-Side's Gym Leader instead.

Name: Allosaurus
Summary: Allosaurus is a genus of theropod dinosaur that lived during the Kimmeridgian to early Tithonian stage of the late Jurassic period, from 155 to 150 million years ago, in North America (Morrison Formation), Portugal (Lourinhã Formation), and possibly Tanzania (Tendaguru Formation).

Name: Ambush Drake
Summary: The Ambush Drake is a draconic group predator which uses telepathy to communicate with its own kind, and in combat they use stealth tactics alongside their poisonous breath to defeat opponets. Like dragons they have a natural desire to hoard but a group of Ambush Drakes does not have a concept of private ownership and they share all their belongings.

Name: American Bison
Summary: American Bison, usually referred to as bison or simply buffalo, are the largest land mammals in North America. They held cultural significance to Native Americans, becoming animals of spiritual importance. The Sioux, for instance, saw the birth of a white buffalo as the return of the White Buffalo Calf Woman, their primary cultural prophet and the bringer of their "Seven Sacred Rites."

Name: American Black Bear
Summary: The American black bear (Ursus americanus) is a medium-sized bear endemic to North America.[1][2][3] It is the continent's smallest and most widely distributed bear species.[2] American black bears are omnivores,[1][2] with their diets varying greatly depending on season and location.[1][2] They typically live in largely forested areas,[1][2] but will leave forests in search of food[2] and are sometimes attracted to human communities due to the immediate availability of food.[1][2] Despite the name, some subspecies can be brown or even blond in coloration.[4][3][5][note 1]

Name: Amidor
Summary: Quick to fall in love and an idealist, Amidor is a 3 foot tall dandelion.

Name: Amphicyon
Summary: Amphicyon was a prehistoric genus of bear-sized carnivorans closely related to canids and ursids.

Name: Amrik Vanthampur
Summary: The middle child and favorite of Thalamra Vanthampur, Amrik Vanthampur is a cunning schemer who plays an important part in his mother's plan to take over Baldur's Gate.

Name: Anabel (Pokémon)
Summary: Anabel is a Frontier Brain from the Battle Frontier in Pokémon Emerald. While that is the end of her role in Emerald, she plays a bigger part in Pokémon Sun and Moon in the post-game, where it is revealed that she was sucked through an Ultra Wormhole into the Sun/Moon universe, where she becomes part of the International Police and their UB Task Force.

Name: Ancient One (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: The Ancient One was the Sorcerer Supreme and leader of the Masters of the Mystical Arts. She taught Kaecilius, Karl Mordo, Wong, and many others in the ways of sorcery. Her unusually long life is fuelled by her energy use from the Dark Dimension, a technique she prohibits others from doing. When Kaecilius challenged the Ancient One's ways and stole a spell from the forbidden Book of Cagliostro, the Ancient One was determined to prevent Kaecilius from summoning Dormammu to the Earth.

Name: Animal Man (Post-Crisis)
Summary: Buddy Baker is the Animal Man, the chosen protector of The Red, the force which connects all animal life. He is both a family man and a super-hero, often struggling to keep balance between the two.

Name: Animated Armor
Summary: Animated Armor is a common occurrence in any Dungeons and Dragons setting, generally being the creation of some mage or other spellcaster. The armor itself is not normally of notable make, and instead, the power is derived from magic imbued in it from its creator, allowing the armor to act and perform simple tasks as if it were alive. Frequently such creations are able to speak simple phrases and demand passwords, making them nominal guards and wardens.

Name: Ankheg
Summary: Ankhegs are enormous burrowing insects that hunt smaller prey via detecting tremors through the ground. Among the earliest monsters added to Dungeons and Dragons, they have persisted through every edition, providing a solid example of an iconic low-level creature. Invariably an Ankheg is larger than a cattle and tends to weigh just under 400 kilos.

Name: Ankylosaurus
Summary: Ankylosaurus is a genus of armored Dinosaur from the Cretaceous period, equipped with armor composed of heavy bone plates and osteoderms, and a heavy club on the end of their tail. It is often considered the archetypal example of the Ankylosauria family.

Name: Ant-Man (Eric O'Grady)
Summary: Eric O'Grady was a low level S.H.I.E.L.D. agent working in the reconnaissance department of the S.H.I.E.L.D. Helicarrier. Him and his best friend Chris McCarthy were tasked with guarding Dr. Henry Pym's lab by a higher ranking agent, Mitch Carson. When Pym went to leave the lab, Eric and Chris panicked and Eric attacked Pym, knocking him unconscious. Inside the lab, they found the most recent version of Ant-Man's Suit, which Chris put on and promptly activated, shrinking down. Thinking him gone, Eric panicked again and ran off, only to run into each other as a Hydra siege infiltrated the Helicarrier. While trying to find a safe place to hide, Chris was killed, and Eric took the Ant-Man's Suit off his body. Surviving the Helicarrier crash, Eric kept the suit and operated as Ant-Man.

Name: Ant-Man (Scott Lang)
Summary: Scott Lang was born and raised in Coral Gables, Florida. He later became an electronic engineer and met and married Peggy Rae. Together they had a daughter Cassandra "Cassie" Lang. Although he was an electronics expert he could not support his family doing repair work, so he turned his talents to burglary. Apprehended, he served his prison sentence and was paroled for good behavior. During his time in prison, however, Peggy divorced him. Lang had furthered his studies of electronics while in prison and was soon hired by Stark International to work in its design department.

Name: Apatosaurus
Summary: Apatosaurus ajax was a species of herbivorous sauropod dinosaur that lived in North America during the Late Jurassic period. It was one of the largest dinosaurs in the world, growing up to 23 meters long.

Name: Apollomon
Summary: Tier: 9-B | High 8-C | 6-C | At least High 6-C | 5-B | 1-C

Name: Aranea
Summary: Aranea were a species of artificial demi-lycanthropes that maintained the ability to shapeshift from humanoid form to that of an enormous monstrous spider. Long ago they were cast out of their cities once their use in the Night Wars had been completed, and since then have spread and traded through illusions and secret means. Long ago they were purged from their homes in genocide, and took to worshiping demons to get revenge on their attackers.

Name: Archangel (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Warren Worthington III was a mutant member of the X-Men, named Angel, who was born with a pair of wings until he was one day captured by En Sabah Nur. Apocalypse brainwashed Warren and enhanced his body with modifications, turning him into his "Horseman of Death" Archangel.

Name: Archer (Pokémon)
Key: '''By Himself''' | '''Pokémon Team (Let's Go P/E)''' | '''Pokémon Team (FR/LG and HG/SS)'''
Summary: Archer (Japanese: アポロ Apollo) is one of the four Team Rocket Executives introduced in Pokémon Gold and Silver. However, he went unnamed until Pokémon HeartGold and SoulSilver.

Name: Archnemon
Summary: Tier: 9-B | High 8-C | 6-C | At least 4-C, Possibly Low 1-C

Name: Argentinosaurus
Summary: Argentinosaurus is a genus of titanosaur sauropod dinosaur first discovered by Guillermo Heredia in Argentina. The generic name refers to the country in which it was discovered. The dinosaur lived on the then-island continent of South America somewhere between 97 and 93.5 million years ago, during the Late Cretaceous Period. It is among the largest known dinosaurs.

Name: Arkadimon
Key: '''Baby Arkadimon''' | '''Rookie Arkadimon''' | '''Champion Arkadimon''' | '''Ultimate Arkadimon''' | '''Mega Arkadimon''' | '''Ultra Arkadimon'''
Summary: Tier: 9-B | At least 5-B | At least 5-B | At least 5-B | At least 5-B | At least Low 1-C, likely far higher

Name: Arkadimon (Cyber Sleuth)
Key: '''Arkadimon Baby''' | '''Arkadimon Rookie''' | '''Arkadimon Champion''' | '''Arkadimon Ultimate''' | '''Arkadimon Mega''' | '''Arkadimon Ultra'''
Summary: Arkadimon is one of the main antagonists of Digimon Story: Cyber Sleuth Hacker's Memory. It was imprisoned in Underzero but was freed when the worlds connected. Reacting to Ryuji's negative emotions, It becomes his partner Digimon and causes havoc in both Eden and the Real world.

Name: Armadimon (Iori Hida)
Summary: Iori Hida and his partner Armadillomon are two of the DigiDestined in Digimon Adventure 02. Iori was a one of passengers on the plane that was saved by Kabuterimon and Garudamon in the Digimon Adventure.

Name: Arnim Zola (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Brilliant Nazi geneticist Dr. Arnim Zola transferred his mind to a mechanical body to live forever, and now continues his war against freedom with the help of his clones and bio-servants, making him a persistent thorn to Captain America.

Name: Arrowhawk
Summary: Arrowhawks were four-winged birds of prey from the Elemental Plane of Air, and were well-known for their ability to fly and levitate indefinitely from the second they were born. Their striking blue plumage was in fact scales developed for protection.

Name: Arsinoitherium
Summary: Arsinoitherium is a genus of large paenungulate mammals in the order Embrithopoda. Despite its resemblance to rhinoceroses, Arsinoitherium and its order are considered to be related to elephants and sirenians. The prefix of its name comes from Pharaoh Arsinoe II, with the suffix as the Greek word θηρίον (theríon), which means "beast." It lived in North Africa around 36–27 million years ago, during the late Eocene and early Oligocene epochs, inhabiting rainforests and mangrove swamps.

Name: Ascomoid
Summary: The Ascomoid is a big ball of fungus which rolls around the world trying to crush whatever crosses it in order to eat them.

Name: Ash Ketchum
Key: '''By Himself''' | '''Pokémon Team (Original Series)''' | '''Pokémon Team (Advance Generation through Best Wishes)''' | '''Pokémon Team (XY)''' | '''Pokémon Team (Sun and Moon)''' | '''Pokémon Team (Journeys)'''
Summary: Ash Ketchum (Japanese: サトシ Satoshi) is the main character of the original Pokémon anime. He is also the main character of various manga based on the anime, including The Electric Tale of Pikachu, Ash & Pikachu, Magical Pokémon Journey, and Pocket Monsters Diamond & Pearl, including some direct adaptations like the Pokémon Journeys manga.

Name: Ash Ketchum (I Choose You)
Key: '''Himself''' | '''Start of Adventure''' | '''Mid-Adventure Pokémon''' | '''End of M20/M21 Pikachu'''
Summary: nan

Name: Assassin Bug
