While they were recognized by the giant community as one of their own, they were called runt- in a literal sense, "ettin" now means "runt" in Jotun, tongue of the giants. Each head has its own personality and quirks, and each head generally hates the other due to constant exposure to the other's slights.

Name: Evice
Summary: Evice (Japanese: ワルダック Wardack) is the criminal mastermind behind Cipher. He is the only character in the games to have the Trainer class Cipher Head (Japanese: シャドーのボス Shadow Boss). He disguises himself as the mayor of Phenac City under the name of Es Cade (Japanese: バックレー Backley). In his disguise, he is a fat and jolly gentleman who appears to be worried about the increase in crime caused by Cipher and Team Snagem, yet as the head of Cipher, he appears to have done nothing to stop either of them, ensuring that Snagem and Cipher work without interference.

Name: F-14 Tomcat
Summary: The F-14 Tomcat is a supersonic, twin-engine, variable sweep wing, two-place fighter designed to attack and destroy enemy aircraft at night and in all weather conditions. Although now retired in the U.S. Navy, it remains in use, seeing service with the Iranian Air Force.

Name: F-15 Eagle
Summary: The F-15 is a fighter aircraft currently serving in the United States Air Force, and several other air forces around the world. Created in response to a satelite photograph of the MiG-25, to this day it remains one of the primary fighters of the USAF, having served over 3 decades with a combat record including 104 enemy aircraft shot down, 1 satellite, no air-to-air losses of its own, and only 3 confirmed losses from groundfire.

Name: F-22 Raptor
Summary: The F-22 Raptor is an advanced, all-weather twin engine single seat stealth 5th generation fighter developed by Lockheed Martin. It is the end result of the USAF's Advanced Tactical Fighter program, and although it was designed first and foremost for air superiority, it also has other roles in the form of ground attack, electronic warfare, and signal intelligence.

Name: F-35 Lightning II
Summary: The F-35 Lightning II is family of single-seat, single-engine, all-weather stealth multi-role fighters developed and manufactured by Lockheed Martin for the Joint Strike Fighter program. The fifth-generation combat aircraft is designed to perform ground-attack and air-superiority missions.

Name: M109 Paladin
Summary: The M109 Paladin is an American 155 mm turreted self-propelled howitzer, first introduced in the early 1960s to replace the M44 and M52. It has been upgraded a number of times, most recently to the M109A7. The M109 family is the most common Western indirect-fire support weapon of maneuver brigades of armored and mechanized infantry divisions. It has a crew of four: the section chief/commander, the driver, the gunner, and the ammunition handler/loader.

Name: F-86 Sabre
Summary: The North American F-86 Sabre was a fighter used by the US and it's allies during the early Cold War period, and saw military service in the Korean War. It's closest Soviet equivalent is the MiG-15, and often saw combat against it during the Korean War. The aircraft was finally retired in 1994 in Bolivia, 47 years after it has made it's first flight and 45 years after it first entered service with the USAF.

Name: F/A-18 Hornet
Summary: The F/A-18 Hornet is a twin engine all-weather carrier capable multirole fighter developed and designed by McDonnell Douglas (Now Boeing) and Northrop. It was derived from the earlier YF-17 design designed by the latter in the 1970s for use by the US Navy and Marine Corps. It has also seen service in use by several other nations, and first flew in 1978, entering service for the first time in 1983.

Name: Faba
Key: '''By Himself''' | '''First Fights Teams''' | '''Pokémon Team (Post Game/Title Defense)'''
Summary: Faba is the Branch Chief of the Aether Foundation and the foundation's "last line of defense".

Name: Faerie Dragon
Summary: Faerie Dragons are fey-touched dragons closely related to pseudodragons. They are roughly the size of a cat and bear vibrant butterfly-like wings. Unlike other dragons, their scales change as they grow older, which indicates how strong that particular faerie dragon is. They are also much smaller than their great dragon cousins, being only the size of a housecat.

Name: Falcon (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: Living deep in the Neverwinter woods, Falcon established a lodge there where rich nobles can enjoy a stay there.

Name: Falcon (Joaquín Torres)
Summary: Joaquín Torres came to the United States of America with his mother and grandmother when he was six years old. He lived in Sonoita, Arizona, and he graduated from high school in the honor roll. He was kidnapped by the Sons of the Serpent, as part of their agenda to capture people in the border to send them to Karl Malus for experimenting.

Name: Falcon (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Sam Wilson is the son of Paul Wilson, a minister, and Darlene Wilson. Paul died trying to break up a neighborhood fight, and Darlene was killed during a mugging. Before they died, they instilled a great deal of idealism and a desire to help the fellow man into him. Experimented upon by the Red Skull with the Cosmic Cube to grant him the ability to telepathically communicate and control with birds, he aided Captain America in stopping his evil schemes. Steve and Sam would become great life-long friends. Captain America trained Sam in martial arts, making him a very skilled combatant, and both Black Panther and Iron Man have provided him with wings which give him the ability to fly. These wings have varied in design, from hardlight wings to regenerating vibranium.

Name: Fancy Dan (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Daniel Brito was born and raised in Brooklyn, New York. Bullied at a young age due to his height, he took martial arts classes to better defend himself and earn respect, but the mocking only continued as he was branded Fancy Dan by his tormentors. He soon joined forces with Montana and Ox to form the mercenary collective the Enforcers, and have been a thorn in Spider-Man's side ever since.

Name: Fantomex (Marvel Comics)
Summary: The product of a mating between his mother and a machine, Charlie-Cluster 7 was born in the World, a secret square mile of experimental micro-reality built by the military industrial complex. In the World, artificially evolved super-soldiers destined to serve mankind during the inevitable war between humans and mutants were bred and trained by the Weapon Plus Program. The World’s scientists heated up time itself until it flowed in all directions at once. Into this pliant, fast-moving substance, they introduced human test groups, whose genetic material was crudely spliced with adaptive Nano-Sentinel technology, and ran the result through half a million years of cyborg mutation in eighteen months. Charlie’s nervous system was extracted and mutated into the autonomous entity named E.V.A.

Name: Faramir
Summary: Faramir is a soldier of Gondor the Lord of the Rings series, he first appears in the book The Two Towers. Faramir was the second son of Denethor II and the younger brother of Boromir. He was the Captain of the Rangers of Ithilien and Captain of the White Tower upon his brother's death.

Name: Farel
Summary: One of the many nobles in Waterdeep, Faerl is a cruel and proud wood elf.

Name: Fasolasuchus
Summary: Fasolasuchus is a large loricatan. It is the largest "rauisuchian" and likely the largest non-dinosaurian terrestrial carnivore. It's name means "Fasola crocodile," with the suffix "suchus" derived from the Greek word soukhos (σοῦχος), which means "crocodile". The primarily known species is Fasolasuchus tenax.

Name: Fire Bat
Summary: Hailing from the Elemental Plane of Fire, Fire Bats for casual observers appears simply as a flaming bat but one should not underestimate it in combat for they're quite cunning and can't be truly killed unless proper precautions are taken.

Name: Flag-Smasher (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Karl Morgenthau, better known as Flag-Smasher was the son of a wealthy Swiss banker turned diplomat. Due to his father's job, he often moved from country to country feeling like a foreigner and an outcast, and at the age of 19 he tried to follow his father's footsteps by getting a degree in political science.

Name: Flail Snail
Summary: A Flail Snail is an elemental creature originating from the earth. In the wild, the snail moves slowly across the ground, consuming raw materials off the surface while leaving a shimmering trail of transparent substance. If a threat were to attempt to harm the creature, it will unleash a scintillating light that stuns enemies before it uses it's flail-like tentacles.

Name: Flame Snake
Summary: Often used as guards the Flame Snake comes in 3 variants; Small, Lesser and Greater Flame Snake with each one being stronger then the former, the strongest of their kin being theorised to be banished demons cursed into being snakes.

Name: Fleshraker
Summary: A relative of the velociraptor, the Fleshraker is one Dungeon and Dragons's unique dinosaurs not found in our world. They hunt as pacts, preferring lone targets, though if hungry will attack groups. They are skilled at hiding and jumping which they use to great effect for ambushes during hunts, with them appearing out of nowhere to their prey. Against prey they can't take in one surprise attack they have their poisonous bite, which worsens the victim's dexterity which the Fleshraker uses as a chance to attack later.

Name: Flumph
Summary: Flumph is a term for a species of psionic, magic creatures dwelling in the underdark of D&D settings. They are an odd creature that feed on thoughts, dispelling bad ones when they come across them. Generally, Flumphs are non-violent.

Name: Flying Fingers
Summary: A variant of the Crawling Claw, the Flying Finger as the name suggests is a flying construct made from the hands of various evil people. Each hand has an eye sown into it in order to give it potent sensory ability, which aids it in its main duty of guarding locations for evil casters.

Name: Flying Monkey
Summary: At first it was one monkey. It scared away the doves and built a little home in the headman's eaves. The children loved it. Then it was a dozen monkeys, tearing at the children's hair and making them drop their sweets and bits of cocount. The children hated it, and oh how they cried. Now it's hundred monkeys! They must be stopped, before they drive everyone out of the village!

Name: Flying Snake
Summary: A colorful snake with wings, the Flying Snake is a small venomous snake that is also able to spit acid. They can be used as familiars for spellcasers and be turned into an undead creature, one that is called Deathfang.

Name: Flying Sword
Summary: This animated sword dances through the air, fighting with the confidence of a warrior that can't be injured. Swords are the most common weapons animated by magic. They are often found fighting alongside Animated Armor.

Name: FN P90
Summary: The FN P90, also known as the FN Project 1990, is a compact personal defense weapon (PDW) designed and manufactured by FN Herstal in Belgium. Created in response to NATO requests for a replacement for 9×19mm Parabellum firearms, the P90 was designed as a compact but powerful firearm for vehicle crews, operators of crew-served weapons, support personnel, special forces, and counter-terrorist groups.

Name: Ford Crown Victora Police Interceptor
Summary: The Ford Crown Victoria Police Interceptor (Colloquially referred to simply as the CVPI, P71, P7B, or Crown Vic) is a four-door body-on-frame sedan that was manufactured by Ford from 1992 to 2011. It is the law enforcement version of the Ford Crown Victoria. From 1997 to 2011, the Ford Crown Victoria Police Interceptor was the most widely used automobile in law enforcement operations in the United States, Canada, and Saudi Arabia. They were also used for this purpose on a more limited scale in other countries.

Name: Forest Gnome
Summary: Shy and reclusive, Forest Gnomes are the rarest of the Gnome types. They seldom get out of their woods, so their impact on the world at large is often minor. They are deeply connected to nature, being able to communicate with animals while also easily hiding in a forest environment.

Name: Formian
Summary: Formians are ant-like outsiders hellbent on meticulous keeping of order, to the point that their views often align with that of the Modron civilization. They resided in Mechanus, always keeping perfect order in their strict hierarchy of society. Formians create a hivemind based around their queen at a vast radius of fifty miles, thus ensuring their civilizations may never falter.

Name: Frost Folk
Summary: Many people seek power, Frost Folk are the descents of humans who sold their souls to winter Gods in exchange for power. Frost Folk at a first glance appear like a regular blond, pale skinned people with blue eyes but anyone who stands even 30 feet of them can tell they're no regular humans due to the chill that follows them around. They often hunted animals to use their fur to craft an armor.

Name: Galaxy Team
Summary: Many years ago, the land of Sinnoh was completely uninhabited by humans. Eventually, a large band of explorers landed upon its shore and over time they built a village to call their own; that being Jubilife Village, officially kicking off the colonization of the Sinnoh region. There was one major problem that they faced, however: Humans did not nearly have the standards of Pokémon training that they do in modern days, making even navigating areas with Pokémon present a life-threatening journey. To get around this, they set up the Galaxy Team in their proud village, splitting among 6 Corps everything they would need to do to thrive in the land of Sinnoh:

Name: Gambit
Summary: Remy Lebeau, better known as Gambit, is a semi-reformed thief and member of the X-Men whose troubled past has sometimes come back to haunt him, on the whole however Gambit has left his past behind and is a hero - sharing an on-and-off romantic interest with Rogue, despite the fact he can't touch her without fear of death.

Name: Gargoyle (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: Gargoyles are monstrosities of stone hailing from the planes of Earth. These prideful predators wait in dormancy, patiently watching for enemies to inflict pain upon. A gathering of Gargoyles oftentimes will resort to banter and bragging to pass the time.

Name: Gary Oak
Summary: Gary Oak is the grandson of Professor Oak and formerly a rival of Ash Ketchum.

Name: Gas Spore
Summary: Gas Spores are spherical specimens of fungi that strongly resemble a Beholder, a fact which some suspect it has naturally evolved to achieve as a natural defense system. These plants often form symbiotic relationships with the eye tyrants, sprouting from their corpses and imbuing their miasma with the beholder's memories.

Name: GAU-8 Avenger
Summary: The General Electric GAU-8/A Avenger is a 30mm hydraulically driven seven-barrel Gatling-type rotary autocannon that is typically mounted in the United States Air Force's Fairchild Republic A-10 Thunderbolt II. Designed specifically for the anti-tank role, the Avenger delivers very powerful rounds at a high rate of fire. The GAU-8/A is also used in the Goalkeeper CIWS ship weapon system, an autonomous and completely automatic weapon system for short-range defense of ships against highly maneuverable missiles, aircraft and fast maneuvering surface vessels

Name: Gaur
Summary: The gaur (also known as indian bison, or Bos gaurus scientifically) are the largest extant bovidae that lives throughout asia, albeit listed as a vulnerable species on the IUCN Red List.[1][2] They're wild cattle that live near accesssible fresh water in undisturbed, large, forested areas and hilly terrain.[1]

Name: Gelatinous Cube
Summary: Gelatinous Cubes are large, transparent cubes known for picking up whatever they come across. They are notoriously hard to see, with the only hints of their presence being the glint of something reflecting off of their vacuous hide or, if one was lucky, the telltale sign of floating remnants of the cube's last meal still seen dangling, inanimate, within it.

Name: General Zod (Post-Flashpoint)
Summary: Prisoners, you have been found guilty. By order of the council, you will be exiled forever to the Phantom Zone. Do you have any final words before execution of your sentence? Zod: My name is Zod. And no matter what you do, no matter where you send me-- I promise you this. I... Will always... Be your monster. As the Phantom zone takes me, I see your faces. And I know you understand. I will turn your fear into action. I will show you all that you are capable of. I will make you great. And because of me... You will have the chance to survive... And grow strong.

Name: Gharial
Summary: The Gharial (Gavialis gangeticus) is a species of crocodylomorph adapted to a predominantly piscivorous lifestyle. They are known for their long and thin jaws, with the males sporting a lump on the tip of their snouts which resembles an earthen pot called a "ghara" (hence the name "Gharial"). This lump forms following sexual maturity in males. They are among the largest crocodilians alive today, with females can reach 4.5 meters long, while males can reach 6 meters long; average adult mass is 160-180 kg, while males can reach a mass of 600 kg, and the largest found was 977 kg.

Name: Ghetsis
Summary: Ghetsis Harmonia (Japanese: ゲーチス・ハルモニア G-Cis Harmonia) is one of the Seven Sages, the true mastermind behind Team Plasma and the primary antagonist in Black, White, Black 2, and White 2.

Name: Ghoul (Dungeons and Dragons)
Key: '''Ghoul''' | '''Lacedon''' | '''Elder Ghoul''' | '''Vapour Ghoul''' | '''Shadow Ghoul''' | '''Noble/Wizard Ghoul''' | '''Cleric Ghoul''' | '''Abyssal Ghoul''' | '''Flesh Seeker''' | '''Whisperer Ghoul''' | '''Gatherer Ghoul''' | '''Ghoul Warrior''' | '''Ghoul Stalker''' | '''Gravetouched Ghoul''' | '''Ghast''' | '''Darkpach Ghoul'''
Summary: Ghouls are malicious undead that haunt battlefields and scenes of slaughter. Not unlike maggots or Carrion Crawlers, they sweep to the scent of freshly killed flesh in droves to devour and consume. The first ghoul was made when Doresain, an elf worshiper of Orcus, consumed human flesh. As a reward, Orcus granted him a domain in his layer of the Abyss- however, this was lost when Yeenoghu overthrew Doresain. When Orcus failed to act on his behalf, Doresain turned back to the elf gods, who saved him from total annihilation once more.

Name: Giant Badger
Summary: Like its smaller variant, the Giant Badger is a vicious hunter and fighter, who flies into a frenzy whenever it gets hurt. They are unable to burrow in stone, but can in soil and anything softer, with the act leaving behind a 5 feet wide tunnel behind.

Name: Giant Bat (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: One of the many giant versions of mundane animals, the Dire Bat true to its name is a giant version of a bat. Its own body is the size of a horse, while its wing span reaches up to 15 feet long.

Name: Giant Bee
Summary: A far bigger variant of a regular bee, the Giant Bee can reach a size of 5 feet. Behavior wise it acts no different than regular bees, although the queen is able to produce jelly that has healing properties when eaten.

Name: Giant Cockroach
Summary: Far bigger and more aggressive then their regular counterparts, Giant Cockroaches are found mainly underground in areas where there's water and enough decaying organic matter, although it should be noted that they could live anywhere they wanted. In combat this creatures use chemicals they emit to cause nasua in their opponet, said chemicals also the exsoskeleton appear shiny or oily.

Name: Giant Constrictor Snake
Summary: A massive beast, the Giant Constrictor Snake is a large variant of a constrictor snake. They live in warm forests, dropping on prey from tree tops to strangle them to death.

Name: Giant Crab (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: An oversized crab, the Giant Crab is a relatively rare creature that one can encounter in the Forgotten Realms. They are basic creatures, working purely of basic survival instincts.

Name: Giant Crocodile
Summary: The Giant Crocodile is a giant variant of the common crocodile and they can reach an impressive size of 30 feet.

Name: Giant Dragonfly
Summary: One of many insects that people use as mounts, the Giant Dragonfly is often favored over creatures such as the Giant Bee or Giant Wasp. They are highly agile, with them easily evading enemy attacks. However, their wings emit a loud buzz, alerting anyone to the rider's presence.

Name: Giant Eagle
Summary: A noble creature which has its own language, the Giant Eagle is a giant version of an eagle which can be trained to be a mount.

Name: Giant Fire Beetle
Summary: The Giant Fire Beetle is an oversized beetle species. They get their name from their ability to emit a bright light, with it coming from glands on their body. This glands can be harvested and used as light sources for adventurers.

Name: Giant Firefly
Summary: Firefriend or more commonly known Giant Firefly are a giant variant of the common bug who are known for being a kind animal that seeks out friendly companions and can act as a great mount for search missions due to their natural light production.

Name: Giant Frog (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: A variation of the average frog, this creature can reach a size between 4-6 feet with its tongue being 3 times its body lengths. The Giant Frog will mostly hunt large insects and small animals but is known to sometimes swallow small humans too, they also are scared of fire.

Name: Giant Goat
Summary: A giant variant of a regular goat, the Giant Goat reside in hills. If threatened they will be rather hostile, quickly charging at enemies with all their might. On rare occasions some people tamed these goats.

Name: Giant Hyena
Summary: A larger, and more ancient version of the regular Hyena, the Giant Hyena is a prehistoric version of a regular hyena. They possess powerful jaws, which they will readily use whenever they're hungry. They are found mainly in warm plains.

Name: Giant Lizard (Dungeons and Dragons)
Key: '''Giant Lizard''' | '''Footpad Lizard''' | '''Quicksilver Lizard''' | '''Subterranean Lizard''' | '''Giant Banded Lizard'''
Summary: Giant Lizards are monstrously large creatures bred in the Underdark by Drow as potential replacements to their typical spider mounts. They roam the subterranean parts of the world, commonly hunting in packs or being used as pack animals for their fearsome overlords[1].

Name: Giant Oceanic Manta Ray
Summary: The giant oceanic manta ray (Mobula birostris) is a species of ray endemic to oceans worldwide. It is the largest species of ray in the world, and can weigh up to 3,000 kilograms (6,600 pounds).

Name: Giant Owl
Summary: A fearsome predator, a Giant Owl inspires fear in people due to its ability to strike its prey out of nowhere thanks to its excellent stealth abilities.

Name: Giant Sea Horse
Summary: The Giant Sea Horse like its smaller kin is a colorful and odd looking aquatic creature. They are often tamed by aquatic elves and Locata to be mounts.

Name: Giant Snapping Turtle
Summary: An oversized animal, the Giant Snapping Turtle is one of many giant versions of mundane animals. Their bite is strong enough to easily cut a person in half.

Name: Giant Stag Beetle
Summary: The Giant Stag Beetle is as the name implies, a giant version of a stag beetle. It is able to reach to a size of 10 feet long, with a horn being 8 feet long itself. Their wings are too heavy for flight but their armor makes them well defended.

Name: Giant Vulture
Summary: A giant version of the regular vulture, the Giant Vulture or also known as the Dire Vulture, is a far more aggressive creature which attacks wounded creatures in order to hasten their death.

Name: Giant Wasp (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: While not as exotic as other monsters in D&D a giant wasp is none the less a fearsome opponent to fight it combat due to its ability to inject one with devastating poison which can paralysis them, outside this the wasps behave like regular wasps with the only difference being what prey they hunt.

Name: Giant Weasel
Summary: The Giant Weasel is a ten feet long animal. They use their powerful jaws to attach to prey in order to suck out all their blood.

Name: Gibbering Mouther
Summary: Gibbering Mouthers are amorphous monstrosities made entirely of eyeballs and mouths. Each mouth sings out in inhuman tongues about the madness experienced by the creature each and every second of its life. Very few Gibbering Mouthers possess the fortitude to retain intelligence following transformation- one such Mouther is Shond Tharovin, a former archmage who was transformed into a 20-mile wide Mouther. Shond currently resides in the Trackless Sea, plotting revenge.

Name: Giff
Summary: One of the many space faring races, the Giff is in appearance basically a hippopotamus walking on two legs. Their original world lost to the sands of time, the Giff can be found anywhere in space offering their services to the highest bidder. Giff are natural masters of guns, and are often trained in using a multitude of other weapons as well. They enjoy the thrill of combat, especially the sight of explosions, which is why they take payment in the form of gunpowder.

Name: Giganotosaurus (Real World)
Summary: Giganotosaurus is a genus of theropod dinosaurs that lived in what is now Argentina, during the early Cenomanian age of the Late Cretaceous period, approximately 98 to 97 million years ago. Giganotosaurus is thought to have been one of the largest theropod dinosaurs, but the incompleteness of its remains have made it difficult to estimate its size reliably.

Name: Gimli
Summary: Gimli is a stubborn, war-hungry dwarf and one of the many heroes in J.R.R Tolkien's The Lord of the Rings and Peter Jackson's films of the same name respectively. He joins the fellowship to destroy the ring and kill many orcs along the way. He is close friends with Aragorn and Legolas but still clashes with the elf due to the thousand-year-old feud between elves and dwarves. He participates in many battles including Moria, Helm's Deep and the Black Gate. His weapons include twin hatchets and a giant battle ax. He is very stubborn and often explains the stubbornness of dwarves. He loves fighting and even when outnumbered, he never backs down and always competes with Legolas to kill more orcs than him.

Name: Giovanni (Pokémon)
Key: '''By Himself''' | '''Pokèmon Team (Rocket Hideout)''' | '''Pokèmon Team (Silph Co.)''' | '''Pokèmon Team (Viridian Gym)''' | '''Pokèmon Team (Gen 2)''' | '''Pokèmon Team (Gen 5)''' | '''Pokèmon Team (Gen 7)'''
Summary: Giovanni is the leader of Team Rocket and the Viridian Gym, the father of Silver and a recurring antagonist in the series.

Name: Githyanki
Summary: Githyanki are the half of the Gith species that ended up following the original Gith, a member of their formerly nameless species hailing from a distant planet. When the time came to rebel against those who had enslaved them- the Mind Flayer empire, at the peak of its power- Gith led the charge and the Githyanki by her side. Now, battalions of the Githyanki scour the universe for more signs of their eternal foes, the Mind Flayers.

Name: Githzerai
Summary: In times long lost to the rampages of war, the Githzerai were once normal Githyanki who dissented from their brethren and formed a non-evil neutral faction. The Githzerai are ascetic monk-like folk who have settled in Limbo, a plane of chaos- a direct counter to their Lawful nature. They seek to battle the Slaadi, specifically to expand their knowledge in the face of direct adversity, building on the traits they learned from their slavery under the Mind Flayer empire.

Name: Glabbagool
Summary: An average Gelatinous Cube, Glabbagool gained heightened intelligence when the demon lord Juiblex arrived to the Underdark. Curious about the world and those in it he will not go out of his way to attack other beings but merely will self defend, he can be found in the Ooze Temple and is willing to offer assistance to adventurers who get into there, and if the part gains his trust he may even offer loot that's inside his body.

Name: Gladion
Key: '''By Himself''' | '''Pokèmon Team (Route 5)''' | '''Pokémon Team (Aether Paradise)''' | '''Pokémon Team (Mount Lanakila)''' | '''Pokémon Team (Pokémon League)'''
Summary: Gladion is a former member of the Aether Foundation and the son of Lusamine. He originally lived in harmony with his family in Aether Paradise until he noted his mother's obsession with the Ultra Beasts. Realizing the Ultra Beasts would bring ruin to Alola should they be released, Gladion left the foundation and stole one of their Type: Nulls. He then set out to stop Lusamine and free his Type: Null from its mask while working as an enforcer of Team Skull.

Name: Gloria (Pokémon)
Summary: Gloria is a girl from Postwick and the main protagonist of Pokémon Sword version and Pokémon Shield version. Born and raised as the neighbor of Leon, the greatest Trainer that Galar has ever known, Gloria was destined for greatness at a young age as she became fast childhood friends with his younger brother, Hop.

Name: Gnoll (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: It is His blessing.

Name: Goblin (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: They breed fast, they spread fast; the Goblins are a small humanoid race and most well known of the Goblinoids.

Name: Godzilla (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Godzilla is the name of the titular character of a Marvel comic series of the same name. The Marvel Godzilla was awakened by nuclear weapon testing in the Pacific Ocean and attacked Tokyo in 1956. Over the ensuing years, Godzilla became the lesser of two evils, fending off malevolent monsters that would attack Japan. By unknown means, he was eventually trapped in an iceberg and managed to break free once the iceberg reached Alaska in the 1970's.

Name: Goose (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Goose is a Flerken that was the former pet of Mar-Vell before her death. Years later, she finds and joins Carol Danvers and Nick Fury, who initially believe she's just a normal cat.

Name: Gordon Freeman
Summary: Dr. Gordon Freeman is the main protagonist of the Half-Life series. He is a theoretical physicist who is forced to defend himself and the Human race against hostile Aliens and other enemies following an experiment gone wrong. In the process, he becomes an almost legendary resistance hero, eventually becoming one of the leaders of an uprising against the alien invaders.

Name: Gorgosaurus (Real World)
Summary: Gorgosaurus is a genus of theropod dinosaur that lived in western North America during the Late Cretaceous period, approximately 76.6 to 75.1 million years ago. Like most known tyrannosaurids, Gorgosaurus was a large bipedal predator, measuring 8 to 9 meters in length and weighing 2 to 3 metric tons.

Name: Gotou (Parasyte)
Summary: Gotou (後藤, lit. Gotō) is an 'experimental' Parasite created by Reiko. His body is composed of five different individuals, something he can utilize to the fullest extent. He is the main antagonist of the series.

Name: Gray Ooze
Summary: Gray Oozes are monstrous collections of single-cell organisms that essentially form a single large sensory organ, prowling dungeons for their sustenance. Unlike most other oozes, these creatures bear a heightened capacity for evolution, growing more sentient as it grows in size. While most often found in dungeon environments, they are often found slithering through the muck of brackish swamp-water.

Name: Great White Shark
Summary: The Great White Shark is a species of large lamniform shark which can be found in the coastal surface waters of all the major oceans. Great White Sharks are notable for their size, with mature female individuals growing up to 6.1 meters (20 feet) in length and 1,950 kg (4,300 lb) in weight. However, most are smaller with males measuring 3.35 - 3.96 meters (11 - 13 feet) and females 4.57 - 4.88 meters (15 - 16 feet) on average. According to a 2014 study the lifespan of Great White Sharks is estimated to be as long as 70 years or more, well above older estimates, making it one of the longest lived cartilaginous fish currently known. According to the same study, male individuals take 26 years to reach sexual maturity, while the females take 33 years to be ready to produce offspring. Great White Sharks can accelerate up to 56 km/h (35 mph) in short bursts.

Name: Green (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: One of several adventurers which solved Harmony City's energy crisis, Green is a Lore Bard, using their magic and martial skills to help.

Name: Greevil
Summary: Greevil (Japanese: デスゴルド Deathgold) is the leader of the criminal group Cipher. He is the only character in the game to have the Trainer class Grand Master (Japanese: シャドー総帥 Shadow Leader).

Name: Grell
Summary: Grell are creatures that resemble floating brains with tentacles and a large beak protruding from the front. They are most famous for their voracious feeding habits- they bear little else in terms of dastardly plans outside of planning their next meal, going so far as to classify all things in life as "edible", "inedible", or "Great Eater" (those few things that might feed on a grell). While generally solitary, a rare few grell form great colonies led by philosophers, grell wizards that study the aberrant sciences of their native realm. The grell are non-hostile to other grell, and generally consider the choice of joining a colony as a matter of opinion.

Name: Grick
Summary: Gricks are rubbery predators most commonly encountered in the Underdark. Generally, these creatures are passive hunters- that is to say, they create dens by populated areas and regularly traveled passes, and grab whatever passes by. They will only leave once the area becomes less populated, then searching for greener pastures. Gricks often travel in packs, led by the strongest, best fed member.

Name: Griffon (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: Griffons are intelligent hybrids of lions and eagles. Their majesty is often hailed by cultures throughout the planes as a sign of goodness, and as such they are regularly used as mounts for good-aligned societies. The city of Waterdeep, the largest city of Faerun, maintained a large arsenal of Griffon cavalry. Netheril and Thay are two other superpowers that wielded the might of Griffons as their cavalry units. They are known to feed almost exclusively on horse flesh.

Name: Grimlock (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: Grimlocks are a species of humanoid creatures descended from two tribes of ancient barbarians that disappeared into the Underdark many millennia ago. Their children, blind and decrepit, now wander in the endless vistas of darkness in the subterranean landscape, serving mightier creatures when they can.

Name: Grimsley
Summary: Grimsley is a member of the Unova Elite Four and specializes in Dark-type Pokémon.

Name: Grippli
Summary: A peaceful tribal race, the Grippli appears like an oversized froh with human like limbs, they're native to jungle areas and only do trades with beings they have complete trust in. Grippli are quite good in learning, although they rarely produce metal products so any metal object they have is from a trade. Each tribe posseesses a Tribe Mother which one can distinguish from the rest through her size, she's said to possess the blood of the Gods and is the main priest in the tribe.

Name: Grizzly Bear
Summary: The Grizzly Bear is a subspecies of the Brown Bear found mostly in North America.[1] It is noted for being one of the largest subspecies of bears.

Name: Grung
Summary: One of the many amphibian humanoids in Dungeons and Dragons, the Grung are based on poisonous frogs. They emit a deadly poison from their skin, and also have a nasty bite and weapons to go alongside that.

Name: Guard Drake
Summary: A Guard Drake is a medium sized dragonic creature which is the result of a magical ritual involving dragon scales. A Guard Drake could be trained like a dog to protect a place, they also had various unique powers depending on whch dragon scales were used to make them

Name: Guilmon
Summary: Tier: Unknown | 9-B | High 8-C | At least High 8-C | 6-C | At least 6-C | At least 3-C, Up To 1-C with Digital Hazard | 1-C

Name: Half Ogre
Summary: The Half Ogre is a hybrid between humans and Ogres, smaller then Ogres but taller then most humans Half Ogres often act as leaders for Ogres who use their social skills, wits and battle skills to help their tribe.

Name: Halfling (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: The closest demihuman to humans, to the point where their name comes from being half as tall as human, Halflings are a naturally lucky race. Their society values comfort and security above all else, with them seldom venturing outside their home lands besides the dire of situations. This makes any Halfling adventurer the more fierce when going out to help their local community, with Halflings being naturally gifted in ranged combat and stealth.

Name: Hammer Drones
Summary: The Hammer Drones were the result of Justin Hammer enlisting Ivan Vanko to render Iron Man obsolete. Hammer wanted manned suits, but Vanko created remote-controlled drones instead, wishing to use them to attack Tony Stark. Hammer brought the drones to the Stark Expo in the hopes of regaining his contract with the government. Vanko sabotaged Hammer's efforts by activating the drones and making them wreak havok across the site of the Expo. Iron Man and War Machine were eventually able to defeat the drones, as well as Vanko himself.

Name: Hammerhead (Marvel Comics)
Summary: When left for dead in an alleyway after a brawl, a surgeon found Joseph and operated to fix him up, replacing his broken skull with a steel plate.

Name: Hank Pym (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Hank Pym, is a genius, one of the founding members of the Avengers, the creator of Pym Particles and Ultron, a sufferer of bipolar disorder and a modern-day superhero. He has acted under many memorable identities, such as Ant-Man, Giant Man, Goliath, Yellowjacket, and the Wasp. He is also the Earth's Scientist Supreme, as decreed by Eternity.

Name: Harpy (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: Harpies are predatory humanoids, a grotesque mixture of vulture and human. Their origin lies in the longing of the elves- once, an elf heard the song of a beautiful bird, and as she wandered through the forest, she saw yet another elven youth- a god, unbeknownst to her. Immediately, the god fled, but the youth was struck by his presence, and came to despair when she failed to find him. Another god came to her aid, and taught her the song of the birds in an attempt to lure the other deity back. After failing, the elf maiden cursed the gods, and became the first Harpy.

Name: Hatzegopteryx
Summary: Hatzegopteryx is a genus of azdarchid pterosaur, and is among the largest of them all (with a greater mass than even Quetzalcoatlus). Its name means "Hateg basin wing," referring to the place it was found in Transylvania, Romania, where it once inhabited in the Late Cretaceous period. Despite its robust structure, this large pterosaur was capable of flight much like other large azhdarchids.

Name: Havok
Summary: Havok (Alexander "Alex" Summers) is a fictional superhero appearing in American comic books published by Marvel Comics, commonly in association with the X-Men. He first appears in Uncanny X-Men No. 54 (March 1969), and was created by writerArnold Drake and penciller Don Heck. Havok generates powerful "plasma blasts", an ability he has had difficulty controlling. One of the sons of Corsair, he is the younger brother of the X-Men's Cyclops, and the older brother of Vulcan. He often resents Cyclops' authoritarian attitude and reputation as a model X-Man.

Name: Hawkeye (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Clinton "Clint" Barton was a former circus worker and criminal-turned-hero, who received his archery skills as a young boy through training with Swordsman and Trickshot. Barton would eventually join both the East Coast and West Coast branches of The Avengers, even leading at one time.

Name: Hawkmon (Miyako Inoue)
Summary: Miyako Inoue and Hawkmon are main characters from Digimon Adventure 02. Miyako one of the many viewers watching the battle against Keramon in Our War Game.

Name: Heckler & Koch MP7 Submachine Gun
Summary: The Heckler & Koch MP7 (Maschinenpistole 7) is a German personal defence weapon (PDW) designed and manufactured by Heckler & Koch (H&K) and chambered for the HK 4.6×30mm cartridge. It was designed with the new cartridge to meet NATO requirements published in 1989, as these requirements call for a personal defense weapon (PDW) class firearm, with a greater ability to penetrate body armor than current weapons limited to conventional pistol cartridges. The MP7 went into production in 2001. It is a direct rival to the FN P90, also developed in response to NATO's requirement. The weapon has been revised since its introduction and the latest production variants are the MP7A1 and MP7A2.

Name: Heinrich Zemo (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Baron Heinrich Zemo was born in 1900, the 12th Baron Zemo joined the Nazi Party early in its existence, quickly becoming one of the Nazis' top scientists and the most wanted Axis agent during World War II. Zemo was working on his invention known as Adhesive X when Captain America invaded his laboratories. In the course of destroying the only supply, the adhesive covered Zemo's cowled head, which became permanently affixed. As a result, Zemo was consumed with a violent, insane hatred for Captain America and mankind in general.

Name: Helicoprion
Summary: Helicoprion is a genus of large eugeneodont fish, a group of shark-like cartilaginous fish within the same group that includes modern chimaeras; while chimaeras are the closest living relative of Helicoprion, they are only distantly related. It lived around 290–270 million years ago during the early to middle Permian and were widespread in the oceans, found around the United States, Canada, Mexico, Norway, Russia, Kazakhstan, China, Japan, Laos, and Western Australia. They are famous for their one-rowed and laterally-compressed "tooth whorl" shape of their lower jaws, which aided them in catching prey at the time, and is the part most often fossilized. These creatures were among the largest cartilaginous fish, and the largest aquatic predators of their time and place.

Name: Hellcat (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Patricia "Patsy" Walker was a celebrity thanks to her mother's comic book series centered around her, and was living a model life with a husband who she had a crush on since high school, and money without hassle. But thanks to a particularly nasty divorce, she decided that her passion resided elsewhere from the typical household life, and with assistance from Beast scoured the streets as the crime-fighting vigilante known as Hellcat.

Name: Hellhound (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: Hell Hounds are a breed of extraplanar, fiery hound, often used as pets of infernal lords. Wild packs of Hell Hounds often roamed Baator, the Abyss, and even the Elemental Plane of Fire. As such, they could be found in the service of all manner of fiery outsiders, including Efreeti, Balors, and Pit Fiends.

Name: Helmed Horror
Summary: Helmed Horrors are silent warriors and guardians hailing from the time of the Netherese empire, created through powerful magic to create a construct with a sentience of its own. These warriors are designed to be loyal beyond a fault, and highly effective against invading spellcasters in particular. Despite appearing like simple animated suits of armor, Helmed Horrors in fact bear many magical abilities of their own, including the ability to imbue their weapons with arcane power and to see invisible foes.

Name: Helmut Zemo (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Baron Zemo is the 13th of the Zemos of Zeulniz and is one of Captain America's most notorious enemies, often giving him a run for his money with his sinister plots and tactical thinking. His father, Baron Heinrich Zemo was the master Nazi scientist in World War II and convinced his son of the ideology of the Nazis being the master race, and that he was the only Zemo in line for ruling the world. However, after his fathers apparent death, Zemo blamed Captain America and vowed revenge on him, and to this day, still remains one of his most deadly foes. Despite his conflict with Captain America, he has on occasions teamed up with the Avengers and has served as a founding member of the Thunderbolts.

Name: Hippogriff (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: Hippogriffs are believed to be distant cousins of Griffons, though instead of being an eagle-and-lion mixture, Hippogriffs bear more resemblance to a horse. Despite this they are still remarkably popular as mounts and, much like their cousins, are regularly used in airborne cavalry units.

Name: Hippopotamus
Summary: The hippopotamus is a herbivourous mammal that inhabits most of sub-saharan Africa.

Name: Hit-Monkey (Marvel Comics)
Summary: In mountainous wilderness, a clan of Japanese macaques took in a fugitive assassin, nursing him back to health with herbal remedies and hot springs, who upon regaining his health, began to hone his skills once more, practicing on snowmen.

Name: Hobgoblin (Dungeon and Dragons)
Summary: They fall beneath our blades,

Name: Homunculus (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: Homunculi are small contructs of magic users, created to act as assistants in their experiments. Indeed, such constructs are merely an extension of the master- it shares the thoughts and senses it has with its master, and the two are one being. They are telepathically bonded to their masters, and will never willingly leave them.

Name: Hook Horror
Summary: Hook Horrors are predators originating from the Underdark, and mixes traits of eagles and insects into a single malign entity. Unlike most animals, especially in the hostile caverns of the Underdark, Hook Horrors form castes of clans, maintaining familial ties all through its life- thus, it is not uncommon to encounter a large horde of Hook Horrors.

Name: Hop (Pokémon)
Key: '''By Himself''' | '''Pokémon Team (Early Game)''' | '''Pokémon Team (Mid Game)''' | '''Pokémon Team (Late Game/Beginning of Post Game)''' | '''Pokémon Team (End of Post Game/Galarian Star Tournament)'''
Summary: Hop (Japanese: ホップ Hop) is one of the rival characters in Pokémon Sword and Shield and Leon's younger brother. He is your main rival throughout the games, eventually undergoing a period of self-doubt after a humiliating defeat at the hands of Bede, as he didn't want to be so weak as to drag down his older brother's name. After his defeat at the hands of the player in the Champion Cup, he eventually decides to work toward becoming a Pokémon Professor.

Name: Horse
Summary: The horse (Equus ferus caballus) is one of two extant subspecies of Equus ferus. It is an odd-toed ungulate mammal belonging to the taxonomic family Equidae. The horse has evolved over the past 45 to 55 million years from a small multi-toed creature, Eohippus, into the large, single-toed animal of today. Humans began domesticating horses around 4000 BC, and their domestication is believed to have been widespread by 3000 BC. Horses in the subspecies caballus are domesticated, although some domesticated populations live in the wild as feral horses. These feral populations are not true wild horses, as this term is used to describe horses that have never been domesticated, such as the endangered Przewalski's horse, a separate subspecies, and the only remaining true wild horse. There is an extensive, specialized vocabulary used to describe equine-related concepts, covering everything from anatomy to life stages, size, colors, markings, breeds, locomotion, and behavior.

Name: Hououmon
Summary: Its Special Move "Starlight Explosion" has become even more powerful due to the increase in its holy power.

Name: Howard the Duck (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Howard Duckson, native of a parallel universe named Duckworld, was but an ordinary individual like many others, stuck in aimless and unsatisfying life. On a fateful day, a shift in the cosmic axis caused Howard to be trasported across the multiverse and into our universe. Him and other people likewise stranded from their home worlds banded together to find the source of their problem, but Howard's adventure was cut short when he fell into a dimensional abyss, ending up in the city of Cleveland. Howard had no choice by trying to make sense of his new situation the best he could, amongst hairless apes living in a world he never made!

Name: Howler
Summary: Howlers are predatory animals originating from Pandemonium, a realm of pure chaos. Often the creatures are imported from the plane, generally to the Lower Planes, for use as war hounds and exotic pets, often rivaling the status of creatures such as the Hellhound. They are famed for their unique, mind-numbing howl, which cripples enemies for easier hunting.

Name: Hulk (Marvel Comics)
Key: '''Bruce Banner''' | '''Grey Hulk''' | '''Childlike Hulk''' | '''World War Hulk''' | '''Devil Hulk'''
Summary: nan

Name: Human Torch
Summary: The Human Torch is a fictional character, a superhero that appears in comic books published by Marvel Comics. He is a founding member of the Fantastic Four. A similar, unrelated character of the same name and powers had been created in 1939 by writer-artist Carl Burgos for Marvel Comics' predecessor company, Timely Comics.

Name: Hunter (Fossil Fighters)
Summary: Tier: 9-B | At least 7-B, likely far higher | At least 7-B, likely far higher

Name: Hydra (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: Hydras are monstrosities with crocodile-like bodies and serpentine heads, ranging in number from five to twelve. Each hydra is descended from the primordial hydras, created when the dragon goddess Tiamat slew a fellow dragon deity, spreading her blood across the multiverse, each blood drop spawning a fearsome hydra. Hydras are famed for their unending hunger, for their sickening gluttony that often leads each head to turn on each other, devouring itself alive. Many warriors would hunt down and kill a Hydra in order to prove their strength.

Name: I, Vampire (Pre-Flashpoint)
Summary: The only vampire capable of resisting his own lust for blood, Andrew Bennett, I, Vampire, is a hunter of his own kind, having dedicated his immortal life to taking the life of Mary, Queen of Blood, his former love, and her Cult of the Blood Red Moon.

Name: Ice Mephit
Summary: The cruelest of Mephits, the Ice Mephit is composed of air and water. Alongside a Mephit's usual array of abilities, they have many cold-based abilities, being able to generate ice and fog alike.

Name: Iguanodon
Summary: The Iguanodon is a herbivorous dinosaur from the Cretaceous Period. It is the second dinosaur discovered. It is surprisingly famous even though it did not make an appearance in any of the Jurassic Park movies. They come in many different weights.

Name: Ijin Yu
Summary: Ijin Yu is the main protagonist of the Mercenary Enrollment manhwa. When Ijin was nine, he and his parents were involved in a plane crash. Although Ijin survived, he was orphaned and was stranded from his remaining family. Eventually he was taken in by an group called The Numbers. Ijin underwent harsh training, and he worked as a mercenary for about eight years, serving in the harshest battlefields across the world. Later, during a rescue mission, he saved a RoK major named Kang Hamchan, his team and a doctor. Kang Hamchan traced Ijin's family and helped him retire. Ijin underwent a six-month orientation from Major Kang to help him adjust to civilian life. He's currently living with his grandfather and his sister in Seoul. Aside from attending Shinan high school, Ijin works as a part-time bodyguard at the SW group's security team, along with classmate Koh Sukjoo.

Name: Immortus (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Growing old after after centuries of conquest and administrating timelines, Nathaniel Richards began seeking a way to achieve immortality and began studying the realm of Limbo and learned that it was a timeless place where he could live forever and decided to retire there to learn mastery of time. Breaching the barrier into Limbo, he later reinvented himself as Immortus and began following this destiny. But upon meeting the Time-Keepers he was manipulated into their servitude, and began working on his master plan to take over the timestreams and ensure by the end of time, only he remains.

Name: Imp (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: Imps are the most typical and average devils above the lemure fodder. Imps serve any number of purposes for their Archdevil overlords, ranging from assassins, foot-soldiers, scouts, and general cannon fodder.

Name: Indo-Pacific Sailfish
Summary: The Indo-Pacific sailfish (Istiophorus platypterus) is a species of billfish endemic to the Indian, Pacific, and Atlantic oceans. They are one of the fastest fish in the world.

Name: Inostrancevia (Real World)
Summary: Inostrancevia is a large carnivorous therapsid reptile, belonging to the group Gorgonopsia. Of all the gorgonopsids, Inostrancevia was the largest. It lived throughout present-day Siberia and North Africa during the late Permian Period. between 259-251.9 million years ago, and was an apex predator of its place and time. However, it would go extinct during the most catastrophic mass extinction event in Earth's history, the Permian-Triassic Extinction, at the end of both the Permian Period and the Paleozoic Era.

Name: Intellect Devourer
Summary: Intellect Devourers are, in simple terms, transformed brains of the victims of Mind Flayers. They are intelligent predators bred to take over the bodies of others, draining their intellect, and using their hollow shell to lure in more victims. As such, the creatures are extremely dangerous monstrosities that often rake in multiple victims.

Name: Invisible Blade
Summary: Masters of daggers and similar weapons, the Invisible Blade often appears suicidal to those looking from the side. However, their prowess with the blade is such that they can slay opponents far larger than them despite carrying nothing but a blade.

Name: Invisible Woman (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Dr. Susan "Sue" Richards (née 'Storm) was a college student before she was exposed to high levels of cosmic radiation when boyfriend and scientist, Dr. Reed Richards, took her with her younger brother, Johnny Storm and pilot Ben Grimm, into space in the stolen rocket Marvel-1. The radiation mutated her and her friends, turning her invisible and allowing her to create forcefields. Together they became the Fantastic Four, a team of adventurers who explored space, time and alternate dimensions and saved the world along the way from science-based threats, with Sue going by the name the Invisible Woman.

Name: Iowa-class Battleship
Key: '''Pre-Refit (World War II/Korean War/Vietnam War-era)''' | '''Post-Refit (Persian Gulf War-era)'''
Summary: The Iowa-class battleships were a class of fast battleships designed and fielded by the United States Navy in 1939–1940 to escort their Fast Carrier Task Forces operating in the Pacific Theater during World War II. Four were completed, while two more were laid down but were not finished before the war's end and were ultimately scrapped. Like other third-generation American battleships, the Iowa class emphasized speed in addition to secondary and anti-aircraft batteries.

Name: Iris (Pokémon)
Summary: Iris is a trainer from Unova. Originally one of the two gym leaders for Opelucid City, she became the champion of the Unova league after extensive training from Drayden.

Name: Iron Fist (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Iron Fist (Daniel "Danny" Rand) is a fictional character, a superhero appearing in comic books published by Marvel Comics. Created by Roy Thomas and Gil Kane, he first appeared in Marvel Premiere #15 (May 1974). He is a practitioner of martial arts and the wielder of a mystical force known as the Iron Fist, which allows him to summon and focus his chi. The character starred in his own solo series in the 1970s, and shared the title Power Man and Iron Fist for several years with Luke Cage, partnering with Cage to form the superhero team Heroes for Hire. The character has starred in numerous solo titles since, including The Immortal Iron Fist, which expanded on his origin story and the history of the Iron Fist.

Name: Iron Man (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: J.A.R.V.I.S.: Sir, there are still terabytes of calculations needed before an actual flight is adju- Tony: J.A.R.V.I.S., sometimes you gotta run before you can walk.

Name: Ironheart (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Riri Williams is an MIT student, and one of the smartest people on earth. She was hired by the CIA to find vibranium, but later got taken by the Wakandans to find the Tolokanil base. She has created a suit of armor for herself, granting her the name Ironheart.

Name: Isabeau (In Stars and Time)
Summary: Isabeau Manon Constantin Moineau is a major character in the game In Stars and Time and START AGAIN: a prologue, traveling with Mirabelle, Odile, Siffrin, and Bonnie on a quest to defeat the King and save Vaugarde from the fate of being frozen in time. Isabeau is a kind, cheerful person from the city of Jouvente. Throughout the game, he’s often shown making puns with Siffrin.

Name: J'son (Marvel Comics)
Summary: J'son was the ruler of the Spartax Empire who fell in love with a human, Meredith Quill, when he crash-landed on Earth. He promised to return for her, but never did, and his son grew to become Star-Lord.

Name: Jack Carver
Summary: Jack, a former United States Army Special Forces soldier, has left his past behind and offers his services as a freelance boat charter in the South Pacific. He is employed by a reporter named Valerie Constantine to take her to a mysterious island, once occupied by the Japanese during the war, claiming to study its little-known World War II ruins. When Valerie goes ashore alone on a jetski, Jack anchors down shortly before his boat is destroyed by a missile launched by an army of mercenaries occupying the island.

Name: Jack Russell (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Jack Russell is a werewolf dubbed Werewolf by Night. Afflicted with a curse that causes him to transform during a full moon, Russell strove to help other monsters in need and hunt monsters that were a danger to others. In order to assist his friend, Ted Sallis, Russell attended a gathering of monster hunters competing for the Bloodstone. Russell worked with Elsa Bloodstone to free Sallis, but in doing so exposed himself as a monster. Verussa Bloodstone captured him and forced him to transform, inadvertently unleashing the werewolf by night on her own forces. Russell spared Elsa and fled, reuniting with Sallis.

Name: Jackalwere
Summary: Jackalwere are infernal creatures created by the demon lord Graz'zt to serve his insidious servants, the Lamias. Cowards and charmers, the Jackalwere lulls enemies into a false sense of security and ease, then tears them apart. The creatures are designed to lie and to steal, to kidnap and to kill, for their masters.

Name: Jaculi
Summary: Being a 15 foot long snake it uses its innate camouflage abilities which it derives from the ability to alter its skin to either stone or wood it uses it to sneak on top of a tree and then long at an unsuspecting target with the precision and power of a spear.

Name: Jaguar (Real World)
Summary: The Jaguar (Panthera onca) is the largest felid in the Americas and has the highest bite force of any cat. Overall, the jaguar is the largest native cat species of the New World and the third largest in the world. This spotted cat closely resembles the Leopard, but is usually larger and sturdier. It ranges across a variety of forested and open terrains, but its preferred habitat is tropical and subtropical moist broadleaf forest, swamps and wooded regions. The jaguar enjoys swimming and is largely a solitary, opportunistic, stalk-and-ambush predator at the top of the food chain. As a keystone species it plays an important role in stabilizing ecosystems and regulating prey populations.

Name: Janma Gleamsilver
Summary: Janma Gleamsilver was an assassin working for the Zhentarim during the Tiamat crisis. Working as an investigator, she eventually joins a caravan of Dragon Cultists and a party of adventurers. From here, she works to manipulate the party into assisting her, using them to fight against a common enemy.

Name: Jasmine (Pokémon)
Summary: Jasmine is the leader of the Olivine Gym who specializes in Steel-type Pokemon.

Name: Jayna (Post-Rebirth)
Summary: Jayna is an Exxorian superhero who was sent to Earth after realizing her grandfather was an infamous corrupt politician who ruined the lives of virtually every family on their planet. As her father was a friend of Superman, she was offered an internship at the Hall of Justice an quickly became a true-blue member of the Justice League, sometimes assisting Superman and Batman on missions and later joined Young Justice as well. After going on a world-saving adventure without the permission of Superman and the other Leaguers, Jayna and her brother were kicked from the league, but became members of Asterisk, a team set up by the league to help the world in non-violent means.

Name: Jean-Luc Picard
Key: '''TV Picard''' | '''Movie Picard''' | '''Piloting auxiliary crafts''' | '''Assimilated into the Borg'''
Summary: Jean-Luc Picard, known to the Borg Collective by his designation of Locutus, was a celebrated Starfleet officer, archaeologist and diplomat who served during the latter two thirds of the 24th century. The highlights of his career were centered around assignments as commanding officer of the Federation starships: USS Stargazer, USS Enterprise-D, and the USS Enterprise-E. In these roles, Picard not only witnessed the major turning points of recent galactic history, but also played a key role in them, from making first contact as captain of the Federation's flagship with 27 alien species, including the Ferengi and the Borg.

Name: Jeff the Land Shark
Summary: Jeff is one of several land sharks created by M.O.D.O.K. Superior as a result of his many experiments. Jeff was incidentally found and rescued by the West Coast Avengers, leading him to be adopted by Gwenpool and becoming her pet, much to the uncertainty of her teammates. From there on, Jeff's charm earned him the favours of several other superheroes, such as Deadpool, Elsa Bloodstone and Kate Bishop, who attended him from time to time and even made him tag along in their adventures.

Name: Jigsaw (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Billy Russo was a favourite hitman for the Costa mob, nicknamed "the Beaut" because of his good looks. Russo was hired by the Costas to assassinate Frank Castle, but failed to do so as Frank narrowly avoided death in an explosion. Hours later, Castle, now turned into the Punisher, tracked down Russo to one of the Maggia's nightclubs: Salvagno's. Several criminals were killed, and Russo was thrown through a glass pane head-first. Somehow, he survived with his face torn to shreds; surgeons stitched it back together like a jigsaw puzzle. Taking advantage of his now hideous visage, the formerly handsome gangster took on the identity of Jigsaw and swore revenge against the vigilante, becoming his archnemesis.

Name: Jihyeon Lee
Summary: (이지현 Lee Ji-hyeon) Jihyeon Lee is a secondary character in Questism. She is currently the No.8 of West Gangbuk High, but was previously the No.9 of South Gangbuk High. She is also the love interest of Gukja Yang.

Name: Jim Hopper
Summary: Jim Hopper, nicknamed "Hop", is the chief of Hawkins Police Department. Hopper has lived in Hawkins nearly all his life, having attended high school with Joyce Byers and Bob Newby. He has also been addressed as "Sheriff Hopper," but this is not a correct title. Hopper was married and they had a daughter together, Sarah. They divorced after his young daughter died of cancer, which caused him to lapse into alcoholism. For a few years after Sarah's death, he was a cop in "a big city"; the show never states which city. When he had been in the city long enough, he moved back to Hawkins. Eventually, he grows to be more responsible, saving Will Byers as well as taking Eleven in as his adopted daughter. In Season 3, he tries to break up Eleven and Mike since their relationship is moving too fast for him, whilst simultaneously trying to rekindle his relationship with Joyce. After the events of Season 3, he was kidnapped by the Soviets and forced to do manual labor for them as their prisoner. He eventually managed to escape, and returned to his life with Eleven and Joyce.

Name: Josephoartigasia Monesi
Summary: Josephoartigasia monesi is the largest known rodent ever. It is significantly larger than any living rodent, weighing in at a range from 480-500 kg.[1] It may have used its incisors for the same reasons elephants used their tusks: for digging and as a defense mechanism. It lived from 4 to 2 million years ago during the Pliocene and early Pleistocene.

Name: Jubilee (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Jubilation Lee was the daughter of two wealthy Chinese immigrants, but after her parents lost all their money in the stock market and were subsequently killed, Jubilation was sent to an orphanage that she would soon run away from. Living in a mall, Jubilation discovered her mutant powers when she was cornered in a back alley by security guards, creating blinding lights that allowed her to escape. One day, the M-Squad was called in to capture her, but she was saved by Psylocke, Storm, Rogue and Dazzler. Jubilation followed them through a portal to the X-Men base. Eventually she freed Wolverine from the Reavers and went on several adventures with him before finally joining the X-Men as Jubilee.

Name: JumboGamemon
Summary: A gigantic Cyborg Digimon that added beam cannons to its entire body until the strength of its Metal Body's shell was compromised.

Name: Kamen Rider Kabuto
Summary: Souji: I'll only tell you this once. Those walking the same path don't merely pass at comrades. But those who walk different paths, and arrive together at the end are... Arata: …Friends. Are those your grandmother's words? Souji: No. They're my words.

Name: Kamen Rider KickHopper
Key: '''Sou Yaguruma''' | '''Kamen Rider TheBee/KickHopper''' | '''Post-Oma Day (Kamen Rider KickHopper)''' | '''Post-Oma Day (Another Kabuto)'''
Summary: Sou Yaguruma was originally an agent of ZECT who was the first user of the TheBee Zector and led the elite Shadow ZECT Troopers, being a perfectionist and tactician. But Souji Tendou constantly outwitted him, causing Yaguruma to place his sense of "Perfect Harmony" over his squad, resulting in him being dismissed. Upon his next arrival, he became a self-loathing man. Yaguruma became Kamen Rider KickHopper and used his new power to become a reoccurring threat to Tendou and the Worms.

Name: Kamen Rider Kuuga
Key: '''Yusuke Godai''' | '''Growing Form''' | '''Regular Forms''' | '''Rising Forms''' | '''Amazing Mighty Form''' | '''Ultimate Form'''
Summary: I don't want to see people crying anymore. I want everyone to smile! So have a good look... at my... transformation!

Name: Kang the Conqueror (Classic)
Summary: Nathaniel Richards, a 31st-century scholar and possible descendant of Reed Richards, becomes fascinated with history and discovers the time travel technology created by Victor von Doom. Richards then travels back in time to ancient Egypt aboard a Sphinx-shaped timeship and becomes the Pharaoh Rama-Tut, with plans to claim En Sabah Nur as his heir. Rama-Tut's rule is cut short when he is defeated by the time-displaced Fantastic Four.

Name: Karnak
Summary: Karnak is a fictional character appearing in American comic books published by Marvel Comics. He was created by Stan Lee and Jack Kirby and debuted in Fantastic Four (vol. 1) #45 (1965) along with other members of the Inhuman Royal Family.

Name: Kenku
Summary: Kenku are shady tricksters present in the land of Faerun. Known for their striking inability to speak on their own, they solely communicate via mimicking the voice patterns of others around them. They have the characteristics of large, flightless birds, and are descended from magical avians from the land of Kara-Tur. Thanks to the chaos of the Spellplague, Kenku were able to spread their influence across most of Faerun, and are noted as exceptional spies and assassins in Waterdeep and beyond. However, their primary bases were still exclusively in the Southeast in a territory known as "The Beastlands".

Name: King Cobra (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Klaus Voorhees was an ex-convict working with the humanitarian medical researcher Professor Ezekiel Shecktor in India on a universal antitoxin for snake venom. Jealous of Shecktor's success, Voorhees plotted to kill him and make the murder look like an accident. Hence, Voorhees induced one of the cobras kept in the laboratory to bite both Shecktor and himself. Voorhees planned to use the universal antitoxin to save himself from death. Unknown to Voorhees, the cobra had been irradiated. The combination of the radioactive venom in his bloodstream and the experimental anti-toxin which he used created a mutagenic catalyst which gave Voorhees certain cobra-like powers.

Name: Kobold (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: Kobolds are the lowest evolutionary form of dragons, and worship Tiamat (and her lesser god vassal, Kurtulmak, in particular). The creatures are cowardly, conniving, and experts in teamwork. Due in large part to their physical frailty, kobolds are extremely easy prey for the larger creatures of the world. Thus, Kobolds tend to form massive warbands fitted with warriors, mages, and inventors to increase their likelihood of survival.

Name: Koolasuchus
Summary: Koolasuchus is a large temnospondyl (Tetrapods that are possibly amphibians) that lived in Australia back when Australia was beneath the Antarctic Circle during the Cretaceous period 120 million years ago. It is also the last known temnospondyl unless it can be confirmed that modern amphibians are indeed related to temnospondyls. Koolasuchus presumably was 4-5 meters long and weighed nearly 500 kg.

Name: Korrina
Summary: Korrina is the Fighting-type gym leader of Shalour City and granddaughter of the Mega Evolution Guru.

Name: Kraven the Hunter
Summary: Sergei Kravinoff was born the scion of disgraced russian nobility, forcefully driven out of their homeland following the revolution and sent looking for refuge in the US. After years of abuse at his father's hands and the trauma of witnessing his mother's slow descent into madness and subsequent death, Sergei grew utterly dissatisfied with modern society and left looking for the peace that only a primeval world could give him. For decades he roamed the worlds' wildest lands, hunting any beast imaginable and earning fame as the matchless Kraven the Hunter. A fateful meeting with Aja Orisha allowed Sergei to be initiated to the mystical arts and acquire supernatural skills, although at great expenses due to his troubled mind.

Name: Kraven the Hunter (Last Son)
Summary: nan

Name: Kree (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Gleen Talbot: You're telling me that we got our asses handed to us by little green men. Phil Coulson: They were big and blue.

Name: Krenshar
Summary: Krenshars are large cat-like predators with extremely flexible flesh on its skull. While they otherwise mimic non-magical large predatory cat behavior, their unique trait of folding the skin on their head back to reveal the skull (an intimidation tactic) is documented as a fascinating evolutionary trait by sages.

Name: Krinth
Summary: Originally created from the forced union of demons and their slaves, the Krinth were originally an infertile race, however in the last 1,000 years they suddenly gained the ability to reproduce which lead to a rapid increase in their numbers. They are considered dour and humorless, and are also generally chaotic as a race. Their demonic heritage alongside familiarity with the shadow realm made them resistant to shadow magic and fear inducing effects.

Name: Kubanochoerus
Summary: Kubanochoerus is an extinct genus of large, long-legged suid. It lived in Africa, Europe, and Asia during the Miocene epoch, about 15.9 to 7.3 million years ago. The largest species, Kubanochoerus gigas, could reach notable sizes, standing about 1 meter at the shoulder and attaining masses of 500 kg.[1] Its most distinctive feature is the presence of horns on their skulls, with two small brow horns, and males possessing long horns on the top of their heads often likened to unicorn horns. It is thought the males used their horns for jousting in intraspecific combat. The adults would have likely inhabited open woodlands and savannas during its time.[2]

Name: Kuo-Toa
Summary: Kuo-Toa are a species of fish-human hybrids that once dominated the surface world, ruling the islands and seas alike. However, they were driven away from their homes, deep into the Underdark, the evil world beneath the world.

Name: Lady Bullseye (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Lady Bullseye was once a girl captured and being shipped overseas by slavers. However the operation was interrupted by Bullseye. When she saw Bullseye easily dispatch her captors, she became enamored with him, and when she was trained as an assassin, took up a guise similar to his. She first came into contact with Daredevil as an assassin of The Hand, but she was soon removed from The Hand and became a lieutenant of the Kingpin

Name: Lamia (Merlin: BBC Series)
Summary: In their wars with the Ancient Kings, the High Priestesses of the Old Religion combined the blood of a girl with the blood of a serpent's, creating fearsome and powerful monsters who were able to kill with a single touch. The Lamia were extremely powerful, but proved to be more dangerous than their creators imagined: the High Priestesses lost control of them and the Lamia continued to kill, unwilling to stop.

Name: Lance (Pokémon)
Summary: Lance (ワタル Wataru) is a Dragon-type Trainer, a member of the Kanto Elite Four in Pokémon Red, Blue, Fire Red and Leaf Green. 3 years later, after Red and Blue left the Indigo Plateau, he became Pokémon Champion of Kanto in Gold, Silver, Crystal, HeartGold and SoulSilver. Later on, he participated in the Pokémon World Tournament in Black 2 and White 2.

Name: Lantern Archon
Summary: Lantern Archons are simple celestial beings, gaseous orbs of light and the lowest orders of the Archons defending the Celestial realms. Often they are the converted souls of the Lawful Good mortals of the Prime Material. As newly converted souls, regardless of their intelligence in life, they are often simple creatures, merely the simple embodiment of goodness and order.

Name: Lascivious (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Davida DeVito was professional wrestler/mercenary under the alias Titania, being the member of all-female team known as the Grapplers. After a life of crime, she was killed by the Scourge of the Underworld.

Name: Latveria
Summary: The Kingdom of Latveria was once a small, isolated nation that was annexed from Hungary, but after it was conquered by Doctor Doom, who assumed the position of its absolute dictator, it became one of the world's greatest superpowers, solely because of his brilliance.

Name: Le Peregrine (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Alain Racine was a French writer who found a pair of wings, allowing him to soar the skies as Le Peregrine, France's most famous superhero.

Name: Leaf
Summary: Leaf is the female protagonist of FireRed and LeafGreen, the remakes of the original games Red, Blue, Green, and Yellow, being the counterpart of Red. She is revamped in Let's Go Pikachu and Let's Go Eevee into Green, a young and quirky but quite powerful Pokémon Trainer on the search for Mewtwo to make him part of her team, and battles the player in retaliation for them beating her to it.

Name: Leatherback Sea Turtle
Summary: The leatherback sea turtle (Dermochelys coriacea) is a critically endangered species of sea turtle native to oceans worldwide. They are the largest living turtle, the fastest living reptile, and the fourth largest living reptile, behind three crocodilian species.

Name: Leedsichthys
Summary: Leedsichthys problematicus ("leeds fish") was a giant fish of the Jurassic period. Its fossils were first found in England.

Name: Lenco Bearcat G2
Summary: The Lenco BearCat is a wheeled armored personnel carrier designed for military and law enforcement use. It is in use by several military forces and law enforcement agencies around the world.

Name: Leon (Pokémon)
Summary: Leon is the Champion of the Galar region's Pokémon League in Pokémon Sword and Shield. He is known far and wide for taking part in the Gym League Challenge at the tender age of 10 years old—and even more so for claiming victory in the Champion Cup on his first attempt.

Name: Leopard (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: One of the many animals that roam the jungle, the Leopard is a big feline that jumps down from trees in order to hunt.

Name: Leopard Seal
Summary: Leopard seals are the third largest species of pinniped, behind the walrus and the elephant seal. Leopard seals are named after their spotted coat and are known to have eaten a wide range in prey, ranging from penguins to other seals. Leopard seals are 2.4-3.5 meters long and weigh around 200 to 600 kg.

Name: Leshy (Inscryption)
Summary: There never seems to be enough time to do the things you want to do...

Name: Leucrotta
Summary: An evil and repulsive creature, the Leucrotta enjoys to torment and kill any creature it thinks it can. They have a hybrid body of a stag and hyena alongside a head akin to a badger which has bodily fluids constantly ooze from its mouth.

Name: Lex Luthor (Post-Flashpoint)
Summary: Lex Luthor appears as a representative the government has recruited to investigate and bring down Superman. Based on background signage seen throughout the New 52 books (including Justice League), LexCorp also exists. In Justice League No. 2, Batman notes that he and Superman have at least one thing in common: both of them speak openly of their distaste for Luthor. In the New 52 Action Comics (a series set some time before the events of Justice League #1), Luthor is hired by General Sam Lane to capture Superman by setting a train accident as a trap for him. The younger Superman, who is weaker and inexperienced, barely stops the train and is left unconscious. Lex collects Superman and subjects him to a series of tests to ascertain his strengths and weaknesses. He tortures Superman until the latter manages to escape. Lex is later revealed to have obtained contact with the "Collector of Worlds" through unknown means and was told to say the word "Krypton" to Superman. He later appears when the Collector abducts New Troy as one of the residents in the area. He along with Lois and Jimmy go into Glen Glenmorgan's hotel where Lex calls the Collector and it is revealed that Lex had made a deal with him. It is later revealed that Lex Luthor was the secret caller named "Icarus" that was giving secret information on Glen Glenmorgan to Clark Kent.

Name: Liger
Summary: The Liger is the result of a Male lion mating with a female tiger. It is notable for being the largest big cat in the world even surpassing Lions and Tigers.

Name: Lila Cheney
Summary: Young Lila Cheney discovered her mutant powers at a young age, exploring the stars galaxies afar.
