He is an opponent of the antihero known as The Punisher - originally a fairly traditional Punisher foe (having little in the way of superhuman powers) he evolved into a more powerful comic book super villain following his resurrection by a paramilitary group.

Name: Rust Monster
Summary: Rust Monsters are iconic creatures of the Dungeons and Dragons universe, and are the renowned antithesis to most fighter classes due to their ability to destroy metal on contact. Despite their fairly large size (being the size of a pony), they rarely deal in combat aside from their hunger for metal.

Name: Rylkar
Summary: Rylkar are rats that have evolved during heir time in the Underdark. They are known to enter an area, consume everything within it, and reproduce using all resources exponentially- thus leaving a rat-infested barrens. Rylkars bear a strong tie to flame, and view it as raw energy, something they can use to reproduce their thousands of young.

Name: Ryuki
Key: '''By Himself''' | '''Pokémon Team (Malie City)''' | '''Post-Game and Title Defense Team'''
Summary: Ryuki (Japanese: リュウキ Ryūki) is a non-player character in the Generation VII games, Pokémon Sun and Moon. He is a Pokémon Trainer who specializes in Dragon-type Pokémon.

Name: Saber-Toothed Tiger (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: Smilodon, or better known as Saber-Toothed Tiger is a large prehistoric cat which lived in icy plains and hills.They favor ambushes as their main way to get food, with their long fangs being especially deadly.

Name: Sabrina (Pokémon)
Summary: Sabrina is one of the eight gym leaders of Kanto, and the first psychic gym leader. She is the gym leader of Saffron City. Unlike many humans in the Pokemon universe, she has actual powers.

Name: Sahuagin
Summary: Utterly vile and ruthless, the Sahuagin, also known as Sea Devils, terrorize the sea and beaches alike. They hold incredible hate for sea elves, going of their way to destroy nearby communities of them.

Name: Sailsnake
Summary: The Sailsnake is a mutated form of the viper snake which has fins it uses to glide from place to place. Their size varies from 4 to 6 feet long and they can weigh up to 50 pound, but larger specimens can be bred if one desires so.

Name: Sakuyamon
Summary: Tier: Unknown | 9-B | High 8-C | At least High 8-C | 6-C | At least 4-C, Possibly 3-C | At least 3-C, Possibly higher | At least 3-C, Possibly higher

Name: Salamander (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: Native to the Realm of Fire, the Salamander are a hierarchical race which roams the land. The weaker Salamanders are often enslaved by other races, while the Noble are among some of the strongest inhabitants of the realm.

Name: Salmon Shark
Summary: The salmon shark (Lamna ditropis) is a species of mackerel shark endemic to subtropical waters worldwide. It is one of the fastest sharks in the world, and is one of the few known homeothermatic fish.

Name: Saltwater Crocodile
Summary: The Saltwater Crocodile is the largest of all living reptiles, as well as the largest terrestrial and riparian predator in the world.

Name: Samurai (Totally Accurate Battle Simulator)
Summary: The Samurai is a unit from the game Totally Accurate Battle Simulator, first introduced with the Dynasty faction, the Samurai is capable of deflecting multiple different projectiles in the game, making it a very useful troop in battle.

Name: Sand Tiger Shark
Summary: Sand Tiger Sharks (Carcharhinus leucas), also known as the grey nurse shark, are a species of mackerel shark found worldwide in temperate and subtropical ocean waters. They are a relatively placid and slow-moving shark, with no confirmed human fatalities, and can reach up to 3.2 meters in length and 159 kg in weight. Notably, they are widely kept in public aquariums due to their tolerance for captivity.

Name: Santánico Pandemonium
Summary: Santánico Pandemonium, formerly Esmeralda or Kisa, is a fictional character in the From Dusk till Dawn media franchise. She is the primary Queen Vampire/Culebra of the "Titty Twister", a strip club in the middle of a desolate part of Mexico.

Name: Sarcosuchus (Real World)
Summary: Sarcosuchus is an extinct genus of crocodyliform and a distant relative of living crocodylians. It lived 112 million years ago in Africa and South America during the Early Cretaceous period. It was much larger than the modern Saltwater Crocodile, weighing up to 4.3 metric tons.

Name: Satana Hellstrom (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Black Cat: Should we take him to the, I dunno, magic cops? Satana: No. That's not how this works. The penalty for upsetting the cart-- and pissing me off-- is stiff and immediate.

Name: Satyr (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: Half man and half goat in appearance, the Satyr is an all male fey creature that roams the Forgotten Lands. They are more concerned with courting women than anything else, with them most of the time not even having weapons on.

Name: Sauropelta
Summary: Sauropelta is a genus of armored dinosaur, belonging to the family of ankylosaurs known as Nodosaurids, of which it is one of the earliest best described. It's name means "lizard shield," due to its armored hide covered in osteoderms. It lived in North America around 108.5 million years ago, during the early Cretaceous, with fossils predominantly found in the Cloverly Formation in Montana, Wyoming, and possibly Utah. It had a narrow beak much like other Nodosaurids, indicating it was a browser,[1] inhabiting floodplains in the place and time it lived.[2]

Name: Sauroposeidon
Summary: Sauroposeidon is a genus of sauropod rivaling the Argentinosaurus in size (excluding weight), as well as being both taller and heavier than the Giraffatitan. It existed towards the end of the Early Cretaceous Period and it was the last known North American sauropod prior to an absence of the group on the continent for roughly 40 million years that ended with the appearance of Alamosaurus during the Maastrichtian (End of the Late Cretaceous Period).

Name: Scarecrow (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: A type of Golem, a Scarecrow is made via binding an evil soul to a regular scarecrow which gives it supernatural abilities like a gaze that can strike fear into people.

Name: Scientist Supreme (Andrew Forson)
Summary: Andrew Forson is an A.I.M. scientist who has served as its Scientist Supreme in the past. A manipulative yet driven personality, he led A.I.M. initially as it went public, and was able to use his charisma and leadership to form the new High Council of A.I.M. He was eventually ousted from his position by Sunspot, and has remained a prominent leader within the now-fractured organization.

Name: Screwball (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Screwball is a self-proclaimed performance artist, who livestreams her crimes to the internet for fame and attention. Possessing incredible parkour skills, she has been a frequent foe to Spider-Man.

Name: Sea Hag (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: Sea Hags are horrific appearing fey creatures often found around shorelines (as their name implies). Twisted and changed by the oceans they live in, they are considered the ugliest of all hags, even by other hags with whom they share sisterhood. As such, she is spiteful, and easily enraged- if something beautiful causes hope, she intends to counter it with fear. If something beautiful can improve life, she would instead unleash death.

Name: Sea Otter (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: One of the unique animals of Frostfell the Otter is a medium sized aquatic animal.

Name: Sea Spawn
Summary: Krakens, Sea Hags and Dragon Turtles are some of the creatures which can create Sea Spawns.

Name: Selphie Tilmitt (Kingdom Hearts)
Summary: Selphie Tilmitt is a minor character in the Kingdom Hearts series, originally from Final Fantasy X. She is one of the residents living in Destiny Islands and is part of a trio including Tidus and Wakka. In Sora's Dive to the Heart, She appears in the Destiny Islands area along with Wakka and Tidus. She asks Sora "What is most important to you?" Later, Selphie talks to Sora about the legends of mysterious effects the paopu fruit has on people. Sora can also challenge her to a duel. Selphie's fate after the Destiny Islands's destruction is unknown, but she reappears on the island once Sora defeats Ansem and the worlds are restored.

Name: Serag Kull
Summary: Cruel and sly, captain Serag Kull is a prime example of all that is wrong with the Red Plumes. A well connected man, he uses his position to get away with beating people senseless and extorting local merchants.

Name: Sewerm
Summary: The Sewerm is a relatively big aquatic snake that measures up to 2.4 m, this snake has also adapted to live in swamps and sewers hence its name but its most noteworthy ability is the oil it secrets which can numb one's sense of touch. Due to this oil the Sewerm is sought up by doctors in order to use the oil as a pain killer.

Name: Shades (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Hernan Enrique Salazar Alvarez, also known as Shades, is a criminal and member of the Rivals, before being sent to Seagate Penitentiary where he worked for Albert Rackham, organizing illegal prison fights. Once released from Seagate, Shades was recruited by Diamondback and was sent to Harlem to watch over the criminal operations of Cottonmouth, which put him back into conflict with Luke Cage, while also watching the rise of Mariah Dillard, in the wake of Cottonmouth's death. As Diamondback arrived into Harlem to kill Cage, Shades stayed by his side although his constant questioning of his employer eventually made him his target, forcing him to side with Dillard and then betray Diamondback in order to save his own life.

Name: Shadow (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: An enemy of the living that lurks in the darkness, the Shadow is a menacing foe to face in combat. As their name implies, they're animated shadows of dead people. Their origins are shrouded in mystery however one thing is for certain, that being that their touch is deadly. Their touch siphons life and strength from those unlucky enough to be hit by it, and if one dies from this their shadow becomes a new Shadow monster.

Name: Shadowcat
Summary: Katherine Anne "Kitty" Pryde is a fictional character and superhero that appears in comic books published by Marvel Comics. The character first appeared in Uncanny X-Men #129 (January 1980) and was co-created by writer-artist John Byrne and Chris Claremont.

Name: Shang-Chi (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Born to the fearsome Fu Manchu, Shang-Chi was trained to be a living weapon to serve under Si-Fan, becoming one of the greatest martial artists in the world. However, during his first assignment, he came to know of his father's true identity as an international criminal mastermind, and defected soon afterwards. He has fought against the tyranny of his father ever since, and continues to fight for the safety of those around him.

Name: Shastasaurus
Summary: Shastasaurus ("Mount Shasta lizard") is an extinct genus of ichthyosaur from the Late Triassic. Specimens have been found in the United States, Canada, and China.

Name: Shinobu Kawasaki
Summary: Shinobu Kawasaki is a combatant in the Mega Fight Tournament, seeking to win the tournament to get back at Tamaki Shindou for her previous defeat.

Name: Shocker Lizard
Summary: The Shocker Lizard is small reptile while is able to produce none lethal shocks on its own but in groups their electricty becomes quite dangerous.

Name: Siffrin
Summary: This profile contains major spoilers for the entirety of In Stars And Time. It is highly suggested that you fully complete the game before reading this profile.

Name: Silver (Pokémon)
Key: '''By Himself''' | '''Pokémon Team (Cherrygrove City)''' | '''Pokémon Team (Azalea Town)''' | '''Pokémon Team (Burned Tower)''' | '''Pokémon Team (Goldenrod Tunnel)''' | '''Pokémon Team (Victory Road)''' | '''Pokémon Team (Post-Game Battles)'''
Summary: Silver (Japanese: シルバー Silver) is one of the main characters and the rival of Pokémon Gold, Silver, Crystal and Pokémon HeartGold and SoulSilver. He is the son of Team Rocket Boss Giovanni that fought many times with Ethan, Kris or Lyra.

Name: Silver Sable (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Daughter of a famed Nazi hunter Ernst Sablinova, Silvija asked to train under her father to avenge her mother's death, soon exceeding her father's expectations to be one of the best assassins across the globe, and succeeded him as the Head of Sable International, leader of the Wild Pack and monarch of Symkaria.

Name: Siv
Summary: Possessing a frog-like head and skin (With their skin color being either pale green or blue), the Siv are a Humanoid race that is rather egotistical, considering how relatively small they are in the grand scheme of things. They're known as a rather graceful and calculating race, which is further shown by their favored class being monks.

Name: Skeleton (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: Skeletons are one of, if not the most common types of Undead in any D&D setting. Cheap, loyal, and easy to make, they often serve as the vast majority of a necromancer's army or are found wandering, mindless, across the world. Oftentimes skeletons were made of a variety of creatures, even non-humanoids such as dragons, giants, and beasts.

Name: Skin (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Angelo Espinosa was born in the barrio in South Central Los Angeles. His girlfriend, Tores, became a gang member, straining their relationship because Angelo refused to fly colors, mostly for his mother's sake. One night, Tores and some of her friends picked Angelo up to cruise, but it turned into a drive-by shooting. The stress of the incident caused Angelo's powers to manifest, and he passed out. He woke up with the car on fire, Tores' friend Gordo dead, and Tores gone. A homeless man was trying to steal Angelo's wallet while he was sleeping, and, as Angelo fled the burning car, it exploded, killing the man. With his wallet found on the unidentifiable corpse of the homeless man, Angelo Espinosa was declared legally dead. None of his friends or family were aware of this and many truly believed him to be dead. Angelo left town to keep his mutation secret, and because he believed he was protecting Tores from a murder rap.

Name: Skin Kite
Summary: Made from stolen skin and needing to absorb new skin in order to repair their rotting body, a Skin Kite is a terrible sight to behold. They possess the ability to fly which they use alongside their stealth ability to latch onto creatures and absorb their skin in order to both repair the skin Kite's body and produce new Skin Kites.

Name: Skum
Summary: The Skum is a monster created by the Aboleth, it's made from human stock but unlike a human it must stay in water or else its skin may start errupting which harms them.

Name: Slaad Tadpole
Summary: The baby stage of Blue and Green Slaads, the Slaad Tadpole is the result of terrible misfortune. They are created by either Red Slaad's claw attack, where they implant an egg which after some time hatches inside the creature, eating them from the inside out. Afterwards it takes for the Slaad Tadpole between 2 to 24 hours to become a full Slaad, assuming no one kills them before hand.

Name: SMAW
Summary: The SMAW (Shoulder-launched Multipurpose Assault Weapon) is a shoulder launched rocket weapon with the primary function of being an assault weapon, and secondary purpose being an anti armor rocket launcher.

Name: Smilodon
Summary: Smilodon or the Saber-Toothed Cat, is an extinct genus of saber-toothed cat that inhabited North and South America during the Ice Age. Smilodon is often erroneously called the Saber-Toothed Tiger. In reality, the Smilodon genus is very distantly related to the Panthera genus, which is the genus that the tiger belongs to.

Name: Smilosuchus
Summary: Smilosuchus is a genus of leptosuchomorph parasuchid, a group of phytosaurs, which were large reptiles similar to crocodiles but not closely related; phytosaurs displayed convergent evolution with crocodiles and occupied the niche of semi-aquatic ambush predators,[1] especially based on the positioning of their eyes and nostrils. Three species of this genus have been identified: Smilosuchus gregorii, Smilosuchus adamanensis, and Smilosuchus lithodendrorum. The ridges on the snout varied among the three species.

Name: Snow Cloak
Summary: Appearing like a 2 headed mantis ray, the Snow Cloak is a cunning hunter of the frozen lands using its natural colouring alongside great stealth abilities to ambush prey and then attack it with varuious spells.

Name: Snow Goblin
Summary: Standing between 3 to 4 feet tall, Snow Goblins are a Goblinoid creature that inhabits cold lands. Their voices can be heard from miles away and are used as hunting signals. The females are usually larger and more aggressive then males.

Name: Snow Golem (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: Made from snow this golems are found in both Icewind where they appear in their weaker forms and while their stronger variant exist in Ravenloft where they act like guardians for various places and appear like statues

Name: South American short-faced bear
Summary: The South American short-faced bear is an extinct bear species in the genus Arctotherium. It is often considered to be the largest bear of all time. A specimen from Buenos Aires showed an individual estimated, using the humerus, to weigh between 983 and 2042 kg, though authors consider the upper limit as improbable and say that 1588 to 1749 kg is more likely. An estimated standing height for the bear is 3.4–4.3 meters.

Name: Sovereign Glut
Summary: Sovereign Glut is a deposed myconid regent, his circle destroyed by duergars who left him as the sole survivor. Now hiding out in another myconid circle, Glut seeks aid in destroying the duergar who slaughtered his people and silenced their song. Once his people are avenged, he then prepares to take down his benefactor, Sovereign Spaw, another myconid ruler who did nothing as Glut's people perished around him- in swearing his revenge, Glut swears to initiate the "Age of Glut" in the Underdark, where he will lead his people with a new song- a song of war and bloodshed.

Name: Space Eel
Summary: One of the many creatures that roam space in Dungeons and Dragons, the Space Eel is a scavenger that flies around. They are 5 feet long, and prefer to target smaller creatures than themselves for food. They are sought after for their meat, which is easier said than done.

Name: Space Swine
Summary: Created and breed by the dohwars, the Space Swine is a species of winged boars. They stand 3 feet tall, and 5-6 feet long. The Space Boar can be used for many things, be it a beast of burden, a tracker, or even as a battle beast. Space Swine trained for combat are called Death Squealers.

Name: Spectacled Bear
Summary: The spectacled bear is also known as the Andean bear, mainly because the spectacled bear is native to the Andes mountain range of South America. The spectacled bears territory ranges from northwest Colombia, into Argentina, Venezuela and Brazil. The spectacled bear generally feeds on berries and shoots found both on ground level and in the trees. The spectacled bear also feeds on insects and small mammals and reptiles, and occasionally cattle.

Name: Spectral Panther
Summary: Mysterious creatures, the Spectral Panther is a panther warped by the Shadowfell to the point where it has became far larger and gained various magical abilities.

Name: Spider-Man (Reign)
Summary: In an alternate universe, Peter Parker's time with Mary Jane had given her cancer, which she died from. Parker had retired from superheroics and was working as a florist, while a merciless and oppressive police force, named "The Reign", take power, imprisoning every superhuman they can find.

Name: Spider-Man Noir
Summary: Spider-Man Noir (Peter Parker), often referred to as Spider-Noir, Spider-Man, or simply Noir, is a superhero appearing in American comic books published by Marvel Comics. Part of the Marvel Noir universe (Earth-90214), this alternate version of Spider-Man is a noir-themed take on the character and emerges in a version of New York during the Great Depression.

Name: Spinosaurus (Real World)
Summary: Spinosaurus (meaning "spine lizard") is a genus of theropod dinosaur that lived in what now is North Africa, about 112 to 93.5 million years ago.

Name: Spitfire
Summary: The Spitfire is a single seat, single engine fighter aircraft designed and manufactured by Supersubmarine before World War II, making its first flight in 1936 and entering service a year before the start of the second world war. The fighter was built in many different variants, and more Spitfires have been produced than any other British aircraft, with over 20000 built by the end of the war.

Name: Spitting Crawler
Summary: The Spitting Crawler is a small lizard which is a popular companion choice by Drow wizards, it's also a hunter of bugs and various slimes.

Name: Spock
Summary: Tier: 9-C physically. At least 8-C with phaser. | 9-B. At least 8-C with phaser.

Name: Spore Servant Octopus
Summary: A creation of the Myconid, this creature is a dead giant octopus animated by spores. It in one of many possible creatures Myconid might employ to defend themselves. One notable example of this creature resides in Stormwreck Isle, where the creature was made as a latch ditch effort to protect the colony.

Name: Spotted Lion (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: Twice the size of a regular lion, the Spotted Lion is a common pet for Stone and Cloud Giants. It often forms massive prides to hunt animals such as Giant Elks or Mammoths.

Name: Sprite (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: A possible relative of the Pixies, the Sprites are a warrior race of fey that fiercely protects their forest. They are far more martial than other Fey, using poisonous arrows to incapacitate intruders.

Name: Star-Lord (Classic)
Summary: Peter Quill, alias Star-Lord, was born during an unusual astronomical phenomenon when many of the planets aligned. Quill was raised by his single mother, Meredith. One day Peter saw an Ariguan spaceship land, and his mother was killed by the aliens. When he told the police his mother had been killed by aliens, no one believed him and he was put in a state orphanage. He ran off when he was fifteen and eventually became a trainee NASA astronaut. When the alien entity called the Master of the Sun visited the space station that Quill was stationed at and offered the mantle of Star-Lord to a worthy candidate, Quill volunteered, but was rejected in favour of another astronaut. Quill was outraged, stole a scoutship, and on returning to the space station took his colleague's place. Quill was then chosen to become Star-Lord, with the Master of the Sun first creating an illusion in which he was able to find and kill the aliens that murdered his mother to free him of his past. Equipped with a sentient vessel called "Ship", Quill commenced his role as Star-Lord.

Name: Star-Lord (Modern)
Summary: Peter Quill is a human-Spartoi hybrid who took the title Star-Lord and patrol the stars, earning a reputation as a hero during his various travels. However, an encounter with the Fallen One forced Peter to commit genocide in order to defeat him. Guilt-stricken, he would sign on to fight against the Annihilation Wave that had invaded the universe, serving as an invaluable tactician. After the war, he would inadvertently allow the Phalanx, a robotic race, to cripple the Kree, and would go on to lead a suicide squad to help save the galaxy. This team would soon blossom into the Guardians of the Galaxy, believing that the universe in its current state was in need of heroes.

Name: Stegosaurus
Summary: Stegosaurus is a herbivorous dinosaur from the Jurassic period. It lived in North America. It is one of the most popular herbivorous dinosaurs.

Name: Stegosaurus (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: It is the same creature as it is in real life but exists in Dungeons and Dragons.

Name: Stench Kow
Summary: The Stench Kow is a cattle variant found across the Nine Hells with some found as low as Acheron, Gehenna, and even Hades. As herd animals they graze the fields and eat the local plants, they're also often raised by Archdevil.

Name: Steven Stone
Summary: Steven Stone is the current (previously former) champion of the Hoenn region, and the heir to the Devon Corporation. He enjoys going out to collect rare gems and stones, and will travel all around the world for them. He has been seen in Kanto, Johto, and Unova.

Name: Stielhandgranate
Summary: The Stielhgandgranate (German for "stick hand grenade") was a standard issue of hand grenade of the German Empire during World War I, and became the widespread issue of Nazi Germany's Wehrmacht during World War II. The very distinctive appearance led to it being called a "stick grenade", or "potato masher" in British Army slang, and is today one of the most easily recognized infantry weapons of the early 20th century.

Name: Stilt-Man
Summary: Wilbur Day was an engineer working for Kaxton Laboratories when he stole a hydraulic apparatus, which he built into a battle suit that he used to work as the criminal "Stilt-Man".

Name: Stirge
Summary: Appearing like a hybrid of a mosquito and a bat the Stirge while on its not a great danger is a deadly foe if one encounters it in swarms. Its prey is any warm blooded creature, some Stirges even have a prefernce for humans, it will attack via attaching itself to its prey and suck their blood until they're full and even suck extra blood for reserves, after they're done eating they'll go to sleep for several days depending on how much blood they drained.

Name: Styracosaurus
Summary: Styracosaurus is a ceratopsian known for its spiked frill. It had four to six parietal spikes, a jugal horn on each cheek, and a long nasal horn in front that can reach up to 60 cm.

Name: Suzuyama Reo
Summary: Suzuyama Reo was a kindhearted girl until a man killed her sister and just like Uruma she felt a lust for revenge. Determined to make the man that killed her sister suffer. She trains to be able to torture and assasinate him.

Name: Swarm of Animated Books
Summary: One of the many constructs in Dungeons and Dragons, the Swarm of Animated Books is what the name implies. They are able to fly around, battering enemies with their bodies. As books they are weak to flames.

Name: Swordfish
Summary: Swordfish are one of many commercially-harvested fish. Named after their swordlike beaks, swordfish use their beaks to slash at prey before gulping them up. Smaller prey are simply swallowed whole. Aside from parasites such as cookiecutter sharks, lampreys, and remoras, few creatures can prey on adult swordfish, namely orcas and shortfin mako.

Name: Taichi Yagami (Adventure 2020)
Summary: Taichi "Tai" Yagami and Agumon are main characters from the 2020 Reboot of Digimon Adventure. After being forcefully sucked into a Digital Space, Taichi meets Agumon alongside Yamato and Gabumon and defeats Algomon. Afterwards, Taichi and Co end up being sent to the Digital World where they go on an adventure to save the Holy Digimon while learning the secrets behind the Holy War between the forces of Light and Darkness.

Name: Tamaki Shindou
Summary: Tamaki Shindou is a combatant in the Mega Fight Tournament, and its returning champion after two consecutive wins. She is a prominent member of the Tennis Club.

Name: Tapir
Summary: Tapir is a large, herbivorous mammal, similar in shape to a pig, with a short, prehensile nose trunk. Tapirs inhabit jungle and forest regions of South America, Central America, and Southeast Asia.

Name: Tarantula (Anton Miguel Rodriquez)
Summary: Anton Miguel Rodriquez, also known as Tarantula was a soldier in South America, using his skills to kidnap politicians and get ransom for their release. However, his greed got the best of him, causing him to shoot his own commander, leading to a series of events that had him flee the area. Afterwards he came to the USA, continuing his crime spree, with Spider-Man thwarting him multiple times.

Name: Tarantula (Luis Alvarez)
Summary: The replacement of Anton Miguel Rodriquez, Luiz Alvarez, also known as Tarantula is one of the many super soldiers in Marvel. Serving the Delvadian army, he's a ruthless killer, aiming to eliminate anyone who poses a threat to the Delvadian regime.

Name: Tarbosaurus
Summary: Tarbosaurus is a genus of theropod dinosaur that lived in what is now Asia, during the end of the late Cretaceous period, about 70 million years ago. Although slightly smaller than the Tyrannosaurus, Tarbosaurus was one of the largest tyrannosaurids, with large specimens measuring about 9.5-10m in length.

Name: Taskmaster (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Tony Masters is a man who can mimic and copy physical actions. He considered a career as a crime fighter but decided to become a professional criminal. After using his skills to complete a series of jobs, he used the capital to start an academy to train aspiring professional criminals around the world. Eventually, his operations were discovered and shut down by the Avengers. Since then Taskmaster has worked as a spy, a mercenary and still acts as a teacher to certain individuals, all for the sake of profit.

Name: Team Rocket Trio
Summary: ...and make it double!

Name: Teresa Parker (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Teresa Parker was the daughter of C.I.A. agents Richard and Mary Parker, and the younger sister of Peter Parker. After the death of their parents, Peter was sent to live with their Aunt May and Uncle Ben, while Teresa, whose birth had been kept a secret, was adopted. Many years following the deaths of Richard and Mary, Teresa was personally recruited into the C.I.A. by Nick Fury, and during one of her assignments, she discovered the truth of her parentage, and has since worked alongside her surviving brother to save the world any way she can.

Name: Texas Twister (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Drew Daniels was just a cattle hand in Texas, when a tornado and radiation from a nearby nuclear reactor affected him at the same time. The net effect was to give him the power to generate tornadoes at will.

Name: Thalamra Vanthampur
Summary: Starting life as a simple worker in the cellars inside Baldur's Gate, Thalamra Vanthampur managed through her charisma, skills and dedication to rise all the way to the position of Master of Drains and Underways in the city.

Name: Thanos Simonattoi
Summary: Thanos, full name being Thanos simonattoi, is the single dinosaur species contained in the genus of carnivorous Brachyrostran Abelisaurid theropods also named Thanos. This animal, obviously named after the Marvel Comics character of the same name, lived during the Santonian stage of the Late Cretaceous Period in what is now known as Brazil.

Name: The Black Knight (Monty Python)
Summary: The Black Knight is a mysterious figure who guards a "bridge" (a plank of wood) over a small stream. Arthur encounters him while searching for the Holy Grail, leading to a duel in which the Black Knight loses his arm. Despite declaring himself the victor (and getting his other arm chopped off), the Black Knight refused to relent, causing Arthur to lop off his foe's legs before continuing on his way, with the Black Knight screaming and cussing for the King of Britain to return.

Name: The Hood (Marvel Comics)
Summary: The man who will become known as the Hood was originally a simple thug from the suburbs of New York City. His life was made of small crimes committed alongside his cousin John King, a relationship with a girl waiting their child and the preoccupations for his mentally-ill mother. Parker Robbins always aspired to be a supervillain and his career began when a would-be robbery turned into an encounter with a demon clad in red. Parker shot the monster down and looted it of its hood and boots. Upon realizing that these items bore magical powers, Parker finally saw the potential to satisfy his ambitions and began his journey to reach the top of the city's underworld.

Name: The King (In Stars and Time)
Summary: The King is the main antagonist of the game In Stars and Time and START AGAIN: a prologue, opposing the saviors by freezing Vaugarde in time in an effort to preserve it and save it from the fate that his own country, the island north of Vaugarde, met: being erased from people’s memories.

Name: The Mad Hermit
Summary: The Mad Hermit is a crazed and insane hermit living near the Keep on the Borderlands, a low-level module for Dungeons and Dragons. The hermit has lived cast out of society for some time, and has been deemed a danger to travelers of the area.

Name: The Owl (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Leland "Owl" Owlsley was a ruthless financier, although he had a respectable image. An internal audit by IRS discovered files relating Owlsley with different illegal business enterprises. Owlsley decided to get rid of his previous image, and began scheming to become a crimelord in New York City. He began by hiring thugs for the Owl's Gang and created a small crime empire. Somehow, "the Owl" managed to get a serum he supposedly used to glide and even fly for short distances; he had to use the serum frequently to retain these powers.

Name: The Player (Block Tales)
Summary: The Player is an unofficial name belonging to the playable character in Block Tales. They're a Robloxian from the future that was sent back to the past after hitting a device with the ability to mess with time in an effort to stop the main antagonist from kidnapping Builderman. After being sent back to 2010, they encounter Shedletsky, who is heavily injured from fighting Red and Blue. Upon defeating red and blue, Shedletsky sends them on a quest to find the seven sword fight on the heights swords (Sfoth swords/Sfoths) in order to both stop mysterious individuals who had fought Shedletsky beforehand from misusing their power and rescue Builderman

Name: The Question (Vic Sage) (Post-Crisis)
Summary: Charlie Szasz was abandoned on an orphanage's steps in Hub City, and grew up as a ruffian who would eventually pursue a career path in investigative journalism as the hard-headed Vic Sage. One of his cases led him to reconnect with his old professor, Dr. Aristotle Rodor, who gave him a pseudoderm mask to better hide his identity when pursuing the case. Thus the Question was born, a vigilante using his fists to solve crimes and get answers much needed.

Name: The Red Bee (Golden Age)
Summary: Richard Raleigh was the first Red Bee, a superhero of the Golden Age. An assistant to the District Attorney, Richard Raleigh became tired of seeing criminals get off on technicalities and decided to use his skills as an apiarist and fighting abilities to fight crime as the Red Bee.

Name: The Saviors (In Stars and Time)
Summary: This profile contains major spoilers for In Stars And Time. It is highly suggested that you fully complete the game before reading this profile.

Name: The Scavenger
Summary: The Scavenger is the main character of the indie game Raw Metal, their goal is to stop an evil organisation, Orpheus Technologies, from exploiting the planet Charybdis for all its dangerous resources.

Name: Thurstwell Vanthampur
Summary: The eldest son of Thalamra Vanthampur, Thurstwell Vanthampur is a hateful frail man in his 40s.

Name: Tidus (Kingdom Hearts)
Summary: Tidus is a minor character in the Kingdom Hearts series, originally from Final Fantasy X. He is one of the residents living in Destiny Islands and is part of a trio including Selphie and Wakka. In Sora's Dive to the Heart, Tidus appears in the Destiny Islands area along with Wakka and Selphie. He asks Sora, "What are you so afraid of?" Later, Tidus will offer to duel Sora on the small island. Tidus's fate after the Destiny Islands's destruction is unknown, but he reappears on the island once Sora defeats Ansem and the worlds are restored.

Name: Tiger (Real World)
Summary: The tiger (Panthera tigris) is a member of the Panthera genus and is the largest living felid around. It is widely recognized due its pattern of dark vertical stripes on reddish-orange fur with a lighter underside.[1]

Name: Tiger Shark (Real World)
Summary: Tiger sharks are among the most dangerous sharks to humans. They rank second in shark attacks, only behind the great white shark. Tiger sharks typically reach lengths of 3.25 to 4.25 meters (10 ft 8 in to 13 ft 11 in) and weigh around 175 to 635 kg (386 to 1400 lb), although some females reportedly measured over 5 meters (16 ft 5 in).

Name: TigerVespamon
Summary: Tier: 9-B | High 8-C | 6-C | At least High 6-C, higher with Nitro Stinger | 5-B, higher with Nitro Stinger

Name: Tigra (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Tier: 9-B | At least 8-C, at most High 8-C

Name: Titanis
Summary: Titanis is a genus of phorusrhacid, the group of birds informally dubbed "Terror Birds." It is unique among the phorusrhacids in that it took part in the Great American Interchange; it was among some South American animals that spread to North America, while some North American animals spread to South America. It inhabited North America during the early Pliocene to early Pleistocene, and would have lived alongside canids, hyaenids, and felids, along with ursids; it lived in a xeric thorn-scrubland and grassland environment in places such as Florida.

Name: Titanoboa
Summary: Titanoboa, meaning "titanic boa", is a prehistoric, extinct genus of a snake that lived in what is now Colombia, living about 58-60 million years ago. The only species discovered so far is Titanoboa cerrejonensis, with specimens being able to reach 13 meters (42.65 ft) in length and weighing up to 1,135 kg (2,500 lb).

Name: Tomb Mote
Summary: Tomb Motes are animated pieces of corpses that come to life after some time in undisturbed tombs. They are born from matted hair, bone chips, the odd tooth, pieces of tombstones, and the dirt itself. They serve no particular purpose but are invariably evil, attacking any intruders in the domain of the dead.

Name: Topi
Summary: A Topi is a type of undead created from a shrunken corpse of a human, they're 2 feet high, they also often have fixed expressions due to the process of shrinking their body endured. They're excellent jumpers for their size, which they often use to get in advantageous positions where they can ambush targets and use their poisonous claws to harm them.

Name: Torami Honjou
Summary: Torami Honjou is a combatant in the Mega Fight Tournament. She is a prominent member of the Karate Club, who lost to Tamaki Shindou in the last competition, stoping at nothing in order to prove herself and reclaim her victory.

Name: Tortle
Summary: Now I search for a friend

Name: Toxodon
Summary: Toxodon is a genus of ungulate megafauna. It's name means "bow tooth," referring to the shape of the teeth on its somewhat hippopotamus-like mouth.[1] This large herbivore was prevalent throughout South America 11.6 million to 11,000 years ago, during the late Miocene to Holocene epochs, feeding on a variety of vegetation based on location.[2] Among many other forms of megafauna, Toxodon died aout during the extinctions around the end of the Last Ice Age.

Name: Trapper (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: One of many manta-like creatures in Dungeons and Dragons, the Trapper mimics the environment, springing upon prey that steps upon it, crushing them to death.

Name: Trapster (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Born in Gary, Indiana, Peter Petruski he worked as a research scientist in New York City for a major corporation. While working there he patented a multi-polymer adhesive that made him very wealthy and made him the top of his profession. However, instead of continuing his successful career, Petruski decided to turn his skills toward a life of crime, a move he believed would be more lucrative, and under the moniker of Paste Pot Pete, committed various robberies, all of which were stopped by the Human Torch.

Name: Trebuchet
Summary: The Trebuchet, also known as the Counterweight Trebuchet, is a type of catapult that utilizes a counterweight to launch a powerful stone projectile over great distances. It became increasingly more common than catapults and were preferred over said weapons due to being far more accurate and powerful.

Name: Tri-Flower Frond
Summary: Found in deep jungles this plant is a dangerous hunter which uses its different flowers in tendam in order to kill its prey via poison and corrison and then absorb its bodily fluids.

Name: Triceratops
Summary: Triceratops is a genus of ceratopsid dinosaur that lived during the late Maastrichtian stage of the Late Cretaceous period, from 68 to 66 million years ago, in what is now North America.

Name: Tristesse
Summary: Remnants of the people that were defeated by the King... Their grief and sadness is all that remains. They cannot tell friend from foe anymore. Defeating them is all we can do... Every sadness has a different resistance and weakness. Maybe there's a way to figure it out from their appearance...

Name: Trixie Lulamoon
Summary: Trixie Lulamoon is a recurring character in My Little Pony: Friendship is Magic, being a staple of the series since Season 1.

Name: Troglodyte
Summary: The Troglodyte is a bit shorter then an average human but is far more deadlier due to their sharp claws, teeth and expertise with using spears in combat. Troglodytes also release a foul stench when ever they're angry, said smell is so horrid most creatures get repulsed by it, but the Troglodyte uses it both as an offensive tool and a communication device, as their sense of smell is rather potent.

Name: Troll (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: Trolls are giants outside of the Ordining, largely due to their predatorial and uncivilized ways of life. In fact, they are not believed to be direct relatives of giants at all, and are only classified as such due to their large stature and ability to mate with true giants. They could be found almost anywhere, with multitudes of sub-species forming as a result of their extremely varied environment choices. Some could be found in the boiling hot jungle, while others function perfectly fine in the bone-chilling arctic wastelands, while yet others could survive in active volcanoes.

Name: Tu-95
Summary: The Tupolev Tu-95 is a 4-engine turboprop strategic bomber and missile platform developed by Tupolev, with it being an upscaled version of the previous Tu-4, which is a reverse engineering of the B-29. The bomber is the first intercontinental bomber developed by the USSR, with it's closest US Counterpart being the B-52 Stratofortress. Much like the B-52, it has gone through various upgrades and maintenance, remaining in service to this day.

Name: Type 97 Chi-Ha
Summary: The Type 97 Chi-Ha Medium Tank (九七式中戦車 チハ Kyūnana-shiki chū-sensha Chi-ha) was a medium tank used by the Imperial Japanese Army during the Second Sino-Japanese War, the Battles of Khalkhin Gol against the Soviet Union, and the Second World War. It was the most widely produced Japanese medium tank of World War II.

Name: Tyrannosaurus rex (Real World)
Summary: Tyrannosaurus rex, commonly abbreviated as T. rex, is a species of theropod dinosaur that lived throughout what is now western North America from 68 to 66 million years ago.

Name: Ultron Sentries (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: The Ultron Sentries are mass produced robots that function as extensions of Ultron's will and can sometimes house his AI if his main body is destroyed.

Name: Ulysses Klaue (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Ulysses Klaue was a black-market arms dealer and smuggler as well as a gangster who had operated out of South Africa. He was a former acquaintance of Tony Stark from his weapons-dealing days, and was an associate of N'Jobu when he attempted to expose Wakanda to the rest of the world. In 2015, during an encounter with Ultron, Klaue sold his entire stockpile of the Vibranium to the A.I. before losing his arm in an argument with Ultron, and fled when the Avengers arrived.

Name: Utahraptor
Summary: Utahraptor is a theropod dinosaur from the Cretaceous Period. It is currently the largest Dromaeosaur ever discovered at 2-2.5 meters tall, 7 meters long and weighing at least 500 kg.

Name: V-mon (Daisuke Motomiya)
Summary: Daisuke "Davis" Motomiya and his partner Veemon are two of the protagonists of Digimon Adventure 02. The de facto leader of the DigiDestined, their hot-blooded and reckless natures mean they have a lot of room for improvement, but they nevertheless step up to the plate and take the reins of their adventures with enthusiasm.

Name: Valerie (Pokémon)
Summary: Valerie is one of the many Gym Leaders of the Kalos region, and the only Fairy Type one. She also is a fashion designer from the Johto region.

Name: Varag
Summary: Standing at 7 feet tall, the Varag is a Goblinoid like Goblins or Hobgoblins. The average Varag knows the Goblin language but is barely able to talk in it, and outside combat they are not the brightest creatures. However pact leaders are capable fighters, with them leading entire brigades.

Name: Verdan
Summary: Created by the That-Which-Endures, Verdans are mutated Goblins and Hobgoblins that were recently created in the Forgotten Realm. Unlike the creatures which they came from, the Verdan are peaceful, with them still learning many new things about their own race.

Name: Vigilante (Pre-Crisis)
Summary: Adrian Chase was a district attorney and later judge in New York City. After his wife and children were murdered by the mob, he became the vengeful Vigilante to punish those the justice system couldn't.

Name: Viola (Pokémon)
Summary: Viola is the current Leader of the Santalune Gym in the Kalos region, serving as the first Gym Leader that Calem/Serena has to fight. An avid photographer, she is almost never seen without a camera in her hand, and she simply adores Bug type Pokemon.

Name: Violet Fungus
Summary: Violet Fungi are specimens of toxic mushroom that grow in certain areas of Faerun, Greyhawk, and many other multiverses. They rely on symbiotic relationships with Shriekers to lure in and, for their part, poison prey. After killing such wanderers in all of their folly, the fungi will scavenge nutrients off of their corpses. Remarkably, this plant has developed the ability to move somewhat.

Name: Viper (Jordan Dixon)
Summary: Jordan Stryke was the brother of the notorious costumed criminal known as the Eel. When Stryke went into the advertising business, he legally changed his last name to Dixon so as to avoid association with his brother's criminal reputation. Dixon spent years planning advertising campaigns for children's toys and other products, but believed that through his marketing abilities he was making fortunes for his clients, while he himself labored in relative obscurity for far less financial gain. Moreover, Dixon believed that through his advertising projects he was perpetrating lies on behalf of his clients and subverting the nation's moral values. Dixon even took a perverse pleasure in such activities. He prided himself on selling products he regarded as worthless so successfully to the public, and he regarded the American public with contempt, believing them willing to believe any lie spread through the mass media, if it was crafted convincingly enough.

Name: Wahoo
Summary: The wahoo (Acanthocybium solandri) is a species of scombrid fish endemic to subtropical and tropical waters worldwide. It is one of the fastest fish in the world, capable of reaching speeds up to 77 kilometers per hour. It is a popular sport fish, and prized for its speed and high-quality meat.

Name: Wakanda (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Wakanda is a country in eastern Africa that has become far more technologically and scientifically advanced than any other nation on Earth, due to its supply of the highly valuable, rare and versatile metal Vibranium, brought to the country by a meteor impact thousands of years in the past. However, to avoid being conquered and pillaged of its resources by foreign invaders, the kingdom keeps itself very reclusive and isolated from the rest of the world.

Name: Wally (Pokémon)
Key: '''By Himself''' | '''Pokémon Team (Mauville City)''' | '''Pokémon Team (Victory Road)''' | '''Pokémon Team (Third and Fourth Battle)'''
Summary: Wally is one of the player's rivals in Pokémon Ruby and Sapphire as well as their remakes, Pokémon Omega Ruby and Alpha Sapphire. He is a meek and sickly young boy who aspires to become a great Pokemon Trainer, having covered his entire room and filled multiple notebooks with information on strategy and raising Pokemon. Over the course of his journey, he gains confidence and a stronger constitution, eventually amassing a powerful Pokémon team and defeating every Gym Leader in the Hoenn region before the player does. He then goes on to battle the player right before they go on to challenge the Pokemon League. Although he lost, he refused to let go of his dream, becoming even stronger and regularly challenging the player at the Battle Resort.

Name: Walrus (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: Found in arctic climates such as Icewind Dale, the Walrus is a bulky and massive mammal. They are often hunted for their meat and tusks.

Name: WarGreymon
Summary: An ultimate form of Greymon-species Digimon, it is a subspecies of War Greymon armed with electric-powered weapons.

Name: Water Buffalo
Summary: The Water Buffalo (Bubalus bubalis) are the second largest bovidae. Wild water buffalo live in wildlife preserves in southeast asia, while their domestic counterparts are very common.[1]

Name: Water Weird
Summary: Made from water, the Water Weird is one of the possible Elemental Weirds. In their younger form they appear like a water serpent, shooting cold water at enemies and using their physiology to drown people who come close to them. Their adult self meanwhile is a powerful caster, being able to use various healing and water spells alongside regular Sorcerer spells.

Name: Wereboar
Summary: Wereboars are among the most common forms of lycanthropes in the lands of Faerun and beyond and, much like other lycanthropes, are afflicted with a curse that causes them to transform into animals and go on rampages of uncontrollable rage.

Name: Wererat
Summary: Wererats are among the most common and most despicable of all lycanthropes, and can generally be found in gangs inhabiting sewer systems and similar constructs. They are noted for their nervous and suspicious behaviors and, much like all other lycanthropes, they tend to take on traits of their animal even in human form- short, matted hair and quickly darting eyes are often signs of a wererat.

Name: Weretiger
Summary: Regal and graceful, Weretigers are, even in human form, beings of pedigree and class. Afflicted with the lycanthropy curse, weretigers make ideal hunters thanks to their sleek dexterity in all environments. They tend to live alone on the outskirts of humanity, only interacting with humanity to trade when needed. Weretigers are commonly found in warm jungles, where their true animal counterparts reside with them.

Name: Werewolf (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: Werewolves are canine lycanthropes and are generally regarded as beings of incredible evil (though this is not always the case). In their human forms, werewolves merely seem agitated, easily angered by the slightest inconvenience. Both good and evil werewolves alike flee from civilized society- those that fear the curse fear too for their fellow man, and wish to refrain from killing them. Those that embrace the curse seek to save their own hides, and do not wish to be held responsible for their murderous acts.

Name: Werner Werman (Cuphead Show)
Summary: https://vsbattles.fandom.com/wiki/File:WernerWermanIntro.ogg

Name: West Indian Manatee
Summary: The West Indian manatee (Trichechus manatus), also known as the sea cow, is a large species of marine mammal native to the Caribbean and the east coast of the United States. It is herbivorous, and primarily grazes on seagrass.

Name: Whale Shark
Summary: The whale shark (Rhincodon typus) is the largest extant fish in the world. Unlike most other sharks, the whale shark is a filter feeder, and primarily feeds on zooplankton and krill. Despite their size, whale sharks are docile, and pose no threat to humans.

Name: White Rabbit (Marvel Comics)
Summary: White Rabbit: We don't need them! We're the Terrible Two! We're evil personified! The vilest villains on the face of the-- Walrus: They hung up on you, didn't they? White Rabbit: Uh-huh. After they were done laughing.

Name: White Rhinoceros
Summary: The White Rhinoceros is one of the largest land animals on Earth. They are well known due their trademark horn and their build. They are herbivores.

Name: Wiggan Nettlebee
Summary: Wiggan Nettlebee is a halfling clan leader, and is in theory a modest rancher. However, behind closed doors he dedicates himself to studying darker powers to advance himself, he joined the Cult of the Black Earth.

Name: Wights
Summary: A Wight is a reanimated corpse, either human or animal, raised from death by the Night King or the White Walkers with the use of necromancy. Wights were often referred to collectively as the Army of the Dead. Anyone who falls against the White Walkers must be burned, or else the dead will rise again as their slaves. Fear of their own dead becoming wights leads the free folk to burn them.

Name: Wild Boar
Summary: The wild boar (Sus scrofa), also known as the wild swine, Eurasian wild pig, or simply wild pig, is native to much of Eurasia, North Africa, and the Greater Sunda Islands. Human intervention has spread its distribution further, making the species one of the widest-ranging mammals in the world. It has become an invasive species in part of its introduced range.

Name: Winter Wolf
Summary: White and larger then their regular counterpart the Winter Wolf is a fearsome predator whose well adepted to hunting in snowy areas.

Name: Wolf of the Overworld
Summary: Inhabiting cold taigas, the Wolf of the Overworld roams the lands as a pact, hunting animals such as sheep and rabbits. They are not hostile to humans, however if one harms a member of a pact they will all attack the human.

Name: Wolverine-Pool (Deadpool: Samurai)
Summary: Wolverine-Pool is a variant of Deadpool who appeared in Cable & Deadpool #46 and Deadpool Kills Deadpool #3. He was sent to kill Deadpool in Deadpool Samurai second season.

Name: Wood Elf
Summary: One of the major sub races of elves, the Wood Elves who are also known as Sylvan Elves live deep in the forests. They are so attuned with nature that they are able to make use of any small cover to hide away, and they are naturally faster on their feet.

Name: Woolly Mammoth
Summary: The Woolly mammoths were a species of mammoth that lived during the Pleistocene. They were members of the Elephantidae family, making them related to the modern day Elephant.

Name: Woolly Rhinoceras (Real World)
Summary: The Woolly Rhinoceros is a species within the extinct genus Coelodonta. It lived during the mid to late Pleistocene epoch in northern Eurasia. It was likely a grazer that fed on herbaceous plants, with its horn functioning to sweep snow off the ground for it to feed.[1] Along with creatures such as the Woolly Mammoth and Smilodon, it is among the more iconic megafauna of the Last Ice Age.

Name: Worg (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: A variant of the Dire Wolf, the Worg is an evil wolf.

Name: Worghest
Summary: Descendants of Barghest and Goblins, the Worghest are a race of humanoid outsiders that often live amongst goblin or orc tribes, acting as respected warriors there but never seeking a leadership position.

Name: Wormmon (Ken Ichijouji)
Summary: Ken Ichijouji and Wormmon are main characters from Digimon Adventure 02. Ken as the Digimon Kaiser was the first major enemy of the Chosen Children. Being cruel, cold and sadistic person who enjoyed nothing more than causing pain to others and seeing them suffer. This persona was fueled by a corrupting Dark Seed that was planted in the back of his neck from defeating of Millenniummon.

Name: Xefros Tritoh
Summary: Xefros Tritoh is one of the main protagonists of the Homestuck video game Hiveswap. He is a rustblooded troll from the planet Alternia who is part of a revolution to overthrow the tyrannical caste-based government. He meets main protagonist Joey Claire after she gets swapped with Xefros' best friend Dammek and with her help manages to escape the destruction of his home town.

Name: Xiphactinus
Summary: Xiphactinus was an extinct genus of predatory fish dating back to the late Cretaceous period. Growing up to six meters in length, they were one of the most formidable predators in the Western Interior Sea.

Name: Yalah Gralhund
Summary: A noblewoman in Waterdeep, Yalah Gralhund is an ambitious lady who will use her resources alongside blackmail, threats and whatever is needed to achieve her goals.

Name: Yangchuanosaurus
Summary: Yangchuanosaurus is a genus of theropod dinosaur that lived in what is now China, during the middle to late Jurassic period, about 161.2 to 157.3 million years ago. Yangchuanosaurus was a large, powerful meat-eater, being around 8-11 meters long and weighing as much as 3.4 metric tons.

Name: Yellow (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: A humble knowledge cleric, Yellow resides at the Monastery of Inspiration in the city of Harmony. They are one of seven Nerds tasked with solving the city's power outage issues.

Name: Yellowfin Tuna
Summary: The yellowfin tuna (Thunnus albacares) is a species of tuna found in subtropical and tropical waters worldwide. They are one of the few known warm-blooded fish, which in turn allows them to be exceptionally strong swimmers.

Name: Yeti (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: The Yeti is a distant relative of both primates and bears that lives in the high mountain peaks. Unlike their cousins the Yeti possesses the ability to absorb the heat of their area and have a gaze that can induce terror into those that are unprepared for it, but the former ability comes with a weakness to any great source of it as they'd absorb it too which would raise their internal body tempature to dangerous levels.

Name: Yondu Udonta (Ravager)
Summary: Yondu Udonta is a Centaurian born in a tribe on the primitive planet of Centauri-IV. At a very young age, Yondu presenced the coming of an alien species to his tribe, the Syneca. The Syneca wished to share their technology in exchange for some Yaka ore. Yondu, amazed by the Syneca's crystal spaceships, took an opportunity to steal one so he and his friend Babatuku could go for a short flight. However, Yondu lost control of the ship, crashing into the elders' temple of his tribe, killing Chondu, an important elder of the tribe. Yondu tried to keep the incident a secret, but, as the Syneca demanded for justice, Babatuku revealed Yondu's role in Chondu's death.

Name: Youngster Joey
Summary: Youngster Joey is considered the first Pokémon trainer that Ethan ever faces in the Johto Pokémon games. He is first seen battling a trainer named Mikey on Route 30, later seemingly having been defeated after Ethan delivers the Mystery Egg.

Name: Yutyrannus
Summary: Yutyrannus is a genus of large theropod dinosaur, represented by the species Yutyrannus huali. It is famous for being the largest dinosaur discovered with clear evidence of having feathers; these are thought to have aided in regulating body heat (especially useful in a land with an average annual temperature of 10 degrees Celsius) or for display, depending on how much of the body was covered.[1] It lived around 125 million years ago during the early Cretaceous, in what is now northeastern China, inhabiting the temperate rainforest habitat that existed in this creature's place and time. It was a relative of the more iconic Tyrannosaurus rex, but was a more primitive representative of the tyrannosauroids.

Name: Zark
Summary: Zark is a dwarven delinquent living in the city of Loudwater, who in recent years has turned to a life of crime (including slavery and smuggling) to support his lazy lifestyle. He has been in cahoots with the Zelbross Bandits since they spared his life in return for his services.

Name: Zebra (Real World)
Summary: Zebras are African equines that are distinguished by they black-and-white stripes. There are three known species of zebras, with the most common being the Burchell's zebra (also known as the plains zebra). Due to their wild temperament, it is ill-advised to saddle up or attempt to ride a zebra.

Name: Zinnia (Pokémon)
Summary: Zinnia (Japanese: ヒガナ Higana) is a mysterious Draconid woman and a Pokémon Trainer from Hoenn introduced in Omega Ruby and Alpha Sapphire. She is seen as an important character that holds the key to the Delta Episode and aims to accomplish her objectives.

Name: Zorbo
Summary: From a distance appearing like a koala, if an adventurer mistakes the Zorbo for one and approaches it to pat it then they'll get a nasty surprise.

Name: Zulkir
Summary: A Dire Badger, Zulkir is a specimen who was granted intelligence far beyond animals by an Awakening spell.

Name: .950 JDJ Rifle
Summary: The .950 JDJ Rifle is known as being "the largest sporting rifle made." It was developed by J.D. Jones, president of SSK Industries. It normally would be classified as a "destructive device" due to the rifle's groove diameter of .950 inches. However SSK was given a "Sporting Use Exception" in order to deregulate the rifle. Due to its heavy weight and massive recoil, it can only be shot from a bench rest or heavy bipod, which even then runs risk of injury. As such, the gun is more of a novelty than any combat or sporting weapon.

Name: Aardvark
Summary: The aardvark (Orycteropus afer) is a nocturnal mammal native to sub-Saharan Africa. It uses its powerful claws to dig burrows, and primarily feeds on termites and other insects. Despite its appearance, it is most closely related to the elephant.

Name: Aaron Covenant
Summary: Aaron Covenant is the second child of the Covenant family and the twin brother of Bethany Covenant. He was tortured and killed by his twin sister but resurrected as a revenant form and as a ghost. He is one of the bosses in Clive Barker's Undying.

Name: Accuracy International Arctic Warfare
Summary: The Accuracy International Arctic Warfare rifle is a bolt-action sniper rifle designed and manufactured by the British company Accuracy International. It has proved popular as a civilian, police, and military rifle since its introduction in the 1980s. The rifles have some features that improve performance in very cold conditions (which gave the rifle its name), without impairing operation in less extreme conditions. Arctic Warfare rifles are generally fitted with a Schmidt & Bender PM II telescopic sight with fixed or variable magnification. Variable telescopic sights can be used if the operator wants more flexibility to shoot at varying ranges, or when a wide field of view is required. Accuracy International actively promotes fitting the German-made Schmidt & Bender MILITARY MK II product line as sighting components on their rifles, which is rare for a rifle manufacturer. The German and Russian forces preferred a telescopic sight made by Zeiss over Accuracy International's recommendation.

Name: African Buffalo
Summary: nan

Name: African Wild Dog (Real World)
Summary: The African wild dog (Lycaon pictus), also called the painted wolf or Cape hunting dog, is a canine native to sub-Saharan Africa. It is the largest indigenous canine in Africa, and the only extant member of the genus Lycaon, which is distinguished from Canis by dentition highly specialised for a hypercarnivorous diet, and a lack of dewclaws.

Name: Air Gun
Summary: Air guns, also known as air rifles, are guns that make use of diabolo-shaped pellets or spherical pellets called "BBs." They represent the oldest pneumatic technology, dating back to 1580. Air guns are used for hunting, pest control, recreational shooting (also known as plinking), and competitive sports such as the Olympics.

Name: AK-12
Summary: The AK-12 is a Russian assault rifle chambered in 5.45×39mm respectively. It is designed and manufactured by Kalashnikov Concern (formerly Izhmash). It is one of the modern derivatives of the Russian AK-Pattern series of assault rifles.

Name: AK-15
Summary: The AK-15 is a Russian assault rifles chambered in 7.62×39mm respectively. It is designed and manufactured by Kalashnikov Concern (formerly Izhmash). It is one of the modern derivatives of the Russian AK-Pattern series of assault rifles.

Name: AK-308
Summary: The AK-308 is a battle rifle under development in 2018 upon request of non-Russian potential clients. It is based on the AK-103 and AK-12, chambered for 7.62×51mm NATO/.308 Winchester. The basic Kalashnikov assault rifle design intended for intermediate cartridges has been stretched and strengthened to handle the extra bolt thrust produced by full-power ammunition. It features a 415 mm (16.3 in) long barrel, has a weight of 4.1 to 4.3 kg (9.04 to 9.48 lb) with an empty box magazine and has a 20 or 30-round magazine capacity. In addition, the AK-308 uses a diopter sight line. It has the ability to attach accessories also used by the AK-12. The overall length of the rifle measures between 880 to 945 mm (34.6 to 37.2 in).

Name: AK-47
Summary: The AK-47, officially known as the Avtomat Kalashnikova (Russian: Автома́т Кала́шникова, tr. Avtomát Kaláshnikova, lit. Kalashnikov's Automatic Rifle; also known as the Kalashnikov and AK), is a gas-operated, 7.62×39mm assault rifle, developed in the Soviet Union by Mikhail Kalashnikov. It is the originating firearm of the Kalashnikov rifle (or "AK") family.

Name: AK-74
Summary: The AK-74 (Russian: Автомат Калашникова образца 1974 года or "Kalashnikov automatic rifle model 1974") is an assault rifle developed in the early 1970s by Russian designer Mikhail Kalashnikov as the replacement for the earlier AKM (itself a refined version of the AK-47). It uses a smaller 5.45×39mm cartridge, replacing the 7.62×39mm chambering of earlier Kalashnikov-pattern weapons.

Name: Akagi (5 Ronin)
Summary: Ronin Akagi returns home from war to find his house burnt to ashes, and his wife and seven year old son dead at the hands of the Daimyo. Vowing revenge, he endlessly stalks the soldiers of Daimyo to slaughter them mercilessly, considering himself already dead.

Name: AKM
Summary: The AKM (Russian: модернизи́рованный Автома́т Кала́шникова, tr. modernizírovanny Avtomát Kaláshnikova, lit. Modernized Kalashnikov Automatic Rifle) is a 7.62mm assault rifle designed by Mikhail Kalashnikov. It is a common modernized variant of the AK-47 rifle developed in the 1940s.

Name: Alabai
Summary: The Central Asian Shepherd Dog, also known as alabai is a livestock guardian dog breed. Traditionally, the breed was used for guarding sheep and goat herds, as well as to protect and for guard duty. This breed presents a robust dog of greater than average size with great strength and power.

Name: Ambulocetus
Summary: Ambulocetus is a genus of semi-aquatic cetacean, the group that would later include fully aquatic whales. Its name comes from the Latin words ambulare, or "walking", and cetus, or "whale." It lived during the Early Eocene from around 48–47 million years ago, on the Indian Subcontinent, inhabiting the mangrove swamps that covered the then tropical environment there,[1] and favored brackish water at river mouths.[2]

Name: Amelia Voght (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Amelia Voght discovered her powers of transubtantiating matter into vapour at a young age and was ostracized by her parents, like many other mutants. Choosing to embark on a journey far from the judgmental eyes of her past, she pursued a career in nursing and eventually found herself in India. Here, she met Charles Xavier, a fellow American who had lost the use of his legs. Amelia cared for Charles after his injury, and her positive and friendly attitude helped Xavier get over his depression. The two quickly fell in love, and shared an apartment in Mumbai. Eventually discovering that Xavier was a mutant himself, this link strengthened their relationship even more, but over time they both developed different stances on human-mutant interaction. Xavier wanted open co-existence with humans, while Amelia thought it was best for mutants to hide themselves. When Xavier brought Scott Summers to his mansion for training, Amelia left him, telling him that his plans for the X-Men would only lead to a genetic arms race and ultimately doom mutantkind.

Name: American Alligator
Summary: The American Alligator is a large crocodillian reptile native to the Southeastern regions of the United States. They are one of the two extant species of alligator.

Name: American Black Bear
Summary: The American black bear (Ursus americanus) is a medium-sized bear endemic to North America.[1][2][3] It is the continent's smallest and most widely distributed bear species.[2] American black bears are omnivores,[1][2] with their diets varying greatly depending on season and location.[1][2] They typically live in largely forested areas,[1][2] but will leave forests in search of food[2] and are sometimes attracted to human communities due to the immediate availability of food.[1][2] Despite the name, some subspecies can be brown or even blond in coloration.[4][3][5][note 1]

Name: American Pit Bull
Summary: This page contains or depicts disturbing and/or graphic content that some may find upsetting, and that is only intended for mature audiences. Please proceed with caution.

Name: Amphicyon
Summary: Amphicyon was a prehistoric genus of bear-sized carnivorans closely related to canids and ursids.

Name: AMT AutoMag II
Summary: The AutoMag II looks extremely different from the original AutoMag, and even uses a different action. The weapon has a stainless steel cutout over the slide, and 18 holes are drilled 90 degrees to the chamber to prevent extraction problems with the .22 WMR bullet in the weapon.

Name: Anaconda
Summary: Anaconda or water boas are a group of large snakes of the genus Eunectes. They are found in tropical South America. Four species are currently recognized. All anacondas live in South America east of the Andes. Green anacondas are found in the Brazilian Amazon basin, the Orinoco basin, Colombia, Venezuela, Ecuador, Peru, Bolivia, Trinidad and the Guianas, according to the Jacksonville Zoo, with specimens being able to reach The maximum verified length of an anaconda is 30 feet (9 m), but on average they grow to around 15 feet (4.5 m) for females, and around 9 feet (2.7 m) for males.

Name: Aniliade
Summary: Aniliade is a Youtuber and the main antagonist in several of Eight Blackey's Indie Horror Games, such as: Aniliade’s Jumpscare Castle and Aniliade's Dungeon of Misfortune, as well as the protagonist of the webcomic series: The Misadventures of Aniliade and Banshee. She also appears as a Cameo in various other games from the same Game Developer. Aniliade is also known as the best friend of Banshee.

Name: Anteosaurus
Summary: Anteosaurus is a genus of large carnivorous dinocephalian synapsid, represented by the single species, Anteosaurus magnificus. It lived in the lush and marshy environment that existed in what is present-day South Africa around 265–260 million years ago, during the Capitanian stage of the middle Permian, and likely hunted other large synapsids in its time. It is among the largest non-mammalian carnivorous synapsids, reaching up to 6 meters long and around 600 kg.

Name: Arapaima
Summary: Arapaimas are freshwater fish residing in the Amazon River and one of the largest species of freshwater fish.[1] Arapaima normally reach lengths of up to 2 meters, although in rare cases they can exceed 2.5 meters and over 100 kg.[2][1]

Name: ArmaLite AR-15
Summary: The ArmaLite AR-15 is a select-fire, air-cooled, gas-operated, magazine-fed assault rifle manufactured in the United States between 1959 and 1964, and adopted by the United States Armed Forces as the M16 rifle. Designed by American gun manufacturer ArmaLite in 1956, it was based on its AR-10 rifle. The ArmaLite AR-15 was designed to be a lightweight assault rifle and to fire a new high-velocity, lightweight, small-caliber cartridge to allow infantrymen to carry more ammunition.

Name: Arquebus
Summary: The Arquebus is the first handheld firearm equipped with a mechanical ignition system, having been invented in 1411 after the hand cannon was invented. The arquebus, unlike bows and hand cannons, were easier to wield and were easy weapons to train soldiers with.

Name: Atchisson Assault Shotgun
Summary: The Auto Assault-12 (AA-12), originally designed and known as the Atchisson Assault Shotgun, is a shotgun developed in 1972 by Maxwell Atchisson. The most prominent feature is reduced recoil. The current 2005 version has been developed over 18 years since the patent was sold to Military Police Systems, Inc. The original design was the basis of several later weapons, including the original USAS-12 combat shotgun. It is available for commercial purchase only in full automatic mode, however, it fires at a rate of 300 rounds per minute, allowing it to fire one round at a time with brief trigger pulls. It is compatible with either an 8-shell box magazine, or a 20- or 32-shell drum magazine.

Name: Atlantic Goliath Grouper
Summary: The Atlantic Goliath Grouper (Epinephelus itajara), also known as the itjara or the jewfish, is the largest grouper species in the Atlantic Ocean, weighing up to 800 pounds. It is found primarily in shallow tropical waters among coral and artificial reefs. Its range includes the Gulf of Mexico and Florida Keys in the United States, the Bahamas, most of the Caribbean, and most of the Brazilian coast. On some occasions, goliath grouper have been caught off the coast of New England in Massachusetts and Maine. In the eastern Atlantic Ocean, goliath grouper are found off the coast of Africa from the Congo to Senegal.[1]

Name: Auto Mag Pistol
Summary: The .44 AutoMag pistol (AMP) is a large caliber semi-automatic pistol. It was designed between 1966 and 1971 by the AutoMag Corporation to make a semi-automatic pistol chambered in .44 AMP.

Name: Avengers (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Iron Man: How were you guys planning on beating that? Captain America: Together. Iron Man: We'll lose. Captain America: Then we'll do that together, too.

Name: Bacteria (Kane Pixels)
Summary: Bacteria, are a species of entity that are recurring characters in the analog horror series The Backrooms. Bacteria resemble tall, thin, black humanoids that appear to be made of wires. Bacteria first was shown in The Backrooms: Found Footage, the first episode of the series, in which one chases and presumably kills Kane Pints. It exhibits similar behavior in the episodes Found Footage #2 and Pitfalls and is seen climbing on the ceiling in The Backrooms- Motion Detected. In Autopsy Report, more is learned about the nature of Bacteria, with it being implied to be a mutated strain of the hay bacillus disease. Despite all this, much about Bacteria is still left to be seen.

Name: Bald Eagle
Summary: This page contains or depicts disturbing and/or graphic content that some may find upsetting, and that is only intended for mature audiences. Please proceed with caution.

Name: Baseball Bat
Summary: A Baseball Bat is a wooden/metal club used in baseball. In baseball, they are used to hit the ball, sending it flying after it is thrown at the batter by the pitcher. But due its structure, it can be used as clubbing weapon and due to its ease of access and use, it is common in street fights or in home defense in a few countries.

Name: Bayonet
Summary: The Bayonet was made in the 17th century in Bayonne, France. It was highly popular in Britain, and The Bayonet became a popular tool in combat. After WW1, the weapon started to Wane due to the popularity of rapid-fire weapons. To this day, the Bayonet is still used in combat in the Marines.

Name: Benelli M4
Summary: The Benelli M4 is a semi-automatic combat shotgun produced by Italian firearm manufacturer Benelli Armi SpA, and the last of the "Benelli Super 90" series of semi-automatic shotguns. The M4 uses a proprietary action design called the "auto-regulating gas-operated" (ARGO) system, which was created specifically for the weapon. It was designed in 1998, and was adopted by the armed forces of Italy, the United States, United Kingdom, among others, and has been used in a variety of conflicts, leading up to the present day.

Name: Beretta ARX160
Summary: The Beretta ARX160 is an Italian modular rifle manufactured by Beretta. Developed for the Italian Armed Forces as part of the Soldato Futuro (English: "Future Soldier") program, the ARX160 was launched in 2008 as a commercial weapon system independent from the Soldato Futuro ensemble, complete with a companion single-shot 40×46mm NATO low-velocity grenade launcher, called the GLX160, which can be mounted underneath the rifle or used with an ad hoc stock system as a stand-alone weapon.

Name: Beretta M9
Summary: The Beretta M9, officially the Pistol, Semiautomatic, 9mm, M9, is the designation for the Beretta 92FS semi-automatic pistol by the United States Armed Forces. The M9 was adopted by the United States' military as their service pistol in 1985. The 92FS itself has been manufactured by Beretta of Italy since its origin in 1975, and its production continues on even today with a variety of caliber options.

Name: Black Adam (Post-Crisis)
Summary: Once the son to an ancient pharaoh, Teth-Adam miraculously gained powers from an ageing wizard named Shazam. By saying his name, the mere prince became the champion of Shazam, gaining himself the powers of six Egyptian gods: Shu, Heru, Amon, Zehuti, Aton and Mehen. However, as time went on, Adam started to crave for more power and authority, and forcefully overthrew the government to become the ruler of Kahndaq. Believing Adam to be corrupted, the old wizard casted a spell which trapped Adam's memories, soul and powers in a scarab, however, this in turn aged Adam's physical body into dust. Millennials later, one of Adam's descendants and murderer of Billy Batson's parents: Theo Adam would stumble upon this scarab and calling out Shazam, Theo would reborn Teth into his own body to become Black Adam.

Name: Black Fox (Marvel Comics)
Summary: A master thief past his prime, Black Fox had taught best of the best in his heydays, but only looks now to save up for his retirement to the French Riviera.

Name: Black Hand
Summary: William Hand was often described as the black sheep of his family. Obsessed with death and clichés from a young age, Hand was deemed a disgrace by his relatives, no doubt fueling his spiral into psychopathy. Taking up the mantle of Black Hand, he came in possession of the Power Rod, a mysterious artifact that allowed him to steal the powers of others. Using this device, he dueled against Green Lantern and The Flash numerous times. After Hal Jordan became one with The Spectre, he destroyed Black Hand's hand, causing the already fragile man to break entirely, becoming a truly sadistic and cruel-hearted individual who became the first Black Lantern.

Name: Blacktip Reef Shark
Summary: The blacktip reef shark (Carcharhinus melanopterus) is a small species of requiem shark native to coral reefs in the Pacific and Indian oceans. It can be distinguished from other sharks by the prominent black tips on its fins.

Name: Blaser R93 Tactical
Summary: The Blaser R93 Tactical is a German bolt action sniper rifle, based on the Blaser R93 design. It has as variants the Blaser LRS 2 and Tactical 2.
