It is used by German and Dutch police forces as well as the Australian military and special police units. The rifles were manufactured by the German firearms manufacturer Blaser.

Name: Bobby Singer
Summary: Robert Steven "Bobby" Singer (1950-2012) was a hunter, an old friend of John Winchester, and over time evolved into a father-figure for John's sons Sam and Dean. He was also one of the longest lasting recurring characters, appearing in every season so far.

Name: Boomerang (Real World)
Summary: A boomerang is a traditional curved throwing tool that originated with Indigenous Australians, though similar versions have been found in other parts of the world. It is most commonly made of wood, but can also be crafted from bone, stone, or modern materials like plastic. The most famous type is the returning boomerang, which is carefully shaped and balanced so that when thrown with the correct spin, it travels in a curved path and comes back to the thrower. However, not all boomerangs were designed to return—many were larger, heavier hunting boomerangs used to strike animals, and these would fly straight rather than circle back.

Name: Bottlenose Dolphin
Summary: Dolphins are several families of cetaceans in the parvorder Odontoceti. Most famous of these dolphins is the Bottlenose Dolphin. Bottlenose dolphins have gained popularity for their appearances in aquarium shows, but among scientists, they are popular for their intelligence. Studies on dolphin intelligence, ranging from cognition to the use of artificial language.

Name: Bow (Real World)
Summary: Bows are among the earliest weapons known to man. A bow is a simplistic weapon in design; simply put, a lightweight arrow is shot with the pull of a string. While bows were made obsolete in favor of guns in war, bows are still used in hunting and sporting events (particularly the Olympic sport of archery). More recently, compound bows were developed, boasting stronger draw weights than modern recurve bows. Multiple arrows can be fired in a single shot, although generally multiple arrows being fired at once aren't as effective as firing a single shot.

Name: Bradley Fighting Vehicle
Summary: The Bradley Fighting Vehicle (BFV) is a fighting vehicle platform of the United States manufactured by BAE Systems Land & Armaments, formerly United Defense. It was named after U.S. General Omar Bradley.

Name: Brainiac (Pre-Crisis)
Summary: Brainiac was a robot from the distant future who traveled the universe, shrinking cities for his own self-satisfaction. He was among Superman's greatest and most fearsome foes. Though he lacked in physical strength, he more than made up for it with his unmatched mind, arsenal of futuristic weapons and shockingly good agility. After what could have been his final outing involving a weapon known as the Planet-Eater, Brainiac's body was transformed into the New Brainiac, a bio-robot who absorbed all the knowedge in the universe, and embarked on a new quest, a quest that would never be fufilled, to overthrow God himself.

Name: Brandon Rogers (Character)
Summary: Brandon Rogers is the creator of several shows including Magical Funhouse, Theater Class, and Stuff & Sam! He is the creator and "God" of the world and has been manipulating the plot of the shows TV30 run which also affected reality. The source of his power lies within his book, known as The Creator's Book of Doings.

Name: Brass Knuckles
Summary: Brass Knuckles are pieces of metal shaped to fit around the knuckles. They concentrate a person's punching force by directing the force of the punch into a smaller contact area.

Name: Brown Bess
Summary: "Brown Bess" is a nickname of uncertain origin for the British Army's muzzle-loading smoothbore flintlock Land Pattern Musket and its derivatives. This musket was used in the era of the expansion of the British Empire and acquired symbolic importance at least as significant as its physical importance. It was in use for over a century with many incremental changes in its design. These versions include the Long Land Pattern, the Short Land Pattern, the India Pattern, the New Land Pattern Musket and the Sea Service Musket.

Name: Brown Pelican
Summary: Brown Pelicans are one of the 8 members of the genus Pelecanus. The genus is known for its gluttony and willingness to eat nearly anything. Surprisingly, Brown Pelicans are more grounded in terms of their prey variety.

Name: Browning Hi-Power
Summary: The Browning Hi Power is a single-action, semi-automatic handgun available in the 9mm and .40 S&W calibers. It was based on a design by American firearms inventor John Browning, and completed by Dieudonné Saive at Fabrique Nationale (FN) of Herstal, Belgium. Browning died in 1926, several years before the design was finalized. The Hi-Power is one of the most widely used military pistols in history, having been used by the armed forces of over 50 countries. After 82 years of continuous production, the Hi-Power was discontinued in 2017 by Browning Arms, but it remained in production in some countries, under license.

Name: Bull Terrier
Summary: The bull terrier is a breed of terrier developed in the 19th century as a fighting dog. Over the years, the breed has shifted from this original purpose to become a companion and show dog. It is easily distinguished from other breeds by its long, egg-shaped head.

Name: Bulldog
Summary: The Bulldog, also known as the British Bulldog or English Bulldog, is a medium-sized dog breed. It is a muscular, hefty dog with a wrinkled face and a distinctive pushed-in nose. Bulldogs are popular pets; they were the fifth most popular purebreed in the US in 2017 according to the American Kennel Club.

Name: Burmese Python
Summary: The Burmese python is a python that is once considered a subspecies of the Indian python before it was split into its own species in 2009. While Burmese pythons are Vulnerable species in its native range in India, Burmese pythons have taken an invasive stronghold in Florida, with its presence mostly extirpating many native species within their range.

Name: California Sea Lion
Summary: The California sea lion (Zalophus californianus) is a species of eared seal native to the coastlines of western North America. It is the fastest species of seal in the world, and can swim up to 25 miles per hour.

Name: Camel
Summary: Camels are animals domesticated for millenia. They are primarily domesticated for desert travel and the transport of goods, but they have also been used for textiles, warfare, dairy products, and meat. There are two types of camels: dromedary and bactrian camels, both which are distinguished by the amount of humps on their back. 94% of the camels are dromedary camels while the remaining 6% are bactrian camels. A population of wild bactrian camels live in parts of northern China and southern Mongolia; however, these camels are critically endangered. An adult male dromedary camel typically weighs in at around 300 to 600 kg. An adult male bactrian camel, however, weighs in at around 300 to 1000 kg.

Name: Captain Cold (Pre-Crisis)
Summary: Once just a run-of-the-mill thief, Len Snart managed to get his hands on the 'Cold Gun', a piece of strange, futuristic technology capable of freezing seemingly anything it fired at, from people to buildings, from energy constructs to New Gods. With weapon in tole, Snart donned the identity of Captain Cold and quickly became one of Flash's most persistent and deadly foes.

Name: Capybara
Summary: The capybara (Hydrochoerus hydrochaeris) is a giant rodent native from South America. Capybaras are the largest living rodent and a member of the genus Hydrochoerus. They are close relatives include guinea pigs and rock cavies. Capybaras inhabits savannas and dense forests and lives near bodies of water. The capybaras are hunted for its meat and hide and also for grease from its thick fatty skin.

Name: Caracal
Summary: The caracal (Caracal caracal) is a medium-sized wild cat native to Africa, the Middle East, Central Asia, and arid areas of Pakistan and northwestern India. It is characterised by a robust build, long legs, a short face, long tufted ears, and long canine teeth.

Name: Carcinosoma
Summary: Carcinosoma is a one of the eurypterids, an extinct group of aquatic arthropods. Fossils of Carcinosoma are restricted to deposits of late Silurian (Late Llandovery to Early Pridoli) age. Classified as part of the family Carcinosomatidae, which the genus lends its name to, Carcinosoma contains seven species from North America and Great Britain. Carcinosomatid eurypterids had unusual proportions and features compared to other eurypterids, with a broad abdomen, thin and long tail and spined and forward-facing walking appendages. They were not as streamlined as other groups but had considerably more robust and well developed walking appendages. In Carcinosoma, these spined walking appendages are thought to have been used to create a trap to capture prey in. The telson (final segment of the body) of Carcinosoma appears to have possessed distinct segmentation, Carcinosoma is the only known eurypterid to possess this feature.

Name: Cassowary
Summary: Cassowaries are known as the third tallest bird (behind the emu and ostrich) and the second heaviest bird (behind the ostrich). Cassowaries, however, are #1 in the aggression department, having been known to attack humans, occasionally fatally. If you see a cassowary, do not crouch or turn your back against it; instead, keep a good eye on the cassowary and move away. Female cassowaries average at a weight of 58.5 kg while males average in at 29-34 kg. Of all birds, the cassowary is among the most closely related to their dinosaur ancestors.

Name: Cattle
Summary: The Cow is a domesticated ungulate and a popular species used as livestock. The docile and castrated male version of the species is called an Ox, and is usually trained as a draft animal. A Bull is the non-castrated version of an Ox, used for bullfighting. It is primarily herbivorous, but has been known to eat small animals.

Name: Cave Bear
Summary: The Cave Bear is an extinct species of bear that lived during the Ice Age from 250,000 years ago to 24,000 years ago. Unlike modern grizzly bears, which only went into caves during hibernation season, cave bears resided in caves throughout their life. According to genetic research, 0.9 to 2.4% of cave bear DNA is found in modern bears. Cave bears were comparable in size to polar bears with an average weight range of 350-600 kg for males and 225-250 kg for females. Some large specimens were recorded to weigh up to 1000 kg.

Name: Chainsaw (Real World)
Summary: This page contains or depicts disturbing and/or graphic content that some may find upsetting, and that is only intended for mature audiences. Please proceed with caution.

Name: Chameleon (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Born a Russian citizen named Dmitri Smerdyakov (Russian: Дмитрий Смердяков), he was the half-brother of Sergei Kravinoff.

Name: CheyTac Intervention
Summary: The CheyTac Intervention, also known as the CheyTac M200, is an American bolt-action sniper rifle manufactured by CheyTac USA, which can also be classified as an anti-materiel rifle. It is fed by a 7-round detachable single-stack magazine (an optional 5-round magazine is also available). It is specifically chambered in either .408 Chey Tac or .375 Chey Tac ammunition. CheyTac Inc. states that the system is capable of delivering sub-MOA accuracy at ranges of up to 2,500 yd (2,286 m). It is based on the EDM Arms Windrunner.

Name: Chimpanzee
Summary: The Chimpanzee is a primate and is the closest relative to humans (According to studies, their DNA is extremely similar to that of humans). They mainly eat fruit, vegetables and sometimes meat.

Name: Circus Baby (Games)
Key: '''Circus Baby''' | '''Scrap Baby''' | '''Circus Baby (UCN)''' | '''Scrap Baby (UCN)''' | '''Circus Baby (Special Delivery)'''
Summary: Circus Baby was the mascot of Circus Baby's Pizza World, a pizzeria made by William Afton. Alongside this, the "Funtime" animatronics were rented out to birthday parties, but this was merely a front for Afton's true goals with the animatronics: to abduct children and allow Afton to experiment on them in his underground bunker to discover the secrets of Remnant. Circus Baby was originally made for Afton's daughter, Elizabeth, but he forbade her from getting near Baby due to her programming.[6] Ignoring her father's warnings, Elizabeth got alone with Circus Baby, and was snatched and sealed inside of the animatronic, where she would come to die and possess Baby.[7] After Circus Baby's Pizza World closed down, Baby was trapped inside of the rental bunker until her brother, Michael Afton, came to the bunker to find her as per his father's instructions.[8] Despite seemingly still caring about her brother, Baby's isolation-induced madness lead her to fuse with the other animatronics into Ennard and scoop out Mike's innards to inhabit his body, allowing her to escape her prison.[2] The other animatronics within would come to reject her,[9] and she would rebuild herself as Scrap Baby, now intent on following in her murderous father's footsteps.[10]

Name: Cloak (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Tyrone Johnson is the "dark" half of the vigilante duo known as Cloak and Dagger. After a drug-related experiment awakened his powers, he became a living personification of darkness. Cloak is the Yin to his partner Dagger's Yang. Superheroes of the streets, Cloak and Dagger wage a war against dangerous drugs and drug-related crimes.

Name: Clouded Leopard
Summary: The clouded leopard (Neofelis nebulosa) is a wild cat inhabiting dense forests from the foothills of the Himalayas through mainland Southeast Asia into South China. Its head-and-body length ranges from 68.6 to 108 cm (27.0 to 42.5 in) with a 61 to 91 cm (24 to 36 in) long tail. It uses its tail for balancing when moving in trees and is able to climb down vertical tree trunks head first. It rests in trees during the day and hunts by night on the forest floor. They have two subspecies: the Mainland clouded leopard & Sunda clouded leopard, with the later being the largest.[1][2]

Name: CMMG Mk47 Mutant
Summary: The CMMG Mk47 Mutant is an American-made semi-automatic rifle chambered in 7.62×39mm caliber, made by CMMG Inc. It can accept all types of 7.62-type magazines, including steel, polymer and drum magazines.

Name: Coelophysis
Summary: Coelophysis is a genus of small, carnivorous dinosaurs that lived during the Late Triassic period. The name "Coelophysis" means "Hollow Form" and refers to the hollow bones that were a notable characteristic of this dinosaur.

Name: Colonel Radec
Summary: Colonel Mael Radec was the leader of the Helghast forces defending the Helghan capital of Pyrrhus City. He is the founder of Radec Academy and Scolar Visari's personal bodyguard. He is the secondary antagonist of Killzone 2 and is known to be one of the most ruthless enemies there.

Name: Colossal Squid
Summary: Colossal squids (Mesonychoteuthis hamiltoni) are large cephalopods that live within deep ocean waters in the Southern Ocean. They are one of the largest of all living invertebrates, and the largest living cephalopod, with an estimated maximum length and weight of 14 meters and 750 kilograms.

Name: Colt Anaconda
Summary: Introduced in 1990, the Colt Anaconda is a large frame double-action revolver featuring a full length under-barrel ejection-rod lug and six round cylinder, designed and produced by the Colt's Manufacturing Company. Chambered for the powerful .44 Magnum and .45 Colt centerfire ammunition cartridges, the Anaconda marked the Hartford, Connecticut firm’s first foray into the popular large-bore Magnum pistol market.

Name: Colt Detective Special
Summary: The Colt Detective Special is a six-shot, carbon steel framed, 2" barreled, double-action revolver, and the first example of a class of firearms known to gun enthusiasts as "snubnosed revolvers". Made by Colt's Manufacturing Company this model revolver, as the name "Detective Special" suggests, was intended to be concealed weapon used by plainclothes police detectives.

Name: Colt Paterson
Summary: The Colt Paterson is the very first commercial repeating firearm with a revolving cylinder (known as a revolver). It was created by Samuel Colt in 1836.

Name: Colt Python
Summary: The Colt Python is a .357 Magnum caliber revolver formerly manufactured by Colt's Manufacturing Company of Hartford, Connecticut. It is sometimes referred to as a "Combat Magnum". It was first introduced in 1955, the same year as Smith & Wesson's M29 .44 Magnum. Now discontinued, the Colt Python was intended for the premium revolver market segment. Some firearm collectors and writers such as Jeff Cooper, Ian V. Hogg, Chuck Hawks, Leroy Thompson, Scott Wolber, Renee Smeets and Martin Dougherty have described the Python as the finest production revolver ever made.

Name: Colt Single Action Army
Summary: The Colt Single Action Army, also known as the Single Action Army, SAA, Model P, Peacemaker and M1873, is a single-action revolver with a revolving cylinder holding six metallic cartridges. It was designed for the U.S. government service revolver trials of 1872 by Colt's Patent Firearms Manufacturing Company—today's Colt's Manufacturing Company—and was adopted as the standard military service revolver until 1892.

Name: Colt Walker
Summary: The Colt Walker, often known as the Walker Colt, is a single-action revolver with a revolving cylinder holding six charges of black powder behind six bullets (typically .44 caliber lead balls). It was designed in 1846 as a collaboration between Captain Samuel Hamilton Walker and American firearms inventor Samuel Colt.

Name: Condiment King (Post-Crisis)
Summary: Mitchell Mayo, once an average guy went inexplicably crazy and donned the identity of the Condiment King to cause crime. He was shown tormenting multiple policemen with his special designed sauce, until he was swiftly defeated by Batgirl and Robin. He was then taken to Arkham Asylum, where he eventually was able to work in the kitchen and fuel his obsession, as well as improve upon his formula. This was further aided by Poison Ivy, who taught him vast knowledge on roots, herbs, and spices. Years later, he would get out of Arkham and be "jokerized". Jokerization is stated to amplify the infected's personality, which actually made Mitchell a credible threat. This would almost cause the Birds of Prey to lose to him, as they though he was a joke. It is later stated due to the nature of Condiment King's obsession/portrayal as a joke, juries and parole boards don't take him seriously, thus allowing him to be set free on Gotham again and again. During Final Crisis Aftermath, Mitchell was one of Immortus' followers, The Army of the Endangered, and was cybernetically enhanced by the brilliant Professor Achilles Milo. He was the one to introduce the "Human Flame" to the group, which would be a mistake. Human Flame would rebel, and along with Seductress, kill every member of The Army of the Endangered, including Mitchell.

Name: Conductor (The Final Station)
Summary: The conductor is the engineer of one of the last few trains in a dying world where a zombie-alien apocalypse has occurred. His job is to keep the passengers alive as well as maintaining the train.

Name: Cottonmouth (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Cornell Stokes, also known as Cottonmouth, is a crime boss stationed in Harlem, New York City. His negative influence on the people of Harlem led him to be opposed by Luke Cage.

Name: Cotylorhynchus
Summary: Cotylorhynchus is an extinct genus of herbivorous caseid synapsids that lived during the late Lower Permian (Kungurian) and possibly the early Middle Permian (Roadian) in what is now Texas and Oklahoma in the United States.

Name: Coyote
Summary: The coyote (Canis latrans) is a carnivorous animal that is native to North America. It is closely related to the Gray Wolf and is much smaller than the more famous canine. It mainly eats meat, though it may also eat fruits and vegetables occasionally. The coyote has 19 recognized subspecies, with one of the most common being the Western Coyote, and the largest subspecies being the Eastern Coyote, which is the result of various historical and recent matings with various types of wolves.

Name: Crowbar
Summary: Crowbars are tools used for opening nailed wooden crates or prying away boards, or in criminal applications, for prying open doors and safes in burglary. In mining, they can be used to break and remove rock. They are usually made from medium-carbon steel, but can also be made out of titanium, which is lighter. In a fight, they are capable of stabbing their opponent to the point of penetrating bone in addition to the ability of being used as a club-style weapon.

Name: Cryolophosaurus
Summary: Cryolophosaurus is a genus of large theropod that inhabited Antarctica during the early Jurassic. Its name comes from the Greek words κρυος, which means "cold" or "frozen"; λοφος, which means "crest"; σαυρος, which means "lizard." The Antarctica around the time of this theropod was warmer than modern times, with a temperate, humid climate and temperatures ranging between 17-18 degrees Celsius[1] The most distinctive feature of Cryolophosaurus is its "pompadour" crest, which had even named it the nickname Elvisaurus due to its similarity to the famous singer.

Name: CV90
Summary: The Combat Vehicle 90 (CV90) (Swedish: stridsfordon 90ⓘ, strf 90 or Stridsfordon 90) is a family of Swedish tracked armoured combat vehicles designed by the Swedish Defence Materiel Administration (FMV), Hägglund & Söner and Bofors during the mid-1980s to early 1990s, before entering service in Sweden in the mid-1990s. The CV90 platform design has continuously evolved from the Mk 0 to the current Mk IV with technological advances and changing battlefield requirements.

Name: CZ 75
Summary: The CZ 75 is a semi-automatic pistol made by Czech firearm manufacturer ČZUB. First introduced in 1975, it is one of the original "wonder nines" and features a staggered-column magazine, all-steel construction, and a hammer forged barrel. It is widely distributed throughout the world and is the most common handgun in the Czech Republic. Firearms expert Colonel Jeff Cooper considered the CZ 75, at least its original version (short rail), to be the best 9mm service pistol ever made.

Name: Darren Cross (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Doctor Darren Cross was the protégé of Hank Pym, who usurped his mentor as CEO of Pym Technologies and rebranded it as Cross Technologies. Cross became obssessed with the Pym Particles and using Pym's technologies to achieve success, but the constant exposure to the particles negatively affected his mind. Cross had developed the Yellowjacket Suit and intended to sell it to HYDRA and the Ten Rings, but Pym and Hope Van Dyne joined forces with Ant-Man, who destroyed his entire research. Driven mad after losing everything he built, Cross wore the suit himself and became Yellowjacket, to get revenge by killing Ant-Man and his family. As Yellowjacket threatened Cassie Lang, he was confronted by Ant-Man, who neutralized him by shrinking him down to a sub-atomic level and destroying his suit.

Name: Demon (Season of the Witch)
Summary: After the country suffers from the Black Death, two church elders accuse a girl of being a witch responsible for the destruction.

Name: Desmatosuchus
Summary: Desmatosuchus is a genus of large, quadrupedal aetosaur Pseudosuchian; its name comes from the Greek words δεσμός (desmos), which means "link," and σοῦχος (soûkhos), which means "crocodile." This heavily armored reptile's back was covered by median scutes surrounded by two more rows of lateral scutes,[1] along with large acromion processes (or shoulder spikes),[2] which would have served as its primary defense against predators such as Postosuchus. It is most widely thought to be a herbivore, with its blunt teeth and shovel-like snout helping it to dig up vegetation to eat.[1][2] It was widely spread across Pangaea during the late Triassic around 228–210 million years ago, found in the Dockum formation, Chinle formation, and Post quarry; the density of numbers in specific areas also hints it was likely a herd animal.[2]

Name: Destiny (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Irene Adler hailed from a prosperous Austrian family, born near the close of the 19th century. Raised in Salzburg, Austria, her mutant gift of precognition emerged at the tender age of 13. Without guidance in harnessing her newfound powers, she faced a deluge of disconcerting, alien sights and sounds. Struggling to preserve her mental faculties, Adler embarked on a journey to record her visions in diaries. a lifeline amidst the chaos. A few years later, Irene hired Raven Darkhölme, a consulting detective, to help her make sense of her diaries. They tried to use Irene's visions to change the future and fell in love in the process. But even though they could make money using Irene's abilities, they couldn't make big changes in society, which left them both frustrated.

Name: Detective Chimp (Post-Flashpoint)
Summary: Bobo T. Chimpanzee, the Detective Chimpanzee, used to be a normal circus animal, until an unlikely series of events led to him drinking from a magical fountain that augmented his mind to an incredible level of intelligence and gifted him immortality.

Name: Diamondback (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Willis Stryker, also known as Diamondback, is the half brother of Luke Cage and a deadly criminal equipped with advanced weaponry from Hammer Industries.

Name: Diamondback (Willis Stryker)
Summary: Willis Stryker was born and raised in Harlem, New York. He grew up on the streets alongside Carl Lucas, his best friend and future partner, and founded the Rivals gang together, where he took on the name of Diamondback. Stryker eventually became convinced however, that Lucas had seduced his girlfriend Reva, and in a fit of jealousy, got his ex-girlfriend murdered and his friend jailed.

Name: Dilophosaurus
Summary: The Dilophosaurus is a medium sized theropod from the early Jurassic period. It is famous for its appearance in Jurassic Park, where it spits venom at an antagonist before killing and eating him. In real life, it apparently did not have the ability to spit venom.

Name: Dimetrodon
Summary: The Dimetrodon was among the earliest land animals, belonging to a proto-mammalian group known as synapsids. Dimetrodons were predatory creatures, with larger dimetrodons often being apex predators. Despite being confused with dinosaurs, Dimetrodons had a temporal range between 295 and 272 million years ago and were more closely related to mammals than modern reptiles, although they were not direct ancestors.

Name: Dingo (Real World)
Summary: The Dingo is a dog that is found in Australia. Its taxonomic classification is debated. It is a medium-sized canine that possesses a lean, hardy body adapted for speed, agility, and stamina.

Name: Dinofelis
Summary: Dinofelis was an early saber-toothed cat widely believed to have preyed on early hominids. It's known as a "false saber-toothed cat" since its teeth weren't as knife-like as other saber-toothed cats, resembling the teeth of modern domesticated cats more closely than other felines at the time.

Name: Dire Wolf
Summary: The Dire Wolf is an extinct species of the genus Aenocyon that lived in North and South America during the Late Pleistocene and early Holocene epochs.

Name: Django Freeman
Summary: Tier: 10-A. 9-C with firearms. 8-C with preparation

Name: Dobermann
Summary: The Dobermann is a German breed of medium-large working dog of pinscher type. It was originally bred in Thuringia in about 1890 by Louis Dobermann, a tax collector. It has a long muzzle and – ideally – an even and graceful gait. The ears were traditionally cropped and the tail docked, practices which are now illegal in many countries.

Name: Doctor Strange (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Thor: So, Earth has wizards now? Strange: The preferred term is "Master of the Mystic Arts".

Name: Dogo Argentino
Summary: This page contains or depicts disturbing and/or graphic content that some may find upsetting, and that is only intended for mature audiences. Please proceed with caution.

Name: Domestic Cat
Summary: The Cat, also known as housecat, alley cat or Domestic Cat, is small, furry mammal. It is a subspecies F. s. catus belonging to the species Felis silvestris in the family Felidae. This animal is the most popular pet in the world.

Name: Domestic Sheep
Summary: Since descending from the Asiatic Mouflon (Ovis Orentalis) and Bezoar Ibex (Capra aegagrus) in the middle east 10,500 years before present (YBP),[1][2] the raising of domestic sheep is responsible for much of the world's lamb supply, mutton supply,[1][3] wool,[1] sheep milk,[4][3] wool,[1][3] and cheese.[1][3][5] In 2011, there were more than 1 billion sheep in the world.[4] Their presence as the most common livestock affected the cultures that raised them.[6][7][8] Even domesticated, sheep preferably moves in flocks for protection.[9][10]

Name: Dr. Mundo
Summary: Utterly mad, tragically homicidal, and horrifyingly purple, Dr. Mundo is what keeps many of Zaun's citizens indoors on particularly dark nights. Now a self-proclaimed physician, he was once a patient of Zaun's most infamous asylum. After "curing" the entire staff, Dr. Mundo established his practice in the empty wards that once treated him and began mimicking the highly unethical procedures he had so often experienced himself. With a full cabinet of medicines and zero medical knowledge, he now makes himself more monstrous with each injection and terrifies the hapless "patients" who wander near his office.

Name: Dragunov Sniper Rifle
Summary: The Dragunov sniper rifle (formal Russian: Сна́йперская Винто́вка систе́мы Драгуно́ва образца́ 1963 года, Snáyperskaya Vintóvka sistém'y Dragunóva obraz'tsá 1963 goda (SVD-63), officially "Sniper Rifle, System of Dragunov, Model of the Year 1963") (GRAU index 6V1 (ГРАУ Индекс 6В1)) is a semi-automatic designated marksman rifle chambered in the 7.62×54mmR cartridge and developed in the Soviet Union.

Name: Dunkleosteus terrelli
Summary: Dunkleosteus terrelli,[1][2][3][4] was a member of the extinct genus Dunkleosteus,[4] it roamed the ocean during the Late Devonian,[4][5][6] about 358 to 382 million years ago, measuring at least 4.1 m (13.5 ft) long and 950 to 1200 kg in weight[7] but was likely larger[1][4][5][6][Note 1], the Dunkleosteus was a hypercarnivorous apex predator of its time[1][2]. Few other placoderms, save, perhaps, its contemporary Titanichthys[1], rivaled Dunkleosteus in size[5].

Name: Edaphosaurus
Summary: Edaphosaurus is a genus of herbivorous synapsid reptiles that are notable for its sail-back. Its name comes from the greek words έδαφος (edaphos), which most directly means "pavement," and σαῦρος (sauros), which means "lizard," with "edaphos" in reference to how closely packed its teeth were. Edaphosauruss emerged in the late Carboniferous around 303.4 million years ago and lived very prominently in the early Permian to around 272.5 million years ago, coexisting with a variety of other pelycosaurs including Dimetrodon. It lived throughout many parts of the United States in North America, along with Central Europe.

Name: Ekko
Summary: Tier: At least 10-B, 9-C with Piltover Clock Hand, Low 2-C Environmental Damage Via Chronobreak | At least 10-B, likely higher, 9-C with QWQRE83 Chrono Blade, Low 2-C Environmental Damage Via Chronobreak

Name: Ekko (Arcane)
Summary: nan

Name: Elephant Gun
Summary: An elephant gun is any kind of gun that either used black powder bullets or was used to hunt large animals such as elephants, buffaloes, and others.

Name: Emu
Summary: The emu is a ratite that also serves as the 2nd tallest extant bird behind the ostrich. The emu is a flightless bird that can reach up to 1.9 meters in height. Adult emus weigh between 18 and 60 kg (40 and 132 lbs), with an average of 31.5 and 37 kg (69 and 82 lbs) in males and females, respectively.[1]

Name: English Mastiff
Summary: https://vsbattles.fandom.com/wiki/File:English_mastiff_barking_sound.mp3

Name: Ennis
Summary: Tier: 9-C

Name: Epicyon
Summary: The Epicyon ("more than a dog") is a large, extinct, canid genus of the subfamily Borophaginae ("bone-crushing dogs"), native to North America. Epicyon existed for about 15 million years from the Hemingfordian age of the Early Miocene to the Hemphillian of the Late Miocene.

Name: Eryops
Summary: Eryops is a large semi aquatic temnospondyl amphibian, the name of which comes from the Greek words ἐρύειν (eryein), which means 'drawn-out,' and ὤψ (ops), which means 'face.' The sole species Erypos megacephalus. It lived in the southwestern United States 299–278 million years ago, predominantly during the early Permian in what is now Texas,[1] while older specimens found in New Mexico from the late Carboniferous.[2] It inhabited lowlands around various bodies of freshwater, where it would hunt. Among the largest animals of it's time, they could reach 1.5 to 2 meters long on average,[2] and the largest could grow to 3 meters in length, with a mass of 102-222 kg.[3] Based on the structure of its vertebrae, limb girdle and ribs, this heavily built creature was well adapted for traversing land for prolonged periods of time.[4]

Name: Erythrosuchus
Summary: Erythrosuchus is a genus of erythrosuchid archosauriform, and the largest of this family of archosauriformes. Its name comes from the Greek words ἐρυθρός (eruthrós), which means "red," and σοῦχος (soukhos), which means "crocodile," named for the reddish color of the rock the fossils were formed in and collected from. It lived in South Africa 249–244 million years ago, during the early to mid Triassic, and was the apex predator of its place and time. Erythrosuchus, along with others in the family of erythrosuchidae, were known for their exceptionally large heads in proportion to their body size. Unlike more basal archosauriformes like Proterosuchus, this creature and its relatives were some of the earliest to have an erect posture.[1]

Name: European Longsword
Summary: A longsword is a type of European sword characterized as having a cruciform hilt with a grip for two-handed use (around 16 to 28 cm (6 to 11 in)) and a straight double-edged blade of around 85 to 110 cm (33 to 43 in). It was prevalent during the late medieval and Renaissance periods (approximately 1350 to 1550), with early and late use reaching into the 13th and 17th centuries, and can owe it's success to its versatile cross-guard, and it's flexible, straight blade, which is effective at stabbing and resisting damage.

Name: M109 Paladin
Summary: The M109 Paladin is an American 155 mm turreted self-propelled howitzer, first introduced in the early 1960s to replace the M44 and M52. It has been upgraded a number of times, most recently to the M109A7. The M109 family is the most common Western indirect-fire support weapon of maneuver brigades of armored and mechanized infantry divisions. It has a crew of four: the section chief/commander, the driver, the gunner, and the ammunition handler/loader.

Name: Federal Riot Gun
Summary: The Federal Riot Gun, or FRG, is a US-manufactured firearm by Federal Laboratories Inc., designed to fire non-lethal munitions. Its ammunition include 37 and 38mm baton and tear gas rounds. The baton rounds were cylindrical, rubber projectiles.

Name: Fire Axe
Summary: The Fire axe, camp axe or fireman's axe is a tool used to break down wood, although it can be used fairly well as a weapon.

Name: Flamethrower
Summary: A Flamethrower is a weapon that projects a long stream of fire. This is usually fueled either by flammable liquids, or natural gas/propane.

Name: Flintlock pistol
Summary: Flintlock is a general term for any firearm that uses a flint striking ignition mechanism. The term may also apply to a particular form of the mechanism itself, also known as the true flintlock, that was introduced in the early 17th century, and rapidly replaced earlier firearm-ignition technologies, such as the matchlock, the wheellock, and the earlier flintlock mechanisms.

Name: FN F2000
Summary: The FN F2000 is a 5.56×45mm NATO bullpup assault rifle, designed by FN Herstal in Belgium. The F2000 made its debut in March 2001 at the IDEX defence exhibition held in Abu Dhabi, in the United Arab Emirates.

Name: FN FAL
Summary: The FAL (French: Fusil Automatique Léger, English: Light Automatic Rifle) is a battle rifle designed by Belgian small arms designers Dieudonné Saive and Ernest Vervier and manufactured by FN Herstal.

Name: FN Five-seven
Summary: The FN Five-seven, trademarked as the Five-seveN, is a semi-automatic pistol designed and manufactured by FN Herstal in Belgium. The pistol is named for its 5.7-mm (.224 in) bullet diameter, and the trademark capitalization style is intended to emphasize the manufacturer's initials—FN.

Name: FN MAG/M240 machine gun
Summary: The FN MAG is a Belgian 7.62 mm general-purpose machine gun, designed in the early 1950s at Fabrique Nationale (FN) by Ernest Vervier. It has been used by more than 80 countries and it has been made under licence in several countries, including Argentina, Canada (as the C6 GPMG), Egypt, India and the United Kingdom. It has also been used in various terrorist organizations.

Name: FN Minimi/M249 light machine gun
Key: '''FN Minimi and its variants, M249 machine gun and Mk 46 machine gun''' | '''Mk 48 machine gun'''
Summary: The FN Minimi (short for French: Mini Mitrailleuse; "mini machine gun") is a Belgian 5.56mm Squad Automatic Weapon, or SAW developed by Fabrique Nationale (FN) in Herstal by Ernest Vervier. First introduced in the late 1970s, it is now in service in more than 75 countries. The weapon is currently manufactured at the FN facility in Herstal and their U.S. subsidiary FN Manufacturing LLC. The Minimi is a SAW that fires from an open bolt. It is an air-cooled weapon that is capable of fully automatic fire only. It can be belt fed or fired from a magazine. The Minimi is configured in several variants: the Standard model as a platoon or squad support weapon, the Para version for paratroopers and the Vehicle model as secondary armament for fighting vehicles.

Name: FN P90
Summary: The FN P90, also known as the FN Project 1990, is a compact personal defense weapon (PDW) designed and manufactured by FN Herstal in Belgium. Created in response to NATO requests for a replacement for 9×19mm Parabellum firearms, the P90 was designed as a compact but powerful firearm for vehicle crews, operators of crew-served weapons, support personnel, special forces, and counter-terrorist groups.

Name: FN SCAR
Summary: The FN SCAR (Special Operations Forces Combat Assault Rifle) is a gas-operated (short-stroke gas piston) self-loading rifle with a rotating bolt. It is constructed to be extremely modular, including barrel change to switch between calibers. The rifle was developed by Belgian manufacturer FN Herstal (FNH) for the United States Special Operations Command (SOCOM) to satisfy the requirements of the SCAR competition. This family of rifles consist of two main types. The SCAR-L, for "light," is chambered in 5.56×45mm NATO cartridge and the SCAR-H, for "heavy," is chambered in 7.62×51mm NATO. Both are available in Close Quarters Combat (CQC), Standard (STD), and Long Barrel (LB) variants.

Name: Francis Dolarhyde (Film)
Summary: In the 2002 film Red Dragon, the Tooth Fairy is the main antagonist, portrayed by Ralph Fiennes. The character is based on Francis Dolarhyde, a disturbed individual with a traumatic past who becomes a serial killer. Dolarhyde, who is often referred to as the Tooth Fairy, is named after his method of killing, which involves removing the teeth of his victims.

Name: Gastornis
Summary: Gastornis is a genus of large, flightless bird, considered to be related to modern fowl. It was initially thought to be carnivorous, but more recent evidence (such as the tips its beak and claws lacking a hook-like shape, and analysis of calcium isotopes in its bones[1]) indicates that it was herbivorous,[2] its large beak suited to breaking seeds and other tough plant matter rather than catching small mammals. It lived during the mid Paleocene to mid Eocene epochs, throughout North America, Europe, and Asia, inhabiting lush environments that existed even in the Arctic during its time.

Name: Gaur
Summary: The gaur (also known as indian bison, or Bos gaurus scientifically) are the largest extant bovidae that lives throughout asia, albeit listed as a vulnerable species on the IUCN Red List.[1][2] They're wild cattle that live near accesssible fresh water in undisturbed, large, forested areas and hilly terrain.[1]

Name: German Shepherd
Summary: The German Shepherd is a medium to large-sized German Breed of herding dog that was later used for police and military work. It is also commonly kept as a companion.

Name: Gharial
Summary: The Gharial (Gavialis gangeticus) is a species of crocodylomorph adapted to a predominantly piscivorous lifestyle. They are known for their long and thin jaws, with the males sporting a lump on the tip of their snouts which resembles an earthen pot called a "ghara" (hence the name "Gharial"). This lump forms following sexual maturity in males. They are among the largest crocodilians alive today, with females can reach 4.5 meters long, while males can reach 6 meters long; average adult mass is 160-180 kg, while males can reach a mass of 600 kg, and the largest found was 977 kg.

Name: Ghiaccio
Summary: Ghiaccio is a minor antagonist in JoJo's Bizarre Adventure Part V: Vento Aureo. A member of Risotto's sub-gang in Passione, he attacks Giorno Giovanna and Guido Mista in search for taking Trish Una and information leading to finding the Boss of Passione. He is the last member of the squad encountered by Bucciarati's group.

Name: Ghoul (Dungeons and Dragons)
Key: '''Ghoul''' | '''Lacedon''' | '''Elder Ghoul''' | '''Vapour Ghoul''' | '''Shadow Ghoul''' | '''Noble/Wizard Ghoul''' | '''Cleric Ghoul''' | '''Abyssal Ghoul''' | '''Flesh Seeker''' | '''Whisperer Ghoul''' | '''Gatherer Ghoul''' | '''Ghoul Warrior''' | '''Ghoul Stalker''' | '''Gravetouched Ghoul''' | '''Ghast''' | '''Darkpach Ghoul'''
Summary: Ghouls are malicious undead that haunt battlefields and scenes of slaughter. Not unlike maggots or Carrion Crawlers, they sweep to the scent of freshly killed flesh in droves to devour and consume. The first ghoul was made when Doresain, an elf worshiper of Orcus, consumed human flesh. As a reward, Orcus granted him a domain in his layer of the Abyss- however, this was lost when Yeenoghu overthrew Doresain. When Orcus failed to act on his behalf, Doresain turned back to the elf gods, who saved him from total annihilation once more.

Name: Giant Anteater
Summary: The giant anteater is the largest of the four extant species of anteater. Unlike other anteaters and sloths, the giant anteater is a mostly terrestrial animal. The giant anteater is recognizable for its long snout, bushy tail, long foreclaws, and distinctive fur markings. The giant anteater's bold marking serves as warning coloration. The giant anteater has been featured in pre-Colombian myths and folklore and popular culture.

Name: Giant Panda
Summary: The Giant Panda (Ailuropoda melanoleuca; Chinese: 大熊猫; pinyin: dàxióngmāo), also known as the panda bear or simply the panda, is a bear native to south central China.

Name: Giant Squid
Summary: Giant squids (Architeuthis dux) are large cephalopods that live within deep ocean waters worldwide. They are one of the largest of all living invertebrates and the second-largest cephalopod, with an estimated maximum length and weight of 13 meters and 275 kilograms.

Name: Giant Trevally
Summary: The giant trevally (Caranx ignobilis) is a large species of fish native to oceans worldwide. It is an apex predator in most of its range, and hunts both alone and in schools.

Name: Gigantopithecus
Summary: The Gigantopithecus was a large primate that lived during the Pleistocene. It lived in India, China and Vietnam.

Name: Giraffe
Summary: Giraffes are the tallest living terrestrial animal and the largest ruminant.[1][2] Giraffes are characterized by their long necks and legs,[1][2] their horn-like ossicones,[1][2] and their distinctive coat patterns.[1][2] This appearance intrigued many cultures, both modern and ancient, and has often been featured in books, paintings, and cartoons.[3]

Name: Gleek (Post-Rebirth)
Summary: Gleek is an Exxorian Monkey and a performer in the Trans-World Carnival where he was abused by his owner, Ringmaster, but cared for by the Bearded Woman. Gleek was, for unknown reasons, eventually dropped and deemed a 'failure' before he was adopted by Zan of the Wonder Twins, who dearly loved him the moment he laid eyes on him. Gleek became a member of the Justice League and later, Asterisk, and accompanied the Wonder Twin on their many adventures.

Name: Glock pistol
Summary: The Glock is a semi-automatic pistol used mostly by law enforcement and military. It was created in Austria in 1980 to be a substitute of the outdated Walther P38.

Name: Goat
Summary: Domesticated goats (Capra aegagrus hircus) are a subspecies of goat bred from the vulnerable Wild Goat. Goats vary greatly in weight based on breed, ranging from 20-27 kg for small goat does to over 140 kg for larger bucks such as Boer goats.

Name: Goblin Shark
Summary: The goblin shark (Mitsukurina owstoni) is a species of deep-sea shark native to oceans worldwide. It inhabits depths of over 1300 meters below the surface, and primarily feeds on rays and crustaceans near the seafloor.

Name: Gojirasaurus Quayi
Summary: Gojirasaurus quayi (Meaning "Godzilla lizard") is one of the largest known theropod carnivores of the Triassic Period. While it is somewhat of a dubious genus, it is thought to be a coelophysoid. Comparing the size of Gojirasaurus' tibia to its relatives, it has been estimated to be 5.5 meters or 18 feet in length and weighing up to 150-200 kg or 330–440 lb. As obviously shown in the name, this dinosaur was named after the iconic kaiju named Godzilla (Gojira).

Name: Golden Eagle
Summary: The Golden Eagle is a famous bird of prey native to most of the world. It has been trained by falconers and Steppe cultures for hundreds of years.

Name: Golf Club
Summary: A Golf Club is one of a set of specially shaped wooden or metal sticks used for hitting a golf ball

Name: Gorilla
Summary: The Gorilla is the largest genus of primate that currently roams the Earth, and is one of the closest living relatives to humans apart from chimps. Gorillas are found in Sub-Saharan Africa, and they can cover a wide range of elevations.

Name: Gray Wolf
Summary: The Gray wolf is an infamous carnivorous animal found all in the Americas and Eurasia. It is known to humans more than almost any other predatory animal, with more importance to human culture than most others. Although the fear of wolves is common in humans, wolf attacks are very rare.

Name: Great Barracuda
Summary: The great barracuda (Sphyraena barracuda) is a species of scrombid fish endemic to subtropical waters worldwide. It is renowned for its ferocity and intimidating appearance.

Name: Greenland Shark
Summary: The Greenland shark (Somniosus microcephalus) is a species of sleeper shark endemic to cold waters in the North Atlantic and Arctic Oceans. It is the longest living vertebrate species, with a lifespan of more than 400 years.

Name: Grizzly Bear
Summary: The Grizzly Bear is a subspecies of the Brown Bear found mostly in North America.[1] It is noted for being one of the largest subspecies of bears.

Name: Groot (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Groot is a hyper-intelligent, tree-like organism from the species Flora colossus native to the planet X. While he possesses human level intellect, Groot's robust and heavyweight physiology causes the organs of his acoustic generation to become stiff and inflexible, rendering the limits of his speech to the simple phrase, "I am Groot."

Name: Guanlong
Summary: Guanlong is a genus of small proceratosaurid theropod family that lived during the late Jurassic in China. Its name comes from the Chinese words 冠, which means "crown", and 龍, which means "dragon." Its most distinctive feature is the crest on its head, which due to its fragile nature, was most likely for display.[1] It is the earliest discovered tyrannosauroid, and distantly related to the much larger and more famous Tyrannosaurus rex, which would emerge 92 million years later.

Name: Guardians of the Galaxy (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Nebula: All any of you do is yell at each other. You're not friends. Drax: You're right... We're family.
ID: Guardians of the Galaxy (Marvel Cinematic Universe)-MarvelCinematicUniverse-9-C

Name: Gwenpool
Summary: Gwendolyn Poole was just a normal girl, living an unsatisfactory life and with a fierce passion for Marvel Comics, when one day she was mysterious transported within the exciting world of her beloved stories. Extremely galvanized at this prospect, Gwen donned a costume and took on the identity of Gwenpool, determined to have the most fun of her new life. Extremely erratic, reckless and borderline psychotic, Gwen viewed herself as the protagonist of the story and the world around her as a playground, uncaring for even the lives of others, for they were expendable fictional characters. However, things quickly escalated and slipped out of her hands, making her bitterly realize the harsh truth: she was not in control .

Name: Haast's Eagle
Summary: The Haast's eagle was the largest eagle to have ever existed. It existed until a few hundred years ago when its primary prey source was hunted to death by humans.

Name: Heckler & Koch G3
Summary: The G3 (Gewehr 3) is a 7.62×51mm NATO, select-fire battle rifle developed in the 1950s by the German armament manufacturer Heckler & Koch (H&K) in collaboration with the Spanish state-owned design and development agency CETME (Centro de Estudios Técnicos de Materiales Especiales).

Name: Heckler & Koch G36
Summary: The Heckler & Koch G36 is a 5.56×45mm assault rifle, designed in the early 1990s by Heckler & Koch in Germany as a replacement for the heavier 7.62mm G3 battle rifle. It was accepted into service with the Bundeswehr in 1997, replacing the G3. The G36 is gas-operated and feeds from a 30-round detachable box magazine or 100-round C-Mag drum magazine.

Name: Heckler & Koch HK416
Summary: The Heckler & Koch HK416 is a rifle designed and manufactured by Heckler & Koch. Although its design is in large part based on the AR-15 class of weapons, specifically the Colt M4 carbine family issued to the U.S. military, it uses an HK-proprietary short-stroke gas piston system originally derived from the ArmaLite AR-18 (the same system was also used in Heckler & Koch's earlier G36 family of rifles). It is the standard assault rifle of the Norwegian Armed Forces, and was the weapon used by SEAL Team Six to kill Osama Bin Laden in 2011. It has also been selected as replacement of the FAMAS in the French Armed Forces. Since 2013, a new updated version called the HK416 A3 has effectively replaced the original HK416, with the A5 featuring several improvements like an improved tool-less adjustable gas regulator for suppressor use that can accommodate barrel lengths down to 10.5 inches without modifications, a redesigned lower receiver with ambidextrous fire controls, optimised magazine and ammunition compatibility, a repair kit housed inside the pistol grip, and additional heavy nuts to make its weak spots more resistant to accidental impact. The A7 version is basically a German-exclusive selector update on the A5, where the selector now rotates 90 degrees instead of the typical 180 degrees on most M16 rifles and their variants. The A8 version of the rifle, dubbed the G95KA1, was selected as the successor to the G36 as the new standard issue rifle for the German Bundeswehr in 2022.

Name: Heckler & Koch Mark 23 pistol
Summary: The Heckler & Koch MK 23, MK 23 MOD 0, Mark 23, or USSOCOM MARK 23 is a semi-automatic large-frame pistol chambered in .45 ACP, designed specifically to be an offensive pistol. The USSOCOM version of the MK23 came paired with a laser aiming module (LAM) and suppressor. The USSOCOM MK23 was adopted by the United States Special Operations Command (USSOCOM) for special operations units, beating out the nearest competitor, Colt's OHWS. Development of the pistol began in 1991 as special operations representatives identified the need for an "Offensive Handgun Weapons System—Special Operations Peculiar", and delivery of the pistols began in May 1996 to the special operation units.

Name: Heckler & Koch MP5
Summary: The MP5 (German: Maschinenpistole 5) is a 9x19mm Parabellum submachine gun, developed by a team of engineers from the German small arms manufacturer Heckler & Koch GmbH (H&K) in the 1960s. There are over 100 variants and clones of the MP5, including some semi-automatic variants.

Name: Heckler & Koch MP7 Submachine Gun
Summary: The Heckler & Koch MP7 (Maschinenpistole 7) is a German personal defence weapon (PDW) designed and manufactured by Heckler & Koch (H&K) and chambered for the HK 4.6×30mm cartridge. It was designed with the new cartridge to meet NATO requirements published in 1989, as these requirements call for a personal defense weapon (PDW) class firearm, with a greater ability to penetrate body armor than current weapons limited to conventional pistol cartridges. The MP7 went into production in 2001. It is a direct rival to the FN P90, also developed in response to NATO's requirement. The weapon has been revised since its introduction and the latest production variants are the MP7A1 and MP7A2.

Name: Heckler & Koch UMP
Summary: The Heckler & Koch UMP (Universale Maschinenpistole, German for "Universal Machine Pistol") is a submachine gun developed and manufactured by Heckler & Koch. Heckler & Koch developed the UMP as a lighter and cheaper successor to the MP5, though both remain in production. The UMP has been adopted for use by various countries, including Brazil, Canada, and the United States. Some of the weapons saw limited service in the early years of the Iraqi insurgency, making them one of the more popular submachine guns being deployed by the U.S. military personnel in recent conflicts around the world.

Name: Heckler & Koch USP
Summary: The USP (Universelle Selbstladepistole or "universal self-loading pistol") is a semi-automatic pistol developed in Germany by Heckler & Koch GmbH (H&K) of Oberndorf am Neckar as a replacement for the P7 series of handguns.

Name: Helmut Zemo (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Colonel Helmut Zemo was a member of a death squad in Sokovian Armed Forces who lost his family to Ultron during the Battle of Sokovia. Zemo blamed the Avengers and sought revenge on them. He knew the Avengers could not be beaten through force, and instead attempted to manipulate them into destroying each other and took advantage of the friction between the Avengers during the signing of the Sokovia Accords by committing acts of terrorism and framing James Barnes, causing further conflict between Steve Rogers and Tony Stark. Zemo would eventually be caught by the Black Panther and imprisoned.

Name: Herrerasaurus
Summary: Herrerasaurus is a dinosaur that lived during the Late Triassic period, approximately 231 to 228 million years ago.[1] It is considered one of the earliest known dinosaurs and belongs to the group called theropods, which includes famous dinosaurs like Tyrannosaurus rex and Velociraptor.[1] Herrerasaurus was first discovered in the Ischigualasto Formation of northwestern Argentina in the 1960s.[1] The name "Herrerasaurus" is derived from the name of the rancher Victorino Herrera, who owned the land where the fossils were found.[1]

Name: Homo Floresiensis
Summary: Homo Floresiensis or commonly nicknamed the Hobbit was a human species that lived from 190,000 years ago to around 50,000 years ago on the islands of Indonesia. They are famous for being very small, smaller than the range for normal modern humans and even Chimpanzees. They display the affect that Island Dwarfism has on animals, including humans.

Name: Honey Badger
Summary: The Ratel or Honey Badger is an animal native to Africa and Asia known for its impressive durability and aggression.

Name: Horse
Summary: The horse (Equus ferus caballus) is one of two extant subspecies of Equus ferus. It is an odd-toed ungulate mammal belonging to the taxonomic family Equidae. The horse has evolved over the past 45 to 55 million years from a small multi-toed creature, Eohippus, into the large, single-toed animal of today. Humans began domesticating horses around 4000 BC, and their domestication is believed to have been widespread by 3000 BC. Horses in the subspecies caballus are domesticated, although some domesticated populations live in the wild as feral horses. These feral populations are not true wild horses, as this term is used to describe horses that have never been domesticated, such as the endangered Przewalski's horse, a separate subspecies, and the only remaining true wild horse. There is an extensive, specialized vocabulary used to describe equine-related concepts, covering everything from anatomy to life stages, size, colors, markings, breeds, locomotion, and behavior.

Name: Humboldt Squid
Summary: The Humboldt Squid (Dosidicus gigas) is a popularly fished species of squid in the waters of the eastern pacific.[1] It's the largest member of the flying squid family and abundant due to overfishing.[1][2] Despite being a well-studied animal, the IUCN has classified the conservation status of the squid as data deficient.[1]

Name: Husky
Summary: The Siberian Husky is a breed of dog from, unsurprisingly, Siberia, bred for both working for humans and acting as a companion to them.

Name: Hyacinth Macaw
Summary: The Hyacinth Macaw (Anodorhynchus hyacinthinus), or hyacinthine macaw, is a parrot native to central and eastern South America. With a length (from the top of its head to the tip of its long pointed tail) of about one meter it is longer than any other species of parrot. It is the largest macaw and the largest flying parrot species.

Name: Hybodus
Summary: Hybodus is a genus of hybodont, a group of cartilaginous fish that emerged in the Middle Triassic and lasted until the Late Cretaceous[1]. Hybodus as a genus was prevalent throughout the early Jurassic. It is known for its distinctive fin spines, which likely served as protection from larger predators. They also displayed sexual dimorphism with the presence of clasper fins on the males, a trait maintained in modern sharks.[2]

Name: Hyneria
Summary: Hyneria is a genus of lobe finned fish, named after the village of Hyner in Pennsylvania where it was first discovered.[1] It lived in the Famennian part of the Devonion period, which was around 371.1 to 359.3 million years ago, and was an apex predator in freshwater environments it inhabited.

Name: Ichika Orimura
Summary: Ichika Orimura (織斑 一夏, Orimura Ichika) is the main protagonist of the Infinite Stratos series. A normal Japanese teenage boy, until it is discovered that he can pilot an IS which could only be used by women. Realizing the potential, Ichika is forced by the Japanese government to attend the prestigious Infinite Stratos Academy, an international academy where IS pilots from all over the world are trained. Thus his busy school life surrounded by girls begins.

Name: Ichthyosaurus
Summary: Ichthyosaurus is among the most well-known genera of ichthyosaurs: marine reptiles that bore fishlike features. Ichthyosaurus first appeared in the late Triassic period, with most fossils being dated back into the early Jurassic period. Ichthyosaurus is typically smaller than other ichthyosaurs, with a typical length of 6 feet and a typical weight of around 200 lbs (90.7184 kg), although one species of ichthyosaurus was assumed to be around 300-330 cm long.

Name: Idunn
Summary: Idunn (イドゥン, Idenn in the Japanese version) is the final boss of Fire Emblem: Binding Blade. She is also the Demon Dragon who is known as the Dark Priestess.

Name: Ijin Yu
Summary: Ijin Yu is the main protagonist of the Mercenary Enrollment manhwa. When Ijin was nine, he and his parents were involved in a plane crash. Although Ijin survived, he was orphaned and was stranded from his remaining family. Eventually he was taken in by an group called The Numbers. Ijin underwent harsh training, and he worked as a mercenary for about eight years, serving in the harshest battlefields across the world. Later, during a rescue mission, he saved a RoK major named Kang Hamchan, his team and a doctor. Kang Hamchan traced Ijin's family and helped him retire. Ijin underwent a six-month orientation from Major Kang to help him adjust to civilian life. He's currently living with his grandfather and his sister in Seoul. Aside from attending Shinan high school, Ijin works as a part-time bodyguard at the SW group's security team, along with classmate Koh Sukjoo.

Name: IMI Desert Eagle
Summary: The Desert Eagle is a semi-automatic pistol, it is used by U.S Soldiers and Israeli forces.

Name: Inostrancevia (Real World)
Summary: Inostrancevia is a large carnivorous therapsid reptile, belonging to the group Gorgonopsia. Of all the gorgonopsids, Inostrancevia was the largest. It lived throughout present-day Siberia and North Africa during the late Permian Period. between 259-251.9 million years ago, and was an apex predator of its place and time. However, it would go extinct during the most catastrophic mass extinction event in Earth's history, the Permian-Triassic Extinction, at the end of both the Permian Period and the Paleozoic Era.

Name: Iron Man (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: J.A.R.V.I.S.: Sir, there are still terabytes of calculations needed before an actual flight is adju- Tony: J.A.R.V.I.S., sometimes you gotta run before you can walk.

Name: Jack Carver
Summary: Jack, a former United States Army Special Forces soldier, has left his past behind and offers his services as a freelance boat charter in the South Pacific. He is employed by a reporter named Valerie Constantine to take her to a mysterious island, once occupied by the Japanese during the war, claiming to study its little-known World War II ruins. When Valerie goes ashore alone on a jetski, Jack anchors down shortly before his boat is destroyed by a missile launched by an army of mercenaries occupying the island.

Name: Jaekelopterus
Summary: Jaekelopterus is a genus of predatory eurypterid, a group of extinct aquatic arthropods. Fossils of Jaekelopterus have been discovered in deposits of Early Devonian age, from the Pragian and Emsian stages. There are two known species: the type species J. rhenaniae from brackish to fresh water strata in the Rhineland, and J. howelli from estuarine strata in Wyoming. The generic name combines the name of German paleontologist Otto Jaekel, who described the type species, and the Greek word πτερόν (pteron) meaning "wing".

Name: Jaguar (Real World)
Summary: The Jaguar (Panthera onca) is the largest felid in the Americas and has the highest bite force of any cat. Overall, the jaguar is the largest native cat species of the New World and the third largest in the world. This spotted cat closely resembles the Leopard, but is usually larger and sturdier. It ranges across a variety of forested and open terrains, but its preferred habitat is tropical and subtropical moist broadleaf forest, swamps and wooded regions. The jaguar enjoys swimming and is largely a solitary, opportunistic, stalk-and-ambush predator at the top of the food chain. As a keystone species it plays an important role in stabilizing ecosystems and regulating prey populations.

Name: Jayna (Post-Rebirth)
Summary: Jayna is an Exxorian superhero who was sent to Earth after realizing her grandfather was an infamous corrupt politician who ruined the lives of virtually every family on their planet. As her father was a friend of Superman, she was offered an internship at the Hall of Justice an quickly became a true-blue member of the Justice League, sometimes assisting Superman and Batman on missions and later joined Young Justice as well. After going on a world-saving adventure without the permission of Superman and the other Leaguers, Jayna and her brother were kicked from the league, but became members of Asterisk, a team set up by the league to help the world in non-violent means.

Name: Jean-Luc Picard
Key: '''TV Picard''' | '''Movie Picard''' | '''Piloting auxiliary crafts''' | '''Assimilated into the Borg'''
Summary: Jean-Luc Picard, known to the Borg Collective by his designation of Locutus, was a celebrated Starfleet officer, archaeologist and diplomat who served during the latter two thirds of the 24th century. The highlights of his career were centered around assignments as commanding officer of the Federation starships: USS Stargazer, USS Enterprise-D, and the USS Enterprise-E. In these roles, Picard not only witnessed the major turning points of recent galactic history, but also played a key role in them, from making first contact as captain of the Federation's flagship with 27 alien species, including the Ferengi and the Borg.

Name: Jericho 941
Summary: The Jericho 941 is a double-action/single-action semi-automatic pistol developed by Israel Weapon Industries (prior to 2005, Israel Military Industries) that was introduced in 1990.

Name: Jim Hopper
Summary: Jim Hopper, nicknamed "Hop", is the chief of Hawkins Police Department. Hopper has lived in Hawkins nearly all his life, having attended high school with Joyce Byers and Bob Newby. He has also been addressed as "Sheriff Hopper," but this is not a correct title. Hopper was married and they had a daughter together, Sarah. They divorced after his young daughter died of cancer, which caused him to lapse into alcoholism. For a few years after Sarah's death, he was a cop in "a big city"; the show never states which city. When he had been in the city long enough, he moved back to Hawkins. Eventually, he grows to be more responsible, saving Will Byers as well as taking Eleven in as his adopted daughter. In Season 3, he tries to break up Eleven and Mike since their relationship is moving too fast for him, whilst simultaneously trying to rekindle his relationship with Joyce. After the events of Season 3, he was kidnapped by the Soviets and forced to do manual labor for them as their prisoner. He eventually managed to escape, and returned to his life with Eleven and Joyce.

Name: Jinny Hex (Post-Rebirth)
Summary: Jinny Hex is a superhero from Texas and the great-great-granddaughter of Jonah Hex. Raised by a single mother in a rural town, Jinny was ignorant of her heritage until her mother, now on her deathbed, told her of the adventures of her distant relative and the treasure he left behind. After gaining the stash of treasure, Jinny traveled to Metropolis and ended up joining Young Justice and accompanied them on many adventures across the multiverse before she traveled back to Texas to face her deadbeat father in his quest to become king of the world.

Name: John Constantine (Classic)
Summary: This page contains or depicts disturbing and/or graphic content that some may find upsetting, and that is only intended for mature audiences. Please proceed with caution.

Name: K-999
Summary: K-999 is a robotic dog created by Tux Dog to assist the Problem Solverz. He was programmed with the task of assisting the Problem Solverz with solving problems, although for the most part, he only got in their way and acted as a nuisance in his first appearance on the show. He is friendly towards Alfe and has a small disdain for Roba and Horace.

Name: Kaecilius (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Kaecilius was a sorcerer and a former member of the Masters of the Mystic Arts. He became corrupted and opposed the Ancient One and his former brothers-in-arms when he felt his mentor had failed in her promise to help him find meaning to his wife and son's tragic deaths or found a way to bring them back together. Becoming angered by this, Kaecilius rebelled against his allies and formed the Zealots, aiming to find their meaning in the Mystic Arts that the Ancient One was hiding from them. He and his followers then stole a few pages of the Book of Cagliostro from Kamar-Taj's library as part of his scheme to summon Dormammu of the Dark Dimension to Earth. He is ultimately defeated when Dormammu accepts Doctor Strange's bargain to leave Earth and take the souls of Kaecilius and his minions with him in return for freedom from the time-loop that Strange created.

Name: Kang Chan
Summary: Kang Chan, or God of Blackfield is the main protagonist of God Of Blackfield and a Reincarnate. In his previous life, Kang Chan was a captain of the French foreign legion along with Dayeru, Smithen, and Sharlan. During one of his missions, he gained infamy and became known as the "God of Blackfield". In 2016, he was assigned with a mission to clear out enemy soldiers of a head executive named Masallan in Africa. Five squads were dispatched including Chan's team which included Smithen and Dayeru along with six other members. Two kilometers before the arrived at their destination the team fell into an enemy's ambush, Smithen got shot first and the whole team was overwhelmed under enemy's fire. As the firefight continued, Dayeru got shot whilst Kang Chan tried to keep Smithen from bleeding out. However, as he stood to fight the enemy and help his follow soldiers, Chan was killed by a shot from a sniper to the back of his head; his last sight as he lay dying was the enemy troops moving forward and killing his teammates. As Kang Chan's mind fell into oblivion, he felt severe headache and thirst. As he gradually came to his senses, he could heard a person speaking Korean. He finds out that he is in Se-Byeol Hospital in Gangnam, South Korea. As he learns that he was unconscious for 3 days, he runs over to a mirror and discovers that he's now in the body of an 18-years-old Korean boy who's also named Kang Chan.

Name: Kangal Dog
Summary: The Kangal dog is a breed of guard dog originating from Kangal Province, Sivas, Turkey, used to defend both livestock herds and human families. Unlike many other domestic dogs, Kangals are rather antisocial and do not like being around too many people.

Name: Karl Mordo (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Karl Mordo came to the Kamar-Taj to become one of the Masters of the Mystic Arts in order to avenge a tragedy in his life. Mordo was initially arrogant and disrespectful to others, but he eventually humbled and set aside his thirst for revenge. He was noted for being rigid and unwilling to compromise his beliefs of the natural order that he gained. Mordo became a Master and assisted the Ancient One in recruiting and training others in the ways of magic.

Name: Katana (Real Life)
Summary: The Katana is a type of single-edged longsword indigenous to Japan. It first saw use during the Muramachi period of Japan's history, just prior to the rise of Oda Nobunaga. Since then, its decidedly impressive design and former status as a symbol of nobility has ingrained it into pop culture, leading to its production even in the modern day.

Name: Kate Bishop (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Clint: This life you wanna live. To really help people. I mean, try to help people, anyway. Comes a lot of sacrifices. And some things you'll lose... forever. Kate: Well, there's also things you gain, like trick arrows and a cool costume.

Name: KelTec P11
Summary: The KelTec P11 is a compact, semi-automatic, short-recoil operated pistol chambered in 9 mm Luger. Discontinued in 2019, the P11 was manufactured by Kel-Tec CNC Industries of Cocoa, FL from 1995 to 2019.

Name: Kilij (Real World)
Summary: A kilij (from Turkish kılıç, literally "sword") is a type of one-handed, single edged and moderately curved saber used by the Turarian Empire, Uyghur Khaganate, Seljuk Empire, Timurid Empire, Mamluk Empire, Ottoman Empire, and the later Turkic Khanates of Central Asia and Eurasian steppes. These blades evolved from Turko-Mongol sabers that had been used over all the lands invaded and/or influenced by the Turkic peoples.

Name: Kite Man (Post-Flashpoint)
Summary: Charles Brown was a simple aerodynamics engineer with a son, however, his past with working with the Joker caught up with him gravely during the War of Jokes and Riddles, where he was the "punchline" of the Riddler's attempt to make Joker laugh. Riddler tried to achieve this by killing his son so Charles would seek vengeance and in his grief become: Kite Man. Despite, knowingly knowing that everyone treats him like a joke, Charles's sheer resolve and determination ended up prevailing him over Riddler and his army, which turned out to be Nygma's ultimate goal.

Name: Knife
Summary: A knife is a tool or weapon with an edge or blade, often attached to a handle or hilt. Knives are one of the first tools used by mankind, appearing at least 2.5 million years ago, as evidenced by the Oldowan tools.

Name: Kodiak Bear
Summary: The Kodiak bear, also known as the Kodiak brown bear, sometimes the "Alaskan brown bear", inhabits the islands of the Kodiak Archipelago in southwest Alaska. It is the largest recognized subspecies or population of the brown bear, and one of the two largest bears alive today, the other being the polar bear.

Name: Komodo Dragon
Summary: Tier: 9-C, higher via piercing damage

Name: Korath the Pursuer (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Vers: Has a Skrull ever simmed you? Korath: Once. It was deeply disturbing. Vers: Why? Korath: Because I stared into the face of my mortal enemy and the face staring back was my own. Att-Lass: Maybe if you were more attractive, then it would be less disturbing. Korath: You think you’re funny. I’m not laughing. Att-Lass: You never laugh. Korath: I laugh, on the inside. I’m not doing it now.

Name: Kree (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Kree is an alien species originally from planet Hala, but conquered worlds all over their own galaxy becoming a giant empire. At some point they built the super computer Supreme Intelligence, which ended up becoming a ruler that they workship as a god. Kree give a great value to technology, which they have evolved leaps and bounds since their creation, because of constant wars with other races specially the Skrulls their military power increases the most. Power is also greatly valued among the race which meant making their military ranks based on individual power. At some point Kree reached a stagnation point in their evolution which the Supreme intelligence tried to fix by exploding a Nega-Bomb killing 90% of the Kree.

Name: Kubanochoerus
Summary: Kubanochoerus is an extinct genus of large, long-legged suid. It lived in Africa, Europe, and Asia during the Miocene epoch, about 15.9 to 7.3 million years ago. The largest species, Kubanochoerus gigas, could reach notable sizes, standing about 1 meter at the shoulder and attaining masses of 500 kg.[1] Its most distinctive feature is the presence of horns on their skulls, with two small brow horns, and males possessing long horns on the top of their heads often likened to unicorn horns. It is thought the males used their horns for jousting in intraspecific combat. The adults would have likely inhabited open woodlands and savannas during its time.[2]

Name: Kukri (Real World)
Summary: The kukri, also known as the khukuri (Nepali: खुकुरी khukuri) is a knife, originating from the Indian subcontinent, associated with the Nepali speaking Gurkhas of Nepal. The knife has an inwardly curved blade, similar to a machete, used as both a tool and as a weapon in Nepal and India. Traditionally, it was, and in many cases still is, the basic utility knife of the Gurkha. It is a characteristic weapon of the Nepalese Army, the Royal Gurkha Rifles of the British Army, the Assam Rifles, the Assam Regiment, the Garhwal Rifles, the Gorkha regiments of the Indian Army, and of all Gurkha regiments throughout the world, so much so that some English-speakers refer to the weapon as a "Gurkha blade" or "Gurkha knife". The khukuri often appears in Nepalese and Indian Gorkha heraldry and is used in many traditional rituals such as wedding ceremonies. The kukri, khukri, and kukkri spellings are of Indian origin, the original Nepali form being khukuri.

Name: Lamia (Merlin: BBC Series)
Summary: In their wars with the Ancient Kings, the High Priestesses of the Old Religion combined the blood of a girl with the blood of a serpent's, creating fearsome and powerful monsters who were able to kill with a single touch. The Lamia were extremely powerful, but proved to be more dangerous than their creators imagined: the High Priestesses lost control of them and the Lamia continued to kill, unwilling to stop.

Name: Leader Dynamics Series T2 MK5
Summary: The Leader T2 MK5 Series firearms were chambered for the 5.56×45mm NATO cartridge and manufactured by Leader Dynamics of Smithfield, NSW, Australia (1978-1982/1983). The Leader was the brainchild of British weapons designer Charles St. George. It was originally a contender for a 5.56 mm Australian military service rifle to replace the then-issued Lithgow L1A1 SLR and Colt M16A1 rifles. What was unique about this endeavor was that Australia had never designed or manufactured its own commercial gas-operated semi-automatic rifle. The rifle was abandoned when the Steyr AUG was adopted for use by the Australian military.

Name: Leapfrog (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Eugene Paul Patilio, Jr. AKA Leapfrog is a frog-themed vigilante. After attaining a custom-made superhero suit from Luke Jacobson, he started his attempt at crimefighting. However, his lack of skill and responsibility lead to him receiving injuries. He blamed Jacobson and attempted to sue him in court with Jennifer Walters as his attorney, only for Matt Murdock to easily defend his claims, as well as prove that Eugene was at fault for not following the suit's instructions. Frustrated with the verdict, Patilio kidnapped Jacobson and forced him to make him a new suit for his vigilante career.

Name: Leopard
Summary: The leopard is a big cat that lives in Africa, Asia, and the Caucasus. Unlike the other big cats that it lives with, the lion, and the cheetah, who rely on either using their strength to overpower animals and using their speed to chase animals respectively. The leopard relies on ambushing their prey from trees.

Name: Liger
Summary: The Liger is the result of a Male lion mating with a female tiger. It is notable for being the largest big cat in the world even surpassing Lions and Tigers.

Name: Lineage (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Gordo Nobili was head of what was left of the once respected Nobili Crime Family. Along with his two sons Carmen Nobili and Joey Nobili, they were a down on their luck mob family whose credibility was tarnished, as all their attempts ended up in failings. As the Terrigen Bomb was set off by Black Bolt, the Nobili went through a transformation into newly manifested Inhumans, and Gordon lost his sons soon after, owing to the trio's frightening new appearances.

Name: Lion (Real World)
Summary: The Lion is a famous big cat native to Asia and Africa. It is likely one of the most recognizable animals to humans. On their own, they hunt zebras, impalas, and wildebeest, on packs they have shown to hunt buffaloes (Males have been shown to do this on their own with extreme effort), hippopotamuses and rhinos.
