They mostly hunt in packs due to most of their prey being larger and heavier than them. They used to live all around Africa and in some parts of the Middle East, some lions even managed to reach Europe thousands of years ago. They currently live in the center and south of Africa. The Asiatic Lion can be found in the Gir forest in India.

Name: Logan Walker
Summary: Sergeant Logan Walker is the youngest member of the Ghosts and the only one that does not speak. During the events of Ghosts stories, he's 16 years old. He is then 25 years old during the events of the other missions. Him and the other Ghosts are sent to find and capture Gabriel Rorke. At the end of the mission The Ghost Killer, he is captured by Rorke and is sent to an unknown location where he suffers the same torture Rorke had endured.

Name: Long rifle
Summary: The long rifle, also known as longrifle, Kentucky rifle, Pennsylvania rifle, or American longrifle, was one of the first commonly used rifles for hunting and warfare. It is characterized by an unusually long barrel, a development in American rifles that was uncommon in European rifles of the same period.

Name: Long Sky (Hero)
Summary: Long Sky was an accomplished spearman that was told to be one of the three assassins to murder the King of the Qin dynasty during the Warring States Period before he could name himself emperor. He is played by Donnie Yen in the movie "Hero".

Name: Luo-Lang (Sword of the Stranger)
Summary: Luo-Lang (羅狼?)The blonde-haired, blue-eyed, European second-in-command of the Ming group and an extremely skilled swordsman. Luo-Lang is driven by a thirst for great power and craves finding an equally strong opponent to fight so that he may improve his skills.

Name: Lynx (Real World)
Summary: A lynx is any of the four existing species (the Canada lynx, Iberian lynx, Eurasian lynx, or bobcat) within the medium-sized wild cat genus Lynx. The lynx is usually solitary, although a small group of lynx may travel and hunt together occasionally. Mating takes place in the late winter and once a year the female gives birth to between one and four kittens.

Name: Lystrosaurus
Summary: Lystrosaurus is an extinct genus of therapsid, a group of ancient reptiles that includes some of the closest relatives to mammals. Lystrosaurus lived during the Permian and early Triassic periods, approximately 255 to 250 million years ago. It was a herbivorous animal with a beak-like snout and a robust body. Lystrosaurus is notable for its resilience and ability to survive the Permian-Triassic mass extinction event, which wiped out many other species. Its fossils have been found on various continents, and it is often considered an example of a "disaster taxon" that rebounded after a major extinction event, helping to repopulate the Earth with life.

Name: M.O.D.O.K.
Summary: The Advanced Idea Mechanics technician George Tarleton was selected as the victim of a cruel experiment aimed at creating a living computer of unprecedented might. However, instead of becoming the subservient tool his creators craved for, the newly-born M.O.D.O.K. rebelled and imposed himself as the new head of the organization. As twisted in the body as in the mind, he committed himself to further A.I.M.'s ideals according to his personal ambitions.

Name: M.O.D.O.K. Superior
Summary: M.O.D.O.K. Superior is the result of a failsafe program carried out by the original M.O.D.O.K. to ensure the continuation of his legacy in the eventuality of his downfall against the coalition of the Hulks. He is one of many cloned brains, but unlike the others he has been allowed to retain his free will. Upon surfacing as the new M.O.D.O.K., he vowed to not follow the faulty tracks of his predecessor and live his life free of any artificial conditioning, a trait most exemplified in his much more human and varied characterization.

Name: M1 Abrams
Summary: The M1 Abrams is a third-generation main battle tank designed by General Dynamics Land Systems (formerly Chrysler Defense) and named after General Creighton Abrams. Conceived for modern armored ground warfare, it introduced several innovative features, including a multifuel turbine engine, advanced composite armor, a computer fire control system, separate ammunition storage in a blow-out compartment, and NBC protection.

Name: M1 Garand
Summary: The M1 Garand is a .30 caliber semi-automatic rifle that was the standard U.S. service rifle during World War II and the Korean War and also saw limited service during the Vietnam War. Most M1 rifles were issued to U.S. forces, though many hundreds of thousands were also provided as foreign aid to American allies. The Garand is still used by drill teams and military honor guards. It is also widely used by civilians for hunting, target shooting, and as a military collectible.

Name: M134 Minigun
Summary: The M134 Minigun is a 7.62mm six-barreled machine gun with a high firing rate (2,000 to 6,000 shots per minute) employing rotating Gatling-style drums with an external power supply. In popular culture, the term "Minigun" has been applied to any Gatling weapon using rifle gauge and receiving power externally, although the term is sometimes used to refer to firearm cadence and similar configurations, disregarding the power source and caliber. Specifically, minigun refers to a specific weapon model, originally produced by General Electric.

Name: M14 Rifle
Summary: The M14 rifle, officially the United States Rifle, Caliber 7.62 mm, M14, is an American select-fire rifle that fires 7.62×51mm NATO (.308 in) ammunition. It became the standard-issued rifle for the U.S. military in 1959, replacing the M1 Garand rifle in the U.S. Army by 1961 and the U.S. Marine Corps by 1965 until being replaced by the M16 rifle beginning in 1964. The M14 was used by U.S. Army, Navy, and Marine Corps for basic and advanced individual training (AIT) from the mid-1960s to the early 1970s.

Name: M1911
Summary: The M1911, also known as the Colt 1911 or the Colt Government, is a single-action, recoil-operated semi-automatic pistol chambered for the .45 ACP cartridge. The pistol's formal U.S. military designation as of 1940 was Automatic Pistol, Caliber .45, M1911 for the original model adopted in March 1911, and Automatic Pistol, Caliber .45, M1911A1 for the improved M1911A1 model which entered service in 1926. The designation changed to Pistol, Caliber .45, Automatic, M1911A1 in the Vietnam War era.

Name: M4 Carbine
Summary: The M4 carbine is a shorter and lighter variant of the M16A2 assault rifle. The M4 is a 5.56×45mm NATO, air-cooled, direct impingement gas-operated, magazine-fed carbine. It has a 14.5 in (370 mm) barrel and a telescoping stock.

Name: M4 Sherman
Summary: The M4 Sherman, officially “Medium Tank, M4” and named by the British for the American Civil War General William Tecumseh Sherman, was the most widely used medium tank by the United States and Western Allies in World War II. It is one of the few really iconic fighting vehicles of the Allies during World War Two. The M4 Sherman proved to be reliable, relatively cheap to produce, and available in great numbers. Thousands were distributed through the Lend-Lease program to the British Commonwealth and Soviet Union.

Name: M60 machine gun
Summary: The M60, officially the United States Machine Gun, Caliber 7.62 mm, M60, is a family of American general-purpose machine guns firing 7.62×51mm NATO cartridges from a disintegrating belt of M13 links. There are several types of ammunition approved for use in the M60, including ball, tracer, and armor-piercing rounds.

Name: M67 Fragmentation Grenade
Summary: The M67 Fragmentation Grenade is a handheld explosive used by the United States military. The M67 is a further development of the M33 grenade, itself a replacement for the M26-series grenades used during the Korean and Vietnam Wars, and the older Mk 2 "pineapple" grenade used since World War II. The M67 hand grenade has an effective casualty radius of about 15 meters. It is considered a "defensive fragmentation grenade" because it must be used from the safety of cover, since the range of its fragments is greater than a human can throw the grenade.

Name: MAC-10
Summary: The Military Armament Corporation Model 10, officially abbreviated as "M10" or "M-10", and more commonly known as the MAC-10, is a compact, blowback operated machine pistol/submachine gun that was developed by Gordon Ingram in 1964. It is chambered in either .45 ACP or 9mm. A two-stage suppressor by Sionics was designed for the MAC-10, which not only abates the noise created but makes it easier to control on full automatic (although it also makes the gun far less compact and concealable).

Name: Machete
Summary: A machete is a blade used as a substitute of an axe.

Name: Magnum Research BFR
Summary: The Magnum Research BFR is a single-action revolver manufactured by Magnum Research. It is made from stainless steel and is manufactured in a variety of heavy calibers, such as .500 S&W Magnum, including some traditional rifle cartridges, such as the .30-30 and .45-70/.450 Marlin. The name "BFR" officially is an acronym for "Big Frame Revolver", although other meanings, such as "Big Finest Revolver", or "Biggest, Finest Revolver," and even in some cases, "Big Fucking Revolver" have also been used.

Name: Mahi-Mahi
Summary: The mahi-mahi (Coryphaena hippurus), also known as the common dolphinfish, is a medium-sized fish native to tropical and subtropical waters worldwide. They are highly sought after by fishermen, both as sport fish and for food.

Name: Makarov Pistol
Summary: The Makarov pistol or PM (Russian: Пистолет Макарова, Pistolet Makarova, literally Makarov's Pistol) is a Russian semi-automatic pistol. Under the project leadership of Nikolay Fyodorovich Makarov, it became the Soviet Union's standard military and police side arm in 1951, and still sees widespread use in modern-day Russia.

Name: Mandrill
Summary: The Mandrill (Mandrillus sphinx) is a primate and the world's largest monkeys. Mandrills mostly live in tropical rainforest and in very large groups and have an omnivorous diet consisting mostly of fruits and insects.

Name: Maned Wolf
Summary: The maned wolf (Chrysocyon brachyurus) is a large canine of South America. The maned wolf, known locally as Lobo Guará, is found in Argentina, Brazil, Bolivia, Peru, Paraguay and is almost extinct in Uruguay. Its markings resemble those of foxes, but it is neither a fox nor a wolf.[1]

Name: Manjimutt
Summary: Manjimutt is a E rank Yo-Kai of the Eerie tribe. Depicted in the anime to have once been a human salary worker who lose his job and got himself killed while in a drunken stupor, he is one of the only few Yo-Kai that can be seen without the Yo-Kai Watch which in turn gets him in trouble with the police.

Name: Mantis (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Drax: You are horrifying to look at. But that's a good thing. Mantis: Oh? Drax: When you're ugly and someone loves you, you know they love you for who you are. Beautiful people never know how to trust. Mantis: Well, then I am certainly grateful to be ugly!

Name: Marduk Kurios
Summary: Satan, true name Marduk Kurios, though he has gone by many others, is a powerful demon who rules over the underworld as one of the Lords of Hell. While it is unknown whether he truly is the angel cast down from Heaven by God long ago or just the most powerful of the many pretenders to that name, what is certain is that Satan has often attempted to gather more power and conquer the entirety of both Hell and Earth, sometimes seeing his attempts foiled by his two half-human children, Daimon and Satana Hellstrom.

Name: Maria Hill (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Maria Hill is the former second in command of S.H.I.E.L.D. She's highly skilled and capable of combat, often being one of the first to notice and/or react to large distasters. She is known for aiding the Avengers behind the scenes.

Name: Mauser C96
Summary: The Mauser C96 (Construktion 96) is a semi-automatic pistol that was originally produced by German arms manufacturer Mauser from 1896 to 1937. Unlicensed copies of the gun were also manufactured in Spain and China in the first half of the 20th century.

Name: Messerschmitt Bf 109
Summary: The Messerschmitt Bf 109 G-6/R3 is a single-engined, single-seat monoplane fighter and a German World War II fighter aircraft that was the backbone of the Luftwaffe's fighter force. The Bf 109 first saw operational service in 1937 during the Spanish Civil War and was still in service at the dawn of the jet age at the end of World War II in 1945. It was one of the most advanced fighters of the era, including such features as all-metal monocoque construction, a closed canopy, and retractable landing gear. It was powered by a liquid-cooled, inverted-V12 aero engine. From the end of 1941, the Bf 109 was steadily being supplemented by the Focke-Wulf Fw 190. It was commonly called the Me 109, most often by Allied aircrew and among the German aces, even though this was not the official German designation.

Name: Mikoyan-Gurevich MiG-21
Summary: The Mikoyan-Gurevich MiG-21 (Russian: Микоян и Гуревич МиГ-21; NATO reporting name: Fishbed) is a supersonic jet fighter and interceptor aircraft, designed by the Mikoyan-Gurevich Design Bureau in the Soviet Union.

Name: Miss America (Golden Age Marvel Comics)
Summary: Madeline Joyce was a young niece of millionaire James Bennett, who financing an electrical project that would grant the person "the strength of a thousand men". Madeline stumbled upon this experiment accidentally one night, granting her super strength, flight as well as X-ray vision. Naming herself Miss America, Madeline soared through the skies as the premiere heroine protecting the East Coast from Nazi threats for her homeland.

Name: Mission Sub-1
Summary: The Mission SUB-1 was designed to be the most accurate crossbow on the market. The name "SUB-1" means "under 1 inch".

Name: Moa (Real World)
Summary: The Moa were nine species in six genera of extinct flightless birds that were endemic to the island of New Zealand. They were the dominant herbivores in New Zealand's bush, their population reaching a peak of 58,000 around 1280, with their only natural predator being the Haast's eagle. They were driven to extinction due to overhunting by the Polynesian (Maori) settlers around 1440 ± 20 years.

Name: Moff Gideon
Summary: Moff Gideon was an officer of the Imperial Security Bureau who contributed to the Great Purge against the Mandalorians until graduating to the rank of marshal and then Moff. After the Galactic Empire's downfall, he evaded execution for war crimes and became the leader of a powerful imperial fragment army while seeking a force-sensitive baby of the same species as Jedi master Yoda, causing him and his forces to conflict with The Mandalorian and his allies.

Name: Mongrel Dog
Summary: The mongrel dog is called the pedigree dog, whose ancestry is generally unknown, which has characteristics of two or more types of breeds, or is descended from populations of wild or street dogs.

Name: Monica Rambeau (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Monica Rambeau was a New Orleans Harbor Patrol officer until one day she destroyed an energy disruptor device which caused her to gain full control of the electromagnetic spectrum. She joined the Avengers under the name Captain Marvel and later became their leader.

Name: Montana (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Jackson Brice was born in Bozeman, Montana. Along with Fancy Dan and the original Ox, he was a founding member of the Enforcers. He has great proficiency with the lariat. As a member of the Enforcers, he first came into conflict with Spider-Man when they were employed by the Big Man and have been fighting the wall-crawler ever since.

Name: Moon Knight (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Steven Grant: Oh, God. I'm gonna die, I'm gonna die. Marc Spector: Steven, LOOK at me... you're not gonna die. Let me save us.

Name: Moose
Summary: Moose are the largest members of the deer family. Unlike most deer, which would run from danger, moose are aggressive beasts who stand their ground against predators. The moose has few predators, most notably wolves and tigers. Adult bulls typically weigh from 380 to 700 kg while adult cows weigh from 200 to 490 kg. The largest of all the races of moose is the Alaskan subspecies.

Name: Mosin-Nagant
Summary: The 3-line rifle M1891 (Russian: трёхлинейная винтовка образца 1891 года, tryokhlineynaya vintovka obraztsa 1891 goda), colloquially known in the West as Mosin–Nagant and in Russia as Mosin's rifle (Russian: винтовка Мосина, ISO 9: vintovka Mosina) is a 5-shot bolt-action, internal magazine-fed, military rifle developed from 1882 to 1891, and was in widespread use amongst the Russian Empire, the Soviet Union and various other nations across several major conflicts in the history of the world. It is by far one of the most widespread rifles as well, with over 37 million units having been made since its inception in 1891, and despite its age, it still sees intense conflict in the modern age. It primarily makes use of the 7.62x54mm cartridge, though it is also compatible with the following cartridges: 7.62×53mmR (Finnish variants only), 7.92×57mm Mauser (Polish variants and German captures) and 8×50mmR Mannlicher (Austrian captures).

Name: Mossberg 500
Summary: Mossberg 500 is a series of pump action shotguns manufactured by O.F. Mossberg & Sons.

Name: Mother Night (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Susan Scarbo, along with her brother Melvin Scarbo, was a stage hypnotist who turned to crime under the name Suprema. Using their hypnotic ability, they began to recruit an army. Scarbo began taking over criminal gangs in New York by subverting their leaders' minds.

Name: Motormouth (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Young orphan Harley Davis was abandoned on the streets of London's East End, and rough-housed her way to the cusp of adulthood, at which point her foul-mouthed demeanor had earned her the nickname Motormouth.

Name: Muskox
Summary: The muskox (Ovibos moschatus) are one of the largest bovids native to the arctic circle.[1][2] Being a stocky, compact, large herbivorous animal visually similar to bison in appearance, albeit more closely related to goats and sheep.[1]

Name: Mysterio (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Quentin Beck is a former Stark Industries employee who sought out to replace the late Tony Stark as Earth's next defender. Seeking to solidify a reputation for himself, Beck feigned several Elemental attacks across the world with the use of his drones, seeking attention and recognition from the public as a new superhero/supervillain named Mysterio.

Name: Nanashi (Sword of the Stranger)
Summary: A ronin haunted by his terrible past, he has sworn to keep his sword sheathed. However, upon meeting Kotaro, he finds himself re-evaluating his life. While traveling with the young Kotaro, Nanashi finds himself acting as a bodyguard for the boy. This in turn leads to his prolonged struggle against the Ming warriors, particularly Luo-Lang.

Name: Narwhal (Real World)
Summary: The Narwhal (Monodon Monoceros) is a species of toothed whale native to the Arctic. It is the only member of the genus Monodon and one of two living representatives of the family Monodontidae. The narwhal has a similar build to the closely related beluga whale, with which it overlaps in range and can interbreed. It is a stocky cetacean with a relatively blunt snout, a large melon, and a shallow ridge in place of a dorsal fin. Males of this species have a large 1.5–3.0 m (4 ft 11 in – 9 ft 10 in) long tusk, which is a left protruded canine thought to serve as a weapon or as a tool for feeding, attracting mates or sensing water salinity. Specially adapted slow-twitch muscles, along with the jointed neck vertebrae and shallow dorsal ridge allow for easy movement through the Arctic environment, where the narwhal spends extended periods at great depths.

Name: Neanderthal
Summary: The Neanderthals were an early species (or sub-species) of humans that lived during the Middle and Low Pleistocene in Europe and West-Asia until as recently as ~40,000 years ago.

Name: New Nambu M60
Summary: The "New Nambu" M60 is a double-action revolver chambered in .38 Special based upon Smith & Wesson-style designs, used mostly by law enforcement in Japan. It was designed and produced by Shin-Chuō Industries, later merged with Minebea. Approximately 133,400 have been produced since 1961.

Name: Nile Crocodile
Summary: The Nile crocodile (Crocodylus niloticus) is an African crocodile, the largest freshwater predator in Africa, and may be considered the second-largest extant reptile and crocodilian in the world, after the saltwater crocodile (Crocodylus porosus). The Nile crocodile is quite widespread throughout sub-Saharan Africa, occurring mostly in the central, eastern, and southern regions of the continent, and lives in different types of aquatic environments such as lakes, rivers, and marshlands. Although capable of living in saline environments, this species is rarely found in saltwater, but occasionally inhabits deltas and brackish lakes. The range of this species once stretched northward throughout the Nile, as far north as the Nile delta. On average, the adult male Nile crocodile is between 3.5 and 5 m (11.5 and 16.4 ft) in length and weighs 225 to 750 kg (500 to 1,650 lb). However, specimens exceeding 6.1 m (20 ft) in length and weighing up to 1,090 kg (2,400 lb) have been recorded. Sexual dimorphism is prevalent, and females are usually about 30% smaller than males. They have thick, scaly, heavily armored skin.

Name: Nothosaurus
Summary: Nothosaurus is a genus of sauropterygian reptiles that lived around 240–210 million years ago, throughout the mid to late Triassic. Its name comes from the Greek words νόθος (nothos), which means "illegitimate," and σαῦρος (sauros), which means "lizard." It was widespread throughout the world, with 12 species having been found in North Africa, Europe, and China, inhabiting the ancient Tethys Ocean and its shores. These sea reptiles were likely related to plesiosaurs and pliosaurs that would later emerge, with Nothosaur-like reptiles thought to have given rise to them.

Name: Nuke (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Will Simpson was a former patient of IGH who, having struggled to maintain control, left the program and became a police officer from the New York City Police Department. Due to an encounter with Kilgrave, Simpson became obsessed with tracking down and killing him, teaming up with Jessica Jones and Trish Walker in order to complete this goal. However, when Simpson began to believe that Jones' methods weren’t effective, he returned back to the Military Program that he left years before in order to obtain some more of their Combat Enhancers which would increase his strength, while also turning him into a crazed murderer.

Name: Ocean Sunfish
Summary: The Ocean Sunfish, also known as the Mola mola, is a large species of fish that inhabits tropical and temperate waters worldwide. They are the largest bony fish in the world, and have a maximum recorded length and weight of 4.2 meters from fin to fin and 2300 kilograms, respectively. Ocean sunfish typically feed on small fish, jellyfish, and crustaceans, and can jump three meters out of the water in order to rid themselves of parasites.

Name: Ocelot
Summary: The ocelot (Leopardus pardalis) is a medium-sized spotted wild cat that is native to the southwestern United States, Mexico, Central and South America, and to the Caribbean islands of Trinidad and Margarita. It prefers areas close to water sources with dense vegetation cover and high prey availability.

Name: Odobenocetops
Summary: Odobenocetops is a genus tooth whale, belonging to the same group as dolphins or porpoises. Despite this, it bares many similarities to walruses, notably in its distinctive asymmetrical tusks; the type species O. peruvianus had tusk lengths of 45–55 cm and 20 cm for its right and left respectively,[1] while O. leptodon had a left tusk at a longer 25 cm and a right tusk at 1.35 meters[2] The function of these tusks is unknown, but due to their brittle nature, they would have not been used for jousting, and rather they likely served other intraspecific purposes. Along with walruses, they also display convergent evolution with narwhals, with their skulls being entirely toothless aside from these tusks.

Name: Olive Baboon
Summary: The Olive Baboon is a large omnivorous monkey found in Africa. It is considered a pest in many countries and hated for raiding houses and stealing food.

Name: Ornitholestes
Summary: Ornitholestes is a genus of small theropod dinosaur from the late Jurassic, living on the supercontinent of Laurasia in modern day North America around 154 million years ago. Its name means "bird robber," with the second part of the name in honor of Adam Hermann, preparator for the American Museum of Natural History. Ornitholestes could reach around 2 meters long,[1] or longer at around 2.08 meters. More recent studies indicate it likely had feathers, much like other coelurosaurs, theropods more closely related to modern birds than carnosaurs like Allosaurus.

Name: Ornithomimus
Summary: Ornithomimus is a genus of Therapod living in what will one day be North America. Ornithomimus is a genus of ornithomimid dinosaurs from the Late Cretaceous Period of what is now North America. Ornithomimus from fossil evidence indicates it was covered in feathers, equipped with a small toothless beak that may indicate an omnivorous diet.

Name: Ostrich
Summary: Ostriches are known as the fastest and largest birds on earth, weighing in at 145 kilograms, reaching up to 2.7 meters tall, and possessing powerful legs allowing them to run at speeds of up to 43 mph (19,22272 m/s). Also coming naturally from being so big, their eyes can reach 2 inches in diameter and their eggs weigh 12 times as much as chicken eggs.

Name: Otter (Real World)
Summary: Otters are carnivorous mammals in the subfamily Lutrinae. The 13 extant otter species are all semiaquatic, aquatic or marine, with diets based on fish and invertebrates. Lutrinae is a branch of the Mustelidae family, which also includes weasels, badgers, honey badgers, martens, minks, polecats, and wolverines.

Name: Pachycephalosaurus
Summary: Pachycephalosaurus is a genus of dinosaur from the Cretaceus Period, known for their dome-shaped skulls. Cranial lesions in some specimens indicate that pachycephalosaurus may have exhibited headbutting behavior. It would've reached 4.5 meters long and weighed around 450 kg.

Name: Pancor Jackhammer
Summary: The Pancor Corporation Jackhammer was a 12-gauge, blow-forward gas-operated bullpup automatic shotgun designed in 1984 and patented in 1987. Only three working prototypes of the Jackhammer were built. Nonetheless, its distinctive aesthetics and futuristic design have made it a prop in action films, television programs, and video games.

Name: Panzer VI Tiger
Summary: The Panzer VI Tiger or Tiger I was a German heavy tank of World War II deployed from 1942 in Africa and Europe usually in independent heavy tank battalions.

Name: Patriofelis
Summary: Patriofelis ("Father of cats") is a genus of large carnivorous placental mammal that lived in North America during the Early to Middle Eocene epoch, about 50.3–46.2 million years ago. Despite its superficial resemblance to big cats, it is not a feline, nor is it a carnivoran either; instead, it was an oxyaenid, a group of carnivorous mammals that were apex predators during the Eocene. Unlike carnivorans, it had stiffened vertebrae similar to armadillos or pangolins, thought to be a tradeoff of flexibility for larger size.[1] In life, they would have been terrestrial apex predators adapted for hunting on the forest floor.[2]

Name: Peregrine Falcon
Summary: The Peregrine Falcon is a species of falcon that is renowned for its hunting ability and characteristic diving maneuver.

Name: Pfeifer Zeliska Revolver
Summary: The .600 Nitro Express Pfeifer Zeliska revolver is an Austrian single-action revolver produced by Pfeifer firearms. Except for the giant 28mm 1859 Remington revolver, the Zeliska may be the largest handgun in the world (arguably, the giant 1859 should not actually qualify as a handgun, given its size and mass), weighing in at over 6 kilograms (13.23 lb) and having a length of 55 centimeters (22 in); the cylinder section alone weighs 2.041 kilograms (4.5 lb).

Name: Pig (Real World)
Summary: Domestic pigs are pigs raised for meat, leather, or simply as pets. Pigs that either escape or get released into the wild are known as feral pigs and regain their fur. These feral pigs are considered an invasive species and are often targeted by hunters.

Name: PKP Pecheneg machine gun
Summary: The PKP Pecheneg (Pulemyot Kalashnikova Pekhotny "Pecheneg", Russian: Печенег) is a Russian 7.62×54mmR general-purpose machine gun. It is a further development and modification of the PK machine gun. It is said to be more accurate than all its predecessors due to a heavier, non-removable, forced-air-cooling barrel with radial cooling ribs and a handle which eliminates the haze effect from hot gases and keeps the barrel cooler, making the weapon more reliable. Furthermore, the weapon is capable of having a telescopic sight or other sights mounted on it, which increases its accuracy and effective range.

Name: Placerias
Summary: Placerias (meaning 'broad body') is an extinct genus of dicynodonts that lived during the Carnian to the Norian age of the Triassic Period (230–220 million years ago). Placerias belongs to a group of dicynodonts called Kannemeyeriiformes, which was the last known group of dicynodonts before the taxon became extinct at the end of the Triassic.

Name: Plateosaurus
Summary: Plateosaurus is a genus of plateosaurid sauropodomorph dinosaur, informally referred to as "prosauropods." Much debate had been gone through as to creature's posture, more recent studies indicating that it stood bipedally with an erect gait. It had teeth similar to later sauropods and omnivorous animals such as iguanas,[1] and may have had a small portion of their diet comprised of carrion and small animals to supplement a predominantly herbivorous diet.[2] It lived throughout present day northern and central Europe around 227-204 million years ago, during the late Triassic, and was among the first large herbivorous dinosaurs.

Name: Po-2
Summary: The Polikarpov Po-2 is a two-seated general purpose biplane developed by the Polikarpov Design Bureau primarily used as a training aircraft, but could serve other purposes such as ground attack and reconnaissance. Making its first flight in June 24, 1927, and entering service in 1929, it has the longest production run out of any Soviet aircraft, with over 20000 built.

Name: Polar Bear
Summary: The polar bear (Ursus maritimus) is a hypercarnivorous bear whose native range lies largely within the Arctic Circle,[1][2][3] encompassing the Arctic Ocean, its surrounding seas and surrounding land masses.[4][5] It is a large bear, approximately the same size as the omnivorous Kodiak bear (Ursus arctos middendorffi). A boar (adult male) weighs around 350–700 kg (772–1,543 lb), while a sow (adult female) is about half that size. Although it is the sister species of the brown bear, it has evolved to occupy a narrower ecological niche, with many body characteristics adapted for cold temperatures,[6] for moving across snow, ice and open water, and for hunting seals,[6][7][8] which make up most of its diet.[3] Although most polar bears are born on land,[9] they spend most of their time on the sea ice.[10] Their scientific name means "maritime bear" and derives from this fact.[2] Polar bears hunt their preferred food of seals from the edge of sea ice,[3] often living off fat reserves when no sea ice is present. Because of their dependence on the sea ice, polar bears are classified as marine mammals.[2]

Name: Postosuchus
Summary: Postosuchus is a large terrestrial Pseudosuchian of the group Rauisuchidae. It's name mean "Crocodile of Post" named for the city in Texas near where it was found and the suffix "suchus" derived from the Greek word soukhos (σοῦχος), which means "crocodile." It was one of the apex predators of North America during the late Triassic. The two known species are Postosuchus kirkpatricki and Postosuchus alisonae.

Name: Preston Ramirez
Summary: Preston Ramirez is the main antagonist of Preston’s Hourglass, a 2023 mascot horror game by Dreadful Studios. The story follows a team of archaeologists exploring the Prestonian Catacombs, where they uncover an ancient time-manipulating artifact—“Preston’s Hourglass”. Activating it awakens Preston, an eldritch time demon who kills the entire team except one survivor. To escape, the survivor must collect eight spell pieces to seal Preston again. The game’s lore reveals Preston was once a scientist obsessed with time experiments, which caused widespread destruction in the 1970s. His obsession ruined his life and turned him into the monster buried beneath Prestonia, losing his wife in the process.

Name: Prince Xizor
Summary: Xizor is a prominent antagonist in the Star Wars expanded universe. He was a Falleen Prince of House Sizhran and the leader of the powerful criminal organization Black Sun. Xizor was a ruthless competitor and charismatic public figure in high society with his headquarters in the city-planet Coruscant. Close to the Imperial Palace, but less splendid, was Xizor's Palace: his home outside Falleen. Following the Battle of Hoth, Xizor was considered one of the most influential beings in the galaxy, on par with Emperor Palpatine and Darth Vader, due to his exceptional wealth and influence through his criminal activities.

Name: Proterosuchus
Summary: Proterosuchus is a genus of proterosuchid Archosauriform, a group distantly related to true archosaurs such as dinosaurs, pterosaurs, and crocodilians. This moderately sized reptile lived 252-250 million years ago amid the hostile conditions of the early Triassic,[1] following the Permian-Triassic Extinction, in the semi-arid environment that is present day South Africa.[2] It is known that it was a carnivore, but it is debated as to what lifestyle it led; it may have been either fully terrestrial or semi-aquatic, ambushing prey similar to modern crocodiles.

Name: Pteranodon
Summary: The pteranodon is a flying reptile that lived in the Cretaceous. They have a wingspan of 18 feet, some specimens have wingspans of 7 meters.

Name: Pug
Summary: The pug is a breed of dog which was originally bred in China for companionship. It is a friendly dog, and is great for families and children.

Name: Puma Concolor
Summary: The cougar (Puma concolor), also commonly known as the puma, mountain lion, panther or catamount, is a large felid of the subfamily Felinae native to the Americas. Its range, from the Canadian Yukon to the southern Andes of South America, is the widest of any large wild terrestrial mammal in the Western Hemisphere. An adaptable, generalist species, the cougar is found in most American habitat types. It is the biggest cat in North America, and the second-heaviest cat in the New World after the jaguar. Secretive and largely solitary by nature, the cougar is properly considered both nocturnal and crepuscular, although daytime sightings do occur. The cougar is more closely related to smaller felines, including the domestic cat (subfamily Felinae), than to any species of subfamily Pantherinae, of which only the jaguar is native to the Americas.

Name: Rabbit (Real World)
Summary: Rabbits are a common prey animal and, in places where they are introduced, one of the most infamous invasive species on Earth. Rabbits are herbivorous, although a source from 1910 has stated that rabbits have eaten snails. Rabbits were raised as pets, livestock animals, and laboratory animals. European rabbits, which are the most common rabbit, weigh from 1.2 to 2 kg.

Name: Red Fox
Summary: Red Fox (Vulpes vulpes), also called common fox, is the largest of the true foxes. Being present across the entire Northern Hemisphere including most of North America, Europe and Asia, plus parts of North Africa. Apart from its large size, the red fox is distinguished from other fox species by its ability to adapt quickly to new environments and has the largest natural distribution of any land mammal except human beings.

Name: Red Panda
Summary: The red panda (Ailurus fulgens), also known as the lesser panda, is a small mammal native to the eastern Himalayas and southwestern China. The red panda's place on the evolutionary tree has been debated, but modern genetic evidence places it in close affinity with raccoons, weasels, and skunks. It is not closely related to the giant panda, which is a bear, though both possess elongated wrist bones or "false thumbs" used for grasping bamboo.

Name: Remington ACR
Summary: The Remington ACR (Adaptive Combat Rifle) is a modular assault rifle designed by Magpul Industries of Austin, Texas, and known as the Masada.

Name: Remington Model 870
Summary: The Remington Model 870 is a pump-action shotgun manufactured by Remington Arms Company, LLC. It is one of the most well-known shotguns in the world, widely used by the public for shooting sports, hunting and self-defense, as well as by numerous law enforcement and military organizations worldwide.

Name: Riddler (Post-Crisis)
Summary: One of the Dark Knight's most infamous villains, Edward Nygma enjoys flaunting his intellectual superiority by conducting crimes and leaving clues for Batman to piece together. While this habit constantly leads to the aptly named Riddler failing in his criminal endeavors, his puzzle-problem actually stems not only from his own narcissism and ego, but also from a deep-seeded psychological compulsion. Because of this, the Riddler often finds himself a resident of Arkham Asylum following his inevitable capture.

Name: Rika Furude
Key: '''Piece Rika''' | '''Higher Layer/World of Gods/Sea of Fragments Rika and Frederica'''
Summary: nan

Name: Ripsaw (light tank)
Summary: The Ripsaw is a developmental unmanned light tank designed and built by Howe & Howe Technologies for evaluation by the United States Army. The Howe brothers started the Ripsaw as a small family project in 2000, and introduced it at a Dallas vehicle show in 2001.

Name: Risque (Marvel Comics)
Summary: After her Cuban father, and Seminole mother divorced when she was twelve, Gloria Muñoz moved out with her mother and lived with her until she was 16. Having discovered her mutant powers, she left to live on her own and spent some time in Miami. During this time, Sledge helped her out of some trouble, and she promised to aid him in the future, a favor which was eventually repaid when she was tasked with bringing him the mutant Warpath.

Name: Sai (Weapon)
Summary: The Sai is a traditional weapon of Okinawa.

Name: Sako TRG sniper rifle
Summary: The Sako TRG is a bolt-action sniper rifle line designed and manufactured by the Finnish firearms manufacturer, SAKO of Riihimäki. It is used by many units and armies around the world. The sniper rifles are normally fitted with muzzle brakes to reduce recoil, jump, and flash. The Sako factory TRG muzzle brakes vent sideways and are detachable. Generally, TRGs are outfitted with variable telescopic sights for operators demanding more flexibility to shoot at varying ranges, or when a wide field of view is required. Besides its military role, it is increasingly used by hunters and civilian long-range shooting enthusiasts.

Name: Saltwater Crocodile
Summary: The Saltwater Crocodile is the largest of all living reptiles, as well as the largest terrestrial and riparian predator in the world.

Name: Sawn-Off Shotgun
Summary: Sawn-Off Shotgun A sawed-off shotgun (US, CAN) also called a sawn-off shotgun (UK, IRL, AU, NZ) and a short-barreled shotgun (SBS) (U.S. legislative terminology), is a type of shotgun with a shorter gun barrel—typically under 18 inches—and often a shortened or absent stock. Despite the colloquial term, barrels do not, strictly speaking, have to be shortened with a saw. Barrels can be manufactured at shorter lengths as an alternative to traditional, longer barrels. This makes them easier to transport due to their smaller profile and lighter weight. The design also makes the weapon easy to maneuver in cramped spaces, a feature sought by military close quarters combat units, law enforcement SWAT team users, and home defense purposes. As a result of the shorter barrel length, any sawed-off shotgun with a magazine tube will have its capacity reduced.

Name: Scarlet Witch (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Wanda: You took everything from me! Thanos: I don't even know who you are. Wanda: You will.

Name: Scissors
Summary: Scissors are tools used for cutting objects. They rely on 2 blades with a wedge in the middle, and use at least 2 fingers to get through the handle of itself to use it. Designs and uses vary from cutting thin materials like cloth and paper to cutting through chicken bone. The word shears are used to describe tools of the same kind, but larger.[1]

Name: Scutosaurus
Summary: Scutosaurus is a genus of pareiasaur parareptiles, the name of which means "shield lizard." This herbivorous anapsid reptile was among the first large terrestrial animals, reaching well over one ton. It differed from other reptiles in that it had its legs under its body to support its mass.[1] It lived in arid and semi-arid plains across European Russia during the late Permian,[2] around 259.1–251.9 million years ago. Among many other creatures, it would perish during the Permian-Triassic Extinction event.

Name: Serval
Summary: The serval (Leptailurus serval) is a wild cat native to Africa. It is widespread in sub-Saharan countries, except rainforest regions. Across its range, it occurs in protected areas, and hunting it is either prohibited or regulated in range countries.

Name: Shiba Inu
Summary: The Shiba Inu is a small, Japanese dog, originally bred for hunting small game. They nearly went extinct during World War 2, but since then, they have become very popular as a pet. Shibas are also the number one companion dog in Japan.

Name: SIG Sauer P226
Summary: The SIG Sauer P226 is a full-sized, service-type pistol made by SIG Sauer. This model is sold with a choice of four chambers to choose from: the 9×19mm Parabellum, .40 S&W, .357 SIG, or .22 Long Rifle. It has essentially the same basic design as the SIG Sauer P220, but is developed to use higher capacity, double stack magazines in place of the single stack magazines of the P220. The P226 itself has spawned further sub-variants; the P228 and P229 are both compact versions of the double stack P226 design. The SIG Sauer P226 and its variants are in service with numerous law enforcement and military organizations worldwide

Name: SIG Sauer P320
Summary: The SIG Sauer P320 is a modular semi-automatic pistol made by SIG Sauer, Inc. of Exeter, New Hampshire, and SIG Sauer GmbH of Eckernförde, Germany. It is a further development of the SIG Sauer P250, utilizing a striker-fired mechanism in lieu of a double action only hammer system. The P320 can be chambered in 9×19mm Parabellum, .357 SIG, .40 S&W and .45 ACP, and can be easily converted from one caliber to another—a change from .357 SIG to .40 S&W requires only a barrel change; a change between 9mm to .357 SIG or .40 S&W and vice versa are accomplished using a caliber exchange kit.

Name: Sledgehammer
Summary: A sledgehammer is a construction tool used to break stuff like rocks, walls, ceilings and ground tiles.

Name: Sloth Bear
Summary: Sloth Bears are a species of bear that coexists alongside sun bears and Asian black bears. They are known for their aggressive behavior, which developed as a defensive reaction against larger animals such as tigers, rhinos, and elephants. The sloth bear is species that most often attacks humans going off raw numbers, which can be attributed to large amounts of people surrounding bear reserves.

Name: Slyde (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Jalome Beacher was a talented chemical engineer working in the design and development laboratory of Beemont Manufacturing who created a chemical coating that, when applied to any object, eliminated all friction between that object and surfaces. Beacher was about to unveil his discovery when Beemont was purchased by a larger organization and a man named Rockwall was placed in charge. The research and development lab was closed and Beacher was fired. He decided to build his own company founded on the non-stick chemical, but discovered that no bank would lend the money needed without a sizeable down payment.

Name: Smith & Wesson 5906
Summary: The Smith & Wesson 5906 is a pistol manufactured starting in 1988 by Smith & Wesson.

Name: Smith & Wesson Model 29
Summary: The Smith & Wesson Model 29 is a six-shot, double-action revolver chambered for the .44 Special and .44 Magnum cartridge and manufactured by the United States company Smith & Wesson.

Name: Smith & Wesson Model 500
Summary: The S&W Model 500 is a double action revolver, its bullets are .50 caliber, making this gun one of the most powerful production handguns around.

Name: Smith & Wesson Model 686
Summary: The Smith & Wesson Model 686 is a six- or seven-shot double-action revolver manufactured by Smith & Wesson and chambered for the .357 Magnum cartridge. It will chamber and fire .38 Special cartridges, as the .357 Magnum was developed from the .38 Special. The Magnum case is slightly longer to prevent such rounds from being chambered and fired in handguns chambered for the .38 Special. The 686 has been available with 2-1/2 in. (64 mm); 3 in.(76mm); 4 in. (102 mm); 5 in. (127 mm); 6 in. (153 mm); and 8-3/8 in. (214 mm) barrel lengths as standard models and other barrel lengths either by special order from S&W's Performance Center custom shop, or acquired from or built by after-market gunsmiths. The Performance Center made a limited number of 686 in .38 Super for competitive shooters.

Name: Snow Leopard
Summary: The snow leopard (Panthera uncia), also known as the ounce[1], is a felid in the genus Panthera native to the mountain ranges of Central and South Asia. Unlike common leopards, the snow leopard's fur is whitish to grey with black spots on head and neck, with larger rosettes on the back, flanks and bushy tail. The snow leopard is also widely used in heraldry and as an emblem in Central Asia.

Name: Spear
Summary: A spear is a pole weapon consisting of a long shaft and a pointed tip. Spears are one of earliest known weapon in the world, a distinction it shares with axes, knives, and clubs. Spear heads are made out of various materials such as bone, obsidian, flint, iron, steel, and bronze.

Name: Spectacled Bear
Summary: The spectacled bear is also known as the Andean bear, mainly because the spectacled bear is native to the Andes mountain range of South America. The spectacled bears territory ranges from northwest Colombia, into Argentina, Venezuela and Brazil. The spectacled bear generally feeds on berries and shoots found both on ground level and in the trees. The spectacled bear also feeds on insects and small mammals and reptiles, and occasionally cattle.

Name: Spitfire
Summary: The Spitfire is a single seat, single engine fighter aircraft designed and manufactured by Supersubmarine before World War II, making its first flight in 1936 and entering service a year before the start of the second world war. The fighter was built in many different variants, and more Spitfires have been produced than any other British aircraft, with over 20000 built by the end of the war.

Name: Spock
Summary: Tier: 9-C physically. At least 8-C with phaser. | 9-B. At least 8-C with phaser.

Name: Spotted Hyena
Summary: The spotted hyena (Crocuta crocuta), also known as the laughing hyena, is a carnivorous animal found in all of Sub-Saharan Africa. The species is, however, experiencing declines outside of protected areas due to habitat loss and poaching. The species may have originated in Asia, and once ranged throughout Europe for at least one million years until the end of the Late Pleistocene.

Name: Starro (Pre-Flashpoint)
Summary: Starro the Conqueror is the name of a species-wide hive mind of alien starfish-like creatures gifted with powerful psychic powers, who have earned their moniker via the galaxy-wide empire they have assembled by taking over the bodies and minds of all the inhabitants of the countless planets they have taken over. Starro has also attempted to take over the Earth on multiple occasions, only being barely repelled by the combined might of the Justice League time and time again, though they were never able to kill it due to the countless body Starro's conscience resides in.

Name: Stature (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Cassandra Eleanor "Cassie" Lang is the daughter of Scott Lang and Maggie Lang. Fascinated by the Quantum Realm, Lang invented the Quantum Satellite, which resulted in her, her father and the van Dyne family being shrunken deep into the Realm, being trapped in Axia. Wishing to aid the Freedom Fighters in spite of Ant-Man's denies, she donned the Stature suit to battle against Kang's Empire. However, Stature and Ant-Man were captured by M.O.D.O.K. and questioned by Kang the Conqueror, who used her life as leverage for Ant-Man to retrieve the Multiversal Engine Core. Once she escaped, Stature made a speech across Axia to motivate the oppressed citizens to revolve against Kang and his army before facing off M.O.D.O.K. and returning home with her family.

Name: Stature (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Daughter of Scott Lang, Cassie Lang developed growth powers as a result of repeated exposure to Pym Particles, which were interlinked to her emotional state. After the demise of her father, Cassie carried his legacy by becoming a member of the Young Avengers under the alias of Stature.

Name: Steyr AUG
Summary: The Steyr AUG (Armee-Universal-Gewehr — "universal army rifle") is an Austrian 5.56×45mm NATO bullpup assault rifle, designed in the 1960s by Steyr-Daimler-Puch and now manufactured by Steyr Mannlicher GmbH & Co KG.

Name: StG 44
Summary: The StG 44 (abbreviation of Sturmgewehr 44, "assault rifle 44") is a German selective-fire rifle developed during World War II. It is also known as the MP 43 and MP 44 (Maschinenpistole 43 and 44).

Name: Sun Bear
Summary: The Sun Bear is the smallest bear species in the world. They are rare and elusive animals found in the forests of Asia. Due to this fact, much is not known about the Sun Bear, at least in comparison to other bear species. They are known for their small size, long tongues, and their dog-like faces.

Name: Tapir
Summary: Tapir is a large, herbivorous mammal, similar in shape to a pig, with a short, prehensile nose trunk. Tapirs inhabit jungle and forest regions of South America, Central America, and Southeast Asia.

Name: Tawky Tawny (Rebirth)
Summary: Tawky Tawny was a resident of the Wildlands, a dimension populated by anthropomorphic animals which had eradicated humans long ago, and believed tigers to be traitors under the orders of the Mayor. Tawny himself however was a gentlemanly pacifist, and despite being jailed, decides to rescue his fellow inmates Darla Dudley and Freddy Freeman, escaping to Philadelphia. There, he became the caretaker for the Shazam Family.

Name: Thalattosuchus
Summary: Thalatosuchus is a genus of thalattosuchian, a group of crocodylomorphs adapted to an oceanic lifestyle. It's name quite literally means "sea crocodile," and has the single species Thalattosuchus supercilious. Well adapted to swimming in the oceans, it had a streamlined body and a tailfin,[1] while also lacking the armor-like osteoderms of many other crocodyliforms.[2] It lived in oceans during the mid to late Jurassic, with fossils found in England, Germany, and France.

Name: The Hood (Marvel Comics)
Summary: The man who will become known as the Hood was originally a simple thug from the suburbs of New York City. His life was made of small crimes committed alongside his cousin John King, a relationship with a girl waiting their child and the preoccupations for his mentally-ill mother. Parker Robbins always aspired to be a supervillain and his career began when a would-be robbery turned into an encounter with a demon clad in red. Parker shot the monster down and looted it of its hood and boots. Upon realizing that these items bore magical powers, Parker finally saw the potential to satisfy his ambitions and began his journey to reach the top of the city's underworld.

Name: The Mummy (Betrayal)
Summary: The Mummy is one of the many monsters present in the House on the Hill, and the titular antagonist of the haunt scenario 'The Mummy Walks'. In it, the Mummy works with the Traitor in order to reunite the Mummy with the reincarnation of his lone lost love, who has reincarnated in the form of the Girl.

Name: The Penguin (Post-Crisis)
Summary: Oswald Cobblepot, a.k.a The Penguin is a fictional DC supervillain and one of Batman's most notorious adversaries. Oswald was bullied as a child for his bird-like appearance and the fact that he was always forced to carry an umbrella due to an overprotective and insistent mother. Cobblepot, born into a life of wealth, grew to become one of Gotham's most collected and eccentric villains, many times leading a charming public life as the forerunner of the Iceberg Lounge, a high society nightclub.

Name: The Wolf (Bullet Train)
Summary: The Wolf is a minor antagonist in the 2022 action comedy film Bullet Train, based on Kōtarō Isaka's 2010 dark comedic thriller novel Maria Beetle.

Name: Thompson Submachine Gun
Summary: The Thompson submachine gun is an American submachine gun invented by John T. Thompson in 1918 which became infamous during the Prohibition era, being a signature weapon of various crime syndicates in the United States. It was a common sight in the media of the time, being used by both law enforcement officers and criminals. The Thompson submachine gun was also known informally as the "Tommy Gun", "Annihilator", "Chicago Typewriter", "Chicago Piano", "Chicago Style", "Chicago Organ Grinder", "Trench Broom", "Trench Sweeper", "The Chopper", and simply "The Thompson".

Name: Thorvin Twinbeard
Summary: A gifted engineer, Thorvin Twinbeard is a dwarf who is working for Xanathar's Guild, making Xanathar a contraption which will pulverize those he petrifies.

Name: Thylacine
Summary: The Thylacine is a carnivorous marsupial that once lived throughout Australia, New Guinea, and Tasmania. It is nicknamed the Tasmania wolf due to its canine like features that arose from convergent evolution; the Tasmanian tiger nickname comes from its striped appearance. These creatures first emerged around 1.77 million to 780,000 years ago, during the early Pleistocene.[1] Around 3,200 years ago, the Thylacine population on mainland Australia would have died off, the major causes thought to be human activity and the introduction of dingoes.[2] Populations would remain prevalent on the island of Tasmania up until the early 20th century, before extermination by farmers and bounty hunters, along with habitat loss, competition from wild dogs, and disease would devastate them (with possibly already low genetic diversity worsening their chances of survival).[3] The last Thylacine was captured and kept in Hobart Zoo until he died on September 7, 1936.

Name: Tiger (Real World)
Summary: The tiger (Panthera tigris) is a member of the Panthera genus and is the largest living felid around. It is widely recognized due its pattern of dark vertical stripes on reddish-orange fur with a lighter underside.[1]

Name: Tokarev TT-33 Pistol
Summary: The TT-33, commonly known as the Tokarev pistol, is an out-of-production Soviet semi-automatic pistol, designed in the early 1930s by Fedor Tokarev as a service pistol to replace the Nagant M1895 revolver that had been in use since the last days of the Russian Empire, though the Tokarev pistol ended up being used in conjunction with, rather than replacing the M1895 revolver. It would continue to serve until 1952, when it was officially replaced by the Makarov Pistol.

Name: Trejo Pistol
Summary: The Trejo pistol (pronounced tray-ho), and its sub-variant, the Trejo machine pistol, is a Mexican pistol or machine pistol. The machine pistol sub-variant has the distinction of being the smallest fully-automatic weapon ever produced.

Name: Twitch
Summary: Tier: At least 9-C, possibly 7-B with Chem Crossbow

Name: Type 97 Chi-Ha
Summary: The Type 97 Chi-Ha Medium Tank (九七式中戦車 チハ Kyūnana-shiki chū-sensha Chi-ha) was a medium tank used by the Imperial Japanese Army during the Second Sino-Japanese War, the Battles of Khalkhin Gol against the Soviet Union, and the Second World War. It was the most widely produced Japanese medium tank of World War II.

Name: Type 99 Light Machine Gun
Summary: The Type 99 light machine gun (九九式軽機関銃, Kyūkyū-shiki Kei-kikanjū) was a light machine gun used by the Imperial Japanese Army in World War II.

Name: Ultimax 100
Summary: The Ultimax 100 is a Singapore-made 5.56mm light machine gun, developed by the Chartered Industries of Singapore (CIS, now ST Kinetics) by a team of engineers under the guidance of American firearms designer L. James Sullivan. The weapon is extremely accurate due to its constant-recoil operating system. It is considered one of the most lightweight machine guns in the world.

Name: Utahraptor
Summary: Utahraptor is a theropod dinosaur from the Cretaceous Period. It is currently the largest Dromaeosaur ever discovered at 2-2.5 meters tall, 7 meters long and weighing at least 500 kg.

Name: Uzi Submachine Gun
Summary: The Uzi (Hebrew: עוזי‎, officially cased as UZI) is a family of Israeli open-bolt, blowback-operated submachine guns. The Uzi was one of the first weapons to use a telescoping bolt design which allows the magazine to be housed in the pistol grip for a shorter weapon.

Name: Velociraptor (Real World)
Summary: Velociraptor is a genus of small theropods living in the Cretaceous Period. They are one of the most popular species of Dinosaurs, even though their appearance is vastly misunderstood.

Name: Vulture (Marvel Comics)
Summary: The Vulture is a supervillain and one of Spider-Man's most die-hard enemies. Before becoming a criminal, Adrian Toomes was a capable engineer who had made a breakthrough when he invented a new kind of magnetic harness. It was an overwhelming joy after a life of hardships. But everything crumbled when he learned his business partner had been stealing a large sum of his profits before finally ousting him from the company they founded. Adrian was sad and angry, so he used what he knew to make a flying suit and become the Vulture.

Name: Walrus
Summary: The Walrus is a large marine mammal related to seals living around the Arctic regions of Earth. Large individuals weigh in at 2,000 kg, but most male Pacific walruses weigh in at around 800-1700 kg. Atlantic males, on the other hand, weigh on average 900 kg.

Name: Walther PPK
Summary: The Walther PPK pistol is a blowback-operated semi-automatic pistol made famous by the James Bond movies. Today, PPK pistols are manufactured by Carl Walther GmbH Sportwaffen in Germany or under license from Walther in France and the United States. These pistols feature an exposed hammer, a double-action trigger mechanism, a single-column magazine, and a fixed barrel which also acts as the guide rod for the gun's single recoil spring.

Name: Water Buffalo
Summary: The Water Buffalo (Bubalus bubalis) are the second largest bovidae. Wild water buffalo live in wildlife preserves in southeast asia, while their domestic counterparts are very common.[1]

Name: West Indian Manatee
Summary: The West Indian manatee (Trichechus manatus), also known as the sea cow, is a large species of marine mammal native to the Caribbean and the east coast of the United States. It is herbivorous, and primarily grazes on seagrass.

Name: Whip (Real World)
Summary: This page contains or depicts disturbing and/or graphic content that some may find upsetting, and that is only intended for mature audiences. Please proceed with caution.

Name: Wild Boar
Summary: The wild boar (Sus scrofa), also known as the wild swine, Eurasian wild pig, or simply wild pig, is native to much of Eurasia, North Africa, and the Greater Sunda Islands. Human intervention has spread its distribution further, making the species one of the widest-ranging mammals in the world. It has become an invasive species in part of its introduced range.

Name: Wildcat
Summary: The wildcat is a species complex comprising two small wild cat species: the European wildcat and the African wildcat. The European wildcat (Felis silvestris) are natives of continental Europe, Scotland, Turkey and the Caucasus. It inhabits forests from the Iberian Peninsula, Italy, Central and Eastern Europe to the Caucasus. While the African wildcat (Felis lybica) is a small wildcat species native to Africa, West and Central Asia up to Rajasthan in India and Xinjiang in China. Unlike their descendants, wildcats are wild and can't be tamed.

Name: Will Graham (Film)
Summary: Ex-FBI agent Will Graham is an expert investigator who quit the Bureau after almost losing his life in the process of capturing the elusive Dr. Lecter. After a series of particularly grisly murders, Graham soon realizes that the best way to catch this killer, known as the Tooth Fairy, is to find a way to get inside the killer's mind. For Graham, that means confronting his past and facing his former nemesis, the now-incarcerated Lecter.

Name: Winchester Rifle
Summary: The Winchester Model 1894 is a level-actor repeating rifle. It was used by both the United States and France during the many Indian Wars, World War I and World War II. It is widely known as "The Gun That Won the Wild West".

Name: Wolverine (Real World)
Summary: The Wolverine is a mustelid found in North America, some parts in the North of Europe and most of the north of Russia.

Name: Wolverine-Pool (Deadpool: Samurai)
Summary: Wolverine-Pool is a variant of Deadpool who appeared in Cable & Deadpool #46 and Deadpool Kills Deadpool #3. He was sent to kill Deadpool in Deadpool Samurai second season.

Name: Wong (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Doctor Strange: Is that everyone? Wong: You wanted more!?

Name: Zan (Post-Rebirth)
Summary: Zan is the twin brother of Jayna and a member of the Wonder Twins. Originally from planet Exxor, Zan is the grandchild of an infamous figure in Exxorian history and was sent to Earth to avoid harassment. Despite his many shortcomings, Zan is an incredibly friendly, kind-hearted, and sociable person who values love and friendship above everything.

Name: Zebra (Real World)
Summary: Zebras are African equines that are distinguished by they black-and-white stripes. There are three known species of zebras, with the most common being the Burchell's zebra (also known as the plains zebra). Due to their wild temperament, it is ill-advised to saddle up or attempt to ride a zebra.

Name: .950 JDJ Rifle
Summary: The .950 JDJ Rifle is known as being "the largest sporting rifle made." It was developed by J.D. Jones, president of SSK Industries. It normally would be classified as a "destructive device" due to the rifle's groove diameter of .950 inches. However SSK was given a "Sporting Use Exception" in order to deregulate the rifle. Due to its heavy weight and massive recoil, it can only be shot from a bench rest or heavy bipod, which even then runs risk of injury. As such, the gun is more of a novelty than any combat or sporting weapon.

Name: 16”/50 caliber Mark 7 gun
Summary: The 16"/50 (40.6 cm) caliber gun Mark 7 was the main armament of the Iowa-class battleships. This was possibly the best battleship gun ever put into service. Originally intended to fire the relatively light 2240 pound (1016 kg) AP Mark 5 projectile, the shell handling system for these guns was redesigned to use the "super-heavy" 2700 pound (1224.7 kg) AP Mark 8 before any of the USS Iowa class (BB-61) battleships were laid down.

Name: 3”/50 caliber Mark 22 gun
Summary: The 3″/50 (7.62 cm) caliber gun Mark 22 was a US naval gun of a simpler construction than the previous class of 3" guns, and successive versions were improved designs. This gun was widely used up to the 1930s, but were then gradually replaced on larger ships by 5"/25 (12.7 cm) single mountings and later by Bofors 40mm guns in twin and quad mountings. During World War II, this weapon was extensively used on smaller warships such as destroyer escorts, submarines and auxiliaries along with many merchant ships, with about 14,000 guns being produced between 1940 and 1945.

Name: 5”/38 caliber Mark 12 gun
Summary: The 5"/38 (12.7 cm) caliber gun Mark 12 was a US naval gun. It was unquestionably the finest dual purpose gun of World War II. Originally designed to arm new destroyers being built in the 1930s, the 5"/38 (12.7 cm) wound up being used on nearly every major US warship built between 1934 and 1945 and was still being used on new construction as late as the 1960s.

Name: 6"/47 caliber Mark 16 gun
Summary: The 6"/47 (15.2 cm) caliber gun Mark 16 was a feature of many US Navy light cruisers during World War II. These guns were used to arm the Brooklyn- and Cleveland-class light cruisers, the latter being the most numerous class of cruisers ever built. The 6"/47 caliber gun was one of several weapons developed by the United States Navy in the 1930s to fire "super-heavy" armor-piercing projectiles, thus increasing warships' destructive power while complying with the limits on bore diameter set by the London Naval Treaty. Compared with the previous 6"/53 caliber guns, the 6"/47 Mark 16 fired a 59 kilogram (130 pounds) projectile instead of a 48 kilogram (105 pounds) projectile. These new projectiles had almost double the penetration performance when compared against the older 6"/53 (15.2 cm) AP projectiles used for the Omaha class (CL-4) light cruisers.

Name: 8”/55 caliber Mark 15 gun
Summary: The 8"/55 (20.8 cm) caliber gun Mark 15 formed the main batteries of United States Navy Baltimore, Oregon City, Boston, and Albanyclass cruisers. This gun is similar in construction to the previous 8"/55 caliber Mark 12, and related to the 8"/55 caliber Mark 9, 10, 11, 13, and 14 (but of much lighter construction) which served as the main guns for several earlier heavy cruisers as well as the self-defense guns on the only two Lexington-class aircraft carrier, the first operational aircraft carriers in the US Navy, until their removal at Pearl Harbor in 1942 to be used as coastal artillery It was superseded by the improved 8"/55RF caliber gun Mark 16 by 1948, which were only installed on three Des Moines-class heavy cruisers.

Name: A-10 Thunderbolt II
Summary: The A-10 Thunderbolt II is a close-air support and forward air control aircraft designed to tank hits from high-explosive and armor piercing rounds up to at least 23 mm. It was designed by the company known as Fairchild Republic. It is primarily used by the US military.

Name: Aarakocra
Summary: Aarakocra are denizens of the Elemental Plane of Air that serve the Wind Dukes of Aaqa. They stand as constantly vigilant scouts and warriors protecting against both invaders of the Elemental Plane of Earth (most notably against gargoyles) and worshippers of Elemental Evil (in their case, Yan-C-Bin). They are duty-bound to eternally attempt to restore the Wind Dukes of Aaqa to their previous state of power as vaati, which was lost when fighting against the Queen of Chaos, the former ruler of the Abyss.

Name: Aardvark
Summary: The aardvark (Orycteropus afer) is a nocturnal mammal native to sub-Saharan Africa. It uses its powerful claws to dig burrows, and primarily feeds on termites and other insects. Despite its appearance, it is most closely related to the elephant.

Name: Aaron Covenant
Summary: Aaron Covenant is the second child of the Covenant family and the twin brother of Bethany Covenant. He was tortured and killed by his twin sister but resurrected as a revenant form and as a ghost. He is one of the bosses in Clive Barker's Undying.

Name: Aaron Tide (The Boxer)
Summary: Aaron Tide was the previous World Heavyweight Boxing Champion, and seemingly the strongest boxer in history. Having never lost a single match due to his monstrous strength and reason defying power, Aaron lived a life of luxury and fame.

Name: Aballin
Summary: While inert one can't tell an Aballin apart from a pool of water, also they often contain treasure from previous victims inside them. But if one is foolish enough to try and drink from the supposed pool of water or take the tressure in it they'll meet an unpleasent surpise of the Aballin morphing into a gelatinous form which tries to suffocate the person.

Name: Aboleth
Summary: Aboleths are ancient, primordial entities that have existed since the creation of the multiverse, supposedly being spontaneously created when the empty void of reality was touched by an alien entity in the Far Realm, allowing the Aboleths to bleed into the multiverse. They formed an empire throughout the void through sheer psionic might, being the gods before gods came to be- though the dawn of these creatures, the gods as we know them, caused the Abolethic Sovereignity to crumble.

Name: Abrian
Summary: Strongly resembling an ostrich, the Abrian is a flightless bird which are common in the lower planes and are smart enough to talk the common language of Abyssal. In combat Abrians prefer to fight in groups due to their sonic abilities being enhanced by numbers and if they lose the numeric advantage in combat they're not above escaping the fight.

Name: Abyssal Chicken
Summary: The Abyssal Chicken is a small fiend which to an extent resembles a chicken, mainly sharing the fact that both creatures can only fly at short bursts of time but unlike a regular chicken this creature is a carnivore and is a rather murderous beast.

Name: AC-130
Summary: The AC-130 is a gunship modification of the C-130 Hercules and is a heavily armed, long endurance ground attack aircraft which carries a variety of various ground attack weapons ranging from machine guns to howitzers. Due to its large profile, low operating altitude, and slow speed making it an easy target, it usually flies close air support missions at night. During an attack, the gunship performs a pylon run, flying a circle around the target.

Name: Accablement & Abattement
Summary: Accablement & Abattement is a pair of sadnesses in the game In Stars and Time, acting as the game’s second floor boss in Dormont’s House of Change.

Name: Accuracy International Arctic Warfare
Summary: The Accuracy International Arctic Warfare rifle is a bolt-action sniper rifle designed and manufactured by the British company Accuracy International. It has proved popular as a civilian, police, and military rifle since its introduction in the 1980s. The rifles have some features that improve performance in very cold conditions (which gave the rifle its name), without impairing operation in less extreme conditions. Arctic Warfare rifles are generally fitted with a Schmidt & Bender PM II telescopic sight with fixed or variable magnification. Variable telescopic sights can be used if the operator wants more flexibility to shoot at varying ranges, or when a wide field of view is required. Accuracy International actively promotes fitting the German-made Schmidt & Bender MILITARY MK II product line as sighting components on their rifles, which is rare for a rifle manufacturer. The German and Russian forces preferred a telescopic sight made by Zeiss over Accuracy International's recommendation.

Name: Achaierai
Summary: Achaierai were evil birds of prey, enormous and flightless, that roamed the pleanes of existence that dedicated themselves wholly to war and despair. Achaierai are known throughout the planes for their vicious nature, lethal torture effects, and their powerful poison.

Name: Acrocanthosaurus (Real World)
Summary: Acrocanthosaurus is a genus of theropod dinosaur that lived in what is now North America.

Name: Addled Frog
Summary: The Addled Frog is a swamp-dwelling creature found in the wetlands surrounding the lair of Auntie Ethel, and is apparently corrupted by her presence. If spoken to by someone who can communicate with animals, its dialogue is unfocused and confused, and can become outright hostile if engaged with for too long. Yet, when Ethel's presence has been cleansed, the frog regains clarity and offers a reward to whomever may have destroyed the hag (or, at least, forced her from her home).

Name: AeroVeedramon
Summary: A small, blue-colored, Dragon Digimon child. Although it is small and powerless, it has the potential to evolve to every Dragon Digimon. For that reason, it is a Digimon that is considered exceedingly valuable by tamers and researchers of Dragon Digimon. It is cherished due to its personality of friendliness and overflowing curiosity, characteristic of Baby Digimon. Just like other Baby Digimon, it spits acidic bubbles to attack, but as usual, their power is nonexistent.

Name: African Buffalo
Summary: nan

Name: African Wild Dog (Real World)
Summary: The African wild dog (Lycaon pictus), also called the painted wolf or Cape hunting dog, is a canine native to sub-Saharan Africa. It is the largest indigenous canine in Africa, and the only extant member of the genus Lycaon, which is distinguished from Canis by dentition highly specialised for a hypercarnivorous diet, and a lack of dewclaws.

Name: Agatha (Pokémon)
Summary: Agatha (キクコ Kikuko) is a member of the Kanto Elite 4. She is the third member as well as the oldest. She specializes in Ghost-types and other menacing looking pokemon.

Name: Agatha Harkness (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Agatha Harkness is a witch who was a member of the Salem Witch Coven, and daughter to its leader, Evanora Harkness. After being put on trial for execution in 1693 for practicing dark magic and betraying her coven, Agatha killed her clan and her mother through the use of her dark magic, after they attempted to execute her for her crimes. Agatha absorbed their magic in the process and took the brooch off of her mother's rotten corpse before flying off. Hundreds of years later in the modern day, Agatha resurfaced and took on the name 'Agnes' and entered the town of Westview, New Jersey to investigate the odd Pocket Reality created by Wanda Maximoff, encasing the town. Agatha then meets Wanda herself and observes her under the suspicion that Wanda may be the Scarlet Witch, a powerful mythical being referenced in the Darkhold, desiring to take her chaotic powers for herself.

Name: AH-64 Apache
Summary: The Boeing AH-64 Apache is an American twin-turboshaft attack helicopter with a tailwheel-type landing gear arrangement and a tandem cockpit for a crew of two. It features a nose-mounted sensor suite for target acquisition and night vision systems. It is armed with a 30 mm (1.18 in) M230 chain gun carried between the main landing gear, under the aircraft's forward fuselage, and four hard points mounted on stub-wing pylons for carrying armament and stores, typically a mixture of AGM-114 Hellfire missiles and Hydra 70 rocket pods. The AH-64 has a large amount of systems redundancy to improve combat survivability.

Name: Air Gun
Summary: Air guns, also known as air rifles, are guns that make use of diabolo-shaped pellets or spherical pellets called "BBs." They represent the oldest pneumatic technology, dating back to 1580. Air guns are used for hunting, pest control, recreational shooting (also known as plinking), and competitive sports such as the Olympics.

Name: AK-12
Summary: The AK-12 is a Russian assault rifle chambered in 5.45×39mm respectively. It is designed and manufactured by Kalashnikov Concern (formerly Izhmash). It is one of the modern derivatives of the Russian AK-Pattern series of assault rifles.

Name: AK-15
Summary: The AK-15 is a Russian assault rifles chambered in 7.62×39mm respectively. It is designed and manufactured by Kalashnikov Concern (formerly Izhmash). It is one of the modern derivatives of the Russian AK-Pattern series of assault rifles.

Name: AK-308
Summary: The AK-308 is a battle rifle under development in 2018 upon request of non-Russian potential clients. It is based on the AK-103 and AK-12, chambered for 7.62×51mm NATO/.308 Winchester. The basic Kalashnikov assault rifle design intended for intermediate cartridges has been stretched and strengthened to handle the extra bolt thrust produced by full-power ammunition. It features a 415 mm (16.3 in) long barrel, has a weight of 4.1 to 4.3 kg (9.04 to 9.48 lb) with an empty box magazine and has a 20 or 30-round magazine capacity. In addition, the AK-308 uses a diopter sight line. It has the ability to attach accessories also used by the AK-12. The overall length of the rifle measures between 880 to 945 mm (34.6 to 37.2 in).

Name: AK-47
Summary: The AK-47, officially known as the Avtomat Kalashnikova (Russian: Автома́т Кала́шникова, tr. Avtomát Kaláshnikova, lit. Kalashnikov's Automatic Rifle; also known as the Kalashnikov and AK), is a gas-operated, 7.62×39mm assault rifle, developed in the Soviet Union by Mikhail Kalashnikov. It is the originating firearm of the Kalashnikov rifle (or "AK") family.

Name: AK-74
Summary: The AK-74 (Russian: Автомат Калашникова образца 1974 года or "Kalashnikov automatic rifle model 1974") is an assault rifle developed in the early 1970s by Russian designer Mikhail Kalashnikov as the replacement for the earlier AKM (itself a refined version of the AK-47). It uses a smaller 5.45×39mm cartridge, replacing the 7.62×39mm chambering of earlier Kalashnikov-pattern weapons.

Name: Akagi (5 Ronin)
Summary: Ronin Akagi returns home from war to find his house burnt to ashes, and his wife and seven year old son dead at the hands of the Daimyo. Vowing revenge, he endlessly stalks the soldiers of Daimyo to slaughter them mercilessly, considering himself already dead.

Name: AKM
Summary: The AKM (Russian: модернизи́рованный Автома́т Кала́шникова, tr. modernizírovanny Avtomát Kaláshnikova, lit. Modernized Kalashnikov Automatic Rifle) is a 7.62mm assault rifle designed by Mikhail Kalashnikov. It is a common modernized variant of the AK-47 rifle developed in the 1940s.

Name: Alabai
Summary: The Central Asian Shepherd Dog, also known as alabai is a livestock guardian dog breed. Traditionally, the breed was used for guarding sheep and goat herds, as well as to protect and for guard duty. This breed presents a robust dog of greater than average size with great strength and power.

Name: Alaghi
Summary: A distant cousin of the Yeti, the Alaghi are a peaceful race of hunters which only kill those they hunt.

Name: Alain (Pokémon)
Summary: Alain is a character appearing in Pokémon the Series: XYZ and the Mega Evolution Acts. He is Ash's main rival in the Kalos region, and the eventual Kalos League Champion after defeating Ash in the finals.

Name: Albertosaurus
Summary: Albertosaurus is a genus of theropod dinosaur that lived during the Late Cretaceous period, approximately 70 to 73 million years ago. It belongs to the same family as Tyrannosaurus rex and is closely related to it. The name "Albertosaurus" translates to "Alberta lizard," as the fossils of this dinosaur were first discovered in Alberta, Canada.

Name: Alcatraz (Crysis)
Summary: James "Alcatraz" Rodriquez is the protagonist in Crysis 2 and the novel Crysis: Legion, which contains additional personal background about him.
