He is a Force Recon Marine originally sent to New York City to (unknowingly) combat the Ceph, before receiving the Crynet Nanosuit 2.0 from Prophet, and ultimately becomes a "reincarnation" of Laurence Barnes, as shown in Crysis 3, having merged with the original's personality and conscious being stored within the nanosuit.

Name: Alder
Summary: Alder (アデク Adeku) is the Champion of the Unova region's Pokémon League in Pokémon Black and White.

Name: Aldo the Cleric
Summary: Aldo the Cleric is one of King of Dragons' selectable characters and protagonists, being one of the heroes that goes against Gildiss, the mighty Red Dragon.

Name: Alfred Pennyworth (Post-Crisis)
Summary: Alfred Pennyworth is the butler of the Wayne Family and the guardian of Bruce Wayne. He served in the military as a field medic, before becoming an actor, retiring, and becoming a butler for the Wayne Family. Following the deaths of Thomas and Martha Wayne, he became Bruce Wayne's legal guardian and raised him to become Batman.

Name: Algomon
Summary: Tier: Unknown | 9-B | High 8-C | 6-C | At least 4-C, Possibly Low 1-C | At least Low 1-C, up to 1-C

Name: Alligator Loki
Summary: Alligator Loki is the pseudonym assigned to a counterpart of Earth-616 Loki, accidentally displaced from his universe during a fight between the latter and Thor. The God of Thunder took him in as his pet, regardless of the protests of the Alligator himself. After an initial quarrel with his "human" version, the two realized they have much in common and became partners in crime. Alligator Loki eventually settled down in the new universe, living in the rivers of Asgard or in Thor and Loki's apartment in Midgard.

Name: Allip
Summary: An Allip is a powerful undead created from the restless spirit of a being that killed itself. It was driven mad in life and now seeks only revenge on the living, attempting to get vengeance on those who pushed them over the edge.

Name: Allister
Key: '''By Himself''' | '''Pokémon Team (Stow-on-Side Stadium)''' | '''Pokémon Team (Champion Cup Finals)''' | '''Pokémon Team (Champion Tournament)'''
Summary: Allister (Japanese: オニオン Onion) is the Gym Leader of Stow-on-Side's Gym, known officially as Stow-on-Side Stadium. He specializes in Ghost-type Pokémon. He gives the Ghost Badge to Trainers who defeat him. He is also an exclusive Gym Leader on Pokémon Shield. In Pokémon Sword, Bea takes his place as Stow-on-Side's Gym Leader instead.

Name: Allosaurus
Summary: Allosaurus is a genus of theropod dinosaur that lived during the Kimmeridgian to early Tithonian stage of the late Jurassic period, from 155 to 150 million years ago, in North America (Morrison Formation), Portugal (Lourinhã Formation), and possibly Tanzania (Tendaguru Formation).

Name: Almiraj
Summary: The Almiraj at a first glance appears simply as a rabbit with the horn of a unicorn, and while that asessment is true they can still be quite dangerous due to their unpredictable nature and their inante teleportation ability which earned them the nickname Blink Rabbit. An even more dangerous variant of the Almiraj is the Psionic one which has a 10% to appear when ever an Almiraj gives birth, this Almiraj has various abilities such as Detonate and Molecular Agitation which makes it a formidable foe.

Name: Altaïr Ibn-La'Ahad
Summary: Altaïr Ibn-La'Ahad (Arabic: الطائر ابن لا أحد‎, The Bird, Son of None; 1165 – 1257) was a Syrian member of the Levantine Brotherhood of Assassins who served as their Mentor from 1191 until his death in 1257. During his tenure as Mentor, through the knowledge of an Apple of Eden, Altaïr made several discoveries and inventions that greatly helped the Order's progression. His leadership saw to the spread of the Assassins' influence throughout the Old World.

Name: Ambulocetus
Summary: Ambulocetus is a genus of semi-aquatic cetacean, the group that would later include fully aquatic whales. Its name comes from the Latin words ambulare, or "walking", and cetus, or "whale." It lived during the Early Eocene from around 48–47 million years ago, on the Indian Subcontinent, inhabiting the mangrove swamps that covered the then tropical environment there,[1] and favored brackish water at river mouths.[2]

Name: Ambush Drake
Summary: The Ambush Drake is a draconic group predator which uses telepathy to communicate with its own kind, and in combat they use stealth tactics alongside their poisonous breath to defeat opponets. Like dragons they have a natural desire to hoard but a group of Ambush Drakes does not have a concept of private ownership and they share all their belongings.

Name: Amelia Voght (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Amelia Voght discovered her powers of transubtantiating matter into vapour at a young age and was ostracized by her parents, like many other mutants. Choosing to embark on a journey far from the judgmental eyes of her past, she pursued a career in nursing and eventually found herself in India. Here, she met Charles Xavier, a fellow American who had lost the use of his legs. Amelia cared for Charles after his injury, and her positive and friendly attitude helped Xavier get over his depression. The two quickly fell in love, and shared an apartment in Mumbai. Eventually discovering that Xavier was a mutant himself, this link strengthened their relationship even more, but over time they both developed different stances on human-mutant interaction. Xavier wanted open co-existence with humans, while Amelia thought it was best for mutants to hide themselves. When Xavier brought Scott Summers to his mansion for training, Amelia left him, telling him that his plans for the X-Men would only lead to a genetic arms race and ultimately doom mutantkind.

Name: American Alligator
Summary: The American Alligator is a large crocodillian reptile native to the Southeastern regions of the United States. They are one of the two extant species of alligator.

Name: American Bison
Summary: American Bison, usually referred to as bison or simply buffalo, are the largest land mammals in North America. They held cultural significance to Native Americans, becoming animals of spiritual importance. The Sioux, for instance, saw the birth of a white buffalo as the return of the White Buffalo Calf Woman, their primary cultural prophet and the bringer of their "Seven Sacred Rites."

Name: American Black Bear
Summary: The American black bear (Ursus americanus) is a medium-sized bear endemic to North America.[1][2][3] It is the continent's smallest and most widely distributed bear species.[2] American black bears are omnivores,[1][2] with their diets varying greatly depending on season and location.[1][2] They typically live in largely forested areas,[1][2] but will leave forests in search of food[2] and are sometimes attracted to human communities due to the immediate availability of food.[1][2] Despite the name, some subspecies can be brown or even blond in coloration.[4][3][5][note 1]

Name: American Pit Bull
Summary: This page contains or depicts disturbing and/or graphic content that some may find upsetting, and that is only intended for mature audiences. Please proceed with caution.

Name: Amidor
Summary: Quick to fall in love and an idealist, Amidor is a 3 foot tall dandelion.

Name: Amphicyon
Summary: Amphicyon was a prehistoric genus of bear-sized carnivorans closely related to canids and ursids.

Name: Amrik Vanthampur
Summary: The middle child and favorite of Thalamra Vanthampur, Amrik Vanthampur is a cunning schemer who plays an important part in his mother's plan to take over Baldur's Gate.

Name: AMT AutoMag II
Summary: The AutoMag II looks extremely different from the original AutoMag, and even uses a different action. The weapon has a stainless steel cutout over the slide, and 18 holes are drilled 90 degrees to the chamber to prevent extraction problems with the .22 WMR bullet in the weapon.

Name: Anabel (Pokémon)
Summary: Anabel is a Frontier Brain from the Battle Frontier in Pokémon Emerald. While that is the end of her role in Emerald, she plays a bigger part in Pokémon Sun and Moon in the post-game, where it is revealed that she was sucked through an Ultra Wormhole into the Sun/Moon universe, where she becomes part of the International Police and their UB Task Force.

Name: Anaconda
Summary: Anaconda or water boas are a group of large snakes of the genus Eunectes. They are found in tropical South America. Four species are currently recognized. All anacondas live in South America east of the Andes. Green anacondas are found in the Brazilian Amazon basin, the Orinoco basin, Colombia, Venezuela, Ecuador, Peru, Bolivia, Trinidad and the Guianas, according to the Jacksonville Zoo, with specimens being able to reach The maximum verified length of an anaconda is 30 feet (9 m), but on average they grow to around 15 feet (4.5 m) for females, and around 9 feet (2.7 m) for males.

Name: Anarky (Post-Crisis)
Summary: A possible child of the Joker and Linda Penman, Lonnie Machin was a prodigal high school student until influence from anarchist philosophy turned him into the aptly-named vigilante Anarky. Though he was taken down by Batman and sent to a juvenile detention center, he soon escaped to become a consistent adversary to both the Batman and the criminals of Gotham City.

Name: Ancient One (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: The Ancient One was the Sorcerer Supreme and leader of the Masters of the Mystical Arts. She taught Kaecilius, Karl Mordo, Wong, and many others in the ways of sorcery. Her unusually long life is fuelled by her energy use from the Dark Dimension, a technique she prohibits others from doing. When Kaecilius challenged the Ancient One's ways and stole a spell from the forbidden Book of Cagliostro, the Ancient One was determined to prevent Kaecilius from summoning Dormammu to the Earth.

Name: Angajuk
Summary: An old sperm whale, Angajuk is a whale granted human like intelligence by a druid. They are over 200 years old and have been serving as underwater transport system for people for many years. On their back there is a boat which is enchanted to create an air bubble when Angajuk goes underwater in order to let those who ride on him to breath underwater.

Name: Angel of Valor
Summary: The Angel of Valor are the weakest and most numerous of the angels that serve the gods, they are used as foot soldiers of their deities. while following the orders of higher ranking angels or even clerics of their gods.

Name: Aniliade
Summary: Aniliade is a Youtuber and the main antagonist in several of Eight Blackey's Indie Horror Games, such as: Aniliade’s Jumpscare Castle and Aniliade's Dungeon of Misfortune, as well as the protagonist of the webcomic series: The Misadventures of Aniliade and Banshee. She also appears as a Cameo in various other games from the same Game Developer. Aniliade is also known as the best friend of Banshee.

Name: Animal Man (Post-Crisis)
Summary: Buddy Baker is the Animal Man, the chosen protector of The Red, the force which connects all animal life. He is both a family man and a super-hero, often struggling to keep balance between the two.

Name: Animated Armor
Summary: Animated Armor is a common occurrence in any Dungeons and Dragons setting, generally being the creation of some mage or other spellcaster. The armor itself is not normally of notable make, and instead, the power is derived from magic imbued in it from its creator, allowing the armor to act and perform simple tasks as if it were alive. Frequently such creations are able to speak simple phrases and demand passwords, making them nominal guards and wardens.

Name: Ankheg
Summary: Ankhegs are enormous burrowing insects that hunt smaller prey via detecting tremors through the ground. Among the earliest monsters added to Dungeons and Dragons, they have persisted through every edition, providing a solid example of an iconic low-level creature. Invariably an Ankheg is larger than a cattle and tends to weigh just under 400 kilos.

Name: Ankylosaurus
Summary: Ankylosaurus is a genus of armored Dinosaur from the Cretaceous period, equipped with armor composed of heavy bone plates and osteoderms, and a heavy club on the end of their tail. It is often considered the archetypal example of the Ankylosauria family.

Name: Annis Hag
Summary: Vast talons, foul with human flesh, there grew In place of hands, and her features livid blue, Glared in her visage; whilst her obscene waist Warm skins of human victims embraced.

Name: Ant-Man (Eric O'Grady)
Summary: Eric O'Grady was a low level S.H.I.E.L.D. agent working in the reconnaissance department of the S.H.I.E.L.D. Helicarrier. Him and his best friend Chris McCarthy were tasked with guarding Dr. Henry Pym's lab by a higher ranking agent, Mitch Carson. When Pym went to leave the lab, Eric and Chris panicked and Eric attacked Pym, knocking him unconscious. Inside the lab, they found the most recent version of Ant-Man's Suit, which Chris put on and promptly activated, shrinking down. Thinking him gone, Eric panicked again and ran off, only to run into each other as a Hydra siege infiltrated the Helicarrier. While trying to find a safe place to hide, Chris was killed, and Eric took the Ant-Man's Suit off his body. Surviving the Helicarrier crash, Eric kept the suit and operated as Ant-Man.

Name: Ant-Man (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Scott Edward Harris Lang is a former professional criminal who was convinced by Hank Pym to take on the mantle of Ant-Man. He fought against Pym's former protégé Darren Cross, who had gone insane while trying to recreate the Pym Particles, leading to Lang defending his friends, family and the world as the Ant-Man.

Name: Ant-Man (Scott Lang)
Summary: Scott Lang was born and raised in Coral Gables, Florida. He later became an electronic engineer and met and married Peggy Rae. Together they had a daughter Cassandra "Cassie" Lang. Although he was an electronics expert he could not support his family doing repair work, so he turned his talents to burglary. Apprehended, he served his prison sentence and was paroled for good behavior. During his time in prison, however, Peggy divorced him. Lang had furthered his studies of electronics while in prison and was soon hired by Stark International to work in its design department.

Name: Anteosaurus
Summary: Anteosaurus is a genus of large carnivorous dinocephalian synapsid, represented by the single species, Anteosaurus magnificus. It lived in the lush and marshy environment that existed in what is present-day South Africa around 265–260 million years ago, during the Capitanian stage of the middle Permian, and likely hunted other large synapsids in its time. It is among the largest non-mammalian carnivorous synapsids, reaching up to 6 meters long and around 600 kg.

Name: Apatosaurus
Summary: Apatosaurus ajax was a species of herbivorous sauropod dinosaur that lived in North America during the Late Jurassic period. It was one of the largest dinosaurs in the world, growing up to 23 meters long.

Name: Apollomon
Summary: Tier: 9-B | High 8-C | 6-C | At least High 6-C | 5-B | 1-C

Name: Aranea
Summary: Aranea were a species of artificial demi-lycanthropes that maintained the ability to shapeshift from humanoid form to that of an enormous monstrous spider. Long ago they were cast out of their cities once their use in the Night Wars had been completed, and since then have spread and traded through illusions and secret means. Long ago they were purged from their homes in genocide, and took to worshiping demons to get revenge on their attackers.

Name: Arapaima
Summary: Arapaimas are freshwater fish residing in the Amazon River and one of the largest species of freshwater fish.[1] Arapaima normally reach lengths of up to 2 meters, although in rare cases they can exceed 2.5 meters and over 100 kg.[2][1]

Name: Archangel (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Warren Worthington III was a mutant member of the X-Men, named Angel, who was born with a pair of wings until he was one day captured by En Sabah Nur. Apocalypse brainwashed Warren and enhanced his body with modifications, turning him into his "Horseman of Death" Archangel.

Name: Archer (Pokémon)
Key: '''By Himself''' | '''Pokémon Team (Let's Go P/E)''' | '''Pokémon Team (FR/LG and HG/SS)'''
Summary: Archer (Japanese: アポロ Apollo) is one of the four Team Rocket Executives introduced in Pokémon Gold and Silver. However, he went unnamed until Pokémon HeartGold and SoulSilver.

Name: Archie (Pokémon)
Key: '''By Himself''' | '''Pokémon Team (Mt. Chimney)''' | '''Pokémon Team (Seafloor Cavern)''' | '''Pokémon Team (Battle Maison)''' | '''Pokémon (Team Gen 7)'''
Summary: Archie is the boss of Team Aqua. The player only battles him in Seafloor Cavern in Emerald and Mt. Chimney and Seafloor Cavern in Sapphire. In Ruby, he is an ally to the player on his/her mission to stop Team Magma from expanding the land mass and in Sapphire, he is the main antagonist of the game.

Name: Archnemon
Summary: Tier: 9-B | High 8-C | 6-C | At least 4-C, Possibly Low 1-C

Name: Ardos
Summary: Ardos (Japanese: アルドス Ardos) is one of the five Cipher Admins from Pokémon XD: Gale of Darkness. Ardos is one of Grand Master Greevil's two bodyguards, and is revealed at the end of the game to also be one of Greevil's sons (the other bodyguard/son being his twin brother Eldes).

Name: Argentinosaurus
Summary: Argentinosaurus is a genus of titanosaur sauropod dinosaur first discovered by Guillermo Heredia in Argentina. The generic name refers to the country in which it was discovered. The dinosaur lived on the then-island continent of South America somewhere between 97 and 93.5 million years ago, during the Late Cretaceous Period. It is among the largest known dinosaurs.

Name: Arkadimon
Key: '''Baby Arkadimon''' | '''Rookie Arkadimon''' | '''Champion Arkadimon''' | '''Ultimate Arkadimon''' | '''Mega Arkadimon''' | '''Ultra Arkadimon'''
Summary: Tier: 9-B | At least 5-B | At least 5-B | At least 5-B | At least 5-B | At least Low 1-C, likely far higher

Name: Arkadimon (Cyber Sleuth)
Key: '''Arkadimon Baby''' | '''Arkadimon Rookie''' | '''Arkadimon Champion''' | '''Arkadimon Ultimate''' | '''Arkadimon Mega''' | '''Arkadimon Ultra'''
Summary: Arkadimon is one of the main antagonists of Digimon Story: Cyber Sleuth Hacker's Memory. It was imprisoned in Underzero but was freed when the worlds connected. Reacting to Ryuji's negative emotions, It becomes his partner Digimon and causes havoc in both Eden and the Real world.

Name: Armadimon (Iori Hida)
Summary: Iori Hida and his partner Armadillomon are two of the DigiDestined in Digimon Adventure 02. Iori was a one of passengers on the plane that was saved by Kabuterimon and Garudamon in the Digimon Adventure.

Name: ArmaLite AR-15
Summary: The ArmaLite AR-15 is a select-fire, air-cooled, gas-operated, magazine-fed assault rifle manufactured in the United States between 1959 and 1964, and adopted by the United States Armed Forces as the M16 rifle. Designed by American gun manufacturer ArmaLite in 1956, it was based on its AR-10 rifle. The ArmaLite AR-15 was designed to be a lightweight assault rifle and to fire a new high-velocity, lightweight, small-caliber cartridge to allow infantrymen to carry more ammunition.

Name: Arnim Zola (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Brilliant Nazi geneticist Dr. Arnim Zola transferred his mind to a mechanical body to live forever, and now continues his war against freedom with the help of his clones and bio-servants, making him a persistent thorn to Captain America.

Name: Arquebus
Summary: The Arquebus is the first handheld firearm equipped with a mechanical ignition system, having been invented in 1411 after the hand cannon was invented. The arquebus, unlike bows and hand cannons, were easier to wield and were easy weapons to train soldiers with.

Name: Arrowhawk
Summary: Arrowhawks were four-winged birds of prey from the Elemental Plane of Air, and were well-known for their ability to fly and levitate indefinitely from the second they were born. Their striking blue plumage was in fact scales developed for protection.

Name: Arsinoitherium
Summary: Arsinoitherium is a genus of large paenungulate mammals in the order Embrithopoda. Despite its resemblance to rhinoceroses, Arsinoitherium and its order are considered to be related to elephants and sirenians. The prefix of its name comes from Pharaoh Arsinoe II, with the suffix as the Greek word θηρίον (theríon), which means "beast." It lived in North Africa around 36–27 million years ago, during the late Eocene and early Oligocene epochs, inhabiting rainforests and mangrove swamps.

Name: Ascomoid
Summary: The Ascomoid is a big ball of fungus which rolls around the world trying to crush whatever crosses it in order to eat them.

Name: Ash Ketchum
Key: '''By Himself''' | '''Pokémon Team (Original Series)''' | '''Pokémon Team (Advance Generation through Best Wishes)''' | '''Pokémon Team (XY)''' | '''Pokémon Team (Sun and Moon)''' | '''Pokémon Team (Journeys)'''
Summary: Ash Ketchum (Japanese: サトシ Satoshi) is the main character of the original Pokémon anime. He is also the main character of various manga based on the anime, including The Electric Tale of Pikachu, Ash & Pikachu, Magical Pokémon Journey, and Pocket Monsters Diamond & Pearl, including some direct adaptations like the Pokémon Journeys manga.

Name: Ash Ketchum (I Choose You)
Key: '''Himself''' | '''Start of Adventure''' | '''Mid-Adventure Pokémon''' | '''End of M20/M21 Pikachu'''
Summary: nan

Name: Ashe (League of Legends)
Summary: Iceborn warmother of the Avarosan tribe, Ashe commands the most populous horde in the north. Stoic, intelligent, and idealistic, yet uncomfortable with her role as leader, she taps into the ancestral magics of her lineage to wield a bow of True Ice. With her people’s belief that she is the mythological hero Avarosa reincarnated, Ashe hopes to unify the Freljord once more by retaking their ancient, tribal lands.

Name: Assassin Bug
Summary: Assassin Bugs are human-sized insectoid creatures that typically swarm the frontier areas of civilization. Sages suspect they are artificially created, due to the stunted humanoid appendages they bear- though no conclusive evidence has been drawn up to confirm this. Their greatest danger is their ability to implant their young inside of a host, killing them from within unless direct magical assistance is had, or unless the host is burned alive. The young consume their host from within until ultimately "hatching" from the creature.

Name: Assassin Vine
Summary: Assassin Vines are a typical breed of low-level encounter for any Dungeons and Dragons campaign setting. The concept is one of a simple plant typically found attached to steep walls that reaches out and grabs prey, strangling them and ultimately using their decomposing corpses as fertilizer. Its berries were delicious (presumably as bait) and were known to make a unique sort of wine.

Name: AT4
Summary: The AT4 (also AT-4) is an 84-mm unguided, portable, single-shot recoilless smoothbore weapon built in Sweden by Saab Bofors Dynamics (previously Bofors Anti-Armour Systems). Saab has had considerable sales success with the AT4, making it one of the most common light anti-tank weapons in the world.

Name: Atchisson Assault Shotgun
Summary: The Auto Assault-12 (AA-12), originally designed and known as the Atchisson Assault Shotgun, is a shotgun developed in 1972 by Maxwell Atchisson. The most prominent feature is reduced recoil. The current 2005 version has been developed over 18 years since the patent was sold to Military Police Systems, Inc. The original design was the basis of several later weapons, including the original USAS-12 combat shotgun. It is available for commercial purchase only in full automatic mode, however, it fires at a rate of 300 rounds per minute, allowing it to fire one round at a time with brief trigger pulls. It is compatible with either an 8-shell box magazine, or a 20- or 32-shell drum magazine.

Name: Atlantic Blue Marlin
Summary: The Atlantic blue marlin (Makaira nigricans) is a species of marlin native to the Atlantic Ocean. It is a close relative of the swordfish, and one of the fastest species of fish in the world.

Name: Atlantic Goliath Grouper
Summary: The Atlantic Goliath Grouper (Epinephelus itajara), also known as the itjara or the jewfish, is the largest grouper species in the Atlantic Ocean, weighing up to 800 pounds. It is found primarily in shallow tropical waters among coral and artificial reefs. Its range includes the Gulf of Mexico and Florida Keys in the United States, the Bahamas, most of the Caribbean, and most of the Brazilian coast. On some occasions, goliath grouper have been caught off the coast of New England in Massachusetts and Maine. In the eastern Atlantic Ocean, goliath grouper are found off the coast of Africa from the Congo to Senegal.[1]

Name: Atrocitus
Summary: Atrocitus is a Red Lantern and an enemy of the Guardians of the Universe, and the Sinestro Corps. He was originally the leader of The Five Inversions, having joined the group after escaping the genocide committed by the Manhunters and watching them kill his family, and thereupon established the Empire of Tears that spanned a great swathe of space, until their eventual imprisonment and defeat. Atrocitus, however, convinced Abin Sur to free him by using his knowledge of the prophecy of the Blackest Night--later manipulating Abin Sur into experiencing fear, and ultimately mortally wounding Abin Sur, directly causing the events that would lead to Hal Jordan becoming the new Green Lantern of his Sector. Later, on Ysmault, he performed a blood ritual, slaying three of the four Inversions and using their blood to create the first Red Power Battery and ring. He then christened the battery in the last Inversion's blood, thus establishing the Red Lantern Corps.

Name: Attuma (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Attuma is a fierce Talokanil warrior and one of Namor's advisors.

Name: Auntie Ethel
Summary: Why are you so cruel? Please. It's you lot who come to me. All you do is want - to be prettier, to be richer, to be loved. People are their own worst enemies, petal. I just let them see it.

Name: Auroch
Summary: Aurochs are an extinct species of large cattle that once lived in Europe, Asia, and North America. While they were domesticated, aurochs survived until 1627 when the last of the aurochs died in Jaktorów Forest, Poland. Causes of auroch extinction include overhunting, habitat loss, and diseases brought on by domestic cattle. Efforts to revive the aurochs through selective breeding have been ongoing since the 1920s when two German zoo directors used selective breeding to create the Heck cattle breed.

Name: Auto Mag Pistol
Summary: The .44 AutoMag pistol (AMP) is a large caliber semi-automatic pistol. It was designed between 1966 and 1971 by the AutoMag Corporation to make a semi-automatic pistol chambered in .44 AMP.

Name: Avengers (1960s Team)
Summary: When Loki, the Asgardian God of Mischief, influenced the monstrous Hulk to destroy a railway line, the Hulk's friend, Rick Jones, and his Teen Brigade attempted to radio the Fantastic Four for help. However, Loki relayed the information to his brother instead, the God of Thunder and wielder of Mjolnir Thor, in order to draw him into battle. Circumstantially, other super heroes – namely Iron Man and Ant-Man and the Wasp – also received the intercepted signal unbeknownst to Loki and arrived at the scene to reason with the green goliath. Not falling for the trick, Thor confronted Loki and exposed his scheme to the other heroes. With Loki defeated and captured, the group agreed they had worked well together and should be formalized as a team. The Wasp suggested the name Avenger, and Earth's Mightiest Heroes were born.

Name: Avengers (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Iron Man: How were you guys planning on beating that? Captain America: Together. Iron Man: We'll lose. Captain America: Then we'll do that together, too.

Name: Awakened Tree
Summary: An Awakened Tree is a mundane tree given sentience by either the Awaken spell or similar magic. These trees are sturdy and strong, with them being on par with humans intelligence wise.

Name: Axe Beak
Summary: Axe Beaks are large, flightless birds that are often used as mounts by adventurers, their most notable trait being their sharp, axe-shaped beaks which they use to attack their victims.

Name: AZ (Pokémon)
Summary: AZ is an important backstory character of Pokémon X & Y. 3,000 years prior, AZ was the King of the Kalos region, at the same time as the war. His Floette was forcibly introduced in the conflict, causing its death. In grief, and in an attempt to revive his lost companion, he built the Ultimate Weapon, which ultimately ended the war, and made him immortal.

Name: Azazel (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Azazel claimed he was one of the oldest mutants, part of a group of demonic-looking mutants called the Neyaphem. He even claimed that he once battled Mephisto and others for the title of "Satan". The Neyaphem were eventually banished to the Brimstone Dimension by another group of mutants with angelic appearances, the Cheyarafim.

Name: Azbara Jos
Summary: Azbara Jos is a Red Wizard of Thay, an organization of magic users attempting to overthrow the rule of the lich Szass Tam. Azbara, in particular, is an associate of Rath Modar, leader of the Red Wizards. The two were once working with the Cult of the Dragon to free Tiamat from the Nine Hells. The Red Wizards are undertaking this endeavor in the hope that the goddess will assist them in the destruction of the Lich. Azbara is arrogant and actively works towards several goals- particularly investigating the portals used by the cult and working alongside their local leader, a dragon named Rezmir.

Name: Azer
Summary: An Azer is a bronze-skinned dwarf forged by the fire giants. Azers serve as warriors for many pantheons of gods, most notably Moradin- though they are not many, as each Azer is forged by his ancestors with excruciating detail. Azers live largely confined to their volcanic kingdom in the Plane of Fire.

Name: B-1 Lancer
Summary: The Rockwell (Now part of Boeing) B-1 Lancer is a four engine, supersonic variable sweep swing strategic bomber developed in the 1960s originally to replace the aging B-52 Stratofortress. The bomber's original design has evolved into the current B-1B Lancer, a low-level penetration bomber with a long range while retaining supersonic capability.

Name: B-17 Flying Fortress
Summary: The B-17 Flying Fortress is a four engine heavy bomber designed by Boeing, primarily employed by the US Army Air Corps in the European theatre as a strategic bomber against German targets, but also saw service albeit in lesser quantities against the Japanese in the Pacific Theatre. The long range, durability, heavy defensive armament, and speed of the aircraft lent it it's reputation as a strategic bomber. Over 10,000 were built over the course of World War II.

Name: B-2 Spirit
Summary: The B-2 Spirit is a 2-seat stealth bomber developed by Northrop-Grumman. It is a heavy penetration strategic bomber sporting low observable stealth technology for piercing into high density air defenses. It is capable of carrying both conventional and nuclear payloads. There are currently 21 built.

Name: B-52 Stratofortress
Summary: The B-52 Stratofortress is a strategic bomber developed by Boeing. It is a long range jet powered aircraft and has been operated by the USAF since the 1950s and still continues to serve the USAF to this day with continuing upgrades and maintenance. The B-52 made its first flight on April 1952. It was also made to replace the earlier Convair B-36 peacemaker, especially in the role of carrying nuclear weapons for Cold War-era deterrence missions.

Name: Babau
Summary: Babau are the assassins of the Abyss, and will only engage in combat with enemies that it has an advantage over. While not cowardly, the Babau is far from courageous, and carefully analyzes every encounter before engaging. Most lieutenants of the Abyss have a small army of Babau in their pay, to ensure quickly accessible killers for hire.

Name: Bacteria (Kane Pixels)
Summary: Bacteria, are a species of entity that are recurring characters in the analog horror series The Backrooms. Bacteria resemble tall, thin, black humanoids that appear to be made of wires. Bacteria first was shown in The Backrooms: Found Footage, the first episode of the series, in which one chases and presumably kills Kane Pints. It exhibits similar behavior in the episodes Found Footage #2 and Pitfalls and is seen climbing on the ceiling in The Backrooms- Motion Detected. In Autopsy Report, more is learned about the nature of Bacteria, with it being implied to be a mutated strain of the hay bacillus disease. Despite all this, much about Bacteria is still left to be seen.

Name: Bahariasaurus
Summary: Bahariasaurus is a genus of theropod dinosaur from the Egyptian Bahariya formation. It was discovered by Ernest Stromer, who also discovered Spinosaurus and new remains of Carcharodontosaurus. He thought Bahariasaurus could even be the largest theropod genus known. Its remains were destroyed during World War II. Wwhile it is often thought to be related to Deltadromeus and Noasaurids, it is completely different from Ceratosaurians (incl. Noasaurs) in general and shows more Tetanuran traits (e.g. sacral pleurocoels, caudal foraminae and other traits). It also has strongly opisthocoelous and short cervicals, completely different from Noasaur ones. Despite the fact that the overlap with Deltadromeus is poor, it still shows large diferences (very different caudals, Bahariasaurus has caudals that are shorter proportionally). It is likely a Megaraptoran similar to Aoniraptor, as both have elongated vertebrae with pleurocoels only in sacrals and anterior caudals, but not in middle caudals.

Name: Bakemono
Summary: An eastern counterpart to the more well known Goblin, the Bakemono is a larger, buffer and stupider version of the Goblin.

Name: Bakuto (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Bakuto is a leader of a Hand faction who spent his entire life training under many different masters to become a skilled martial artist. During his training, Bakuto would be told the legend of K'un-Lun and the Immortal Iron Fist who was said to be the Hand's most dangerous enemy. After learning of the Iron Fist's existence, Bakuto would attempt to learn as much as he could on the subject. When Danny Rand was revealed to be alive after being missing for fifteen years, Bakuto, believing Rand to be the new Iron Fist, would travel to New York City to investigate himself.

Name: Bald Eagle
Summary: This page contains or depicts disturbing and/or graphic content that some may find upsetting, and that is only intended for mature audiences. Please proceed with caution.

Name: Baltimore-class Heavy Cruiser
Summary: The Baltimore-class Heavy Cruiser was a large class of heavy cruisers in the United States Navy commissioned during or shortly after World War II. Fourteen Baltimores were completed, more than any other class of heavy cruiser, along with three ships of the Oregon City-class sub-class. Fast and heavily armed, the Baltimore cruisers were mainly used in World War II to protect the fast aircraft carriers in battle groups from air attack. Additionally, their 8"/55 (203mm) main guns and secondary 5"/38 (127mm) guns were regularly used to bombard land targets in support of amphibious landings. After the war, only six Baltimores and two Oregon City-class ships remained in service, while the rest were moved to the reserve fleet.

Name: BanchoLilimon
Summary: Tier: Unknown | 9-B | High 8-C | At least High 8-C | 6-C | At least 6-C | At least 4-C, Possibly 3-C | 3-C | At least 3-C, possibly higher

Name: Bane (Post-Crisis)
Summary: This man was born in the prison of Peña Duro, where he would have to serve a life sentence in the place of his father. He grew up in the prison, and killing one of his fellow prisoners, the guards bestowed a name upon him: Bane. The prison guards locked Bane in a pit for ten years as penance, expecting him to die, but he survived and became a legend to the other inmates. Bane trained his mind and his body and was eventually chosen as a test subject for a drug called Venom. Bane was the only subject who survived the test, and he was subsequently given surgery so the drug could be injected directly into his brain. After faking his own death to escape Peña Duro, Bane returned to free the inmates, kill the warden and steal a helicopter so he could travel to Gotham City, home of the man that Bane wanted to destroy: the Batman.

Name: Barghest
Summary: Barghests are fiendish shapechangers hailing from the plane of Gehenna, though they are often sighted on the Prime Material due to their growth rituals. In essence, they are often sent to the Prime Material to devour powerful mortals so that they may grow in power.

Name: Barinasuchus
Summary: Barinasuchus is a large genus of sebecosuchid, a group of terrestrial crocodylomorphs. It’s name means "Barinas Crocodile" after Barina in Venezuela where the holotype was discovered. It inhabited the wetland environment in South America from the mid Eocene to mid Miocene epochs, around 42.2–11.8 million years ago. It was very likely the apex predator of its time and location, hunting a variety of animals in its environment.

Name: Barrett M82
Summary: The Barrett M82, standardized by the US Military as the M107, is a recoil-operated, semi-automatic sniper rifle developed by the American Barrett Firearms Manufacturing company. It is used by many units and armies around the world. Despite its designation as an anti-materiel rifle, it is used by some armed forces as an anti-personnel sniper rifle. It is also called the Light Fifty for its .50 BMG (12.7×99 mm NATO) chambering and significantly lighter weight compared to previous applications.

Name: Barry (Pokémon)
Summary: Barry is the childhood friend of Lucas and the rival in Sinnoh. Always in a hurry, Barry is the reason that Lucas and him get Pokémon, as Barry convinces his friend to go search for the Red Gyarados, and in the process, they run into Professor Rowan, his starter Pokémon, and some wild Starlys. The duo's adventure begins when they use Rowan's Pokémon to defend themselves.

Name: Baseball Bat
Summary: A Baseball Bat is a wooden/metal club used in baseball. In baseball, they are used to hit the ball, sending it flying after it is thrown at the batter by the pitcher. But due its structure, it can be used as clubbing weapon and due to its ease of access and use, it is common in street fights or in home defense in a few countries.

Name: Basilisk (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: Basilisks are reptilian magical creatures bestowed with the capability to turn enemies to stone. Their abilities are renowned enough that a seasoned adventurer will recognize the threat of remaining in the area when they begin seeing remarkably life-like statues of frightened wildlife.

Name: Basilosaurus
Summary: Basilosaurus (King Lizard) is a genus of prehistoric whales that existed during the Late Eocene, 40 to 35 million years ago. The genus contains 2 species, B. cetoides in the United States, and B. isis from Egypt and Jordan.

Name: Basking Shark
Summary: The basking shark (Cetorhinus maximus) is the second-largest extant fish in the world. Unlike most other sharks, the basking shark is a filter feeder, and primarily feeds on zooplankton. Despite their size and massive mouth, basking sharks are docile, and pose no threat to humans.

Name: Batman (Earth-43)
Key: '''Living Vampire (Red Rain)''' | '''Undead Vampire (Bloodstorm)''' | '''Evil Undead Vampire (Crimson Mist)''' | '''With Preparation'''
Summary: Batman, real name Bruce Wayne, is the protagonist of the Earth-43 trilogy of vampire stories: Red Rain, Bloodstorm, and Crimson Mist.

Name: Batman (Millerverse)
Summary: It's a SHAME to expose one of my SAFE HOUSES. Now it'll be USELESS. But I've got DOZENS around town, and this one's RENT wouldn't amount to a VALET TIP. Hell. It'll be worth TEN TIMES the rent just to get a chance to knock the SNOT out of GREEN LANTERN. This guy really GRINDS MY GEARS. Here he's got a POWER RING that can do ANYTHING he can IMAGINE-- but that's his whole PROBLEM. He's got the IMAGINATION of a goddamn POTATO. He makes giant green FISHING POLES and MOUSETRAPS when he could, well... ...Put that ring on MY finger and just as a WARM-UP I'd send a few TIDAL WAVES in just the right DIRECTIONS. Knock out a few ENEMY FLEETS. Then get started on bringing some REAL firepower to a nasty GROUND WAR or two. Then maybe I'd spank SUPERMAN'S butt back to what's left of KRYPTON. Just for LAUGHS. Thing is, old Hal (Hal Jordan, that's his real name-- the moron can't keep any secrets from ME), old Hal, he can't even make himself a green DANDELION with that RING of his if what he's up against is YELLOW. Dumbest WEAKNESS I ever HEARD of...

Name: Batman (One Million)
Summary: In 853rd century, it was on the prison planet of Pluto that the seeds would be sowed for this Batman. The planet was home to tens of thousands of the worst criminals from across the galaxy, kept under strict control. However, one day, a virus infected members of the prison guard, driving them utterly insane. In their madness, they released the prisoners. The worst scum of the galaxy routed the remaining guards in hours and took control. They dragged guards and their families to exercise area. It was there that the sadistic prisoners made fifteen thousand children watch as their parents were gunned down over a period of days. The resulting trauma drove hundreds to commit suicide with hundreds more driven mad from the experience. But one child did not succumb. Instead, he took a vow to never allow such an atrocity to occur again. He vowed to become the Batman.

Name: Batman (Thomas Wayne)
Summary: Batman (Thomas Wayne) is a fictional character appearing in American comic books published by DC Comics. Created by Geoff Johns (writer) and Andy Kubert (artist), he made his first appearance in Flashpoint #1 (July 2011). He is a hardened version of Thomas Wayne seen in Geoff Johns's alternate timeline comic Flashpoint (2011) whose son was killed instead of Martha Wayne and himself. His character returned to the main DC Universe in DC Rebirth as a revived amalgamation of his original self that was killed by Joe Chill and the Flashpoint Batman that was killed by Eobard Thawne in a storyline revolving around the "Smiley-face" button from Watchmen.

Name: Batwoman (Post-Crisis)
Summary: Kate Kane is Batwoman, one of many vigilantes who protect Gotham City using the imagery of a Bat. She is both Jewish and an open lesbian, playing a socialite during the day and working with her cousin Bette as vigilantes by night.

Name: Bayonet
Summary: The Bayonet was made in the 17th century in Bayonne, France. It was highly popular in Britain, and The Bayonet became a popular tool in combat. After WW1, the weapon started to Wane due to the popularity of rapid-fire weapons. To this day, the Bayonet is still used in combat in the Marines.

Name: Bea (Pokémon)
Key: '''By Herself''' | '''Pokèmon Team (Stow-on-Side Stadium)''' | '''Pokèmon Team (Champion Cup Finals)''' | '''Pokèmon Team (Champion tournament)'''
Summary: Bea (Japanese: サイトウ Saitō) is the Gym Leader of Stow-on-Side's Gym, known officially as Stow-on-Side Stadium. She specializes in Fighting-type Pokémon. She gives the Fighting Badge to Trainers who defeat her. She is also an exclusive Gym Leader on Pokémon Sword.

Name: Bearded Devil
Summary: Bearded Devils (also referred to as Barbazu in the Infernal tongue) are the front line soldiers of the Blood War, and the shock troopers of the Hells. Often seen directly battling the demonic threat along the Styx, Bearded Devils are also known to lead other low-ranking devils in combat. They are most known abroad for their striking beards, which serve as a sort of secondary weapon, and their glaives, which leave horrific wounds that can kill just as easily as the weapons that made them.

Name: Bede (Pokémon)
Key: '''By Himself''' | '''Pokèmon Team (First battle)''' | '''Pokèmon Team (Second battle)''' | '''Pokèmon Team (Third battle)''' | '''Pokèmon Team (Fourth battle)''' | '''Pokèmon Team (Fifth battle/Champion tournament)'''
Summary: Bede (Japanese: ビート Beet) is one of the rival characters in Pokémon Sword and Shield, the others being Hop and Marnie. He initially specializes in Psychic-type Pokémon, but is eventually scouted by Opal to succeed her as a Fairy-type Gym Leader, and thus changes his specialty type accordingly. As the Gym Leader of Ballonlea Stadium, he gives the Fairy Badge to Trainers who defeat him.

Name: Beetle (Janice Lincoln)
Summary: Daughter of the mobster Tombstone, Janice Lincoln always wanted to become a powerful supervillain like her father. After becoming a lawyer, she had a chance encounter with Baron Zemo and Fixer and debuted as the new Beetle by poisoning Bucky Barnes.

Name: Belker
Summary: Belkers are beings made of smoke residing in the Elemental Plane of Air. Such creatures are invariably evil but also reclusive, hiding away from any they might inflict their evil upon. Though their shape changes with the wind, they always present themselves with large bat wings and vile faces, giving them a certain demonic visage.

Name: Beluga Whale (The Real World)
Summary: The Beluga Whale (scientifically known as Delphinapterus leucas) is a social, Arctic, Sub-Arctic, river, & deep offshore Cetacean under the conservation status of "Least Concern" by the IUCN.[2][1][3] It's an extremely vocal cetacean capable of vocalizing up to 120 kHz & mimicking a variety of sounds with its vocals & melon,[2][4] which can be heard above water & through the hulls of ships.[4] This gives it the nickname "Canary of the sea" or "Sea Canaries."[2][4] This whale is one of the most commonly kept cetaceans in captivity since the 1860s due to it being easily captured in shallow waters, it's coloration, & it's adaptability.[2] During the 19th & early 20th centuries, it was hunted for it's oil, flesh & hides,[2] with some populations being threatened by shipping, & pollution currently & historically.[2][5] Though they're hunted as food by humans,[2] dogs,[2] polar bears,[1][6] & orcas.[1][7]

Name: Benelli M4
Summary: The Benelli M4 is a semi-automatic combat shotgun produced by Italian firearm manufacturer Benelli Armi SpA, and the last of the "Benelli Super 90" series of semi-automatic shotguns. The M4 uses a proprietary action design called the "auto-regulating gas-operated" (ARGO) system, which was created specifically for the weapon. It was designed in 1998, and was adopted by the armed forces of Italy, the United States, United Kingdom, among others, and has been used in a variety of conflicts, leading up to the present day.

Name: Benjamin Franklin (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Benjamin Franklin is the historic founding father of the United States of America. His life remains mostly the same as in our real world, but he had somehow found a way to cheat death and remain as a form of electrical apparition. He became a frequent ally of Deadpool after assisting him in getting rid of the zombified presidents.

Name: Beretta ARX160
Summary: The Beretta ARX160 is an Italian modular rifle manufactured by Beretta. Developed for the Italian Armed Forces as part of the Soldato Futuro (English: "Future Soldier") program, the ARX160 was launched in 2008 as a commercial weapon system independent from the Soldato Futuro ensemble, complete with a companion single-shot 40×46mm NATO low-velocity grenade launcher, called the GLX160, which can be mounted underneath the rifle or used with an ad hoc stock system as a stand-alone weapon.

Name: Beretta M9
Summary: The Beretta M9, officially the Pistol, Semiautomatic, 9mm, M9, is the designation for the Beretta 92FS semi-automatic pistol by the United States Armed Forces. The M9 was adopted by the United States' military as their service pistol in 1985. The 92FS itself has been manufactured by Beretta of Italy since its origin in 1975, and its production continues on even today with a variety of caliber options.

Name: Bernard (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: New sounds through damp and dark oppression break Is it the foe, that foul, contemptuous heel? Or art thou friend, a rescue from my lonely wake? Come out of love for me, not love for blood and steel.

Name: Betelgeuse (Musical)
Summary: Betelgeuse is an eccentric and crude self-proclaimed bio-exorcist who seeks to obtain his goal of becoming alive again by any means necessary.

Name: Bianca (Pokémon)
Key: '''By Herself''' | '''Pokémon Team (Early Game)''' | '''Pokémon Team (Mid Game)''' | '''Pokémon Team (End and Post-Game)''' | '''Pokémon Team (BW2)'''
Summary: Bianca (ベル, Bel) is a Pokémon Trainer from the Unova region.

Name: Bison (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: A large herb animal, the Bison is one of the many mammals that roams the lands of Dungeons and Dragons.

Name: Black Adam (Post-Crisis)
Summary: Once the son to an ancient pharaoh, Teth-Adam miraculously gained powers from an ageing wizard named Shazam. By saying his name, the mere prince became the champion of Shazam, gaining himself the powers of six Egyptian gods: Shu, Heru, Amon, Zehuti, Aton and Mehen. However, as time went on, Adam started to crave for more power and authority, and forcefully overthrew the government to become the ruler of Kahndaq. Believing Adam to be corrupted, the old wizard casted a spell which trapped Adam's memories, soul and powers in a scarab, however, this in turn aged Adam's physical body into dust. Millennials later, one of Adam's descendants and murderer of Billy Batson's parents: Theo Adam would stumble upon this scarab and calling out Shazam, Theo would reborn Teth into his own body to become Black Adam.

Name: Black Bear (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: One of the various bears in Dungeons and Dragons, the Black Bear is one of the smaller variants. They only attack those who try to steal their food or threaten them and their family.

Name: Black Canary (Post-Crisis)
Summary: Dinah Laurel Lance, better known as Black Canary, is a super heroine and a member of the Justice League of America. The daughter of the original Black Canary, a charter member of the Justice Society of America, Dinah was inspired by her mother and detective father to fight crime and corruption wherever possible. However, after her father's passing and her subsequent rejection from the police force, she turned to vigilantism as a means of fighting the growing threats to the peace she so loves.

Name: Black Cat (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Black Cat (Felicia Hardy) is a fictional character appearing in American comic books published by Marvel Comics. Created by writer Marv Wolfman and artist Keith Pollard, she first appeared in The Amazing Spider-Man #194 (July 1979). Felicia Hardy is the daughter of a world-renowned cat burglar. After suffering a traumatic event as a college freshman, she trained herself in various fighting styles and acrobatics and, after deciding to follow in her father's footsteps, adopted her costumed identity as the Black Cat.

Name: Black Fox (Marvel Comics)
Summary: A master thief past his prime, Black Fox had taught best of the best in his heydays, but only looks now to save up for his retirement to the French Riviera.

Name: Black Hand
Summary: William Hand was often described as the black sheep of his family. Obsessed with death and clichés from a young age, Hand was deemed a disgrace by his relatives, no doubt fueling his spiral into psychopathy. Taking up the mantle of Black Hand, he came in possession of the Power Rod, a mysterious artifact that allowed him to steal the powers of others. Using this device, he dueled against Green Lantern and The Flash numerous times. After Hal Jordan became one with The Spectre, he destroyed Black Hand's hand, causing the already fragile man to break entirely, becoming a truly sadistic and cruel-hearted individual who became the first Black Lantern.

Name: Black Mask (Post-Crisis)
Summary: Raised in a wealthy home by neglectful parents, Roman Sionis exhibited psychopathic tendencies since childhood, however they emerged in full force when he murdered his own parents and took on the persona of "Black Mask". Now a ruthless crime boss most recognized by the black skull mask burned onto his head and his penchant for sadistic torture, Black Mask has proven himself to be one of Batman's most dangerous foes over years of encounters.

Name: Black Order (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: The Black Order, also known as the Children of Thanos, was an elite team comprised of powerful individuals who used their abilities to serve their adoptive father Thanos. As his vicious generals, they assisted him in his mission to find and harness the power of the Infinity Stones.

Name: Black Panther (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: T'Challa, also known by the moniker of Black Panther, is the protector of the nation of Wakanda. Following the untimely death of his father T'Chaka, he inherited his father's position as king. In his rush to avenge his father, he became involved in the internal conflict among the Avengers, siding with Iron Man. However, upon seeing how vengeance drove Helmut Zemo's actions and subsequently Iron Man's as well, he saw the error of his judgement and became an ally to Captain America.

Name: Black Pudding
Summary: Black Puddings are quasi-sentient globs of viscous black goop, most often found in poorly-lit dungeon halls where it might be dismissed as nothing more than a blot of shadow. In truth, it is a malevolent carnivore that strips and dissolves even the most durable materials, leaving behind only stone. It is a painful and not altogether quick way to perish.

Name: Black Widow (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Thaddeus Ross: You've got some nerve, I'll give you that. Natasha: You could use some of that right now.

Name: Black Widow (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Former KGB agent Natasha Romanova, known as Black Widow, is one of the greatest spies on Earth and is one of the best agents S.H.I.E.L.D. has ever had. She's a long-time member of the Avengers and was a founding member and the only leader of the short-lived Los Angeles-based superteam: The Champions.

Name: Blacktip Reef Shark
Summary: The blacktip reef shark (Carcharhinus melanopterus) is a small species of requiem shark native to coral reefs in the Pacific and Indian oceans. It can be distinguished from other sharks by the prominent black tips on its fins.

Name: Blade (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Blade, real name Eric Brooks, is a vampire hunter, as well as a half-vampire hybrid himself, known to the blood-drinking undead as a "Dhampir" or "Daywalker", as he possesses all the strengths of a vampire without any of their weaknesses. The reason for his unique condition is that as his mother was giving birth to him, the vampire Deacon Frost, posing as a doctor, bit her, turning her into a vampire before immediately killing her. The vampiric corruption reached Eric through the umbilical chord, and turned him into a unique being with a vengeance against the vampiric kind, who would all eventually come to fear him.

Name: Blaser R93 Tactical
Summary: The Blaser R93 Tactical is a German bolt action sniper rifle, based on the Blaser R93 design. It has as variants the Blaser LRS 2 and Tactical 2. It is used by German and Dutch police forces as well as the Australian military and special police units. The rifles were manufactured by the German firearms manufacturer Blaser.

Name: Blaze (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: An elemental that lives in the Nether, the Blaze spends its days floating above the ground. The Blaze's rods can be used as ingredients for potion making, which makes Blaze hunting alluring for adventurers.

Name: Blight
Summary: Blights are the ill-bred results of a bloodied stake being driven through the heart of one Gulthias the Vampire, killing him. However, the evil of this undead was so great that the stake was given his life, and grew into a mighty tree. The roots of the tree birthed horrendous creatures, now known as Blights, who have transformed huge swathes of land into corrupted places where only the flora may tread.

Name: Blindspot (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Sam Chung was an illegal immigrant living in Chinatown, New York, who wished to patent his invisibility suit, but due to his legal status he decided against it, and instead put it to use as the vigilante Blindspot.

Name: Blink (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Clarice Ferguson, first discovered her mutant abilities after a traumatic and bloody accident, which left her fearful of her own powers. Alongside other young mutants, she was captured by the techno-organic Phalanx, who sought to assimilate their abilities. In a selfless act of bravery, Clarice sacrificed herself to save her fellow captives—an act that deeply affected the survivors and inspired them to form the team known as Generation X.

Name: Blink Dog
Summary: Blink Dogs are the mortal enemies of Displacer Beasts, and are canine-appearing magical beasts with the ability to teleport at will. Unlike most beasts present in most Dungeons and Dragons settings, Blink Dogs are known to be good so while they will not interact with humans, they do defend their lands.

Name: Blizzard (Gregor Shapanka)
Summary: Dr. Gregor Shapanka, Ph.D., an employee of Stark Industries, was conducting private research into a means for achieving physical immortality, who got fired for attempting to steal from Anthony Stark's vault.

Name: Blood Hawk
Summary: Blood Hawks are vicious hunters who not only attack nearly all creatures, but will not back down from a fight even when they're in a losing position. Their blood lust is so strong that they go hunting even when they're not hungry, and decide to cut meals short just to attack other creatures. They favour eating human flesh and, given the option, will target them first.

Name: Bloodmote Cloud
Summary: Bloodmote Clouds are groups of undead mosquitoes intent on drawing blood from all living creatures. They are wildly more dangerous than their living counterparts, being capable of draining a human in mere seconds.

Name: Bloodthorn
Summary: Growing in deserts and plains of evil and chaotic realms, the Bloodthorn is a deadly plant. This plant gets its name from its eating habits, with it ensnaring and draining the blood of living creatures.

Name: Blue (Pokémon Let's Go)
Summary: This version of Blue is quite a unique one. Instead of taking the role of an antagonistic rival that is meant to be overcome, he is an older, more mature mentor for the main characters, Chase and Trace. Furthermore, Let’s Go itself is a universe that takes place a bit later than others, where Red, Blue, and Green have all already gone on their Pokémon adventures.

Name: Blue (Pokémon)
Key: '''By Himself''' | '''Gen 1 Team (First Battle)''' | '''Gen 1 Team (Second Battle)''' | '''Gen 1 Team (Third Battle)''' | '''Gen 1 Team (Fourth Battle)''' | '''Gen 1 Team (Fifth Battle)''' | '''Gen 1 Team (Sixth Battle)''' | '''Gen 1 Team (Seventh Battle)''' | '''Gen 1 Team (Champion Battle)''' | '''Gen 2 Team''' | '''Gen 7 Teams'''
Summary: Blue Oak was the rival in the first Generation of Pokémon. Characterized by his rude and crude personality, Blue embarked on his Pokémon journey at the same time as his rival, Red and was always one step ahead of him no matter where he went. Cocky, arrogant and even a little devious, Blue quickly found himself becoming the Pokémon Master of Kanto, only to be defeated by Red.

Name: Blue Shark
Summary: The blue shark (Prionace glauca) is a species of requiem shark native to oceans worldwide. It is one of the fastest known sharks.

Name: Blue Slaad
Summary: The second lowest of the Slaadi race, the Blue Slaad is also a fearsome enemy. Their claw attacks inflict a terrible disease that turns creatures into Red Slaad, with it being unironic as the two Slaad types both loath each other.

Name: Blue Whale
Summary: The blue whale (Balaenoptera musculus) is a marine mammal belonging to the parvorder Mysticeti, the baleen whales. At up to 29.9 meters in length and a maximum recorded weight of 173 tonnes, it is the largest animal to have ever existed.

Name: Boar (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: A wild cousin of the domesticated pig, the Boar is a medium-sized omnivore mammal. They are fierce fighters, being able to fight even past the point of fatal harm, charging at foes with their tusks.

Name: Bobby Singer
Summary: Robert Steven "Bobby" Singer (1950-2012) was a hunter, an old friend of John Winchester, and over time evolved into a father-figure for John's sons Sam and Dean. He was also one of the longest lasting recurring characters, appearing in every season so far.

Name: Bofors 40mm Gun
Summary: The Bofors 40mm/60 Gun, often referred to simply as the Bofors gun, is an anti-aircraft/multi-purpose autocannon designed in the 1930s by the Swedish arms manufacturer AB Bofors. It was one of the most popular medium-weight anti-aircraft systems during World War II, used by most of the western Allies as well as by the Axis powers. Probably the best heavy MG AA weapon of World War II, Bofors guns of this type remained in service long after the war ended. This weapon was used on almost every major USA and UK warship of World War II and was a very potent AA gun. These guns are recoil operated and use a monobloc barrel with a detachable breech ring, breech casing and automatic loader. Breech block is a vertical sliding type. Although often listed as being 60 calibers long, all of these guns except for the Japanese version were actually 56.25 calibers in length. The US version was therefore named the Bofors 40mm/56.

Name: Bone Naga
Summary: Bone Nagas are a member of the immortal species known as nagas. They were created by the mighty Creator Race Sarrukh, though they are ultimately an incomplete perversion of true nagas. During the ritual made to cement the naga's immortality, yuan-ti necromantic rituals rendered the creature undead, twisting them into servants of the yuan-ti instead, and with merely a fraction of the power their siblings possessed.

Name: Bone Rat Swarm
Summary: Bone Rat Swarms are hordes of skeletal, undead rats created for some nefarious necromantic purpose. They gather in great masses and rampage through urban environments, stripping anything they find to the bone.

Name: Bone Whelk
Summary: Deep in Avernus, the Bone Whelk lives. This creature is a giant mollusk which forms its shell from body parts that get stuck on its sticky body.

Name: Bonegnasher
Summary: Seeking power, the ogre named Bonegnasher alongside his men attacked King Damara in order to obtain the Orb of Dragonkind, in the porcess slaying the king's men and forcing Drama as a last ditch effort to hide the orb. If the adventurers tasked to stop Bonegnasher from finding the orb inside the castle fail he will use the orb to call forth a red dragon and lay destruction upon the land.

Name: Bonnie (In Stars and Time)
Summary: Bonnie, full name Boniface Sohane Aglae Zabor, is a major character in the game In Stars and Time and START AGAIN: a prologue, traveling with Mirabelle, Isabeau, Odile, and Siffrin on a quest to defeat the King and save Vaugarde from the fate of being frozen in time. Bonnie is described as a loud and brave kid from the coastal town of Bambouche. Throughout the game, they help out randomly in battles and are on snack duty.

Name: Boomerang (Real World)
Summary: A boomerang is a traditional curved throwing tool that originated with Indigenous Australians, though similar versions have been found in other parts of the world. It is most commonly made of wood, but can also be crafted from bone, stone, or modern materials like plastic. The most famous type is the returning boomerang, which is carefully shaped and balanced so that when thrown with the correct spin, it travels in a curved path and comes back to the thrower. However, not all boomerangs were designed to return—many were larger, heavier hunting boomerangs used to strike animals, and these would fly straight rather than circle back.

Name: Boromir
Summary: ‘Beneath Amon Hen I heard his cry. There many foes he fought, His cloven shield, his broken sword, they to the water brought. His head so proud, his face so fair, his limbs they laid to rest, And Rauros, golden Rauros-falls, bore him upon its breast. ‘O Boromir! The Tower of Guard shall ever northward gaze, To Rauros, golden Rauros-falls, until the end of days.

Name: Bottlenose Dolphin
Summary: Dolphins are several families of cetaceans in the parvorder Odontoceti. Most famous of these dolphins is the Bottlenose Dolphin. Bottlenose dolphins have gained popularity for their appearances in aquarium shows, but among scientists, they are popular for their intelligence. Studies on dolphin intelligence, ranging from cognition to the use of artificial language.

Name: Bourdon
Summary: Very nice of those hands to not attack us. But none of our attacks are hurting that big one...

Name: Bow (Real World)
Summary: Bows are among the earliest weapons known to man. A bow is a simplistic weapon in design; simply put, a lightweight arrow is shot with the pull of a string. While bows were made obsolete in favor of guns in war, bows are still used in hunting and sporting events (particularly the Olympic sport of archery). More recently, compound bows were developed, boasting stronger draw weights than modern recurve bows. Multiple arrows can be fired in a single shot, although generally multiple arrows being fired at once aren't as effective as firing a single shot.

Name: Brachiosaurus
Summary: Brachiosaurus is a genus of sauropod dinosaur that lived in North America during the Late Jurassic, about 154–153 million years ago. It was first described by American paleontologist Elmer S. Riggs in 1903 from fossils found in the Colorado River valley in western Colorado, United States. Riggs named the dinosaur Brachiosaurus altithorax; the generic name is Greek for "arm lizard", in reference to its proportionately long arms, and the specific name means "deep chest". It had a disproportionately long neck, small skull, and large overall size, all of which are typical for sauropods. Atypically, Brachiosaurus had longer forelimbs than hindlimbs, which resulted in a steeply inclined trunk, and a proportionally shorter tail.

Name: Bradley Fighting Vehicle
Summary: The Bradley Fighting Vehicle (BFV) is a fighting vehicle platform of the United States manufactured by BAE Systems Land & Armaments, formerly United Defense. It was named after U.S. General Omar Bradley.

Name: Brain in a Jar
Summary: Brains in Jars are masterpieces of technology and necromancy merged into a single being. They are undead, brains kept alive by preservative fluid and given reign to focus on their psionic power rather than supporting their physical body. The ritual for creating such a creature is relatively unknown- merely placing the brain in the correct fluids will not produce any of the same effects. Only those with enough control over the brain commit such rituals, as the brain is adept at taking control of the thoughts of others.

Name: Brainiac (Post-Crisis)
Summary: Vril Dox was an unbelievably intelligent but callous inventor on the planet Colu. Caring for nothing but the gaining of new knowledge, Dox aided the Computer Tyrants in their fascist rule of the planet in order to further his own experiments and projects. However, the Computer Tyrants hated Dox and feared his intellect, and sabotaged one of his experiments, vaporizing his body, but his mind remained. Years later, Dox would possess the man known as Milton Fine, the Amazing Brainiac and use his body for over a decade in his schemes.

Name: Brainiac (Pre-Crisis)
Summary: Brainiac was a robot from the distant future who traveled the universe, shrinking cities for his own self-satisfaction. He was among Superman's greatest and most fearsome foes. Though he lacked in physical strength, he more than made up for it with his unmatched mind, arsenal of futuristic weapons and shockingly good agility. After what could have been his final outing involving a weapon known as the Planet-Eater, Brainiac's body was transformed into the New Brainiac, a bio-robot who absorbed all the knowedge in the universe, and embarked on a new quest, a quest that would never be fufilled, to overthrow God himself.

Name: Bralani
Summary: The Brelani were a species of wild Eladrin, good-aligned celestials hailing from the Plane of Arborea. These eladrin in particular refused to outright serve any particular god, instead agreeing to ally with them. They embody the snow, wind, and sand, and were considered lesser to their Ghaele brothers.

Name: Brandon (Pokémon)
Summary: Brandon (Japanese: ジンダイ Jindai) is the Frontier Brain and chief of the Battle Frontier's Battle Pyramid. He is the only character in the games to have the Trainer class Pyramid King (Japanese: ピラミッドキング Pyramid King).

Name: Brandon Rogers (Character)
Summary: Brandon Rogers is the creator of several shows including Magical Funhouse, Theater Class, and Stuff & Sam! He is the creator and "God" of the world and has been manipulating the plot of the shows TV30 run which also affected reality. The source of his power lies within his book, known as The Creator's Book of Doings.

Name: Brass Knuckles
Summary: Brass Knuckles are pieces of metal shaped to fit around the knuckles. They concentrate a person's punching force by directing the force of the punch into a smaller contact area.

Name: Braum
Summary: Blessed with massive muscles, and an even bigger heart, Braum is a beloved hero of the Freljord. Every child born to the ice knows of his legendary strength, capable of felling entire forests of frost-oaks in a single night or rending the very mountains asunder. With a colossal vault door borne across his back as a shield, Braum roams the land as a friend to those in need and a terrible foe of evildoers.

Name: Braun Strowman (WWE)
Summary: Braun Strowman also known as The Monster Among Men started out as a successful strongman when eventually he met Mark Henry who introduced him to the WWE. There he became a member of the Wyatt Family while wearing the mask of the Black sheep. Once he broke away from the group, he eventually started a successful solo-run that has resulted in him being a one time WWE Champion and accomplishing very powerful feats of destroying vehicles and breaking objects. Braun is 2.03 m tall and weighs over 385 lb.

Name: Breachgnome
Summary: Specialized in fighting within cramped spaces, a well-positioned Breachgnome can hold off superior enemy forces for a long duration. They are trained to fight alone, although sometimes they work in small units that coordinate to block off several paths at once. They are seldom seen outside Gnome communities, though when are found outside they are often looking for Gnomes to help.

Name: Brock (Pokémon)
Summary: Brock "The Rock-Solid Pokémon Trainer!" is the first Gym Leader Red encountered in his adventures in Kanto. He is an expert and specialist of the Rock typing. Arguably one of the most iconic Gym Leaders in the entire series [Only really rivaled by Misty and Giovanni], Brock has become a recurring character in the Pokémon franchise, appearing in Pokémon Red/Blue/Yellow, Pokémon Adventures and arguably most famously, the Pokémon anime series.

Name: Brontornis
Summary: Brontornis is the largest bird-of-prey; it is often considered to be a cariamiform, either a phorusrhacid (a group informally called "terror birds") or an anserimorph, but overall, its classification is widely debated. Due to its size, it was likely either an ambush predator like leopards or a bird that actively chased down its prey. Brontornis was estimated to be 2.8 meters tall and weigh in at 350-400 kg.

Name: Brother Power (DC Comics)
Summary: Brought to life at the height of the hippie age, Brother Power The Geek was a short-lived superhero who represented the hippie ideals of love, peace, and harmony. However, as the world constantly changed around him, Brother Power found himself in a seemingly endless cycle of death-and-rebirth, getting 'stuck' in the idealistic age of the 1960s. In his final days, after all of his friends passed on, Brother Power helped save many lives during a gang war in Gotham City, ultimately losing his own in the process, optimistically hoping that those he saved would usher the world into a brighter tomorrow.

Name: Brown Bear (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: One of the many bears in Dungeons and Dragons, the Brown Bear is the larger cousin of the Black Bear. They are around 9 feet long, and are far stronger than black bears. Like other bears, they are omnivores, and they are noted to be rather aggressive.

Name: Brown Bess
Summary: "Brown Bess" is a nickname of uncertain origin for the British Army's muzzle-loading smoothbore flintlock Land Pattern Musket and its derivatives. This musket was used in the era of the expansion of the British Empire and acquired symbolic importance at least as significant as its physical importance. It was in use for over a century with many incremental changes in its design. These versions include the Long Land Pattern, the Short Land Pattern, the India Pattern, the New Land Pattern Musket and the Sea Service Musket.

Name: Brown Pelican
Summary: Brown Pelicans are one of the 8 members of the genus Pelecanus. The genus is known for its gluttony and willingness to eat nearly anything. Surprisingly, Brown Pelicans are more grounded in terms of their prey variety.

Name: Browning Hi-Power
Summary: The Browning Hi Power is a single-action, semi-automatic handgun available in the 9mm and .40 S&W calibers. It was based on a design by American firearms inventor John Browning, and completed by Dieudonné Saive at Fabrique Nationale (FN) of Herstal, Belgium. Browning died in 1926, several years before the design was finalized. The Hi-Power is one of the most widely used military pistols in history, having been used by the armed forces of over 50 countries. After 82 years of continuous production, the Hi-Power was discontinued in 2017 by Browning Arms, but it remained in production in some countries, under license.

Name: Browning M2
Summary: The M2 Machine Gun or Browning .50 Caliber Machine Gun is a heavy machine gun designed towards the end of World War I by John Browning. Its design is similar to Browning's earlier M1919 Browning machine gun, which was chambered for the .30-06 cartridge. The M2 uses the much larger and much more powerful .50 BMG cartridge, which was developed alongside and takes its name from the gun itself (BMG standing for Browning Machine Gun). It has been referred to as "Ma Deuce", in reference to its M2 nomenclature. The design has had many specific designations; the official designation for the current infantry type is Browning Machine Gun, Cal. .50, M2, HB, Flexible. It is effective against infantry, unarmored or lightly armored vehicles and boats, light fortifications and low-flying aircraft. The M2 machine gun has been produced longer than any other machine gun.

Name: Bruno (Pokémon)
Summary: Bruno (シバ Siba) is a Fighting-type Trainer and member of the Elite Four of Kanto and Johto.

Name: Bryweludramon
Summary: Tier: Unknown | 9-B | High 8-C | 6-C | At least 4-C, Possibly 3-C | At least 3-C, Possibly higher | Low 1-C

Name: Bugbear
Summary: One of the stronger Goblinoids, the Bugbear bullies and hunts whatever it wishes to. Unlike their Goblin brothers, they aren't weak to light and stand at around 7 feet tall with strong physique.

Name: Bulette
Summary: Bulettes, or as they are famously known, Land Sharks, are massive shelled-creatures that live solely to eat and will in fact eat anything, with their powerful digestive systems quickly working through even arcane and metal objects. They hunt via sensing tremors above them.

Name: Bull Shark
Summary: Bull Sharks (Carcharhinus leucas), also known as the Zambezi shark or as Zambi in Africa and the Lake Nicaragua shark in Nicaragua, is a requiem shark found across the world in warm, shallow waters along coasts and in rivers, known for its aggressive disposition, preference for lurking in warm, shallow waters, and in freshwater systems such as rivers.

Name: Bull Terrier
Summary: The bull terrier is a breed of terrier developed in the 19th century as a fighting dog. Over the years, the breed has shifted from this original purpose to become a companion and show dog. It is easily distinguished from other breeds by its long, egg-shaped head.

Name: Bulldog
Summary: The Bulldog, also known as the British Bulldog or English Bulldog, is a medium-sized dog breed. It is a muscular, hefty dog with a wrinkled face and a distinctive pushed-in nose. Bulldogs are popular pets; they were the fifth most popular purebreed in the US in 2017 according to the American Kennel Club.

Name: Bullseye (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Benjamin Leonard "Dex" Poindexter is a veteran of the United States Army and a former FBI agent who possesses a remarkable talent for accuracy. Struggling with a mental illness throughout his life, Poindexter relied on structure and rules to maintain his sanity with the counseling of Eileen Mercer, whose death affected Poindexter, leading him to stalk his former co-worker Julie Barnes. When he used his skills to save Wilson Fisk's life as a member of his federal escort, Poindexter was manipulated into becoming Fisk's personal assassin. He was tasked with impersonating Daredevil in order to turn the public against him while ensuring Ray Nadeem and Karen Page did not expose Fisk. Upon the real Daredevil's revelation to Poindexter that Fisk had been playing him and had orchestrated Barnes' murder, Poindexter turned against his superior and went on a rampage at Fisk's wedding in an attempt to kill him. While fighting Daredevil, Poindexter was defeated by Fisk, who broke his spine.

Name: Bullseye (Marvel Comics)
Summary: The man known only as Lester once aimed to become a Major League Baseball player with his immense throwing skill, but his personality led to the game quickly becoming boring for him. Thus, he instead decided to use his talent to become the mercenary assassin Bullseye.

Name: Bullywug
Summary: Bullywugs are amphibious, frog-like humanoids that form crude societies in the damper parts of the world, generally residing in rainforests, caves, and swamps. They form a clans based around their leaders (self-proclaimed "lords of the muck") and capture trespassers, forcing them to grovel before their leaders.

Name: Burmese Python
Summary: The Burmese python is a python that is once considered a subspecies of the Indian python before it was split into its own species in 2009. While Burmese pythons are Vulnerable species in its native range in India, Burmese pythons have taken an invasive stronghold in Florida, with its presence mostly extirpating many native species within their range.

Name: Bushwhacker (Marvel Comics)
Summary: It's inevitable. A slow car wreck -- you see it coming, you can't stop it. And we're the cats that got the cream. Starts as a kiss, then the fenders wrap'round each other, a nice warm metal embrace...like war. Like women...car wrecks...you see it comin' and can't stop it...everything buckles and crumples and melts into one...metal wraps metal, glass showers over twisted bodies.... ...and we're the wreckage...

Name: BX-series droid commando
