Summary: BX-series droid commandos, also known as commando droids, were a type of advanced battle droid used by the Confederacy of Independent Systems during the Clone Wars. They were created as an improvement over the standard B1 battle droids and had great agility and far superior computer processing power. They were feared for their accuracy with blasters and fighting skill as well as the fact that they did not go down easily.

Name: Caitlin (Pokémon)
Summary: Caitlin is a Pokémon Trainer that first appeared in Johto as the princess of the Battle Castle. She later reappeared as one of the Elite Four of the Unova Region.

Name: Calamité
Summary: Something appeared for a second on the big ball head!!! That was... A [Rock/Paper/Scissors] sign?

Name: California Sea Lion
Summary: The California sea lion (Zalophus californianus) is a species of eared seal native to the coastlines of western North America. It is the fastest species of seal in the world, and can swim up to 25 miles per hour.

Name: Cambion
Summary: Cambions are the spawn of demons mating with humans, generally between a succubus (or an incubus) as well as a mortal being. The result is a demi-fiend, something not wholly one or the other. Many such Cambions result from demon lords themselves, especially Graz'zt, who commonly partakes of earthly flesh.

Name: Camel
Summary: Camels are animals domesticated for millenia. They are primarily domesticated for desert travel and the transport of goods, but they have also been used for textiles, warfare, dairy products, and meat. There are two types of camels: dromedary and bactrian camels, both which are distinguished by the amount of humps on their back. 94% of the camels are dromedary camels while the remaining 6% are bactrian camels. A population of wild bactrian camels live in parts of northern China and southern Mongolia; however, these camels are critically endangered. An adult male dromedary camel typically weighs in at around 300 to 600 kg. An adult male bactrian camel, however, weighs in at around 300 to 1000 kg.

Name: Camel (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: The camel is the best mundane mount one can use if they wish to travel through the desert. They are able to endure the desert heat far better then most animals and require little food and water. Some camels are breed for strength and aggression and are used for desert warfare.

Name: Candice (Pokémon)
Summary: Candice is a Gym Leader from Sinnoh and the leader of the Snowpoint Gym.

Name: Captain Atom (Post-Crisis)
Summary: During the Vietnam War, Nathaniel Christopher Adam served in the United States Air Force. Under the watchful eye of Col. Wade Eiling, he was framed for a crime he didn't commit and condemned to death in 1968. He was offered the option to engage in a military experiment with a slim chance of surviving in exchange for a presidential pardon if he survived. The experiment entailed blasting a huge nuclear bomb beneath the hull of a wrecked extra-terrestrial ship while Adam was inside it to evaluate its resilience. Against all chances, Adam lived, with the alien metal merging with his flesh and the surplus energy propelling him twenty years forward in time.

Name: Captain Boomerang Jr. (Post-Crisis)
Summary: Owen Mercer also known as Captain Boomerang Jr. is the son of George Harkness, the original Captain Boomerang and his idol, taking up his mantle after a mission to assassinate the father of Tim Drake went south. He decides to choose to become a different man, to change the outlook of the legacy his father left behind, walking the thin line between hero and villain.

Name: Captain Cold (Post-Crisis)
Summary: Once a jovial, well-respected gentleman thief of a bygone age, Leonard Snart, better known as Captain Cold let his heart grow colder and bitter after the world kept grinding him down and spitting in his face. After many failed heists and the increasing violence of superheroes, Snart became the very thing he hated; a true-blue supervillain, though he never quite lost his core morals of only killing when necessary, or for vengeance. Despite his demeanor and image, Snart was among the most warm-hearted villains on the street, showing compassion for those in need, and truly loved his friends and sister, though rarely let them know it.

Name: Captain Cold (Pre-Crisis)
Summary: Once just a run-of-the-mill thief, Len Snart managed to get his hands on the 'Cold Gun', a piece of strange, futuristic technology capable of freezing seemingly anything it fired at, from people to buildings, from energy constructs to New Gods. With weapon in tole, Snart donned the identity of Captain Cold and quickly became one of Flash's most persistent and deadly foes.

Name: Captain Marvel (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Captain Carol Susan Jane Danvers, also known as Captain Marvel, is a former United States Air Force pilot who, upon being exposed to the energy of the Tesseract, obtained cosmic powers. She was made into a Kree-Human hybrid via a blood transfusion from Yon-Rogg, while having her memories removed, turning her into the Kree's weapon and a member of Starforce. During the Kree's war with the Skrulls, Danvers returned to Earth and began recalling her past, with help from Nick Fury and Maria Rambeau. Danvers also discovered that Yon-Rogg had been manipulating her for years, learning from Talos that the Skrulls were merely seeking to find a new home. With this information, Danvers unlocked her true powers and defeated the Kree invasion onto Earth that was being led by Ronan the Accuser, before setting off out to the far reaches of the galaxy to finish what her late mentor Mar-Vell had once started.

Name: Captain Othelstan
Summary: Captain Othelstan is the leader of the Parnast Cult of the Dragon and direct liaison with Blagothkus. He is a large, powerfully-built figure, and trained in unique means of warfare- specifically, the captain rides wyverns into combat. In terms of the Cult, he is a Dragonsoul- one of the highest ranks below the reformed Cult's leadership, the Wyrmspeakers.

Name: Capybara
Summary: The capybara (Hydrochoerus hydrochaeris) is a giant rodent native from South America. Capybaras are the largest living rodent and a member of the genus Hydrochoerus. They are close relatives include guinea pigs and rock cavies. Capybaras inhabits savannas and dense forests and lives near bodies of water. The capybaras are hunted for its meat and hide and also for grease from its thick fatty skin.

Name: Caracal
Summary: The caracal (Caracal caracal) is a medium-sized wild cat native to Africa, the Middle East, Central Asia, and arid areas of Pakistan and northwestern India. It is characterised by a robust build, long legs, a short face, long tufted ears, and long canine teeth.

Name: Carcass Eater
Summary: Carcass Eaters are enormous rat-like creatures known (and named for) their habit of digging up newly made graves and devouring the corpse within.

Name: Carcharodontosaurus (Real World)
Summary: Carcharodontosaurus is a genus of carcharodontosaurid theropod dinosaur, the name of which is Greak for "jagged toothed lizard," meant to reference it's teeth that were akin to Carcharodon carcharias. It is among the largest theropods to have lived, with the type species Carcharodontosaurus saharicus reaching 12-12.5 meters long and a mass of 5-7 metric tons.[1]

Name: Carcinosoma
Summary: Carcinosoma is a one of the eurypterids, an extinct group of aquatic arthropods. Fossils of Carcinosoma are restricted to deposits of late Silurian (Late Llandovery to Early Pridoli) age. Classified as part of the family Carcinosomatidae, which the genus lends its name to, Carcinosoma contains seven species from North America and Great Britain. Carcinosomatid eurypterids had unusual proportions and features compared to other eurypterids, with a broad abdomen, thin and long tail and spined and forward-facing walking appendages. They were not as streamlined as other groups but had considerably more robust and well developed walking appendages. In Carcinosoma, these spined walking appendages are thought to have been used to create a trap to capture prey in. The telson (final segment of the body) of Carcinosoma appears to have possessed distinct segmentation, Carcinosoma is the only known eurypterid to possess this feature.

Name: Carnivorous Ape
Summary: A larger, stronger, and more violent variant of a regular gorilla, the Carnivorous Ape is a menace for anyone in the jungle. They are extremely smart for an animal, reaching IQ scores over 70, with them also being rather cunning. They prefer to stalk their prey, following them for miles before jumping them. In combat they can either use their claws or their sharp teeth to rip victims to shreds.

Name: Carnotaurus
Summary: Carnotaurus was a theropod dinosaur that existed in South America during the Late Cretaceous. It was a medium-sized theropod, being around 7.5-9 meters long and weighing 1.5 tons. Carnotaurus sastrei is the only known species of its genus.

Name: Carrion Crawler
Summary: Carrion Crawlers are the ultimate parasite, feeding on all decomposing parts of rotten corpses- even the bones. It prefers not to compete with other scavengers, but will instead remain patiently in places of death and wait for the sign of coming prey- light. A carrion crawler will follow a torch for hours or longer, awaiting the bearer's death.

Name: Cassowary
Summary: Cassowaries are known as the third tallest bird (behind the emu and ostrich) and the second heaviest bird (behind the ostrich). Cassowaries, however, are #1 in the aggression department, having been known to attack humans, occasionally fatally. If you see a cassowary, do not crouch or turn your back against it; instead, keep a good eye on the cassowary and move away. Female cassowaries average at a weight of 58.5 kg while males average in at 29-34 kg. Of all birds, the cassowary is among the most closely related to their dinosaur ancestors.

Name: Cat (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Sheng Kuei is a Chinese hitman who operates globally under the alias of the Cat. A master of kung-fu on par with Shang-Chi, he has been a frequent thorn and a reluctant ally to the hero in their extensive history together.

Name: Catman (Post-Crisis)
Summary: Thomas Blake is Catman, a former super-criminal and enemy of Batman, who had somewhat reformed and turned his efforts for good instead of evil. Despite still upholding poor regard for the law, Catman has become an anti-hero for his intermittent code of honor.

Name: Catoblepas
Summary: A head of a a bufflo, legs of a hippopotamus, and a tail with a mace on the end alongside an extremely long neck, the Catoblepas is a terrible beast which no adventurer wants to meet.

Name: Cattle
Summary: The Cow is a domesticated ungulate and a popular species used as livestock. The docile and castrated male version of the species is called an Ox, and is usually trained as a draft animal. A Bull is the non-castrated version of an Ox, used for bullfighting. It is primarily herbivorous, but has been known to eat small animals.

Name: Catwoman (Post-Crisis)
Summary: Selina Kyle, also known by her alias, Catwoman, is a costumed thief of Gotham City. Her criminal activities are often tempered by a reluctant altruism, making her an inconsistent villain and occasional heroine. She regularly eludes capture by the Dark Knight, and maintains a complicated, adversarial relationship with Batman that frequently turns flirtatious and occasionally romantic. Over the years, their relationship has developed to the point where they each have both become increasingly reliable allies. She is also the daughter of crime boss Rex “The Lion” Calabrese, and heiress to his crime family.

Name: Cave Bear
Summary: The Cave Bear is an extinct species of bear that lived during the Ice Age from 250,000 years ago to 24,000 years ago. Unlike modern grizzly bears, which only went into caves during hibernation season, cave bears resided in caves throughout their life. According to genetic research, 0.9 to 2.4% of cave bear DNA is found in modern bears. Cave bears were comparable in size to polar bears with an average weight range of 350-600 kg for males and 225-250 kg for females. Some large specimens were recorded to weigh up to 1000 kg.

Name: Cave Fisher
Summary: The Cave Fisher is a spider like creature which primarily lives underground. It produces a sticky filament in order to trap prey and allow it to easily drag it to itself, in case where it's successful it'll use its big claws to cut the prey into various chunks.

Name: CBU-97 Sensor Fuzed Weapon
Summary: The CBU-97 Sensor Fuzed Weapon is a United States Air Force Cluster Bomb developed by Textron Defense Systems. The weapon is designed for destroying vehicles using an explosively fromed penetrator. Unlike standard Cluster Bombs, a CBU-97 detect the target using laser sensors and infrared sensors.

Name: Centaur (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: Centaurs are a species of half-horse half-humanoid creatures that often wander the planes in tribal communities. Typically Centaurs will avoid conflicts though are known to fight fiercely and to the death if pressed. It is the nature of centaurs to make enormous treks across entire continents, and might take decades to return. Often a conflict will start due to settlements appearing in their nomadic pathways.

Name: Chainsaw (Real World)
Summary: This page contains or depicts disturbing and/or graphic content that some may find upsetting, and that is only intended for mature audiences. Please proceed with caution.

Name: Chairman Rose
Summary: Chairman Rose is the president of Macro Cosmos and the chairman of the Galar Pokémon League. He was the first person to endorse Leon as a Champion, and is also currently sponsoring Bede's Gym Challenge. He also designed and developed the metropolis of Wyndon, which houses the headquarters for both the Galar Pokémon League and Macro Cosmos.

Name: Chameleon (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Born a Russian citizen named Dmitri Smerdyakov (Russian: Дмитрий Смердяков), he was the half-brother of Sergei Kravinoff.

Name: Changeling (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: A race with the ability to freely shapeshift their body, their origins are shrouded in mystery. Some sources say they are fey, while others have them as descendants of Doppelgangers. No matter which origin you believe, the Changelings are unrivaled when it comes to disguising their form and using that to their advantage.

Name: Cheetah
Summary: The cheetah is a feline and a member of the "big cat family". They hunt by ambush and running full speed towards the prey, then sinking their teeth into their throat until the prey suffocates. The cheetah has a weight of 77 to 143 pounds and is the fastest land animal in real life.

Name: Cheetah (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: Found in tropical plains and grasslands, the Cheetah is the only cat with non retractable claws. If taken young they can be domesticated. They are skilled hunters, and are incredibly fast as well.

Name: Cheren (Pokémon)
Key: '''By Himself''' | '''Pokémon Team (Early Game)''' | '''Pokémon Team (End Game)''' | '''Pokémon Team (Post-Game)''' | '''Pokémon Team (Gym Battle)'''
Summary: Cheren, "The one who seeks the right path" is a main character in Pokémon Black/White and its sequel, Pokémon Black/White 2. Cheren, Bianca and Hilbert all went off on their Pokémon journey on the same day and thus their individual journeys intersected quite often, with Cheren occasionally finding himself duking it out with Hilbert and fighting by his side against Team Plasma. Though Cheren sometimes comes off as cold and distant, he's actually a good hearted and very honest person who seeks to do the right thing. He is also very smart and knowledgeable about Pokémon.

Name: CheyTac Intervention
Summary: The CheyTac Intervention, also known as the CheyTac M200, is an American bolt-action sniper rifle manufactured by CheyTac USA, which can also be classified as an anti-materiel rifle. It is fed by a 7-round detachable single-stack magazine (an optional 5-round magazine is also available). It is specifically chambered in either .408 Chey Tac or .375 Chey Tac ammunition. CheyTac Inc. states that the system is capable of delivering sub-MOA accuracy at ranges of up to 2,500 yd (2,286 m). It is based on the EDM Arms Windrunner.

Name: Chimera (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: Chimeras are creations of the Demon Lord Demogorgon, and famous creatures of legend- the result of fusing a goat, a lion, and a dragon together. Each head maintains a different personality trait latent to that creature- lions to hunt and protect their lands, dragons to seek treasure and slay, and the goat head to simply fight to the absolute death. A chimera is a relatively simple creature and can be lured into service of more powerful creatures easily.

Name: Chimpanzee
Summary: The Chimpanzee is a primate and is the closest relative to humans (According to studies, their DNA is extremely similar to that of humans). They mainly eat fruit, vegetables and sometimes meat.

Name: Chitauri (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: The Chitauri are a race of cybernetically enhanced aliens who serve under the leadership of Thanos, who gave them over to Loki for use in his invasion of Earth in an attempt to acquire the Tesseract. Though they successfully invaded the planet through a wormhole created by the Tesseract, they were ultimately defeated by the Avengers.

Name: Chocomon (Wallace)
Summary: Chocomon is an antagonist in Digimon Adventure 02: Digimon Hurricane Landing!! Transcendent Evolution!! The Golden Digimentals. He is one of Wallace's partner Digimon, being the twin brother of Terriermon. He was driven insane by a virus, forcing the Chosen Children to fight him to prevent him from doing irreparable damage.

Name: Choker
Summary: Chokers lurk underground and in urban areas, lashing out at whatever prey happens to wander by. It is capable of extending its limbs massively due to limited structure in them- merely cartilage joints.

Name: Choyun
Summary: nan

Name: Chuul
Summary: Chuuls are the creations of the mighty abeloths created by twisting normal marine life so that they could have servants on the land. All chuuls are the creations of these eldritch aquatic creatures, and have survived since the fall of the Aboleth's empire, constantly growing.

Name: Cinderspawn
Summary: Cinderspawn are undead elementals of flame. They have burnt out, and have their lifespan extended supernaturally. Now, in undeath, they seek to eliminate the heat of the living.

Name: Cioccolata
Summary: Cioccolata is a minor antagonist in JoJo's Bizarre Adventure Part V: Vento Aureo. A former doctor who was fired for "accidentally" killing a patient during surgery, he joins Passione alongside his "pet", Secco, as one of the Boss' Guard Squad members. Due to his malevolent nature, he is rarely called upon, but the Boss had no other choice but to call him to fight Bruno Bucciarati and his gang in Rome.

Name: Circus Baby (Games)
Key: '''Circus Baby''' | '''Scrap Baby''' | '''Circus Baby (UCN)''' | '''Scrap Baby (UCN)''' | '''Circus Baby (Special Delivery)'''
Summary: Circus Baby was the mascot of Circus Baby's Pizza World, a pizzeria made by William Afton. Alongside this, the "Funtime" animatronics were rented out to birthday parties, but this was merely a front for Afton's true goals with the animatronics: to abduct children and allow Afton to experiment on them in his underground bunker to discover the secrets of Remnant. Circus Baby was originally made for Afton's daughter, Elizabeth, but he forbade her from getting near Baby due to her programming.[6] Ignoring her father's warnings, Elizabeth got alone with Circus Baby, and was snatched and sealed inside of the animatronic, where she would come to die and possess Baby.[7] After Circus Baby's Pizza World closed down, Baby was trapped inside of the rental bunker until her brother, Michael Afton, came to the bunker to find her as per his father's instructions.[8] Despite seemingly still caring about her brother, Baby's isolation-induced madness lead her to fuse with the other animatronics into Ennard and scoop out Mike's innards to inhabit his body, allowing her to escape her prison.[2] The other animatronics within would come to reject her,[9] and she would rebuild herself as Scrap Baby, now intent on following in her murderous father's footsteps.[10]

Name: Clair (Pokémon)
Key: Herself | Gym Battle | Postgame | Pokémon World Tournament
Summary: Clair is the 8th and final Gym Leader in the Johto region. Born to the same clan of Dragon Tamers as Lance (and also being his cousin), Clair has had an affinity for Dragon type Pokémon ever since she was a child. Not to be outdone by her cousin, who became a member of the Elite Four when she was young, Clair too trained vigorously in the ways of Dragon type Pokémon until she finally became the Gym Leader of her hometown. However, as she ascended to the role of Gym Leader, Lance too ascended beyond a member of the Elite Four to become the Indigo League Champion, driving her motivation to catch up to him and prove herself as the ultimate Dragon type Trainer even further to this day.

Name: Clemont
Summary: Clemont is the Lumiose City Gym Leader; the fifth Gym Leader that a Pokémon Trainer must face if they want to challenge the Kalos Elite Four. For the Lumiose Gym’s challenge before the actual Gym battle, much like Blaine, his little sister Bonnie likes to quiz would-be challengers on general information on Pokémon, with the punishment of facing a trainer if they answer wrong.

Name: Cleveland-class Light Cruiser
Summary: The Cleveland-class light cruisers were built for the U.S. Navy during World War II, and were the most numerous class of light cruisers ever built. The ships were designed with the goal of increased cruising range, anti-aircraft armament, torpedo protection, etc., compared with earlier U.S. cruisers. Fifty-two ships of this class were originally planned, but nine of them were completed as the light aircraft carriers of the Independence class, and two of them were completed to a somewhat different design, called the Fargo class. The Fargo-class cruisers were a modified version of the previous Cleveland-class cruiser design; the main difference was a more compact pyramidal superstructure with single trunked funnel, intended to improve the arcs of fire of the anti-aircraft guns. In all, 13 Fargo-class ships were planned but only Fargo and Huntington were ever completed, the rest being cancelled at varying states of completion with the de-escalation of World War II. Of the 27 Cleveland-class cruisers that were commissioned, one (Galveston) was completed as a guided missile cruiser and five were later modified as Galveston and Providence-class guided missile cruisers. Following the naming convention at the time, all the ships completed as cruisers were named for US cities and towns.

Name: Cloak (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Tyrone Johnson is the "dark" half of the vigilante duo known as Cloak and Dagger. After a drug-related experiment awakened his powers, he became a living personification of darkness. Cloak is the Yin to his partner Dagger's Yang. Superheroes of the streets, Cloak and Dagger wage a war against dangerous drugs and drug-related crimes.

Name: Clock King (William Tockman)
Summary: William Tockman was a criminal who was said to only have 7 months to live, causing him to become obsessed with time keeping. Even though he outlived his expected life-expectancy by decades, he never outgrew his love for time. Though he briefly became a hero and even a member of the Justice League, he soon fell into the grasps of villainy once again.

Name: Clouded Leopard
Summary: The clouded leopard (Neofelis nebulosa) is a wild cat inhabiting dense forests from the foothills of the Himalayas through mainland Southeast Asia into South China. Its head-and-body length ranges from 68.6 to 108 cm (27.0 to 42.5 in) with a 61 to 91 cm (24 to 36 in) long tail. It uses its tail for balancing when moving in trees and is able to climb down vertical tree trunks head first. It rests in trees during the day and hunts by night on the forest floor. They have two subspecies: the Mainland clouded leopard & Sunda clouded leopard, with the later being the largest.[1][2]

Name: CMMG Mk47 Mutant
Summary: The CMMG Mk47 Mutant is an American-made semi-automatic rifle chambered in 7.62×39mm caliber, made by CMMG Inc. It can accept all types of 7.62-type magazines, including steel, polymer and drum magazines.

Name: Cockatrice (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: The Cockatrice is a combination of chicken, reptile, and bat- and is renowned for its capability of turning foes to stone, making it a feared creature in the lower echelons of magical threats. They are predatory and will eat anything from berries to creatures smaller than itself.

Name: Coelophysis
Summary: Coelophysis is a genus of small, carnivorous dinosaurs that lived during the Late Triassic period. The name "Coelophysis" means "Hollow Form" and refers to the hollow bones that were a notable characteristic of this dinosaur.

Name: Coldlight Walker
Summary: People die in many places and due to various reasons, and those who die due to extreme cold can have the misfortune of becoming a Coldlight Walker.

Name: Colleen Wing (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Colleen Wing is a skilled martial artist who was trained by the mysterious Bakuto. She would later open up her own dojo in New York City. Colleen would eventually meet Danny Rand and help him adjust to the changes that had occurred in the city since his disappearance 15 years prior.

Name: Colonel Radec
Summary: Colonel Mael Radec was the leader of the Helghast forces defending the Helghan capital of Pyrrhus City. He is the founder of Radec Academy and Scolar Visari's personal bodyguard. He is the secondary antagonist of Killzone 2 and is known to be one of the most ruthless enemies there.

Name: Colossal Squid
Summary: Colossal squids (Mesonychoteuthis hamiltoni) are large cephalopods that live within deep ocean waters in the Southern Ocean. They are one of the largest of all living invertebrates, and the largest living cephalopod, with an estimated maximum length and weight of 14 meters and 750 kilograms.

Name: Colress
Key: '''By Himself''' | '''Pokémon Team (Route 4)''' | '''Pokémon Team (Pokémon World Tournament)''' | '''Pokémon Team (Plasma Frigate)''' | '''Pokémon Team (Post-Game Battles)''' | '''Pokémon Team (Battle Tree)'''
Summary: However, I disagree!

Name: Colt Anaconda
Summary: Introduced in 1990, the Colt Anaconda is a large frame double-action revolver featuring a full length under-barrel ejection-rod lug and six round cylinder, designed and produced by the Colt's Manufacturing Company. Chambered for the powerful .44 Magnum and .45 Colt centerfire ammunition cartridges, the Anaconda marked the Hartford, Connecticut firm’s first foray into the popular large-bore Magnum pistol market.

Name: Colt Detective Special
Summary: The Colt Detective Special is a six-shot, carbon steel framed, 2" barreled, double-action revolver, and the first example of a class of firearms known to gun enthusiasts as "snubnosed revolvers". Made by Colt's Manufacturing Company this model revolver, as the name "Detective Special" suggests, was intended to be concealed weapon used by plainclothes police detectives.

Name: Colt Paterson
Summary: The Colt Paterson is the very first commercial repeating firearm with a revolving cylinder (known as a revolver). It was created by Samuel Colt in 1836.

Name: Colt Python
Summary: The Colt Python is a .357 Magnum caliber revolver formerly manufactured by Colt's Manufacturing Company of Hartford, Connecticut. It is sometimes referred to as a "Combat Magnum". It was first introduced in 1955, the same year as Smith & Wesson's M29 .44 Magnum. Now discontinued, the Colt Python was intended for the premium revolver market segment. Some firearm collectors and writers such as Jeff Cooper, Ian V. Hogg, Chuck Hawks, Leroy Thompson, Scott Wolber, Renee Smeets and Martin Dougherty have described the Python as the finest production revolver ever made.

Name: Colt Single Action Army
Summary: The Colt Single Action Army, also known as the Single Action Army, SAA, Model P, Peacemaker and M1873, is a single-action revolver with a revolving cylinder holding six metallic cartridges. It was designed for the U.S. government service revolver trials of 1872 by Colt's Patent Firearms Manufacturing Company—today's Colt's Manufacturing Company—and was adopted as the standard military service revolver until 1892.

Name: Colt Walker
Summary: The Colt Walker, often known as the Walker Colt, is a single-action revolver with a revolving cylinder holding six charges of black powder behind six bullets (typically .44 caliber lead balls). It was designed in 1846 as a collaboration between Captain Samuel Hamilton Walker and American firearms inventor Samuel Colt.

Name: Condiment King (Post-Crisis)
Summary: Mitchell Mayo, once an average guy went inexplicably crazy and donned the identity of the Condiment King to cause crime. He was shown tormenting multiple policemen with his special designed sauce, until he was swiftly defeated by Batgirl and Robin. He was then taken to Arkham Asylum, where he eventually was able to work in the kitchen and fuel his obsession, as well as improve upon his formula. This was further aided by Poison Ivy, who taught him vast knowledge on roots, herbs, and spices. Years later, he would get out of Arkham and be "jokerized". Jokerization is stated to amplify the infected's personality, which actually made Mitchell a credible threat. This would almost cause the Birds of Prey to lose to him, as they though he was a joke. It is later stated due to the nature of Condiment King's obsession/portrayal as a joke, juries and parole boards don't take him seriously, thus allowing him to be set free on Gotham again and again. During Final Crisis Aftermath, Mitchell was one of Immortus' followers, The Army of the Endangered, and was cybernetically enhanced by the brilliant Professor Achilles Milo. He was the one to introduce the "Human Flame" to the group, which would be a mistake. Human Flame would rebel, and along with Seductress, kill every member of The Army of the Endangered, including Mitchell.

Name: Conductor (The Final Station)
Summary: The conductor is the engineer of one of the last few trains in a dying world where a zombie-alien apocalypse has occurred. His job is to keep the passengers alive as well as maintaining the train.

Name: Corki
Summary: The yordle pilot Corki loves two things above all others: flying, and his glamorous mustache... though not necessarily in that order. After leaving Bandle City, he settled in Piltover and fell in love with the wondrous machines he found there. He dedicated himself to the development of flying contraptions, leading an aerial defense force of seasoned veterans known as the Screaming Yipsnakes. Calm under fire, Corki patrols the skies around his adopted home, and has never encountered a problem that a good missile barrage couldn’t solve.

Name: Corpse Rat Swarm
Summary: Corpse Rats are undead rats that swarm in countless multitudes to devour the flesh of the living. They essentially serve the same purpose as zombies in terms of undead classification.

Name: Cottonmouth (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Cornell Stokes, also known as Cottonmouth, is a crime boss stationed in Harlem, New York City. His negative influence on the people of Harlem led him to be opposed by Luke Cage.

Name: Cotylorhynchus
Summary: Cotylorhynchus is an extinct genus of herbivorous caseid synapsids that lived during the late Lower Permian (Kungurian) and possibly the early Middle Permian (Roadian) in what is now Texas and Oklahoma in the United States.

Name: Coyote
Summary: The coyote (Canis latrans) is a carnivorous animal that is native to North America. It is closely related to the Gray Wolf and is much smaller than the more famous canine. It mainly eats meat, though it may also eat fruits and vegetables occasionally. The coyote has 19 recognized subspecies, with one of the most common being the Western Coyote, and the largest subspecies being the Eastern Coyote, which is the result of various historical and recent matings with various types of wolves.

Name: Crag Cat
Summary: Able to live at any terrain, the Crag Cat has earned itself the nickname "Hunters-of-Men" due to its great strength and resilience.

Name: Crawling Claw
Summary: Crawling Claws are the dismembered hands of murderous humanoids, animated by evil spellcasters to continue the slaughter they wrought in life. Essentially, a ritual is done to place the soul of a creature in the severed hand, allowing it to work as a laborer for evil casters. Notably, these evil beings are immune to the powers of others concerning undead- and indeed, since their soul is totally under the supervision of their caster, they cannot be affected by such powers, making them ideal servants.

Name: Crazy Quilt (Post-Crisis)
Summary: Paul Dekker was a criminal artist, who left hidden messages in his paintings leading to the hiding places of his ill-gotten goods. His career came to an end, however, when he was betrayed by a henchman, suffering a gunshot wound that robbed him of his sight. Desperate to regain his vision, he accepted an experimental procedure. While the surgery did restore his ability to see, it was entirely in bright, disorienting colors. Dekker was driven mad, and took up the new identity of Crazy Quilt.

Name: Creeper (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: Creepers are green, explosive creatures found prowling the Overworld at night. They are evil creatures that seek to explode and destroy anything else, destroying themselves and their targets in one destructive blast. They are known to become even more powerful when struck with lightning, making them an even greater threat.

Name: Cretoxyrhina (Real World)
Summary: Cretoxyrhina was an ancient mackerel shark alive during the Mesozoic era.

Name: Crimson Dynamo I
Summary: Anton Vanko was born in Armenia and went on to becoming one of Russia's top inventors, and supposedly the world's greatest expert in electricity. One of his inventions was an armor that could control electromagnetism. With its red covering, he named it the Crimson Dynamo. After a demonstration in which he used the armor to destroy a dummy robot modeled after Iron Man and controlled a tank, he was sent to the United States to sabotage Stark Industries, the main supplier of armament technology for the American government. Vanko regretted being set on this course as he admired the young Tony Stark's work, and during his fight with Iron Man, he was convinced to serve the United States, leaving his dastardly ways.

Name: Crinkle
Summary: Living in the Firefly Cellar Crinkle is a chaotic neutral Kenku. She is a general grump who mainly cares for her own belongings, with her even having a rare magical ring. She lost a good chunk of her feathers, with her covering that with her robe.

Name: Crocodile (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: A large reptile, the Crocodile is one of the many animals that roam the land. They are skilled hunters that employ stealth, usually hiding underwater to let them bite their prey. The crocodile is even found in places such as the Feywilds, with the Feymire Crocodile being larger and stronger then its regular counterpart.

Name: Crossbones (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Brock Rumlow was a HYDRA infiltrator who had been posing as a S.H.I.E.L.D. agent, and STRIKE's team field commander. Due to his training from S.H.I.E.L.D. and HYDRA, Rumlow had become a world-class combatant, with extensive experience in street fighting, martial arts, and military combat techniques.

Name: Crossfire (Marvel Comics)
Summary: William Cross was born in Madison, Wisconsin. Cross joined the CIA with the intent to learn the secrets of the trade and to make contacts which might one day prove useful to him. He intended to use CIA training and knowledge to obtain a profit for himself, working as a colleague of Marc Spector. Quitting it soon after, Cross used his skills and resources to begin a number of highly profitable criminal operations including drug trafficking, extortion, and assassinations. Assuming the codename Crossfire, he diverted a portion of his profits to hire a small army of mercenaries to serve as his enforcers. Crossfire's goal became to foment disorder and subversion within society in order to make a profit. At one point in his career, some of his enemies booby-trapped his headquarters. The ensuing explosion robbed him of his left eye and ear, plus 85% of his hearing. He replaced his losses with cybernetic equipment. Crossfire eventually located the men who had injured him, and eliminated them personally. He has been a recurring foe of Hawkeye and Mockingbird ever since.

Name: Crowbar
Summary: Crowbars are tools used for opening nailed wooden crates or prying away boards, or in criminal applications, for prying open doors and safes in burglary. In mining, they can be used to break and remove rock. They are usually made from medium-carbon steel, but can also be made out of titanium, which is lighter. In a fight, they are capable of stabbing their opponent to the point of penetrating bone in addition to the ability of being used as a club-style weapon.

Name: Cryolophosaurus
Summary: Cryolophosaurus is a genus of large theropod that inhabited Antarctica during the early Jurassic. Its name comes from the Greek words κρυος, which means "cold" or "frozen"; λοφος, which means "crest"; σαυρος, which means "lizard." The Antarctica around the time of this theropod was warmer than modern times, with a temperate, humid climate and temperatures ranging between 17-18 degrees Celsius[1] The most distinctive feature of Cryolophosaurus is its "pompadour" crest, which had even named it the nickname Elvisaurus due to its similarity to the famous singer.

Name: Cube Monsters (Fortnite)
Summary: The Cube Monsters are a recurring enemy from Fortnite: Battle Royale, named for their affinity and relation to The Cube. The Monsters are spawned by Cube Fragments, which can quickly create hordes of the Monsters. Later in the story, the Ice King was able to create similar Winter themed Monsters with striking resemblance to the Cube Monsters.

Name: CV90
Summary: The Combat Vehicle 90 (CV90) (Swedish: stridsfordon 90ⓘ, strf 90 or Stridsfordon 90) is a family of Swedish tracked armoured combat vehicles designed by the Swedish Defence Materiel Administration (FMV), Hägglund & Söner and Bofors during the mid-1980s to early 1990s, before entering service in Sweden in the mid-1990s. The CV90 platform design has continuously evolved from the Mk 0 to the current Mk IV with technological advances and changing battlefield requirements.

Name: Cyclops (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: Cyclopes are savage giants that have forsaken the gods. Though not unintelligent, they prefer simple lifestyles tending to livestock for food, and generally remain reclusive. Cyclops are only sociable among their kin, meeting to trade and find mates occasionally. They bear a strong distaste for humans and other sentient species, though will normally never attack unless they are extremely vulnerable.

Name: Cyclops (Marvel Comics)
Key: '''Base''' | '''1/5 of the Phoenix Force''' | '''1/2 of the Phoenix Force''' | '''Dark Phoenix'''
Summary: Cyclops, also known as Scott Summers, is the leader of the X-Men and one of Professor Xavier's first students - he and Jean Grey have been a couple for many years and although not always getting along with some of the X-Men (such as Wolverine) Scott always tries to do his job professionally and with consideration for others, though this can make him come across as bossy at times to people that don't understand or appreciate his style of leadership.

Name: Cymbospondylus
Summary: Cymbospondylus is a genus of large, even gigantic ichthyosaurs, and was a more primitive representative of that group of marine reptiles, with a slenderer build than the dolphin-like ichthyosaurs that would emerge later. It lived around 251–242 million years ago, during the early to middle Triassic in oceans around present-day North America and Europe. The largest of this genus were not only one of the largest ichthyosaurs, but also among the largest animals of its time.

Name: Cynthia (Pokémon)
Summary: Cynthia is the champion of the Sinnoh region's Pokémon League. She makes several appearances before she is battled, helping the player along the way. She has a lot of interest in the mythology of the Sinnoh region. She also appears in Johto and Unova in the next sets of games.

Name: Cyrus
Key: '''By Himself''' | '''Pokémon Team (Celestic Town)''' | '''Pokémon Team (Team Galactic HQ)''' | '''Pokémon Team (Distortion World)''' | '''Pokémon Team (Gen 7)'''
Summary: Cyrus is the nihilistic main antagonist of the Sinnoh Pokémon games. He is the leader of Team Galactic and wishes to use the power of Palkia and Dialga to erase the universe, and remake it as a realm devoid of spirit.

Name: CZ 75
Summary: The CZ 75 is a semi-automatic pistol made by Czech firearm manufacturer ČZUB. First introduced in 1975, it is one of the original "wonder nines" and features a staggered-column magazine, all-steel construction, and a hammer forged barrel. It is widely distributed throughout the world and is the most common handgun in the Czech Republic. Firearms expert Colonel Jeff Cooper considered the CZ 75, at least its original version (short rail), to be the best 9mm service pistol ever made.

Name: Dacentrurus
Summary: Dacentrurus is a genus of dacentrurine stegosaurid. Its name comes from the Greek words meaning "tail full of points," (δα~, or da~, which means "very" or "full of"; κέντρον, or kentron, which means "point"; οὐρά, or oura, which means "tail")[1] describing the spines that run along its tail. It lived in present day Europe around 154-140 million years ago, spanning the late Jurassic to early Cretaceous. By length and mass, Dacentrurus is among the largest (if not the largest) stegosaurid dinosaur, on average exceeding the size of both species of the more iconic Stegosaurus.

Name: Daeodon
Summary: Daeodon is a genus of entelodont, a group informally referred to as "Hell Pigs" or "Terminator Pigs"; however, entelodonts are thought to be more closely related to hippos and cetaceans than pigs, hogs, or peccaries. Among the entelodonts, Daeodon is the largest known from a complete skeleton. Its name comes from the Greek words daios, meaning "hostile" or "dreadful," and odon, meaning "teeth."[1] The specifics of this creature's diet are uncertain, but it is most likely an opportunistic omnivore. Though some have suggested it would have more likely been a scavenger, there has been evidence in other entelodonts of predatory behavior and it had multiple characteristics that would indicate it was a predator.[2] It inhabited North America during the late Oligocene to early Miocene epochs, with many fossils found in the Agate Fossil Beds, inhabiting a seasonal floodplain environment.

Name: Dahlia (Pokémon)
Summary: Dahlia is the Frontier Brain of the Battle Arcade. She gives the Silver Print when defeated, and the Gold Print when re-challenged.

Name: Daimon Hellstrom (Marvel Comics)
Summary: I am the scion of hell, yet I have forsaken that world to walk among men. I am heir-apparent to the throne of Satan, yet I denied myself the power. I am son of demon and mortal, yet I am neither demon nor mortal. I am the Son of Satan. I am myself.

Name: Daisy Johnson (Quake)
Summary: Daisy Johnson is the daughter of Calvin Zabo with a woman with the inhuman gene. Her mother gave her to adoption little after she was born, she ended up being adopted and her name become Cory Sutter. As a teen she tried to steal but ended up being caught and causing an earthquake, she was interrogated by Nick Fury who told her the truth about her biological parents and recruited her to S.H.I.E.L.D. She was personally trained by Nick Fury to become the best spy and at the age of 18 she become the director of S.H.I.E.L.D. She named herself Quake after an encounter with the avengers.

Name: Daredevil (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Leapfrog: So, the devil ninja guy, he's a lawyer? Daredevil: No. I'm just a big fan of legal dramas.

Name: Daredevil (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Born in the historically gritty or crime-ridden, working-class Irish-American neighborhood of Hell's Kitchen in New York City, Matthew "Matt" Michael Murdock is blinded by a radioactive substance that falls from a truck after he pushes a man to safety from the oncoming vehicle. While he no longer can see, the radioactive exposure heightens his remaining senses beyond normal human ability and gives him a "radar sense". His father, a boxer named Jack Murdock, supports him as he grows up, though Jack is later killed by gangsters after refusing to throw a fight. After donning a yellow and dark red costume (later all dark red), Matt seeks out revenge against his father's killers as the superhero Daredevil, fighting against his many enemies, including Bullseye and Kingpin.

Name: Darius (League of Legends)
Summary: There is no greater symbol of Noxian might than

Name: Darkmantle
Summary: Darkmantles are cave-dwelling creatures that remain in wait on cave ceilings, only moving when a creature passes below. These monsters are renowned for their auras of darkness. The methods of hunting used by darkmantles often causes it to be mistaken as a stalactite.

Name: Darren Cross (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Doctor Darren Cross was the protégé of Hank Pym, who usurped his mentor as CEO of Pym Technologies and rebranded it as Cross Technologies. Cross became obssessed with the Pym Particles and using Pym's technologies to achieve success, but the constant exposure to the particles negatively affected his mind. Cross had developed the Yellowjacket Suit and intended to sell it to HYDRA and the Ten Rings, but Pym and Hope Van Dyne joined forces with Ant-Man, who destroyed his entire research. Driven mad after losing everything he built, Cross wore the suit himself and became Yellowjacket, to get revenge by killing Ant-Man and his family. As Yellowjacket threatened Cassie Lang, he was confronted by Ant-Man, who neutralized him by shrinking him down to a sub-atomic level and destroying his suit.

Name: Daspletosaurus
Summary: Daspletosaurus is a genus of tyrannosaurid theropod dinosaurs, and was closely related to Tyrannosaurus rex. Its name means "frightful lizard." Three species have been identified: Daspletosaurus torosus, Daspletosaurus horneri, and Daspletosaurus wilsoni. It lived 78–74.4 million years ago, during the late Cretaceous, on the landmass of Laramidia, an island apart of North America when the continent was split by the Western Interior Seaway. It is thought to have coexisted alongside the albertosaurine Gorgosaurus, with niche partitioning limiting competition between the two tyrannosaurids.[1]

Name: Deadpool (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Deadpool (Wade Winston Wilson) is a fictional character, a mercenary and anti-hero appearing in comic books published by Marvel Comics. Created by writer and artist Rob Liefeld and scripted by Fabian Nicieza, Deadpool first appeared in New Mutants #98 (Feb. 1991).

Name: Deadshot (Floyd Lawton)
Summary: Floyd Lawton and his brother Ed both grew up wealthy, but despite their money, the boys did not grow up happy. Both of their parents were sociopathic monsters, constantly fighting and using the boys as ammo. Eventually, their mother convinced Ed to shoot his father. Desperate to keep his beloved brother from going through the guilt of killing someone, Floyd tried to stop his brother by shooting him in the arm with a rifle. But sadly, the branch he was perched on broke, and Floyd accidentally shot his brother in the head, killing him. After this Floyd spiraled into mental instability, honing his marksmanship skills and eventually becoming the masked assassin, Deadshot, and became reputed as the Man Who Never Misses.

Name: Death (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Alice Wu-Gulliver: So.. you’re a- a green witch? Rio Vidal: Um… less a green witch, more, the Green Witch.

Name: Death Dog
Summary: Looking like a black dog with two heads and about the size of a wolf, the Death Dog is a canine that roams primarily the deserts. It holds incredible hate within its heart, and it also has a taste for human flesh which leads it to attack adventures and explorers alike.

Name: Death-Stalker (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Phillip Wallace Sterling was a member of an old, wealthy and prestigious family that had lived in America for centuries. He conducted his first known criminal activities under the alias of the Exterminator. In this role, Sterling was the costumed mastermind behind a series of crimes committed by the original criminal team known as the Unholy Three (Ape-Man, Bird-Man, and Cat-Man). During a clash with the costumed crimefighter Daredevil, Ape-Man succeeded in exiling Daredevil to the void with his t-ray gun. Daredevil was able to use his powers and skills to escape through a dimensional warp, and he tracked the Exterminator and the Unholy Three to their lair. After defeating the four, Daredevil intentionally triggered the explosion of the Exterminator's main displacement machine; he had become temporarily tired of being a costumed super-hero at the time, and he was hoping to end his career as one by faking his own death with the explosion.

Name: Deep Gnome
Summary: Deep Gnomes, also known as Svirfneblin, are Gnomes primarily found underground in the Underdark. Their time in the underground has made so they naturally blend in and understand stone. They possess both great fighting skills and innate magical abilities, which they use greatly in combat.

Name: Deep Scion
Summary: Born of a person submitting themselves towards a great aquatic evil such as a Kraken, the Deep Scion is a monstrous humanoid creature that is able to assume any shape it wants in order to infiltrate society and do said evil being's bidding.

Name: Defenders (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: The Defenders were a team of four street-based superheroes who banded together to save New York City from the Hand.

Name: Deinosuchus
Summary: Deinosuchus is an extinct genus of crocodilian related to the modern alligator that lived 82 to 73 million years ago, during the late Cretaceous period. The name translates as "terrible crocodile" and is derived from the Greek deinos (δεινός), "terrible", and soukhos (σοῦχος), "crocodile". The first remains were discovered in North Carolina (United States) in the 1850s; the genus was named and described in 1909.

Name: Deinotherium
Summary: Deinotherium were a group of large proboscideans similar to elephants, but not as closely related. The name is derived from the Ancient Greek words δεινός, deinos meaning "terrible" and θηρίον, therion meaning "beast." This group lived during the mid Miocene to early Pleistocene throughout East Africa, southern Europe, and and all the way to the Indian subcontinent.

Name: Demon (Season of the Witch)
Summary: After the country suffers from the Black Death, two church elders accuse a girl of being a witch responsible for the destruction.

Name: Demonhive
Summary: Demonhives are massive colonies of millions of tiny, diabolical insects that swarm the Lower Planes, though were first seen on the Infinite layers of the Abyss (hence their name), though were later found elsewhere. By right of sheer numbers they lay waste to entire planar locales, ripping through and absorbing all resources. It is only thanks to their destruction by Planeswalkers and warriors of the Blood War that they don't spread beyond the Lower Planes, bring ruin to all other places of existence. The single greatest sign of a Demonhive infestation outside of direct confrontation is the constant, dizzying drone of its millions of Demonets.

Name: Derro
Summary: Derro are small, pale creatures hailing from the Underdark, with burrows of their kind in almost every major Drow or Mind Flayer city. Despite being generally accepted among such societies, they are largely considered among the lower class. The species as a whole maintains a sort of innate cleverness and sadism towards others, likely owing to their creation story- twisted and tormented beasts from dwarf and human stock, likely made by some lost deity of darkness and madness.

Name: Desiccator
Summary: Desiccators are small undead remains of water elementals. Now dried of their life source (water), they long eternally to quench their undying thirst. These creatures are often mistaken for mummies due to their extremely dry appearance.

Name: Desmatosuchus
Summary: Desmatosuchus is a genus of large, quadrupedal aetosaur Pseudosuchian; its name comes from the Greek words δεσμός (desmos), which means "link," and σοῦχος (soûkhos), which means "crocodile." This heavily armored reptile's back was covered by median scutes surrounded by two more rows of lateral scutes,[1] along with large acromion processes (or shoulder spikes),[2] which would have served as its primary defense against predators such as Postosuchus. It is most widely thought to be a herbivore, with its blunt teeth and shovel-like snout helping it to dig up vegetation to eat.[1][2] It was widely spread across Pangaea during the late Triassic around 228–210 million years ago, found in the Dockum formation, Chinle formation, and Post quarry; the density of numbers in specific areas also hints it was likely a herd animal.[2]

Name: Destiny (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Irene Adler hailed from a prosperous Austrian family, born near the close of the 19th century. Raised in Salzburg, Austria, her mutant gift of precognition emerged at the tender age of 13. Without guidance in harnessing her newfound powers, she faced a deluge of disconcerting, alien sights and sounds. Struggling to preserve her mental faculties, Adler embarked on a journey to record her visions in diaries. a lifeline amidst the chaos. A few years later, Irene hired Raven Darkhölme, a consulting detective, to help her make sense of her diaries. They tried to use Irene's visions to change the future and fell in love in the process. But even though they could make money using Irene's abilities, they couldn't make big changes in society, which left them both frustrated.

Name: Detective Chimp (Post-Flashpoint)
Summary: Bobo T. Chimpanzee, the Detective Chimpanzee, used to be a normal circus animal, until an unlikely series of events led to him drinking from a magical fountain that augmented his mind to an incredible level of intelligence and gifted him immortality.

Name: Diablomon
Summary: Tier: 9-B | High 8-C | At least High 8-C, 8-B via Crazy Giggle, Up to 3-C, Possibly higher with Direct Absorption | 6-C | At least 4-C, Possibly 3-C | Low 1-C, Up to 1-C | Low 1-C, 1-C via Direct Absorption | At least Low 1-C, Up to 1-C

Name: Diaboromon (Digimon Adventure)
Summary: Diaboromon is the main antogonist of Our war game and Diaboromon Strikes back. It hatched as a kuramon from a Digi-Egg that had formed on the Internet from a collection of viruses. It caused constant chaos in the Real World by eating data, and Digivolved rapidly with each sufficient amount of food. It was eventually defeated by Omegamon.

Name: Diamondback (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Willis Stryker, also known as Diamondback, is the half brother of Luke Cage and a deadly criminal equipped with advanced weaponry from Hammer Industries.

Name: Diamondback (Willis Stryker)
Summary: Willis Stryker was born and raised in Harlem, New York. He grew up on the streets alongside Carl Lucas, his best friend and future partner, and founded the Rivals gang together, where he took on the name of Diamondback. Stryker eventually became convinced however, that Lucas had seduced his girlfriend Reva, and in a fit of jealousy, got his ex-girlfriend murdered and his friend jailed.

Name: Dianamon
Summary: Tier: 9-B | High 8-C | 6-C | At least High 6-C | 5-B | 1-C

Name: Diantha
Summary: Diantha is an actress and the Champion of the Kalos region.

Name: Diatryma
Summary: Diatrymas are a species of large, flightless birds who are most often found in the Underdark.

Name: Dilophosaurus
Summary: The Dilophosaurus is a medium sized theropod from the early Jurassic period. It is famous for its appearance in Jurassic Park, where it spits venom at an antagonist before killing and eating him. In real life, it apparently did not have the ability to spit venom.

Name: Dimetrodon
Summary: The Dimetrodon was among the earliest land animals, belonging to a proto-mammalian group known as synapsids. Dimetrodons were predatory creatures, with larger dimetrodons often being apex predators. Despite being confused with dinosaurs, Dimetrodons had a temporal range between 295 and 272 million years ago and were more closely related to mammals than modern reptiles, although they were not direct ancestors.

Name: Dimetrodon (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: While looking like one, the Dimetrodon is in fact not a dinosaur and is closer to mammals than to reptiles They occupy a niche similar to crocodiles but instead of good water mobility the Dimetrodon has excellent sprinting ability which allows it to get to its prey in order to deliver a powerful bite.

Name: Dingo (Real World)
Summary: The Dingo is a dog that is found in Australia. Its taxonomic classification is debated. It is a medium-sized canine that possesses a lean, hardy body adapted for speed, agility, and stamina.

Name: Dinofelis
Summary: Dinofelis was an early saber-toothed cat widely believed to have preyed on early hominids. It's known as a "false saber-toothed cat" since its teeth weren't as knife-like as other saber-toothed cats, resembling the teeth of modern domesticated cats more closely than other felines at the time.

Name: Diprotodon
Summary: Diprotodon is a extinct marsupial that lived in Australia during the Pleistocene era, about two million years ago. Diprotodon was a herbivorous mammal about the size of a hippo, making it the largest marsupial ever. Diprotodon became extinct sometime after 44,000 years ago, after the initial settlement of the continent; the role of human and climatic factors in its extinction are uncertain and contested. The closest surviving relatives of Diprotodon are the wombats and the koala, and so Diprotodon have sometimes been referred to as "giant wombats" in the popular press.

Name: Dire Ape
Summary: A Dire Ape is a far larger and deadlier version of a Gorilla. They are extremely territorial and will try to maul anyone entering their turf.

Name: Dire Boar
Summary: The Dire Boar is a giant variant of the regular boar, it's a rather vicious animal who when engages in combat attempts to tear its enemies into shreds with its tusks. The Dire Boar has 2 variants, the Thunderfury Boar which is a Fey Dire Boar and the Fhorge which is a variant found in the Outlands.

Name: Dire Elk
Summary: A bigger version of an elk, the Dire Elk is a rather aggressive and will try to gore its enemies with its massive antlers. It's incredibly rare, to the point where people believe that sighting is a foreshadowing of important events such as the birth of a king.

Name: Dire Maggot
Summary: An enlarged version of a regular maggot, the Dire Maggot is a larva of a massive flying vermin. Unlike their smaller counterpart which feed only on decaying matter Dire Maggots are capable enough to try and hunt their own food.

Name: Dire Rat
Summary: The city hereby offers a silver coin for each giant rat slain within its walls. To receive payment, evidence must be delivered to the watch captain at the docks between nighsun and dusk.''

Name: Dire Wolf
Summary: The Dire Wolf is an extinct species of the genus Aenocyon that lived in North and South America during the Late Pleistocene and early Holocene epochs.

Name: Dire Wolf (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: The Dire Wolf is a prehistoric version of the regular wolf, it's bigger and deadlier then its regular counterpart. The Dire Wolf is also one of the most popular animals for Druids to assume the form of via their Wild Shape ability in early levels.

Name: Displacer Beast
Summary: Displacer Beasts were the mortal enemies of Blink Dogs, feral feline monstrosities most commonly encountered in the Feywild. They are noted as being huge, and possess heavily mutated genes, which leads to mutant offspring appearing every once in a while. Such mutants will generally lead enormous packs of Displacer Beasts in their hunts for blink dog packs.

Name: Django Freeman
Summary: Tier: 10-A. 9-C with firearms. 8-C with preparation

Name: Dobermann
Summary: The Dobermann is a German breed of medium-large working dog of pinscher type. It was originally bred in Thuringia in about 1890 by Louis Dobermann, a tax collector. It has a long muzzle and – ideally – an even and graceful gait. The ears were traditionally cropped and the tail docked, practices which are now illegal in many countries.

Name: Doctor Strange (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Thor: So, Earth has wizards now? Strange: The preferred term is "Master of the Mystic Arts".

Name: Doedicurus (Real World)
Summary: Doedicurus is an extinct genus of glyptodont from North and South America containing one species, D. clavicaudatus.

Name: Dogo Argentino
Summary: This page contains or depicts disturbing and/or graphic content that some may find upsetting, and that is only intended for mature audiences. Please proceed with caution.

Name: Dolphin (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: One of the many aquatic creatures of the seas, the dolphin is a good aligned mammal that roams said seas. It's incredibly smart, with it being above regular people. They are even able to create entire communities, with them getting other sea creatures to defend said locations.

Name: Domestic Cat
Summary: The Cat, also known as housecat, alley cat or Domestic Cat, is small, furry mammal. It is a subspecies F. s. catus belonging to the species Felis silvestris in the family Felidae. This animal is the most popular pet in the world.

Name: Domestic Sheep
Summary: Since descending from the Asiatic Mouflon (Ovis Orentalis) and Bezoar Ibex (Capra aegagrus) in the middle east 10,500 years before present (YBP),[1][2] the raising of domestic sheep is responsible for much of the world's lamb supply, mutton supply,[1][3] wool,[1] sheep milk,[4][3] wool,[1][3] and cheese.[1][3][5] In 2011, there were more than 1 billion sheep in the world.[4] Their presence as the most common livestock affected the cultures that raised them.[6][7][8] Even domesticated, sheep preferably moves in flocks for protection.[9][10]

Name: Domino (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Neena "Domino" Thurman is a character from Marvel Comics. She is best known as a member of the X-Force. Domino made her first full main story appearance in X-Force #8 as a unique individual from the Wild Pack group driven by the mutant Cable.

Name: Domovoi
Summary: The Domovoi is a fey that lives in homes of creatures such as Gnomes, Dwarves, Kobolds, Orcs and even Ogres and Giants.

Name: Don-Jon Raskin
Summary: Holding multiple jobs from being a miner all the way to a gold prospector Don-Jon Raskin has seen quite a bit, which is reflected by his non nonsense attitude and steel nerves. Don-Jon's experience and intelligence has recently let him to hired to be an overseer of the Mountain Toe Gold Mine's mines.

Name: Doorman (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Being one of the founding members of the Great Lakes Avengers, Doorman AKA DeMarr Davis has a unique ability brought on due to being a mutant. His unique teleportation ability allows his teammates to both perform a stealthy entrance and perform a surprise attack should the need arises. DeMarr's body is actually a portal to the Darkforce Dimension, which allows him to not only teleport but let people walk through him and any solid objects that DeMarr is standing against.

Name: Doppelganger (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: We want what is ours! I chose your chaplain- his life was to be mine! His wealth, his fine robes, his women- had you not interfered, they would all belong to me!''

Name: Doric
Summary: Doric is an tiefiling who lives in the Neverwinter Wood after being abandoned there as a child and created among an community of wood elves. Even thought she keeps herself emotionally distant she has great affection for her land and her fellow comrades.

Name: Dorudon
Summary: Dorudon is a genus of moderately-sized basilosaurid cetacean. Its name means "spear tooth." It lived 40.4–33.9 million years ago during the Eocene epoch, in warm waters worldwide, with fossils found in the United States, Egypt and the western Sahara, Pakistan, and New Zealand. When first found, it was thought to be a juvenile specimen of its larger relative Basilosaurus, but after later analysis, it was revealed to be a creature entirely.[1]

Name: Dorugoramon
Summary: Tier: Unknown | 9-B | High 8-C | 6-C | 3-C | 1-C

Name: Dottie Underwood
Summary: Dottie Underwood was a Russian spy, who was trained from a young age in the red room, a Soviet training program. She ended up working with Leviathan, to bring down the SSR, and kill Howard Stark. She is defeated by Peggy Carter, and captured by the SSR, and she later helped them out, but then escaped.

Name: Dr. Mundo
Summary: Utterly mad, tragically homicidal, and horrifyingly purple, Dr. Mundo is what keeps many of Zaun's citizens indoors on particularly dark nights. Now a self-proclaimed physician, he was once a patient of Zaun's most infamous asylum. After "curing" the entire staff, Dr. Mundo established his practice in the empty wards that once treated him and began mimicking the highly unethical procedures he had so often experienced himself. With a full cabinet of medicines and zero medical knowledge, he now makes himself more monstrous with each injection and terrifies the hapless "patients" who wander near his office.

Name: Dragonne
Summary: Dragonnes are apparent hybrids of bronze dragons and lions, with fur replaced by a scaly hide. They are renowned as remorseless hunters of wanderers and travelers- a fact more based on fear than fact. In truth, the Dragonne only attacks those directly threatening its lair.

Name: Dragonnel
Summary: Distant relatives of dragons, the Dragonnel is a decently intelligent creature which can serve as a good mount for those who get their hands on its eggs.

Name: Dragunov Sniper Rifle
Summary: The Dragunov sniper rifle (formal Russian: Сна́йперская Винто́вка систе́мы Драгуно́ва образца́ 1963 года, Snáyperskaya Vintóvka sistém'y Dragunóva obraz'tsá 1963 goda (SVD-63), officially "Sniper Rifle, System of Dragunov, Model of the Year 1963") (GRAU index 6V1 (ГРАУ Индекс 6В1)) is a semi-automatic designated marksman rifle chambered in the 7.62×54mmR cartridge and developed in the Soviet Union.

Name: Dralmorrer Borngray
Summary: Once a member of Evermeet, an Elf territory, Dralmorrer Borngray was an elf supremacist who left his homeland in disgust at the open arms offered to non-elves. He was a member of Eldreth Veluuthra, an organization dedicated to wiping out humankind, among others. However, he saw no means of destroying them and lamented, now wandering the world in search of answers. Eventually, he found Rezmir, a Half-Dragon who convinced him that Tiamat would destroy all non-elves in her coming. Thus, Dralmorrer joined the Cult of the Dragon to serve Rezmir.

Name: Drasna
Summary: nan

Name: Draven
Summary: In Noxus, warriors known as reckoners face one another in arenas where blood is spilled and strength tested—but none has ever been as celebrated as

Name: Dreadpool
Summary: In the alternate reality of Earth-12101, the X-Men attempted to cure Deadpool of his mental illness by bringing him to an appointment with Psycho-Man. However, Psycho-Man had secretly been brainwashing his patients instead of curing them, and his treatment failed to affect Wade, only making his insanity worse. This caused him to go on a universal (eventually multiversal) genocide spree as Dreadpool.

Name: Dretch
Summary: A Dretch is nearly the lowest form of life in the Infinite Layers of the Abyss. A dretch's life is one of torture and slavery, servitude over any other class of demon. It is said a single Balor may own thousands, or even millions of dretches. Every pitiful soul that ends up in hell, every chaotic evil death that doesn't have some divine purpose, becomes a dretch or merely withers away. Thus the armies of the damned are fueled. The only escape is to attain a better form, a difficult process that often takes centuries. Few dretches survive for that long.

Name: Droki
Summary: Living in Gracklstugh, Droki is a Derro criminal who is wanted by major factions due to him engaging in trade with a demon worshiping cult.

Name: Dror Ragzlin
Summary: Dror Ragzlin is a barbarian chieftain of a large goblinoid tribe that resides in the Shattered Sanctum, a former Selunite temple located in the Western Heartlands near the Emerald Grove. As the tribe's de facto leader (and sole hobgoblin member), Dror is one of three leaders of the Absolute Cult in the area, along with Priestess Gut and Minthara. In particular, Dror is interested in discovering an artifact that threatens the Absolute's existence that was rumored to be in the area- to this end, he seeks to investigate a nautiloid crash located not far from his location. Dror is an ambitious individual who sees himself as being better than his fellow True Souls, such that he aims to be the right hand of the Absolute some day.

Name: Dryad (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: Dryads are forest spirits and guardians of the plants within them, generally residing within the trees. Dryads are peaceful by nature (though not unwilling to fight), and are often considered to be exemplary messengers of the gods- including the likes of Corellon Larethian and Erevan Ilesere.

Name: Dunkleosteus terrelli
Summary: Dunkleosteus terrelli,[1][2][3][4] was a member of the extinct genus Dunkleosteus,[4] it roamed the ocean during the Late Devonian,[4][5][6] about 358 to 382 million years ago, measuring at least 4.1 m (13.5 ft) long and 950 to 1200 kg in weight[7] but was likely larger[1][4][5][6][Note 1], the Dunkleosteus was a hypercarnivorous apex predator of its time[1][2]. Few other placoderms, save, perhaps, its contemporary Titanichthys[1], rivaled Dunkleosteus in size[5].

Name: Durandamon
Summary: Tier: Unknown | 9-B | High 8-C | 6-C | At least 4-C, Possibly 3-C | At least 3-C, Possibly higher | Low 1-C

Name: Dust Mephit
Summary: One of the many Mephit types, the Dust Mephit is an impish looking elemental. They are composed of earth and air, with them having great control over dust.

Name: Eblis
Summary: Standing 8 feet tall, the Eblis appears like a regular stork but holds far more nefarious intentions. Unlike a regular bird it delights in hunting and murdering its prey, it also will take any shiny objects from its victims; There're rumors that the Eblis is actually a product of reincarnation of an evil spirit as some sort of punishment.

Name: Ebony Maw (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Ebony Maw is an adopted child of Thanos and a member of the Black Order. After taking the Tesseract with Thanos and his fellow henchmen, Ebony Maw and Cull Obsidian were sent to take the Time Stone from Doctor Strange. Cull Obsidian is teleported away, but Ebony Maw managed to capture Doctor Strange and attempted transport him to Titan on his ship. However, Iron Man and Spider-Man attacked the ship, and Ebony Maw was killed in the skirmish by being thrown into space.

Name: Echo (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Maya Lopez is a deaf member of the Choctaw tribe who moved out of her hometown as a child with her father William Lopez, and became the protégé of Wilson Fisk, growing up under his care. Losing his father due to Ronin's hunt for criminals, Lopez became the Tracksuit Mafia's commander, vowing revenge on Ronin. Lopez worked for Fisk alongside Kazi Kazimierczak. However, Lopez learned that Ronin had seemingly returned, she fell into conflict with Kate Bishop and Clint Barton, who were searching for Ronin's Suit, with Lopez believed that they could be her chance to find Ronin; however, Barton revealed himself to be Ronin.

Name: Edaphosaurus
Summary: Edaphosaurus is a genus of herbivorous synapsid reptiles that are notable for its sail-back. Its name comes from the greek words έδαφος (edaphos), which most directly means "pavement," and σαῦρος (sauros), which means "lizard," with "edaphos" in reference to how closely packed its teeth were. Edaphosauruss emerged in the late Carboniferous around 303.4 million years ago and lived very prominently in the early Permian to around 272.5 million years ago, coexisting with a variety of other pelycosaurs including Dimetrodon. It lived throughout many parts of the United States in North America, along with Central Europe.

Name: Edgin Darvis
Summary: Edgin Darvis is an human bard from Icewind Dale and was in the past a member of the Harpers, a spy organization dedicated to protecting Faerûn’s common folk, this changed after the death of his wife, when Edgin has forsworn his oath and turned to thievery to support his family. His strong moral compass whoever compels him to steal only from people he believes deserve will not suffer from it.

Name: Edmontosaurus
Summary: Edmontosaurus ("Lizard from Edmonton") is a genus of hadrosaurid dinosaur that lived in North America during the Late Cretaceous, about 73–66 million years ago. The size of Edmontosaurus makes it among the largest hadrosaurs. It was named for the place that the first specimen identified as this genus: Edmonton, the capital city of the Canadian province of Alberta. It was widespread across North America, and several specimens previously identified as different genera have been attributed to Edmontosaurus. This creature favored coastal plains and coasts, and its widespread distribution indicates that they would migrate and lived in herds. E. annectens differed from E. regalis in that it lacked a comb-like crest adorning its head.

Name: Eduardo Lobo (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Eduardo Lobo was an orphaned youth on the streets of Mexico, making ends meet alongside his brother Carlos, until one faithful night the love of his life was shot right before his eyes. This awakened a transformation within the young lad, and he discovered he was a mutant capable of transforming into a werewolf, similar to his brother. The two soon after took control of the local cartel in the late 1980s, with their empire reaching South Texas at its height.

Name: Egghead (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Dr. Elihas Starr was a scientist working at an US atomic research center. He was caught when trying to smuggle drafts of an atomic project, and then subsequently fired from the center, waiting to be judged for treason. However, the criminal world discovered his ordeal and offered him freedom if he was ready to put his intellect to the service of the crime lords. Taking on the name Egghead, Starr became a criminal mastermind, and arch enemy to Ant-Man.

Name: Ein (Pokémon)
Key: '''By Himself''' | '''Pokémon Team (Shadow PKMN Lab)''' | '''Pokémon Team (Realgam Tower)''' | '''Pokémon Team (Deep Colosseum)'''
Summary: Ein (Japanese: ボルグ Borg) is one of the original four Cipher Admins. A cruel and callous young scientist, he is long on ambition and short on emotion. He is obsessed with the idea of creating an insanely powerful Pokémon at any cost which he managed to do with amazing results.

Name: Ekko
Summary: Tier: At least 10-B, 9-C with Piltover Clock Hand, Low 2-C Environmental Damage Via Chronobreak | At least 10-B, likely higher, 9-C with QWQRE83 Chrono Blade, Low 2-C Environmental Damage Via Chronobreak

Name: Ekko (Arcane)
Summary: nan

Name: Elasmotherium
Summary: Elasmotherium is an extinct genus of rhinoceroses that lived from 7 million to 39,000 years ago. Most famous of the species of Elasmotherium is E. Sibiricum, which is also known as the Siberian Unicorn and is best known for being a real-life unicorn. Of the species of Elasmotherium, E. Sibiricum went up to 4.5 meters in length with a shoulder height of up to 2.5 meters and a weight of up to 3.5 tonnes.[1][2] E. Causasicum, however, went up to at least 5 meters in length and weighed 3.5 to 5 tonnes.[3][4]

Name: Eldes
Summary: Eldes (Japanese: エルデス Eldes) is the younger brother of Ardos and one of the five Cipher Admins of Pokémon XD: Gale of Darkness.

Name: Electro (Marvel Comics)
Summary: It's pitch black out there now. They're the faceless ones. They're the invisible nobodies. And me? I hurt. I'm scared. So afraid I'm gonna die. But it'll be worth it, won't it? When they look up and see me. The biggest. The brightest. The highest, the greatest. Oh it will be all worth it... when I... LIGHT THE NIGHT! Look at me, all of you! Look at Max Dillon! Look at ELECTRO!

Name: Elektra (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Elektra Natchios is an assassin who was trained under Stick to join the Chaste. She fell in love with Matt Murdock during a mission for Stick to bring Murdock into the organization. She returned to his life after years of absence, putting her beliefs and methods at conflict with his own. Later, she was revealed to potentially be the Black Sky, the one who is supposed to lead the Hand. However, Elektra chose to help Murdock defeat the malevolent organization, and was killed in the final confrontation with Nobu Yoshioka. The Hand then retrieved Elektra's corpse from the grave and placed it in a stone chamber to be exposed to the Resurrection Elixir.

Name: Elephant
Summary: Elephants are the largest land animals on Earth, they are members of the family Elephantidae and the order Proboscidea.

Name: Elephant (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: One of the many options for a mount animal, the Elephant is a large herbivore people in Dungeons And Dragons can use. They are extremely large and rather smart for an animal, being able to avoid attacking objects that will harm them if touched.

Name: Elephant Gun
Summary: An elephant gun is any kind of gun that either used black powder bullets or was used to hunt large animals such as elephants, buffaloes, and others.

Name: Elephant Seal
Summary: Elephant seals are large pinnipeds named after their trunk-like proboscises. The southern elephant seal, which is significantly larger than the northern elephant seal, is the largest marine mammal that is not a cetacean. Elephant seals are rarely seen on the surface of water.

Name: Elesa
Key: '''By Herself''' | '''Pokémon Teams (Gym Battle)''' | '''Pokémon Team (World Leaders Tournament)'''
Summary: Elesa, "The Shining Beauty" is a model and Gym Leader in Nimbasa City, region of Unova. She specializes in Electric-type Pokémon.

Name: Elsa Bloodstone (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Elsa Bloodstone is the daughter of the immortal monster hunter, Ulysses Bloodstone, who follows her father's footsteps to be a monster hunter herself. Armed with an arsenal of rifles, shotguns, pistols and other weapons, alongside being imbued by the power of the Bloodgem thanks to her choker, she hunts the various beasts and creatures of the Marvel Universe with expertise.

Name: Emu
Summary: The emu is a ratite that also serves as the 2nd tallest extant bird behind the ostrich. The emu is a flightless bird that can reach up to 1.9 meters in height. Adult emus weigh between 18 and 60 kg (40 and 132 lbs), with an average of 31.5 and 37 kg (69 and 82 lbs) in males and females, respectively.[1]
