Name: Enderman (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: Mysterious and dangerous, the Enderman is a tall entity with thin limbs, purple eyes and black body. They mainly reside at the End, but have been spotted in other dimensions. The Enderman shun water and sunlight, and if a human gazes at their eyes it will attack them with all its might.

Name: English Mastiff
Summary: https://vsbattles.fandom.com/wiki/File:English_mastiff_barking_sound.mp3

Name: Ennis
Summary: Tier: 9-C

Name: Entomber
Summary: Entombers are thralls of necromancers and serve both as acquirers and disposers of corpses. Thus, they wait silently in tombs and graveyards, treating all intruders as targets. They all have their mouths shut at their creation, sewn tight to prevent them from speaking.

Name: Epicyon
Summary: The Epicyon ("more than a dog") is a large, extinct, canid genus of the subfamily Borophaginae ("bone-crushing dogs"), native to North America. Epicyon existed for about 15 million years from the Hemingfordian age of the Early Miocene to the Hemphillian of the Late Miocene.

Name: Equinox (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Born to two brilliant scientists, Terry Sorenson was granted the power of thermokinesis upon failing to save his father during a lab explosion.

Name: Erik Killmonger (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Erik Stevens (born N'Jadaka) was a former American black-ops soldier of Wakandan origin through his father, Prince N'Jobu. His savagery while serving in the US black-ops earned him the nickname Erik Killmonger. Years after T'Chaka killed his father for betraying Wakanda, Killmonger then planned to forcibly dethrone T'Challa in order to accomplish his father's plan to use Wakanda's technology to conquer the world via imperialistic, supremacist, world-spanning, and likely genocidal warfare, to stop what he perceived to be the oppression of people of African descent by the world. Manipulating and then killing Ulysses Klaue to gain access to their city, Killmonger seemingly killed T'Challa during ritual combat and took the throne, but just before Killmonger unleashed his plan, the Black Panther had returned and challenged Killmonger, eventually killing him in their final battle.

Name: Erika (Pokémon)
Summary: Erika is the sleepy fourth Gym leader of Kanto, known as the Nature Loving Princess. She specializes in the Grass-type, and gives out the Rainbow badge when defeated.

Name: Eryops
Summary: Eryops is a large semi aquatic temnospondyl amphibian, the name of which comes from the Greek words ἐρύειν (eryein), which means 'drawn-out,' and ὤψ (ops), which means 'face.' The sole species Erypos megacephalus. It lived in the southwestern United States 299–278 million years ago, predominantly during the early Permian in what is now Texas,[1] while older specimens found in New Mexico from the late Carboniferous.[2] It inhabited lowlands around various bodies of freshwater, where it would hunt. Among the largest animals of it's time, they could reach 1.5 to 2 meters long on average,[2] and the largest could grow to 3 meters in length, with a mass of 102-222 kg.[3] Based on the structure of its vertebrae, limb girdle and ribs, this heavily built creature was well adapted for traversing land for prolonged periods of time.[4]

Name: Erythrosuchus
Summary: Erythrosuchus is a genus of erythrosuchid archosauriform, and the largest of this family of archosauriformes. Its name comes from the Greek words ἐρυθρός (eruthrós), which means "red," and σοῦχος (soukhos), which means "crocodile," named for the reddish color of the rock the fossils were formed in and collected from. It lived in South Africa 249–244 million years ago, during the early to mid Triassic, and was the apex predator of its place and time. Erythrosuchus, along with others in the family of erythrosuchidae, were known for their exceptionally large heads in proportion to their body size. Unlike more basal archosauriformes like Proterosuchus, this creature and its relatives were some of the earliest to have an erect posture.[1]

Name: Ethan (Pokémon)
Summary: Ethan is a young boy who turned 10 and went on his Pokémon journey in HeartGold and SoulSilver, 3 years after the original FireRed and LeafGreen. Having a similar story to his predecessor, on his tenth birthday he got to see his local Professor and pick out a First Partner Pokémon to take on his journey.

Name: Ethereal Filcher
Summary: Ethereal Filchers are bizarre pickpockets who excel at moving between planes to escape capture. Whatever they take, they store in their lairs, which they line with treasures in the most inaccessible places imaginable- oftentimes at the bottom of ruined mines, in forgotten cellars, or merely immensely deep caverns.

Name: Ethereal Marauder
Summary: Ethereal Marauders are predatory animals from, as their name might suggest, the Ethereal Plane, and are known to be kept as pets and guardians of the magic users hailing from that plane. Despite their magical nature they lack intelligence beyond an animalistic level, and are quite savage hunters.

Name: Etrigan (Post-Flashpoint)
Summary: Etrigan was once a rhyming demon of low standing, belittled by Lucifer, the lord of Hell. Fed up with his treatment, he decided to start a revolt, managing to get many demons to serve him due to his sheer battle prowess, but he couldn't hope to stand up to Lucifer, and was cast down to Earth, where the wizard Merlin fused him with his own unruly apprentice, Jason of Norwich, which would later go on to be known as Jason Blood.

Name: Ettercap
Summary: Ettercaps are solitary creatures that act as guardians to writhing hordes of spiders, shepherding them as a human might do to sheep. Ettercaps tend to create massive webs to kill wanderers who find their lairs, so that they might feast upon their remains alongside their flock. The presence of an Ettercap attracts monstrous vermin to their forests, twisting the once peaceful landscape into a horrible, dark place.

Name: Ettin
Summary: Ettins are immense, brutish giant-like creatures known for their hatred of all other things to the point of violent isolationism. While they were recognized by the giant community as one of their own, they were called runt- in a literal sense, "ettin" now means "runt" in Jotun, tongue of the giants. Each head has its own personality and quirks, and each head generally hates the other due to constant exposure to the other's slights.

Name: European Longsword
Summary: A longsword is a type of European sword characterized as having a cruciform hilt with a grip for two-handed use (around 16 to 28 cm (6 to 11 in)) and a straight double-edged blade of around 85 to 110 cm (33 to 43 in). It was prevalent during the late medieval and Renaissance periods (approximately 1350 to 1550), with early and late use reaching into the 13th and 17th centuries, and can owe it's success to its versatile cross-guard, and it's flexible, straight blade, which is effective at stabbing and resisting damage.

Name: Evice
Summary: Evice (Japanese: ワルダック Wardack) is the criminal mastermind behind Cipher. He is the only character in the games to have the Trainer class Cipher Head (Japanese: シャドーのボス Shadow Boss). He disguises himself as the mayor of Phenac City under the name of Es Cade (Japanese: バックレー Backley). In his disguise, he is a fat and jolly gentleman who appears to be worried about the increase in crime caused by Cipher and Team Snagem, yet as the head of Cipher, he appears to have done nothing to stop either of them, ensuring that Snagem and Cipher work without interference.

Name: Ezmerelda d'Avenir
Summary: Ezmerelda d'Avenir is the warrior protoge of Rudolph van Richten, a renowned vampire hunter. As a child, her family kidnapped Richten's son, Erasmus, and delivered him to a vampire. His screams, begging for mercy, haunt her. Richten tracked down her family and interrogated them on the location of his son- and spared them. This act of mercy inspired Ezmerelda.

Name: Ezra Bridger
Summary: Ezra Bridger was a human male Jedi Padawan who, as an orphan on the Outer Rim planet of Lothal, became a rebel fighter and revolutionary leader in the early rebellion against the Galactic Empire. He was born to Ephraim and Mira Bridger, two outspoken opponents of the Imperial regime on Lothal. As a boy, his parents were taken prisoner by the Empire, leaving Bridger to fend for himself on the streets of Lothal. He joined the rebel crew of the Ghost five years before the Battle of Yavin and, with his Force-sensitivity having been discovered, became the apprentice of Kanan Jarrus, a Jedi who survived Order 66. Bridger's abilities with the Force grew quickly, which aided in many of the crew's efforts against the Empire.

Name: F-117 Nighthawk
Summary: The F-117 Nighthawk is a single seat, twin engine attack aircraft developed by the secretive Skunk Works division of Lockheed and operated chiefly by the USAF. The aircraft is based on the earlier Have Blue technology demonstrator and was the first operational aircraft to be designed around stealth technology.

Name: F-14 Tomcat
Summary: The F-14 Tomcat is a supersonic, twin-engine, variable sweep wing, two-place fighter designed to attack and destroy enemy aircraft at night and in all weather conditions. Although now retired in the U.S. Navy, it remains in use, seeing service with the Iranian Air Force.

Name: F-15 Eagle
Summary: The F-15 is a fighter aircraft currently serving in the United States Air Force, and several other air forces around the world. Created in response to a satelite photograph of the MiG-25, to this day it remains one of the primary fighters of the USAF, having served over 3 decades with a combat record including 104 enemy aircraft shot down, 1 satellite, no air-to-air losses of its own, and only 3 confirmed losses from groundfire.

Name: F-22 Raptor
Summary: The F-22 Raptor is an advanced, all-weather twin engine single seat stealth 5th generation fighter developed by Lockheed Martin. It is the end result of the USAF's Advanced Tactical Fighter program, and although it was designed first and foremost for air superiority, it also has other roles in the form of ground attack, electronic warfare, and signal intelligence.

Name: F-35 Lightning II
Summary: The F-35 Lightning II is family of single-seat, single-engine, all-weather stealth multi-role fighters developed and manufactured by Lockheed Martin for the Joint Strike Fighter program. The fifth-generation combat aircraft is designed to perform ground-attack and air-superiority missions.

Name: M109 Paladin
Summary: The M109 Paladin is an American 155 mm turreted self-propelled howitzer, first introduced in the early 1960s to replace the M44 and M52. It has been upgraded a number of times, most recently to the M109A7. The M109 family is the most common Western indirect-fire support weapon of maneuver brigades of armored and mechanized infantry divisions. It has a crew of four: the section chief/commander, the driver, the gunner, and the ammunition handler/loader.

Name: F-86 Sabre
Summary: The North American F-86 Sabre was a fighter used by the US and it's allies during the early Cold War period, and saw military service in the Korean War. It's closest Soviet equivalent is the MiG-15, and often saw combat against it during the Korean War. The aircraft was finally retired in 1994 in Bolivia, 47 years after it has made it's first flight and 45 years after it first entered service with the USAF.

Name: F/A-18 Hornet
Summary: The F/A-18 Hornet is a twin engine all-weather carrier capable multirole fighter developed and designed by McDonnell Douglas (Now Boeing) and Northrop. It was derived from the earlier YF-17 design designed by the latter in the 1970s for use by the US Navy and Marine Corps. It has also seen service in use by several other nations, and first flew in 1978, entering service for the first time in 1983.

Name: Faba
Key: '''By Himself''' | '''First Fights Teams''' | '''Pokémon Team (Post Game/Title Defense)'''
Summary: Faba is the Branch Chief of the Aether Foundation and the foundation's "last line of defense".

Name: Faerie Dragon
Summary: Faerie Dragons are fey-touched dragons closely related to pseudodragons. They are roughly the size of a cat and bear vibrant butterfly-like wings. Unlike other dragons, their scales change as they grow older, which indicates how strong that particular faerie dragon is. They are also much smaller than their great dragon cousins, being only the size of a housecat.

Name: Falcon (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: Living deep in the Neverwinter woods, Falcon established a lodge there where rich nobles can enjoy a stay there.

Name: Falcon (Joaquín Torres)
Summary: Joaquín Torres came to the United States of America with his mother and grandmother when he was six years old. He lived in Sonoita, Arizona, and he graduated from high school in the honor roll. He was kidnapped by the Sons of the Serpent, as part of their agenda to capture people in the border to send them to Karl Malus for experimenting.

Name: Falcon (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Samuel Thomas "Sam" Wilson, better known as the Falcon, was a former United States Air Force pararescue airman who left active duty when his wing-man Riley died in combat, choosing instead to begin helping any of his fellow veterans who were suffering from post-traumatic stress disorder at Veterans Affairs. During this time, Wilson met and soon became an ally of Captain America during the beginning of the HYDRA Uprising, assisting him in bringing down Alexander Pierce's schemes for Project Insight before then choosing to remain with Captain America. Falcon later joined the Avengers, and has been an active member ever since.

Name: Falcon (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Sam Wilson is the son of Paul Wilson, a minister, and Darlene Wilson. Paul died trying to break up a neighborhood fight, and Darlene was killed during a mugging. Before they died, they instilled a great deal of idealism and a desire to help the fellow man into him. Experimented upon by the Red Skull with the Cosmic Cube to grant him the ability to telepathically communicate and control with birds, he aided Captain America in stopping his evil schemes. Steve and Sam would become great life-long friends. Captain America trained Sam in martial arts, making him a very skilled combatant, and both Black Panther and Iron Man have provided him with wings which give him the ability to fly. These wings have varied in design, from hardlight wings to regenerating vibranium.

Name: Fancy Dan (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Daniel Brito was born and raised in Brooklyn, New York. Bullied at a young age due to his height, he took martial arts classes to better defend himself and earn respect, but the mocking only continued as he was branded Fancy Dan by his tormentors. He soon joined forces with Montana and Ox to form the mercenary collective the Enforcers, and have been a thorn in Spider-Man's side ever since.

Name: Fantomex (Marvel Comics)
Summary: The product of a mating between his mother and a machine, Charlie-Cluster 7 was born in the World, a secret square mile of experimental micro-reality built by the military industrial complex. In the World, artificially evolved super-soldiers destined to serve mankind during the inevitable war between humans and mutants were bred and trained by the Weapon Plus Program. The World’s scientists heated up time itself until it flowed in all directions at once. Into this pliant, fast-moving substance, they introduced human test groups, whose genetic material was crudely spliced with adaptive Nano-Sentinel technology, and ran the result through half a million years of cyborg mutation in eighteen months. Charlie’s nervous system was extracted and mutated into the autonomous entity named E.V.A.

Name: Faramir
Summary: Faramir is a soldier of Gondor the Lord of the Rings series, he first appears in the book The Two Towers. Faramir was the second son of Denethor II and the younger brother of Boromir. He was the Captain of the Rangers of Ithilien and Captain of the White Tower upon his brother's death.

Name: Farel
Summary: One of the many nobles in Waterdeep, Faerl is a cruel and proud wood elf.

Name: Fasolasuchus
Summary: Fasolasuchus is a large loricatan. It is the largest "rauisuchian" and likely the largest non-dinosaurian terrestrial carnivore. It's name means "Fasola crocodile," with the suffix "suchus" derived from the Greek word soukhos (σοῦχος), which means "crocodile". The primarily known species is Fasolasuchus tenax.

Name: Federal Riot Gun
Summary: The Federal Riot Gun, or FRG, is a US-manufactured firearm by Federal Laboratories Inc., designed to fire non-lethal munitions. Its ammunition include 37 and 38mm baton and tear gas rounds. The baton rounds were cylindrical, rubber projectiles.

Name: Fire Axe
Summary: The Fire axe, camp axe or fireman's axe is a tool used to break down wood, although it can be used fairly well as a weapon.

Name: Fire Bat
Summary: Hailing from the Elemental Plane of Fire, Fire Bats for casual observers appears simply as a flaming bat but one should not underestimate it in combat for they're quite cunning and can't be truly killed unless proper precautions are taken.

Name: Firefly (Garfield Lynns) (Post-Crisis)
Summary: Garfield Lynns was a professional pyrotechnic effects expert who was eventually driven insane by his obsession with flames, eventually leading Lynns to adopt a hi-tech suit of armour and the name: Firefly and became a crazed arsonist terrorising Gotham. Initially being the partner of Killer Moth he eventually took off to do his own crimes after their relationship became problematic.

Name: Firestorm (Pre-Crisis)
Summary: The original Firestorm was distinguished by his integrated dual identity. High school student Ronnie Raymond and Nobel Prize-winning physicist Martin Stein were caught in a nuclear accident that allowed them to fuse into the "nuclear man" Firestorm. Due to Stein's being unconscious during the accident, Raymond was prominently in command of the Firestorm form with Stein as a voice of reason inside his mind. The banter between the two was a hallmark of their adventures.

Name: Flag-Smasher (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Karl Morgenthau, better known as Flag-Smasher was the son of a wealthy Swiss banker turned diplomat. Due to his father's job, he often moved from country to country feeling like a foreigner and an outcast, and at the age of 19 he tried to follow his father's footsteps by getting a degree in political science.

Name: Flail Snail
Summary: A Flail Snail is an elemental creature originating from the earth. In the wild, the snail moves slowly across the ground, consuming raw materials off the surface while leaving a shimmering trail of transparent substance. If a threat were to attempt to harm the creature, it will unleash a scintillating light that stuns enemies before it uses it's flail-like tentacles.

Name: Flame Snake
Summary: Often used as guards the Flame Snake comes in 3 variants; Small, Lesser and Greater Flame Snake with each one being stronger then the former, the strongest of their kin being theorised to be banished demons cursed into being snakes.

Name: Flameskull
Summary: Flameskulls are undead guardians crafted from the remains of deceased wizards. When created, they begin cackling in a disturbing manner, and fly about the lair of their new master, patrolling for intruders. It maintains very little recollection of its former life, and is instead totally devoted to its new master. They are exceptionally hard to destroy, as they simply reform unless doused in holy water, making them an exceptional threat to the underprepared adventurer.

Name: Flamethrower
Summary: A Flamethrower is a weapon that projects a long stream of fire. This is usually fueled either by flammable liquids, or natural gas/propane.

Name: Flaming Fist Marcus
Summary: Flaming Fist Marcus is a member of the mercenary and police organization known as the Flaming Fist, himself holding a high-ranking title within the group. During the Absolute Crisis, he can be found at the Last Light Inn, a sanctuary against the creeping shadow curse that has tainted a large swathe of land surrounding the Moonrise Towers. Unknown to his allies in the Flaming Fist, or to the Harpers who maintain the Last Light Inn, Marcus has long since betrayed them in favor of the Absolute, going to their base of operations at Moonrise and receiving an illithid tadpole in his head and granted supernatural powers.

Name: Flesh Golem (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: Created by various evil spellcasters across D&D, a Flesh Golem is various bodies sown together and animated through magic in order to create a minion for one's bidding. Flesh Golems can be created from various creatures ranging from humans, Scale Ones, and all the way to demons. No matter what a Flesh Golem is a fierce enemy to face in combat.

Name: Fleshraker
Summary: A relative of the velociraptor, the Fleshraker is one Dungeon and Dragons's unique dinosaurs not found in our world. They hunt as pacts, preferring lone targets, though if hungry will attack groups. They are skilled at hiding and jumping which they use to great effect for ambushes during hunts, with them appearing out of nowhere to their prey. Against prey they can't take in one surprise attack they have their poisonous bite, which worsens the victim's dexterity which the Fleshraker uses as a chance to attack later.

Name: Flintlock pistol
Summary: Flintlock is a general term for any firearm that uses a flint striking ignition mechanism. The term may also apply to a particular form of the mechanism itself, also known as the true flintlock, that was introduced in the early 17th century, and rapidly replaced earlier firearm-ignition technologies, such as the matchlock, the wheellock, and the earlier flintlock mechanisms.

Name: Flumph
Summary: Flumph is a term for a species of psionic, magic creatures dwelling in the underdark of D&D settings. They are an odd creature that feed on thoughts, dispelling bad ones when they come across them. Generally, Flumphs are non-violent.

Name: Flying Fingers
Summary: A variant of the Crawling Claw, the Flying Finger as the name suggests is a flying construct made from the hands of various evil people. Each hand has an eye sown into it in order to give it potent sensory ability, which aids it in its main duty of guarding locations for evil casters.

Name: Flying Monkey
Summary: At first it was one monkey. It scared away the doves and built a little home in the headman's eaves. The children loved it. Then it was a dozen monkeys, tearing at the children's hair and making them drop their sweets and bits of cocount. The children hated it, and oh how they cried. Now it's hundred monkeys! They must be stopped, before they drive everyone out of the village!

Name: Flying Snake
Summary: A colorful snake with wings, the Flying Snake is a small venomous snake that is also able to spit acid. They can be used as familiars for spellcasers and be turned into an undead creature, one that is called Deathfang.

Name: Flying Sword
Summary: This animated sword dances through the air, fighting with the confidence of a warrior that can't be injured. Swords are the most common weapons animated by magic. They are often found fighting alongside Animated Armor.

Name: FN F2000
Summary: The FN F2000 is a 5.56×45mm NATO bullpup assault rifle, designed by FN Herstal in Belgium. The F2000 made its debut in March 2001 at the IDEX defence exhibition held in Abu Dhabi, in the United Arab Emirates.

Name: FN FAL
Summary: The FAL (French: Fusil Automatique Léger, English: Light Automatic Rifle) is a battle rifle designed by Belgian small arms designers Dieudonné Saive and Ernest Vervier and manufactured by FN Herstal.

Name: FN Five-seven
Summary: The FN Five-seven, trademarked as the Five-seveN, is a semi-automatic pistol designed and manufactured by FN Herstal in Belgium. The pistol is named for its 5.7-mm (.224 in) bullet diameter, and the trademark capitalization style is intended to emphasize the manufacturer's initials—FN.

Name: FN MAG/M240 machine gun
Summary: The FN MAG is a Belgian 7.62 mm general-purpose machine gun, designed in the early 1950s at Fabrique Nationale (FN) by Ernest Vervier. It has been used by more than 80 countries and it has been made under licence in several countries, including Argentina, Canada (as the C6 GPMG), Egypt, India and the United Kingdom. It has also been used in various terrorist organizations.

Name: FN Minimi/M249 light machine gun
Key: '''FN Minimi and its variants, M249 machine gun and Mk 46 machine gun''' | '''Mk 48 machine gun'''
Summary: The FN Minimi (short for French: Mini Mitrailleuse; "mini machine gun") is a Belgian 5.56mm Squad Automatic Weapon, or SAW developed by Fabrique Nationale (FN) in Herstal by Ernest Vervier. First introduced in the late 1970s, it is now in service in more than 75 countries. The weapon is currently manufactured at the FN facility in Herstal and their U.S. subsidiary FN Manufacturing LLC. The Minimi is a SAW that fires from an open bolt. It is an air-cooled weapon that is capable of fully automatic fire only. It can be belt fed or fired from a magazine. The Minimi is configured in several variants: the Standard model as a platoon or squad support weapon, the Para version for paratroopers and the Vehicle model as secondary armament for fighting vehicles.

Name: FN P90
Summary: The FN P90, also known as the FN Project 1990, is a compact personal defense weapon (PDW) designed and manufactured by FN Herstal in Belgium. Created in response to NATO requests for a replacement for 9×19mm Parabellum firearms, the P90 was designed as a compact but powerful firearm for vehicle crews, operators of crew-served weapons, support personnel, special forces, and counter-terrorist groups.

Name: FN SCAR
Summary: The FN SCAR (Special Operations Forces Combat Assault Rifle) is a gas-operated (short-stroke gas piston) self-loading rifle with a rotating bolt. It is constructed to be extremely modular, including barrel change to switch between calibers. The rifle was developed by Belgian manufacturer FN Herstal (FNH) for the United States Special Operations Command (SOCOM) to satisfy the requirements of the SCAR competition. This family of rifles consist of two main types. The SCAR-L, for "light," is chambered in 5.56×45mm NATO cartridge and the SCAR-H, for "heavy," is chambered in 7.62×51mm NATO. Both are available in Close Quarters Combat (CQC), Standard (STD), and Long Barrel (LB) variants.

Name: Fomorian
Summary: Fomorians are wretched, malformed giants of once previous good breeding. They live in the Feywild, once alongside the elves, pixies, and other fey of that plane- until their inner malice wrent their forms into the horrible disfigured creatures they are now. Angered by their change, they fled to the Feydark, that plane's counterpart to the Underdark of the Prime Material. No fomorian looks alike, though each bears certain consistent features: pale white to dark purple skin, hairless forms, and two differently shaped eyes, the larger of which is known as their "Evil Eye", which they can use to pass on their race's intrinsic curse.

Name: Ford Crown Victora Police Interceptor
Summary: The Ford Crown Victoria Police Interceptor (Colloquially referred to simply as the CVPI, P71, P7B, or Crown Vic) is a four-door body-on-frame sedan that was manufactured by Ford from 1992 to 2011. It is the law enforcement version of the Ford Crown Victoria. From 1997 to 2011, the Ford Crown Victoria Police Interceptor was the most widely used automobile in law enforcement operations in the United States, Canada, and Saudi Arabia. They were also used for this purpose on a more limited scale in other countries.

Name: Forest Gnome
Summary: Shy and reclusive, Forest Gnomes are the rarest of the Gnome types. They seldom get out of their woods, so their impact on the world at large is often minor. They are deeply connected to nature, being able to communicate with animals while also easily hiding in a forest environment.

Name: Formian
Summary: Formians are ant-like outsiders hellbent on meticulous keeping of order, to the point that their views often align with that of the Modron civilization. They resided in Mechanus, always keeping perfect order in their strict hierarchy of society. Formians create a hivemind based around their queen at a vast radius of fifty miles, thus ensuring their civilizations may never falter.

Name: Francis Dolarhyde (Film)
Summary: In the 2002 film Red Dragon, the Tooth Fairy is the main antagonist, portrayed by Ralph Fiennes. The character is based on Francis Dolarhyde, a disturbed individual with a traumatic past who becomes a serial killer. Dolarhyde, who is often referred to as the Tooth Fairy, is named after his method of killing, which involves removing the teeth of his victims.

Name: Frost Folk
Summary: Many people seek power, Frost Folk are the descents of humans who sold their souls to winter Gods in exchange for power. Frost Folk at a first glance appear like a regular blond, pale skinned people with blue eyes but anyone who stands even 30 feet of them can tell they're no regular humans due to the chill that follows them around. They often hunted animals to use their fur to craft an armor.

Name: Frulam Mondath
Summary: Frulam Mondrath is a division leader of the Cult of the Dragon, an organization whose most recent goal has been summoning Tiamat, Queen of Dragons to the Prime Material Plane, and freeing the goddess from her prison in the Nine Hells. Frulam has been a longstanding member of this cult, generally taking on tasks of raiding towns and villages for plunder for their dragon overlords. She considers Langdedrosa Cyanwrath her right-hand man and trusts the half-dragon to watch over the dragon hatchery.

Name: G'iah (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: G'iah is the daughter of Talos and Soren, as well as one of the Skrull refugees who were rescued from the Kree Empire by Captain Marvel and Nick Fury. Losing her faith in Fury and her father, G'iah joined Gravik and the Skrull Resistance to take over Earth. However, upon learning of her mother's demise, G'iah's loyalty started wavering and she started secretly working with Talos. She was eventually caught by Gravik, who tried executing her, but she survived by infusing herself with the Extremis. Turning against Gravik completely, she impersonated Fury and confronted him at the New Skrullos, as she turned into the Super Skrulls using the Harvest. G'iah managed to kill Gravik and liberate all the abducted humans, after which she was recruited by Sonya Falsworth in a mutually beneficial agreement to protect Skrulls in return for their services to Falsworth.

Name: Galaxy Team
Summary: Many years ago, the land of Sinnoh was completely uninhabited by humans. Eventually, a large band of explorers landed upon its shore and over time they built a village to call their own; that being Jubilife Village, officially kicking off the colonization of the Sinnoh region. There was one major problem that they faced, however: Humans did not nearly have the standards of Pokémon training that they do in modern days, making even navigating areas with Pokémon present a life-threatening journey. To get around this, they set up the Galaxy Team in their proud village, splitting among 6 Corps everything they would need to do to thrive in the land of Sinnoh:

Name: Galeb Duhr
Summary: Galeb Duhr is an intelligent elemental from the Plane of Earth, bearing the ability to invoke life in rocks and dirt. They were most often encountered on the Prime Material, hiding themselves as boulders unless someone invaded their territories (though they typically allied themselves with other defenders of nature, such as treants or pech). They spent their days endlessly tending to their boulders, much like a gardener might tend to their plants. They were often called upon by druids to protect groves and other places sacred to nature, and used their innate camouflage abilities to remain staunch in their sentinel duty, sitting still for years at a time.

Name: Gambit
Summary: Remy Lebeau, better known as Gambit, is a semi-reformed thief and member of the X-Men whose troubled past has sometimes come back to haunt him, on the whole however Gambit has left his past behind and is a hero - sharing an on-and-off romantic interest with Rogue, despite the fact he can't touch her without fear of death.

Name: Garcia Hotspur
Summary: Garcia Hotspur is the main protagonist of Shadows of the Damned.

Name: Gargoyle (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: Gargoyles are monstrosities of stone hailing from the planes of Earth. These prideful predators wait in dormancy, patiently watching for enemies to inflict pain upon. A gathering of Gargoyles oftentimes will resort to banter and bragging to pass the time.

Name: Gary Oak
Summary: Gary Oak is the grandson of Professor Oak and formerly a rival of Ash Ketchum.

Name: Gas Spore
Summary: Gas Spores are spherical specimens of fungi that strongly resemble a Beholder, a fact which some suspect it has naturally evolved to achieve as a natural defense system. These plants often form symbiotic relationships with the eye tyrants, sprouting from their corpses and imbuing their miasma with the beholder's memories.

Name: Gastornis
Summary: Gastornis is a genus of large, flightless bird, considered to be related to modern fowl. It was initially thought to be carnivorous, but more recent evidence (such as the tips its beak and claws lacking a hook-like shape, and analysis of calcium isotopes in its bones[1]) indicates that it was herbivorous,[2] its large beak suited to breaking seeds and other tough plant matter rather than catching small mammals. It lived during the mid Paleocene to mid Eocene epochs, throughout North America, Europe, and Asia, inhabiting lush environments that existed even in the Arctic during its time.

Name: GAU-8 Avenger
Summary: The General Electric GAU-8/A Avenger is a 30mm hydraulically driven seven-barrel Gatling-type rotary autocannon that is typically mounted in the United States Air Force's Fairchild Republic A-10 Thunderbolt II. Designed specifically for the anti-tank role, the Avenger delivers very powerful rounds at a high rate of fire. The GAU-8/A is also used in the Goalkeeper CIWS ship weapon system, an autonomous and completely automatic weapon system for short-range defense of ships against highly maneuverable missiles, aircraft and fast maneuvering surface vessels

Name: Gaur
Summary: The gaur (also known as indian bison, or Bos gaurus scientifically) are the largest extant bovidae that lives throughout asia, albeit listed as a vulnerable species on the IUCN Red List.[1][2] They're wild cattle that live near accesssible fresh water in undisturbed, large, forested areas and hilly terrain.[1]

Name: Gelatinous Cube
Summary: Gelatinous Cubes are large, transparent cubes known for picking up whatever they come across. They are notoriously hard to see, with the only hints of their presence being the glint of something reflecting off of their vacuous hide or, if one was lucky, the telltale sign of floating remnants of the cube's last meal still seen dangling, inanimate, within it.

Name: General Zod (Post-Flashpoint)
Summary: Prisoners, you have been found guilty. By order of the council, you will be exiled forever to the Phantom Zone. Do you have any final words before execution of your sentence? Zod: My name is Zod. And no matter what you do, no matter where you send me-- I promise you this. I... Will always... Be your monster. As the Phantom zone takes me, I see your faces. And I know you understand. I will turn your fear into action. I will show you all that you are capable of. I will make you great. And because of me... You will have the chance to survive... And grow strong.

Name: German Shepherd
Summary: The German Shepherd is a medium to large-sized German Breed of herding dog that was later used for police and military work. It is also commonly kept as a companion.

Name: Gharial
Summary: The Gharial (Gavialis gangeticus) is a species of crocodylomorph adapted to a predominantly piscivorous lifestyle. They are known for their long and thin jaws, with the males sporting a lump on the tip of their snouts which resembles an earthen pot called a "ghara" (hence the name "Gharial"). This lump forms following sexual maturity in males. They are among the largest crocodilians alive today, with females can reach 4.5 meters long, while males can reach 6 meters long; average adult mass is 160-180 kg, while males can reach a mass of 600 kg, and the largest found was 977 kg.

Name: Ghetsis
Summary: Ghetsis Harmonia (Japanese: ゲーチス・ハルモニア G-Cis Harmonia) is one of the Seven Sages, the true mastermind behind Team Plasma and the primary antagonist in Black, White, Black 2, and White 2.

Name: Ghiaccio
Summary: Ghiaccio is a minor antagonist in JoJo's Bizarre Adventure Part V: Vento Aureo. A member of Risotto's sub-gang in Passione, he attacks Giorno Giovanna and Guido Mista in search for taking Trish Una and information leading to finding the Boss of Passione. He is the last member of the squad encountered by Bucciarati's group.

Name: Ghost (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Ava Starr was the daughter of Elihas and Catherine Starr until they were both killed in an accidental quantum explosion. However, Ava was only left with the power to turn invisible and intangible, powers that led S.H.I.E.L.D. to recruit her as a special agent for dealing with extra-dangerous threats until she was adopted by Bill Foster. The two worked together to steal from Bill's nemesis, Hank Pym, and possibly find a solution to Ava's unstable body condition, with her working as "Ghost".

Name: Ghoul (Dungeons and Dragons)
Key: '''Ghoul''' | '''Lacedon''' | '''Elder Ghoul''' | '''Vapour Ghoul''' | '''Shadow Ghoul''' | '''Noble/Wizard Ghoul''' | '''Cleric Ghoul''' | '''Abyssal Ghoul''' | '''Flesh Seeker''' | '''Whisperer Ghoul''' | '''Gatherer Ghoul''' | '''Ghoul Warrior''' | '''Ghoul Stalker''' | '''Gravetouched Ghoul''' | '''Ghast''' | '''Darkpach Ghoul'''
Summary: Ghouls are malicious undead that haunt battlefields and scenes of slaughter. Not unlike maggots or Carrion Crawlers, they sweep to the scent of freshly killed flesh in droves to devour and consume. The first ghoul was made when Doresain, an elf worshiper of Orcus, consumed human flesh. As a reward, Orcus granted him a domain in his layer of the Abyss- however, this was lost when Yeenoghu overthrew Doresain. When Orcus failed to act on his behalf, Doresain turned back to the elf gods, who saved him from total annihilation once more.

Name: Giant Anteater
Summary: The giant anteater is the largest of the four extant species of anteater. Unlike other anteaters and sloths, the giant anteater is a mostly terrestrial animal. The giant anteater is recognizable for its long snout, bushy tail, long foreclaws, and distinctive fur markings. The giant anteater's bold marking serves as warning coloration. The giant anteater has been featured in pre-Colombian myths and folklore and popular culture.

Name: Giant Badger
Summary: Like its smaller variant, the Giant Badger is a vicious hunter and fighter, who flies into a frenzy whenever it gets hurt. They are unable to burrow in stone, but can in soil and anything softer, with the act leaving behind a 5 feet wide tunnel behind.

Name: Giant Bat (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: One of the many giant versions of mundane animals, the Dire Bat true to its name is a giant version of a bat. Its own body is the size of a horse, while its wing span reaches up to 15 feet long.

Name: Giant Bee
Summary: A far bigger variant of a regular bee, the Giant Bee can reach a size of 5 feet. Behavior wise it acts no different than regular bees, although the queen is able to produce jelly that has healing properties when eaten.

Name: Giant Cockroach
Summary: Far bigger and more aggressive then their regular counterparts, Giant Cockroaches are found mainly underground in areas where there's water and enough decaying organic matter, although it should be noted that they could live anywhere they wanted. In combat this creatures use chemicals they emit to cause nasua in their opponet, said chemicals also the exsoskeleton appear shiny or oily.

Name: Giant Constrictor Snake
Summary: A massive beast, the Giant Constrictor Snake is a large variant of a constrictor snake. They live in warm forests, dropping on prey from tree tops to strangle them to death.

Name: Giant Crab (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: An oversized crab, the Giant Crab is a relatively rare creature that one can encounter in the Forgotten Realms. They are basic creatures, working purely of basic survival instincts.

Name: Giant Crocodile
Summary: The Giant Crocodile is a giant variant of the common crocodile and they can reach an impressive size of 30 feet.

Name: Giant Dragonfly
Summary: One of many insects that people use as mounts, the Giant Dragonfly is often favored over creatures such as the Giant Bee or Giant Wasp. They are highly agile, with them easily evading enemy attacks. However, their wings emit a loud buzz, alerting anyone to the rider's presence.

Name: Giant Eagle
Summary: A noble creature which has its own language, the Giant Eagle is a giant version of an eagle which can be trained to be a mount.

Name: Giant Fire Beetle
Summary: The Giant Fire Beetle is an oversized beetle species. They get their name from their ability to emit a bright light, with it coming from glands on their body. This glands can be harvested and used as light sources for adventurers.

Name: Giant Firefly
Summary: Firefriend or more commonly known Giant Firefly are a giant variant of the common bug who are known for being a kind animal that seeks out friendly companions and can act as a great mount for search missions due to their natural light production.

Name: Giant Frog (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: A variation of the average frog, this creature can reach a size between 4-6 feet with its tongue being 3 times its body lengths. The Giant Frog will mostly hunt large insects and small animals but is known to sometimes swallow small humans too, they also are scared of fire.

Name: Giant Goat
Summary: A giant variant of a regular goat, the Giant Goat reside in hills. If threatened they will be rather hostile, quickly charging at enemies with all their might. On rare occasions some people tamed these goats.

Name: Giant Hyena
Summary: A larger, and more ancient version of the regular Hyena, the Giant Hyena is a prehistoric version of a regular hyena. They possess powerful jaws, which they will readily use whenever they're hungry. They are found mainly in warm plains.

Name: Giant Lizard (Dungeons and Dragons)
Key: '''Giant Lizard''' | '''Footpad Lizard''' | '''Quicksilver Lizard''' | '''Subterranean Lizard''' | '''Giant Banded Lizard'''
Summary: Giant Lizards are monstrously large creatures bred in the Underdark by Drow as potential replacements to their typical spider mounts. They roam the subterranean parts of the world, commonly hunting in packs or being used as pack animals for their fearsome overlords[1].

Name: Giant Oceanic Manta Ray
Summary: The giant oceanic manta ray (Mobula birostris) is a species of ray endemic to oceans worldwide. It is the largest species of ray in the world, and can weigh up to 3,000 kilograms (6,600 pounds).

Name: Giant Owl
Summary: A fearsome predator, a Giant Owl inspires fear in people due to its ability to strike its prey out of nowhere thanks to its excellent stealth abilities.

Name: Giant Panda
Summary: The Giant Panda (Ailuropoda melanoleuca; Chinese: 大熊猫; pinyin: dàxióngmāo), also known as the panda bear or simply the panda, is a bear native to south central China.

Name: Giant Sea Horse
Summary: The Giant Sea Horse like its smaller kin is a colorful and odd looking aquatic creature. They are often tamed by aquatic elves and Locata to be mounts.

Name: Giant Shark
Summary: A massive predator, the Giant Shark roams the seas, hunting whatever crosses its path be it whales or ships. This creature is not the same as a Megalodon, as it only reaches around half of their size.

Name: Giant Snapping Turtle
Summary: An oversized animal, the Giant Snapping Turtle is one of many giant versions of mundane animals. Their bite is strong enough to easily cut a person in half.

Name: Giant Squid
Summary: Giant squids (Architeuthis dux) are large cephalopods that live within deep ocean waters worldwide. They are one of the largest of all living invertebrates and the second-largest cephalopod, with an estimated maximum length and weight of 13 meters and 275 kilograms.

Name: Giant Stag Beetle
Summary: The Giant Stag Beetle is as the name implies, a giant version of a stag beetle. It is able to reach to a size of 10 feet long, with a horn being 8 feet long itself. Their wings are too heavy for flight but their armor makes them well defended.

Name: Giant Trevally
Summary: The giant trevally (Caranx ignobilis) is a large species of fish native to oceans worldwide. It is an apex predator in most of its range, and hunts both alone and in schools.

Name: Giant Vulture
Summary: A giant version of the regular vulture, the Giant Vulture or also known as the Dire Vulture, is a far more aggressive creature which attacks wounded creatures in order to hasten their death.

Name: Giant Wasp (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: While not as exotic as other monsters in D&D a giant wasp is none the less a fearsome opponent to fight it combat due to its ability to inject one with devastating poison which can paralysis them, outside this the wasps behave like regular wasps with the only difference being what prey they hunt.

Name: Giant Weasel
Summary: The Giant Weasel is a ten feet long animal. They use their powerful jaws to attach to prey in order to suck out all their blood.

Name: Giant-Killer
Summary: Experts in fighting Giants, the Giant-Killer is a prestige class dedicated to combating that category of monsters. Often born from disasters caused by Giants, when not out hunting Giants they are often a nuisances, with them usually being boastful and arrogant. However once a Giant is involved they are the people one wants the most in the forefront.

Name: Gibbering Mouther
Summary: Gibbering Mouthers are amorphous monstrosities made entirely of eyeballs and mouths. Each mouth sings out in inhuman tongues about the madness experienced by the creature each and every second of its life. Very few Gibbering Mouthers possess the fortitude to retain intelligence following transformation- one such Mouther is Shond Tharovin, a former archmage who was transformed into a 20-mile wide Mouther. Shond currently resides in the Trackless Sea, plotting revenge.

Name: Giff
Summary: One of the many space faring races, the Giff is in appearance basically a hippopotamus walking on two legs. Their original world lost to the sands of time, the Giff can be found anywhere in space offering their services to the highest bidder. Giff are natural masters of guns, and are often trained in using a multitude of other weapons as well. They enjoy the thrill of combat, especially the sight of explosions, which is why they take payment in the form of gunpowder.

Name: Giganotosaurus (Real World)
Summary: Giganotosaurus is a genus of theropod dinosaurs that lived in what is now Argentina, during the early Cenomanian age of the Late Cretaceous period, approximately 98 to 97 million years ago. Giganotosaurus is thought to have been one of the largest theropod dinosaurs, but the incompleteness of its remains have made it difficult to estimate its size reliably.

Name: Gigantopithecus
Summary: The Gigantopithecus was a large primate that lived during the Pleistocene. It lived in India, China and Vietnam.

Name: Gildiss the Red Dragon
Summary: Gildiss the Red Dragon is the main antagonist of King of Dragons, a hack'n'slash game with fantasy themes.

Name: Gimli
Summary: Gimli is a stubborn, war-hungry dwarf and one of the many heroes in J.R.R Tolkien's The Lord of the Rings and Peter Jackson's films of the same name respectively. He joins the fellowship to destroy the ring and kill many orcs along the way. He is close friends with Aragorn and Legolas but still clashes with the elf due to the thousand-year-old feud between elves and dwarves. He participates in many battles including Moria, Helm's Deep and the Black Gate. His weapons include twin hatchets and a giant battle ax. He is very stubborn and often explains the stubbornness of dwarves. He loves fighting and even when outnumbered, he never backs down and always competes with Legolas to kill more orcs than him.

Name: Giovanni (Pokémon)
Key: '''By Himself''' | '''Pokèmon Team (Rocket Hideout)''' | '''Pokèmon Team (Silph Co.)''' | '''Pokèmon Team (Viridian Gym)''' | '''Pokèmon Team (Gen 2)''' | '''Pokèmon Team (Gen 5)''' | '''Pokèmon Team (Gen 7)'''
Summary: Giovanni is the leader of Team Rocket and the Viridian Gym, the father of Silver and a recurring antagonist in the series.

Name: Giraffe
Summary: Giraffes are the tallest living terrestrial animal and the largest ruminant.[1][2] Giraffes are characterized by their long necks and legs,[1][2] their horn-like ossicones,[1][2] and their distinctive coat patterns.[1][2] This appearance intrigued many cultures, both modern and ancient, and has often been featured in books, paintings, and cartoons.[3]

Name: Girallon
Summary: Girallon are a species of gorilla-like monsters found in D&D. They are known for their carniverous eating habits and their quasi-society found in the jungles of the world. Despite their animalistic intelligence, these creatures did indeed acknowledge the eldest among them as their leaders.

Name: Githyanki
Summary: Githyanki are the half of the Gith species that ended up following the original Gith, a member of their formerly nameless species hailing from a distant planet. When the time came to rebel against those who had enslaved them- the Mind Flayer empire, at the peak of its power- Gith led the charge and the Githyanki by her side. Now, battalions of the Githyanki scour the universe for more signs of their eternal foes, the Mind Flayers.

Name: Githzerai
Summary: In times long lost to the rampages of war, the Githzerai were once normal Githyanki who dissented from their brethren and formed a non-evil neutral faction. The Githzerai are ascetic monk-like folk who have settled in Limbo, a plane of chaos- a direct counter to their Lawful nature. They seek to battle the Slaadi, specifically to expand their knowledge in the face of direct adversity, building on the traits they learned from their slavery under the Mind Flayer empire.

Name: Glabbagool
Summary: An average Gelatinous Cube, Glabbagool gained heightened intelligence when the demon lord Juiblex arrived to the Underdark. Curious about the world and those in it he will not go out of his way to attack other beings but merely will self defend, he can be found in the Ooze Temple and is willing to offer assistance to adventurers who get into there, and if the part gains his trust he may even offer loot that's inside his body.

Name: Gladion
Key: '''By Himself''' | '''Pokèmon Team (Route 5)''' | '''Pokémon Team (Aether Paradise)''' | '''Pokémon Team (Mount Lanakila)''' | '''Pokémon Team (Pokémon League)'''
Summary: Gladion is a former member of the Aether Foundation and the son of Lusamine. He originally lived in harmony with his family in Aether Paradise until he noted his mother's obsession with the Ultra Beasts. Realizing the Ultra Beasts would bring ruin to Alola should they be released, Gladion left the foundation and stole one of their Type: Nulls. He then set out to stop Lusamine and free his Type: Null from its mask while working as an enforcer of Team Skull.

Name: Gleek (Post-Rebirth)
Summary: Gleek is an Exxorian Monkey and a performer in the Trans-World Carnival where he was abused by his owner, Ringmaster, but cared for by the Bearded Woman. Gleek was, for unknown reasons, eventually dropped and deemed a 'failure' before he was adopted by Zan of the Wonder Twins, who dearly loved him the moment he laid eyes on him. Gleek became a member of the Justice League and later, Asterisk, and accompanied the Wonder Twin on their many adventures.

Name: Glock pistol
Summary: The Glock is a semi-automatic pistol used mostly by law enforcement and military. It was created in Austria in 1980 to be a substitute of the outdated Walther P38.

Name: Gloria (Pokémon)
Summary: Gloria is a girl from Postwick and the main protagonist of Pokémon Sword version and Pokémon Shield version. Born and raised as the neighbor of Leon, the greatest Trainer that Galar has ever known, Gloria was destined for greatness at a young age as she became fast childhood friends with his younger brother, Hop.

Name: Glyptodon (Dungeons And Dragons)
Summary: A prehistoric mammal, the Glyptodon lived in the Ice Age and used its mace like tail to defend itself from predators such sabertoothed tigers, dire lions, and other deadly hunters such as dragons and humans.

Name: Gnoll (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: It is His blessing.

Name: Goat
Summary: Domesticated goats (Capra aegagrus hircus) are a subspecies of goat bred from the vulnerable Wild Goat. Goats vary greatly in weight based on breed, ranging from 20-27 kg for small goat does to over 140 kg for larger bucks such as Boer goats.

Name: Goblin (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: They breed fast, they spread fast; the Goblins are a small humanoid race and most well known of the Goblinoids.

Name: Goblin Shark
Summary: The goblin shark (Mitsukurina owstoni) is a species of deep-sea shark native to oceans worldwide. It inhabits depths of over 1300 meters below the surface, and primarily feeds on rays and crustaceans near the seafloor.

Name: Godzilla (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Godzilla is the name of the titular character of a Marvel comic series of the same name. The Marvel Godzilla was awakened by nuclear weapon testing in the Pacific Ocean and attacked Tokyo in 1956. Over the ensuing years, Godzilla became the lesser of two evils, fending off malevolent monsters that would attack Japan. By unknown means, he was eventually trapped in an iceberg and managed to break free once the iceberg reached Alaska in the 1970's.

Name: Gojirasaurus Quayi
Summary: Gojirasaurus quayi (Meaning "Godzilla lizard") is one of the largest known theropod carnivores of the Triassic Period. While it is somewhat of a dubious genus, it is thought to be a coelophysoid. Comparing the size of Gojirasaurus' tibia to its relatives, it has been estimated to be 5.5 meters or 18 feet in length and weighing up to 150-200 kg or 330–440 lb. As obviously shown in the name, this dinosaur was named after the iconic kaiju named Godzilla (Gojira).

Name: Golden Eagle
Summary: The Golden Eagle is a famous bird of prey native to most of the world. It has been trained by falconers and Steppe cultures for hundreds of years.

Name: Golf Club
Summary: A Golf Club is one of a set of specially shaped wooden or metal sticks used for hitting a golf ball

Name: Goose (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Goose is a Flerken that was the former pet of Mar-Vell before her death. Years later, she finds and joins Carol Danvers and Nick Fury, who initially believe she's just a normal cat.

Name: Gordon Freeman
Summary: Dr. Gordon Freeman is the main protagonist of the Half-Life series. He is a theoretical physicist who is forced to defend himself and the Human race against hostile Aliens and other enemies following an experiment gone wrong. In the process, he becomes an almost legendary resistance hero, eventually becoming one of the leaders of an uprising against the alien invaders.

Name: Gorgon (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: Gorgons are horrific bull-like creatures covered head-to-toe in iron plates protecting its true body. Their plates perpetually remain oiled thanks to secretions from their skin beneath, ensuring that it never rusts and remains as silent as possible. Gorgons, when they find prey, charge through them, oftentimes simply pulverizing weaker foes. The vapors that emit from the Gorgon are known to petrify enemies on contact, and not even those on other planes can escape its effects.

Name: Gorgosaurus (Real World)
Summary: Gorgosaurus is a genus of theropod dinosaur that lived in western North America during the Late Cretaceous period, approximately 76.6 to 75.1 million years ago. Like most known tyrannosaurids, Gorgosaurus was a large bipedal predator, measuring 8 to 9 meters in length and weighing 2 to 3 metric tons.

Name: Gorilla
Summary: The Gorilla is the largest genus of primate that currently roams the Earth, and is one of the closest living relatives to humans apart from chimps. Gorillas are found in Sub-Saharan Africa, and they can cover a wide range of elevations.

Name: Gorthok, the Thunder Boar
Summary: Gorthok, the Thunder Boar is a primordial spirit taken the physical form of a monstrous boar.

Name: Gotou (Parasyte)
Summary: Gotou (後藤, lit. Gotō) is an 'experimental' Parasite created by Reiko. His body is composed of five different individuals, something he can utilize to the fullest extent. He is the main antagonist of the series.

Name: Gragas
Summary: Equal parts jolly and imposing, Gragas is a massive, rowdy brewmaster on his own quest for the perfect pint of ale. Hailing from parts unknown, he now searches for rare ingredients among the unblemished wastes of the Freljord, trying each recipe as he goes. Often intoxicated and extremely impulsive, he is legendary for the brawls he starts, which often end in all-night parties and widespread property damage. Any appearance from Gragas must surely foreshadow drinking and destruction—in that order.

Name: Grand Admiral Thrawn
Summary: Tier: 9-A physically. 9-A with blasters

Name: Gravik (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Gravik was the leader of the radical Skrull Resistance and Skrull General in the Skrull Council, who grew disillusioned and spiteful of Nick Fury for abandoning him after Fury went into exile. Replacing Talos as the newly appointed Skrull General, Gravik initiated the Secret Invasion, launching covert terrorist attacks and attempting to manipulate humanity to engage in self-destructive nuclear war. By selling his movement as a way to allow the Skrulls to inhabit Earth as their new home planet, he began a war with the ultimate goal of getting revenge on Nick Fury for hurting him as a boy. Intending to raise an army of Super Skrulls, he sought the Harvest containing combatants' DNA from the Battle of Earth, although Gravik was killed by G'iah before he could fulfill his war.

Name: Gray Ooze
Summary: Gray Oozes are monstrous collections of single-cell organisms that essentially form a single large sensory organ, prowling dungeons for their sustenance. Unlike most other oozes, these creatures bear a heightened capacity for evolution, growing more sentient as it grows in size. While most often found in dungeon environments, they are often found slithering through the muck of brackish swamp-water.

Name: Gray Wolf
Summary: The Gray wolf is an infamous carnivorous animal found all in the Americas and Eurasia. It is known to humans more than almost any other predatory animal, with more importance to human culture than most others. Although the fear of wolves is common in humans, wolf attacks are very rare.

Name: Great Barracuda
Summary: The great barracuda (Sphyraena barracuda) is a species of scrombid fish endemic to subtropical waters worldwide. It is renowned for its ferocity and intimidating appearance.

Name: Great White Shark
Summary: The Great White Shark is a species of large lamniform shark which can be found in the coastal surface waters of all the major oceans. Great White Sharks are notable for their size, with mature female individuals growing up to 6.1 meters (20 feet) in length and 1,950 kg (4,300 lb) in weight. However, most are smaller with males measuring 3.35 - 3.96 meters (11 - 13 feet) and females 4.57 - 4.88 meters (15 - 16 feet) on average. According to a 2014 study the lifespan of Great White Sharks is estimated to be as long as 70 years or more, well above older estimates, making it one of the longest lived cartilaginous fish currently known. According to the same study, male individuals take 26 years to reach sexual maturity, while the females take 33 years to be ready to produce offspring. Great White Sharks can accelerate up to 56 km/h (35 mph) in short bursts.

Name: Green (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: One of several adventurers which solved Harmony City's energy crisis, Green is a Lore Bard, using their magic and martial skills to help.

Name: Green Arrow (Post-Crisis)
Summary: This page contains or depicts disturbing and/or graphic content that some may find upsetting, and that is only intended for mature audiences. Please proceed with caution.

Name: Green Hag
Summary: Green Hags are corrupted fey beings, evil incarnate originating from the land of fairies. Hags are best known for their tendencies of kidnapping and devouring children. In this way, they may birth their own kin- a week after consumption, hags birth a daughter exactly identical to their devoured counterpart, only to transform into a hag over a decade later. Hags view themselves as infinitely cunning and devious spellcasters, and will often accept dealing with mortals so long as they treat the hag with "proper" respect.

Name: Greenland Shark
Summary: The Greenland shark (Somniosus microcephalus) is a species of sleeper shark endemic to cold waters in the North Atlantic and Arctic Oceans. It is the longest living vertebrate species, with a lifespan of more than 400 years.

Name: Greevil
Summary: Greevil (Japanese: デスゴルド Deathgold) is the leader of the criminal group Cipher. He is the only character in the game to have the Trainer class Grand Master (Japanese: シャドー総帥 Shadow Leader).

Name: Grell
Summary: Grell are creatures that resemble floating brains with tentacles and a large beak protruding from the front. They are most famous for their voracious feeding habits- they bear little else in terms of dastardly plans outside of planning their next meal, going so far as to classify all things in life as "edible", "inedible", or "Great Eater" (those few things that might feed on a grell). While generally solitary, a rare few grell form great colonies led by philosophers, grell wizards that study the aberrant sciences of their native realm. The grell are non-hostile to other grell, and generally consider the choice of joining a colony as a matter of opinion.

Name: Grick
Summary: Gricks are rubbery predators most commonly encountered in the Underdark. Generally, these creatures are passive hunters- that is to say, they create dens by populated areas and regularly traveled passes, and grab whatever passes by. They will only leave once the area becomes less populated, then searching for greener pastures. Gricks often travel in packs, led by the strongest, best fed member.

Name: Griffon (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: Griffons are intelligent hybrids of lions and eagles. Their majesty is often hailed by cultures throughout the planes as a sign of goodness, and as such they are regularly used as mounts for good-aligned societies. The city of Waterdeep, the largest city of Faerun, maintained a large arsenal of Griffon cavalry. Netheril and Thay are two other superpowers that wielded the might of Griffons as their cavalry units. They are known to feed almost exclusively on horse flesh.

Name: Grimlock (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: Grimlocks are a species of humanoid creatures descended from two tribes of ancient barbarians that disappeared into the Underdark many millennia ago. Their children, blind and decrepit, now wander in the endless vistas of darkness in the subterranean landscape, serving mightier creatures when they can.

Name: Grimsley
Summary: Grimsley is a member of the Unova Elite Four and specializes in Dark-type Pokémon.

Name: Grippli
Summary: A peaceful tribal race, the Grippli appears like an oversized froh with human like limbs, they're native to jungle areas and only do trades with beings they have complete trust in. Grippli are quite good in learning, although they rarely produce metal products so any metal object they have is from a trade. Each tribe posseesses a Tribe Mother which one can distinguish from the rest through her size, she's said to possess the blood of the Gods and is the main priest in the tribe.

Name: Grizzly Bear
Summary: The Grizzly Bear is a subspecies of the Brown Bear found mostly in North America.[1] It is noted for being one of the largest subspecies of bears.

Name: Groot (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Groot is a hyper-intelligent, tree-like organism from the species Flora colossus native to the planet X. While he possesses human level intellect, Groot's robust and heavyweight physiology causes the organs of his acoustic generation to become stiff and inflexible, rendering the limits of his speech to the simple phrase, "I am Groot."

Name: Grung
Summary: One of the many amphibian humanoids in Dungeons and Dragons, the Grung are based on poisonous frogs. They emit a deadly poison from their skin, and also have a nasty bite and weapons to go alongside that.

Name: Guanlong
Summary: Guanlong is a genus of small proceratosaurid theropod family that lived during the late Jurassic in China. Its name comes from the Chinese words 冠, which means "crown", and 龍, which means "dragon." Its most distinctive feature is the crest on its head, which due to its fragile nature, was most likely for display.[1] It is the earliest discovered tyrannosauroid, and distantly related to the much larger and more famous Tyrannosaurus rex, which would emerge 92 million years later.

Name: Guard Drake
Summary: A Guard Drake is a medium sized dragonic creature which is the result of a magical ritual involving dragon scales. A Guard Drake could be trained like a dog to protect a place, they also had various unique powers depending on whch dragon scales were used to make them

Name: Guardians of the Galaxy (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Nebula: All any of you do is yell at each other. You're not friends. Drax: You're right... We're family.

Summary: Guzma (Japanese: グズマ Guzma) is the leader of Team Skull.

Name: Gwenpool
Summary: Gwendolyn Poole was just a normal girl, living an unsatisfactory life and with a fierce passion for Marvel Comics, when one day she was mysterious transported within the exciting world of her beloved stories. Extremely galvanized at this prospect, Gwen donned a costume and took on the identity of Gwenpool, determined to have the most fun of her new life. Extremely erratic, reckless and borderline psychotic, Gwen viewed herself as the protagonist of the story and the world around her as a playground, uncaring for even the lives of others, for they were expendable fictional characters. However, things quickly escalated and slipped out of her hands, making her bitterly realize the harsh truth: she was not in control .

Name: Gyarados
Summary: Gyarados is a Water/Flying Pokémon introduced in Generation I. It is the evolved form of Magikarp. Extremely vicious, enormously destructive, ferociously violent, and horribly brutal, it has a very aggressive nature. Although rarely seen in the wild, once it appears it goes on a rampage. When this happens, it doesn't calm until it has burned everything down and razed the fields and mountains around it. Not even harsh storms are able to stop its rage, and there are records of this Pokémon's rampages lasting a whole month. A single Gyarados has enough destructive power to totally annihilate even a major city. Gyarados is attracted to violence and tends to appear when there is a world conflict or war. When humans begin to fight, it will appear and burn everything to the ground with intensely hot flames. During past wars Gyarados would appear and leave blazing ruins in its wake, and in ancient literature there is a record of a Gyarados that razed a village when violence flared. When Magikarp evolves into Gyarados, its brain cells undergo a structural transformation. It is said that this transformation is to blame for this Pokémon's wildly violent nature.

Name: Haast's Eagle
Summary: The Haast's eagle was the largest eagle to have ever existed. It existed until a few hundred years ago when its primary prey source was hunted to death by humans.

Name: Half Ogre
Summary: The Half Ogre is a hybrid between humans and Ogres, smaller then Ogres but taller then most humans Half Ogres often act as leaders for Ogres who use their social skills, wits and battle skills to help their tribe.

Name: Halfling (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: The closest demihuman to humans, to the point where their name comes from being half as tall as human, Halflings are a naturally lucky race. Their society values comfort and security above all else, with them seldom venturing outside their home lands besides the dire of situations. This makes any Halfling adventurer the more fierce when going out to help their local community, with Halflings being naturally gifted in ranged combat and stealth.

Name: Hammer Drones
Summary: The Hammer Drones were the result of Justin Hammer enlisting Ivan Vanko to render Iron Man obsolete. Hammer wanted manned suits, but Vanko created remote-controlled drones instead, wishing to use them to attack Tony Stark. Hammer brought the drones to the Stark Expo in the hopes of regaining his contract with the government. Vanko sabotaged Hammer's efforts by activating the drones and making them wreak havok across the site of the Expo. Iron Man and War Machine were eventually able to defeat the drones, as well as Vanko himself.

Name: Hammerhead (Marvel Comics)
Summary: When left for dead in an alleyway after a brawl, a surgeon found Joseph and operated to fix him up, replacing his broken skull with a steel plate.

Name: Hank Pym (Marvel Cinematic Universe: What If...?)
Summary: Hank Pym, also known as Yellowjacket, is the main antagonist of "What If... the World Lost Its Mightiest Heroes?", the third episode of the Marvel animated anthology series What If...?. He is the inventor of size-changing "Pym Particles" and a former superhero working for S.H.I.E.L.D. as Ant-Man. However, after the death of his wife and daughter, he became disgruntled against Nick Fury, and decided to take revenge on him by killing every potential member for his "Avengers Initiative".
ID: Hank Pym (Marvel Cinematic Universe: What If...?)-MarvelCinematicUniverse-9

Name: Hank Pym (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Hank Pym, is a genius, one of the founding members of the Avengers, the creator of Pym Particles and Ultron, a sufferer of bipolar disorder and a modern-day superhero. He has acted under many memorable identities, such as Ant-Man, Giant Man, Goliath, Yellowjacket, and the Wasp. He is also the Earth's Scientist Supreme, as decreed by Eternity.

Name: Hanno Minstrelsong
Summary: Hanno Minstrelsong was a former thief and current businessman residing within Cormyr during the late 14th century. A proprietor of herbs and spices, Hanno generally err'd on the side of good, though he did sell non-lethal poison to those who seemed trustworthy. His original name is unknown, as he dropped it after a long, successful career as a thief- so successful than multitudes of assassins were sent to kill him, forcing him to leave his former life and adopt his position in Cormyr. He is described as always smiling.

Name: Harley Quinn (Post-Crisis)
Summary: Harley Quinn (Dr. Harleen Frances Quinzel) is a fictional character appearing in American comic books published by DC Comics, commonly as an adversary of the superhero Batman. The character was created by Paul Dini and Bruce Timm, and first appeared on Batman: The Animated Series in September 1992. She later appeared in DC Comics' Batman comic books, with her first comic book appearance in The Batman Adventures #12 (Sept. 1993).

Name: Harpy (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: Harpies are predatory humanoids, a grotesque mixture of vulture and human. Their origin lies in the longing of the elves- once, an elf heard the song of a beautiful bird, and as she wandered through the forest, she saw yet another elven youth- a god, unbeknownst to her. Immediately, the god fled, but the youth was struck by his presence, and came to despair when she failed to find him. Another god came to her aid, and taught her the song of the birds in an attempt to lure the other deity back. After failing, the elf maiden cursed the gods, and became the first Harpy.

Name: Hatzegopteryx
Summary: Hatzegopteryx is a genus of azdarchid pterosaur, and is among the largest of them all (with a greater mass than even Quetzalcoatlus). Its name means "Hateg basin wing," referring to the place it was found in Transylvania, Romania, where it once inhabited in the Late Cretaceous period. Despite its robust structure, this large pterosaur was capable of flight much like other large azhdarchids.

Name: Havok
Summary: Havok (Alexander "Alex" Summers) is a fictional superhero appearing in American comic books published by Marvel Comics, commonly in association with the X-Men. He first appears in Uncanny X-Men No. 54 (March 1969), and was created by writerArnold Drake and penciller Don Heck. Havok generates powerful "plasma blasts", an ability he has had difficulty controlling. One of the sons of Corsair, he is the younger brother of the X-Men's Cyclops, and the older brother of Vulcan. He often resents Cyclops' authoritarian attitude and reputation as a model X-Man.

Name: Hawkeye (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Iron Man: Clearly retirement doesn't suit you. Got tired of shooting golf? Hawkeye: Well, I played 18, shot 18... Just can't seem to miss.

Name: Hawkeye (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Clinton "Clint" Barton was a former circus worker and criminal-turned-hero, who received his archery skills as a young boy through training with Swordsman and Trickshot. Barton would eventually join both the East Coast and West Coast branches of The Avengers, even leading at one time.

Name: Hawkmon (Miyako Inoue)
Summary: Miyako Inoue and Hawkmon are main characters from Digimon Adventure 02. Miyako one of the many viewers watching the battle against Keramon in Our War Game.

Name: Heckler & Koch G3
Summary: The G3 (Gewehr 3) is a 7.62×51mm NATO, select-fire battle rifle developed in the 1950s by the German armament manufacturer Heckler & Koch (H&K) in collaboration with the Spanish state-owned design and development agency CETME (Centro de Estudios Técnicos de Materiales Especiales).

Name: Heckler & Koch G36
Summary: The Heckler & Koch G36 is a 5.56×45mm assault rifle, designed in the early 1990s by Heckler & Koch in Germany as a replacement for the heavier 7.62mm G3 battle rifle. It was accepted into service with the Bundeswehr in 1997, replacing the G3. The G36 is gas-operated and feeds from a 30-round detachable box magazine or 100-round C-Mag drum magazine.

Name: Heckler & Koch HK416
Summary: The Heckler & Koch HK416 is a rifle designed and manufactured by Heckler & Koch. Although its design is in large part based on the AR-15 class of weapons, specifically the Colt M4 carbine family issued to the U.S. military, it uses an HK-proprietary short-stroke gas piston system originally derived from the ArmaLite AR-18 (the same system was also used in Heckler & Koch's earlier G36 family of rifles). It is the standard assault rifle of the Norwegian Armed Forces, and was the weapon used by SEAL Team Six to kill Osama Bin Laden in 2011. It has also been selected as replacement of the FAMAS in the French Armed Forces. Since 2013, a new updated version called the HK416 A3 has effectively replaced the original HK416, with the A5 featuring several improvements like an improved tool-less adjustable gas regulator for suppressor use that can accommodate barrel lengths down to 10.5 inches without modifications, a redesigned lower receiver with ambidextrous fire controls, optimised magazine and ammunition compatibility, a repair kit housed inside the pistol grip, and additional heavy nuts to make its weak spots more resistant to accidental impact. The A7 version is basically a German-exclusive selector update on the A5, where the selector now rotates 90 degrees instead of the typical 180 degrees on most M16 rifles and their variants. The A8 version of the rifle, dubbed the G95KA1, was selected as the successor to the G36 as the new standard issue rifle for the German Bundeswehr in 2022.

Name: Heckler & Koch Mark 23 pistol
Summary: The Heckler & Koch MK 23, MK 23 MOD 0, Mark 23, or USSOCOM MARK 23 is a semi-automatic large-frame pistol chambered in .45 ACP, designed specifically to be an offensive pistol. The USSOCOM version of the MK23 came paired with a laser aiming module (LAM) and suppressor. The USSOCOM MK23 was adopted by the United States Special Operations Command (USSOCOM) for special operations units, beating out the nearest competitor, Colt's OHWS. Development of the pistol began in 1991 as special operations representatives identified the need for an "Offensive Handgun Weapons System—Special Operations Peculiar", and delivery of the pistols began in May 1996 to the special operation units.

Name: Heckler & Koch MP5
Summary: The MP5 (German: Maschinenpistole 5) is a 9x19mm Parabellum submachine gun, developed by a team of engineers from the German small arms manufacturer Heckler & Koch GmbH (H&K) in the 1960s. There are over 100 variants and clones of the MP5, including some semi-automatic variants.

Name: Heckler & Koch MP7 Submachine Gun
Summary: The Heckler & Koch MP7 (Maschinenpistole 7) is a German personal defence weapon (PDW) designed and manufactured by Heckler & Koch (H&K) and chambered for the HK 4.6×30mm cartridge. It was designed with the new cartridge to meet NATO requirements published in 1989, as these requirements call for a personal defense weapon (PDW) class firearm, with a greater ability to penetrate body armor than current weapons limited to conventional pistol cartridges. The MP7 went into production in 2001. It is a direct rival to the FN P90, also developed in response to NATO's requirement. The weapon has been revised since its introduction and the latest production variants are the MP7A1 and MP7A2.

Name: Heckler & Koch UMP
Summary: The Heckler & Koch UMP (Universale Maschinenpistole, German for "Universal Machine Pistol") is a submachine gun developed and manufactured by Heckler & Koch. Heckler & Koch developed the UMP as a lighter and cheaper successor to the MP5, though both remain in production. The UMP has been adopted for use by various countries, including Brazil, Canada, and the United States. Some of the weapons saw limited service in the early years of the Iraqi insurgency, making them one of the more popular submachine guns being deployed by the U.S. military personnel in recent conflicts around the world.

Name: Heckler & Koch USP
Summary: The USP (Universelle Selbstladepistole or "universal self-loading pistol") is a semi-automatic pistol developed in Germany by Heckler & Koch GmbH (H&K) of Oberndorf am Neckar as a replacement for the P7 series of handguns.

Name: Heinrich Zemo (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Baron Heinrich Zemo was born in 1900, the 12th Baron Zemo joined the Nazi Party early in its existence, quickly becoming one of the Nazis' top scientists and the most wanted Axis agent during World War II. Zemo was working on his invention known as Adhesive X when Captain America invaded his laboratories.
