In the course of destroying the only supply, the adhesive covered Zemo's cowled head, which became permanently affixed. As a result, Zemo was consumed with a violent, insane hatred for Captain America and mankind in general.

Name: Helicoprion
Summary: Helicoprion is a genus of large eugeneodont fish, a group of shark-like cartilaginous fish within the same group that includes modern chimaeras; while chimaeras are the closest living relative of Helicoprion, they are only distantly related. It lived around 290–270 million years ago during the early to middle Permian and were widespread in the oceans, found around the United States, Canada, Mexico, Norway, Russia, Kazakhstan, China, Japan, Laos, and Western Australia. They are famous for their one-rowed and laterally-compressed "tooth whorl" shape of their lower jaws, which aided them in catching prey at the time, and is the part most often fossilized. These creatures were among the largest cartilaginous fish, and the largest aquatic predators of their time and place.

Name: Hellcat (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Patricia "Patsy" Walker was a celebrity thanks to her mother's comic book series centered around her, and was living a model life with a husband who she had a crush on since high school, and money without hassle. But thanks to a particularly nasty divorce, she decided that her passion resided elsewhere from the typical household life, and with assistance from Beast scoured the streets as the crime-fighting vigilante known as Hellcat.

Name: Hellhound (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: Hell Hounds are a breed of extraplanar, fiery hound, often used as pets of infernal lords. Wild packs of Hell Hounds often roamed Baator, the Abyss, and even the Elemental Plane of Fire. As such, they could be found in the service of all manner of fiery outsiders, including Efreeti, Balors, and Pit Fiends.

Name: Hellwasp
Summary: Hellwasps, were insect-like fiends that inhabited the warmer levels of the Nine Hells.

Name: Helmed Horror
Summary: Helmed Horrors are silent warriors and guardians hailing from the time of the Netherese empire, created through powerful magic to create a construct with a sentience of its own. These warriors are designed to be loyal beyond a fault, and highly effective against invading spellcasters in particular. Despite appearing like simple animated suits of armor, Helmed Horrors in fact bear many magical abilities of their own, including the ability to imbue their weapons with arcane power and to see invisible foes.

Name: Helmut Zemo (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Colonel Helmut Zemo was a member of a death squad in Sokovian Armed Forces who lost his family to Ultron during the Battle of Sokovia. Zemo blamed the Avengers and sought revenge on them. He knew the Avengers could not be beaten through force, and instead attempted to manipulate them into destroying each other and took advantage of the friction between the Avengers during the signing of the Sokovia Accords by committing acts of terrorism and framing James Barnes, causing further conflict between Steve Rogers and Tony Stark. Zemo would eventually be caught by the Black Panther and imprisoned.

Name: Helmut Zemo (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Baron Zemo is the 13th of the Zemos of Zeulniz and is one of Captain America's most notorious enemies, often giving him a run for his money with his sinister plots and tactical thinking. His father, Baron Heinrich Zemo was the master Nazi scientist in World War II and convinced his son of the ideology of the Nazis being the master race, and that he was the only Zemo in line for ruling the world. However, after his fathers apparent death, Zemo blamed Captain America and vowed revenge on him, and to this day, still remains one of his most deadly foes. Despite his conflict with Captain America, he has on occasions teamed up with the Avengers and has served as a founding member of the Thunderbolts.

Name: Herrerasaurus
Summary: Herrerasaurus is a dinosaur that lived during the Late Triassic period, approximately 231 to 228 million years ago.[1] It is considered one of the earliest known dinosaurs and belongs to the group called theropods, which includes famous dinosaurs like Tyrannosaurus rex and Velociraptor.[1] Herrerasaurus was first discovered in the Ischigualasto Formation of northwestern Argentina in the 1960s.[1] The name "Herrerasaurus" is derived from the name of the rancher Victorino Herrera, who owned the land where the fossils were found.[1]

Name: Hetfish
Summary: The Hetfish is a type of fish which is unable to breath in water and instead relies on their body heat to boil water around them in order to create a steam environment in which they can live in. This fish is often murdered by civilised species due to them causing damage structures.

Name: Hill Giant
Key: '''Regular''' | '''Mouth of Grolantor''' | '''Barrowghast''' | '''Maw of Yeenoghu''' | '''Wereboar''' | '''Avalancher''' | '''Scion of Grolantor'''
Summary: Hill Giants are the lowest ranked of the True Giants, and fittingly are both the dumbest and shortest of them, but they're capable of surprisingly cunning actions in combat and they still possess great physical abilities.

Name: Hinome Hawakata
Summary: Hinome is the secondary main protagonist of the Im: Great Priest Imhotep series. She's Imhotep's first friend after being set free from his punishment for 3,000 years. She's a rather unorthodox high school girl who had a dark past involving the Magai which ties into Imhotep's origins. However, she has a brave, kind, and fierce heart. Helping Imhotep in his endeavors despite being a mere human. Always being willing to stick by his side and cheering him on, making him better himself.

Name: Hippogriff (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: Hippogriffs are believed to be distant cousins of Griffons, though instead of being an eagle-and-lion mixture, Hippogriffs bear more resemblance to a horse. Despite this they are still remarkably popular as mounts and, much like their cousins, are regularly used in airborne cavalry units.

Name: Hippopotamus
Summary: The hippopotamus is a herbivourous mammal that inhabits most of sub-saharan Africa.

Name: Hit-Monkey (Marvel Comics)
Summary: In mountainous wilderness, a clan of Japanese macaques took in a fugitive assassin, nursing him back to health with herbal remedies and hot springs, who upon regaining his health, began to hone his skills once more, practicing on snowmen.

Name: Hobgoblin (Dungeon and Dragons)
Summary: They fall beneath our blades,

Name: Homo Floresiensis
Summary: Homo Floresiensis or commonly nicknamed the Hobbit was a human species that lived from 190,000 years ago to around 50,000 years ago on the islands of Indonesia. They are famous for being very small, smaller than the range for normal modern humans and even Chimpanzees. They display the affect that Island Dwarfism has on animals, including humans.

Name: Homunculus (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: Homunculi are small contructs of magic users, created to act as assistants in their experiments. Indeed, such constructs are merely an extension of the master- it shares the thoughts and senses it has with its master, and the two are one being. They are telepathically bonded to their masters, and will never willingly leave them.

Name: Honey Badger
Summary: The Ratel or Honey Badger is an animal native to Africa and Asia known for its impressive durability and aggression.

Name: Hook Horror
Summary: Hook Horrors are predators originating from the Underdark, and mixes traits of eagles and insects into a single malign entity. Unlike most animals, especially in the hostile caverns of the Underdark, Hook Horrors form castes of clans, maintaining familial ties all through its life- thus, it is not uncommon to encounter a large horde of Hook Horrors.

Name: Hop (Pokémon)
Key: '''By Himself''' | '''Pokémon Team (Early Game)''' | '''Pokémon Team (Mid Game)''' | '''Pokémon Team (Late Game/Beginning of Post Game)''' | '''Pokémon Team (End of Post Game/Galarian Star Tournament)'''
Summary: Hop (Japanese: ホップ Hop) is one of the rival characters in Pokémon Sword and Shield and Leon's younger brother. He is your main rival throughout the games, eventually undergoing a period of self-doubt after a humiliating defeat at the hands of Bede, as he didn't want to be so weak as to drag down his older brother's name. After his defeat at the hands of the player in the Champion Cup, he eventually decides to work toward becoming a Pokémon Professor.

Name: Hope Summers
Summary: Hope Summers is a fictional character appearing in American comic books published by Marvel Comics. The superheroine first appeared in X-Men #205 in 2007 (Chapter five of the "X-Men: Messiah Complex" storyline). She is the first mutant born after the events of the "House of M" and "Decimation" storyline

Name: Horse
Summary: The horse (Equus ferus caballus) is one of two extant subspecies of Equus ferus. It is an odd-toed ungulate mammal belonging to the taxonomic family Equidae. The horse has evolved over the past 45 to 55 million years from a small multi-toed creature, Eohippus, into the large, single-toed animal of today. Humans began domesticating horses around 4000 BC, and their domestication is believed to have been widespread by 3000 BC. Horses in the subspecies caballus are domesticated, although some domesticated populations live in the wild as feral horses. These feral populations are not true wild horses, as this term is used to describe horses that have never been domesticated, such as the endangered Przewalski's horse, a separate subspecies, and the only remaining true wild horse. There is an extensive, specialized vocabulary used to describe equine-related concepts, covering everything from anatomy to life stages, size, colors, markings, breeds, locomotion, and behavior.

Name: Hououmon
Summary: Its Special Move "Starlight Explosion" has become even more powerful due to the increase in its holy power.

Name: Howard the Duck (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Howard Duckson, native of a parallel universe named Duckworld, was but an ordinary individual like many others, stuck in aimless and unsatisfying life. On a fateful day, a shift in the cosmic axis caused Howard to be trasported across the multiverse and into our universe. Him and other people likewise stranded from their home worlds banded together to find the source of their problem, but Howard's adventure was cut short when he fell into a dimensional abyss, ending up in the city of Cleveland. Howard had no choice by trying to make sense of his new situation the best he could, amongst hairless apes living in a world he never made!

Name: Howler
Summary: Howlers are predatory animals originating from Pandemonium, a realm of pure chaos. Often the creatures are imported from the plane, generally to the Lower Planes, for use as war hounds and exotic pets, often rivaling the status of creatures such as the Hellhound. They are famed for their unique, mind-numbing howl, which cripples enemies for easier hunting.

Name: Hrabbaz
Summary: Hrabbaz is a half-orc bodyguard currently working for the House of Gradlhund in Watredeep. He is extremely loyal to Yalah Gralhund while finding her husband annoying and hoping he'll be knocked down a peg.

Name: Hulk (Marvel Comics)
Key: '''Bruce Banner''' | '''Grey Hulk''' | '''Childlike Hulk''' | '''World War Hulk''' | '''Devil Hulk'''
Summary: nan

Name: Hulking Hurler
Summary: A class for massive creatures, the Hulking Hurler is someone who specializes in throwing objects incredibly hard. Often found amongst Giants, there are some smaller creatures which employ these tactics and act as a sort of artillery.

Name: Human Torch
Summary: The Human Torch is a fictional character, a superhero that appears in comic books published by Marvel Comics. He is a founding member of the Fantastic Four. A similar, unrelated character of the same name and powers had been created in 1939 by writer-artist Carl Burgos for Marvel Comics' predecessor company, Timely Comics.

Name: Humboldt Squid
Summary: The Humboldt Squid (Dosidicus gigas) is a popularly fished species of squid in the waters of the eastern pacific.[1] It's the largest member of the flying squid family and abundant due to overfishing.[1][2] Despite being a well-studied animal, the IUCN has classified the conservation status of the squid as data deficient.[1]

Name: Hunter (Fossil Fighters)
Summary: Tier: 9-B | At least 7-B, likely far higher | At least 7-B, likely far higher

Name: Hush (Post-Crisis)
Summary: Thomas Elliot is a renowned surgeon and childhood friend of Bruce Wayne. A meticulous planner, Elliot resents the fact that Bruce's father thwarted his plot to murder his parents. Aware of Bruce Wayne's secret identity, and assuming the identity of criminal mastermind Hush, he sets out to destroy Batman.

Name: Husky
Summary: The Siberian Husky is a breed of dog from, unsurprisingly, Siberia, bred for both working for humans and acting as a companion to them.

Name: Hyacinth Macaw
Summary: The Hyacinth Macaw (Anodorhynchus hyacinthinus), or hyacinthine macaw, is a parrot native to central and eastern South America. With a length (from the top of its head to the tip of its long pointed tail) of about one meter it is longer than any other species of parrot. It is the largest macaw and the largest flying parrot species.

Name: Hybodus
Summary: Hybodus is a genus of hybodont, a group of cartilaginous fish that emerged in the Middle Triassic and lasted until the Late Cretaceous[1]. Hybodus as a genus was prevalent throughout the early Jurassic. It is known for its distinctive fin spines, which likely served as protection from larger predators. They also displayed sexual dimorphism with the presence of clasper fins on the males, a trait maintained in modern sharks.[2]

Name: Hydra (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: Hydras are monstrosities with crocodile-like bodies and serpentine heads, ranging in number from five to twelve. Each hydra is descended from the primordial hydras, created when the dragon goddess Tiamat slew a fellow dragon deity, spreading her blood across the multiverse, each blood drop spawning a fearsome hydra. Hydras are famed for their unending hunger, for their sickening gluttony that often leads each head to turn on each other, devouring itself alive. Many warriors would hunt down and kill a Hydra in order to prove their strength.

Name: Hyneria
Summary: Hyneria is a genus of lobe finned fish, named after the village of Hyner in Pennsylvania where it was first discovered.[1] It lived in the Famennian part of the Devonion period, which was around 371.1 to 359.3 million years ago, and was an apex predator in freshwater environments it inhabited.

Name: I, Vampire (Pre-Flashpoint)
Summary: The only vampire capable of resisting his own lust for blood, Andrew Bennett, I, Vampire, is a hunter of his own kind, having dedicated his immortal life to taking the life of Mary, Queen of Blood, his former love, and her Cult of the Blood Red Moon.

Name: Ibrandlin
Summary: Ibrandlin, also known as lurkers in Darkness is a dragon like creature which is was created by priests of Ibrandul and are trained to be guards of various places.

Name: Ice Mephit
Summary: The cruelest of Mephits, the Ice Mephit is composed of air and water. Alongside a Mephit's usual array of abilities, they have many cold-based abilities, being able to generate ice and fog alike.

Name: Ichika Orimura
Summary: Ichika Orimura (織斑 一夏, Orimura Ichika) is the main protagonist of the Infinite Stratos series. A normal Japanese teenage boy, until it is discovered that he can pilot an IS which could only be used by women. Realizing the potential, Ichika is forced by the Japanese government to attend the prestigious Infinite Stratos Academy, an international academy where IS pilots from all over the world are trained. Thus his busy school life surrounded by girls begins.

Name: Ichthyosaurus
Summary: Ichthyosaurus is among the most well-known genera of ichthyosaurs: marine reptiles that bore fishlike features. Ichthyosaurus first appeared in the late Triassic period, with most fossils being dated back into the early Jurassic period. Ichthyosaurus is typically smaller than other ichthyosaurs, with a typical length of 6 feet and a typical weight of around 200 lbs (90.7184 kg), although one species of ichthyosaurus was assumed to be around 300-330 cm long.

Name: Idunn
Summary: Idunn (イドゥン, Idenn in the Japanese version) is the final boss of Fire Emblem: Binding Blade. She is also the Demon Dragon who is known as the Dark Priestess.

Name: Iguanodon
Summary: The Iguanodon is a herbivorous dinosaur from the Cretaceous Period. It is the second dinosaur discovered. It is surprisingly famous even though it did not make an appearance in any of the Jurassic Park movies. They come in many different weights.

Name: Ijin Yu
Summary: Ijin Yu is the main protagonist of the Mercenary Enrollment manhwa. When Ijin was nine, he and his parents were involved in a plane crash. Although Ijin survived, he was orphaned and was stranded from his remaining family. Eventually he was taken in by an group called The Numbers. Ijin underwent harsh training, and he worked as a mercenary for about eight years, serving in the harshest battlefields across the world. Later, during a rescue mission, he saved a RoK major named Kang Hamchan, his team and a doctor. Kang Hamchan traced Ijin's family and helped him retire. Ijin underwent a six-month orientation from Major Kang to help him adjust to civilian life. He's currently living with his grandfather and his sister in Seoul. Aside from attending Shinan high school, Ijin works as a part-time bodyguard at the SW group's security team, along with classmate Koh Sukjoo.

Name: IMI Desert Eagle
Summary: The Desert Eagle is a semi-automatic pistol, it is used by U.S Soldiers and Israeli forces.

Name: Immortus (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Growing old after after centuries of conquest and administrating timelines, Nathaniel Richards began seeking a way to achieve immortality and began studying the realm of Limbo and learned that it was a timeless place where he could live forever and decided to retire there to learn mastery of time. Breaching the barrier into Limbo, he later reinvented himself as Immortus and began following this destiny. But upon meeting the Time-Keepers he was manipulated into their servitude, and began working on his master plan to take over the timestreams and ensure by the end of time, only he remains.

Name: Imp (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: Imps are the most typical and average devils above the lemure fodder. Imps serve any number of purposes for their Archdevil overlords, ranging from assassins, foot-soldiers, scouts, and general cannon fodder.

Name: Indo-Pacific Sailfish
Summary: The Indo-Pacific sailfish (Istiophorus platypterus) is a species of billfish endemic to the Indian, Pacific, and Atlantic oceans. They are one of the fastest fish in the world.

Name: Inostrancevia (Real World)
Summary: Inostrancevia is a large carnivorous therapsid reptile, belonging to the group Gorgonopsia. Of all the gorgonopsids, Inostrancevia was the largest. It lived throughout present-day Siberia and North Africa during the late Permian Period. between 259-251.9 million years ago, and was an apex predator of its place and time. However, it would go extinct during the most catastrophic mass extinction event in Earth's history, the Permian-Triassic Extinction, at the end of both the Permian Period and the Paleozoic Era.

Name: Intellect Devourer
Summary: Intellect Devourers are, in simple terms, transformed brains of the victims of Mind Flayers. They are intelligent predators bred to take over the bodies of others, draining their intellect, and using their hollow shell to lure in more victims. As such, the creatures are extremely dangerous monstrosities that often rake in multiple victims.

Name: Invisible Blade
Summary: Masters of daggers and similar weapons, the Invisible Blade often appears suicidal to those looking from the side. However, their prowess with the blade is such that they can slay opponents far larger than them despite carrying nothing but a blade.

Name: Invisible Stalker
Summary: Invisible Stalkers are elementals originating from the Elemental Plane of Air, and are most commonly encountered as minions of stronger spellcasters. The creatures themselves are truly made of air, and almost impossible to detect as a result. They often tear enemies apart from the inside, viciously dealing with the enemies of their masters.

Name: Invisible Woman (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Dr. Susan "Sue" Richards (née 'Storm) was a college student before she was exposed to high levels of cosmic radiation when boyfriend and scientist, Dr. Reed Richards, took her with her younger brother, Johnny Storm and pilot Ben Grimm, into space in the stolen rocket Marvel-1. The radiation mutated her and her friends, turning her invisible and allowing her to create forcefields. Together they became the Fantastic Four, a team of adventurers who explored space, time and alternate dimensions and saved the world along the way from science-based threats, with Sue going by the name the Invisible Woman.

Name: Iowa-class Battleship
Key: '''Pre-Refit (World War II/Korean War/Vietnam War-era)''' | '''Post-Refit (Persian Gulf War-era)'''
Summary: The Iowa-class battleships were a class of fast battleships designed and fielded by the United States Navy in 1939–1940 to escort their Fast Carrier Task Forces operating in the Pacific Theater during World War II. Four were completed, while two more were laid down but were not finished before the war's end and were ultimately scrapped. Like other third-generation American battleships, the Iowa class emphasized speed in addition to secondary and anti-aircraft batteries.

Name: Iris (Pokémon)
Summary: Iris is a trainer from Unova. Originally one of the two gym leaders for Opelucid City, she became the champion of the Unova league after extensive training from Drayden.

Name: Iron Fist (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Danny Rand was the child of owners of Rand Enterprises. After a plane crash where his parents died he was rescued by two monks who took him to K'un-Lun where he trained and later earned the title of Iron Fist.

Name: Iron Fist (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Iron Fist (Daniel "Danny" Rand) is a fictional character, a superhero appearing in comic books published by Marvel Comics. Created by Roy Thomas and Gil Kane, he first appeared in Marvel Premiere #15 (May 1974). He is a practitioner of martial arts and the wielder of a mystical force known as the Iron Fist, which allows him to summon and focus his chi. The character starred in his own solo series in the 1970s, and shared the title Power Man and Iron Fist for several years with Luke Cage, partnering with Cage to form the superhero team Heroes for Hire. The character has starred in numerous solo titles since, including The Immortal Iron Fist, which expanded on his origin story and the history of the Iron Fist.

Name: Iron Man (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: J.A.R.V.I.S.: Sir, there are still terabytes of calculations needed before an actual flight is adju- Tony: J.A.R.V.I.S., sometimes you gotta run before you can walk.

Name: Iron Man (Marvel Comics)
Key: '''Human''' | '''Extremis Enhanced and RepulsorTech Node''' | '''With Iron Man Armors''' | '''Cosmic Iron Man'''
Summary: Iron Man, or Tony Stark, is the main hero of a comic by the same name. Stark: an inventive genius, industrialist, and multi-billionaire, went to Vietnam to oversee a field test for one of his transistorized weapons, that his company Stark Industries made.

Name: Iron Man Armor Model 1
Summary: Model 1 was the first ever Iron Man armor created by Anthony Stark with help of Ho Yinsen, with the purpose of keep Stark heart beating after having his chest being lodged with shrapnel and as way to escape from his capturers in Vietnam. It would later be upgraded into several new advanced armors over the years.

Name: Iron Man Armor Model 2
Summary: After a disastrous battle with the criminal known as Mister Doll, Tony Stark came to realize that the Iron Man Armor Model 1 was too cumbersome, especially in his state, which caused specially an unnecessary excessive use of energy for the armor to simply sustain its own weight. To remedy this, Tony designed a sleeker, lightweight armor while increasing its strength.

Name: Ironheart (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Riri Williams is an MIT student, and one of the smartest people on earth. She was hired by the CIA to find vibranium, but later got taken by the Wakandans to find the Tolokanil base. She has created a suit of armor for herself, granting her the name Ironheart.

Name: Isabeau (In Stars and Time)
Summary: Isabeau Manon Constantin Moineau is a major character in the game In Stars and Time and START AGAIN: a prologue, traveling with Mirabelle, Odile, Siffrin, and Bonnie on a quest to defeat the King and save Vaugarde from the fate of being frozen in time. Isabeau is a kind, cheerful person from the city of Jouvente. Throughout the game, he’s often shown making puns with Siffrin.

Name: Isti-Zar
Summary: Isti-Zar was a banelar naga serving the Church of Cyric, the Mad God, in the 14th century. He was allied with the followers of Shar attempting to create a magical dead zone in the Vast Marsh by tearing and ripping a hole in the Spellweave. During this time, Isti-Zar was slain by an adventuring party invading his territory, failing to assist the cult he had been allied with.

Name: Izek Stranzi
Summary: A child born with no soul, Izek Stranzi naturally lacked the emotional capacity granted by the souls of humans. He only felt emotion in regards to his family. One night, his family was attacked by a dire wolf, separating him from his sister.

Name: J'son (Marvel Comics)
Summary: J'son was the ruler of the Spartax Empire who fell in love with a human, Meredith Quill, when he crash-landed on Earth. He promised to return for her, but never did, and his son grew to become Star-Lord.

Name: Jack Carver
Summary: Jack, a former United States Army Special Forces soldier, has left his past behind and offers his services as a freelance boat charter in the South Pacific. He is employed by a reporter named Valerie Constantine to take her to a mysterious island, once occupied by the Japanese during the war, claiming to study its little-known World War II ruins. When Valerie goes ashore alone on a jetski, Jack anchors down shortly before his boat is destroyed by a missile launched by an army of mercenaries occupying the island.

Name: Jack Cooper (Titanfall 2)
Summary: As the main and playable protagonist of Titanfall 2, Rifleman Jack Cooper forms a bond with his Titan, BT-7274, in the game's campaign, where he and his new ally must complete their mission that could save multiple worlds in the frontier from destruction. He stands with the Militia against the IMS, the two strongest factions in the Frontier.

Name: Jack Russell (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Jack Russell is a werewolf dubbed Werewolf by Night. Afflicted with a curse that causes him to transform during a full moon, Russell strove to help other monsters in need and hunt monsters that were a danger to others. In order to assist his friend, Ted Sallis, Russell attended a gathering of monster hunters competing for the Bloodstone. Russell worked with Elsa Bloodstone to free Sallis, but in doing so exposed himself as a monster. Verussa Bloodstone captured him and forced him to transform, inadvertently unleashing the werewolf by night on her own forces. Russell spared Elsa and fled, reuniting with Sallis.

Name: Jackalwere
Summary: Jackalwere are infernal creatures created by the demon lord Graz'zt to serve his insidious servants, the Lamias. Cowards and charmers, the Jackalwere lulls enemies into a false sense of security and ease, then tears them apart. The creatures are designed to lie and to steal, to kidnap and to kill, for their masters.

Name: Jaculi
Summary: Being a 15 foot long snake it uses its innate camouflage abilities which it derives from the ability to alter its skin to either stone or wood it uses it to sneak on top of a tree and then long at an unsuspecting target with the precision and power of a spear.

Name: Jaekelopterus
Summary: Jaekelopterus is a genus of predatory eurypterid, a group of extinct aquatic arthropods. Fossils of Jaekelopterus have been discovered in deposits of Early Devonian age, from the Pragian and Emsian stages. There are two known species: the type species J. rhenaniae from brackish to fresh water strata in the Rhineland, and J. howelli from estuarine strata in Wyoming. The generic name combines the name of German paleontologist Otto Jaekel, who described the type species, and the Greek word πτερόν (pteron) meaning "wing".

Name: Jaguar (Real World)
Summary: The Jaguar (Panthera onca) is the largest felid in the Americas and has the highest bite force of any cat. Overall, the jaguar is the largest native cat species of the New World and the third largest in the world. This spotted cat closely resembles the Leopard, but is usually larger and sturdier. It ranges across a variety of forested and open terrains, but its preferred habitat is tropical and subtropical moist broadleaf forest, swamps and wooded regions. The jaguar enjoys swimming and is largely a solitary, opportunistic, stalk-and-ambush predator at the top of the food chain. As a keystone species it plays an important role in stabilizing ecosystems and regulating prey populations.

Name: Janma Gleamsilver
Summary: Janma Gleamsilver was an assassin working for the Zhentarim during the Tiamat crisis. Working as an investigator, she eventually joins a caravan of Dragon Cultists and a party of adventurers. From here, she works to manipulate the party into assisting her, using them to fight against a common enemy.

Name: Jasmine (Pokémon)
Summary: Jasmine is the leader of the Olivine Gym who specializes in Steel-type Pokemon.

Name: Jayna (Post-Rebirth)
Summary: Jayna is an Exxorian superhero who was sent to Earth after realizing her grandfather was an infamous corrupt politician who ruined the lives of virtually every family on their planet. As her father was a friend of Superman, she was offered an internship at the Hall of Justice an quickly became a true-blue member of the Justice League, sometimes assisting Superman and Batman on missions and later joined Young Justice as well. After going on a world-saving adventure without the permission of Superman and the other Leaguers, Jayna and her brother were kicked from the league, but became members of Asterisk, a team set up by the league to help the world in non-violent means.

Name: Jean-Luc Picard
Key: '''TV Picard''' | '''Movie Picard''' | '''Piloting auxiliary crafts''' | '''Assimilated into the Borg'''
Summary: Jean-Luc Picard, known to the Borg Collective by his designation of Locutus, was a celebrated Starfleet officer, archaeologist and diplomat who served during the latter two thirds of the 24th century. The highlights of his career were centered around assignments as commanding officer of the Federation starships: USS Stargazer, USS Enterprise-D, and the USS Enterprise-E. In these roles, Picard not only witnessed the major turning points of recent galactic history, but also played a key role in them, from making first contact as captain of the Federation's flagship with 27 alien species, including the Ferengi and the Borg.

Name: Jeff the Land Shark
Summary: Jeff is one of several land sharks created by M.O.D.O.K. Superior as a result of his many experiments. Jeff was incidentally found and rescued by the West Coast Avengers, leading him to be adopted by Gwenpool and becoming her pet, much to the uncertainty of her teammates. From there on, Jeff's charm earned him the favours of several other superheroes, such as Deadpool, Elsa Bloodstone and Kate Bishop, who attended him from time to time and even made him tag along in their adventures.

Name: Jericho 941
Summary: The Jericho 941 is a double-action/single-action semi-automatic pistol developed by Israel Weapon Industries (prior to 2005, Israel Military Industries) that was introduced in 1990.

Name: Jericho Swain
Summary: Tier: 9-A | 7-C

Name: Jessica Jones (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Jessica Jones is a private investigator from New York City. After she was orphaned at a young age, Jones was taken in by Dorothy Walker and developed a sisterly bond with her daughter, Trish. During adolescence, Jones discovered she possessed superhuman strength and used her ability in adulthood to fight crime as a superhero.

Name: Jigsaw (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: William "Billy" Russo was abandoned by his mother as a child and taken in at the Ray of Hope group home, until he suffered injuries while fighting off abuse by one of the carers. Joining the U.S. Marine Corps by adulthood, he became close friends with Francis "Frank" Castle, but they were both recruited into Operation Cerberus, a secret illegal military drug trafficking scheme in Afghanistan which resulted in the murder of an Afghan police officer and the deaths of numerous soldiers, ostensibly to help win the war. After returning home, Billy (who now owned a private military firm) was hired by the operation's ringleader to cover up the campaign by killing all involved personnel still alive, including Frank (now known as "the Punisher"), but the conspiracy was ultimately foiled and Russo's face was violently mutilated during a fight with his former friend, before being arrested.

Name: Jigsaw (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Billy Russo was a favourite hitman for the Costa mob, nicknamed "the Beaut" because of his good looks. Russo was hired by the Costas to assassinate Frank Castle, but failed to do so as Frank narrowly avoided death in an explosion. Hours later, Castle, now turned into the Punisher, tracked down Russo to one of the Maggia's nightclubs: Salvagno's. Several criminals were killed, and Russo was thrown through a glass pane head-first. Somehow, he survived with his face torn to shreds; surgeons stitched it back together like a jigsaw puzzle. Taking advantage of his now hideous visage, the formerly handsome gangster took on the identity of Jigsaw and swore revenge against the vigilante, becoming his archnemesis.

Name: Jihyeon Lee
Summary: (이지현 Lee Ji-hyeon) Jihyeon Lee is a secondary character in Questism. She is currently the No.8 of West Gangbuk High, but was previously the No.9 of South Gangbuk High. She is also the love interest of Gukja Yang.

Name: Jim Hopper
Summary: Jim Hopper, nicknamed "Hop", is the chief of Hawkins Police Department. Hopper has lived in Hawkins nearly all his life, having attended high school with Joyce Byers and Bob Newby. He has also been addressed as "Sheriff Hopper," but this is not a correct title. Hopper was married and they had a daughter together, Sarah. They divorced after his young daughter died of cancer, which caused him to lapse into alcoholism. For a few years after Sarah's death, he was a cop in "a big city"; the show never states which city. When he had been in the city long enough, he moved back to Hawkins. Eventually, he grows to be more responsible, saving Will Byers as well as taking Eleven in as his adopted daughter. In Season 3, he tries to break up Eleven and Mike since their relationship is moving too fast for him, whilst simultaneously trying to rekindle his relationship with Joyce. After the events of Season 3, he was kidnapped by the Soviets and forced to do manual labor for them as their prisoner. He eventually managed to escape, and returned to his life with Eleven and Joyce.

Name: Jinny Hex (Post-Rebirth)
Summary: Jinny Hex is a superhero from Texas and the great-great-granddaughter of Jonah Hex. Raised by a single mother in a rural town, Jinny was ignorant of her heritage until her mother, now on her deathbed, told her of the adventures of her distant relative and the treasure he left behind. After gaining the stash of treasure, Jinny traveled to Metropolis and ended up joining Young Justice and accompanied them on many adventures across the multiverse before she traveled back to Texas to face her deadbeat father in his quest to become king of the world.

Name: John Constantine (Classic)
Summary: This page contains or depicts disturbing and/or graphic content that some may find upsetting, and that is only intended for mature audiences. Please proceed with caution.

Name: John Pilgrim
Summary: A man known only as Robert was once an assassin who did work for the Aryan Brotherhood until he was imprisoned following a failed assassination at a bar. Bailed out by Anderson and Eliza Schultz, leaders of the powerful Testament Industries corporation, Robert turned to a new life as pious family man and pastor John Pilgrim.

Name: Josephoartigasia Monesi
Summary: Josephoartigasia monesi is the largest known rodent ever. It is significantly larger than any living rodent, weighing in at a range from 480-500 kg.[1] It may have used its incisors for the same reasons elephants used their tusks: for digging and as a defense mechanism. It lived from 4 to 2 million years ago during the Pliocene and early Pleistocene.

Name: Jubilee (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Jubilation Lee was the daughter of two wealthy Chinese immigrants, but after her parents lost all their money in the stock market and were subsequently killed, Jubilation was sent to an orphanage that she would soon run away from. Living in a mall, Jubilation discovered her mutant powers when she was cornered in a back alley by security guards, creating blinding lights that allowed her to escape. One day, the M-Squad was called in to capture her, but she was saved by Psylocke, Storm, Rogue and Dazzler. Jubilation followed them through a portal to the X-Men base. Eventually she freed Wolverine from the Reavers and went on several adventures with him before finally joining the X-Men as Jubilee.

Name: JumboGamemon
Summary: A gigantic Cyborg Digimon that added beam cannons to its entire body until the strength of its Metal Body's shell was compromised.

Name: K-999
Summary: K-999 is a robotic dog created by Tux Dog to assist the Problem Solverz. He was programmed with the task of assisting the Problem Solverz with solving problems, although for the most part, he only got in their way and acted as a nuisance in his first appearance on the show. He is friendly towards Alfe and has a small disdain for Roba and Horace.

Name: Kaecilius (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Kaecilius was a sorcerer and a former member of the Masters of the Mystic Arts. He became corrupted and opposed the Ancient One and his former brothers-in-arms when he felt his mentor had failed in her promise to help him find meaning to his wife and son's tragic deaths or found a way to bring them back together. Becoming angered by this, Kaecilius rebelled against his allies and formed the Zealots, aiming to find their meaning in the Mystic Arts that the Ancient One was hiding from them. He and his followers then stole a few pages of the Book of Cagliostro from Kamar-Taj's library as part of his scheme to summon Dormammu of the Dark Dimension to Earth. He is ultimately defeated when Dormammu accepts Doctor Strange's bargain to leave Earth and take the souls of Kaecilius and his minions with him in return for freedom from the time-loop that Strange created.

Name: Kagha
Summary: Kagha is a low-level archdruid who places herself in control of the Emerald Grove following the disappearance of the grove's master, Halsin, amidst the Absolute Crisis in 1492 DR. Kagha is secretly an agent of the Shadow Druids, a follower of Archdruid Kaelis who subtly goaded Kagha to accept her patronage, leading her to believe that the grove would be safer in their hands. As a result, when she became First Druid, Kagha worked to seal the grove from the outside world in its entirety, attempting to forcefully banish a large group of tieflings in doing so.

Name: Kamen Rider Kabuto
Summary: Souji: I'll only tell you this once. Those walking the same path don't merely pass at comrades. But those who walk different paths, and arrive together at the end are... Arata: …Friends. Are those your grandmother's words? Souji: No. They're my words.

Name: Kamen Rider KickHopper
Key: '''Sou Yaguruma''' | '''Kamen Rider TheBee/KickHopper''' | '''Post-Oma Day (Kamen Rider KickHopper)''' | '''Post-Oma Day (Another Kabuto)'''
Summary: Sou Yaguruma was originally an agent of ZECT who was the first user of the TheBee Zector and led the elite Shadow ZECT Troopers, being a perfectionist and tactician. But Souji Tendou constantly outwitted him, causing Yaguruma to place his sense of "Perfect Harmony" over his squad, resulting in him being dismissed. Upon his next arrival, he became a self-loathing man. Yaguruma became Kamen Rider KickHopper and used his new power to become a reoccurring threat to Tendou and the Worms.

Name: Kamen Rider Kuuga
Key: '''Yusuke Godai''' | '''Growing Form''' | '''Regular Forms''' | '''Rising Forms''' | '''Amazing Mighty Form''' | '''Ultimate Form'''
Summary: I don't want to see people crying anymore. I want everyone to smile! So have a good look... at my... transformation!

Name: Kamen Rider OOO
Key: '''Eiji Hino''' | '''The Revival of Greeed, the Birth of OOO, and the Scramble of Medals (Episodes 1-16)''' | '''The Man of One Hundred Million, the Other Ankh, and the Purple Medals (Episodes 17-38)''' | '''The Bond of Allies, the End of the World, and the Greed Towards Tomorrow (Episodes 39-48)''' | '''Post-Series''' | '''Heisei Generations FINAL''' | '''OOO 10th: Core Medal of Resurrection'''
Summary: Eiji Hino (火野 映司, Hino Eiji?) is the main protagonist of Kamen Rider OOO. He is a 21-year-old homeless traveller who was the son of a politician. When traveling to Africa, he befriended a little girl named Ruu and attempted to use his fortune to help her struggling village. Unfortunately, this would drag Eiji into the civil war that this village was involved in. During the situation, he failed to save Ruu from being tragically killed. Eiji was then held for ransom which his parents ended up paying for, as well as using the situation as a means to gain support for their public platform.

Name: Kang Chan
Summary: Kang Chan, or God of Blackfield is the main protagonist of God Of Blackfield and a Reincarnate. In his previous life, Kang Chan was a captain of the French foreign legion along with Dayeru, Smithen, and Sharlan. During one of his missions, he gained infamy and became known as the "God of Blackfield". In 2016, he was assigned with a mission to clear out enemy soldiers of a head executive named Masallan in Africa. Five squads were dispatched including Chan's team which included Smithen and Dayeru along with six other members. Two kilometers before the arrived at their destination the team fell into an enemy's ambush, Smithen got shot first and the whole team was overwhelmed under enemy's fire. As the firefight continued, Dayeru got shot whilst Kang Chan tried to keep Smithen from bleeding out. However, as he stood to fight the enemy and help his follow soldiers, Chan was killed by a shot from a sniper to the back of his head; his last sight as he lay dying was the enemy troops moving forward and killing his teammates. As Kang Chan's mind fell into oblivion, he felt severe headache and thirst. As he gradually came to his senses, he could heard a person speaking Korean. He finds out that he is in Se-Byeol Hospital in Gangnam, South Korea. As he learns that he was unconscious for 3 days, he runs over to a mirror and discovers that he's now in the body of an 18-years-old Korean boy who's also named Kang Chan.

Name: Kang the Conqueror (Classic)
Summary: Nathaniel Richards, a 31st-century scholar and possible descendant of Reed Richards, becomes fascinated with history and discovers the time travel technology created by Victor von Doom. Richards then travels back in time to ancient Egypt aboard a Sphinx-shaped timeship and becomes the Pharaoh Rama-Tut, with plans to claim En Sabah Nur as his heir. Rama-Tut's rule is cut short when he is defeated by the time-displaced Fantastic Four.

Name: Kang the Conqueror (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Nathaniel Richards was a scientist from the 31st Century who discovered the Multiverse's existence and joined the Council of Kangs in ruling over the foreseeable realities. Deeming the council's actions to be destroying the Multiverse, Richards sparked the Multiversal War, seeking to conquer as many worlds as possible as Kang the Conqueror. However, the council decided to banish him to the Quantum Realm, where he allied with Janet van Dyne to rebuild his Time Sphere, until he was betrayed after van Dyne discovered his true nature. Kang was once again trapped in the Quantum Realm, using that time to conquer part of it and build an empire in Axia.

Name: Kangal Dog
Summary: The Kangal dog is a breed of guard dog originating from Kangal Province, Sivas, Turkey, used to defend both livestock herds and human families. Unlike many other domestic dogs, Kangals are rather antisocial and do not like being around too many people.

Name: Karate Kid (Earth-Prime)
Summary: Val Armorr, the Karate Kid, is a founding member of the Legion of Super-Heroes, a group of teenagers inspired by the actions of superheroes from centuries ago, to rise up and stand against a society of quiet inaction and strict protocol.

Name: Karl Mordo (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Karl Mordo came to the Kamar-Taj to become one of the Masters of the Mystic Arts in order to avenge a tragedy in his life. Mordo was initially arrogant and disrespectful to others, but he eventually humbled and set aside his thirst for revenge. He was noted for being rigid and unwilling to compromise his beliefs of the natural order that he gained. Mordo became a Master and assisted the Ancient One in recruiting and training others in the ways of magic.

Name: Karnak
Summary: Karnak is a fictional character appearing in American comic books published by Marvel Comics. He was created by Stan Lee and Jack Kirby and debuted in Fantastic Four (vol. 1) #45 (1965) along with other members of the Inhuman Royal Family.

Name: Katana (Post-Crisis)
Summary: Tatsu Yamashiro (or just Katana) is a samurai warrior whose skill with a sword allows her to fight for justice as a superhero. Her tragic backstory includes the death of her husband, Maseo, whose soul becomes trapped in her blade, the Soultaker.

Name: Katana (Real Life)
Summary: The Katana is a type of single-edged longsword indigenous to Japan. It first saw use during the Muramachi period of Japan's history, just prior to the rise of Oda Nobunaga. Since then, its decidedly impressive design and former status as a symbol of nobility has ingrained it into pop culture, leading to its production even in the modern day.

Name: Kate Bishop (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Clint: This life you wanna live. To really help people. I mean, try to help people, anyway. Comes a lot of sacrifices. And some things you'll lose... forever. Kate: Well, there's also things you gain, like trick arrows and a cool costume.

Name: KelTec P11
Summary: The KelTec P11 is a compact, semi-automatic, short-recoil operated pistol chambered in 9 mm Luger. Discontinued in 2019, the P11 was manufactured by Kel-Tec CNC Industries of Cocoa, FL from 1995 to 2019.

Name: Kenku
Summary: Kenku are shady tricksters present in the land of Faerun. Known for their striking inability to speak on their own, they solely communicate via mimicking the voice patterns of others around them. They have the characteristics of large, flightless birds, and are descended from magical avians from the land of Kara-Tur. Thanks to the chaos of the Spellplague, Kenku were able to spread their influence across most of Faerun, and are noted as exceptional spies and assassins in Waterdeep and beyond. However, their primary bases were still exclusively in the Southeast in a territory known as "The Beastlands".

Name: Ketsarra Shadowscale
Summary: Ketsarra Shadowscale is one of two leaders of a cult of Shar, and is the half-dragon lizardfolk descendant of the dragon Despayr, an extremely unique dragon with strong ties to the Plane of Shadow. Ketsarra was made into an undead shadowy creature at birth as a pawn in Despayr's schemes. Ketsarra became the leader of the Dragonslayer tribe of lizardfolk (an ironic title to hold) and commanded tribes on both the Prime and the Plane of Shadow.

Name: KGBeast (Post-Crisis)
Summary: Trained by a top-secret cell of the KGB known as The Hammer, Anatoli Knyazev was an assassin known to the C.I.A. as the KGBeast. Having over 200 kills in his debut he was sent to America by The Hammer to assassinate 10 U.S officials, one of which was to visit Gotham City. This caught the Batman's eye and after battling twice the Beast cut his left arm off after it was restrained by the Batrope. He had his left arm replaced with a cybernetic gun, but in their 3rd battle Batman destroyed the gun arm and trapped him in a sewer where, he was later captured by police. Despite this, Anatoli escaped and became a recurring enemy of Batman, until he was killed by Tally Man under orders by Great White Shark.

Name: Kilij (Real World)
Summary: A kilij (from Turkish kılıç, literally "sword") is a type of one-handed, single edged and moderately curved saber used by the Turarian Empire, Uyghur Khaganate, Seljuk Empire, Timurid Empire, Mamluk Empire, Ottoman Empire, and the later Turkic Khanates of Central Asia and Eurasian steppes. These blades evolved from Turko-Mongol sabers that had been used over all the lands invaded and/or influenced by the Turkic peoples.

Name: Killer Moth (Post-Crisis)
Summary: Having decided that the lawbreakers of Gotham City needed a costumed protector just as honest citizens had Batman, Drury Walker emulated the Dark Knight in every way, copying his paraphernalia and building on his legend to create his own super villain identity, The Killer Moth. He eventually came to resemble a dark mirror image of Batman, even adopting the alter ego of a wealthy philanthropist similar to Bruce Wayne. Moth was motivated by greed rather than justice, and only served the criminal underworld for a price.

Name: King Cobra (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Klaus Voorhees was an ex-convict working with the humanitarian medical researcher Professor Ezekiel Shecktor in India on a universal antitoxin for snake venom. Jealous of Shecktor's success, Voorhees plotted to kill him and make the murder look like an accident. Hence, Voorhees induced one of the cobras kept in the laboratory to bite both Shecktor and himself. Voorhees planned to use the universal antitoxin to save himself from death. Unknown to Voorhees, the cobra had been irradiated. The combination of the radioactive venom in his bloodstream and the experimental anti-toxin which he used created a mutagenic catalyst which gave Voorhees certain cobra-like powers.

Name: King of Feathers
Summary: A monstrous Tyrannosaurus Rex, the King of Feathers was a beast that served the monster lord of Omu and was feared by all creatures in the forbidden city. Its name is from the fact that it has a plumage across its head, outside this it was also different from a regular T-Rex via its magical abilities like being able to cast Misty Step and summoning swarms of wasps

Name: Kingdom of Blackmoor
Summary: An ancient nation that predates the modern world of Mystara. Possessing hyper-advanced technology, Blackmoor was able to construct weapons of enormous destruction and objects of incredible power. Prideful and arrogant, eventually they destroyed themselves when a nuclear reactor went critical and destroyed the majority of their civilization. The survivors of Blackmoor would colonize another planet, but like before their arrogance resulted in their destruction.

Name: Kingpin (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Wilson Grant Fisk is a powerful businessman and crime lord with an interest in controlling New York City. Having formed alliances with other criminal enterprises, Fisk used the aftermath of the Battle of New York to gain power in the city, and attempting to rebuild Hell's Kitchen by destroying and gentrifying it. His criminal activities brought him into a conflict with Daredevil, as well as some of his partners who betrayed him, and he was arrested after his actions were leaked to the FBI. Within Ryker's Island, Fisk began building up a following and came to run the prison. Seeking to destroy the crime competition in New York by the time he got free, Fisk assisted with the Punisher's escape, as he desired to eliminate all competing criminal empires as the Kingpin, pitting him in conflict with Nelson and Murdock who had sought to send him to prison.

Name: Kingpin (Marvel Comics)
Summary: The Kingpin (real name Wilson Fisk) is a major fictional Marvel Comics supervillain that originated in the Spider-Man comics and media. He has since then gone on to be a major enemy of Daredevil as well as a recurring villain for both Spider-Man and the Punisher. In recent years, he has been revised as being more of Daredevil's enemy rather than Spider-Man's and has appeared in more mature, realistic and adult-themed comic appearances. He is portrayed as one of the most feared and powerful crime lords in the Marvel Universe, typically holding the position of New York City's crime overlord.

Name: Kite Man (Post-Flashpoint)
Summary: Charles Brown was a simple aerodynamics engineer with a son, however, his past with working with the Joker caught up with him gravely during the War of Jokes and Riddles, where he was the "punchline" of the Riddler's attempt to make Joker laugh. Riddler tried to achieve this by killing his son so Charles would seek vengeance and in his grief become: Kite Man. Despite, knowingly knowing that everyone treats him like a joke, Charles's sheer resolve and determination ended up prevailing him over Riddler and his army, which turned out to be Nygma's ultimate goal.

Name: Kithlord Thieraven
Summary: Kithlord Thieraven was a Shadar-Kai Sorcerer and ally of Esvele Greycastle, a cleric of Shar. Thieraven was drawn to the dark goddess when an offer of sanctuary was made- while the curse of the Shadar Kai couldn't be dealt with, its effects could be mitigated if Thieraven assisted Esvele's other contact in tearing a whole in the Spellweave. So it was that Thieraven joined Ketsarra Shadowscale in the Vast Swamp and began preparations.

Name: Kled
Summary: A warrior as fearless as he is ornery, Kled is a popular folk hero in Noxus. Embodying the furious bravado of his nation, he is an icon beloved by the empire's soldiers, distrusted by its officers, and loathed by the nobility. Tall tales such as "The Great Hussar", "The High General Marshal Sergeant", and "The Mountain Admiral" trace back to the founding of the empire. Many soldiers claim Kled has fought in every campaign the legions have waged, has "acquired" every military title, and has never once backed down from a fight. Though the veracity of the details is often questionable, one part of his legend is undeniable: Charging into battle on his untrusty steed, Skaarl, Kled fights to protect what's his...and to take whatever he can get.

Name: Knell Beetle
Summary: Being an off shoot of giant beetles they're a mutated form of giant beetles due to magic and sonic energies, being mindless hunters who only seek to breed they make great use of their innate magical abilities and deadly claws in combat.

Name: Knife
Summary: A knife is a tool or weapon with an edge or blade, often attached to a handle or hilt. Knives are one of the first tools used by mankind, appearing at least 2.5 million years ago, as evidenced by the Oldowan tools.

Name: Kobold (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: Kobolds are the lowest evolutionary form of dragons, and worship Tiamat (and her lesser god vassal, Kurtulmak, in particular). The creatures are cowardly, conniving, and experts in teamwork. Due in large part to their physical frailty, kobolds are extremely easy prey for the larger creatures of the world. Thus, Kobolds tend to form massive warbands fitted with warriors, mages, and inventors to increase their likelihood of survival.

Name: Kodiak Bear
Summary: The Kodiak bear, also known as the Kodiak brown bear, sometimes the "Alaskan brown bear", inhabits the islands of the Kodiak Archipelago in southwest Alaska. It is the largest recognized subspecies or population of the brown bear, and one of the two largest bears alive today, the other being the polar bear.

Name: Komodo Dragon
Summary: Tier: 9-C, higher via piercing damage

Name: Koolasuchus
Summary: Koolasuchus is a large temnospondyl (Tetrapods that are possibly amphibians) that lived in Australia back when Australia was beneath the Antarctic Circle during the Cretaceous period 120 million years ago. It is also the last known temnospondyl unless it can be confirmed that modern amphibians are indeed related to temnospondyls. Koolasuchus presumably was 4-5 meters long and weighed nearly 500 kg.

Name: Korath the Pursuer (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Vers: Has a Skrull ever simmed you? Korath: Once. It was deeply disturbing. Vers: Why? Korath: Because I stared into the face of my mortal enemy and the face staring back was my own. Att-Lass: Maybe if you were more attractive, then it would be less disturbing. Korath: You think you’re funny. I’m not laughing. Att-Lass: You never laugh. Korath: I laugh, on the inside. I’m not doing it now.

Name: Korrina
Summary: Korrina is the Fighting-type gym leader of Shalour City and granddaughter of the Mega Evolution Guru.

Name: Kraken Priest
Summary: A Kraken Priest is a humanoid spellcaster devoted to serving a Kraken in exchange for power, with those who become priests likely having mistaken the kraken's fury as a sign of divine power, or are simply twisted enough to appraise the kraken in awe.

Name: Kraven the Hunter
Summary: Sergei Kravinoff was born the scion of disgraced russian nobility, forcefully driven out of their homeland following the revolution and sent looking for refuge in the US. After years of abuse at his father's hands and the trauma of witnessing his mother's slow descent into madness and subsequent death, Sergei grew utterly dissatisfied with modern society and left looking for the peace that only a primeval world could give him. For decades he roamed the worlds' wildest lands, hunting any beast imaginable and earning fame as the matchless Kraven the Hunter. A fateful meeting with Aja Orisha allowed Sergei to be initiated to the mystical arts and acquire supernatural skills, although at great expenses due to his troubled mind.

Name: Kraven the Hunter (Last Son)
Summary: nan

Name: Kree (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Gleen Talbot: You're telling me that we got our asses handed to us by little green men. Phil Coulson: They were big and blue.

Name: Kree (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Kree is an alien species originally from planet Hala, but conquered worlds all over their own galaxy becoming a giant empire. At some point they built the super computer Supreme Intelligence, which ended up becoming a ruler that they workship as a god. Kree give a great value to technology, which they have evolved leaps and bounds since their creation, because of constant wars with other races specially the Skrulls their military power increases the most. Power is also greatly valued among the race which meant making their military ranks based on individual power. At some point Kree reached a stagnation point in their evolution which the Supreme intelligence tried to fix by exploding a Nega-Bomb killing 90% of the Kree.

Name: Krenshar
Summary: Krenshars are large cat-like predators with extremely flexible flesh on its skull. While they otherwise mimic non-magical large predatory cat behavior, their unique trait of folding the skin on their head back to reveal the skull (an intimidation tactic) is documented as a fascinating evolutionary trait by sages.

Name: Krinth
Summary: Originally created from the forced union of demons and their slaves, the Krinth were originally an infertile race, however in the last 1,000 years they suddenly gained the ability to reproduce which lead to a rapid increase in their numbers. They are considered dour and humorless, and are also generally chaotic as a race. Their demonic heritage alongside familiarity with the shadow realm made them resistant to shadow magic and fear inducing effects.

Name: Kubanochoerus
Summary: Kubanochoerus is an extinct genus of large, long-legged suid. It lived in Africa, Europe, and Asia during the Miocene epoch, about 15.9 to 7.3 million years ago. The largest species, Kubanochoerus gigas, could reach notable sizes, standing about 1 meter at the shoulder and attaining masses of 500 kg.[1] Its most distinctive feature is the presence of horns on their skulls, with two small brow horns, and males possessing long horns on the top of their heads often likened to unicorn horns. It is thought the males used their horns for jousting in intraspecific combat. The adults would have likely inhabited open woodlands and savannas during its time.[2]

Name: Kukri (Real World)
Summary: The kukri, also known as the khukuri (Nepali: खुकुरी khukuri) is a knife, originating from the Indian subcontinent, associated with the Nepali speaking Gurkhas of Nepal. The knife has an inwardly curved blade, similar to a machete, used as both a tool and as a weapon in Nepal and India. Traditionally, it was, and in many cases still is, the basic utility knife of the Gurkha. It is a characteristic weapon of the Nepalese Army, the Royal Gurkha Rifles of the British Army, the Assam Rifles, the Assam Regiment, the Garhwal Rifles, the Gorkha regiments of the Indian Army, and of all Gurkha regiments throughout the world, so much so that some English-speakers refer to the weapon as a "Gurkha blade" or "Gurkha knife". The khukuri often appears in Nepalese and Indian Gorkha heraldry and is used in many traditional rituals such as wedding ceremonies. The kukri, khukri, and kukkri spellings are of Indian origin, the original Nepali form being khukuri.

Name: Kuo-Toa
Summary: Kuo-Toa are a species of fish-human hybrids that once dominated the surface world, ruling the islands and seas alike. However, they were driven away from their homes, deep into the Underdark, the evil world beneath the world.

Name: Kureto Hiragi
Summary: Kureto Hiragi is a lieutenant general in the Imperial Demon Army and the brother of Shinoa and Mahiru. He killed his father to become the head of the Hiragi family.

Name: Lady Bullseye (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Lady Bullseye was once a girl captured and being shipped overseas by slavers. However the operation was interrupted by Bullseye. When she saw Bullseye easily dispatch her captors, she became enamored with him, and when she was trained as an assassin, took up a guise similar to his. She first came into contact with Daredevil as an assassin of The Hand, but she was soon removed from The Hand and became a lieutenant of the Kingpin

Name: Lady Fiona Wachter
Summary: Lady Fiona Wachter is the leader of a cult of devil worshipers within Vallaki. She actively seeks to overcome the current Burgomaster, and seeks to manipulate any tools she might come into contact with to pursue this goal. Through illusory devil summoning and political planning, she aims to turn the town against the current Burgomaster, and place herself in charge, subservient to Strahd von Zarovich.

Name: Lamia (Merlin: BBC Series)
Summary: In their wars with the Ancient Kings, the High Priestesses of the Old Religion combined the blood of a girl with the blood of a serpent's, creating fearsome and powerful monsters who were able to kill with a single touch. The Lamia were extremely powerful, but proved to be more dangerous than their creators imagined: the High Priestesses lost control of them and the Lamia continued to kill, unwilling to stop.

Name: Lance (Pokémon)
Summary: Lance (ワタル Wataru) is a Dragon-type Trainer, a member of the Kanto Elite Four in Pokémon Red, Blue, Fire Red and Leaf Green. 3 years later, after Red and Blue left the Indigo Plateau, he became Pokémon Champion of Kanto in Gold, Silver, Crystal, HeartGold and SoulSilver. Later on, he participated in the Pokémon World Tournament in Black 2 and White 2.

Name: Langdedrosa Cyanwrath
Summary: Langdedrosa Cyanwrath is a champion of the Cult of the Dragon initially introduced as an invader of the town of Greenest. He is a warrior and acts as a defender of his master- Frulam Mondath. Together the two sacked the town, destroying its supplies, capturing its members, and killing its defenders. If allowed to live, Langdedrosa goes on to defend a sanctuary of Tiamat, and is killed in combat.

Name: Lantern Archon
Summary: Lantern Archons are simple celestial beings, gaseous orbs of light and the lowest orders of the Archons defending the Celestial realms. Often they are the converted souls of the Lawful Good mortals of the Prime Material. As newly converted souls, regardless of their intelligence in life, they are often simple creatures, merely the simple embodiment of goodness and order.

Name: Lascivious (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Davida DeVito was professional wrestler/mercenary under the alias Titania, being the member of all-female team known as the Grapplers. After a life of crime, she was killed by the Scourge of the Underworld.

Name: Latveria
Summary: The Kingdom of Latveria was once a small, isolated nation that was annexed from Hungary, but after it was conquered by Doctor Doom, who assumed the position of its absolute dictator, it became one of the world's greatest superpowers, solely because of his brilliance.

Name: Le Peregrine (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Alain Racine was a French writer who found a pair of wings, allowing him to soar the skies as Le Peregrine, France's most famous superhero.

Name: Leader Dynamics Series T2 MK5
Summary: The Leader T2 MK5 Series firearms were chambered for the 5.56×45mm NATO cartridge and manufactured by Leader Dynamics of Smithfield, NSW, Australia (1978-1982/1983). The Leader was the brainchild of British weapons designer Charles St. George. It was originally a contender for a 5.56 mm Australian military service rifle to replace the then-issued Lithgow L1A1 SLR and Colt M16A1 rifles. What was unique about this endeavor was that Australia had never designed or manufactured its own commercial gas-operated semi-automatic rifle. The rifle was abandoned when the Steyr AUG was adopted for use by the Australian military.

Name: Leaf
Summary: Leaf is the female protagonist of FireRed and LeafGreen, the remakes of the original games Red, Blue, Green, and Yellow, being the counterpart of Red. She is revamped in Let's Go Pikachu and Let's Go Eevee into Green, a young and quirky but quite powerful Pokémon Trainer on the search for Mewtwo to make him part of her team, and battles the player in retaliation for them beating her to it.

Name: Leapfrog (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Eugene Paul Patilio, Jr. AKA Leapfrog is a frog-themed vigilante. After attaining a custom-made superhero suit from Luke Jacobson, he started his attempt at crimefighting. However, his lack of skill and responsibility lead to him receiving injuries. He blamed Jacobson and attempted to sue him in court with Jennifer Walters as his attorney, only for Matt Murdock to easily defend his claims, as well as prove that Eugene was at fault for not following the suit's instructions. Frustrated with the verdict, Patilio kidnapped Jacobson and forced him to make him a new suit for his vigilante career.

Name: Leatherback Sea Turtle
Summary: The leatherback sea turtle (Dermochelys coriacea) is a critically endangered species of sea turtle native to oceans worldwide. They are the largest living turtle, the fastest living reptile, and the fourth largest living reptile, behind three crocodilian species.

Name: Leedsichthys
Summary: Leedsichthys problematicus ("leeds fish") was a giant fish of the Jurassic period. Its fossils were first found in England.

Name: Lenco Bearcat G2
Summary: The Lenco BearCat is a wheeled armored personnel carrier designed for military and law enforcement use. It is in use by several military forces and law enforcement agencies around the world.

Name: Leon (Pokémon)
Summary: Leon is the Champion of the Galar region's Pokémon League in Pokémon Sword and Shield. He is known far and wide for taking part in the Gym League Challenge at the tender age of 10 years old—and even more so for claiming victory in the Champion Cup on his first attempt.

Name: Leopard
Summary: The leopard is a big cat that lives in Africa, Asia, and the Caucasus. Unlike the other big cats that it lives with, the lion, and the cheetah, who rely on either using their strength to overpower animals and using their speed to chase animals respectively. The leopard relies on ambushing their prey from trees.

Name: Leopard (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: One of the many animals that roam the jungle, the Leopard is a big feline that jumps down from trees in order to hunt.

Name: Leopard Seal
Summary: Leopard seals are the third largest species of pinniped, behind the walrus and the elephant seal. Leopard seals are named after their spotted coat and are known to have eaten a wide range in prey, ranging from penguins to other seals. Leopard seals are 2.4-3.5 meters long and weigh around 200 to 600 kg.

Name: Leshy (Inscryption)
Summary: There never seems to be enough time to do the things you want to do...

Name: Leucrotta
Summary: An evil and repulsive creature, the Leucrotta enjoys to torment and kill any creature it thinks it can. They have a hybrid body of a stag and hyena alongside a head akin to a badger which has bodily fluids constantly ooze from its mouth.

Name: Lex Luthor (Post-Crisis)
Summary: Lex Luthor, since his first appearance, has been the most consistent adversary of Superman. His origins have varied somewhat, from the son of an abusive household to the childhood friend of a young Clark Kent, but upon reaching the city of Metropolis, he used his genius intellect and scientific knowledge to become a highly corrupt businessman, and eventually the head of his own corporation, secure in his position as one of the most powerful men in the world.

Name: Lex Luthor (Post-Flashpoint)
Summary: Lex Luthor appears as a representative the government has recruited to investigate and bring down Superman. Based on background signage seen throughout the New 52 books (including Justice League), LexCorp also exists. In Justice League No. 2, Batman notes that he and Superman have at least one thing in common: both of them speak openly of their distaste for Luthor. In the New 52 Action Comics (a series set some time before the events of Justice League #1), Luthor is hired by General Sam Lane to capture Superman by setting a train accident as a trap for him. The younger Superman, who is weaker and inexperienced, barely stops the train and is left unconscious. Lex collects Superman and subjects him to a series of tests to ascertain his strengths and weaknesses. He tortures Superman until the latter manages to escape. Lex is later revealed to have obtained contact with the "Collector of Worlds" through unknown means and was told to say the word "Krypton" to Superman. He later appears when the Collector abducts New Troy as one of the residents in the area. He along with Lois and Jimmy go into Glen Glenmorgan's hotel where Lex calls the Collector and it is revealed that Lex had made a deal with him. It is later revealed that Lex Luthor was the secret caller named "Icarus" that was giving secret information on Glen Glenmorgan to Clark Kent.

Name: Liger
Summary: The Liger is the result of a Male lion mating with a female tiger. It is notable for being the largest big cat in the world even surpassing Lions and Tigers.

Name: Lila Cheney
Summary: Young Lila Cheney discovered her mutant powers at a young age, exploring the stars galaxies afar. Over the years fashioning herself as an informal ambassador to Earth, she became an intergalactic punk rocker, while also being a kleptomaniac gave her a separate reputation as one of the most notorious thieves in all of the universe, residing in an abandoned Dyson sphere which she calls her home base.

Name: Lillend
Summary: Lillends were feminine celestials native to Ysgard, but present in many other domains including Limbo and Arborea. Oftentimes they directly served the gods, notably including the likes of Selune, Corellon Larethian, Labelas Enoreth, and many other elvish deities. Rarely would a lillend don clothing as it was an alien concept to their celestial natures. They were great lovers of decadence and luxury, and even were afforded the ultimate luxury from the gods- a lillend could choose the hour in which they die.

Name: Lillie (Pokémon)
Summary: Lillie is one of the main protagonists of Pokémon Sun and Moon. Elio or Seline encounters her by a bridge as Nebby, her Cosmog, is being attacked by Spearow. Sun or Moon goes in an effort to save the Cosmog as the bridge breaks and Sharpedo are under them. Luckily, he is saved by Tapu Koko. Admiring Elio or Seline's bravery, she travels a companion to the protagonist and helps to evolve Cosmog into either Solgaleo or Lunala with the trainer.

Name: Lineage (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Gordo Nobili was head of what was left of the once respected Nobili Crime Family. Along with his two sons Carmen Nobili and Joey Nobili, they were a down on their luck mob family whose credibility was tarnished, as all their attempts ended up in failings. As the Terrigen Bomb was set off by Black Bolt, the Nobili went through a transformation into newly manifested Inhumans, and Gordon lost his sons soon after, owing to the trio's frightening new appearances.

Name: Lion (Real World)
Summary: The Lion is a famous big cat native to Asia and Africa. It is likely one of the most recognizable animals to humans. On their own, they hunt zebras, impalas, and wildebeest, on packs they have shown to hunt buffaloes (Males have been shown to do this on their own with extreme effort), hippopotamuses and rhinos. They mostly hunt in packs due to most of their prey being larger and heavier than them. They used to live all around Africa and in some parts of the Middle East, some lions even managed to reach Europe thousands of years ago. They currently live in the center and south of Africa. The Asiatic Lion can be found in the Gir forest in India.

Name: Liopleurodon (The Real World)
Summary: The Liopleurodon is a marine reptile belonging to a clade of short-necked pliosaur plesiosaurs. It was popularized by the Walking With... series and later the Charlie the Unicorn series. In the Walking With series, it was claimed to be 25 meters (82 feet) long and weighing in at 150 tonnes. However, these measurements were based on very fragmentary remains and later measurements concluded it to be a more conservative 4.8 to 5.7 meters (16 to 19 feet) and weighing in at 1 to 1.7 tonnes, with the largest specimen measuring at 6.6 meters long (22 feet) and weighing in at 3.3 tonnes.

Name: Lisowicia
Summary: Lisowicia is a genus of dicynodont that lived 210-205 million years ago in the Late Triassic, named for the place of its discovery: Lisowice, a village in Poland. Among its most outstanding traits was its size; it was not only the largest dicynodont, but also the largest non-mammalian synapsid to have lived, rivalling the size of modern African Elephants.[1] In the place Lisowycia was discovered, there were no plateosaurid sauropodomorphs, which may explain why it could have reached comparable sizes; it could also have been also to support a larger gut for metabolic demands, among other possible causes.[2][3] Another trait that set it apart from other dicynodonts was that it had an erect gait, as opposed to a sprawling gait.[1] It inhabited a swampy wetland environment that was present in Poland during its time, and was the only large herbivore in its habitat.[3]

Name: Livyatan (Real World)
Summary: Livyatan melvillei, Livyatan, or sometimes called Leviathan, is a prehistoric sperm whale which lived approximately 13 million years ago during the Miocene Period.

Name: Lizardfolk
Summary: Lizardfolk are reptilian humanoids native to the world of Toril that tend to dwell in semi-aquatic environments (such as swamplands and coastlines). An exceedingly practical folk, they do not desire riches or knowledge that don't have use in normal day-to-day survival activities. Their people are hardy, and can adapt to most environments- so despite being dominated culturally by the likes of humans, dwarves, and elves, they rarely hold complaint for the lands leftover for their dominions.

Name: Llama
Summary: Llamas are very social animals and live with other members of their species as a herd. The wool produced by a llama is very soft and lanolin-free. Llamas are intelligent and can learn simple tasks after a few repetitions. When using a pack, they can carry about 25 to 30% of their body weight for 8 to 13 km (5–8 miles).

Name: LoaderLiomon
Summary: Tier: 9-B, occasionally High 8-C with Shippo Binta | High 8-C, occasionally 6-C with Critical Bite | At least 4-C, Possibly 3-C | At least 4-C, Possibly 3-C

Name: Locathah
Summary: One of D&D's aquatic races, the Locathah is a playable race of fish people. They are resilient, adept in using weapons, and possess natural athleticism alongside sharp senses. However they are bound to water, being only able to be above ground for 4 hours before needing to be covered in water as to not suffocate to death.

Name: Logan Walker
Summary: Sergeant Logan Walker is the youngest member of the Ghosts and the only one that does not speak. During the events of Ghosts stories, he's 16 years old. He is then 25 years old during the events of the other missions. Him and the other Ghosts are sent to find and capture Gabriel Rorke. At the end of the mission The Ghost Killer, he is captured by Rorke and is sent to an unknown location where he suffers the same torture Rorke had endured.

Name: Long rifle
Summary: The long rifle, also known as longrifle, Kentucky rifle, Pennsylvania rifle, or American longrifle, was one of the first commonly used rifles for hunting and warfare. It is characterized by an unusually long barrel, a development in American rifles that was uncommon in European rifles of the same period.

Name: Long Sky (Hero)
Summary: Long Sky was an accomplished spearman that was told to be one of the three assassins to murder the King of the Qin dynasty during the Warring States Period before he could name himself emperor. He is played by Donnie Yen in the movie "Hero".

Name: Loop
Summary: This profile contains major spoilers for In Stars And Time and START AGAIN: a prologue. It is highly suggested that you complete In Stars and Time before reading this profile.

Name: Lorelei
Summary: Lorelei is the ice user of the Elite Four, and is the first Elite Four member ever met. She is known for her cool and calculated tactics. She is from Four Island on the Sevii Islands, and has a deep affinity to the Icefall Cave there, as that is where she first got her Lapras when she was a child.

Name: Lt. Surge
Summary: Lt. Surge "The Lightning American" is the leader of the Vermillion Gym and mainly uses Electric-type Pokémon. He is the third Gym Leader Red and Blue encounter in their adventures through Kanto. Characterized by his bold and brash composure, Lt. Surge is a war vet who served in the mysterious "Kanto War" of some years ago.
