Name: Luke Cage (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Luke Cage (real name Carl Lucas) is a former policeman from Savannah, Georgia, who was wrongfully convicted into Seagate Prison, where he met and fell in love with therapist Reva Connors. During his time in prison, he underwent an experiment to save his life that ended up giving him superhuman strength and a seemingly unbreakable skin. After he escaped from his prison, he changed his name and moved to New York City, marrying Connors and living there until her death seemingly due to a random bus crash.

Name: Lulu (League of Legends)
Summary: The yordle mage Lulu is known for conjuring dreamlike illusions and fanciful creatures as she roams Runeterra with her fairy companion Pix. Lulu shapes reality on a whim, warping the fabric of the world, and what she views as the constraints of this mundane, physical realm. While others might consider her magic at best unnatural, and at worst dangerous, she believes everyone could use a touch of enchantment.

Name: Luo-Lang (Sword of the Stranger)
Summary: Luo-Lang (羅狼?)The blonde-haired, blue-eyed, European second-in-command of the Ming group and an extremely skilled swordsman. Luo-Lang is driven by a thirst for great power and craves finding an equally strong opponent to fight so that he may improve his skills.

Name: Lurker
Summary: Appearing like giant mantarays this monsters have a black back and an underside that looks like stone which aids them to hide in tops of caves where they stay still until a prey passes them by, and when it does they lung at themslves at the target, wrapping around them and crushing them to death.

Name: Lusamine
Key: '''By Herself''' | '''Pokémon Team''' | '''Merged Lusamine''' | '''Pokémon Team (Post-Merge Lusamine)''' | '''Pokémon Team (Title Defense)'''
Summary: Lusamine is the current president of the Aether Foundation, an organization created to shelter Pokémon from villainous organizations like Team Skull and nurse these Pokémon back to health to be returned to the wild. She is the insane and corrupt president of the Aether Foundation, who not only abuses her own children and has performed various gruesome experiments on the very Pokemon she's supposed to take care of and protect but also plans to go to Ultra Space to reach the Ultra Beasts, even if it means unleashing their fury on the Alola region.

Name: Lynx (Real World)
Summary: A lynx is any of the four existing species (the Canada lynx, Iberian lynx, Eurasian lynx, or bobcat) within the medium-sized wild cat genus Lynx. The lynx is usually solitary, although a small group of lynx may travel and hunt together occasionally. Mating takes place in the late winter and once a year the female gives birth to between one and four kittens.

Name: Lysandre
Summary: Lysandre (Japanese: フラダリ Fuladari) is the leader of Team Flare and the main antagonist of Pokémon X and Y. Formerly the student of Professor Sycamore, he later went on to found Lysandre Labs and create the Holo Caster. At some point in the future, Lysandre was convinced of humanity's stupidity and became misanthropic, generating his desire to wipe the world of all humans and Pokémon not affiliated with Team Flare through the use of his ancestor's Ultimate Weapon. However, thanks to the efforts of Calem/Serena, he is stopped right before the weapon’s activation, but even after their attempts to convince him that the world is not as bad as he thinks, Lysandre rejects the idea and tries to kill them by detonating the Ultimate Weapon with what little power remains in it. While Calem/Serena escape the explosion, Lysandre is presumed dead and Team Flare disbands.

Name: Lystrosaurus
Summary: Lystrosaurus is an extinct genus of therapsid, a group of ancient reptiles that includes some of the closest relatives to mammals. Lystrosaurus lived during the Permian and early Triassic periods, approximately 255 to 250 million years ago. It was a herbivorous animal with a beak-like snout and a robust body. Lystrosaurus is notable for its resilience and ability to survive the Permian-Triassic mass extinction event, which wiped out many other species. Its fossils have been found on various continents, and it is often considered an example of a "disaster taxon" that rebounded after a major extinction event, helping to repopulate the Earth with life.

Name: M'Baku (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: M'Baku is the leader of the Jabari Tribe and a staunch opponent of T'Challa's rule who ends up torn between challenging him for the throne only to help him defend the Wakanda from Erik Killmonger.

Name: M.O.D.O.K.
Summary: The Advanced Idea Mechanics technician George Tarleton was selected as the victim of a cruel experiment aimed at creating a living computer of unprecedented might. However, instead of becoming the subservient tool his creators craved for, the newly-born M.O.D.O.K. rebelled and imposed himself as the new head of the organization. As twisted in the body as in the mind, he committed himself to further A.I.M.'s ideals according to his personal ambitions.

Name: M.O.D.O.K. Superior
Summary: M.O.D.O.K. Superior is the result of a failsafe program carried out by the original M.O.D.O.K. to ensure the continuation of his legacy in the eventuality of his downfall against the coalition of the Hulks. He is one of many cloned brains, but unlike the others he has been allowed to retain his free will. Upon surfacing as the new M.O.D.O.K., he vowed to not follow the faulty tracks of his predecessor and live his life free of any artificial conditioning, a trait most exemplified in his much more human and varied characterization.

Name: M1 Abrams
Summary: The M1 Abrams is a third-generation main battle tank designed by General Dynamics Land Systems (formerly Chrysler Defense) and named after General Creighton Abrams. Conceived for modern armored ground warfare, it introduced several innovative features, including a multifuel turbine engine, advanced composite armor, a computer fire control system, separate ammunition storage in a blow-out compartment, and NBC protection.

Name: M1 Garand
Summary: The M1 Garand is a .30 caliber semi-automatic rifle that was the standard U.S. service rifle during World War II and the Korean War and also saw limited service during the Vietnam War. Most M1 rifles were issued to U.S. forces, though many hundreds of thousands were also provided as foreign aid to American allies. The Garand is still used by drill teams and military honor guards. It is also widely used by civilians for hunting, target shooting, and as a military collectible.

Name: M134 Minigun
Summary: The M134 Minigun is a 7.62mm six-barreled machine gun with a high firing rate (2,000 to 6,000 shots per minute) employing rotating Gatling-style drums with an external power supply. In popular culture, the term "Minigun" has been applied to any Gatling weapon using rifle gauge and receiving power externally, although the term is sometimes used to refer to firearm cadence and similar configurations, disregarding the power source and caliber. Specifically, minigun refers to a specific weapon model, originally produced by General Electric.

Name: M14 Rifle
Summary: The M14 rifle, officially the United States Rifle, Caliber 7.62 mm, M14, is an American select-fire rifle that fires 7.62×51mm NATO (.308 in) ammunition. It became the standard-issued rifle for the U.S. military in 1959, replacing the M1 Garand rifle in the U.S. Army by 1961 and the U.S. Marine Corps by 1965 until being replaced by the M16 rifle beginning in 1964. The M14 was used by U.S. Army, Navy, and Marine Corps for basic and advanced individual training (AIT) from the mid-1960s to the early 1970s.

Name: M1911
Summary: The M1911, also known as the Colt 1911 or the Colt Government, is a single-action, recoil-operated semi-automatic pistol chambered for the .45 ACP cartridge. The pistol's formal U.S. military designation as of 1940 was Automatic Pistol, Caliber .45, M1911 for the original model adopted in March 1911, and Automatic Pistol, Caliber .45, M1911A1 for the improved M1911A1 model which entered service in 1926. The designation changed to Pistol, Caliber .45, Automatic, M1911A1 in the Vietnam War era.

Name: M4 Carbine
Summary: The M4 carbine is a shorter and lighter variant of the M16A2 assault rifle. The M4 is a 5.56×45mm NATO, air-cooled, direct impingement gas-operated, magazine-fed carbine. It has a 14.5 in (370 mm) barrel and a telescoping stock.

Name: M4 Sherman
Summary: The M4 Sherman, officially “Medium Tank, M4” and named by the British for the American Civil War General William Tecumseh Sherman, was the most widely used medium tank by the United States and Western Allies in World War II. It is one of the few really iconic fighting vehicles of the Allies during World War Two. The M4 Sherman proved to be reliable, relatively cheap to produce, and available in great numbers. Thousands were distributed through the Lend-Lease program to the British Commonwealth and Soviet Union.

Name: M60 machine gun
Summary: The M60, officially the United States Machine Gun, Caliber 7.62 mm, M60, is a family of American general-purpose machine guns firing 7.62×51mm NATO cartridges from a disintegrating belt of M13 links. There are several types of ammunition approved for use in the M60, including ball, tracer, and armor-piercing rounds.

Name: M61 Vulcan
Summary: The 20mm/99 M61 Vulcan hydraulically/pneumatically-driven, electrically-fired, air-cooled, 20mm six-barrelled rotary cannon fires at an extremely high rate of between 4000 to 6000 rounds per minute. The Vulcan has been the main cannon armament of United States military combat aircraft for over fifty years. The several aircraft at the time were originally designed without an internal cannon, as it was believed that missiles had made guns obsolete; however, air-to-air combat experience in Vietnam showed that a gun could still be more effective than guided missiles in many combat situations, and that an externally carried gun pod was less effective than an internal gun, so the M61A1 Vulcan became standard as of the F-4E Phantom II. The initial M61 used linked, belted ammunition, but the ejection of spent links created considerable problems, and was soon replaced by the improved M61A1 with a linkless feed system. A lighter version of the Vulcan, the M61A2, was developed for use on the F-22 Raptor, which is mechanically the same as the M61A1 but with thinner barrels to reduce overall weight to 93 kilograms (202 pounds), allowing it to reach a slightly higher maximum rate of fire at 6600 rounds per minute. In addition to being mounted on the majority of combat aircraft, there also exist two land-based applications: the M163 Vulcan Air Defense System self-propelled anti-aircraft gun and the M167 Vulcan Air Defense System towed anti-aircraft gun.

Name: M67 Fragmentation Grenade
Summary: The M67 Fragmentation Grenade is a handheld explosive used by the United States military. The M67 is a further development of the M33 grenade, itself a replacement for the M26-series grenades used during the Korean and Vietnam Wars, and the older Mk 2 "pineapple" grenade used since World War II. The M67 hand grenade has an effective casualty radius of about 15 meters. It is considered a "defensive fragmentation grenade" because it must be used from the safety of cover, since the range of its fragments is greater than a human can throw the grenade.

Name: M72 LAW
Summary: The M72 LAW (light anti-tank weapon, also referred to as the light anti-armor weapon or LAW as well as LAWS: light anti-armor weapons system) is a portable one-shot 66 mm (2.6 in) unguided anti-tank weapon. Production of the weapon started in the year 1963 by Hesse-Eastern; however, the company's production of the weapon was terminated in 1983. Currently it is produced by Nammo Raufoss AS in Norway and their subsidiary, Nammo Talley, Inc. in Arizona

Name: MAC-10
Summary: The Military Armament Corporation Model 10, officially abbreviated as "M10" or "M-10", and more commonly known as the MAC-10, is a compact, blowback operated machine pistol/submachine gun that was developed by Gordon Ingram in 1964. It is chambered in either .45 ACP or 9mm. A two-stage suppressor by Sionics was designed for the MAC-10, which not only abates the noise created but makes it easier to control on full automatic (although it also makes the gun far less compact and concealable).

Name: Machete
Summary: A machete is a blade used as a substitute of an axe.

Name: Machinesmith (Marvel Comics)
Summary: At the age of fourteen, Samuel Saxon discovered one of Doctor Doom's robots abandoned in a subway tunnel, and took it piece by piece to his father's garage, where for months he studied its components until mastering its operating principles and building his own robot from scratch. His obsession with robots grew as he amassed an army of droids at his service, that he used for his crimes, only to entangle with Daredevil, outsmarting him vastly in their first encounter.

Name: Madame Masque (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Giuletta Nefaria's mother had died in childbirth. Her father, Count Luchino Nefaria had her sent to the Frost family in order to give her a 'good life', and partially because he had preferred a male heir instead. In their care she was given the identity Whitney Frost.

Name: Madcap (Marvel Comics)
Summary: A deeply religious young man was on the way to a picnic with his family and church community, their bus collides with a tanker truck full of Compound X07 (an experimental nerve agent developed by A.I.M.). Everyone aboard the bus, including his parents and sister Katy, are killed, leaving him as the only survivor, his body mixing with the Compound. When being told of the deaths of all his friends and family, his mind shatters, his belief in a rational universe swept away.

Name: Magma Mephit
Summary: Befitting their name, the Magma Mephit are made from lava, with them using their natural body heat in combat.

Name: Magmin
Summary: Magmin are small fiery elementals that are often summoned by cults of elemental flame. The sole reason these creatures do not explode into fire the second they enter the Material Plane is due to their magma shells which contain their flame. They are chaotic pyromaniacs, who view all that is flammable as kindling for a grand flame to be birthed from. Despite this they are not actively evil, and instead simply do not understand the threat their flames pose to mortals.

Name: Magneto (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Max Eisenhardt, better known as Magneto, is one of the most powerful mutants in the world and a recurring foe of the X-Men. After suffering from multiple tragedies throughout his life, he became determined to end humanity's oppression of mutants by upending the human-led governments of the world.

Name: Magnum Research BFR
Summary: The Magnum Research BFR is a single-action revolver manufactured by Magnum Research. It is made from stainless steel and is manufactured in a variety of heavy calibers, such as .500 S&W Magnum, including some traditional rifle cartridges, such as the .30-30 and .45-70/.450 Marlin. The name "BFR" officially is an acronym for "Big Frame Revolver", although other meanings, such as "Big Finest Revolver", or "Biggest, Finest Revolver," and even in some cases, "Big Fucking Revolver" have also been used.

Name: Mahi-Mahi
Summary: The mahi-mahi (Coryphaena hippurus), also known as the common dolphinfish, is a medium-sized fish native to tropical and subtropical waters worldwide. They are highly sought after by fishermen, both as sport fish and for food.

Name: Maip macrothorax
Summary: Maip macrothorax is a species of large megaraptorid theropod dinosaur, and possibly the largest of this group of theropods.[1] Its name is derived from "Maip," a malevolent entity in Aonikenk mythology, and "macrothorax," which is Greek for "large chest," for its large thoracic cavity.[1] It lived in South America during the Late Cretaceous.

Name: Makarov Pistol
Summary: The Makarov pistol or PM (Russian: Пистолет Макарова, Pistolet Makarova, literally Makarov's Pistol) is a Russian semi-automatic pistol. Under the project leadership of Nikolay Fyodorovich Makarov, it became the Soviet Union's standard military and police side arm in 1951, and still sees widespread use in modern-day Russia.

Name: Mammoth (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: An ancient ancestor of the modern day elephant , the Mammoth is massive herbivore from the ice age. Mammoths live in cold plains in in big herds, where their general size makes so besides humanoids nobody bothers trying to hunt them.

Name: Mandarin (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Xu Wenwu (Chinese: 文武), better known as The Mandarin, is a major antagonist in the Marvel Cinematic Universe, mostly serving as the unseen overarching antagonist of the Iron Man trilogy and the Marvel one-shot All Hail The King, and the main antagonist of Shang-Chi and the Legend of the Ten Rings.

Name: Mandarin (Marvel Comics)
Summary: The Mandarin was born the child of Mongolian and British aristocrats, both of whom died shortly after his birth. He was raised by his aunt, who was bitter about not being the inheritor of the family fortune and decided to twist his mind, raising him to be vain and bloodthirsty.

Name: Mandrill
Summary: The Mandrill (Mandrillus sphinx) is a primate and the world's largest monkeys. Mandrills mostly live in tropical rainforest and in very large groups and have an omnivorous diet consisting mostly of fruits and insects.

Name: Maned Wolf
Summary: The maned wolf (Chrysocyon brachyurus) is a large canine of South America. The maned wolf, known locally as Lobo Guará, is found in Argentina, Brazil, Bolivia, Peru, Paraguay and is almost extinct in Uruguay. Its markings resemble those of foxes, but it is neither a fox nor a wolf.[1]

Name: Manjimutt
Summary: Manjimutt is a E rank Yo-Kai of the Eerie tribe. Depicted in the anime to have once been a human salary worker who lose his job and got himself killed while in a drunken stupor, he is one of the only few Yo-Kai that can be seen without the Yo-Kai Watch which in turn gets him in trouble with the police.

Name: Manticore (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: Manticores were savage, man-eating magical beasts not dissimilar from the likes of Griffons and Chimeras, in that it was primarily a combination of three other creatures- a lion, a dragon, and a human. Its tail was from some unknown creature or possibly none at all, though it was an extremely deadly tool as it could rapidly fire out spikes as large as a sword.

Name: Mantis (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Drax: You are horrifying to look at. But that's a good thing. Mantis: Oh? Drax: When you're ugly and someone loves you, you know they love you for who you are. Beautiful people never know how to trust. Mantis: Well, then I am certainly grateful to be ugly!

Name: Marduk Kurios
Summary: Satan, true name Marduk Kurios, though he has gone by many others, is a powerful demon who rules over the underworld as one of the Lords of Hell. While it is unknown whether he truly is the angel cast down from Heaven by God long ago or just the most powerful of the many pretenders to that name, what is certain is that Satan has often attempted to gather more power and conquer the entirety of both Hell and Earth, sometimes seeing his attempts foiled by his two half-human children, Daimon and Satana Hellstrom.

Name: Maria Hill (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Maria Hill is the former second in command of S.H.I.E.L.D. She's highly skilled and capable of combat, often being one of the first to notice and/or react to large distasters. She is known for aiding the Avengers behind the scenes.

Name: Marnie (Pokémon)
Key: '''By Herself''' | '''Pokèmon Team (First battle)''' | '''Pokèmon Team (Second battle)''' | '''Pokèmon Team (Third battle)''' | '''Pokèmon Team (Fourth battle/Champion tournament)'''
Summary: Marnie (Japanese: マリィ Mary) is one of the rival characters in Pokémon Sword and Shield, the others being Hop and Bede, and specializes in Dark-type Pokémon. She eventually replaces her older brother Piers as the Gym Leader of her hometown Spikemuth. As the Spikemuth Gym Leader, she gives the Dark Badge to Trainers who defeat her.

Name: Mastiff (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: A big and powerful dog breed, the Mastiff is prized by humanoid races for their keen senses and great loyalty. They can be trained for a variety of tasks, and smaller races such as Halflings use them as mounts.

Name: Mastodonsaurus
Summary: Mastodonsaurus (meaning "teat tooth lizard") is an extinct genus of temnospondyl from the Middle Triassic of Europe.

Name: Mauser C96
Summary: The Mauser C96 (Construktion 96) is a semi-automatic pistol that was originally produced by German arms manufacturer Mauser from 1896 to 1937. Unlicensed copies of the gun were also manufactured in Spain and China in the first half of the 20th century.

Name: Maxie (Pokémon)
Key: '''By Himself''' | '''Pokémon Team (Mt. Chimney)''' | '''Pokémon Team (Seafloor Cavern)''' | '''Pokémon Team (Battle Maison)''' | '''Pokémon (Team Gen 7)'''
Summary: Maxie is the boss of Team Magma. The player battles him in the Mossdeep Space Center in Emerald and Mt. Chimney and Seafloor Cavern in Ruby. In Sapphire, he is an ally to the player on his/her mission to stop Team Aqua from expanding the sea and in Ruby, he is the main villain of the game.

Name: Maylene
Summary: Maylene is the Veilstone City Gym Leader in Pokémon Diamond, Pearl, and Platinum, and is the fourth Gym Leader that a Trainer in the Sinnoh region must battle in order to challenge the Elite Four. Maylene constantly chases perfection alongside her Fighting-type Pokémon, and her training has made her one of the greatest martial artists and Pokémon trainers in the Sinnoh region. She doesn't remember how, but somewhere along the line she became the Gym Leader for her hometown, earning countless other martial artists as her Gym trainers that she was suddenly in charge of. Undeterred, she continues training, using her challengers as opportunities to locate her own weak points and meet new people.

Name: McMillan TAC-50
Summary: The McMillan TAC-50 is a long-range anti-materiel sniper rifle, based on designs from the same company, which first appeared during the late 1980s. From May 2017 to November 2023, it held the record for the longest ever sniper kill. McMillan makes several .50 caliber rifles, based on the same proprietary action, for military, law enforcement and civilian use. It is produced in Phoenix, Arizona, in the United States by McMillan Firearms Manufacturing.

Name: Me 262 Schwalbe
Summary: The Me 262, nicknamed "Schwalbe" (Swallow), is a twin engine turbojet fighter and the world's first operational jet fighter aircraft. The aircraft made its very first flight on April 18, 1941 with piston engines, making it's maiden flight with jet engines on July 18, one year later. However, it's entrance into Luftwaffe service into the war would be delayed, only being introduced into service in April 1944.

Name: Medusa (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: Medusas are creations of powerful Demon Lords or Archdevils, mortals who begged to become beautiful, to become loved. In return, after years of status and acting as a demigod among mortals, they are reduced to medusas, horrifying to behold. They live forever, secluded, turning any who might see them to stone.

Name: Meepo
Summary: Meepo the Dragon-Keeper was once the lowliest of kobolds, weak even for their lowly kind. As such, he was assigned by his then-master, Yusdrayl, to tend to the dragon their tribe had captured, who went by the name of Calcryx; this essentially meant Meepo was assigned to clean the dragon's feces. However, when the dragon was captured by the goblins who also lived in the same dungeon space (dubbed the Sunless Citadel), Meepo's reputation amongst his kin plummeted even lower, and he was destitute, until a party of adventurers arrived and assisted Meepo's tribe in re-capturing the dragon. This state of affairs lasted only briefly before the adventurers ultimately slew the dragon, killing all of Meepo's tribe as a consequence: only Meepo escaped.

Name: Megacerops
Summary: Megacerops ("Big horned face") is a genus of large, rhinoceros-like perissodactyl that belongs to a unique family Brontotheriidae, which is related to horses. Their most distinctive feature is the large, blunt horn-like protrusion on their snout that takes on a forked "Y" shape. The "horns" in males were large as a form of sexual dimorphism, indicating social behavior such as intraspecific conflict.[1] This creature lived in North America 38–33.9 million years ago during the Late Eocene, and was adapted to a browsing lifestyle feeding on soft tree material.

Name: Megalania
Summary: Megalania is a giant monitor lizard that is believed to be the largest terrestrial lizard known to have existed. It is believed that a modern relative, the Komodo Dragon, evolved in Australia before having been displaced in Indonesia. Megalania is believed to be an apex predator back in Pleistocene-era Australia around 1.5 million to 40,000 years ago, although there is skepticism towards the claim. The Megalania ranged in length from 3.5 to 7 meters long. It had an estimated maximum weight of 1940 kg, although 320 kg seems to be the average weight of these creatures.[1]

Name: Megaloceros (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: The Megaloceros which is also known as the Irish Deer is a prehistoric variant of the deer which lived in cold marshes. This animal's antlers could grow up to 10 feet in length and they used said antlers to impale who ever they fought, and while most of the years they're not aggressive during mating season they can be quite dangerous.

Name: Megalodon
Summary: Megalodon was a species of giant shark that lived around the world from the late Oligocene to the early Pleistocene periods. The exact classification of Megalodon has been disputed for decades, mostly concerning whether it should be placed in the species Carcharodon megalodon (thus classifying it as a relative of the great white shark) or the species Carcharocles megalodon. As this debate is still unresolved, the creature's full name is currently referred to as Otadus megalodon. Whatever its classification, it was one of the largest and most powerful predatory fish ever to live.

Name: Megasaurus
Summary: Megasaurus is a giant fire breathing, car crushing dinosaur robot modeled after a Tyrannosaurus rex (Real World), with hydraulically activated arms, grasping claws, and jaws, as well as flame throwers set up in the head to give the effect of breathing fire from the mouth. It performs across the United States at Monster Jam Truck Shows and other events. Another, almost exact version exists, known as Transaurus.

Name: Megatherium (Real World)
Summary: Megatherium americanum, otherwise known as the giant ground sloth, was the largest known ground sloth. It was a primarily herbivorous creature, feeding on leaves such as yuccas, agaves, and grasses.

Name: Meramon
Summary: Tier: 9-B | High 8-C | 6-C | At least 6-C | At least 4-C, Possibly Low 1-C

Name: Merfolk (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: Merfolk are humanoid creatures bound to the sea and were half-human, half-fish, created in such a manner by the god Eadro (also known as the Deliverer, the Bather of Gills, and the Lord of the Sunlit Shallows). Aesthetically, they bore more similarities with fey-like creatures such as elves or eladrin than with humans. As with most humanoids they are neutral and can choose their own alignments based on taste. The primary historical threats to their people are merrow (murderous aquatic humanoids), and the consistent Seros wars, terrible conflicts that often decimate the entirety of their population.

Name: Merrow
Summary: Merrow are abyssal aquatic creatures created from fiendishly altered Merfolk. They are spawns of Demogorgon, and serve him as underwater bullies intent on murdering other more wholesome sea-life for the pure sake of chaos. The territory of merrow can generally be identified by their habit of tying corpses to kelp at the boundaries of their underwater dominions. Originally, the merrow were created when a tribe of merfolk opened a portal into the Abyss after a blood sacrifice. Over several generations they transformed into the insane abominations they are now.

Name: Messerschmitt Bf 109
Summary: The Messerschmitt Bf 109 G-6/R3 is a single-engined, single-seat monoplane fighter and a German World War II fighter aircraft that was the backbone of the Luftwaffe's fighter force. The Bf 109 first saw operational service in 1937 during the Spanish Civil War and was still in service at the dawn of the jet age at the end of World War II in 1945. It was one of the most advanced fighters of the era, including such features as all-metal monocoque construction, a closed canopy, and retractable landing gear. It was powered by a liquid-cooled, inverted-V12 aero engine. From the end of 1941, the Bf 109 was steadily being supplemented by the Focke-Wulf Fw 190. It was commonly called the Me 109, most often by Allied aircrew and among the German aces, even though this was not the official German designation.

Name: MetalGarurumon
Summary: Tier: Unknown | 9-B | High 8-C | At least High 8-C | High 7-A | 6-C | At least 6-C | At least High 6-C | At least High 6-C | 5-B | At least 5-B

Name: Mezzoloth
Summary: Mezzoloths serve as the foot soldiers of the Yugoloth armies and thus make up the brunt of their society. Mezzoloths swarm the planar battlefields by the million, hordes of insectoid soldiers goaded forward by their superiors- be they yagnaloths, nycaloths, or ultroloths, the fate remains the same for mezzoloths.

Name: Midnight Sun (Marvel Comics)
Summary: As a child, M'Nai was the lone survivor of a British attack on a village of Fu Manchu's agents. Fu Manchu saw the hatred in the boy's eyes and decided to raise him alongside his own son Shang-Chi, who became M'Nai's best friend. After Shang-Chi broke with his father, Fu Manchu sent M'Nai, now called Midnight, to locate him. They fought a duel which ended with M'Nai breaking his neck after falling off a construction crane.

Name: Mikoyan-Gurevich MiG-21
Summary: The Mikoyan-Gurevich MiG-21 (Russian: Микоян и Гуревич МиГ-21; NATO reporting name: Fishbed) is a supersonic jet fighter and interceptor aircraft, designed by the Mikoyan-Gurevich Design Bureau in the Soviet Union.

Name: Mil Mi-24
Summary: The Mil Mi-24 is a multipurpose helicopter gunship, which doubles as a low capacity troop transport capable of carrying 8 passengers. It is developed by the Mil Moscow Helicopter Plant of the USSR, making it's first flight on September 19, 1969, entering service for the Red Army in 1972. Since then it has been operated by over 30 other nations.

Name: Milotic
Summary: Feebas is a shabby, old-looking fish-like Pokémon. It has large, hollow eyes, large spots covering its body, dull pink lips and a deprived look. Due to its ugly appearance, it is largely ignored by predators, Trainers, and researchers alike. Despite this however, Feebas has the unique trait of being able to survive in any water, no matter how polluted, making it quite hardy.

Name: Mimic (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: Mimics are shapechanging monstrosities typically found in dungeons, posing as lost treasure to lure in unwary creatures for consumption. While they can theoretically become anything of an appropriate size, they are most often depicted as taking the form of chests, imitating a treasure hoard while they await their prey. Rare breeds of mimics can even become humanoid in form, leading to a much more mobile lifestyle. Other variants of mimics exist as well, including "Killer" mimics, which are more lethal than their brethren.

Name: Mind Flayer (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: Mind Flayers are horrific, eldritch creatures associated with the dark depths of the D&D settings. They are renowned for being horrendously evil and for their mental capacities. Mind Flayers thrive by devouring the minds of other creatures, generally only interacting with other species at all to eat them or to enslave their kind.

Name: Mindless Ones (Marvel)
Summary: The Mindless Ones were created by Plokta as a way of slowing the expanding empires of rivals, they were virtually unstoppable engines of destruction; when a rival was deemed to be becoming too powerful, Plokta would let the Mindless Ones loose in the rival's realm, tying up the rival's resources trying to contain them.

Name: Minotaur (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: Minotaurs are cursed individuals, members of a race created by Baphomet, the Horned King, a demon lord that rules an infinite maze in the Abyss. They are massive humanoids with the features of bulls. Previously all minotaurs were male, though this seems to have changed of late now that many minotaurs are breaking free of the curse placed upon them by Baphomet. The most striking thing about these creatures is that, while not particularly intelligent, they are extremely clever in regards to tracking, and it is considered impossible to get them lost.

Name: Mira (Toilet in Wonderland)
Summary: Mira is the main protagonist of Toilet in Wonderland. In the beginning of the game, she wakes up in a dream world that was created by her constipation. Her constipation level starts off at 100%, and as she collects laxatives and discovers the game's various magic toilets, that level will drop. If the level is dropped to 0%, the true ending will be unlocked.

Name: Mirabelle
Summary: Mirabelle Prunille Pois Chevalier is a major character in the game In Stars and Time and START AGAIN: a prologue, traveling with Isabeau, Odile, Siffrin, and Bonnie on a quest to defeat the King and save Vaugarde from the fate of being frozen in time. She is a kind yet anxious Housemaiden of Change, with the Change belief being a religion practiced in most of Vaugarde whose ideals are about change in both its practitioners and in the world as a whole.

Name: MirageGaogamon
Summary: Tier: 9-B | High 8-C | 6-C | At least High 6-C | 5-B, 1-C with Burst Mode

Name: Miror B.
Key: '''By Himself''' | '''Pokémon Team (Pyrite Cave)''' | '''Pokémon Team (Realgam Tower)''' | '''Pokémon Team (Deep Colosseum)''' | '''Pokémon Team (Cave Poké Spot)''' | '''Pokémon Team (Outskirt Stand)''' | '''Pokémon Team (Gateon Port)'''
Summary: Miror B. (Japanese: ミラーボ Mirorbo) is a recurring character and major antagonist from Pokémon Colosseum and Pokémon XD: Gale of Darkness. His name is probably derived from mirror ball. He is the only character in the games to have the Trainer class Wanderer (Japanese: さすらい Wanderer).

Name: Miss America (Golden Age Marvel Comics)
Summary: Madeline Joyce was a young niece of millionaire James Bennett, who financing an electrical project that would grant the person "the strength of a thousand men". Madeline stumbled upon this experiment accidentally one night, granting her super strength, flight as well as X-ray vision. Naming herself Miss America, Madeline soared through the skies as the premiere heroine protecting the East Coast from Nazi threats for her homeland.

Name: Mission Sub-1
Summary: The Mission SUB-1 was designed to be the most accurate crossbow on the market. The name "SUB-1" means "under 1 inch".

Name: Misty
Key: '''By Herself''' | '''Pokèmon Team (Gen 1:Gym Battle)''' | '''Pokèmon Team (Gen 1:Rematch)''' | '''Pokèmon Team (Gen 2)''' | '''Pokèmon Team (Gen 5)'''
Summary: Misty (Japanese: カスミ Kasumi) is a Gym Leader of Cerulean City's Gym, known officially as the Cerulean Gym. She gives the Cascade Badge to Trainers who defeat her in battle. She specializes in Water-type Pokémon.

Name: MK2 Grenade
Summary: The MK2 is a fragmentation-type anti-personnel grenade introduced in 1918 to replace the failed MK1 grenade. Also known as the pineapple grenade, despite being pulled from service in 1969, it continues to be depicted in various cartoons and fictional media as a stand-in for a grenade to this day. It would later be replaced with the M26 series of grenades.

Name: MK3 grenade
Summary: The MK3 offensive hand grenade is a cylindrical concussion grenade designed to produce casualties during close combat while minimizing danger to friendly personnel exposed in the open owing to minimal fragmentation. There is a secondary fragmentation hazard though from rocks, gravel, wood splinters, glass, etc. The grenade is also used for concussion effects in enclosed areas, for blasting, or for demolition tasks. It is commonly known as the "concussion" or "demo" (from demolition) grenade.

Name: Moa (Real World)
Summary: The Moa were nine species in six genera of extinct flightless birds that were endemic to the island of New Zealand. They were the dominant herbivores in New Zealand's bush, their population reaching a peak of 58,000 around 1280, with their only natural predator being the Haast's eagle. They were driven to extinction due to overhunting by the Polynesian (Maori) settlers around 1440 ± 20 years.

Name: Modron
Summary: Quote? You desire a quote? The One and the Prime does not give 'quotes'.

Name: Moff Gideon
Summary: Moff Gideon was an officer of the Imperial Security Bureau who contributed to the Great Purge against the Mandalorians until graduating to the rank of marshal and then Moff. After the Galactic Empire's downfall, he evaded execution for war crimes and became the leader of a powerful imperial fragment army while seeking a force-sensitive baby of the same species as Jedi master Yoda, causing him and his forces to conflict with The Mandalorian and his allies.

Name: Mongrel Dog
Summary: The mongrel dog is called the pedigree dog, whose ancestry is generally unknown, which has characteristics of two or more types of breeds, or is descended from populations of wild or street dogs.

Name: Monica Rambeau (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Monica Rambeau was a New Orleans Harbor Patrol officer until one day she destroyed an energy disruptor device which caused her to gain full control of the electromagnetic spectrum. She joined the Avengers under the name Captain Marvel and later became their leader.

Name: Montana (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Jackson Brice was born in Bozeman, Montana. Along with Fancy Dan and the original Ox, he was a founding member of the Enforcers. He has great proficiency with the lariat. As a member of the Enforcers, he first came into conflict with Spider-Man when they were employed by the Big Man and have been fighting the wall-crawler ever since.

Name: Moon Knight (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Steven Grant: Oh, God. I'm gonna die, I'm gonna die. Marc Spector: Steven, LOOK at me... you're not gonna die. Let me save us.

Name: Moondragon (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Heather Douglas was the daughter of Arthur Douglas. When Heather was still a girl, her father was driving her and her mother through the desert when they accidentally happened to see the spaceship of Thanos land; the space villain didn't want any witnesses, so he blew their car up. Heather was thrown clear off and survived, but her parents were killed. She was found by Thanos' father, Mentor, who took her to his homeworld, Titan, to be raised by the Titanian Shao-Lorn monks in their monastery. While there, Heather studied the Titans' ways and disciplines to unlock her latent psychic potential and gained her mental and physical powers. Dedicating her power to hunting down Thanos, who had returned and razed Titan, she came upon the Avengers and joined their ranks.

Name: Moose
Summary: Moose are the largest members of the deer family. Unlike most deer, which would run from danger, moose are aggressive beasts who stand their ground against predators. The moose has few predators, most notably wolves and tigers. Adult bulls typically weigh from 380 to 700 kg while adult cows weigh from 200 to 490 kg. The largest of all the races of moose is the Alaskan subspecies.

Name: Morgan Le Fay (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Morgan le Fay is the main antagonist of the third season of the TV Series Runaways from the Marvel Cinematic Universe. She is a powerful witch trapped in the Dark Dimension who had sought to take control over Nico Minoru and the Staff of One in order to conquer the world. She managed to escape from the Dark Dimension after inciting Minoru to use the correct spell as she initiated a plan to merge the Dark Dimension and Earth, which she then intended to rule over with an army of slaves created through the Corvus WizPhones. To that end, le Fay enthralled Robert Minoru and took over Wizard, and repeatedly tried to have the Staff of One given to her by Nico. However, le Fay's plans for a world domination were finally foiled by an alliance between both the Runaways and PRIDE, and le Fay was then banished back to the Dark Dimension by Tina Minoru.

Name: Mortlock Vanthampur
Summary: The youngest son of Thalamra Vanthampur, Mortlock Vanthampur was left in her care after his father died while he was young. In his youth he was also a victim of a fire which scarred him for life, leaving his face horribly deformed.

Name: Mosasaurus (Real World)
Summary: The Mosasaurus was a genus of mosasaurs, marine reptiles that lived during the Cretaceous period. They grew up to 17 meters and weighed 15-20 tons.

Name: Mosin-Nagant
Summary: The 3-line rifle M1891 (Russian: трёхлинейная винтовка образца 1891 года, tryokhlineynaya vintovka obraztsa 1891 goda), colloquially known in the West as Mosin–Nagant and in Russia as Mosin's rifle (Russian: винтовка Мосина, ISO 9: vintovka Mosina) is a 5-shot bolt-action, internal magazine-fed, military rifle developed from 1882 to 1891, and was in widespread use amongst the Russian Empire, the Soviet Union and various other nations across several major conflicts in the history of the world. It is by far one of the most widespread rifles as well, with over 37 million units having been made since its inception in 1891, and despite its age, it still sees intense conflict in the modern age. It primarily makes use of the 7.62x54mm cartridge, though it is also compatible with the following cartridges: 7.62×53mmR (Finnish variants only), 7.92×57mm Mauser (Polish variants and German captures) and 8×50mmR Mannlicher (Austrian captures).

Name: Mossberg 500
Summary: Mossberg 500 is a series of pump action shotguns manufactured by O.F. Mossberg & Sons.

Name: Mother Malkin (Seventh Son)
Summary: Mother Malkin is the primary antagonist in the book series The Wardstone Chronicles and in its 2015 film adaptation Seventh Son. Many years ago, she was captured by John Gregory, the last of a knightly order known as the Falcons, who have long defended humanity against supernatural threats but escaped her underground prison with rise of the centennial blood moon. She regrouped with her sister, Lizzie, and her followers, including Radu, and aimed to take over the world. She was ultimately killed by Tom Ward.

Name: Mother Night (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Susan Scarbo, along with her brother Melvin Scarbo, was a stage hypnotist who turned to crime under the name Suprema. Using their hypnotic ability, they began to recruit an army. Scarbo began taking over criminal gangs in New York by subverting their leaders' minds.

Name: Motormouth (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Young orphan Harley Davis was abandoned on the streets of London's East End, and rough-housed her way to the cusp of adulthood, at which point her foul-mouthed demeanor had earned her the nickname Motormouth.

Name: Mr. Freeze (Post-Crisis)
Summary: Victor Fries was a cryogenics worker operating in Gotham City trying to find a way to cure his ill wife Nora. When he preserved her in cryostasis without authorization from GothCorp, the company tried to shut his research down, and in Victor's attempt to stop them he was caught in a dangerous chemical accident that left him unable to survive outside of very cold temperatures. Building a special suit to keep himself alive, he used it to become the supervillain Mr. Freeze.

Name: Mr. Immortal
Summary: As the only Homo Supreme in existence, Craig Hollis was born with the power of complete immortality. He soon established the Great Lakes Avengers and became the superhero Mr. Immortal.

Name: Mud Mephit
Summary: The weakest, slowest, and least intelligent of the Mephit kind, the Mud Mephit is composed of earth and water. They are sluggish, attention seekers, and will beg for attention and treasure. They lack other Mephit's claws, instead being forced to hit foes with punches, and their breath weapon is spitting mud that constricts enemies.

Name: Mud Slaad
Summary: Though many believe that the Red Slaad is the weakest of the Slaad kind the one that truly deserves that title is the Mud Slaad. Despite being weaker then the rest of its kin they are still deadly opponents for adventurer parties to face.

Name: Mule (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: A sterile cross between horses and donkeys, the Mule is the best of both worlds. While somewhat short tempered they are strong, agile, and are incredibly stable on their feet, all of which makes them the perfect work animal.

Name: Mummy (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: Mummies are a type of powerful undead, known primarily for their appearance of ceremonial wrappings around their entire bodies as well as for their horrifying ability to cause creatures to rot away with a single touch. They are typically found in deserts and are raised by the dark gods residing in the sandy dunes. They were normally found guarding tombs containing great wealth, and deterred all but the most resilient adventurers.

Name: Muriel (Hansel & Gretel: Witch Hunters)
Summary: Muriel the Grand Black Witch is the main antagonist of 2013 film Hansel & Gretel: Witch Hunters. She is the leader of the Black Witches, and Hansel and Gretel's arch-nemesis. Powerful, but still vulnerable to fire, she sought an immunity to fire. In order to do so, she needed to sacrifice the heart of a Grand White Witch and twelve children in a ritual sacrifice on the Blood Moon Sabbath.

Name: Muse (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Heather Glenn: Bastian, please. Muse: Don't fucking call me that! I am Muse! Muse. M-U-S-E.

Name: Muse (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Muse was a mysterious, deranged artist whose gruesome work of art was discovered after he anonymously sent the vigilante Blindspot the address of the warehouse in Washington Heights where he had planted it. This work consisted of a mural painted with blood from over a hundred different missing people.

Name: Muskox
Summary: The muskox (Ovibos moschatus) are one of the largest bovids native to the arctic circle.[1][2] Being a stocky, compact, large herbivorous animal visually similar to bison in appearance, albeit more closely related to goats and sheep.[1]

Name: Mustard (Pokémon)
Key: '''By Himself''' | '''Pokèmon Team (First battle)''' | '''Pokèmon Team (Second battle)''' | '''Pokèmon Team (Third battle)'''
Summary: Mustard is a character in The Isle of Armor in Pokémon Sword and Shield. He is a former Champion of the Galar region and the mentor of Leon. He is the only character in the games to have the Trainer class Dojo Master.

Name: Mwaxanare
Summary: Mwaxanare is the oldest living descendant of the ruling dynasty of Omu, an overthrown country on Chult. Alongside her brother, Na, they reside in the protection of the Aarakocra and the Wind Dukes of Aaqa, until such a time as they may reclaim their territory as rulers. During her stay with the bird-people, Mwaxanare has become an apprentice warlock, using spells to ensure she never has to physically work again.

Name: Myconid
Summary: Myconids are fungal organisms typically found in the Underdark that tend toward a pacifistic bent, and are generally more interested in enlightenment than combat. However, they are known to take up campaigns against the more vile races of the Underdark (such as the drow, duergar, mind flayers, and beholders) if threatened enough. They are known to make use of corpses as servants, infecting them with their spores to make them ambulatory once more. Myconids gather in "circles", small communities typically led by an individual of particular prowess and wisdom known as a sovereign. Myconids in such communities tend to form melds, a sort of group consciousness created via spores telepathically linking each and every member of the community. While in the meld, myconids release hallucinatory spores that grant dream-like visions that carry the primary function of entertainment or socializing, but can and are used to communicate complex ideas or memories.

Name: Mysterio (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Quentin Beck is a former Stark Industries employee who sought out to replace the late Tony Stark as Earth's next defender. Seeking to solidify a reputation for himself, Beck feigned several Elemental attacks across the world with the use of his drones, seeking attention and recognition from the public as a new superhero/supervillain named Mysterio.

Name: Mystique (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Mystique is one of the older mutants on the Marvel Earth, as she has been alive since at least the late 19th century. Early on in Mystique's life, she began using her powers to pursue personal goals at the expense of others.

Name: Mystra (Midnight)
Key: '''Beginning of the Avatar Crisis''' | '''End of the Avatar Crisis''' | '''Avatar''' | '''Greater God'''
Summary: Before she was the God of magic, Mystra was known as the wizard Midnight. Born Ariel Manx, she was the second child of the merchant Theus. A hedonist, Ariel would spend her time with the local bards, sorcerers, fighters, and thieves where she would eventually earn her nickname Midnight due to her late night activities. Eventually she would develop a fascination with magic and left her home in the pursuit of a higher calling.

Name: N (Pokémon)
Key: '''By Himself''' | '''Pokémon Team (Early Game)''' | '''Pokémon Team (End Game)''' | '''Black and White 2''' | '''Pokémon Team (Season Battles)'''
Summary: N is a character in Black, White, Black 2, and White 2. He was the puppet leader of Team Plasma in Pokémon Black and White and aspired to create separate worlds for humans and Pokémon. His full name is Natural Harmonia Gropius (ナチュラル・ハルモニア・グロピウス Natural Harmonia Gropius).

Name: Naiad
Summary: One of many water Feys, the Naiad looks like a humanoid composed of water. They are able to use various spells to defend themselves, mainly possessing illusion magic.

Name: Nanashi (Sword of the Stranger)
Summary: A ronin haunted by his terrible past, he has sworn to keep his sword sheathed. However, upon meeting Kotaro, he finds himself re-evaluating his life. While traveling with the young Kotaro, Nanashi finds himself acting as a bodyguard for the boy. This in turn leads to his prolonged struggle against the Ming warriors, particularly Luo-Lang.

Name: Narwhal (Real World)
Summary: The Narwhal (Monodon Monoceros) is a species of toothed whale native to the Arctic. It is the only member of the genus Monodon and one of two living representatives of the family Monodontidae. The narwhal has a similar build to the closely related beluga whale, with which it overlaps in range and can interbreed. It is a stocky cetacean with a relatively blunt snout, a large melon, and a shallow ridge in place of a dorsal fin. Males of this species have a large 1.5–3.0 m (4 ft 11 in – 9 ft 10 in) long tusk, which is a left protruded canine thought to serve as a weapon or as a tool for feeding, attracting mates or sensing water salinity. Specially adapted slow-twitch muscles, along with the jointed neck vertebrae and shallow dorsal ridge allow for easy movement through the Arctic environment, where the narwhal spends extended periods at great depths.

Name: Nascour
Summary: Nascour (Japanese: ジャキラ Jakira) was thought to be the head of Cipher. A man with a terrifying visage, he is gaunt, dressed in dark clothes and possesses wiry, white, serpentine hair. He is the only character in the games to have the Trainer class Cipher (Japanese: シャドー Shadow). Nascour's strategy in battle is to use X Special and other stat-enhancing items on his Pokémon.

Name: Neanderthal
Summary: The Neanderthals were an early species (or sub-species) of humans that lived during the Middle and Low Pleistocene in Europe and West-Asia until as recently as ~40,000 years ago.

Name: Necrophidius
Summary: A necrophidius appears as a skeletal snake with a fanged human skull for a head. It is generally confused for an undead due to its appearance, but in fact is a construct of fiends used for guards and assassinations. It is a master of infiltration and is capable of remaining still indefinitely to gain access to its target.

Name: Needletooth
Summary: The Needletooth, also known as Needlefang Drake is a small green dinosaur around the size of a cat. It comes in large swarms which fearlessly try to devour any animal they come across, their small size and coloring makes them extremely effective in hiding in dense foliage, jungle, or heavy underbrush areas.

Name: NERDS (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: Formed by the Wererat Mr. Honeycomb to solve Harmony city's energy crisis, the NERDS are a group of six adventurers whom each helped the Order of Zimandius to save the city, with them stopping Emo the Beholder from sapping all the color of the world.

Name: Nessa (Pokémon)
Key: '''By Herself''' | '''Pokémon Team (Hulbury Stadium)''' | '''Pokémon Team (Champion Cup Finals)''' | '''Pokémon Team (Champion Tournament)''' | '''Pokémon Team (Galarian Star Tournament)'''
Summary: Nessa is the Gym Leader of Hulbury's Gym, known officially as Hulbury Stadium. She specializes in Water-type Pokémon. She gives the Water Badge to Trainers who defeat her.

Name: New Nambu M60
Summary: The "New Nambu" M60 is a double-action revolver chambered in .38 Special based upon Smith & Wesson-style designs, used mostly by law enforcement in Japan. It was designed and produced by Shin-Chuō Industries, later merged with Minebea. Approximately 133,400 have been produced since 1961.

Name: Nezznar the Black Spider
Summary: Nezznar the Black Spider is a Drow adventurer and leader of a battalion of goblinoids who took over the dwarven mines near Phandelver in the module Lost Mine of Phandelver. Nezznar has led his followers into the dark descents of the mine seeking treasure and to use the mine for his own purposes.

Name: Nick Fury (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Nick Fury is the former S.H.I.E.L.D. director. He is the spy to beat all spies, keeping tabs as best as he can on all supernatural occurences in the Marvel Cinematic Universe.

Name: Nick Fury (Marvel Comics)
Summary: The eldest of three children, Nicholas Joseph Fury grew up in Depression-era New York City with his brother Jacob and sister Dawn. Nick Fury and his friend Hargrove caught the eye of Lt. "Happy Sam" Sawyer who enlisted them for a special mission in Holland. On this mission, Fury made the acquaintance of his future life-long friend, the circus strongman Timothy "Dum Dum" Dugan. Two serious injuries sustained during this time would have a serious impact in his later life: a grenade blast that began the slow deterioration of his sight in his left eye, and a landmine accident that led to Fury being inoculated with the Infinity Formula by Professor Berthold Sternberg in France.

Name: Nifern
Summary: The Nifern is a hybrid between a reptile and a dog, with it possessing the shape of a dog but having scales on its body alongside a stinger on its tail, it's also naturally blind due to not having eyes and instead relying on its sense of smell to battle. Due to their reptile qualities they're a popular animal for scalykind like Lizardfolk and their sense of smell also made them a common tracker animal used by creatures such as the Mind Flayers.

Name: Nightcrawler
Summary: Kurt Wagner is a prominent member of the X-Men and former member and leader of Excalibur. He possesses the mutant ability of teleportation, as well as incredible agility and a prehensile tail. Taking on the name of Nightcrawler, Kurt is a devout Catholic, contrasting his demonic appearance. He is a swashbuckling trickster and former circus acrobat.

Name: Nightmare (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: Nightmares are horse-like creatures originating from the Lower Planes, such as the Abyss, the Nine Hells, or Gehenna. They are the standard choice of mount for high-ranking fiends and undead alike, most often searching devil and demon lords, vampires, liches, and other evil-aligned creatures such as the shadar-kai. They are truly wicked beings and are best known for their flaming bodies and vicious tempers.

Name: Nightwing (Post-Crisis)
Summary: Richard John "Dick" Grayson is a fictional superhero that appears in comic books published by DC Comics. Created by Bob Kane and Bill Finger and illustrator Jerry Robinson, he first appeared in Detective Comics #38 in April 1940. The youngest in a family of acrobats known as the "Flying Graysons", Dick watches a mafia boss kill his parents in order to extort money from the circus that employed them.

Name: Nile Crocodile
Summary: The Nile crocodile (Crocodylus niloticus) is an African crocodile, the largest freshwater predator in Africa, and may be considered the second-largest extant reptile and crocodilian in the world, after the saltwater crocodile (Crocodylus porosus). The Nile crocodile is quite widespread throughout sub-Saharan Africa, occurring mostly in the central, eastern, and southern regions of the continent, and lives in different types of aquatic environments such as lakes, rivers, and marshlands. Although capable of living in saline environments, this species is rarely found in saltwater, but occasionally inhabits deltas and brackish lakes. The range of this species once stretched northward throughout the Nile, as far north as the Nile delta. On average, the adult male Nile crocodile is between 3.5 and 5 m (11.5 and 16.4 ft) in length and weighs 225 to 750 kg (500 to 1,650 lb). However, specimens exceeding 6.1 m (20 ft) in length and weighing up to 1,090 kg (2,400 lb) have been recorded. Sexual dimorphism is prevalent, and females are usually about 30% smaller than males. They have thick, scaly, heavily armored skin.

Name: Nixylanna Vidorant
Summary: Once a member of the Silver Fingers Society Nixylanna Vidorant used to work with Samphith Goldenbeard. However after a robbery where she abandoned him and afterwards refused to share the treasure with him they became bitter rivals. Years later she departs from the Silver Fingers Society while her rival becomes the leader of it, with him soon after sending forces to try and steal from her as revenge and the treasure that he claims is rightfully his.

Name: Nobu (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Daredevil: Wait... you're dead! Nobu: There is no such thing.

Name: Noob Variants
Summary: Noob variants (Sometimes also called nooblet variants) are different variants of nooblet that the player runs into early in block tales. They tend to vary from ninjas like sharp nooblet to knights to even winged and cultist noobs. All nooblets, however, are characterized by resembling the Roblox noob in some way. These variants usually team up together against other enemies either with other variants or with the same type of variant; however, it is also possible for them to be alone.

Name: Noska Ur'gray
Summary: A ruthless enforcer Noska Ur'gray is an evil dwarf working for the Xanathar Guild. His left arm was reduced to a stump by a green slime in Undermountain, he however attached a heavy crossbow to his arm to make up for that loss.

Name: Nostalgie
Summary: Bourdon is a sadness in the game In Stars and Time, appearing on each floor of Dormont’s House of Change and holding a Star Crest.

Name: Nothic
Summary: Nothics are corrupted spellcasters who peered too deeply into the secrets of their vile masters. Vecna, in ages past, created a creeping curse for secretive mages who sought great power. The more they looked into the foul secrets they researched endlessly, the more likely it would be that they would be transformed into a Nothic. Much of the followers of Acererak fell to such a fate, as did many arcanists of Netherese who weren't fortunate enough to become liches following their civilization's collapse.

Name: Nothosaurus
Summary: Nothosaurus is a genus of sauropterygian reptiles that lived around 240–210 million years ago, throughout the mid to late Triassic. Its name comes from the Greek words νόθος (nothos), which means "illegitimate," and σαῦρος (sauros), which means "lizard." It was widespread throughout the world, with 12 species having been found in North Africa, Europe, and China, inhabiting the ancient Tethys Ocean and its shores. These sea reptiles were likely related to plesiosaurs and pliosaurs that would later emerge, with Nothosaur-like reptiles thought to have given rise to them.

Name: Nuke (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Will Simpson was a former patient of IGH who, having struggled to maintain control, left the program and became a police officer from the New York City Police Department. Due to an encounter with Kilgrave, Simpson became obsessed with tracking down and killing him, teaming up with Jessica Jones and Trish Walker in order to complete this goal. However, when Simpson began to believe that Jones' methods weren’t effective, he returned back to the Military Program that he left years before in order to obtain some more of their Combat Enhancers which would increase his strength, while also turning him into a crazed murderer.

Name: Nunu and Willump
Summary: Once upon a time, there was a boy who wanted to prove he was a hero by slaying a fearsome monster—only to discover that the beast, a lonely and magical yeti, merely needed a friend. Bound together by ancient power and a shared love of snowballs, Nunu and Willump now ramble wildly across the Freljord, breathing life into imagined adventures. They hope that somewhere out there, they will find Nunu’s mother. If they can save her, maybe they will be heroes after all…

Name: Oblex
Summary: An Oblex is a collection of sentient slime created by the Illithids through various experiments in the Underdark. Akin to its creators, The Oblex shares a diet for the minds of others and is devoted entirely to absorbing the substance, using its wits to stalk intelligent prey before proceeding to engulf its prey's head, draining out their memories and personality while leaving the prey clueless and perplexed afterward, if not dead. These memories are presumably represented by the head of its victim.

Name: Ocean Sunfish
Summary: The Ocean Sunfish, also known as the Mola mola, is a large species of fish that inhabits tropical and temperate waters worldwide. They are the largest bony fish in the world, and have a maximum recorded length and weight of 4.2 meters from fin to fin and 2300 kilograms, respectively. Ocean sunfish typically feed on small fish, jellyfish, and crustaceans, and can jump three meters out of the water in order to rid themselves of parasites.

Name: Ocelot
Summary: The ocelot (Leopardus pardalis) is a medium-sized spotted wild cat that is native to the southwestern United States, Mexico, Central and South America, and to the Caribbean islands of Trinidad and Margarita. It prefers areas close to water sources with dense vegetation cover and high prey availability.

Name: Ochre Jelly
Summary: Old favorites time, is it? I know that ye folks that play at the sort o' things that happen for real in the Realms are overly fond of pitting yer characters against witless giant amoebas! Just about their style, eh? Witless giant amoebas? Ochre jellies, ye dolt!

Name: Odile
Summary: Sachiko Odile Aiuchi is a major character in the game In Stars and Time and START AGAIN: a prologue, traveling with Mirabelle, Isabeau, Siffrin, and Bonnie on a quest to defeat the King and save Vaugarde from the fate of being frozen in time. She is a curious and perceptive traveler from Ka Bue, thought to be a researcher by the rest of her party.

Name: Odobenocetops
Summary: Odobenocetops is a genus tooth whale, belonging to the same group as dolphins or porpoises. Despite this, it bares many similarities to walruses, notably in its distinctive asymmetrical tusks; the type species O. peruvianus had tusk lengths of 45–55 cm and 20 cm for its right and left respectively,[1] while O. leptodon had a left tusk at a longer 25 cm and a right tusk at 1.35 meters[2] The function of these tusks is unknown, but due to their brittle nature, they would have not been used for jousting, and rather they likely served other intraspecific purposes. Along with walruses, they also display convergent evolution with narwhals, with their skulls being entirely toothless aside from these tusks.

Name: Oerlikon 20mm/70 Gun
Summary: The Oerlikon 20mm Gun is an autocannon widely produced by Oerlikon Contraves during World War II, likely in higher numbers than any other antiaircraft gun of the war, with various models employed by both Allied and Axis forces.

Name: Ogre (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: Ogres are a low-ranking species of giants, taking the position of the bottom rung of the Ordning, the social structure of the Giants. Ogres are big, dumb, and strong- perfect units for the foot soldiers of the giant armies.

Name: Okoye (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Okoye is the general of Dora Milaje and the head of Wakanda's armed forces and intel.

Name: Olaf
Summary: Most men would say that death is a thing to be feared; none of those men would be Olaf. The Berserker lives only for the roar of a battle cry and the clash of steel. Spurred on by his hunger for glory and the looming curse of a forgettable death, Olaf throws himself into every fight with reckless abandon. Surrendering to the bloodlust deep within his being, Olaf is only truly alive when grappling with the jaws of death.

Name: Olive Baboon
Summary: The Olive Baboon is a large omnivorous monkey found in Africa. It is considered a pest in many countries and hated for raiding houses and stealing food.

Name: Oni (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: The Mage Ogre commonly known as the Oni is a variant of the Ogre which is far more dangerous due to its innate magical abilities, regeneration, and higher intelligence.

Name: Onomatopoeia (Post-Crisis)
Summary: Named for his verbal tic of verbally repeating sounds of the world around him, the enigmatic Onomatopoeia is a serial killer of the most dangerous game: superheroes. Generally targeting rookie, third-rate non-powered heroes, Onomatopoeia eventually kills his way up to the likes of Green Arrow and even Batman, using his strategic genius and excellent physical condition to hunt and kill whoever he chooses as his latest target.

Name: Orange (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: An owner of a Martial Arts school, Orange is one of the many adventurers recruited by Mr. Honey to save Harmony city from having its color drained away.

Name: Orca
Summary: Also known as Killer Whale,[1][2][3] the Orca[1][4][2] (Orcinus[1] Orca)[5][2][3][4] is the largest species of ocean dolphins, preying upon a wide variety of foods,[6][2][4][7] from small fish[6][4][7] to other dolphins[6] to even blue whales.[8][9][10] They are also social animals,[11][2] travelling in groups called pods,[11][6][2][4][7] and can be found across the world's oceans.[2][12][4]

Name: Oreioth
Summary: Oreioth was a necromancer during the Elemental Evil crisis, and was born into a world of hatred. At a young age he would commit atrocities such as murdering infant children for the sole intent of savoring his power over their death.

Name: Ornitholestes
Summary: Ornitholestes is a genus of small theropod dinosaur from the late Jurassic, living on the supercontinent of Laurasia in modern day North America around 154 million years ago. Its name means "bird robber," with the second part of the name in honor of Adam Hermann, preparator for the American Museum of Natural History. Ornitholestes could reach around 2 meters long,[1] or longer at around 2.08 meters. More recent studies indicate it likely had feathers, much like other coelurosaurs, theropods more closely related to modern birds than carnosaurs like Allosaurus.

Name: Ornithomimus
Summary: Ornithomimus is a genus of Therapod living in what will one day be North America. Ornithomimus is a genus of ornithomimid dinosaurs from the Late Cretaceous Period of what is now North America. Ornithomimus from fossil evidence indicates it was covered in feathers, equipped with a small toothless beak that may indicate an omnivorous diet.

Name: Osquip
Summary: A magical variant of a rat, the Osquip is a hairless yellow rat which has between 6 to 10 legs. This rodents use their sharp teeth to create undergorund tunnels which they use for living and ambushes on other creatures.

Name: Ostrich
Summary: Ostriches are known as the fastest and largest birds on earth, weighing in at 145 kilograms, reaching up to 2.7 meters tall, and possessing powerful legs allowing them to run at speeds of up to 43 mph (19,22272 m/s). Also coming naturally from being so big, their eyes can reach 2 inches in diameter and their eggs weigh 12 times as much as chicken eggs.

Name: Otter (Real World)
Summary: Otters are carnivorous mammals in the subfamily Lutrinae. The 13 extant otter species are all semiaquatic, aquatic or marine, with diets based on fish and invertebrates. Lutrinae is a branch of the Mustelidae family, which also includes weasels, badgers, honey badgers, martens, minks, polecats, and wolverines.

Name: Otyugh
Summary: Look out to the base of the wall there... look hard, and look for an enemy. An eye! An eye... coming up from the ground like a worm! But- but- what is it, out there? Only your father can tell you that, Erammon. And if I were you, I'd make sure he was in a good mood when I asked him.

Name: Ouryumon
Summary: Tier: 9-B | High 8-C | At least 6-C | At least High 6-C | At least 5-B, possibly 1-C

Name: Owlbear
Summary: Owlbears are a chimeric, magical combination of owls and bears (as the name implies), and are known to be terrible predators. They are famed for their ill tempers and ferocity- a fight with an owlbear is a fight to the death. Once they were natives to the Feywild, however they have since migrated to other worlds.

Name: Owlman (Justice League: Crisis on Two Earths)
Summary: Welcome to Earth Prime. Before there was thought, there was this place. One Earth. With a single history. But with the coming of man came the illusion of free will. And with that illusion came chaos. With every choice we make, we literally create a world. History branches in two, creating one Earth, where we made the choice, and a second, where we didn't. That's the secret of the universe, you know. Billions of people, making billions of choices, creating infinite Earths. Some so similar to each other you could spend a lifetime searching for any distinction, others so radically different they defy comprehension. [...] Every version of reality balances precariously on this singular Earth. It seems so different from the Earths we know. I can't imagine what series of decisions led to this world hurtling out of its orbit. But I know this, the source of the cataclysm was the same as it always is - man. [...] You know better. Man is a cancer and I've chosen to cut out the disease. [...] Everyone who ever lived, who ever will live. I choose to make the only possible real choice.
ID: Owlman (Justice League: Crisis on Two Earths)-Unknown-9

Name: Owlman (Post-Crisis)
Summary: In an antimatter universe, Thomas Wayne and his oldest son, Thomas Jr., survived the murder of the Wayne family, while Bruce was killed. This lead to Thomas Jr. giving himself training, gadgets and artificial intellect enhancements to operate as a prominent criminal, and member of the supervillain Crime Syndicate of Amerika, as Owlman.

Name: P-47 Thunderbolt
Summary: The P-47 Thunderbolt was an escort fighter designed in 1941. Early on in the war it carried out escort missions and bombing missions on key targets. Heavy example of its use for a bomber fighter was in Italy. Constant improvement to the planes design continued but it eventually lost its need as an escort fighter to the P-51D due to increasing demands for range and low altitude speed, however the P-47 remained in service until past the end of the war. the P-47 was retired from service by all nations in 1966, with the last built P-47 was shipped out in October 1945.

Name: Pachycephalosaurus
Summary: Pachycephalosaurus is a genus of dinosaur from the Cretaceus Period, known for their dome-shaped skulls. Cranial lesions in some specimens indicate that pachycephalosaurus may have exhibited headbutting behavior. It would've reached 4.5 meters long and weighed around 450 kg.

Name: Pachyrhinosaurus
Summary: Pachyrhinosaurus is a genus of ceratopsian dinosaur whose name means "thick-nosed lizard," coming from the Greek words Παχυ (pachy) which means "thick," ρινό (rinó), which means "nose," and σαυρος (sauros), which means "lizard." It includes three species: The type species P. Canadensis, which was the largest of them, P. lakustai, and P. perotorum. It lived throughout northern North America, including Canada and US state of Alaska, around 73.5–69 million years ago during the late Cretaceous. It's distinctive feature is the boney boss on its nose, along with two over its eyes, and various horns adorning the frill and skull, which often varioed among species and individuals.

Name: Paco Laburantes
Summary: Paco Laburantes is a major character in the ninth part of JoJo's Bizarre Adventure, The JOJOLands.

Name: Painkiller (CW)
Summary: Khalil Payne (born March 25, 2001) also known as Painkiller, is a former student at Garfield High School who briefly joined The 100 as an enforcer before being killed and resurrected by the A.S.A. to be used as a biological weapons system.

Name: Palaeoloxodon Namadicus
Summary: Palaeoloxodon namadicus or the Asian straight-tusked elephant, was a species of prehistoric elephant that ranged throughout Pleistocene Asia, from India (where it was first discovered) to Japan. Volumetric measurements have shown that this species of prehistoric elephant would have been 5.2 meters (17.1 feet) tall at the withers and weighed in at 22 tonnes (24.3 short tons)

Name: Palmer
Summary: Palmer is the Tower Tycoon of Sinnoh's and Johto's Battle Frontier. He is also the father of Barry, the player's rival.

Name: Pancor Jackhammer
Summary: The Pancor Corporation Jackhammer was a 12-gauge, blow-forward gas-operated bullpup automatic shotgun designed in 1984 and patented in 1987. Only three working prototypes of the Jackhammer were built. Nonetheless, its distinctive aesthetics and futuristic design have made it a prop in action films, television programs, and video games.

Name: Panzer VI Tiger
Summary: The Panzer VI Tiger or Tiger I was a German heavy tank of World War II deployed from 1942 in Africa and Europe usually in independent heavy tank battalions.

Name: Panzerschreck
Summary: The Panzerschreck is a Anti-Tank Rocket Launcher used in World War 2 by the Germans.

Name: Paraceratherium
Summary: Paraceratherium is an extinct genus of hyracodonts, ancient relatives of rhinoceros. Paraceratherium lived from the early to late Oligocene epoch (34 - 23 million years ago) in what is now Eurasia, between China and the Balkans.

Name: Patrina Velikovna
Summary: In life, Patrina Velkovna was sister to Kasimir Velikov, and love interest of Strahd von Zarovich, a fact for which her brother orchestrated her stoning. After her death, Rahadin was ordered to wipe out her people for their transgressions against Strahd's love- every other female of her kind was eradicated, and Kasimir's ears were sliced off.

Name: Patriofelis
Summary: Patriofelis ("Father of cats") is a genus of large carnivorous placental mammal that lived in North America during the Early to Middle Eocene epoch, about 50.3–46.2 million years ago. Despite its superficial resemblance to big cats, it is not a feline, nor is it a carnivoran either; instead, it was an oxyaenid, a group of carnivorous mammals that were apex predators during the Eocene. Unlike carnivorans, it had stiffened vertebrae similar to armadillos or pangolins, thought to be a tradeoff of flexibility for larger size.[1] In life, they would have been terrestrial apex predators adapted for hunting on the forest floor.[2]

Name: Paul (Pokémon)
Summary: Paul is a rather arrogant trainer. From Veilstone City, he headed to Sandgem to get his starter, he has since travelled through Kanto, Johto & Hoenn. However, he is not a caring trainer, what he wants from his Pokémon is pure power and the trainers he faces to be strong. When he first meets Ash, he demands a 3 on 3 Battle, however since Ash was still looking for Pikachu, Ash couldn't battle, this warranted some aggrivation on Paul's part. Paul is also known to release his Pokémon if he deems them weak or useless.

Name: Paul Rabin (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Paul Rabin is the son of the Emissary who encountered Peter Parker and Mary Jane Watson after they entered his reality while fighting their own Emissary. After MJ used a device to send Peter back home, Paul spent nearly four years with her due to time dilation before Peter's return. During that time, Paul and MJ had found and adopted two kids to raise as their own. Apparently married, MJ refused to leave Paul, and they continued their family life in Earth-616.

Name: Pegasus (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: Pegasi are a race of winged equine creatures hailing from the plane of Arborea, and are often considered symbols of peace, goodness, and beauty, and were often used as mounts for the avatars of the Seldarine. Despite sharing some similarities, pegasi despise Griffons and Hippogriffs and will go out of their way to destroy them. However, in general a pegasus would prefer to flee rather than engage in combat.

Name: Peggy Carter (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Peggy Carter was a British agent who ended up working for the SSR with Project Rebirth during WW2. She befriended and started a relationship with Captain America, until his crash into the ice. After WW2 she continued to work for SSR, until she left, and founded S.H.I.E.L.D, with Howard Stark, and Chester Philips. She is the aunt of Sharon Carter, and eventually dies from old age.

Name: Peony
Summary: Peony is Chairman Rose’s younger brother and the main companion of Victor for the Crown Tundra DLC of Pokemon Sword and Pokemon Shield. Rose’s genius was recognized at an early age, causing everyone he knew to constantly compare him to his brother, causing him to run away from home. It was while he was a delinquent that his skill for raising Steel type Pokemon was recognized, and he soon even became a Gym Leader. After Mustard stepped down from being the Galar League Champion, Peony seized the opportunity and became Champion himself, however he soon stepped down too when he discovered that Rose had become the Chairman of Macro Cosmos. Many years later, he had a daughter, Peonia, who he still has a difficult relationship with to this day as she rejects any of his attempts to help or get close to her, though that never once stops him from trying. It is unknown if Peony is aware that Rose was arrested after causing the second Darkest Day.

Name: Peregrine Falcon
Summary: The Peregrine Falcon is a species of falcon that is renowned for its hunting ability and characteristic diving maneuver.

Name: Perucetus Colossus
Summary: Perucetus Colossus is a prehistoric cetacean that lived 39 to 37 million years ago.
