Discovered in August 2023 by a team of Peruvian paleontologists, mainly from the National University of San Marcos, Perucetus Colossus is believed to have potentially been the largest animal ever in terms of mass, with an estimated length of 17 to 20.1 meters and an estimated weight of 60 to 70 tonnes.[1] The original, inaccurate estimate was much higher (85 to 340 tonnes). It is known from thirteen vertebrae, four ribs, and some parts of the pelvic region.

Name: Peryton
Summary: Perytons are large, stag-vulture chimeric creatures originating from another world than our own. Much like Githyanki or Mind Flayerss, they are predatorial beings who wandered to this plane for raiding and colonization purposes (among others) after subjugating their own planet. However, due to the chaotic nature of these beings, their empire quickly fell apart and those that remained here lost the ability to return, stranding them here and reducing them to outcasts.

Name: Pfeifer Zeliska Revolver
Summary: The .600 Nitro Express Pfeifer Zeliska revolver is an Austrian single-action revolver produced by Pfeifer firearms. Except for the giant 28mm 1859 Remington revolver, the Zeliska may be the largest handgun in the world (arguably, the giant 1859 should not actually qualify as a handgun, given its size and mass), weighing in at over 6 kilograms (13.23 lb) and having a length of 55 centimeters (22 in); the cylinder section alone weighs 2.041 kilograms (4.5 lb).

Name: Phaerlin Giant
Summary: The Phaerlin Giant are descendant of the Stone Giant, born from the latter being warped by powerful magic. The Phaerlin Giant is far more bestial then other Giants, not even using boulders in combat and instead relying purely on their claws and teeth.

Name: Pharblex Splattergoo
Summary: Pharblex Splattergoo was the leader of a Bullywug tribe based around Castle Naerytar, who enjoyed tormenting the Lizardfolk vicariously through Dralmorrer Borngray. Thanks to the elf's help, he managed to slay one of the former Lizardfolk chiefs, and planned to kill the next- however, in return for this help, his bullywug acted as servants for the local Dragon Cult leader, Rezmir.

Name: Phase Spider
Summary: The Phase Spider is a horse sized blue and white spider which has the unique ability of shifting between the Prime Material world and the Ethereal Plane. Said ability makes it appear as if the Phase Spider teleports.

Name: Phase Spider Matriarch
Summary: I recall my life upon the surface with more than regret. I weep for the decades spent treading the murky waters of profanity while my true Queen waited in the shadows. Even my name, ‘Eliette’, feels foreign and foul upon my tongue. A high elf exalted by Lolth herself - my drow captors cannot fathom it. But I see their house's downfall in visions granted by the Spider Queen herself. When that day comes, when some unnamed whelp from an insignificant house cuts the matron mother's throat, I will escape. I will find solitude, and I will worship Lolth with my very soul.

Name: Phen-228 (The Boiled One Phenomenon)
Summary: This page contains or depicts disturbing and/or graphic content that some may find upsetting, and that is only intended for mature audiences. Please proceed with caution.

Name: Pidlwick II
Summary: Pidlwick II is a four-foot-tall mechanical toy crafted by the legendary toymaker Fritz von Weerg. He gains his namesake and inspiration from the original Pidlwick, a small jester that brought joy to those in Castle Ravenloft. Jealous of his inspiration, Pidlwick II killed the jester, mutilating his body by pushing him down the stairs. Ever since, Pidlwick has killed those that stay in Castle Ravenloft and do not enjoy his company, once being used as a discrete method of slaughter used by Strahd von Zarovich.

Name: Piers (Pokémon)
Key: '''By Himself''' | '''Pokémon Team (Spikemuth Stadium)''' | '''Pokémon Team (Champion Cup Finals)''' | '''Pokémon Team (Champion tournament)'''
Summary: Piers (Japanese: ネズ Nezu) is Spikemuth's gym leader. His gym is the only gym not built over a power spot, giving him the unique position of the only Galarian gym leader who does not use Dynamax Pokémon in battle. He hopes that, one day, his younger sister Marnie will take his position as Spikemuth's gym leader.

Name: Pig (Real World)
Summary: Domestic pigs are pigs raised for meat, leather, or simply as pets. Pigs that either escape or get released into the wild are known as feral pigs and regain their fur. These feral pigs are considered an invasive species and are often targeted by hunters.

Name: Pink (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: One of many NERDS, Pink lives in Harmony City. They are asked by Mr. Honeycutt to help save the city from having all its color drained, a request which they gladly follow.

Name: PKP Pecheneg machine gun
Summary: The PKP Pecheneg (Pulemyot Kalashnikova Pekhotny "Pecheneg", Russian: Печенег) is a Russian 7.62×54mmR general-purpose machine gun. It is a further development and modification of the PK machine gun. It is said to be more accurate than all its predecessors due to a heavier, non-removable, forced-air-cooling barrel with radial cooling ribs and a handle which eliminates the haze effect from hot gases and keeps the barrel cooler, making the weapon more reliable. Furthermore, the weapon is capable of having a telescopic sight or other sights mounted on it, which increases its accuracy and effective range.

Name: Placerias
Summary: Placerias (meaning 'broad body') is an extinct genus of dicynodonts that lived during the Carnian to the Norian age of the Triassic Period (230–220 million years ago). Placerias belongs to a group of dicynodonts called Kannemeyeriiformes, which was the last known group of dicynodonts before the taxon became extinct at the end of the Triassic.

Name: Plateosaurus
Summary: Plateosaurus is a genus of plateosaurid sauropodomorph dinosaur, informally referred to as "prosauropods." Much debate had been gone through as to creature's posture, more recent studies indicating that it stood bipedally with an erect gait. It had teeth similar to later sauropods and omnivorous animals such as iguanas,[1] and may have had a small portion of their diet comprised of carrion and small animals to supplement a predominantly herbivorous diet.[2] It lived throughout present day northern and central Europe around 227-204 million years ago, during the late Triassic, and was among the first large herbivorous dinosaurs.

Name: Plesiosaurus (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: A massive aquatic dinosaur, the plesiosaurus is a powerful beast that sailors might deal with in their voyages.

Name: Pliosaurus
Summary: Pliosaurus was a genus of aquatic reptiles that lived approximately 146 million years ago in Europe and South America. Also known as "Predator X", it primarily fed on large prey such as Ichthyosaurus and Plesiosaurus. Notably, Pliosaurus had a bite force of over 33,000 pounds per square inch, more than even the Tyrannosaurus rex.

Name: Plumeria
Key: '''By Herself''' | '''Pokémon Team (Akala Outskirts)''' | '''Pokémon Team (Route 15)''' | '''Pokémon Team (Title Defense)'''
Summary: Plumeria is an admin of Team Skull who seems to specialize in Poison-type Pokémon. Due to her actions she is considered a "sisterly figure" to the organization.

Name: Po-2
Summary: The Polikarpov Po-2 is a two-seated general purpose biplane developed by the Polikarpov Design Bureau primarily used as a training aircraft, but could serve other purposes such as ground attack and reconnaissance. Making its first flight in June 24, 1927, and entering service in 1929, it has the longest production run out of any Soviet aircraft, with over 20000 built.

Name: Poison Ivy (Post-Crisis)
Summary: Poison Ivy is an enemy of Batman. She is depicted as one of the world's most prominent eco-terrorists. She is obsessed with plants, botany, and environmentalism. She uses toxins from plants and her own bloodstream for her criminal activities, which are usually aimed at protecting the natural environment. Fellow villain Harley Quinn is her recurring partner-in-crime and possibly her only human friend.

Name: Polar Bear
Summary: The polar bear (Ursus maritimus) is a hypercarnivorous bear whose native range lies largely within the Arctic Circle,[1][2][3] encompassing the Arctic Ocean, its surrounding seas and surrounding land masses.[4][5] It is a large bear, approximately the same size as the omnivorous Kodiak bear (Ursus arctos middendorffi). A boar (adult male) weighs around 350–700 kg (772–1,543 lb), while a sow (adult female) is about half that size. Although it is the sister species of the brown bear, it has evolved to occupy a narrower ecological niche, with many body characteristics adapted for cold temperatures,[6] for moving across snow, ice and open water, and for hunting seals,[6][7][8] which make up most of its diet.[3] Although most polar bears are born on land,[9] they spend most of their time on the sea ice.[10] Their scientific name means "maritime bear" and derives from this fact.[2] Polar bears hunt their preferred food of seals from the edge of sea ice,[3] often living off fat reserves when no sea ice is present. Because of their dependence on the sea ice, polar bears are classified as marine mammals.[2]

Name: Polar Bear (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: One of the many bears that roam the lands, Polar Bears are found in colder climates. They are larger than the Brown Bear and sport a white coat of fur, allowing them to far in snowy plains.

Name: Poppy
Summary: Tier: 9-A | 4-B

Name: Portal Drake
Summary: Dwelling in the Underdark, the Portal Drake is a type of drake that has a variety with various magical abilities.

Name: Postosuchus
Summary: Postosuchus is a large terrestrial Pseudosuchian of the group Rauisuchidae. It's name mean "Crocodile of Post" named for the city in Texas near where it was found and the suffix "suchus" derived from the Greek word soukhos (σοῦχος), which means "crocodile." It was one of the apex predators of North America during the late Triassic. The two known species are Postosuchus kirkpatricki and Postosuchus alisonae.

Name: Preston Ramirez
Summary: Preston Ramirez is the main antagonist of Preston’s Hourglass, a 2023 mascot horror game by Dreadful Studios. The story follows a team of archaeologists exploring the Prestonian Catacombs, where they uncover an ancient time-manipulating artifact—“Preston’s Hourglass”. Activating it awakens Preston, an eldritch time demon who kills the entire team except one survivor. To escape, the survivor must collect eight spell pieces to seal Preston again. The game’s lore reveals Preston was once a scientist obsessed with time experiments, which caused widespread destruction in the 1970s. His obsession ruined his life and turned him into the monster buried beneath Prestonia, losing his wife in the process.

Name: Priestess Gut
Summary: Priestess Gut is the spiritual leader of the Absolute cult of goblinoids growing in the Shattered Sanctum, a former Selune temple-fort located in the Western Heartlands near the Emerald Grove. A spellcaster of some talent, and a gifted enough leader in the goblinoid sense (that is to say, a wretched bully and deceiver), Gut is a True Soul, one of the chosen few of the Absolute gifted with an Illithid tadpole that connects them to their "god".

Name: Prince Xizor
Summary: Xizor is a prominent antagonist in the Star Wars expanded universe. He was a Falleen Prince of House Sizhran and the leader of the powerful criminal organization Black Sun. Xizor was a ruthless competitor and charismatic public figure in high society with his headquarters in the city-planet Coruscant. Close to the Imperial Palace, but less splendid, was Xizor's Palace: his home outside Falleen. Following the Battle of Hoth, Xizor was considered one of the most influential beings in the galaxy, on par with Emperor Palpatine and Darth Vader, due to his exceptional wealth and influence through his criminal activities.

Name: Prisoner 13
Summary: Korda Gilntstone, better known as Prisoner 13 is one of the oldest criminals housed within the prison they're at. They are there for trying to take over a clan by force. Now in prison, they form a spy network where none of those who work for her know how she looks.

Name: Prometheus (Post-Crisis)
Summary: Prometheus is a twisted mirror version of Batman. His parents were hippies inspired by the Bonnie and Clyde movie to become criminals. Eventually, they got cornered by the police and gunned down in front of their son. On that night, he swore he would take his revenge on the system and kill as many forces of justice as he could. He traveled around the world, training and studying, preparing himself to the day he would emerge as Prometheus. On his adult years, he met a group of Tibetan monks who worshipped evil. After gaining their trust, they gave him a Cosmic Key, a gateway to the dimension formally known as the Phantom Zone. There, he built his base and crafted the tools he needed to fight the Justice League.

Name: Prosthesis
Summary: Prosthesis is the world's first purpose built, off-road racing mech, and the flagship machine in the inception of an entirely new human experience - mech racing.

Name: Proterosuchus
Summary: Proterosuchus is a genus of proterosuchid Archosauriform, a group distantly related to true archosaurs such as dinosaurs, pterosaurs, and crocodilians. This moderately sized reptile lived 252-250 million years ago amid the hostile conditions of the early Triassic,[1] following the Permian-Triassic Extinction, in the semi-arid environment that is present day South Africa.[2] It is known that it was a carnivore, but it is debated as to what lifestyle it led; it may have been either fully terrestrial or semi-aquatic, ambushing prey similar to modern crocodiles.

Name: Pseudodragon
Summary: Pseudodragon resembles a miniature red dragon, slightly smaller than a housecoat. It is red-brown in color rather than deep red. It has fine scales and sharp horns and teeth. Its tail is about twice as long as its body, barbed, and very flexible. Pseudodragons are tiny, playful members of the dragon family. A pseudodragon has a body about 1 foot long, with a 2 foot tail. It weighs about 7 pounds. A pseudo dragon can communicate telepathically and can also vocalize animal noises, such as a rasping purr (pleasure), a hiss (unpleasant surprise), a chirp (desire), or a growl (anger).

Name: Psylocke
Summary: A British mutant telepath born into a magical lineage, Elizabeth "Betsy" Braddock's life was bound for weirdness from birth. Though she utilized her telepathic talents for the government shortly before serving as the hero Captain Britain in her brother's stead, it was with the X-Men that Betsy found her true destiny and her greatest tragedies, under the name Psylocke.

Name: Pteranodon
Summary: The pteranodon is a flying reptile that lived in the Cretaceous. They have a wingspan of 18 feet, some specimens have wingspans of 7 meters.

Name: Pug
Summary: The pug is a breed of dog which was originally bred in China for companionship. It is a friendly dog, and is great for families and children.

Name: Puma Concolor
Summary: The cougar (Puma concolor), also commonly known as the puma, mountain lion, panther or catamount, is a large felid of the subfamily Felinae native to the Americas. Its range, from the Canadian Yukon to the southern Andes of South America, is the widest of any large wild terrestrial mammal in the Western Hemisphere. An adaptable, generalist species, the cougar is found in most American habitat types. It is the biggest cat in North America, and the second-heaviest cat in the New World after the jaguar. Secretive and largely solitary by nature, the cougar is properly considered both nocturnal and crepuscular, although daytime sightings do occur. The cougar is more closely related to smaller felines, including the domestic cat (subfamily Felinae), than to any species of subfamily Pantherinae, of which only the jaguar is native to the Americas.

Name: Punisher (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Francis "Frank" David Castle Sr. is a violent vigilante and former member of the United States Marine Corps, who had joined Cerberus Squad while he was serving in Afghanistan. Fearing he was slowly losing his honor under the command of Agent Orange, Castle returned to his family, only to lose them all during a brutal shooting. Castle became the Punisher, as he aimed to clean up New York City of crime by any means necessary. While seeking to avenge his own family's deaths, Castle came into conflict with Daredevil. Castle was soon arrested and, despite the efforts of Nelson and Murdock, was sentenced to life within prison. However, Castle was freed with the help of Wilson Fisk, and discovered the Blacksmith was the one who was responsible for his family's murder.

Name: Punisher (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Lt. Frank Castle returned home from duty only to see his wife and children murdered in front of him in cold blood by the Mafia. Unable to find justice by any fair means for them, Castle vowed to spend the rest of his life avenging them. Now equipped with state-of-the-art weapons, decades of combat experience, guerrilla and urban warfare techniques, as well as detective-like skills, he wages a one-man war against crime as the Punisher, a murderous vigilante that takes no prisoners, and comes at odds with both heroes and villains for his methods.

Name: Purple (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: One of the many residents of the city of Harmony, Purple is an acolyte wizard that worships the God of Knowledge Oghma. They are one of several adventurers that ultimately solve the city's energy crisis.

Name: Purple Worm
Summary: A powerful beast, the Purple Worm is a massive worm which tunnels in the ground in constant search of food, the tunnels it leaves behind are often used by other underground races as living places. In combat a Purple Worm simply tries to sting, bite and swallow its prey until it's dead.

Name: Purussaurus
Summary: Purussaurus is a giant caiman that lived 20.4 to 5.3 million years ago during the Miocene epoch. Purussaurus was once estimated to be 12.5 meters long and weighing in at 8.4 metric tons; however, these measurements were met with lots of scrutiny. More accurate measurements put Purussaurus' max length at 10.9 meters and its weight at 5.6 metric tons. These measurements of length, however, are uncertain as only skull fossils of the creature were found.

Name: Pyro (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Pyro is the mutant name of the terrorist St. John Allerdyce, a mutant extremist that was a member of The Brotherhood of Evil Mutants whose mission is to spread mutant superiority. Pyro originated from Sydney, Australia, where he was known as a famous journalist and popular novelist. Pyro developed his mutant powers, which gave him complete control over any flame and make it come to life. As part of The Brotherhood of Evil Mutants, Pyro was a recurring villain that fought against the X-Men and affiliates for years.

Name: Quaggoth
Summary: One of many races which inhabit the underdark, the Quaggoth is a savage creature which tears enemies apart with their claws and weapons. They often become Drow slaves in order to fight surface world elves.

Name: Quake (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Quake aka Daisy Johnson, formerly known as Skye (Born July 2, 1988), was a hacker working with the Rising Tide who was recruited by Phil Coulson to join his SHIELD team as a consultant before becoming an agent. After being exposed to Terrigen Mist, her dormant Inhuman abilities were activated and she was granted the power of vibration manipulation. She is the daughter of Calvin Zabo, a medical doctor who after losing his family became a violent and unstable villain, and Jiaying, an Inhuman with the power of life force absorption. Daisy was the first recruit and leader of the Secret Warriors, a SHIELD team comprised of superpowered (namely Inhuman) individuals. Daisy Johnson for a short time period assumed the role of the SHIELD Director before the mantle and title of Director was given to Alphonso Mackenzie.

Name: Quasit
Summary: Quasits are miniscule demons from the Abyss, and are known to be particularly insidious due to their lack of impressive physical might. Their small stature and cowardly nature makes them perfectly suited as familiars of malevolent spellcasters, or perhaps contacts with the agents of the Abyss. Though they hunger for power and influence as all demons do, they are unable to achieve it. Quasits are known to adapt guerrilla tactics when they do have to take up combat, preferring to assault an enemy from an invisible state and then run before they're aware of what happened.

Name: Question (Renee Montoya) (Post-Crisis)
Summary: Renee Montoya was a longtime detective for the GCPD. Events surrounding the murder of her partner, Crispus Allen, led her to quit the GCPD, and she began spiraling downwards. However, the original Question, who was dying of lung cancer, chose to make Renee his successor. So, after he died, Renee picked up the mantle of The Question.

Name: Quetzalcoatlus
Summary: Quetzalcoatlus was a pterosaur from the Late Cretaceous that lived mainly throughout the southern United States and was one of the largest known pterosaurs (Hatzegopteryx was likely heavier). Furthermore, it was one of the very last pterosaurs to exist before their extinction in the Cretaceous–Paleogene extinction event, 66 million years ago.

Name: Quipper (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: A carnivorous fish, the Quipper is able to adapt to any aquatic environment. They often go in swarms which go berserk whenever they draw a victim's blood.

Name: Quth-Maren
Summary: Quth-Maren are foul undead created by clerics of Kiaransalee, the Drow godess of murder[1]. They are the result of multiple necromantic rituals performed on a body flayed of all flesh it once possessed. It is composed solely of muscles attached to bone. They serve in the armies of Irae T'sarran as fodder infantry.

Name: Ra's Al Ghul (Post-Crisis)
Summary: Ra's Al Ghul was born to a nomadic tribe hundreds of years ago in Arabia. Always being interested in science, he left his tribe and worked for many years as a physician, marrying the daughter of the man he apprenticed under. When the prince of the city fell sick, the king asked Ra's for his aid in curing him. Using his knowledge of science and mysticism Ra's invented the first Lazarus Pit, using it to cure the prince. However, when the prince came out of the pit he was overtaken in a vengeful rage, killing Ra's wife. The King was unable to believe his son would kill someone and sentenced Ra's for the crime. Ra's would escape, rejoin his old tribe and proceed to lay waste to the city, beginning his reign as the Demon's Head.

Name: Rabbit (Real World)
Summary: Rabbits are a common prey animal and, in places where they are introduced, one of the most infamous invasive species on Earth. Rabbits are herbivorous, although a source from 1910 has stated that rabbits have eaten snails. Rabbits were raised as pets, livestock animals, and laboratory animals. European rabbits, which are the most common rabbit, weigh from 1.2 to 2 kg.

Name: Rac Shade (Post-Flashpoint)
Summary: Where dark falls dark despite the light, I touch. I smell. I breathe. I beat. Running off to the great blue. Our hearts, now lost, just fade away.

Name: Rag Doll (Peter Merkel)
Summary: Peter Merkel, known also as Rag Doll was once an enemy of Jay Garrick. When he got older he became a cult leader which lead to his first time. After being revived he joined the Injustice Society where after trying to bail out from a fight he met his final demise.

Name: Rahab
Summary: One of Kain's seven lieutenants, Rahab ruled over the Rahabim clan, serving Kain for centuries until his departure from that time. Eventually, they managed to overcome the vampiric weakness to water, but degenerated across the following centuries, and were ultimately slain by Raziel in his quest for revenge.

Name: Raihan
Summary: Raihan is the Gym Leader of Hammerlocke Stadium. He specializes in Dragon-type Pokémon and gives the Dragon Badge to Trainers who defeat him. He's also well-known for utilizing weather tactics in his battles, and is one of the few Gym Leaders who do not use a team filled with the same type of Pokemon. He is regarded as one of the strongest Pokemon Trainers in the world, and is rumored to be capable of beating other Champions. He is seen as a rival to Leon, and constantly strives to defeat him.

Name: Rakshasa (Dungeons and Dragons)
Key: '''Rakshasa''' | '''Greater Rakshasa''' | '''Ak'chazar''' | '''Naztharune''' | '''Dread Knight''' | '''Lord of Dust''' | '''Zakya''' | '''Half-Dragon Rakshasa''' | '''Naityan Rakshasa''' | '''Overlord'''
Summary: Rakshasa are fiendish creatures born from the Lower Planes with the appearance of humanoid tigers of proud stature, distinguishable from similar creatures such as Weretigers by their hands, which can bend both backwards and forwards. Extravagant and conniving by nature, Rakshasa plague all the Planes with their manipulations, constantly enacting plots to achieve greater power. They serve countless masters- their own Rajahs, demon lords[1], yugoloths, night hags, and even the mightiest of devils. As manipulators and masterminds, the Rakshasa ply their trade from their luxuriously decorated palaces, subtly tipping the scales in planar and political conflicts as it suited their wants.

Name: Razanandrongobe
Summary: Razanandrongobe is a genus of large notosuchian crocodylomorph that lived in Madagascar during the Bathonian stage of the Middle Jurassic, about 167.7–164.7 million years ago, represented by the single species Razanandrongobe sakalavae. Its generic name comes from the Malagasy words "razana-" (ancestor), "androngo-" (lizard), and "-be" (large), thus it translates to "ancestor of the large lizard"; the species name "sakalavae" is latin for "of Sakalava," the ethnic group of the Mahajanga region where the creature was discovered.[1] At an estimated 7 meters in length, 1.6 meters in height at the hip, and 800-1,000 kg in mass,[2] it was likely an apex predator in its ecosystem.

Name: Reaper (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Pantu Hurageb was a member of the Mutant Liberation Front under the alias of Reaper, where he clashed repeatedly with the New Mutants and X-Force, often finding himself pitted against Shatterstar, losing his limbs in their confrontations. He has also temporarily been a reluctant hero as a member of the Exiles, when he was unwittingly transported to the Ultraverse.

Name: Reaver (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: Reavers[1] are skeletal warriors inevitably mounted on skeletal horses that populate the undead city of Cavitius, the domain of Vecna in Ravenloft. These warriors are the proud elite of the city, and as their god's chosen favorites, they are made nigh-untouchable by the denizens within. They seek to end fights that break out in the city, but are solely interested in ending fights that include undead folk- thus fights exclusively between the living mean little to them[2].

Name: Red (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: Living in the nearby forest around Harmony City, Red is one of the Nerds tasked to save the city from its color shortages.

Name: Red (Pokémon)
Key: '''By Himself''' | '''Gen 1 Team (Beginnings)''' | '''Gen 1 Team (Early Game)''' | '''Gen 1 Team (Mid Game)''' | '''Gen 1 Team (End Game)''' | '''Gen 2 Team''' | '''Gen 7 Teams'''
Summary: Red is the enigmatic and silent protagonist of Pokemon Red/Blue/Yellow and its remakes Pokémon FireRed/LeafGreen, as well as the hidden final boss of Pokémon Gold/Silver/Crystal and its remakes Pokemon HeartGold/SoulSilver.

Name: Red Dragon (Dungeons and Dragons)
Key: '''Wyrmling to Young''' | '''Juvenile to Mature Adult''' | '''Old to Ancient''' | '''Wyrms and Great Wyrms'''
Summary: And belching fire, and began to lunge down

Name: Red Fox
Summary: Red Fox (Vulpes vulpes), also called common fox, is the largest of the true foxes. Being present across the entire Northern Hemisphere including most of North America, Europe and Asia, plus parts of North Africa. Apart from its large size, the red fox is distinguished from other fox species by its ability to adapt quickly to new environments and has the largest natural distribution of any land mammal except human beings.

Name: Red Hood (Post-Crisis)
Key: '''Pre-Death in the Family''' | '''Post-Death in the Family'''
Summary: Robin: Batman, stop…! Stop! You’ll kill him! Batman: He took her from me, Robin… every woman I love, something always takes her from me… Robin: You lost the Catwoman, yeah… but you caught the Joker… and you saved the Bensons… saved their lives… that’s something.[2]

Name: Red Kangaroo
Summary: The red kangaroo (Macropus rufus) is a species of marsupial native to Australia. It is the largest living marsupial, and the largest land-dwelling mammal in Australia. They are notable for their powerful jumps and kicks, which can deliver over 850 PSI of pressure.

Name: Red Noob and Blue Noob
Summary: Blue: And we'll crush you!

Name: Red Panda
Summary: The red panda (Ailurus fulgens), also known as the lesser panda, is a small mammal native to the eastern Himalayas and southwestern China. The red panda's place on the evolutionary tree has been debated, but modern genetic evidence places it in close affinity with raccoons, weasels, and skunks. It is not closely related to the giant panda, which is a bear, though both possess elongated wrist bones or "false thumbs" used for grasping bamboo.

Name: Red Robin (Post-Crisis)
Summary: Tim Drake (also known as Tim Wayne) is a fictional comic book superhero from the DC Comics universe. As the third Robin in the Batman comics, he served as Batman's sidekick, and he is a superhero in his own right. He currently uses the superhero identity of Red Robin.

Name: Red Skull (Golden Age)
Summary: The Red Skull was a Nazi terrorist and one of the earliest and most dangerous foes of Captain America, who had constantly foiled his attempts to destabilize the U.S.A. with elaborate plans.

Name: Red Skull (Marvel Comics)
Summary: When Johann Schmidt was born, his mother Martha died while giving birth to him, leading to his father Hermann attempting to kill him and eventually killing himself. Left an orphan on the streets of early Nazi Germany, Johann turned to a life of theft until he began working as a bellhop in his late teens. During this time he ended up rescuing Germany's then-leader Adolf Hitler from an assassination attempt, who was so impressed with the hatred of mankind he could see within Schmidt that he began to personally train him into a "perfect soldier". Upon his training's completion, he had become the Red Skull, and turned into the archenemy of Captain America.

Name: Red Slaad
Summary: The most common and weakest of the Slaad kind, the Red Slaad is none the less a fearsome foe to face. They are naturally resistant to magic and various damage types, and each claw swipe of theirs is able to infect a creature with its offspring. If a person dies to the disease a Blue Slaad will born from it.

Name: Remington ACR
Summary: The Remington ACR (Adaptive Combat Rifle) is a modular assault rifle designed by Magpul Industries of Austin, Texas, and known as the Masada.

Name: Remington Model 870
Summary: The Remington Model 870 is a pump-action shotgun manufactured by Remington Arms Company, LLC. It is one of the most well-known shotguns in the world, widely used by the public for shooting sports, hunting and self-defense, as well as by numerous law enforcement and military organizations worldwide.

Name: Remorhaz
Summary: Native to frozen lands, the Remorhaz spends all its days hunting prey. They are a millipede like creature that emits incredible heat from its body, using it burrow through ice without any issue.

Name: Rheinmetall 120mm Main Gun
Summary: The Rheinmetall 120mm gun is a smoothbore tank gun designed and produced by the West German Rheinmetall-DeTec AG company, developed in response to Soviet advances in armor technology and development of new armored threats. Production began in 1974, with the first version of the gun, known as the L/44 as it was 44 calibers long, used on the German Leopard 2 tank and soon produced under license for the American M1A1 Abrams and other tanks. The 120-millimeter gun has a length of 5.28 meters, and the gun system weighs approximately 3,317 kilograms. A variety of ammunition has been developed for use by tanks with guns based on Rheinmetall's original L/44 design. This includes a series of kinetic energy penetrators, such as the American M829 series, and high explosive anti-tank warhead warheads. Recent ammunition includes a wide range of new anti-personnel rounds and demolition munitions, giving tanks armed with the L/44 and its derivatives greater versatility on the modern battlefield. The LAHAT, developed in Israel, is a gun-launched missile which has received interest from Germany and other Leopard 2 users, and is designed to defeat both land armor and combat helicopters. The Israelis also introduced a new anti-personnel munition which limits collateral damage by controlling the fragmentation of the projectile.

Name: Riddler (Post-Crisis)
Summary: One of the Dark Knight's most infamous villains, Edward Nygma enjoys flaunting his intellectual superiority by conducting crimes and leaving clues for Batman to piece together. While this habit constantly leads to the aptly named Riddler failing in his criminal endeavors, his puzzle-problem actually stems not only from his own narcissism and ego, but also from a deep-seeded psychological compulsion. Because of this, the Riddler often finds himself a resident of Arkham Asylum following his inevitable capture.

Name: Rika Furude
Key: '''Piece Rika''' | '''Higher Layer/World of Gods/Sea of Fragments Rika and Frederica'''
Summary: nan

Name: Ripsaw (light tank)
Summary: The Ripsaw is a developmental unmanned light tank designed and built by Howe & Howe Technologies for evaluation by the United States Army. The Howe brothers started the Ripsaw as a small family project in 2000, and introduced it at a Dallas vehicle show in 2001.

Name: Risque (Marvel Comics)
Summary: After her Cuban father, and Seminole mother divorced when she was twelve, Gloria Muñoz moved out with her mother and lived with her until she was 16. Having discovered her mutant powers, she left to live on her own and spent some time in Miami. During this time, Sledge helped her out of some trouble, and she promised to aid him in the future, a favor which was eventually repaid when she was tasked with bringing him the mutant Warpath.

Name: Riven
Summary: Once a swordmaster in the warhosts of Noxus, Riven is an expatriate in a land she previously tried to conquer. She rose through the ranks on the strength of her conviction and her brutal efficiency, and was rewarded with a legendary runic blade—however, on the Ionian front, Riven’s faith in her homeland was tested and ultimately broken. Having severed all ties to the empire, she now wanders with her shattered sword, seeking to atone for a past she cannot fully recall.

Name: Robin (Damian Wayne)
Summary: Damian Wayne is the biological son of Bruce Wayne and Talia al Ghul. His existence was hidden from his father up to when he was about ten years old, during which time he was trained by the League of Assassins in a variety of disciplines to make him an extremely efficient killer. Damian was then sent to his father to disrupt his work as a vigilante (a task he completed with ease thanks to his blood relations and lack of social skills), but later grew to prefer his role as the son of Bruce Wayne and his time as Robin over his position as the al Ghul heir.

Name: Robosaurus
Summary: Robosaurus is a 42-foot (12 m) transforming dinosaur robot created by inventor Doug Malewicki in 1989 and is now owned and operated by Monster Robots, Inc. Robosaurus is modeled after Transformers toys with the driver sitting in the head of the robot, and the ability to transform from a 48-foot semi trailer into a mechanical Tyrannosaurus rex (Real World).

Name: Roc
Summary: A massive bird, the Roc is the supreme ruler of the skies in the mountains. They only go against large targets such as elephants, with the Roc being able to lift them with one leg. Sometimes Cloud and Storm Giants tame Rocs and use them as a deadly asset.

Name: Rock Gnome
Summary: The most common of the Gnomes, the Rock Gnomes are found all across the surface world. They are inventive and rather intelligent, using it to construct various devices for fun. They are also considered superb gunsmiths.

Name: Roper
Summary: The larva form, also known as a Piercer is an ambush predator in underground places that uses it camouflage in order to let itself drop upon prey whenever it senses someone below it. The adult form, also known as a Roper meanwhile is a far more active hunter, which while still using stealth, also employs tentacles it tosses at enemies in order to pull them to its maw.

Name: Rot Grub
Summary: The Rot Grub is a parasite that will burrow into any sort of organic material in order to eat it, with a blood warm target they'll go to their heart in order to lay their eggs there.

Name: Rothé
Summary: A large mammal, the Rothé is a sturdy beast which can be found in the mountains, it also has more magical variants like the Deep Rothé which can emit magical lights or the Ghost Rothé which can cast Silence and Jump in order to aid itself.

Name: Rotom-Dex
Summary: The Generation VI Pokédex was a major success, but even it had to finish its product lifespan eventually. Allowed the opportunity to create the next model, Clemont invented a newer, cutting-edge line of Pokédex that could even house a Rotom to assist its user. The results went way beyond expectations; not only is the Pokédex itself much more efficient and containing brand new features, with its Rotom assimilated, it is as much greater than the ordinary Pokédex as Rotom-Wash is to a normal washing machine, Rotom-Fan is to a normal electric fan, and so on. As it is inside what is essentially the greatest Pokémon encyclopedia of the modern age, it easily has the most comprehensive knowledgebase of anything that mankind has ever created.

Name: Roxanne (Pokémon)
Key: '''By Herself''' | '''Gym Pokémon''' | '''Rematch Teams''' | '''Strongest Hoenn Team''' | '''Pokémon World Tournament'''
Summary: Roxanne is the Rustboro City Gym Leader, and is the first Gym Leader that a novice Trainer in the Hoenn region must battle in order to challenge the Elite Four. Roxanne became a Gym Leader to apply what she learned in the Pokémon Trainer School in practice, and thus enjoys using what she’s learned in her studies in battle, and loves even more to see how other people have formed their own strategy. When Brendan challenged her for the Stone Badge, she wasted no time urging him to show her how he battles, and with which Pokémon.

Name: RPG-7
Summary: The RPG-7 (Russian: РПГ-7) is a portable, reusable, unguided, shoulder-launched, anti-tank rocket-propelled grenade launcher. Originally the RPG-7 (Ручной Противотанковый Гранатомёт – Ruchnoy Protivotankovyi Granatomyot – Hand-held anti-tank grenade launcher) and its predecessor, the RPG-2, were designed by the Soviet Union; it is now manufactured by the Russian company Bazalt. The weapon has the GRAU index (Russian armed forces index) 6G3.

Name: Rug of Smothering
Summary: The Rug of Smothering is a magical construct created by powerful spell-casters. Much like other constructs, such as Animated Armor or the Flying Sword, it is an animated object.

Name: Rumble
Summary: Rumble is a young inventor with a temper. Using nothing more than his own two hands and a heap of scrap, the feisty yordle constructed a colossal mech suit outfitted with an arsenal of electrified harpoons and incendiary rockets. Though others may scoff and sneer at his junkyard creations, Rumble doesn't mind—after all, he's the one with the flamespitter.

Name: Russian (Marvel Comics)
Summary: The Russian, real name Ivan Vassilovitch Dragovsky is a supervillain in Marvel Comics. He is an opponent of the antihero known as The Punisher - originally a fairly traditional Punisher foe (having little in the way of superhuman powers) he evolved into a more powerful comic book super villain following his resurrection by a paramilitary group.

Name: Rust Monster
Summary: Rust Monsters are iconic creatures of the Dungeons and Dragons universe, and are the renowned antithesis to most fighter classes due to their ability to destroy metal on contact. Despite their fairly large size (being the size of a pony), they rarely deal in combat aside from their hunger for metal.

Name: Rylkar
Summary: Rylkar are rats that have evolved during heir time in the Underdark. They are known to enter an area, consume everything within it, and reproduce using all resources exponentially- thus leaving a rat-infested barrens. Rylkars bear a strong tie to flame, and view it as raw energy, something they can use to reproduce their thousands of young.

Name: Ryouga
Summary: Ryouga (Japanese: リョウガ) is the main character of the Pokémon RéBURST manga. Hot-blooded, naive, and not particularly worldly, he is able to gain the powers of a Pokémon with the aid of a Burst Heart. The one thing he hates most is the word "impossible", mentioning it riles him up into accomplishing what he was deemed incapable of doing.

Name: Ryuki
Key: '''By Himself''' | '''Pokémon Team (Malie City)''' | '''Post-Game and Title Defense Team'''
Summary: Ryuki (Japanese: リュウキ Ryūki) is a non-player character in the Generation VII games, Pokémon Sun and Moon. He is a Pokémon Trainer who specializes in Dragon-type Pokémon.

Name: Saber-Toothed Tiger (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: Smilodon, or better known as Saber-Toothed Tiger is a large prehistoric cat which lived in icy plains and hills.They favor ambushes as their main way to get food, with their long fangs being especially deadly.

Name: Sabrina (Pokémon)
Summary: Sabrina is one of the eight gym leaders of Kanto, and the first psychic gym leader. She is the gym leader of Saffron City. Unlike many humans in the Pokemon universe, she has actual powers.

Name: Sahuagin
Summary: Utterly vile and ruthless, the Sahuagin, also known as Sea Devils, terrorize the sea and beaches alike. They hold incredible hate for sea elves, going of their way to destroy nearby communities of them.

Name: Sai (Weapon)
Summary: The Sai is a traditional weapon of Okinawa.

Name: Sailsnake
Summary: The Sailsnake is a mutated form of the viper snake which has fins it uses to glide from place to place. Their size varies from 4 to 6 feet long and they can weigh up to 50 pound, but larger specimens can be bred if one desires so.

Name: Sako TRG sniper rifle
Summary: The Sako TRG is a bolt-action sniper rifle line designed and manufactured by the Finnish firearms manufacturer, SAKO of Riihimäki. It is used by many units and armies around the world. The sniper rifles are normally fitted with muzzle brakes to reduce recoil, jump, and flash. The Sako factory TRG muzzle brakes vent sideways and are detachable. Generally, TRGs are outfitted with variable telescopic sights for operators demanding more flexibility to shoot at varying ranges, or when a wide field of view is required. Besides its military role, it is increasingly used by hunters and civilian long-range shooting enthusiasts.

Name: Sakuyamon
Summary: Tier: Unknown | 9-B | High 8-C | At least High 8-C | 6-C | At least 4-C, Possibly 3-C | At least 3-C, Possibly higher | At least 3-C, Possibly higher

Name: Salamander (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: Native to the Realm of Fire, the Salamander are a hierarchical race which roams the land. The weaker Salamanders are often enslaved by other races, while the Noble are among some of the strongest inhabitants of the realm.

Name: Salmon Shark
Summary: The salmon shark (Lamna ditropis) is a species of mackerel shark endemic to subtropical waters worldwide. It is one of the fastest sharks in the world, and is one of the few known homeothermatic fish.

Name: Saltwater Crocodile
Summary: The Saltwater Crocodile is the largest of all living reptiles, as well as the largest terrestrial and riparian predator in the world.

Name: Samurai (Totally Accurate Battle Simulator)
Summary: The Samurai is a unit from the game Totally Accurate Battle Simulator, first introduced with the Dynasty faction, the Samurai is capable of deflecting multiple different projectiles in the game, making it a very useful troop in battle.

Name: Sand Tiger Shark
Summary: Sand Tiger Sharks (Carcharhinus leucas), also known as the grey nurse shark, are a species of mackerel shark found worldwide in temperate and subtropical ocean waters. They are a relatively placid and slow-moving shark, with no confirmed human fatalities, and can reach up to 3.2 meters in length and 159 kg in weight. Notably, they are widely kept in public aquariums due to their tolerance for captivity.

Name: Santánico Pandemonium
Summary: Santánico Pandemonium, formerly Esmeralda or Kisa, is a fictional character in the From Dusk till Dawn media franchise. She is the primary Queen Vampire/Culebra of the "Titty Twister", a strip club in the middle of a desolate part of Mexico.

Name: Sarcosuchus (Real World)
Summary: Sarcosuchus is an extinct genus of crocodyliform and a distant relative of living crocodylians. It lived 112 million years ago in Africa and South America during the Early Cretaceous period. It was much larger than the modern Saltwater Crocodile, weighing up to 4.3 metric tons.

Name: Satana Hellstrom (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Black Cat: Should we take him to the, I dunno, magic cops? Satana: No. That's not how this works. The penalty for upsetting the cart-- and pissing me off-- is stiff and immediate.

Name: Satyr (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: Half man and half goat in appearance, the Satyr is an all male fey creature that roams the Forgotten Lands. They are more concerned with courting women than anything else, with them most of the time not even having weapons on.

Name: Sauropelta
Summary: Sauropelta is a genus of armored dinosaur, belonging to the family of ankylosaurs known as Nodosaurids, of which it is one of the earliest best described. It's name means "lizard shield," due to its armored hide covered in osteoderms. It lived in North America around 108.5 million years ago, during the early Cretaceous, with fossils predominantly found in the Cloverly Formation in Montana, Wyoming, and possibly Utah. It had a narrow beak much like other Nodosaurids, indicating it was a browser,[1] inhabiting floodplains in the place and time it lived.[2]

Name: Sauroposeidon
Summary: Sauroposeidon is a genus of sauropod rivaling the Argentinosaurus in size (excluding weight), as well as being both taller and heavier than the Giraffatitan. It existed towards the end of the Early Cretaceous Period and it was the last known North American sauropod prior to an absence of the group on the continent for roughly 40 million years that ended with the appearance of Alamosaurus during the Maastrichtian (End of the Late Cretaceous Period).

Name: Sawn-Off Shotgun
Summary: Sawn-Off Shotgun A sawed-off shotgun (US, CAN) also called a sawn-off shotgun (UK, IRL, AU, NZ) and a short-barreled shotgun (SBS) (U.S. legislative terminology), is a type of shotgun with a shorter gun barrel—typically under 18 inches—and often a shortened or absent stock. Despite the colloquial term, barrels do not, strictly speaking, have to be shortened with a saw. Barrels can be manufactured at shorter lengths as an alternative to traditional, longer barrels. This makes them easier to transport due to their smaller profile and lighter weight. The design also makes the weapon easy to maneuver in cramped spaces, a feature sought by military close quarters combat units, law enforcement SWAT team users, and home defense purposes. As a result of the shorter barrel length, any sawed-off shotgun with a magazine tube will have its capacity reduced.

Name: Scarecrow (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: A type of Golem, a Scarecrow is made via binding an evil soul to a regular scarecrow which gives it supernatural abilities like a gaze that can strike fear into people.

Name: Scarecrow (Post-Crisis)
Summary: Jonathan Crane was abused by both peers and family alike as a child due to his unusually slender appearance. With this making him grow resentful to all around him, he soon developed an obsession with fear and phobias, getting revenge on everyone who ridiculed him through lethal frights. As an adult, Jonathan becomes a psychologist for Arkham Asylum, where he performs fear-inducing experiments onto the inmates, and he eventually combines a scarecrow suit based off of an incident in his childhood with a special chemical gas he developed to become the criminal Scarecrow.

Name: Scarlet Witch (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Wanda: You took everything from me! Thanos: I don't even know who you are. Wanda: You will.

Name: Scientist Supreme (Andrew Forson)
Summary: Andrew Forson is an A.I.M. scientist who has served as its Scientist Supreme in the past. A manipulative yet driven personality, he led A.I.M. initially as it went public, and was able to use his charisma and leadership to form the new High Council of A.I.M. He was eventually ousted from his position by Sunspot, and has remained a prominent leader within the now-fractured organization.

Name: Scissors
Summary: Scissors are tools used for cutting objects. They rely on 2 blades with a wedge in the middle, and use at least 2 fingers to get through the handle of itself to use it. Designs and uses vary from cutting thin materials like cloth and paper to cutting through chicken bone. The word shears are used to describe tools of the same kind, but larger.[1]

Name: Screwball (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Screwball is a self-proclaimed performance artist, who livestreams her crimes to the internet for fame and attention. Possessing incredible parkour skills, she has been a frequent foe to Spider-Man.

Name: Scutosaurus
Summary: Scutosaurus is a genus of pareiasaur parareptiles, the name of which means "shield lizard." This herbivorous anapsid reptile was among the first large terrestrial animals, reaching well over one ton. It differed from other reptiles in that it had its legs under its body to support its mass.[1] It lived in arid and semi-arid plains across European Russia during the late Permian,[2] around 259.1–251.9 million years ago. Among many other creatures, it would perish during the Permian-Triassic Extinction event.

Name: Sea Hag (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: Sea Hags are horrific appearing fey creatures often found around shorelines (as their name implies). Twisted and changed by the oceans they live in, they are considered the ugliest of all hags, even by other hags with whom they share sisterhood. As such, she is spiteful, and easily enraged- if something beautiful causes hope, she intends to counter it with fear. If something beautiful can improve life, she would instead unleash death.

Name: Sea Otter (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: One of the unique animals of Frostfell the Otter is a medium sized aquatic animal.

Name: Sea Spawn
Summary: Krakens, Sea Hags and Dragon Turtles are some of the creatures which can create Sea Spawns.

Name: Sejuani
Summary: Sejuani is the brutal, unforgiving Warmother of the Winter’s Claw, one of the most feared tribes of the Freljord. Her people’s survival is a constant, desperate battle against the elements, forcing them to raid Noxians, Demacians, and Avarosans alike to survive the harsh winters. Sejuani herself spearheads the most dangerous of these attacks from the saddle of her drüvask boar Bristle, using her True Ice flail to freeze and shatter her enemies.

Name: Selphie Tilmitt (Kingdom Hearts)
Summary: Selphie Tilmitt is a minor character in the Kingdom Hearts series, originally from Final Fantasy X. She is one of the residents living in Destiny Islands and is part of a trio including Tidus and Wakka. In Sora's Dive to the Heart, She appears in the Destiny Islands area along with Wakka and Tidus. She asks Sora "What is most important to you?" Later, Selphie talks to Sora about the legends of mysterious effects the paopu fruit has on people. Sora can also challenge her to a duel. Selphie's fate after the Destiny Islands's destruction is unknown, but she reappears on the island once Sora defeats Ansem and the worlds are restored.

Name: Serag Kull
Summary: Cruel and sly, captain Serag Kull is a prime example of all that is wrong with the Red Plumes. A well connected man, he uses his position to get away with beating people senseless and extorting local merchants.

Name: Serval
Summary: The serval (Leptailurus serval) is a wild cat native to Africa. It is widespread in sub-Saharan countries, except rainforest regions. Across its range, it occurs in protected areas, and hunting it is either prohibited or regulated in range countries.

Name: Sewerm
Summary: The Sewerm is a relatively big aquatic snake that measures up to 2.4 m, this snake has also adapted to live in swamps and sewers hence its name but its most noteworthy ability is the oil it secrets which can numb one's sense of touch. Due to this oil the Sewerm is sought up by doctors in order to use the oil as a pain killer.

Name: Shades (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Hernan Enrique Salazar Alvarez, also known as Shades, is a criminal and member of the Rivals, before being sent to Seagate Penitentiary where he worked for Albert Rackham, organizing illegal prison fights. Once released from Seagate, Shades was recruited by Diamondback and was sent to Harlem to watch over the criminal operations of Cottonmouth, which put him back into conflict with Luke Cage, while also watching the rise of Mariah Dillard, in the wake of Cottonmouth's death. As Diamondback arrived into Harlem to kill Cage, Shades stayed by his side although his constant questioning of his employer eventually made him his target, forcing him to side with Dillard and then betray Diamondback in order to save his own life.

Name: Shadow (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: An enemy of the living that lurks in the darkness, the Shadow is a menacing foe to face in combat. As their name implies, they're animated shadows of dead people. Their origins are shrouded in mystery however one thing is for certain, that being that their touch is deadly. Their touch siphons life and strength from those unlucky enough to be hit by it, and if one dies from this their shadow becomes a new Shadow monster.

Name: Shadowcat
Summary: Katherine Anne "Kitty" Pryde is a fictional character and superhero that appears in comic books published by Marvel Comics. The character first appeared in Uncanny X-Men #129 (January 1980) and was co-created by writer-artist John Byrne and Chris Claremont.

Name: Shambling Mound
Summary: A Shambling Mound (also referred to as a Shambler) is a large plant beast that is composed of a mass of dead vegetation and corpses the Shambler has clung onto itself throughout its life. A predator, the Shambling Mound lives in the swamps and forests, using its appearance to blend in with its surroundings before ambushing its prey and engulfing it into its body, proceeding to crush the prey until it can be absorbed.

Name: Shang-Chi (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Xu Shang-Chi (Chinese: 徐尚氣) is the son of Xu Wenwu, the founder of the Ten Rings. Having been trained by the organization since childhood, he has become a master martial artist with skills that are unsurpassed by many.

Name: Shang-Chi (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Born to the fearsome Fu Manchu, Shang-Chi was trained to be a living weapon to serve under Si-Fan, becoming one of the greatest martial artists in the world. However, during his first assignment, he came to know of his father's true identity as an international criminal mastermind, and defected soon afterwards. He has fought against the tyranny of his father ever since, and continues to fight for the safety of those around him.

Name: Sharon Carter (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Sharon Carter is the great-niece of S.H.I.E.L.D. co-founder Peggy Carter, and became a member of the agency herself. Sharon would be assigned by Nick Fury to monitor Steve Rogers in the apartment he lived in, going by the alias Kate. When the infiltration of HYDRA within S.H.I.E.L.D. was revealed, Sharon participated in the resulting shootout. After S.H.I.E.L.D fell, Sharon would join the CIA, where she would be involved in the investigation of the bombing of the Vienna International Center while secretly helping Steve Rogers and Sam Wilson protect Bucky Barnes, who had been framed for the bombing.

Name: Shastasaurus
Summary: Shastasaurus ("Mount Shasta lizard") is an extinct genus of ichthyosaur from the Late Triassic. Specimens have been found in the United States, Canada, and China.

Name: Shiba Inu
Summary: The Shiba Inu is a small, Japanese dog, originally bred for hunting small game. They nearly went extinct during World War 2, but since then, they have become very popular as a pet. Shibas are also the number one companion dog in Japan.

Name: Shield Guardian
Summary: Created by wizards to serve as personal bodyguards, the Shield Guardian is a fearsome foe for those trying to attack its master.

Name: Shinobu Kawasaki
Summary: Shinobu Kawasaki is a combatant in the Mega Fight Tournament, seeking to win the tournament to get back at Tamaki Shindou for her previous defeat.

Name: Shocker (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Herman Schultz is a former salvage worker who had become a professional criminal and one of the key members of Adrian Toomes' Crew who had sold alien-human hybrid weaponry created by the Tinkerer. As Toomes had murdered his former crewmate Jackson Brice, who had used a modified gauntlet occasionally under the alias of Shocker, Toomes passed the gauntlet down to Schultz and then appointed him as the new Shocker. With his new title and power of the gauntlet, Schultz continued to aid Toomes with fighting Spider-Man's attempts to stop all their black market arms deals, eventually resulting in the Shocker being defeated during a fight and arrested. (Marvel Cinematic Universe Wiki)

Name: Shocker Lizard
Summary: The Shocker Lizard is small reptile while is able to produce none lethal shocks on its own but in groups their electricty becomes quite dangerous.

Name: Shuri (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Shuri is the princess of Wakanda and sister of its king, T'Challa, the Black Panther. Leader of the Wakandan Design Group, she is responsible for the invention of Wakanda's most recent technology and her brother's costume, later helping him retake the Wakandan throne from Erik Killmonger.

Name: Siffrin
Summary: This profile contains major spoilers for the entirety of In Stars And Time. It is highly suggested that you fully complete the game before reading this profile.

Name: SIG Sauer P226
Summary: The SIG Sauer P226 is a full-sized, service-type pistol made by SIG Sauer. This model is sold with a choice of four chambers to choose from: the 9×19mm Parabellum, .40 S&W, .357 SIG, or .22 Long Rifle. It has essentially the same basic design as the SIG Sauer P220, but is developed to use higher capacity, double stack magazines in place of the single stack magazines of the P220. The P226 itself has spawned further sub-variants; the P228 and P229 are both compact versions of the double stack P226 design. The SIG Sauer P226 and its variants are in service with numerous law enforcement and military organizations worldwide

Name: SIG Sauer P320
Summary: The SIG Sauer P320 is a modular semi-automatic pistol made by SIG Sauer, Inc. of Exeter, New Hampshire, and SIG Sauer GmbH of Eckernförde, Germany. It is a further development of the SIG Sauer P250, utilizing a striker-fired mechanism in lieu of a double action only hammer system. The P320 can be chambered in 9×19mm Parabellum, .357 SIG, .40 S&W and .45 ACP, and can be easily converted from one caliber to another—a change from .357 SIG to .40 S&W requires only a barrel change; a change between 9mm to .357 SIG or .40 S&W and vice versa are accomplished using a caliber exchange kit.

Name: Silver (Pokémon)
Key: '''By Himself''' | '''Pokémon Team (Cherrygrove City)''' | '''Pokémon Team (Azalea Town)''' | '''Pokémon Team (Burned Tower)''' | '''Pokémon Team (Goldenrod Tunnel)''' | '''Pokémon Team (Victory Road)''' | '''Pokémon Team (Post-Game Battles)'''
Summary: Silver (Japanese: シルバー Silver) is one of the main characters and the rival of Pokémon Gold, Silver, Crystal and Pokémon HeartGold and SoulSilver. He is the son of Team Rocket Boss Giovanni that fought many times with Ethan, Kris or Lyra.

Name: Silver Sable (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Daughter of a famed Nazi hunter Ernst Sablinova, Silvija asked to train under her father to avenge her mother's death, soon exceeding her father's expectations to be one of the best assassins across the globe, and succeeded him as the Head of Sable International, leader of the Wild Pack and monarch of Symkaria.

Name: Sion (League of Legends)
Summary: Tier: 9-A | High 6-A

Name: Siv
Summary: Possessing a frog-like head and skin (With their skin color being either pale green or blue), the Siv are a Humanoid race that is rather egotistical, considering how relatively small they are in the grand scheme of things. They're known as a rather graceful and calculating race, which is further shown by their favored class being monks.

Name: Skeleton (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: Skeletons are one of, if not the most common types of Undead in any D&D setting. Cheap, loyal, and easy to make, they often serve as the vast majority of a necromancer's army or are found wandering, mindless, across the world. Oftentimes skeletons were made of a variety of creatures, even non-humanoids such as dragons, giants, and beasts.

Name: Skin (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Angelo Espinosa was born in the barrio in South Central Los Angeles. His girlfriend, Tores, became a gang member, straining their relationship because Angelo refused to fly colors, mostly for his mother's sake. One night, Tores and some of her friends picked Angelo up to cruise, but it turned into a drive-by shooting. The stress of the incident caused Angelo's powers to manifest, and he passed out. He woke up with the car on fire, Tores' friend Gordo dead, and Tores gone. A homeless man was trying to steal Angelo's wallet while he was sleeping, and, as Angelo fled the burning car, it exploded, killing the man. With his wallet found on the unidentifiable corpse of the homeless man, Angelo Espinosa was declared legally dead. None of his friends or family were aware of this and many truly believed him to be dead. Angelo left town to keep his mutation secret, and because he believed he was protecting Tores from a murder rap.

Name: Skin Kite
Summary: Made from stolen skin and needing to absorb new skin in order to repair their rotting body, a Skin Kite is a terrible sight to behold. They possess the ability to fly which they use alongside their stealth ability to latch onto creatures and absorb their skin in order to both repair the skin Kite's body and produce new Skin Kites.

Name: Skum
Summary: The Skum is a monster created by the Aboleth, it's made from human stock but unlike a human it must stay in water or else its skin may start errupting which harms them.

Name: Slaad Tadpole
Summary: The baby stage of Blue and Green Slaads, the Slaad Tadpole is the result of terrible misfortune. They are created by either Red Slaad's claw attack, where they implant an egg which after some time hatches inside the creature, eating them from the inside out. Afterwards it takes for the Slaad Tadpole between 2 to 24 hours to become a full Slaad, assuming no one kills them before hand.

Name: Sledgehammer
Summary: A sledgehammer is a construction tool used to break stuff like rocks, walls, ceilings and ground tiles.

Name: Sloth Bear
Summary: Sloth Bears are a species of bear that coexists alongside sun bears and Asian black bears. They are known for their aggressive behavior, which developed as a defensive reaction against larger animals such as tigers, rhinos, and elephants. The sloth bear is species that most often attacks humans going off raw numbers, which can be attributed to large amounts of people surrounding bear reserves.

Name: Slyde (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Jalome Beacher was a talented chemical engineer working in the design and development laboratory of Beemont Manufacturing who created a chemical coating that, when applied to any object, eliminated all friction between that object and surfaces. Beacher was about to unveil his discovery when Beemont was purchased by a larger organization and a man named Rockwall was placed in charge. The research and development lab was closed and Beacher was fired. He decided to build his own company founded on the non-stick chemical, but discovered that no bank would lend the money needed without a sizeable down payment.

Name: SMAW
Summary: The SMAW (Shoulder-launched Multipurpose Assault Weapon) is a shoulder launched rocket weapon with the primary function of being an assault weapon, and secondary purpose being an anti armor rocket launcher.

Name: Smiler
Summary: Once just an elf adventurer, Smiler was abandoned in Avernus by his companions. He has spent over 70 years there, using his charisma and intelligence to survive.

Name: Smilodon
Summary: Smilodon or the Saber-Toothed Cat, is an extinct genus of saber-toothed cat that inhabited North and South America during the Ice Age. Smilodon is often erroneously called the Saber-Toothed Tiger. In reality, the Smilodon genus is very distantly related to the Panthera genus, which is the genus that the tiger belongs to.

Name: Smilosuchus
Summary: Smilosuchus is a genus of leptosuchomorph parasuchid, a group of phytosaurs, which were large reptiles similar to crocodiles but not closely related; phytosaurs displayed convergent evolution with crocodiles and occupied the niche of semi-aquatic ambush predators,[1] especially based on the positioning of their eyes and nostrils. Three species of this genus have been identified: Smilosuchus gregorii, Smilosuchus adamanensis, and Smilosuchus lithodendrorum. The ridges on the snout varied among the three species.

Name: Smith & Wesson 5906
Summary: The Smith & Wesson 5906 is a pistol manufactured starting in 1988 by Smith & Wesson.

Name: Smith & Wesson Model 29
Summary: The Smith & Wesson Model 29 is a six-shot, double-action revolver chambered for the .44 Special and .44 Magnum cartridge and manufactured by the United States company Smith & Wesson.

Name: Smith & Wesson Model 500
Summary: The S&W Model 500 is a double action revolver, its bullets are .50 caliber, making this gun one of the most powerful production handguns around.

Name: Smith & Wesson Model 686
Summary: The Smith & Wesson Model 686 is a six- or seven-shot double-action revolver manufactured by Smith & Wesson and chambered for the .357 Magnum cartridge. It will chamber and fire .38 Special cartridges, as the .357 Magnum was developed from the .38 Special. The Magnum case is slightly longer to prevent such rounds from being chambered and fired in handguns chambered for the .38 Special. The 686 has been available with 2-1/2 in. (64 mm); 3 in.(76mm); 4 in. (102 mm); 5 in. (127 mm); 6 in. (153 mm); and 8-3/8 in. (214 mm) barrel lengths as standard models and other barrel lengths either by special order from S&W's Performance Center custom shop, or acquired from or built by after-market gunsmiths. The Performance Center made a limited number of 686 in .38 Super for competitive shooters.

Name: Snow Cloak
Summary: Appearing like a 2 headed mantis ray, the Snow Cloak is a cunning hunter of the frozen lands using its natural colouring alongside great stealth abilities to ambush prey and then attack it with varuious spells.

Name: Snow Goblin
Summary: Standing between 3 to 4 feet tall, Snow Goblins are a Goblinoid creature that inhabits cold lands. Their voices can be heard from miles away and are used as hunting signals. The females are usually larger and more aggressive then males.

Name: Snow Golem (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: Made from snow this golems are found in both Icewind where they appear in their weaker forms and while their stronger variant exist in Ravenloft where they act like guardians for various places and appear like statues

Name: Snow Leopard
Summary: The snow leopard (Panthera uncia), also known as the ounce[1], is a felid in the genus Panthera native to the mountain ranges of Central and South Asia. Unlike common leopards, the snow leopard's fur is whitish to grey with black spots on head and neck, with larger rosettes on the back, flanks and bushy tail. The snow leopard is also widely used in heraldry and as an emblem in Central Asia.

Name: Snowflake Ooze
Summary: One of the most visually stunning Oozes, the Snowflake Ooze lives in various cold caves or tunnels, seeking to freeze any warm blooded creature it can get its hands on.

Name: South American short-faced bear
Summary: The South American short-faced bear is an extinct bear species in the genus Arctotherium. It is often considered to be the largest bear of all time. A specimen from Buenos Aires showed an individual estimated, using the humerus, to weigh between 983 and 2042 kg, though authors consider the upper limit as improbable and say that 1588 to 1749 kg is more likely. An estimated standing height for the bear is 3.4–4.3 meters.

Name: Sovereign Glut
Summary: Sovereign Glut is a deposed myconid regent, his circle destroyed by duergars who left him as the sole survivor. Now hiding out in another myconid circle, Glut seeks aid in destroying the duergar who slaughtered his people and silenced their song. Once his people are avenged, he then prepares to take down his benefactor, Sovereign Spaw, another myconid ruler who did nothing as Glut's people perished around him- in swearing his revenge, Glut swears to initiate the "Age of Glut" in the Underdark, where he will lead his people with a new song- a song of war and bloodshed.

Name: Space Eel
Summary: One of the many creatures that roam space in Dungeons and Dragons, the Space Eel is a scavenger that flies around. They are 5 feet long, and prefer to target smaller creatures than themselves for food. They are sought after for their meat, which is easier said than done.

Name: Space Swine
Summary: Created and breed by the dohwars, the Space Swine is a species of winged boars. They stand 3 feet tall, and 5-6 feet long. The Space Boar can be used for many things, be it a beast of burden, a tracker, or even as a battle beast. Space Swine trained for combat are called Death Squealers.

Name: Spear
Summary: A spear is a pole weapon consisting of a long shaft and a pointed tip. Spears are one of earliest known weapon in the world, a distinction it shares with axes, knives, and clubs. Spear heads are made out of various materials such as bone, obsidian, flint, iron, steel, and bronze.

Name: Spectacled Bear
Summary: The spectacled bear is also known as the Andean bear, mainly because the spectacled bear is native to the Andes mountain range of South America. The spectacled bears territory ranges from northwest Colombia, into Argentina, Venezuela and Brazil. The spectacled bear generally feeds on berries and shoots found both on ground level and in the trees. The spectacled bear also feeds on insects and small mammals and reptiles, and occasionally cattle.

Name: Spectral Panther
Summary: Mysterious creatures, the Spectral Panther is a panther warped by the Shadowfell to the point where it has became far larger and gained various magical abilities.

Name: Sperm Whale (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: A massive behemoth, the Sperm Whale is a carnivorous whale which roams cold waters. They are massive enough to be able to swallow boats, with it leading to their stomachs containing various treasures.

Name: Spider-Man (Reign)
Summary: In an alternate universe, Peter Parker's time with Mary Jane had given her cancer, which she died from. Parker had retired from superheroics and was working as a florist, while a merciless and oppressive police force, named "The Reign", take power, imprisoning every superhuman they can find.

Name: Spider-Man Noir
Summary: Spider-Man Noir (Peter Parker), often referred to as Spider-Noir, Spider-Man, or simply Noir, is a superhero appearing in American comic books published by Marvel Comics. Part of the Marvel Noir universe (Earth-90214), this alternate version of Spider-Man is a noir-themed take on the character and emerges in a version of New York during the Great Depression.

Name: Spider-Mobile (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Corona Motors, in an effort to promote their new non-polluting car engine, hired the advertising firm of Carter & Lombardo to approach Spider-Man about building a Spider-Mobile. Initially turning down the offer as a dumb idea, Spider-Man reconsidered when he realized how badly he needed the money for rent and expenses. With the aid of the Human Torch, they completed the construction of the Spider-Mobile. After a crash course in driving, Spidey's first capture was of Hammerhead's thugs. Mysterio tricked Spider-Man into dumping the car into the river.

Name: Spinosaurus (Real World)
Summary: Spinosaurus (meaning "spine lizard") is a genus of theropod dinosaur that lived in what now is North Africa, about 112 to 93.5 million years ago.

Name: Spirit Naga
Summary: Spirit Nagas are witch-like nagas hailing from the time of the sarrukh. Irrevocably evil, these creatures are typically found in solitude, guarding some long-forgotten ruin of an ancient civilization, or ruling over a cult of lesser beings who worship the naga like a goddess. These creatures can be found in numerous locales, and are even found in the Orient as spirits. Their appearance varies heavily, with many simply bearing a human head on a serpentine body. It is said to be easy to identify a spirit naga by scent, as their favorite meals include rotten flesh, giving them a terrible odor.

Name: Spitfire
Summary: The Spitfire is a single seat, single engine fighter aircraft designed and manufactured by Supersubmarine before World War II, making its first flight in 1936 and entering service a year before the start of the second world war. The fighter was built in many different variants, and more Spitfires have been produced than any other British aircraft, with over 20000 built by the end of the war.

Name: Spitting Crawler
Summary: The Spitting Crawler is a small lizard which is a popular companion choice by Drow wizards, it's also a hunter of bugs and various slimes.

Name: Spock
Summary: Tier: 9-C physically. At least 8-C with phaser. | 9-B. At least 8-C with phaser.

Name: Spore Servant Octopus
Summary: A creation of the Myconid, this creature is a dead giant octopus animated by spores. It in one of many possible creatures Myconid might employ to defend themselves. One notable example of this creature resides in Stormwreck Isle, where the creature was made as a latch ditch effort to protect the colony.

Name: Spotted Hyena
Summary: The spotted hyena (Crocuta crocuta), also known as the laughing hyena, is a carnivorous animal found in all of Sub-Saharan Africa. The species is, however, experiencing declines outside of protected areas due to habitat loss and poaching. The species may have originated in Asia, and once ranged throughout Europe for at least one million years until the end of the Late Pleistocene.

Name: Spotted Lion (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: Twice the size of a regular lion, the Spotted Lion is a common pet for Stone and Cloud Giants. It often forms massive prides to hunt animals such as Giant Elks or Mammoths.

Name: Sprite (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: A possible relative of the Pixies, the Sprites are a warrior race of fey that fiercely protects their forest. They are far more martial than other Fey, using poisonous arrows to incapacitate intruders.

Name: Star-Lord (Classic)
Summary: Peter Quill, alias Star-Lord, was born during an unusual astronomical phenomenon when many of the planets aligned. Quill was raised by his single mother, Meredith. One day Peter saw an Ariguan spaceship land, and his mother was killed by the aliens. When he told the police his mother had been killed by aliens, no one believed him and he was put in a state orphanage. He ran off when he was fifteen and eventually became a trainee NASA astronaut. When the alien entity called the Master of the Sun visited the space station that Quill was stationed at and offered the mantle of Star-Lord to a worthy candidate, Quill volunteered, but was rejected in favour of another astronaut. Quill was outraged, stole a scoutship, and on returning to the space station took his colleague's place. Quill was then chosen to become Star-Lord, with the Master of the Sun first creating an illusion in which he was able to find and kill the aliens that murdered his mother to free him of his past. Equipped with a sentient vessel called "Ship", Quill commenced his role as Star-Lord.

Name: Star-Lord (Modern)
Summary: Peter Quill is a human-Spartoi hybrid who took the title Star-Lord and patrol the stars, earning a reputation as a hero during his various travels. However, an encounter with the Fallen One forced Peter to commit genocide in order to defeat him. Guilt-stricken, he would sign on to fight against the Annihilation Wave that had invaded the universe, serving as an invaluable tactician. After the war, he would inadvertently allow the Phalanx, a robotic race, to cripple the Kree, and would go on to lead a suicide squad to help save the galaxy. This team would soon blossom into the Guardians of the Galaxy, believing that the universe in its current state was in need of heroes.

Name: Starro (Pre-Flashpoint)
Summary: Starro the Conqueror is the name of a species-wide hive mind of alien starfish-like creatures gifted with powerful psychic powers, who have earned their moniker via the galaxy-wide empire they have assembled by taking over the bodies and minds of all the inhabitants of the countless planets they have taken over. Starro has also attempted to take over the Earth on multiple occasions, only being barely repelled by the combined might of the Justice League time and time again, though they were never able to kill it due to the countless body Starro's conscience resides in.

Name: Stature (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Cassandra Eleanor "Cassie" Lang is the daughter of Scott Lang and Maggie Lang. Fascinated by the Quantum Realm, Lang invented the Quantum Satellite, which resulted in her, her father and the van Dyne family being shrunken deep into the Realm, being trapped in Axia. Wishing to aid the Freedom Fighters in spite of Ant-Man's denies, she donned the Stature suit to battle against Kang's Empire. However, Stature and Ant-Man were captured by M.O.D.O.K. and questioned by Kang the Conqueror, who used her life as leverage for Ant-Man to retrieve the Multiversal Engine Core. Once she escaped, Stature made a speech across Axia to motivate the oppressed citizens to revolve against Kang and his army before facing off M.O.D.O.K. and returning home with her family.

Name: Stature (Marvel Comics)
