Summary: Daughter of Scott Lang, Cassie Lang developed growth powers as a result of repeated exposure to Pym Particles, which were interlinked to her emotional state. After the demise of her father, Cassie carried his legacy by becoming a member of the Young Avengers under the alias of Stature.

Name: Stealth (Image Comics)
Summary: Stealth is a superhero who has battled crime in Detroit for decades with an advanced suit of armor. However, his worsening mental problems begin causing him to mistake federal officers and even his own family for criminals, with increasingly disastrous results.

Name: Stegosaurus
Summary: Stegosaurus is a herbivorous dinosaur from the Jurassic period. It lived in North America. It is one of the most popular herbivorous dinosaurs.

Name: Stegosaurus (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: It is the same creature as it is in real life but exists in Dungeons and Dragons.

Name: Stench Kow
Summary: The Stench Kow is a cattle variant found across the Nine Hells with some found as low as Acheron, Gehenna, and even Hades. As herd animals they graze the fields and eat the local plants, they're also often raised by Archdevil.

Name: Steven Stone
Summary: Steven Stone is the current (previously former) champion of the Hoenn region, and the heir to the Devon Corporation. He enjoys going out to collect rare gems and stones, and will travel all around the world for them. He has been seen in Kanto, Johto, and Unova.

Name: Steyr AUG
Summary: The Steyr AUG (Armee-Universal-Gewehr — "universal army rifle") is an Austrian 5.56×45mm NATO bullpup assault rifle, designed in the 1960s by Steyr-Daimler-Puch and now manufactured by Steyr Mannlicher GmbH & Co KG.

Name: StG 44
Summary: The StG 44 (abbreviation of Sturmgewehr 44, "assault rifle 44") is a German selective-fire rifle developed during World War II. It is also known as the MP 43 and MP 44 (Maschinenpistole 43 and 44).

Name: Stick (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Stick is a member of the Chaste, an ancient, powerful organisation that was created to fight the Hand and stop them from the mysterious Black Sky upon the world. Stick was born blind, but learned to hone his other senses to superhuman degrees. He became an extremely skilled martial artist who would go on to train Matt Murdock and Elektra Natchios, and later aid them in fighting the Hand.

Name: Stielhandgranate
Summary: The Stielhgandgranate (German for "stick hand grenade") was a standard issue of hand grenade of the German Empire during World War I, and became the widespread issue of Nazi Germany's Wehrmacht during World War II. The very distinctive appearance led to it being called a "stick grenade", or "potato masher" in British Army slang, and is today one of the most easily recognized infantry weapons of the early 20th century.

Name: Stilt-Man
Summary: Wilbur Day was an engineer working for Kaxton Laboratories when he stole a hydraulic apparatus, which he built into a battle suit that he used to work as the criminal "Stilt-Man".

Name: Stirge
Summary: Appearing like a hybrid of a mosquito and a bat the Stirge while on its not a great danger is a deadly foe if one encounters it in swarms. Its prey is any warm blooded creature, some Stirges even have a prefernce for humans, it will attack via attaching itself to its prey and suck their blood until they're full and even suck extra blood for reserves, after they're done eating they'll go to sleep for several days depending on how much blood they drained.

Name: Stone Giant
Key: '''Regular''' | '''Elder''' | '''Dreamwalker''' | '''Cairwight''' | '''Stalker of Baphomet''' | '''Evil Earth''' | '''Runecarver''' | '''Earth Titan''' | '''Rockspeaker''' | '''Scion of Skoraeus'''
Summary: One of the main giant races, the Stone Giant is a mighty foe for anyone to face. They are hulking, gray-skinned humanoid-looking creatures that stand 18 feet tall. They can live up to 800 years, and while they're not the smartest of the Giant kin, they are usually far smarter than the likes of Hill Giants.

Name: Styracosaurus
Summary: Styracosaurus is a ceratopsian known for its spiked frill. It had four to six parietal spikes, a jugal horn on each cheek, and a long nasal horn in front that can reach up to 60 cm.

Name: Succubus (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: Succubi (or, as their male presentation is known, Incubi), are demons prone to corruption and subterfuge. They are known throughout the planes to make a very specific trade with mortals- physical love, in return for their soul. A succubus will try to take the souls of more powerful mortal, to gain the souls of their underlings as well. As such, while generally only low-level demons roam the material planes, succubi are exceedingly common.

Name: Sun Bear
Summary: The Sun Bear is the smallest bear species in the world. They are rare and elusive animals found in the forests of Asia. Due to this fact, much is not known about the Sun Bear, at least in comparison to other bear species. They are known for their small size, long tongues, and their dog-like faces.

Name: Super Shotgun
Summary: Essentially this weapon is a traditional (some might say outright old) double barrel shotgun that found its way to Mars and was used to fight off the demon invasion by none other than Doomguy himself. This shotgun is potentially three times more powerful than the typical shots fired from the Combat Shotgun.

Name: Suzuyama Reo
Summary: Suzuyama Reo was a kindhearted girl until a man killed her sister and just like Uruma she felt a lust for revenge. Determined to make the man that killed her sister suffer. She trains to be able to torture and assasinate him.

Name: Swarm of Animated Books
Summary: One of the many constructs in Dungeons and Dragons, the Swarm of Animated Books is what the name implies. They are able to fly around, battering enemies with their bodies. As books they are weak to flames.

Name: Swordfish
Summary: Swordfish are one of many commercially-harvested fish. Named after their swordlike beaks, swordfish use their beaks to slash at prey before gulping them up. Smaller prey are simply swallowed whole. Aside from parasites such as cookiecutter sharks, lampreys, and remoras, few creatures can prey on adult swordfish, namely orcas and shortfin mako.

Name: Taichi Yagami (Adventure 2020)
Summary: Taichi "Tai" Yagami and Agumon are main characters from the 2020 Reboot of Digimon Adventure. After being forcefully sucked into a Digital Space, Taichi meets Agumon alongside Yamato and Gabumon and defeats Algomon. Afterwards, Taichi and Co end up being sent to the Digital World where they go on an adventure to save the Holy Digimon while learning the secrets behind the Holy War between the forces of Light and Darkness.

Name: Tamaki Shindou
Summary: Tamaki Shindou is a combatant in the Mega Fight Tournament, and its returning champion after two consecutive wins. She is a prominent member of the Tennis Club.

Name: Tapir
Summary: Tapir is a large, herbivorous mammal, similar in shape to a pig, with a short, prehensile nose trunk. Tapirs inhabit jungle and forest regions of South America, Central America, and Southeast Asia.

Name: Tarantula (Anton Miguel Rodriquez)
Summary: Anton Miguel Rodriquez, also known as Tarantula was a soldier in South America, using his skills to kidnap politicians and get ransom for their release. However, his greed got the best of him, causing him to shoot his own commander, leading to a series of events that had him flee the area. Afterwards he came to the USA, continuing his crime spree, with Spider-Man thwarting him multiple times.

Name: Tarantula (Luis Alvarez)
Summary: The replacement of Anton Miguel Rodriquez, Luiz Alvarez, also known as Tarantula is one of the many super soldiers in Marvel. Serving the Delvadian army, he's a ruthless killer, aiming to eliminate anyone who poses a threat to the Delvadian regime.

Name: Tarbosaurus
Summary: Tarbosaurus is a genus of theropod dinosaur that lived in what is now Asia, during the end of the late Cretaceous period, about 70 million years ago. Although slightly smaller than the Tyrannosaurus, Tarbosaurus was one of the largest tyrannosaurids, with large specimens measuring about 9.5-10m in length.

Name: Taskmaster (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Tony Masters is a man who can mimic and copy physical actions. He considered a career as a crime fighter but decided to become a professional criminal. After using his skills to complete a series of jobs, he used the capital to start an academy to train aspiring professional criminals around the world. Eventually, his operations were discovered and shut down by the Avengers. Since then Taskmaster has worked as a spy, a mercenary and still acts as a teacher to certain individuals, all for the sake of profit.

Name: Tasthania Silvershade
Summary: Tasthania Silvershade was a young girl when her entire village was slaughtered by orcish raiders. She had been in the woods, and when she returned, she saw a unicorn searching for survivors amongst the smoldering wreckage. The young elf joined it, and the pair found only one survivor- an orc. To Tasthania's astonishment, the unicorn healed it- the elf was enraged as the orc fled. Years later, she had been ambushed by orcs in the same forest- however, she was spared, as the chieftain of the warband was the same orc the unicorn had spared in her village. This caused Tasthania to have an epiphany, and led to her completely changing her worldview- now, she is totally devoted to the redemption of the orcish people, and counts many of those redeemed amongst her closest friends.

Name: Tawky Tawny (Rebirth)
Summary: Tawky Tawny was a resident of the Wildlands, a dimension populated by anthropomorphic animals which had eradicated humans long ago, and believed tigers to be traitors under the orders of the Mayor. Tawny himself however was a gentlemanly pacifist, and despite being jailed, decides to rescue his fellow inmates Darla Dudley and Freddy Freeman, escaping to Philadelphia. There, he became the caretaker for the Shazam Family.

Name: Team Rocket Trio
Summary: ...and make it double!

Name: Teemo
Summary: Undeterred by even the most dangerous and threatening of obstacles, Teemo scouts the world with boundless enthusiasm and a cheerful spirit. A yordle with an unwavering sense of morality, he takes pride in following the Bandle Scout's Code, sometimes with such eagerness that he is unaware of the broader consequences of his actions. Though some say the existence of the Scouts is questionable, one thing is for certain: Teemo's conviction is nothing to be trifled with.

Name: Tenchi Masaki
Key: '''Base Form''' | '''With the Juraian armor and the Tenchi-ken''' | '''Awakened Power''' | '''New Timeline''' | '''Ascended self'''
Summary: Tenchi Masaki (柾木 天地, Masaki Tenchi) is the main protagonist of the Tenchi Muyo! series. Tenchi was a normal boy until he unsealed Ryoko Hakubi, and became the center of events surrounding the highest authority of the galaxy, Jurai. In the Ryo-Ohki continuity, he's actually the grandson of Yosho, the crown prince of Jurai as well as one of the only beings who's able to create Light Hawk Wings as a result of Tokimi's disruption of space-time in the hope of creating a being stronger than her and her sisters.

Name: Teresa Parker (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Teresa Parker was the daughter of C.I.A. agents Richard and Mary Parker, and the younger sister of Peter Parker. After the death of their parents, Peter was sent to live with their Aunt May and Uncle Ben, while Teresa, whose birth had been kept a secret, was adopted. Many years following the deaths of Richard and Mary, Teresa was personally recruited into the C.I.A. by Nick Fury, and during one of her assignments, she discovered the truth of her parentage, and has since worked alongside her surviving brother to save the world any way she can.

Name: Texas Twister (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Drew Daniels was just a cattle hand in Texas, when a tornado and radiation from a nearby nuclear reactor affected him at the same time. The net effect was to give him the power to generate tornadoes at will.

Name: Thalamra Vanthampur
Summary: Starting life as a simple worker in the cellars inside Baldur's Gate, Thalamra Vanthampur managed through her charisma, skills and dedication to rise all the way to the position of Master of Drains and Underways in the city.

Name: Thalattosuchus
Summary: Thalatosuchus is a genus of thalattosuchian, a group of crocodylomorphs adapted to an oceanic lifestyle. It's name quite literally means "sea crocodile," and has the single species Thalattosuchus supercilious. Well adapted to swimming in the oceans, it had a streamlined body and a tailfin,[1] while also lacking the armor-like osteoderms of many other crocodyliforms.[2] It lived in oceans during the mid to late Jurassic, with fossils found in England, Germany, and France.

Name: Thanos Simonattoi
Summary: Thanos, full name being Thanos simonattoi, is the single dinosaur species contained in the genus of carnivorous Brachyrostran Abelisaurid theropods also named Thanos. This animal, obviously named after the Marvel Comics character of the same name, lived during the Santonian stage of the Late Cretaceous Period in what is now known as Brazil.

Name: The Black Knight (Monty Python)
Summary: The Black Knight is a mysterious figure who guards a "bridge" (a plank of wood) over a small stream. Arthur encounters him while searching for the Holy Grail, leading to a duel in which the Black Knight loses his arm. Despite declaring himself the victor (and getting his other arm chopped off), the Black Knight refused to relent, causing Arthur to lop off his foe's legs before continuing on his way, with the Black Knight screaming and cussing for the King of Britain to return.

Name: The Hood (Marvel Comics)
Summary: The man who will become known as the Hood was originally a simple thug from the suburbs of New York City. His life was made of small crimes committed alongside his cousin John King, a relationship with a girl waiting their child and the preoccupations for his mentally-ill mother. Parker Robbins always aspired to be a supervillain and his career began when a would-be robbery turned into an encounter with a demon clad in red. Parker shot the monster down and looted it of its hood and boots. Upon realizing that these items bore magical powers, Parker finally saw the potential to satisfy his ambitions and began his journey to reach the top of the city's underworld.

Name: The Inspector
Summary: From the 1965 cartoon series, stars the inspector. The Inspector is a police detective from France who is always trying to bring justice, thus getting into situations where he must find out a way to solve the problem.

Name: The Joker (Post-Crisis)
Summary: --and his crew goes native on him!

Name: The King (In Stars and Time)
Summary: The King is the main antagonist of the game In Stars and Time and START AGAIN: a prologue, opposing the saviors by freezing Vaugarde in time in an effort to preserve it and save it from the fate that his own country, the island north of Vaugarde, met: being erased from people’s memories.

Name: The Mad Hermit
Summary: The Mad Hermit is a crazed and insane hermit living near the Keep on the Borderlands, a low-level module for Dungeons and Dragons. The hermit has lived cast out of society for some time, and has been deemed a danger to travelers of the area.

Name: The Mummy (Betrayal)
Summary: The Mummy is one of the many monsters present in the House on the Hill, and the titular antagonist of the haunt scenario 'The Mummy Walks'. In it, the Mummy works with the Traitor in order to reunite the Mummy with the reincarnation of his lone lost love, who has reincarnated in the form of the Girl.

Name: The Owl (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Leland "Owl" Owlsley was a ruthless financier, although he had a respectable image. An internal audit by IRS discovered files relating Owlsley with different illegal business enterprises. Owlsley decided to get rid of his previous image, and began scheming to become a crimelord in New York City. He began by hiring thugs for the Owl's Gang and created a small crime empire. Somehow, "the Owl" managed to get a serum he supposedly used to glide and even fly for short distances; he had to use the serum frequently to retain these powers.

Name: The Penguin (Post-Crisis)
Summary: Oswald Cobblepot, a.k.a The Penguin is a fictional DC supervillain and one of Batman's most notorious adversaries. Oswald was bullied as a child for his bird-like appearance and the fact that he was always forced to carry an umbrella due to an overprotective and insistent mother. Cobblepot, born into a life of wealth, grew to become one of Gotham's most collected and eccentric villains, many times leading a charming public life as the forerunner of the Iceberg Lounge, a high society nightclub.

Name: The Player (Block Tales)
Summary: The Player is an unofficial name belonging to the playable character in Block Tales. They're a Robloxian from the future that was sent back to the past after hitting a device with the ability to mess with time in an effort to stop the main antagonist from kidnapping Builderman. After being sent back to 2010, they encounter Shedletsky, who is heavily injured from fighting Red and Blue. Upon defeating red and blue, Shedletsky sends them on a quest to find the seven sword fight on the heights swords (Sfoth swords/Sfoths) in order to both stop mysterious individuals who had fought Shedletsky beforehand from misusing their power and rescue Builderman

Name: The Question (Vic Sage) (Post-Crisis)
Summary: Charlie Szasz was abandoned on an orphanage's steps in Hub City, and grew up as a ruffian who would eventually pursue a career path in investigative journalism as the hard-headed Vic Sage. One of his cases led him to reconnect with his old professor, Dr. Aristotle Rodor, who gave him a pseudoderm mask to better hide his identity when pursuing the case. Thus the Question was born, a vigilante using his fists to solve crimes and get answers much needed.

Name: The Red Bee (Golden Age)
Summary: Richard Raleigh was the first Red Bee, a superhero of the Golden Age. An assistant to the District Attorney, Richard Raleigh became tired of seeing criminals get off on technicalities and decided to use his skills as an apiarist and fighting abilities to fight crime as the Red Bee.

Name: The Saviors (In Stars and Time)
Summary: This profile contains major spoilers for In Stars And Time. It is highly suggested that you fully complete the game before reading this profile.

Name: The Scavenger
Summary: The Scavenger is the main character of the indie game Raw Metal, their goal is to stop an evil organisation, Orpheus Technologies, from exploiting the planet Charybdis for all its dangerous resources.

Name: The Wolf (Bullet Train)
Summary: The Wolf is a minor antagonist in the 2022 action comedy film Bullet Train, based on Kōtarō Isaka's 2010 dark comedic thriller novel Maria Beetle.

Name: Thompson Submachine Gun
Summary: The Thompson submachine gun is an American submachine gun invented by John T. Thompson in 1918 which became infamous during the Prohibition era, being a signature weapon of various crime syndicates in the United States. It was a common sight in the media of the time, being used by both law enforcement officers and criminals. The Thompson submachine gun was also known informally as the "Tommy Gun", "Annihilator", "Chicago Typewriter", "Chicago Piano", "Chicago Style", "Chicago Organ Grinder", "Trench Broom", "Trench Sweeper", "The Chopper", and simply "The Thompson".

Name: Thor (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Thor Odinson is the God of Thunder, prince of Asgard and a former member of the Avengers. When his irresponsible behavior threatened his homeland, he was stripped of his power and banished by his father Odin to Earth. While exiled on Earth, Thor learned humility, found love in Jane Foster, and helped to save his new friends from a destructive threat sent by his jealous adoptive brother Loki. In the process, Thor redeemed himself in the eyes of his father and was granted access to his power once more.

Name: Thorvin Twinbeard
Summary: A gifted engineer, Thorvin Twinbeard is a dwarf who is working for Xanathar's Guild, making Xanathar a contraption which will pulverize those he petrifies.

Name: Thunderbolts (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: The New Avengers, previously named the Thunderbolts by Alexei Shostakov, are a team of extraordinary individuals, with either superpowers or other special characteristics. They were assembled in 2027 as a result of being targeted by Valentina Allegra de Fontaine and working together to stop the Void from taking over New York City. Following their victory, de Fontaine manipulated the situation to declare the team as the newly formed iteration of the Avengers, which was met with a mixed reception from the public.

Name: Thurstwell Vanthampur
Summary: The eldest son of Thalamra Vanthampur, Thurstwell Vanthampur is a hateful frail man in his 40s.

Name: Thylacine
Summary: The Thylacine is a carnivorous marsupial that once lived throughout Australia, New Guinea, and Tasmania. It is nicknamed the Tasmania wolf due to its canine like features that arose from convergent evolution; the Tasmanian tiger nickname comes from its striped appearance. These creatures first emerged around 1.77 million to 780,000 years ago, during the early Pleistocene.[1] Around 3,200 years ago, the Thylacine population on mainland Australia would have died off, the major causes thought to be human activity and the introduction of dingoes.[2] Populations would remain prevalent on the island of Tasmania up until the early 20th century, before extermination by farmers and bounty hunters, along with habitat loss, competition from wild dogs, and disease would devastate them (with possibly already low genetic diversity worsening their chances of survival).[3] The last Thylacine was captured and kept in Hobart Zoo until he died on September 7, 1936.

Name: Tidus (Kingdom Hearts)
Summary: Tidus is a minor character in the Kingdom Hearts series, originally from Final Fantasy X. He is one of the residents living in Destiny Islands and is part of a trio including Selphie and Wakka. In Sora's Dive to the Heart, Tidus appears in the Destiny Islands area along with Wakka and Selphie. He asks Sora, "What are you so afraid of?" Later, Tidus will offer to duel Sora on the small island. Tidus's fate after the Destiny Islands's destruction is unknown, but he reappears on the island once Sora defeats Ansem and the worlds are restored.

Name: Tiger (Real World)
Summary: The tiger (Panthera tigris) is a member of the Panthera genus and is the largest living felid around. It is widely recognized due its pattern of dark vertical stripes on reddish-orange fur with a lighter underside.[1]

Name: Tiger Shark (Real World)
Summary: Tiger sharks are among the most dangerous sharks to humans. They rank second in shark attacks, only behind the great white shark. Tiger sharks typically reach lengths of 3.25 to 4.25 meters (10 ft 8 in to 13 ft 11 in) and weigh around 175 to 635 kg (386 to 1400 lb), although some females reportedly measured over 5 meters (16 ft 5 in).

Name: TigerVespamon
Summary: Tier: 9-B | High 8-C | 6-C | At least High 6-C, higher with Nitro Stinger | 5-B, higher with Nitro Stinger

Name: Tigra (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Tier: 9-B | At least 8-C, at most High 8-C

Name: Titania (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Mary MacPherran is a superpowered social media influencer and entrepreneur under the pseudonym Titania.

Name: Titanis
Summary: Titanis is a genus of phorusrhacid, the group of birds informally dubbed "Terror Birds." It is unique among the phorusrhacids in that it took part in the Great American Interchange; it was among some South American animals that spread to North America, while some North American animals spread to South America. It inhabited North America during the early Pliocene to early Pleistocene, and would have lived alongside canids, hyaenids, and felids, along with ursids; it lived in a xeric thorn-scrubland and grassland environment in places such as Florida.

Name: Titanoboa
Summary: Titanoboa, meaning "titanic boa", is a prehistoric, extinct genus of a snake that lived in what is now Colombia, living about 58-60 million years ago. The only species discovered so far is Titanoboa cerrejonensis, with specimens being able to reach 13 meters (42.65 ft) in length and weighing up to 1,135 kg (2,500 lb).

Name: Titanothere (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: An ancient ancestor of the rhinoceri, the Titanothere is a massive herd animal which once roamed the lands. Easily irritable, if they feel threatened the largest of the herd charges foes with their horn, dealing massive damage and launching man-sized creatures into the air.

Name: Tixie Tockworth
Summary: Once a Svirfneblin, Tixie Tockworth was a bright tinkerer in the town of Little Lockford. However one day she decided she wants to become a machine, which lead to her losing her compassion for others. Her town's militia tried stopping her but was pushed back by her automatons. Afterwards she unleashed them on the rest of the town and driving all the Svirfneblins from Little Lockford. Now left to her own devices she strives to fully change into a machine.

Name: Tokarev TT-33 Pistol
Summary: The TT-33, commonly known as the Tokarev pistol, is an out-of-production Soviet semi-automatic pistol, designed in the early 1930s by Fedor Tokarev as a service pistol to replace the Nagant M1895 revolver that had been in use since the last days of the Russian Empire, though the Tokarev pistol ended up being used in conjunction with, rather than replacing the M1895 revolver. It would continue to serve until 1952, when it was officially replaced by the Makarov Pistol.

Name: Tomb Mote
Summary: Tomb Motes are animated pieces of corpses that come to life after some time in undisturbed tombs. They are born from matted hair, bone chips, the odd tooth, pieces of tombstones, and the dirt itself. They serve no particular purpose but are invariably evil, attacking any intruders in the domain of the dead.

Name: Topi
Summary: A Topi is a type of undead created from a shrunken corpse of a human, they're 2 feet high, they also often have fixed expressions due to the process of shrinking their body endured. They're excellent jumpers for their size, which they often use to get in advantageous positions where they can ambush targets and use their poisonous claws to harm them.

Name: Torami Honjou
Summary: Torami Honjou is a combatant in the Mega Fight Tournament. She is a prominent member of the Karate Club, who lost to Tamaki Shindou in the last competition, stoping at nothing in order to prove herself and reclaim her victory.

Name: Tortle
Summary: Now I search for a friend

Name: Toxodon
Summary: Toxodon is a genus of ungulate megafauna. It's name means "bow tooth," referring to the shape of the teeth on its somewhat hippopotamus-like mouth.[1] This large herbivore was prevalent throughout South America 11.6 million to 11,000 years ago, during the late Miocene to Holocene epochs, feeding on a variety of vegetation based on location.[2] Among many other forms of megafauna, Toxodon died aout during the extinctions around the end of the Last Ice Age.

Name: Trapper (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: One of many manta-like creatures in Dungeons and Dragons, the Trapper mimics the environment, springing upon prey that steps upon it, crushing them to death.

Name: Trapster (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Born in Gary, Indiana, Peter Petruski he worked as a research scientist in New York City for a major corporation. While working there he patented a multi-polymer adhesive that made him very wealthy and made him the top of his profession. However, instead of continuing his successful career, Petruski decided to turn his skills toward a life of crime, a move he believed would be more lucrative, and under the moniker of Paste Pot Pete, committed various robberies, all of which were stopped by the Human Torch.

Name: Treant (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: Living tree; the "'Treant"' serves as the forest's guardian. They are generally peaceful but will attack any evil creature or those who carelessly use fire. Treants come in many varieties, with some having creatures like Rot Grub on their bodies to combat pests.

Name: Trebuchet
Summary: The Trebuchet, also known as the Counterweight Trebuchet, is a type of catapult that utilizes a counterweight to launch a powerful stone projectile over great distances. It became increasingly more common than catapults and were preferred over said weapons due to being far more accurate and powerful.

Name: Trejo Pistol
Summary: The Trejo pistol (pronounced tray-ho), and its sub-variant, the Trejo machine pistol, is a Mexican pistol or machine pistol. The machine pistol sub-variant has the distinction of being the smallest fully-automatic weapon ever produced.

Name: Tri-Flower Frond
Summary: Found in deep jungles this plant is a dangerous hunter which uses its different flowers in tendam in order to kill its prey via poison and corrison and then absorb its bodily fluids.

Name: Triceratops
Summary: Triceratops is a genus of ceratopsid dinosaur that lived during the late Maastrichtian stage of the Late Cretaceous period, from 68 to 66 million years ago, in what is now North America.

Name: Triceratops (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: A large herbivore, the Triceratops is a dinosaur within Dungeons and Dragons. They mainly live in herds, using those to defend themselves from powerful predators like the Tyrannosaurus Rex.

Name: Tristana
Summary: While many other yordles channel their energy into discovery, invention, or just plain mischief-making, Tristana was always inspired by the adventures of great warriors. She had heard much about Runeterra, its factions, and its wars, and believed her kind could become worthy of legend too. Setting foot in the world for the first time, she took up her trusty cannon Boomer, and now leaps into battle with steadfast courage and optimism.

Name: Tristesse
Summary: Remnants of the people that were defeated by the King... Their grief and sadness is all that remains. They cannot tell friend from foe anymore. Defeating them is all we can do... Every sadness has a different resistance and weakness. Maybe there's a way to figure it out from their appearance...

Name: Trixie Lulamoon
Summary: Trixie Lulamoon is a recurring character in My Little Pony: Friendship is Magic, being a staple of the series since Season 1.

Name: Troglodyte
Summary: The Troglodyte is a bit shorter then an average human but is far more deadlier due to their sharp claws, teeth and expertise with using spears in combat. Troglodytes also release a foul stench when ever they're angry, said smell is so horrid most creatures get repulsed by it, but the Troglodyte uses it both as an offensive tool and a communication device, as their sense of smell is rather potent.

Name: Troll (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: Trolls are giants outside of the Ordining, largely due to their predatorial and uncivilized ways of life. In fact, they are not believed to be direct relatives of giants at all, and are only classified as such due to their large stature and ability to mate with true giants. They could be found almost anywhere, with multitudes of sub-species forming as a result of their extremely varied environment choices. Some could be found in the boiling hot jungle, while others function perfectly fine in the bone-chilling arctic wastelands, while yet others could survive in active volcanoes.

Name: True Soul Nere
Summary: Nere is a True Soul of the Absolute cult, making him one of its leaders. He is in charge of their base of operations at Grymforge, an abandoned Sharite complex located in the deep Underdark and trnasformed into a legendary forge capable of molding adamantine into powerful weapons and armor. A cruel and arrogant bully, Nere lords over his duergar underlings and deep gnome slaves as a tyrant, going so far as to beat or even kill them for inconveniencing him.

Name: Trundle
Summary: Trundle is a hulking and devious troll with a mischievous streak. There is nothing he can't beat into submission and bend to his will, not even the ice itself. With his massive, frozen club, he chills his enemies to the core and runs them through with jagged shards of ice. Fiercely territorial, Trundle chases down anyone foolish enough to enter his domain and laughs as they bleed into the tundra.

Name: Tryndamere
Summary: Fueled by unbridled fury and rage, Tryndamere once carved his way through the Freljord, openly challenging the greatest warriors of the north to prepare himself for even darker days ahead.

Name: Tu-95
Summary: The Tupolev Tu-95 is a 4-engine turboprop strategic bomber and missile platform developed by Tupolev, with it being an upscaled version of the previous Tu-4, which is a reverse engineering of the B-29. The bomber is the first intercontinental bomber developed by the USSR, with it's closest US Counterpart being the B-52 Stratofortress. Much like the B-52, it has gone through various upgrades and maintenance, remaining in service to this day.

Name: Twitch
Summary: Tier: At least 9-C, possibly 7-B with Chem Crossbow

Name: Two-Face (Post-Crisis)
Summary: Harvey Dent was abused in childhood by his father Harry, who would decide whether or not to beat him at the flip of a coin, resulting in him developing mental illnesses at a young age. Despite this, he grew up to become the district attorney of Gotham City, until during the trial of Salvatore "Sal" Maroni, the crime boss threw acid in Harvey's face.

Name: Type 72 Anti-Tank Mine
Summary: The Type 72 Anti-Tank Mine is a circular anti-tank blast mine designed by China. It is similar to the Russian TM-46 mine. A metal-cased version and a plastic-cased version of the mine are produced. The mine has a central plastic cased blast resistant fuze.

Name: Type 97 Chi-Ha
Summary: The Type 97 Chi-Ha Medium Tank (九七式中戦車 チハ Kyūnana-shiki chū-sensha Chi-ha) was a medium tank used by the Imperial Japanese Army during the Second Sino-Japanese War, the Battles of Khalkhin Gol against the Soviet Union, and the Second World War. It was the most widely produced Japanese medium tank of World War II.

Name: Type 99 Light Machine Gun
Summary: The Type 99 light machine gun (九九式軽機関銃, Kyūkyū-shiki Kei-kikanjū) was a light machine gun used by the Imperial Japanese Army in World War II.

Name: Tyrannosaurus Rex (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: The Tyrannosaurus Rex is one of the most iconic creatures in fiction and while in the grand scheme of Dungeons and Dragons it's an irrelevant creature, in 5e it's the strongest form a Druid can assume as a Wild Shape assuming they're not from the Moon Circle.

Name: Tyrannosaurus rex (Real World)
Summary: Tyrannosaurus rex, commonly abbreviated as T. rex, is a species of theropod dinosaur that lived throughout what is now western North America from 68 to 66 million years ago.

Name: U.S. Agent (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Jonathan F. "John" Walker is a former Captain of the United States Army's 75th Ranger Regiment and a founding member of the New Avengers. Due to his successful operations around the world, Walker was chosen to succeed Steve Rogers as the second Captain America. However, his aspirations of living up to Rogers' legacy attracted the ire of Sam Wilson and Bucky Barnes in their pursuit of the Flag Smashers, during which he took the Super Soldier Serum after failing to apprehend Karli Morgenthau. When his partner and best friend Lemar Hoskins was killed in action, Walker brutally murdered a surrendering foreign national in public, leading to him being stripped of his mantle and discharged from the United States Army with total loss of rank. Walker confronted Morgenthau again in New York City but chose to abandon his revenge to join Wilson and Barnes in thwarting her attack on the GRC. Despite his discharge, Walker was recruited by government agent Valentina Allegra de Fontaine to continue serving America in secret as U.S. Agent.

Name: Ultimax 100
Summary: The Ultimax 100 is a Singapore-made 5.56mm light machine gun, developed by the Chartered Industries of Singapore (CIS, now ST Kinetics) by a team of engineers under the guidance of American firearms designer L. James Sullivan. The weapon is extremely accurate due to its constant-recoil operating system. It is considered one of the most lightweight machine guns in the world.

Name: Ultron Sentries (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: The Ultron Sentries are mass produced robots that function as extensions of Ultron's will and can sometimes house his AI if his main body is destroyed.

Name: Ulysses Klaue (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Ulysses Klaue was a black-market arms dealer and smuggler as well as a gangster who had operated out of South Africa. He was a former acquaintance of Tony Stark from his weapons-dealing days, and was an associate of N'Jobu when he attempted to expose Wakanda to the rest of the world. In 2015, during an encounter with Ultron, Klaue sold his entire stockpile of the Vibranium to the A.I. before losing his arm in an argument with Ultron, and fled when the Avengers arrived.

Name: Umber Hulk
Key: '''Umber Hulk''' | '''Truly Horrid Umber Hulk''' | '''Vodyanoi''' | '''Shadow Hulk''' | '''Umber Ravager''' | '''Abyssal Hulk''' | '''Astral Hulk'''
Summary: Umber Hulks are ancient mutant creatures born countless eons ago, possibly before the onset of the Dawn War[1]. Hulking bug-eyed monstrosities, the Umber Hulks lurk in the Underdark, tunneling from cavern to cavern in search of food (and little else), often causing wars and conflicts over territory as they move. They are feared on a nearly mythological level to some due to their peculiar ability to incapacitate hostiles with a glance- and leave survivors with nary a memory of what occurred.

Name: Utahraptor
Summary: Utahraptor is a theropod dinosaur from the Cretaceous Period. It is currently the largest Dromaeosaur ever discovered at 2-2.5 meters tall, 7 meters long and weighing at least 500 kg.

Name: Uzi Submachine Gun
Summary: The Uzi (Hebrew: עוזי‎, officially cased as UZI) is a family of Israeli open-bolt, blowback-operated submachine guns. The Uzi was one of the first weapons to use a telescoping bolt design which allows the magazine to be housed in the pistol grip for a shorter weapon.

Name: V-1 Flying Bomb
Summary: The V-1 flying bomb was an early cruise missile and the only production aircraft to use a pulsejet for power. It was the first of the so-called "Vengeance weapons" series (V-weapons or Vergeltungswaffen), developed at Peenemünde Army Research Center in 1939 by the Nazi German Luftwaffe at the beginning of the Second World War, and was deployed at bombarding England. The thousands of V-1 missiles launched into England were fired from launch facilities along the French (Pas-de-Calais) and Dutch coasts. The existence of such a concept as cruise missile inspired the British to operate an arrangement of air defenses, including anti-aircraft guns and fighter aircraft, to intercept the bombs before they reached their targets, while the launch sites and underground storage depots became targets for Allied attacks including strategic bombing.

Name: V-mon (Daisuke Motomiya)
Summary: Daisuke "Davis" Motomiya and his partner Veemon are two of the protagonists of Digimon Adventure 02. The de facto leader of the DigiDestined, their hot-blooded and reckless natures mean they have a lot of room for improvement, but they nevertheless step up to the plate and take the reins of their adventures with enthusiasm.

Name: Valerie (Pokémon)
Summary: Valerie is one of the many Gym Leaders of the Kalos region, and the only Fairy Type one. She also is a fashion designer from the Johto region.

Name: Varag
Summary: Standing at 7 feet tall, the Varag is a Goblinoid like Goblins or Hobgoblins. The average Varag knows the Goblin language but is barely able to talk in it, and outside combat they are not the brightest creatures. However pact leaders are capable fighters, with them leading entire brigades.

Name: Veigar
Summary: An enthusiastic master of dark sorcery, Veigar has embraced powers that few mortals dare approach. As a free-spirited inhabitant of Bandle City, he longed to push beyond the limitations of yordle magic, and turned instead to arcane texts that had been hidden away for thousands of years. Now a stubborn creature with an endless fascination for the mysteries of the universe, Veigar is often underestimated by others—but even though he believes himself truly evil, he possesses an inner morality that leads some to question his deeper motivations.

Name: Velociraptor (Real World)
Summary: Velociraptor is a genus of small theropods living in the Cretaceous Period. They are one of the most popular species of Dinosaurs, even though their appearance is vastly misunderstood.

Name: Verdan
Summary: Created by the That-Which-Endures, Verdans are mutated Goblins and Hobgoblins that were recently created in the Forgotten Realm. Unlike the creatures which they came from, the Verdan are peaceful, with them still learning many new things about their own race.

Name: Vigilante (Pre-Crisis)
Summary: Adrian Chase was a district attorney and later judge in New York City. After his wife and children were murdered by the mob, he became the vengeful Vigilante to punish those the justice system couldn't.

Name: Viola (Pokémon)
Summary: Viola is the current Leader of the Santalune Gym in the Kalos region, serving as the first Gym Leader that Calem/Serena has to fight. An avid photographer, she is almost never seen without a camera in her hand, and she simply adores Bug type Pokemon.

Name: Violet Fungus
Summary: Violet Fungi are specimens of toxic mushroom that grow in certain areas of Faerun, Greyhawk, and many other multiverses. They rely on symbiotic relationships with Shriekers to lure in and, for their part, poison prey. After killing such wanderers in all of their folly, the fungi will scavenge nutrients off of their corpses. Remarkably, this plant has developed the ability to move somewhat.

Name: Viper (Jordan Dixon)
Summary: Jordan Stryke was the brother of the notorious costumed criminal known as the Eel. When Stryke went into the advertising business, he legally changed his last name to Dixon so as to avoid association with his brother's criminal reputation. Dixon spent years planning advertising campaigns for children's toys and other products, but believed that through his marketing abilities he was making fortunes for his clients, while he himself labored in relative obscurity for far less financial gain. Moreover, Dixon believed that through his advertising projects he was perpetrating lies on behalf of his clients and subverting the nation's moral values. Dixon even took a perverse pleasure in such activities. He prided himself on selling products he regarded as worthless so successfully to the public, and he regarded the American public with contempt, believing them willing to believe any lie spread through the mass media, if it was crafted convincingly enough.

Name: Volothamp Geddarm
Summary: No less a peerless font of sagacity as Elminater of Shadowdale has attested that more worlds than this one teem with monsters. As a result, that "Here there be monsters" line has appeared on maps of worlds far from this one, and hidden from your modest scribe. And who am I, you ask?

Name: Vulture (Marvel Comics)
Summary: The Vulture is a supervillain and one of Spider-Man's most die-hard enemies. Before becoming a criminal, Adrian Toomes was a capable engineer who had made a breakthrough when he invented a new kind of magnetic harness. It was an overwhelming joy after a life of hardships. But everything crumbled when he learned his business partner had been stealing a large sum of his profits before finally ousting him from the company they founded. Adrian was sad and angry, so he used what he knew to make a flying suit and become the Vulture.

Name: Wahoo
Summary: The wahoo (Acanthocybium solandri) is a species of scombrid fish endemic to subtropical and tropical waters worldwide. It is one of the fastest fish in the world, capable of reaching speeds up to 77 kilometers per hour. It is a popular sport fish, and prized for its speed and high-quality meat.

Name: Wakanda (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Wakanda is a country in eastern Africa that has become far more technologically and scientifically advanced than any other nation on Earth, due to its supply of the highly valuable, rare and versatile metal Vibranium, brought to the country by a meteor impact thousands of years in the past. However, to avoid being conquered and pillaged of its resources by foreign invaders, the kingdom keeps itself very reclusive and isolated from the rest of the world.

Name: Wally (Pokémon)
Key: '''By Himself''' | '''Pokémon Team (Mauville City)''' | '''Pokémon Team (Victory Road)''' | '''Pokémon Team (Third and Fourth Battle)'''
Summary: Wally is one of the player's rivals in Pokémon Ruby and Sapphire as well as their remakes, Pokémon Omega Ruby and Alpha Sapphire. He is a meek and sickly young boy who aspires to become a great Pokemon Trainer, having covered his entire room and filled multiple notebooks with information on strategy and raising Pokemon. Over the course of his journey, he gains confidence and a stronger constitution, eventually amassing a powerful Pokémon team and defeating every Gym Leader in the Hoenn region before the player does. He then goes on to battle the player right before they go on to challenge the Pokemon League. Although he lost, he refused to let go of his dream, becoming even stronger and regularly challenging the player at the Battle Resort.

Name: Walrus
Summary: The Walrus is a large marine mammal related to seals living around the Arctic regions of Earth. Large individuals weigh in at 2,000 kg, but most male Pacific walruses weigh in at around 800-1700 kg. Atlantic males, on the other hand, weigh on average 900 kg.

Name: Walrus (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: Found in arctic climates such as Icewind Dale, the Walrus is a bulky and massive mammal. They are often hunted for their meat and tusks.

Name: Walther PPK
Summary: The Walther PPK pistol is a blowback-operated semi-automatic pistol made famous by the James Bond movies. Today, PPK pistols are manufactured by Carl Walther GmbH Sportwaffen in Germany or under license from Walther in France and the United States. These pistols feature an exposed hammer, a double-action trigger mechanism, a single-column magazine, and a fixed barrel which also acts as the guide rod for the gun's single recoil spring.

Name: WarGreymon
Summary: An ultimate form of Greymon-species Digimon, it is a subspecies of War Greymon armed with electric-powered weapons.

Name: Wasp (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Hope Van Dyne is the daughter of Hank Pym and Janet Van Dyne who takes on her mother's mantle of the Wasp. Training Scott Lang against Darren Cross, Hope herself fought Ava Starr alongside Lang in order to save her mother from the Quantum Realm.

Name: Water Buffalo
Summary: The Water Buffalo (Bubalus bubalis) are the second largest bovidae. Wild water buffalo live in wildlife preserves in southeast asia, while their domestic counterparts are very common.[1]

Name: Water Weird
Summary: Made from water, the Water Weird is one of the possible Elemental Weirds. In their younger form they appear like a water serpent, shooting cold water at enemies and using their physiology to drown people who come close to them. Their adult self meanwhile is a powerful caster, being able to use various healing and water spells alongside regular Sorcerer spells.

Name: Werebear
Summary: Werebears are a species of benevolent lycnathropes, creatures infected with diseases that transform them from their usual shape into that of some animal. While the affliction itself is considered a curse, werebears are seen as beings of immense good, and generally work to keep their less well-meaning cousins in check (oftentimes fighting the likes of werewolves and wereboars on a regular basis). Unlike others of its kind, the werebear actively works against spreading their curse. When in combat, these enormous ursine creatures avoid biting so as to not infect any others.

Name: Wereboar
Summary: Wereboars are among the most common forms of lycanthropes in the lands of Faerun and beyond and, much like other lycanthropes, are afflicted with a curse that causes them to transform into animals and go on rampages of uncontrollable rage.

Name: Wererat
Summary: Wererats are among the most common and most despicable of all lycanthropes, and can generally be found in gangs inhabiting sewer systems and similar constructs. They are noted for their nervous and suspicious behaviors and, much like all other lycanthropes, they tend to take on traits of their animal even in human form- short, matted hair and quickly darting eyes are often signs of a wererat.

Name: Weretiger
Summary: Regal and graceful, Weretigers are, even in human form, beings of pedigree and class. Afflicted with the lycanthropy curse, weretigers make ideal hunters thanks to their sleek dexterity in all environments. They tend to live alone on the outskirts of humanity, only interacting with humanity to trade when needed. Weretigers are commonly found in warm jungles, where their true animal counterparts reside with them.

Name: Werewolf (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: Werewolves are canine lycanthropes and are generally regarded as beings of incredible evil (though this is not always the case). In their human forms, werewolves merely seem agitated, easily angered by the slightest inconvenience. Both good and evil werewolves alike flee from civilized society- those that fear the curse fear too for their fellow man, and wish to refrain from killing them. Those that embrace the curse seek to save their own hides, and do not wish to be held responsible for their murderous acts.

Name: Werner Werman (Cuphead Show)
Summary: https://vsbattles.fandom.com/wiki/File:WernerWermanIntro.ogg

Name: West Indian Manatee
Summary: The West Indian manatee (Trichechus manatus), also known as the sea cow, is a large species of marine mammal native to the Caribbean and the east coast of the United States. It is herbivorous, and primarily grazes on seagrass.

Name: Whale Shark
Summary: The whale shark (Rhincodon typus) is the largest extant fish in the world. Unlike most other sharks, the whale shark is a filter feeder, and primarily feeds on zooplankton and krill. Despite their size, whale sharks are docile, and pose no threat to humans.

Name: Whip (Real World)
Summary: This page contains or depicts disturbing and/or graphic content that some may find upsetting, and that is only intended for mature audiences. Please proceed with caution.

Name: Whirlwind (Marvel Comics)
Summary: David Cannon was a mutant born with the ability to spin at inhuman speeds, allowing him to create tornadoes as he went along. Turning to a life of crime, Cannon took on the alias of the Human Top, and then Whirlwind, and has been a frequent foe to the Wasp ever since.

Name: White Canary
Summary: The White Canary is a powerful martial artist, the only sister to the Twelve Brothers in Silk, and an opponent of Dinah Lance, the Black Canary.

Name: White Rabbit (Marvel Comics)
Summary: White Rabbit: We don't need them! We're the Terrible Two! We're evil personified! The vilest villains on the face of the-- Walrus: They hung up on you, didn't they? White Rabbit: Uh-huh. After they were done laughing.

Name: White Rhinoceros
Summary: The White Rhinoceros is one of the largest land animals on Earth. They are well known due their trademark horn and their build. They are herbivores.

Name: White Tiger (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Hector Ayala is a vigilante operating in New York City as White Tiger. He became a client of Matt Murdock when he was arrested under false charges of killing a police officer. During the trial, Ayala's identity as White Tiger was revealed to the public, which aided in his acquittal. Upon resuming his activity as White Tiger, he was assassinated by Cole North.

Name: Wiggan Nettlebee
Summary: Wiggan Nettlebee is a halfling clan leader, and is in theory a modest rancher. However, behind closed doors he dedicates himself to studying darker powers to advance himself, he joined the Cult of the Black Earth.

Name: Wights
Summary: A Wight is a reanimated corpse, either human or animal, raised from death by the Night King or the White Walkers with the use of necromancy. Wights were often referred to collectively as the Army of the Dead. Anyone who falls against the White Walkers must be burned, or else the dead will rise again as their slaves. Fear of their own dead becoming wights leads the free folk to burn them.

Name: Wild Boar
Summary: The wild boar (Sus scrofa), also known as the wild swine, Eurasian wild pig, or simply wild pig, is native to much of Eurasia, North Africa, and the Greater Sunda Islands. Human intervention has spread its distribution further, making the species one of the widest-ranging mammals in the world. It has become an invasive species in part of its introduced range.

Name: Wildcat
Summary: The wildcat is a species complex comprising two small wild cat species: the European wildcat and the African wildcat. The European wildcat (Felis silvestris) are natives of continental Europe, Scotland, Turkey and the Caucasus. It inhabits forests from the Iberian Peninsula, Italy, Central and Eastern Europe to the Caucasus. While the African wildcat (Felis lybica) is a small wildcat species native to Africa, West and Central Asia up to Rajasthan in India and Xinjiang in China. Unlike their descendants, wildcats are wild and can't be tamed.

Name: Will Graham (Film)
Summary: Ex-FBI agent Will Graham is an expert investigator who quit the Bureau after almost losing his life in the process of capturing the elusive Dr. Lecter. After a series of particularly grisly murders, Graham soon realizes that the best way to catch this killer, known as the Tooth Fairy, is to find a way to get inside the killer's mind. For Graham, that means confronting his past and facing his former nemesis, the now-incarcerated Lecter.

Name: Winchester Rifle
Summary: The Winchester Model 1894 is a level-actor repeating rifle. It was used by both the United States and France during the many Indian Wars, World War I and World War II. It is widely known as "The Gun That Won the Wild West".

Name: Winter Wolf
Summary: White and larger then their regular counterpart the Winter Wolf is a fearsome predator whose well adepted to hunting in snowy areas.

Name: Wolf of the Overworld
Summary: Inhabiting cold taigas, the Wolf of the Overworld roams the lands as a pact, hunting animals such as sheep and rabbits. They are not hostile to humans, however if one harms a member of a pact they will all attack the human.

Name: Wolverine (Deadpool & Wolverine)
Summary: Logan: Scott used to beg me to wear it. So did Jean, Storm, Beast... All of them. They wanted me to be part of the team, but I wouldn't. Told them they all looked fuckin' ridiculous. I mean, I couldn't have 'em thinking I wanted to be there. And then one day while I was off on my own, the humans came. They went mutant hunting. Laura: I can guess the rest. Logan: No, no, let me say it, I... I need to say it. By the time I stumbled home, shit-faced from the bar, it was too late. They were dead.

Name: Wolverine (Real World)
Summary: The Wolverine is a mustelid found in North America, some parts in the North of Europe and most of the north of Russia.

Name: Wolverine-Pool (Deadpool: Samurai)
Summary: Wolverine-Pool is a variant of Deadpool who appeared in Cable & Deadpool #46 and Deadpool Kills Deadpool #3. He was sent to kill Deadpool in Deadpool Samurai second season.

Name: Wong (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Doctor Strange: Is that everyone? Wong: You wanted more!?

Name: Wood Elf
Summary: One of the major sub races of elves, the Wood Elves who are also known as Sylvan Elves live deep in the forests. They are so attuned with nature that they are able to make use of any small cover to hide away, and they are naturally faster on their feet.

Name: Woolly Mammoth
Summary: The Woolly mammoths were a species of mammoth that lived during the Pleistocene. They were members of the Elephantidae family, making them related to the modern day Elephant.

Name: Woolly Rhinoceras (Real World)
Summary: The Woolly Rhinoceros is a species within the extinct genus Coelodonta. It lived during the mid to late Pleistocene epoch in northern Eurasia. It was likely a grazer that fed on herbaceous plants, with its horn functioning to sweep snow off the ground for it to feed.[1] Along with creatures such as the Woolly Mammoth and Smilodon, it is among the more iconic megafauna of the Last Ice Age.

Name: Worg (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: A variant of the Dire Wolf, the Worg is an evil wolf.

Name: Worghest
Summary: Descendants of Barghest and Goblins, the Worghest are a race of humanoid outsiders that often live amongst goblin or orc tribes, acting as respected warriors there but never seeking a leadership position.

Name: Wormmon (Ken Ichijouji)
Summary: Ken Ichijouji and Wormmon are main characters from Digimon Adventure 02. Ken as the Digimon Kaiser was the first major enemy of the Chosen Children. Being cruel, cold and sadistic person who enjoyed nothing more than causing pain to others and seeing them suffer. This persona was fueled by a corrupting Dark Seed that was planted in the back of his neck from defeating of Millenniummon.

Name: Wyvern (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: 15 feet long and standing on two legs, the Wyvern shares the general apperance of a dragon but lacks the intelligence of one. It's an aggressive predator which dive bombs from the sky on its prey and tries to whisk it away, using its poisonous stinger on them if necessary, some Wyverns also have magic in them due to influnce from the Shadowfell, and they use said magic to cause necrotic damage to their targets.

Name: Xefros Tritoh
Summary: Xefros Tritoh is one of the main protagonists of the Homestuck video game Hiveswap. He is a rustblooded troll from the planet Alternia who is part of a revolution to overthrow the tyrannical caste-based government. He meets main protagonist Joey Claire after she gets swapped with Xefros' best friend Dammek and with her help manages to escape the destruction of his home town.

Name: Xiphactinus
Summary: Xiphactinus was an extinct genus of predatory fish dating back to the late Cretaceous period. Growing up to six meters in length, they were one of the most formidable predators in the Western Interior Sea.

Name: Yalah Gralhund
Summary: A noblewoman in Waterdeep, Yalah Gralhund is an ambitious lady who will use her resources alongside blackmail, threats and whatever is needed to achieve her goals.

Name: Yangchuanosaurus
Summary: Yangchuanosaurus is a genus of theropod dinosaur that lived in what is now China, during the middle to late Jurassic period, about 161.2 to 157.3 million years ago. Yangchuanosaurus was a large, powerful meat-eater, being around 8-11 meters long and weighing as much as 3.4 metric tons.

Name: Yelena Belova (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: This article contains plot details about an upcoming or recently released episode/chapter/movie/book/game/etc.

Name: Yellow (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: A humble knowledge cleric, Yellow resides at the Monastery of Inspiration in the city of Harmony. They are one of seven Nerds tasked with solving the city's power outage issues.

Name: Yellowfin Tuna
Summary: The yellowfin tuna (Thunnus albacares) is a species of tuna found in subtropical and tropical waters worldwide. They are one of the few known warm-blooded fish, which in turn allows them to be exceptionally strong swimmers.

Name: Yellowjacket (Darren Cross)
Summary: Self-made billionaire Darren Cross was diagnosed with a rare heart condition, and was further mutated in the attempts to cure it, but to no avail. Desperate, he kidnapped heart surgeon Dr. Erica Sondheim to replace his damaged heart, but was stopped by Ant-Man, who was trying to rescue Dr. Sondheim so she could operate on his daughter in time.

Name: Yeti (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: The Yeti is a distant relative of both primates and bears that lives in the high mountain peaks. Unlike their cousins the Yeti possesses the ability to absorb the heat of their area and have a gaze that can induce terror into those that are unprepared for it, but the former ability comes with a weakness to any great source of it as they'd absorb it too which would raise their internal body tempature to dangerous levels.

Name: Yondu Udonta (Ravager)
Summary: Yondu Udonta is a Centaurian born in a tribe on the primitive planet of Centauri-IV. At a very young age, Yondu presenced the coming of an alien species to his tribe, the Syneca. The Syneca wished to share their technology in exchange for some Yaka ore. Yondu, amazed by the Syneca's crystal spaceships, took an opportunity to steal one so he and his friend Babatuku could go for a short flight. However, Yondu lost control of the ship, crashing into the elders' temple of his tribe, killing Chondu, an important elder of the tribe. Yondu tried to keep the incident a secret, but, as the Syneca demanded for justice, Babatuku revealed Yondu's role in Chondu's death.

Name: Youngster Joey
Summary: Youngster Joey is considered the first Pokémon trainer that Ethan ever faces in the Johto Pokémon games. He is first seen battling a trainer named Mikey on Route 30, later seemingly having been defeated after Ethan delivers the Mystery Egg.

Name: Yutyrannus
Summary: Yutyrannus is a genus of large theropod dinosaur, represented by the species Yutyrannus huali. It is famous for being the largest dinosaur discovered with clear evidence of having feathers; these are thought to have aided in regulating body heat (especially useful in a land with an average annual temperature of 10 degrees Celsius) or for display, depending on how much of the body was covered.[1] It lived around 125 million years ago during the early Cretaceous, in what is now northeastern China, inhabiting the temperate rainforest habitat that existed in this creature's place and time. It was a relative of the more iconic Tyrannosaurus rex, but was a more primitive representative of the tyrannosauroids.

Name: Yuumi
Summary: A magical cat from Bandle City, Yuumi was once the familiar of a yordle enchantress, Norra. When her master mysteriously disappeared, Yuumi became the Keeper of Norra's sentient Book of Thresholds, traveling through portals in its pages to search for her. Yearning for affection, Yuumi seeks friendly companions to partner with on her journey, protecting them with luminous shields and fierce resolve. While Book strives to keep her on task, Yuumi is often drawn to worldly comforts, such as naps and fish. In the end, however, she always returns to her quest to find her friend.

Name: Zan (Post-Rebirth)
Summary: Zan is the twin brother of Jayna and a member of the Wonder Twins. Originally from planet Exxor, Zan is the grandchild of an infamous figure in Exxorian history and was sent to Earth to avoid harassment. Despite his many shortcomings, Zan is an incredibly friendly, kind-hearted, and sociable person who values love and friendship above everything.

Name: Zark
Summary: Zark is a dwarven delinquent living in the city of Loudwater, who in recent years has turned to a life of crime (including slavery and smuggling) to support his lazy lifestyle. He has been in cahoots with the Zelbross Bandits since they spared his life in return for his services.

Name: Zebra (Real World)
Summary: Zebras are African equines that are distinguished by they black-and-white stripes. There are three known species of zebras, with the most common being the Burchell's zebra (also known as the plains zebra). Due to their wild temperament, it is ill-advised to saddle up or attempt to ride a zebra.

Name: Zhou Cheng (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Zhou Cheng is a deadly servant of the Hand who was trained by the martial artist Ch'i-Lin to become a powerful combatant by consuming large amounts of alcoholic beverages in order to "tame his inner dragon". Cheng was assigned to guard one of Madame Gao's compounds in China, but was approached by the Iron Fist, who was searching for Gao, leading to a showdown between the two martial artists. Cheng ultimately lost the fight, but was left alive.

Name: Zinnia (Pokémon)
Summary: Zinnia (Japanese: ヒガナ Higana) is a mysterious Draconid woman and a Pokémon Trainer from Hoenn introduced in Omega Ruby and Alpha Sapphire. She is seen as an important character that holds the key to the Delta Episode and aims to accomplish her objectives.

Name: Zorbo
Summary: From a distance appearing like a koala, if an adventurer mistakes the Zorbo for one and approaches it to pat it then they'll get a nasty surprise.

Name: Zuggtmoy
Summary: In Zuggtmoy's Cradle your body shall sleep,

Name: Zulkir
Summary: A Dire Badger, Zulkir is a specimen who was granted intelligence far beyond animals by an Awakening spell.

Name: 170,000-Year-Old Cicada Nymph
Summary: 170,000-Year Cicada Nymph (17万年ゼミ幼虫, 17 Man-nen Zemi Yōchū) is a large Mysterious Being that attacked Z-City at some point during Saitama's training years.

Name: A.K.I.
Summary: A.K.I. is a character introduced in Street Fighter 6. She is F.A.N.G's protégé and assistant, as well as a sort of adoptive daughter. A.K.I. was a street child living of expedients and hoaxes, until the day she and her brother tried to extort money from F.A.N.G. The former Shadaloo responded by putting them before a deadly trial that would have killed them both regardless of the choice. However, A.K.I. unexpectedly asked to learn more about F.A.N.G. instead. Intrigued by the child's attitude, F.A.N.G. took her in and raised her in the ways of the Poison Hand.

Name: Aang
Summary: Aang was a male Air Nomad born in 12 BG and the Avatar during the Hundred Year War, succeeding Avatar Roku and preceding Avatar Korra. As the Avatar of his time, he was the only person capable of using all four Bending arts: Airbending, Waterbending, Earthbending, and Firebending. He was also one of a select few Avatars and one of the first in many cycles to learn the ancient art of Energybending and the first Avatar known to have actively used the technique.

Name: Abe Simpson
Summary: Abraham Jay "Abe" Simpson II, commonly known as Grampa Simpson or simply Grampa, is a major recurring character in The Simpsons and a supporting character in The Simpsons Movie. He is the elderly patriarch of the Simpson family, Abe was a World War II veteran who was later sent to the Springfield Retirement Castle by Homer. He is known for his long, rambling, and often inaccurate stories.

Name: Ada Wong
Summary: Ada Wong is a secret agent appearing in the Resident Evil franchise. She was first introduced in Resident Evil 2 as a supporting character and reappeared in Resident Evil 4 and Resident Evil 6 as one of the main characters.

Name: Adam Kane (Dead Rising)
Summary: This page contains or depicts disturbing and/or graphic content that some may find upsetting, and that is only intended for mature audiences. Please proceed with caution.

Name: Adam MacIntyre
Summary: Adam MacIntyre once was a popular clown before the zombie outbreak. He went mad after they ate his audience.

Name: Agnaktor
Summary: Agnaktor is a large Leviathan which was first introduced in Monster Hunter 3 or Monster Hunter Tri.

Name: Alex (Street Fighter)
Summary: Alex is a playable character in the Street Fighter series, and the protagonist of the Street Fighter III games. He is a professional wrestler who lives day-by-day out of his trailer house in New York, which he never left and has no interest in doing so. His day is spent between construction jobs, wrestling events and training. Tom, Alex's mentor and a friend of his father, is worried about him, as he always keeps his emotions in check, isn't very talkative and lacks sensitivity, which makes it seem he lacks a true purpose in his life, although things apparently started to change after his meeting with Dhalsim.

Name: Alligator (Resident Evil)
Summary: The Alligator is an irregular mutant found in the sewer area of Raccoon City. For unknown reasons he was infected by the T-Virus, which greatly increased its size. It inhabits the waste area and its large size prevents it from moving freely through the sewer system. It is different from The Crocodiles that appear in Resident Evil 5.

Name: Angel Quijano (Dead Rising)
Summary: This page contains or depicts disturbing and/or graphic content that some may find upsetting, and that is only intended for mature audiences. Please proceed with caution.

Name: Applejack (Human World)
Summary: Applejack is one of the main characters in My Little Pony Equestria Girls.

Name: Apu Nahasapeemapetilon
Summary: In the 1960s, Apu lived in India and spent some time as a student of the Maharishi Mahesh Yogi. He became a friend of Paul and Linda McCartney. He graduated from Calcutta Technical University and then got a scholarship in the United States at the Springfield Heights Institute of Technology. He achieved a doctorate in Computer Science by designing the world's first tic-tac-toe program that only the top human players could beat. After this, he took a job at the Kwik-E-Mart and continues to work there to this day. Due to his past, he is put in an arranged marriage with a woman named Manjula. After having 8 children (octuplets at that), he continues to raise his family and work his business in Springfield.

Name: Azula
Summary: Azula was the princess of the Fire Nation, daughter of Fire Lord Ozai and Princess Ursa, younger sister of Zuko, niece of Iroh, the older half-sister of Kiyi, the aunt of Izumi, and the grand aunt of Iroh II.

Name: Balrog (Street Fighter)
Summary: Balrog, known as M. Bison (マイク・バイソン Maiku Baison) in Japan, is a character from the Street Fighter series. He first appeared as a boss character in Street Fighter II.

Name: Bart Simpson
Summary: Bartholomew JoJo "Bart" Simpson (born April 1, 1980) is a main character and the tritagonist of The Simpsons.

Name: Bear Thief
Summary: The Bear Thief (Sanzoku Kuma (山賊熊?, lit. "Bandit Bear")) is a minor antagonist encountered by Bulma and Son Goku on their search for the Dragon Balls.[1] He is a large anthropomorthic brown bear who lives near Mt. Paozu, attacking any passerby of their food and valuables.

Name: Beck (TRON)
Summary: Beck is a young program who adopts the persona of Tron to free his home and friends from the reign of the villainous CLU and his henchman General Tesler. With training from Tron, the greatest warrior the Grid has ever come to know, he not only teaches Beck the fighting and lightcycle skills he needs to challenge this brutal military occupation, but becomes a guide and mentor to him as he grows beyond his youthful, impulsive nature into a courageous, powerful, strong leader.

Name: Bee (Hollow Knight)
Summary: Bees are the residents of the Hive, below the Kingdom's Edge, are a species of sentient bees. These airborne warriors possess a hive mind which dictates their behaviour among the Hive. Hivelings carry out simple tasks, and can colonize husks to serve the Hive's purpose.

Name: Belfly
Summary: Belflies are enemies in Hollow Knight. They are quick, highly volatile flying creatures who dive at prey with no sense of self-preservation. The Belfly Hangs from a ceiling, emitting a high-pitched squeak. Listen carefully for this sound as it is usually found in dark or secluded places, where spotting it usually means that it is too late to avoid contact with it.

Name: Birdie (Street Fighter)
Key: '''Street Fighter''' | '''Street Fighter Alpha Series''' | '''Street Fighter V'''
Summary: Birdie is one of the characters who debuted in the first game of the series, and later returned with a drastic change in design and personality, most notably his loved hair and signature chains. He used to be a heel wrestler, until he grew unable to endure the laughter and contempt, and was expelled after having hospitalized several colleagues. He then alternated working as a bouncer in a bar to small illegal activities, becoming renowned in the underground for his great strength.[3]

Name: Bitores Mendez
Summary: Father Bitores Mendez is one of the many antagonists of Resident Evil 4. He was a Catholic priest that fell into the influence of Osmund Saddler and later led the initial hunt for Leon S. Kennedy, Dr. Luis Sera and Ada Wong, which were potential threats to the cult, though Leon ultimately killed him after a long fight.

Name: Blangonga
Summary: Blangonga is a Fanged Beast introduced in Monster Hunter 2.

Name: Blanka
Summary: Blanka (ブランカ, Buranka), also known by his birth name Jimmy (ジミー Jimī), is a video game character from the Street Fighter series. Blanka's first appearance in the series was in Street Fighter II as part of the starting lineup.

Name: Brad Park (Dead Rising)
Summary: This page contains or depicts disturbing and/or graphic content that some may find upsetting, and that is only intended for mature audiences. Please proceed with caution.

Name: Brian Griffin
Summary: https://vsbattles.fandom.com/wiki/File:Family-Guy-Whose-leg-do-you-have-to-hump-YoutubeConvert.cc-_1_1.ogg

Name: Brock Mason
Summary: Brock Mason is the second main antagonist of Dead Rising as well as Dead Rising: Chop Till You Drop.

Name: Broken Vessel
Summary: Broken Vessel is one of the main bosses in Hollow Knight. It blocks the way to the Monarch Wings. Lost Kin is its dream variant. Broken Vessel is one of the many Vessels who escaped the Abyss like the Knight, but unlike the Knight, was met with a tragic death while still in Hallownest.

Name: Bulbous G
Summary: Bulbous G is the second Hollow which attacked Yasutora Sado, was eventually defeated after Sado unlocked his Fullbringer.

Name: Bullfango
Summary: Bullfango are Fanged Beasts (formerly Herbivores), introduced in the first Monster Hunter.

Name: Bushido Brown
Summary: Bushido Brown was a bodyguard for hire who charged exorbitant fees to protect clients with his martial arts skill.

Name: Cammy White
Summary: Cammy White, also known by the codename Killer Bee, is a video game character from the Street Fighter series, first appearing in Super Street Fighter II. She was once a deadly assassin working for Shadaloo before breaking free and becoming an MI6 operative for the British government.

Name: Captain Gutt
Summary: Captain Gutt was a Gigantopithecus who took to being a self-styled master and captain of the high seas, taking whatever food he could find by theft and hoarding it with the help of his crew. Gutt is the main antagonist of Ice Age 4.

Name: Carla Radames
Summary: Carla Radames was a genius researcher who worked for Derek C. Simmons, doppleganger of Ada Wong and the main antagonist of Chris', Jake's and Ada's campaigns in Resident Evil 6, and is the secondary antagonist of Leon's campaign. Overall, Radames is the main antagonist of Resident Evil 6. Radames is one responsible for the discovery and creation of the C-Virus, and she is both the eventual founder and leader of an Umbrella Corporation-typed organization called Neo-Umbrella. Carla is initially portrayed as an uncharacteristically cruel Ada Wong. However, it is eventually revealed in Ada Wong's own campaign that she is in fact a clone Derek C. Simmons created using Carla Radames (without her consent), Ada Wong's DNA, and the C-Virus.

Name: Casey Rhodes
Key: '''Casey Rhodes''' | '''Dai-Shi awakening Arc (1-10)''' | '''Overlords Arc (11-21)''' | '''Phantom Beast Arc (22-32)'''
Summary: Casey Rhodes is the Jungle Fury Red Ranger. He was a fairly new member to the Pai Zhua Academy and hence known as a cub and possessed the spirit of the tiger. He has the power to stand up for what he believes in and for others. He doesn't like other people to get picked on. When Casey stood up one day for a fellow cub who was being verbally abused by Jarrod, Master Mao (the leader of the Pai Zhua Academy) dismissed Jarrod. Master Mao saw the potential that Casey had in him and chose him instead of Jarrod, to guard Dai Shi's imprisonment box.

Name: Chain'n'Toad
Summary: Chain'n'Toad is an A-Class Rank 36 hero for the Hero Association.

Name: Chainsaw Man (Resident Evil)
Summary: The Chainsaw Man is a class of Chainsaw Ganado. This Ganado wears a burlap potato sack as a mask over his head. the Chainsaw Man has been made exceptionally violent, and is compelled to relentlessly chase his enemies with his trademark chainsaw. Also, due to the Plaga's assimilation, he has been made exceptionally robust in comparison to regular villagers and can absorb small arms fire with ease.

Name: Charlie Nash
Summary: Charlie Nash, known as Charlie or Nash dependent upon the game and region, is a character from Capcom's Street Fighter series of fighting games. He is a strong Captain in the United States Air Force and fighting injustice alongside his friend Guile.

Name: Choze
Summary: Choze is a martial arts competitor from One Punch Man. He comes from a clan of eugenicists determined to create a "superior race." Due to years of selective breeding with the best of genes, Choze was born with naturally superhuman abilities, which he uses to brutally torture others for his pleasure.

Name: Chris Griffin
Summary: Chris Griffin is one of the main characters in the animated series, Family Guy.

Name: Chris Redfield
Summary: Chris Redfield is one of the main protagonists of the Resident Evil series. He is a former member of the S.T.A.R.S. unit. He is now an American Special Operations Unit Captain of the BSAA (Bioterrorism Security Assessment Alliance), an anti-Bioterrorist group, of which he is a founding member along with his long-time partner, Jill Valentine. A senior member of an elite security force in Racoon City, S.T.A.R.S. Members of Team 1, they are the pride of S.T.A.R.S. for their competence in firearms and close combat. Chris is also the older brother of TerraSave member Claire Redfield. He appears in the original Resident Evil, Resident Evil - Code: Veronica, Resident Evil 5, Resident Evil 6, Resident Evil 7: Biohazard, and Resident Evil Village.

Name: Chuck Greene
Summary: This page contains or depicts disturbing and/or graphic content that some may find upsetting, and that is only intended for mature audiences. Please proceed with caution.

Name: Chun-Li
Summary: Chun-Li is a character in the Street Fighter series. She is the first female player character that appears in the series, one of the series' major lead characters alongside Ryu and Ken and the first playable female character to appear in a 1-on-1 fighting game. Introduced in Street Fighter II, Chun-Li was the only female character in the game, as well as one of the youngest fighters, and while not as physically powerful as the other characters, she is by far the quickest. She is one of the most popular playable female characters in the series.

Name: Claire Redfield
Summary: Claire Redfield is a current member of the human rights organization, TerraSave. She is the younger sister of BSAA operative and former S.T.A.R.S. member Chris Redfield.
