Claire is a survivor of the Raccoon City Incident, which took place in September 1998 after she traveled to the city in search of her brother. After escaping the city with the help of Leon S. Kennedy, Claire ventured to Europe to resume her search for Chris. In December, she was captured by Umbrella after infiltrating their Paris Laboratory and transported to the Umbrella owned Rockfort Island and imprisoned. When Rockfort Island was attacked by a mysterious Special Forces group, Claire tried to escape with a fellow prisoner, Steve Burnside, leading to both of their involvements in the Antarctic outbreak. Her brother soon learned of her situation and rescued her. In 2005, Claire confronted the t-Virus again when she arrived at Harvardville Airport to meet some friends. While surviving in the airport, she was reunited with Leon, now a U.S. Government agent, who had been sent to deal with the outbreak. Later, in 2011, Claire would be kidnapped along with other TerraSave members by Alex Wesker's organization and left on Sushestvovanie Island, which made her try to escape with Moira Burton amid the outbreak taking place there. Having been the only one to be rescued, she would eventually support Barry Burton in the search for his daughter and in the process participated in the elimination of the last of the Wesker Children. As early as 2014, in the midst of her investigation into bioterrorist activities taking place in the Sonido de Tortuga Island region, Claire was eventually involved in the outbreak that occurred at the site.

Name: Cleveland Brown
Summary: https://vsbattles.fandom.com/wiki/File:ClevelandOHThatsNasty.ogg

Name: Cliff Hudson
Summary: Cliff Hudson is a psychopath appearing in Dead Rising.

Name: CLU
Summary: CLU is an artificial intelligence program that was written in 1983 by Kevin Flynn. CLU is the main antagonist of TRON: Legacy, the secondary antagonist of TRON: Evolution and the overarching antagonist of TRON: Uprising. As with most programs, CLU appears visually identical - albeit at a younger age - to his creator. He represents an evil digital doppelgänger of Kevin Flynn and a twisted embodiment of Flynn's youth.

Name: Cole Evans
Summary: Cole Evans is the Red Ranger Wild Force and the main character of Power Rangers Wild Force, leading his team of rangers against Master Org and other Orgs.

Name: Colmillos (Resident Evil)
Summary: Colmillos (コルミロス) are Plaga-infested wolves encountered in Resident Evil 4. The name 'Colmillos' means 'Fangs' in Spanish.

Name: Conner McKnight
Key: '''Civilian Form''' | '''Red Ranger''' | '''Super Dino Mode''' | '''Triassic Ranger, w/ Battlizers'''
Summary: Conner McKnight is the Dino Thunder Red Ranger and leader of the group. He is given the special power of super speed by his Red Dino Gem and fights alongside the other DT rangers in order to defeat Mesagog. Conner's enjoys soccer, playing at Reefside High School and on a namesake club, and he aspires to be a famous soccer star. At first, he appears to fit the stereotype of being a high school jock as he comes off as hot-headed, arrogant and being a bit of a flirt with woman but he is actually a very well-meaning and honest person who always does the right thing in the end.

Name: Cretaceous and Maelstrom
Summary: Cretaceous and Maelstrom are the primary antagonists of the film Ice Age: The Meltdown. Cretaceous is slender with traits of both a crocodile and a fish, while Maelstrom is stout with a broad snout and a short tail.

Name: Crimson Viper
Summary: Crimson Viper, also known as either C. Viper or by her true name Maya, is a video game character from the Street Fighter series, first appearing in Street Fighter IV. She is an undercover CIA agent who fights using an assortment of gadgets hidden within her battle suit.

Name: Crystal Guardian
Summary: The Crystal Guardian is part of the miners of Crystal Peak who died from the Infection and were reanimated by it. It appears larger than the other husks, has crystal growing on its back and encasing both its arms and its head.

Name: Dave (One-Punch Man)
Summary: Dave, is a Martial Artist and user of the Giant Style Crushing that participated in the 22nd Super Fight Tournament.

Name: Death (Family Guy)
Summary: Death, also known as the Grim Reaper, is a recurring character on Family Guy.

Name: Dee Jay
Summary: Dee Jay is a fighter and musical artist from Jamaica. He made his way as a kickboxer representing his country in tournaments around the world, quickly becoming a world-class champion. His musical career started when a record company scout noticed his extremely charismatic, fun-loving and upbeat attitude during a competition, and offered him a contract. Dee Jay discovered his natural talent for music, scoring a musical success after another and with all of his albums having gone gold. Over time his love for music started waning, but the spark was reignited when he realized the "Rhythm of Attacks" during a fight, and that he could combine his love of music and martial arts into a single journey.

Name: Demoman (Team Fortress 2)
Summary: A fierce temper, a fascination with all things explosive, and a terrible plan to kill the Loch Ness Monster cost the six year old Demoman his original set of adoptive parents. Later, at the Crypt Grammar School for Orphans near Ullapool in the Scottish Highlands, the boy's bomb-making skills improved dramatically. His disposition and total number of intact eyeballs, however, did not.

Name: Diamond Dogs
Summary: The Diamond Dogs were a PMC (Private Military Contractor) formed by Kazuhira Miller in the early 1980s, and commanded from 1984 onwards by Venom Snake, after recovering from his coma. Under his command, it would become an extremely powerful and highly influential player in the worldwide military-industrial complex, taking on jobs for all clients. The organization would end up at odds with XOF, the covert strike force of the shadow government known as The Patriots, due to the feud between Big Boss/Venom Snake and XOF's leader, Skull Face. Ultimately, Diamond Dogs would emerge victorious, with Venom Snake and Kazuhira Miller dealing the finishing blows to Skull Face and scattering XOF. The PMC would remain in operation for roughly a decade more, before being supplanted and its strength absorbed by Big Boss' military fortress nation, Outer Heaven.

Name: Don Kanonji
Summary: Don Kanonji (ドン・観音寺, Don Kanonji), real name Misaomaru Kanonji (観音寺 ミサオ丸, Kanonji Misaomaru) is the host of the Television show Casual Soul Realm Assault Trip, commonly shortened to Cazh Soul.

Name: Dracula Duck
Summary: Count Dracula Duck (Or in some cases, referred as Drake Von Vladstone) is a Disney character and provides the role as the Final Boss in the game, Ducktales for NES, later to be the Final Boss once more for its Remastered version for the Wii U, Ducktales Remastered.

Name: Drain Deimos
Summary: The Drain Deimos (ドレインディモス) are fleas which have been mutated by the t-Virus. Their only confirmed sighting was during the Raccoon City Destruction Incident, in which they were infected by feeding on blood from zombies. Like many other arthropods, the fleas responded to the virus by dramatically increasing in size, strength and aggression, as well as growing more humanoid anatomy, such as its arms and legs.

Name: Dudley
Summary: Dudley is a character in the Street Fighter series. He is a professional boxer known for being quite the gentleman.

Name: Dung Defender
Summary: Ogrim, one of the King's most trusted Five Knights and a Boss in the Waterways. After being defeated, he gifts The Knight the Defender's Crest.

Name: E. Honda
Summary: Edmond Honda, better known as E. Honda, is a recurring character in the Street Fighter series. Having been around since The World Warrior, this practitioner of sumo wrestling is bent on proving the greatness of said art.

Name: Ed (Street Fighter)
Summary: Ed is a playable character introduced in Street Fighter V. Ed is one of Shadaloo's many victims, having been subjected to cruel experiments since childhood that enhanced his physical abilities and grented him control of Psycho Power. Ed's fate was to become a loyal soldier and future spare body for M. Bison, but following the collapse of the facility he was being kept in, Ed was found and taken away by Balrog, who planned to exploit his powers for potential future economical gain.

Name: El Fuerte
Summary: El Fuerte is a luchador and cook from Mexico. He wants to become the ultimate chef, and in order to accomplish such dream he enters the third world tournament with the aim to collect recipes from the strongest fighters around and prove his might as a warrior. His cooking skill is quite mediocre and he doesn't realize how terrible his dishes are, reason why he often yelled at by his colleagues. Competing in the tournament hasn't helped him a bit in that regard, but his cheerful personality and burning passion granted him lots of friends, especially fellow wrestlers such as Zangief and E. Honda.

Name: Elder Hu
Summary: Elder Hu was a travelling sage who sought to purify the borderlands of Hallownest from the Infection. He reached the Mantis Village, but his own Infected mind made him see the Mantis Lords and the Tribe as afflicted by the plague.

Name: Elena (Street Fighter)
Summary: Elena is a princess from Kenya and fighter in the World Championship Tournament who specializes in Capoeira. Her social, cheery and energetic personality has let her make several friends while studying overseas, primarily in France and Japan.

Name: Eminem (Fortnite)
Summary: Eminem is a former Boss/Event Character in Fortnite. He appears Spaghetti Grotto as a Boss, which sports Grenades and RG's Minigun and is a tough foe.[1] He also appears as a character in a Live Event as a large version of Marshall Never More that sings his song Godzilla.

Name: Endermite
Summary: The Endermite is a mysterious creature that appears from Ender Pearls.

Name: Engineer
Summary: This amiable, soft-spoken good ol' boy from tiny Bee Cave, Texas loves barbecues, guns, and higher education. Natural curiosity, ten years as a roughneck in the west Texas oilfields, and eleven hard science PhDs have trained him to design, build and repair a variety of deadly contraptions.

Name: Ernie The Giant Chicken
Summary: Ernie the Giant Chicken is a minor character that appears a few times in the adult television comedy series Family Guy. He is the arch nemesis of Peter Griffin, all because Peter tried to kill him over giving him an expired coupon, further resulting to them beating up each other in incredibly brutal brawls.

Name: Ethan Winters
Summary: Ethan Winters is a major character in the Resident Evil series. An American systems engineer who was happily married to his wife Mia Winters, Ethan's normal life changed when Mia suddenly disappeared without a trace while working away from home.

Name: F.A.N.G
Summary: F.A.N.G (ファン Fan), known as the "Great F.A.N.G" or F.A.N.G-sama in Japanese, is a character in the Street Fighter series who first appeared in Street Fighter V. He was the fourth and last of the first new fighters confirmed for Street Fighter V and he is one of the game's bosses.

Name: Fairies (Touhou)
Summary: A fairy (妖精 yousei) is a small, simple, humanoid creature of magic that represents some aspect of nature. Many of them are also simple-minded. They tend to have short lives, but they will regenerate immediately after dying. In the games themselves, the fairies are by far the most common general stage enemy in the Touhou Project. The way they shoot danmaku all depends on what difficulty the player chooses and what stage they appear in. They can come in different kinds of colored dresses and hair, and can appear bigger than usual at times, such as the Sunflower Fairy.

Name: False Knight
Summary: The False Knight is one of the first bosses The Knight encounters within Hallownest. While appearing large and intimidating, in actuality, the False Knight is actually a small maggot who has taken on the shell of the great knight Hegemol. If the Knight enters the maggot's dream, it can encounter the False Knight's dream form, the Failed Champion, who is a far stronger and faster version of its real-world counterpart.

Name: Fei Long
Summary: Fei Long is a character from the Street Fighter series of fighting games. He makes his first appearance in Street Fighter II. He is an action movie star in Hong Kong, who spends hs free time testing his skills at martial arts tournaments.

Name: Finn the Human
Key: '''Seasons 1-Dungeon Train''' | '''Dungeon Train - Dad's Dungeon''' | '''Dad's Dungeon - Apple Wedding''' | '''Blade of Grass - Reboot''' | '''Two Swords - Elementals Arc''' | '''Season 10''' | '''Deceased'''
Summary: Finn the Human, real name Finn Mertens is the main character of Adventure Time. He, along with his adoptive brother Jake the Dog are the loyal champions of the Candy Kingdom. Finn vowed to keep the Kingdom and its residence safe at all cost. Finn is a very loyal and kind person, always giving a helping hand to those who need it.

Name: Flintheart Glomgold
Summary: Flintheart Glomgold is a Disney character, the rival of Scrooge McDuck, and is one of the main antagonists of the Disney cartoon Ducktales. He is the world's 2nd richest duck, and plans to put Scrooge out of his league, even if it means engineering his rival's death. However, Scrooge tends to outplay Glomgold throughout any plot that he devises.

Name: Fluttershy (Human World)
Summary: Fluttershy is one of the main characters of My Little Pony Equestria Girls, and represents the Element of Kindness.

Name: Fox (Minecraft)
Summary: Foxes are nocturnal neutral mobs that spawn commonly in taiga and snowy taiga biomes.

Name: Frank West
Summary: This page contains or depicts disturbing and/or graphic content that some may find upsetting, and that is only intended for mature audiences. Please proceed with caution.

Name: Frylock
Summary: Frylock is one of the four main characters in Aqua Teen Hunger Force. He is the most rational and intelligent member of the Aqua Teens. He is also considered to be a scientist; although, some of his motives and means of doing scientific research are a bit shady at times.

Name: Galien
Summary: Galien was a brave and undefeated warrior who claimed to be the strongest in Hallownest and desired to prove his valour to the Pale King as a Knight. He travelled to Deepnest in order to test his strength, but eventually found death instead.

Name: Garrador
Summary: Garradors are hosts enhanced by the Plaga parasite, clad in armor and claws to enhance their killing efficiency, but chained in cells with their eyelids sewn shut to keep it controlled. They are encountered by Leon Kennedy during his mission to Spain.

Name: Gendrome
Summary: Gendrome are Bird Wyverns introduced in Monster Hunter.

Name: General Tesler
Summary: General Tesler is the main antagonist of TRON: Uprising. He is one of CLU's generals and is both extremely ambitious and a coldly calculating sadist. Tesler rules over Argon City from his command ship.

Name: Giadrome
Summary: Giadrome is a Bird Wyvern introduced in Monster Hunter Freedom 2. It is physically very similar to the Velocidrome, the only key difference being the pale blue colouration and the presence of a frost sac.

Name: Giant Medic
Summary: The Giant Medic heals its patient (almost always a Giant Robot) at 200 times the heal rate of the standard Quick-Fix, fast enough to virtually instantaneously outheal any kind of damage the players can inflict.

Name: Gigginox
Summary: Gigginox is a Flying Wyvern introduced in Monster Hunter 3.

Name: Glenn Quagmire
Summary: https://vsbattles.fandom.com/wiki/File:Giggity_X_4.ogg

Name: Godzilla (Heisei)
Key: '''Godzillasaurus''' | '''Return of Godzilla/vs. Biollante (Pre-Supercharge)''' | '''vs. King Ghidorah/vs. Mothra (Post-Supercharge)''' | '''vs. Mechagodzilla/Post-Rodan Boost''' | '''vs. SpaceGodzilla''' | '''Burning Godzilla'''
Summary: In the 1970s, a nuclear submarine crashed in the Bering Sea. A Godzillasaurus, barely hanging on to life in the cold ocean depths, was heavily mutated to a staggering height of 80 meters. This dinosaur had been relocated to this remote area by time travelers from the 23rd century, but little did they realize that their actions would actually fulfill the course of history and create the Godzilla they had sought to destroy...

Name: Golden Ball
Summary: Golden Ball (黄金ボール, Ōgon Bōru) is an A-Class Superhero, rank 26. He was partnered with Spring Mustachio to investigate the monster rumor in Z-City.

Name: Gorb
Summary: Gorb was a creature with a distended brain who claimed to be all-knowing. They goaded others to revere their mind and ascend with them to a different plane of existence. Their remains were buried on a hill atop the Howling Cliffs, with a tombstone carved in their image.

Name: Gravedigger
Summary: The Grave Digger (グレイブディガ) is an irregular mutant that was created when an overload of waste transported out from the Raccoon City Underground Laboratory led to the P-12A incinerator facility leaking t-Virus into the soil, thus mutating the local millipedes.

Name: Great Apiposu
Summary: Great Apiposu are Bird Wyverns introduced in Monster Hunter Explore.

Name: Great Baggi
Summary: Great Baggi is a Bird Wyvern introduced in Monster Hunter 3.

Name: Great Maccao
Summary: Great Maccao are Bird Wyverns introduced in Monster Hunter Generations.

Name: Great Nailsage Sly
Summary: Sly is a small bug found in the Forgotten Crossroads suffering from the infection, but is easily brought back to reality when found by The Knight. He will be later found in Dirtmouth in his shop where he sells several items to the Knight including a few charms. After the Knight has learned the three Nail Arts from Oro, Mato and Sheo he will reveal that he is the Great Nailsage and taught Oro, Mato and Sheo everything they know. In the Godmaster DLC he will become the final fight of the Pantheon of the Sage in Godhome.

Name: Great Wroggi
Summary: Great Wroggi is a Bird Wyvern introduced in Monster Hunter Portable 3rd.

Name: Griffon (Godzilla)
Summary: Griffon (グリホン) is a surgically altered lion kaiju who first appeared in the 1969 Toho film, Latitude Zero.

Name: Grimm (Hollow Knight)
Summary: Troupe Master Grimm, or simply known as Grimm, is a character within the metroidvania title Hollow Knight. Grimm is the leader of the Grimm Troupe, having travelling to Hallownest in needs to continue and hopefully finish what he calls, "The Ritual".

Name: Grimmkin
Summary: Grimmkin are enemies in Hollow Knight. They are members of the Grimm Troupe, a group of travelling 'performer bugs' of various species. Their colour theme is red, and they all wear white masks with vertical splits crossing their eyes.

Name: Groundskeeper Willie
Summary: William MacMoran is the groundskeeper for Springfield Elementary. He often is referred to as Groundskeeper Willie, and is a very proud Scotsman, though his past is very shady and clouded with mystery. He consistently lies and changes his past including his father being killed, him being incapable of firing a gun, and the part of Scotland he comes from. He has even made up stories where he himself didn't come out alive. It's likely that Willie is crazy, as him being connected with a famous killer known as The Aberdeen Strangler is something he didn't even try to deny. As well, he has accidentally killed at least two other students. He is dysfunctional and has drinking issues along with his hot headed temper.

Name: Gruzzer
Summary: Gruzzers are enemies in Hollow Knight. They are round bugs with small wings and a shrivelled proboscis who pay little attention to their surroundings.

Name: Guanzorumu
Summary: Guanzorumus are Elder Dragons introduced in Monster Hunter Frontier G10.

Name: Guile
Summary: Guile (ガイル Gairu) is a video game character in Capcom's Street Fighter series of fighting games, introduced in Street Fighter II. Although his role in the Street Fighter story was at first minimal, he is considered the third leading male character in the series, after Ryu and Ken, largely due to his effectiveness as a character and his popularity.

Name: Heavy
Summary: Like a hibernating bear, the Heavy appears to be a gentle giant. Also like a bear, confusing his deliberate, sleepy demeanor with gentleness will get you ripped limb from limb. Though he speaks simply and moves with an economy of energy that's often confused with napping, the Heavy isn't dumb; He's not your big friend and he generally wishes that you would just shut up before he has to make you shut up.

Name: Hedorah
Summary: Hedorah (ヘドラ) is an alien pollution kaiju created by Toho that first faced Godzilla in the 1971 Godzilla film, Godzilla vs Hedorah.

Name: Henry Emily
Summary: nan

Name: Hexapodus
Summary: Hexapodus was a Spider-like Hollow who chased after souls to consume them, was eventually killed and cleansed by Ichigo Kurosaki.

Name: Hive Knight
Summary: Hive Knight is an optional boss in Hollow Knight, introduced in Lifeblood. Defeating him grants a new Charm, Hiveblood. Hive Knight is the most valiant and skilled knight of the Hive; he is flightless and bound to protect Hive Queen Vespa by the Bees' hive mind.

Name: Hoglin
Summary: The Hoglin is a large, boar-like hostile mob that spawn within Crimson Forests in herds.

Name: Hollow Knight
Summary: Show reverence, o meagre one. Show fear! Thou approacheth a great and terrible God. Though its worldly body be bound and defiled, the glory of its pure form endures, ruler of this pantheon. Its endless power shall attune Us to the one greater still, a God of Gods!

Name: Homer Simpson
Summary: Homer Jay Simpson is the main protagonist of the animated sitcom series, The Simpsons, and one of the most recognizable cartoon characters of all time. He lives in the town of Springfield with his wife and three children and usually works as a nuclear power plant safety inspector, although over the years he has taken on many other jobs, such as being a food critic and a bodyguard. Generally, Homer takes a lazy and sometimes ignorant view on the world around him but has also shown genuine care and love for his family and friends. Homer Simpson was created by Matt Groening all the way back in 1987, with the character still going strong today.

Name: Hornet (Hollow Knight)
Summary: Come no closer, ghost. I've seen you, creeping through the undergrowth, stalking me. This old kingdom... A terrible thing awakens. I can smell it in the air... I know what you are. I know what you'd try to do. I can't allow it...

Name: Horseless Headless Horsemann
Summary: The Horseless Headless Horsemann, the undead form of Silas Mann, is a neutral enemy that appears in Mann Manor, the Carnival of Carnage, and the community Payload map Hellstone. In Mann Manor, approximately every 8 minutes, he spawns at the currently contested control point and hunts down players from both teams. He has a great deal of health, deals devastating damage in a single attack, and will continue to rampage until defeated by the players. In the Carnival of Carnage, he spawns in the bumper car games (except Duck Collector) after a certain amount of time, carrying the Necro Smasher instead of his normal weapon.

Name: Hunter (Resident Evil)
Summary: Hunters are bipedal reptilian-like creatures with large claws and teeth, and are noted for their loud shriek. They are B.O.W.s (Bio Organic Weapons) designed by the Umbrella Corporation by combining a fertilized human ovum with reptilian (or in the case of the 'γ' model, amphibian) DNA and then implanting the t-Virus into the resulting creature.

Name: Hunter Thibodeaux (Dead Rising)
Summary: This page contains or depicts disturbing and/or graphic content that some may find upsetting, and that is only intended for mature audiences. Please proceed with caution.

Name: Ibuki
Summary: Ibuki (いぶき) is a video game character from the Street Fighter series, first appearing in Street Fighter III: New Generation. She is a young ninja living in a village entirely composed of ninjas, where she has been training since childhood.

Name: Ice King (Adventure Time)
Summary: The Ice King, also known as Simon Petrikov was a main recurring antagonist in Adventure Time, though now is considered something similar to a protagonist and was reverted back into his sane, non-magic human self in the finale of the main series. In the background of the show, before The Great Mushroom War, Simon was a respectable archaeologist, appearing to be mild-mannered, intelligent, kind and adventurous. On a trip to Scandinavia, Simon discovered a Crown of mysterious origin. After wearing his crown, his life changed for the worse. His relationship with his fiance was shattered and his sanity was starting to diminish. However, the crown would keep him alive, allowing him to be one of the very few human survivors of The Great Mushroom War.

Name: Ice King (Fortnite)
Summary: The Ice King is a character from the game Fortnite. The ruler of Polar Peak and the wielder of the legendary Infinity Blade, he wreaked havoc during Fortnite's seventh season by freezing the entire island over in minutes and summoning a legion of Ice Fiends across the map. The Ice King was formerly unlockable during Season 7 by getting to Tier 100 on the Battle Pass but has since been unavailable.

Name: Iggy
Origin: JoJo's Bizarre Adventure '''(Part III: Stardust Crusaders)'''
Summary: Iggy is a major character in the second half of JoJo's Bizarre Adventure Part III: Stardust Crusaders. Once a pure-breed champion who became a "king" of stray dogs in the slums of New York, he is captured by Muhammad Avdol and Joseph Joestar in order to aid them in their journey to Egypt to defeat Dio Brando.

Name: Impostor (Among Us)
Summary: The Impostor is the antagonist/protagonist (Depending on the role you're given at the start of the game) of the murder mystery game, Among Us. Its mission is to kill every Crewmate before they can finish all of their tasks while also trying to avoid suspicious actions that can make the Crewmates realize that it is the Impostor among them.

Name: Iodrome
Summary: Iodrome is a Bird Wyvern introduced in Monster Hunter.

Name: Iroh
Summary: Iroh is a supporting character in Avatar: The Last Airbender.

Name: Jack Krauser
Summary: Jack Krauser, was a former member of USSOCOM, serving alongside Leon S. Kennedy, then a STRATCOM agent, in an anti-viral weapons mission to South America. Faking his death soon after, Krauser ended up working for Albert Wesker. His SOCOM codename was "Silverdax".

Name: Jake Muller
Summary: Jake Muller is a young mercenary from Eastern Europe who was embroiled in a plot to use the C-Virus in a series of devastating terrorist attacks.

Name: Jake the Dog
Key: '''Seasons 1-Dungeon Train''' | '''Dungeon Train - Dad's Dungeon''' | '''Dad's Dungeon - Apple Wedding''' | '''Blade of Grass - Reboot''' | '''Two Swords - Elementals Arc''' | '''Season 10''' | '''Deceased'''
Summary: Jake is the deuteragonist of Adventure Time, is a dog/shape-shifter hybrid, he is Finn's constant companion, best friend, and adoptive brother. Jake has shape shifting abilities so he can "stretch" into different objects.

Name: Jamie Siu
Summary: Jamie Siu is a character introduced in Street Fighter 6. He protects Metro City's Chinatown using his mastery over drunken boxing and breakdance. Born in an uncaring family, young Jamie expressed his frustration by partaking in street brawls with other kids. This eventually led him to rysk his life in a fight with real criminals and making it out thanks to the intervention of Yun and Yang. That day Jamie decided to set his life straight and follow the example set by the Twin Dragons, in hope to one day become like them.

Name: Jason Lee Scott
Summary: Jason Lee Scott is the original Red Ranger of the Power Rangers series, and in a sense was the first true main character. He led the team during the struggles against Rita and even a bit into the Zedd times, but eventually left to attend a Peace Conference. He has later come back as the Gold Ranger in Zeo and as a Red Ranger in the special Forever Red.

Name: Jasper Beardly
Summary: He is a senior citizen in Springfield and Abe Simpson's best friend. Like Hans Moleman, he suffers many accidents and injuries.

Name: Jed Wright
Summary: Jed Wright is the main antagonist and only psychopath of Dead Rising 2: Case Zero during the mission The Mechanic.

Name: Jill Valentine
Summary: Jill Valentine is one of the main protagonists in the Resident Evil series. She appears in the first game, Resident Evil 3, the "End of Umbrella" scenario, Revelations, and the RE5 DLCs "Desperate Escape" and "Lost in Nightmares." She appears as a member of S.T.A.R.S. and then later fights zombies and bioterrorism. A senior member of S.T.A.R.S. belonging on the same team as Chris. Jill has also resigned from S.T.A.R.S. in Resident Evil 3 Nemesis and attempts to escape from the T-virus infested town, Raccoon City. She runs into Nemesis, a B.O.W. from Umbrella Corp. Nemesis relentlessly pursued Jill throughout the city. At some point, Nemesis managed to infect Jill with T-NE-virus. She also meets a member of the U.B.C.S. Carlos Olivera. In the end, Jill managed to kill Nemesis, and together with Carlos and Barry, escaped the city successfully.

Name: Jo Slade
Summary: Jo Slade is a psychopath appearing in Dead Rising.

Name: Joe Swanson
Summary: Joseph "Joe" Swanson is a macho paraplegic police officer in the Quahog Police Department who is at many times subject to intense anger problems. He is married to Bonnie Swanson and has two children; Susie and Kevin.

Name: John Hemlock (Dead Rising 3)
Summary: John Hemlock was a former General and the Secretary of Defense in the United States. He's commonly referred to as "Hemlock" by civilians. Hemlock worked with Marian Mallon during a zombie outbreak in Los Perdidos by deactivating chips. Although the plan was to find Nick Ramos, Hemlock found out about King Zombies, and instead decided to harvest them for a new, destructive bio-weapon.

Name: JP
Summary: JP is the main antagonist of Street Fighter 6. Former member of Shadaloo, he rose to power in the wake of M. Bison's downfall while also obtaining his Psycho Power for himself. JP is a mastermind who built his wealth through large-scale financial crimes, always escaping unpunished thanks to his ability to manipulate others.

Name: Juri Han
Summary: Juri Han (ハン・ジュリ Han Juri, Hangul: 한주리, Hanja: 韓蛛俐) is a character in the Street Fighter series. She makes her debut in Super Street Fighter IV, where she is a main character in the storyline. She is 25 years old (as of Super Street Fighter IV) and is described as a brutal and sadistic member of S.I.N. who relishes fighting and inflicting pain upon her foes.

Name: Kairi Sisigou
Summary: Kairi Sisigou (獅子劫 界離, Shishigō Kairi) is the Master of Saber of Red in the Great Holy Grail War of Fate/Apocrypha.

Name: Kamacuras
Summary: Kamacuras (カマキラス) is a praying mantis kaiju who first appeared in the 1967 Toho Godzilla film, Son of Godzilla. The result of native giant praying mantises being mutated by United Nations weather-controlling experiments on Sollgel Island, three Kamacuras unearthed Minilla's egg and forced the infant to hatch prematurely, attracting the attention of Godzilla.

Name: Karin Kanzuki
Summary: Karin Kanzuki is a character from the Street Fighter series. She was originally a character from the 1996 Street Fighter manga Sakura Ganbaru! authored by Masahiko Nakahira. Her character would be integrated into the video game series in Street Fighter Alpha 3, where she appears as a playable character. She then returned as a playable character in Street Fighter V.

Name: Ken Masters
Summary: Ken (ケン or 拳 "Fist"), also known by his full name, Ken Masters (ケン・マスターズ Ken Masutāzu), is a video game character created by Capcom. He is one of the main protagonists of the Street Fighter series. Ken is also stated to be the second most popular character in the series, coming second to his best friend Ryu. Like Ryu, Ken's goal is to test his power against many different fighters and strive to become stronger but holds more restraint due to not wanting to jeopardize his family life.

Name: Kenny Dermot (Dead Rising)
Summary: After being unable to save a group of people from Zombies, Kenny Dermot took refuge at Big Bucks Construction Site to cry. However, once he got some help from Nick Ramos, Kenny became confident again... and envious. Kenny strived to be just like Nick, which resulted in the two clashing on a crashed yacht in Central City.

Name: Kent Swanson
Summary: Kent Swanson is a psychopath appearing in Dead Rising.

Name: Kim Kaphwan (The King of Fighters)
Key: '''Prologue Chapter (KOF '94) ''' | '''Chapter of Orochi Saga (KOF '95 to KOF '97)''' | '''Chapter of NESTS Saga (KOF '99 to KOF 2001)''' | '''Chapter of Ash Saga (KOF 2003 to KOF XIII)'''
Summary: nan

Name: Kimberly Jackson
Summary: Kimberly Jackson is a character introduced in Street Fighter 6. She is a young prodigy who pursues the dream to become a ninja and keep her city safe from criminals. After having been saved by Guy from a bunch of thugs, Kimberly's amazement prompted her into forced her way into Bushinryu uninvited.

Name: Kingsmould
Summary: Kingsmoulds are enemies in Hollow Knight. They are Void constructs who were made by the Pale King to serve as guards in and around the White Palace.

Name: Kombu Infinity
Summary: Kombu Infinity is a Tiger level threat that wandered Z-City after hearing rumors of powerful monsters gathering in it. When none of these monsters actually appear, however, Kombu decides to take their place and act as one of the rumored monsters, confronting and easily defeating A-Class heroes Golden Ball and Spring Mustachio in battle. However, when Saitama finds them while wandering the streets after buying groceries he remembers he forgot to buy kombu stock. He proceeds to casually defeat Kombu and strip them of all of their kombu seaweed tentacles to make soup with them, leaving the Mysterious Being's body completely barren.

Name: Kool-Aid Man (Family Guy)
Summary: Kool-Aid Man is a gag character in the animated series, Family Guy.

Name: Koyori Hakui (Holo no Graffiti)
Summary: Koyori Hakui is a scientist and a coyotegirl. She's the self-proclaimed "brains of the operation" of Secret Society holoX and is in charge of R&D. She possesses infinite curiosity and an insatiable thirst for knowledge, which pushes her to sometimes deliberately mess with people just to see how they react, including her fellow members. She's prideful about her creations, but her skill as a researcher is truly genuine.

Name: Krusty the Clown (Fortnite)
Summary: Krusty the Clown, or just Krusty, is a Boss character that can be found during second storm at one of his branded locations. He sports his signature weapon of Krusty's Mr. Blasty to take Loopers down.[1]

Name: Kuyo
Summary: Tier 9-A | 8-C | At least 8-B

Name: Kyo Kusanagi
Key: '''Prologue Chapter (KOF '94)''' | '''Chapter of Orochi Saga (KOF '95 to KOF '97)''' | '''Chapter of NESTS Saga (KOF '99 to KOF 2001)''' | '''KOF Sky Stage''' | '''Chapter of Ash Saga (KOF 2003 to KOF XIII)'''
Summary: nan

Name: Larry Chiang
Summary: Larry Chiang (拉里蔣, Lā lǐ jiǎng) is a psychopath in Dead Rising.

Name: Laura Matsuda
Summary: Laura Matsuda (ララ・マツダ/松田 Rara Matsuda) is a Street Fighter character first appearing in Street Fighter V. She is a highly energetic Brazilian fighter that enjoys thrills and sparring. She likes giving advice to others and is easy to befriend.

Name: Leon S. Kennedy
Summary: Leon Scott Kennedy is one of the main characters in the Resident Evil horror media franchise by Capcom. He debuted as one of the two playable protagonists of the video game Resident Evil 2. Leon later returned as the main character of Resident Evil 4 and as one of the protagonists in Resident Evil Darkside Chronicles and Resident Evil 6.

Name: Licker
Summary: Lickers are the result of a further mutation experienced by Zombies as part of the same V-ACT process that transforms them into a Crimson Head. First encountered during the Raccoon City Incident, they were named nick-named "Lickers" by the surviving officers of the Raccoon Police Department due to their notoriously large tongues which they used to hunt down their prey.

Name: Lily Hawk
Summary: Lily Hawk is a character introduced in Street Fighter 6. She is a member of the Thunderfoot, a tribe from Mexico, of which also T. Hawk was part. Gifted with the power to communicate with the spirits of nature, especially the wind spirit Toyno'Ikonoi, Lily follows their guidance in her journeys.

Name: Lisa Simpson
Summary: Lisa Marie Simpson is a main character in The Simpsons. She is a highly intelligent 8-year-old girl who serves as the voice of reason in her family. Lisa is the eldest daughter and middle child of the Simpson family.

Name: Llama (Minecraft)
Summary: Llamas are neutral mobs that spawn in herds and are found in Savanna Plateaus and Extreme Hills biomes.

Name: Lois Griffin
Summary: Lois Griffin is a main character in the American animated sitcom, Family Guy.

Name: Looters (Dead Rising)
Summary: The Looters is a group of people who after the zombie outbreak, start to loot abandoned stores and robbing ant survivors they find. A group even trying to gang up on Chuck Greene, however failed in their attempt. While most of them are aggressive, a certain few such as Septimus, Banchester, and Tarquin, started to sell stuff they looted from around the mall.

Name: Ludroth
Summary: Ludroth are Leviathans introduced Monster Hunter 3.

Name: Luke Sullivan
Summary: Luke Sullivan is a street fighter, a former member of the US Special Forces and one of the main protagonists of Street Fighter 6. He vowed himself to fight terrorism since the day, as a kid, he witnessed his father sacrificing his life to save him and other people from a bomb planted in a mall.

Name: Lumpy
Summary: Lumpy is the school snake of Springfield Elementary. Lumpy was a frequent predator of Springfield's children, to the point where the school handbook had a clause exempting the school from liability if Milhouse was eaten.

Name: Luna (The Boondocks)
Summary: Luna is a single appearing character in The Boondocks. As a child, Luna grew up with a father who was abusive to her mother, and had multiple horrible relationships with abusive men throughout her adult life. Her best friend, Nicole (who never appears on-screen), constantly feeds the already emotionally unstable Luna bad advice, such as telling her the men are completely at fault and that they should be severely punished, even killed.

Name: M. Bison
Key: '''Base''' | '''Empowered by the Psycho Drive''' | '''Empowered by the Black Moons''' | '''Street Fighter VI'''
Summary: For unknown reasons, the child who grew up to be M. Bison (Vega in Japan) murdered his parents in cold blood before he was adopted by a tribe of Romani who taught him the art of Soul Power, an ancient art that allows the user to manipulate one's soul. Bison quickly mastered Soul Power and used it to expel all of the good and humanity out of him, turning him into an egotistical psychopath. He then evolved Soul Power into Psycho Power, took on the title M. Bison, and organized a group of mercenaries to help him succeed in global conquest.

Name: Maggie Simpson
Summary: Maggie Simpson is one of the main protagonists of The Simpsons. She is the daughter of Marge Simpson and Homer Simpson. She is 1-year old and their youngest child. Most of the time, Maggie is seen chewing on her pacifier or attempting to walk. She mostly seems like an innocent and sweet baby who just wants her family to stay happy, to learn, and to suck on her iconic pacifier. However, she also on some occasions shows far more self-awareness than she lets on. Several times having wielded different guns, intentionally tried to shoot Mr. Burns a second time, saving her family from The Mob, and several other threats.

Name: Magica De Spell
Summary: Magica De Spell is one of the primary antagonists of the Disney cartoon, Ducktales. She is one of the main rivals to Scrooge McDuck, as she plans to make a powerful magic amulet by obtaining his number one dime.

Name: Magma Cube
Summary: The Magma Cube is a monster found in the Nether. It is a sentient cube of Magma, capable of duplicating.

Name: Mai Shiranui (Street Fighter)
Summary: Mai Shiranui is a guest character from the Fatal Fury series. She is the inheritor and current master of Shiranui-style ninjutsu. Together with her boyfriend Andy Bogard, brother of Terry Bogard, she stands at the head of the Shiranui clan and carries on the family legacy to pass the style to new apprentices.

Name: Makoto (Street Fighter)
Summary: Makoto (まこと) is a Street Fighter character from Street Fighter III 3rd Strike and Super Street Fighter IV. She is a tomboyish Japanese teenager looking to bring back the glory to her late father's dōjō. Although she's still young and a bit short, her karate form is very impressive.

Name: Manny (Ice Age)
Summary: Manfred, known more commonly as Manny, is one of the main protagonists of the Ice Age franchise.

Name: Manon Legrand
Summary: Manon Legrand is a character introduced in Street Fighter 6. A judoka and model from France, Manon wants to show the world who she truly is on her own terms. Since she was a child, Manon was torn by the pressure of her family, the abandonment of her mother and the expectations of her peers.

Name: Marge Simpson
Summary: Marge Simpson is one of the main protagonists of the animated sitcom series, The Simpsons. She is a loving mother to her son Bart, and her daughters Lisa and Maggie. As well, married to her husband Homer Simpson. She is a stay-at-home mom often acts as the voice of reason and logic when her husband or the town, in general, is getting into strange or stupid situations. She is generally very loving towards her kids and husband and is willing to almost anything to protect and help them. She is an extremely dedicated and hard worker. Whether she is working at home, taking a job as a police officer, or helping her children. She always puts her best effort into anything she does.

Name: Marisa
Summary: Marisa is a character introduced in Street Fighter 6. She is a Pankratiast who fights in the Colosseum like an ancient gladiator, upholding the legacy of her Greek ancestor and seeking glory in battle against the the mightiest opponents.

Name: Markoth
Summary: Markoth was the only moth to carry a weapon besides Thistlewind. He went to Kingdom's Edge to seclude himself and meditate, hoping to uncover a truth long forgotten. Markoth fought any who would threaten him, regardless of their reasons.

Name: Marmu
Summary: Marmu was the innocent-minded yet strong protector of the Queen's Gardens. The Queen promised to teach her how to fly upon her return to the verdant retreat. Marmu passed away before that day and a totem in her memory was placed upon her grave in the gardens' wilds

Name: Medic (Team Fortress 2)
Summary: What he lacks in compassion for the sick, respect for human dignity, and any sort of verifiable formal training in medicine, the Medic more than makes up for with a bottomless supply of giant needles and a trembling enthusiasm for plunging them into exposed flesh. Raised in Rottenburg, Germany during an era when the Hippocratic oath had been downgraded to an optional Hippocratic suggestion, the Medic considers healing a generally unintended side effect of satisfying his own morbid curiosity.

Name: Meg Griffin
Summary: Megan, aka Megatron "Meg" Harvey Oswald Griffin is the oldest child of Lois and Peter Griffin, and the sister of Chris and Stewie Griffin. She is currently attending James Woods Regional High School.

Name: Megumu Koyama
Summary: Megumu Koyama is an Esper and a former member of Claw. He was part of the upper echelon called "Scar".

Name: Menat
Summary: Menat is a playable character introduced in Street Fighter V. She is an Egyptian fortune teller, who lives at Palazzo Mistero in Genoa, under the teaching of Rose. She is both her assistant and apprentice, helping with various errands while learning to read the future and fight.

Name: Meowscles
Summary: Meowscles is a secret agent revealed in Chapter 2, Season 2. He is the housecat of Midas, a mysterious businessman who can transmute anything he wants into gold. In exchange for his services, Midas seems to have transmuted Meowscles’ weights into solid gold to make them weigh more, allowing Meowscles to bodybuild more easily.

Name: Merasmus
Summary: Merasmus the Magician, or simply Merasmus (also referred to as wizard, magician, or "idiot in a dress") is an important character in Team Fortress 2 Storyline. Merasmus has several appearances or references in the comics, hidden pages, and game maps. He has more roles in game play than any other non-player character. In the Team Fortress 2 Storyline, Merasmus has a connection with Demoman in the origin of MONOCULUS!; however, he most often appears as Soldier's long suffering former roommate. His appearances in comics or other media are usually related to releases of paranormal or haunted maps, with Soldier’s actions generally being the reason the mercenaries end up fighting there.

Name: Midas (Fortnite)
Summary: Midas is a Legendary skin and main antagonist of Fortnite Chapter 2, Season 2. He is the leader of Ghost and a double agent for Shadow. He is based on the Greek mythology, King Midas. At the end of Chapter 2 Season 2, he becomes Cyclo, the Defiant to the Storm. At the start of Chapter 2 Season 3, he gets attacked by a shark and survived. Around Chapter 2 Season 4, he becomes Shadow Midas.

Name: Minilla (Godzilla Final Wars)
Summary: Minilla is an infant member of Godzilla's species. In Godzilla: Final Wars, Minilla appears near Mount Fuji without explaining his origins.

Name: Minilla (Showa)
Summary: Minilla is an infant member of Godzilla's species. The 1998 informational book The Official Godzilla Compendium and Toho's official English-language website both state that Minilla was adopted by Godzilla as Son of Godzilla. In Son of Godzilla, Minilla hatches from an egg on Solgell Island after it is broken open by the Kamacuras.

Name: Moe Szyslak
Summary: Moe Szyslak is the bartender in Springfield. He spends most of his time in his bar selling drinks to his usual customers and friends Homer, Lenny, Carol, and Barney. He as well is shown to run illegal practices like holding and selling animals like Pandas and Orcas in the back of his bar. He is a often sneaky and lazy bar keeper. Refusing to clean his bar, and pulling quick ones on his customers. However, he can and still does feel guilt and compassion towards his closer friends like Homer, and will go out of his way to help them.

Name: Moira Burton
Summary: Moira Burton Moira Burton is one of Barry and Kathy Burton's daughters, and Polly Burton's sister. She is a playable character in Resident Evil Revelations 2 along with Claire Redfield.

Name: Monoculus
Summary: MONOCULUS is the RED Demoman's missing eye, haunted by the Bombinomicon. It was summoned by Merasmus when the RED Soldier broke his staff. In the Bombinomicon comic, it is depicted as a large brown floating eye that fires purple rocket-like eyeballs.

Name: Mother of Thorns
Summary: Mother Of Thorns, also known as Doja Cat, is a boss appearing in Fortnite during the Fortnitemares event.

Name: Mr. Burns
Summary: Charles Montgomery Plantagenet Schicklgruber "Monty" Burns,[1] usually referred to as Mr. Burns, is a recurring character and antagonist in the animated television series The Simpsons, voiced initially by Christopher Collins, and currently by Harry Shearer. He is the evil, devious, greedy, and wealthy owner of the Springfield Nuclear Power Plant and, by extension, Homer Simpson's boss. He is assisted at almost all times by Smithers, his loyal and sycophantic aide, adviser, confidant, and secret admirer. He is Springfield's richest, oldest, and most powerful citizen. His net worth has been stated to be in the billions and in one instance was pegged at exactly $1,800,037,022.[2]

Name: Mysterians
Summary: The Mysterians (ミステリアン) are a race of aliens created by Toho that first appeared in the 1957 film The Mysterians.

Name: Nailmasters Oro & Mato
Summary: Oro and Mato are brothers that trained in the art of Nail combat, alongside Paintmaster Sheo, under the Great Nailsage Sly. Each brother can be found in different locations in Hollownest, Oro in Kingdom's Edge, Mato in Howling Cliffs, and will teach The Knight a different Nail Art when found. In the Godmaster DLC both Brothers can be fought as a duo boss in the Pantheon of the Master in Godhome.

Name: Necalli
Summary: Necalli (ネカリ Nekari) is a character in the Street Fighter series who first appeared in Street Fighter 5. Necalli is described as the 'Emissary of the Gods', with a rather ominous moniker of 'The Soul Consuming Darkness'. As the "Warrior Prophet" reveals, every few hundred years the stars herald the 'Hour of Battle' ('Hour of Necalli'). During this period of time Necalli awakens to consume the souls of strong warriors.

Name: Ned Flanders
Summary: Ned Flanders is a supporting character in the animated series, The Simpsons. He is the extremely religious next-door neighbor of the Simpson family. He is the well-mannered widower of Maude and father of Rod and Todd. He immensely worships God and is a strict follower of the Bible.

Name: Nemesis (Resident Evil)
Summary: https://vsbattles.fandom.com/wiki/File:Nemesis_sound_STARS.ogg

Name: Nick Ramos (Dead Rising)
Summary: This page contains or depicts disturbing and/or graphic content that some may find upsetting, and that is only intended for mature audiences. Please proceed with caution.

Name: No Eyes
Summary: They're coming... What's inside of you... Strip it out!

Name: Nosk
Summary: Nosk is a mysterious shape-shifting infected bug hunting throughout Deepnest. It can mimic the shape of faces it finds in the memories of bugs, usually loved or departed ones, and contort its body to assume the smaller frame of its lures. It hangs its preys from the ceiling within its lair at the bottom of Deepnest including Dirtcarvers, a Stalking Devout, and various Vessels.

Name: Numb Chandelier
Summary: Numb Chandelier is a Hollow, creepy in appearance and vindictive in nature, she was killed after Orihime Inoue first gains her Fullbringer.

Name: Orihime Inoue
Key: '''Substitute Shinigami Arc''' | '''Soul Society Arc''' | '''Arrancar Arc''' | '''Lost Agent Arc''' | '''Thousand Year Blood War Arc'''
Summary: Orihime Inoue (井上いのうえ 織姫おりひめ, Inoue Orihime?) is a Human living in Karakura Town. She is a student at Karakura High School, where she is in the same class as Ichigo Kurosaki and her best friend, Tatsuki Arisawa. At some point during the Epilogue, she and Ichigo fell in love and eventually started a family.

Name: Paintmaster Sheo
Summary: Paintmaster Sheo is a bug that trained under Sly, the Great Nailsage, with the brothers Oro and Mato, but has renounced his title as Nailmaster to seek a peaceful life as an Artist. He can be found in Greenpath and will teach The Knight a nail art if pressed. In the Godmaster DLC he will become the final fight of the Pantheon of the Artist in Godhome.

Name: Peely
Summary: Peely is one of many characters in Fortnite. Peely became a robot in Fortnite's Season X called P-1000. In Season 2, Chapter 2, he becomes an agent named, Agent Peely.

Name: Pekora Usada
Summary: Pekora Usada is a rabbitgirl and the princess of Pekoland, a country in another universe where all citizens are long-living and share rabbit-like traits. Pekora is bratty, devilish, ingenious in her making and pulling of pranks on others, and infamous for causing mischief. Her attempts sometimes backfire, however. She often rides the line between sensible and chaotic, as, behind her pranks and wild antics, she's quick to realize when things have gone too far. She loves carrots so much she always has some at her disposal. Her braids hold bizarre powers.

Name: Pesu
Summary: Pesu is the name of a giant wild beast alien that appears in Gintama. It was defeated by Gintoki at the first part of story.

Name: Pet Shop
Origin: JoJo's Bizarre Adventure '''(Part III: Stardust Crusaders)'''
Summary: Pet Shop is a minor antagonist in JoJo's Bizarre Adventure Part III: Stardust Crusaders. He is a trusted pet of Dio Brando and the guardian of his mansion.

Name: Peter Griffin
Summary: https://vsbattles.fandom.com/wiki/File:RoadHouseByPeterGriffin.ogg

Name: Phantom (Minecraft)
Summary: Phantoms are common, undead flying hostile mobs that attack players who haven't slept in over three in-game days.

Name: Pickaxe (Fortnite)
Summary: The Pickaxe is the starter weapon every player in Fortnite acquires. It can break through walls and significantly hurt other players.

Name: Piers Niavans
Summary: Piers Nivans was a combat operative for the North American Branch of the BSAA, assigned to the SOU (Special Operations Unit). Nivans served under Captain Chris Redfield during the investigation into the incident at the Marhawa School; the 2012 Edonian Civil War and the 2013 campaign in China.

Name: Pinkie Pie (Human World)
Summary: Pinkie Pie is one of the main characters of My Little Pony Equestria Girls, and represents the Element of Laughter.

Name: Pokaradon
Summary: Pokaradon are Leviathans introduced in Monster Hunter Frontier G1.

Name: Popokarimu
Summary: The Popokarimu is a B.O.W. which realized the compatibility of high destruction ability and high flying ability with the increase in size by making the plague infest the bat and repeating the improvement. The symbiosis with the parasite enables complex genetic modification, and the number of wings double as the legs have increased to four. Although the weak plaga is exposed in the tail, the front side is made of a hard armor that can not catch bullets, as seen in the barrier of the majini parasite mutant, and the movement of the prey from the mucous membrane on the back side secretes spider-like filamentous material. ~translated excerpt from kaitaishinsho

Name: Princess Bubblegum
Summary: Princess Bonnibel Bubblegum, also known a P.B. and Peebles is one of the main characters in Adventure Time. She is the kind and compassionate ruler of the Candy Kingdom and is one of Finn's best friends. She originally met Finn when he saved her from the Ice King during the original pilot. Bonnibel is also extremely intelligent and is considered one of the top minds in all of Ooo. She has created many lifeforms such as her Candy People, the Earl of Lemongrab, Goliad and more.

Name: Principal Skinner
Summary: Seymour Skinner, also known as Principal Skinner, is the principal of Springfield Elementary School. He has a passion for education which is consistently challenged by a lack of school funds, incompetent teachers and unenthusiastic students, the most notable being Bart Simpson. He is generally strict on discipline, likely stemming from his time serving in the army, but is otherwise quite nervous and fidgety.

Name: Pyro
Summary: The Pyro is a mumbling pyromaniac of indeterminate origin who has a burning passion for all things fire related. The Pyro appears to be insane and delusional, living in a utopian fantasy world known as Pyroland.

Name: Q (Street Fighter)
Summary: Q (キュ Kyu) is a character in the Street Fighter series. He first appeared in Street Fighter III: 3rd Strike, and is voiced by Len Carlson. While Q can be chosen as a playable character, he is also a "hidden" computer-controlled sub-boss in Arcade Mode that can only be battled after meeting specific requirements: the player must win the first eight matches without losing a round.

Name: Quirrel
Summary: Quirrel is a character that appears throughout Team Cherry's Hollow Knight, an up-beat and recurring ally that appears throughout The Knight's journey across Hallownest. Noted to be more of an observer than a warrior, he is nevertheless a skilled fighter and explorer that finds himself fascinated by the myths of Hallownest for reasons he can't explain.[1]

Name: Quorra
Summary: Quorra is the confidante and apprentice of Kevin Flynn. Flynn has shared his knowledge of the real world with her, and as such, she longs to experience what lies outside the realm of possibility in her own world. She is the last known ISO alive and is referred to by Kevin Flynn as "The Miracle".

Name: Rainbow Dash (Human World)
Summary: Rainbow Dash is one of the main characters in My Little Pony Equestria Girls.

Name: Rainbow Mika
Summary: Rainbow Mika (レインボー・ミカ), often shortened to R. Mika, is a video game character from the Street Fighter series. Her true name is Mika Nanakawa (七川 美華). She is a Japanese professional wrestler from Iwashigahama Japan Women's Pro-Wrestling organization, trained by Yoko Harmageddon. She first made her debut in Street Fighter Alpha 3 and returned in Street Fighter V.

Name: Ramza Beoulve
Summary: Ramza Beoulve, also known as Ramza Lugria, is the main protagonist in Final Fantasy Tactics. Third son of House Beoulve, son of Barbaneth Beoulve and a commoner woman of the Lugria family, Ramza is the younger half-brother of Dycedarg and Zalbaag, and the full older sibling of Alma.

Name: Rarity (Human World)
Summary: Rarity is one of the main characters of My Little Pony Equestria Girls, and represents the Element of Generosity.

Name: Rashid
Summary: Rashid (ラシード Rashīdo, Arabic: رشيد Rashīd) is a character in the Street Fighter series who first appeared in Street Fighter V. He was first officially unveiled on September 11, 2015 at a Dubai game show and was the second of the four new fighters confirmed for Street Fighter V. Rashid is also the second male Middle Eastern fighter within the main games (after Hakan); counting the Street Fighter EX series, he would be the third Middle Eastern fighter, following the Arabic fighter Pullum Purna.

Name: Rebecca Chambers
Summary: Dr. Rebecca Chambers is a former member of S.T.A.R.S., a special forces unit of the Raccoon Police Department. Despite her sweet and seemingly fragile appearance, she is a medical expert and a capable fighter. She is currently a professor at a university in Chicago, USA.

Name: Retep
Summary: Retep is a one-episode character in the animated series, Family Guy.

Name: RJ
Summary: Robert James, usually referred to as RJ, is the laid-back and carefree master and instructor of the Jungle Fury Power Rangers, as well as, the boss and owner of a pizza restaurant that serves as their headquaters. During his childhood, his father, Master Finn, constantly tried to force RJ to learn the Shark Technique in order become a Shark Master. RJ, being against this, left home and found his own master, who instructed him in the ways of the Wolf. Upon mastering his Wolf Spirit, RJ became the new Wolf Master and eventually the Jungle Fury Wolf Ranger after his students help him revert from his werewolf form, a curse inflicted by Da' Shi.

Name: Roman Bridger
Summary: https://vsbattles.fandom.com/wiki/File:RomanMonolouge3.ogg

Name: Rosie (One-Punch Man)
Summary: Rosie was a martial artist and user of the Psycho Analysis Martial Arts. He participated in the 22nd Super Fight Tournament. He became a monster after being threatened by Gouketsu, but was killed by Choze right after.

Name: Ruby Tojo
Summary: As a young child, her parents were killed in a car crash. As a result of this, she became a human-hating witch serving under Lady Oyakata. She later betrayed her after meeting the human Tsukune. She later becomes the Headmaster's assistant and helps defend Japan against Fairy Tale.

Name: Rudy (Ice Age)
Summary: Rudy was a gigantic albino Baryonyx that lived in the underground world during the Ice Age and the bane of the weasel Buck's existence.

Name: Ryoichi Shiraishi
Summary: Ryoichi Shiraishi (白石亮一) is an astrophysicist and one of the main characters in the 1957 Toho film, The Mysterians.

Name: Ryu (Street Fighter)
Summary: The lead character of the Street Fighter franchise and a fighting game character, Ryu is a stoic Japanese martial artist who wanders the globe seeking the meaning of being a "true warrior". He can be recognized by his sleeveless white karate gi and a red or white hachimaki/headband depending on the game. He trained alongside his friendly rival Ken under their mutual master Gouken and was the victor of the first Street Fighter tournament. His encounter with his master's nemesis Akuma during the Street Fighter Alpha sub-series awoke the untapped Satsui no Hadou or "murderous intent" within him although this power was eventually overwhelmed in Street Fighter V, when he mastered the Power of Nothingness, a source of higher power arising from a state of consciousness in which the mind is free from thoughts and emotions. In Street Fighter III, he continues to travel the world in search of strong opponents.

Name: Sagat
Summary: Sagat (サガット, Sagatto, Thai: สกัด) is a character in the Street Fighter series. First appearing in the original Street Fighter as the final boss, Sagat was originally a boss character in the early editions of the series. He was later turned into a regular, playable character.

Name: Sakura Kasugano
Summary: Sakura Kasugano (春日野 さくら, Kasugano Sakura) is a character in the Street Fighter series who made her debut in Street Fighter Alpha 2. She is a seemingly normal Japanese high school girl. Sakura decided to take on street fighting after witnessing her idol Ryu in battle. She has managed to copy and learn some of Ryu's techniques but really wants him to train her personally. She uses a self-taught imitation of Ryu's martial art with her own versions of his special techniques.

Name: Sam Flynn
Summary: Sam Flynn: Your boss works for the CEO, and the CEO works for the shareholders. Now, do you know who the biggest shareholder is? Security Guard: I don't know some kid?... You're Mr. Flynn? Why? This is your fathers company! Sam Flynn: Not anymore.

Name: Santa’s Little Helper
Summary: Santa’s Little Helper is the family dog in The Simpsons.

Name: Scout
Summary: https://vsbattles.fandom.com/wiki/File:Meet_The_Scout_%22Grass_grows%22.wav

Name: Scrooge McDuck
Summary: Scrooge McDuck was born in Glasgow, Scotland in 1867 to a poor family and was the oldest of three siblings. At the age of 10, Scrooge became a shoe polisher to earn more money for his family, but his first client scammed him by paying with an American dime, unusable in Scotland. Nevertheless, Scrooge keeps the dime and, recognizing it as the start of something big, moves to the U.S. at age 13 to work as a river-boater with his uncle.

Name: Sean Keanan
Summary: Sean Keanan is a psychopath appearing in Dead Rising and Dead Rising: Chop Till You Drop. As the leader of the True Eye cult, Sean is obsessed with "purifying" survivors by killing them to cleanse their "tainted" blood. His cult members roam the mall until Frank West discovers their hideout in Colby's Movieland and defeats Sean.

Name: Sensei (Club Penguin)
Summary: Sensei (labeled ?????? before his identity was revealed) is a character in Club Penguin. A long-lived ninja master, he resides in the Dojo he built where he teaches penguins, who he refers to as his students, about the ancient art of Card-Jitsu.

Name: Shaggy Rogers (Cartoon)
Summary: Norville "Shaggy" Rogers is a member of Mystery Inc., and the owner and best friend of their team's mascot: Scooby Doo, a talking Great Dane.

Name: Sherry Birkin
Summary: Sherry Birkin is one of the main characters in the Resident Evil series. She was born around 1986 to the Umbrella virologist, William Birkin, and his research colleague and new wife, Annette, when the two were both working at the Arklay Laboratory. She is one of the survivors of the Raccoon City incident, thanks to Claire Redfield and Leon S. Kennedy, who came to her aid. They eventually escaped the fallen city together.

Name: Sheva Alomar
Summary: Sheva Alomar (シェバ・アローマ Sheba Arōma) is a fictional character in the Resident Evil horror video series by Capcom. She first appeared in Resident Evil 5 as one of the main characters. She was introduced in the E3 trailer and later on in E3 demo videos where she was a playable character that assists Chris Redfield throughout the game. She was introduced in 2009's Resident Evil 5 as a native African operative of the Bioterrorism Security Assessment Alliance (BSAA) and a new partner of the series' veteran Chris Redfield. The character was met with mostly positive reception, but has yet not returned for any further installment of the series. Operating as part of its West African branch. She was assigned to the current mission to assist Chris Redfield, who was unfamiliar with the area. A versatile fighter with extensive experience, her ability to use firearms is on par with Chris. She is much smaller and more flexible than Chris, enabling her to perform certain maneuvers that Chris cannot. In turn, this allows Chris to throw her up to high ledges, or over large gaps in order to reach areas or objectives that a lone operative couldn't reach.

Name: Shrieker
Summary: Shrieker is an extremely cruel and evil Hollow, previously a serial killer in his human life, he hunts down and torments his victims, was eventually killed and sent to hell for his heinous crimes while alive by Ichigo Kurosaki.

Name: Sid (Ice Age)
Summary: Sidney, known more commonly as Sid, is one of the main protagonists of the Ice Age franchise. He is a ground sloth who was part of a herd of different animals after a number of adventures and experiences brought them all together.

Name: Silverfish (Minecraft)
Summary: The Silverfish is a rare kind of monster found either high up in the mountains or in the strongholds near the End. They are quite weak individually, though they often come in very large groups.

Name: Slime (Minecraft)
Summary: A Slime is a hostile mob that spawns in caves underground or in swamps. It is squishy and can vary in sizes. The smallest of the slimes are harmless and deal no damage. However, the bigger the slime is, the more capable it is to harm a player.

Name: Sludge Jellyfish
Summary: Sludge Jellyfish is a member of the Monster Association, and like Phoenix Man, he is one of the few rational monsters who aren't prompt to attack humans on sight, and by his own accord a monster who bears grudges. Sludge Jellyfish's body is comprised of liquids, giving him a natural resistance to physical attacks and the ability to absorb other liquids into his body.

Name: Snake Jailbird
Summary: Chester Turley, better known as Snake Jailbird, is a recurring antagonist in the animated TV series The Simpsons and a minor antagonist in the 2007 theatrical film The Simpsons Movie. He is a recidivist criminal, always getting arrested, but rarely being kept locked up for long. He speaks with a "Valley Boy" accent and has a tattoo of a snake on his arm, which is presumably the source of his nickname.

Name: Sneed
Summary: Sneed is a farmer that appears in the episode E-I-E-I-(Annoyed Grunt). He is the owner of the convenience store Sneed's Feed and Seed (Formerly Chuck's).

Name: Sniper
Summary: The Sniper is one of the support classes in Team Fortress 2. His job is to defend the base while also attacking enemy targets from afar. Half rugged outdoorsman, half alien observer, this taciturn strip of beef jerky has spent the better part of his life alone in the bush, slow baking under the Australian sun.

Name: Snowball 2
Summary: Snowball 2 is the black cat that The Simpsons family took in after their original cat, Snowball 1, was killed. Snowball 2 is often portrayed as fairly intelligent for an animal, understanding human english, and pulling off human activities such as dancing. Aside from her decent intelligence shown every now and then, she is your typical stereotypical cat. She lived as the Simpsons family cat for many years until being ran over and killed by Dr. Herbert in season 15.

Name: Snowball V
Summary: nan

Name: Sokka
Summary: Sokka was a Water Tribe warrior of the Southern Water Tribe and the son of Chief Hakoda and Kya.

Name: Soldier
Summary: I have personally killed 6,578 men in cold blood while looking them in the eye; jumped on 1,336 live grenades; and stuffed fourteen feet of my own intestine back into my stomach. If that doesn't scare you out of your frilly pink leotards, guess what: You are an idiot and you hate America.

Name: Soul Master
Summary: Soul Master is a main boss in Hollow Knight. Defeating him grants the Desolate Dive Spell. The Soul Tyrant is his dream variant. Soul Master is the leader of the Soul Sanctum of Hallownest, which searched for ways to expand the minds of bugs and attain pure focus.

Name: Spider (Minecraft)
Summary: The Spider is a common Minecraft monster from the Overworld. They're larger than usual monsters and are capable of climbing walls.

Name: Spot Master 6000
Summary: The Spot Master 6000 was a device used in the episode "The Krusty Plate" after SpongeBob had unsuccessfully tried to clean a spot off a plate via other means.

Name: Spring Mustachio
Key: '''Beginning of Series''' | '''Monster Raid Arc and Onwards'''
Summary: Spring Mustache (バネヒゲ, Banehige) is an A-Class Superhero, rank 28. He was partnered up with Golden Ball to investigate the monster rumor in Z-City.

Name: Spy
Summary: This Spy has already breached our defenses... You've seen what he's done to our colleagues! And worst of all: He could be any one of us.

Name: Steven Chapman
Summary: Steven Chapman is a psychopath appearing in Dead Rising.

Name: Stewie Griffin
Summary: Stewie Griffin is one of the main characters in the animated series, Family Guy.

Name: Suki
Summary: Suki is a major character in the animated series, Avatar: The Last Airbender.

Name: Sunset Shimmer
Key: '''Human''' | '''Unicorn Form''' | '''Element of Magic (Demon Form)''' | '''Pony-Up Form''' | '''Daydream Shimmer'''
Summary: Sunset Shimmer is a reformed villain from My Little Pony: Friendship is Magic.

Name: SWATbot (Archie Comics)
Summary: SWATbots are military robots in the Sonic the Hedgehog comic series and its spin-offs published by Archie Comics.

Name: T-A.L.O.S.
Summary: T-A.L.O.S. was created to be a superior and controllable version of the Tyrant, and Umbrella North America's response to Umbrella Europe's Nemesis project.

Name: Terry Bogard (Street Fighter)
Summary: Terry: You and I walk down different paths. And maybe the strength we're both after takes a different form, but...

Name: Terry Bogard (The King of Fighters)
Key: '''Prologue Chapter (KOF '94) ''' | '''Chapter of Orochi Saga (KOF '95 to KOF '97)''' | '''Chapter of NESTS Saga (KOF '99 to KOF 2001)''' | '''KOF Sky Stage''' | '''Chapter of Ash Saga (KOF 2003 to KOF XIII)'''
Summary: nan

Name: The Collector (Hollow Knight)
Summary: The Collector is a hidden boss in Hollow Knight. The Collector is a Void creature. It lives hidden away in the locked Tower of Love along with a large collection of bugs from throughout Hallownest that are preserved, both dead and alive, in glass jars.

Name: The Hateocracy
Summary: The Hateocracy are a gang of elderly, nasty, self-hating bigots and the major antagonists of the episode "Stinkmeaner 3: The Hateocracy".

Name: The Hunter (Hollow Knight)
Summary: A true Hunter has no home, no kingdom and I'm eager for new prey. You bear the mark now, but that's only the beginning. That mark will become a part of you, will engrave itself deep within, and that yearning to hunt... It will never leave.

Name: The Knight (Hollow Knight)
Summary: The Knight is the playable character of Team Cherry's hit Indie Metroidvania game, Hollow Knight. Their species was created as vessels by the Pale King to carry the Infection spread by the Radiance. Many details about the character, including their name, are left ambiguous; though it is likely that they do not have one, as all vessels except for one were considered impure by the King, and left to rot in the Abyss. However, the Knight and some of its other siblings managed to escape.

Name: The Looper (Fortnite Battle Royale)
Summary: The Looper (Also simply known as The Player) is the unnamed protagonist of the third-person shooter Fortnite (Battle Royale). The objective of the game is to be the last one standing (or be the last team standing) in a map of 100 other people, finding loot such as guns while avoiding the dangerous storm.

Name: The Player (Club Penguin)
Summary: The Player was the playable character of Club Penguin, a game that took place in an island inhabited by penguins. The Penguin's name depended on the player.

Name: The Player (Minecraft)
Summary: The Player is the protagonist of Minecraft. Known as either Steve or Alex depending on the player's choice, they are a lone miner in an endless blocky world, trying their best to survive.

Name: The Radiance
Summary: The Radiance is the forgotten goddess of Light of the Moth Tribe and source of the Infection plaguing Hollownest. She is the final boss of both the main game and the Godmaster DLC. When the Pale King took over the lands of Hollownest, he attempted to destroy her by erasing all evidence of her existence and allowing her to fade out of memory.

Name: The Visitor (Fortnite)
Summary: The Visitor is a mysterious entity who had arrived to the planet via a meteorite in Season 3 of Fortnite: Battle Royale, responsible for having launched the rocket during Season 4 as well. Though nothing is known about their original intentions, it was through the launching of this rocket that a multitude of spatial and temporal rifts were opened up within the atmosphere, leading to the events in Seasons 4 - 6.

Name: Thunder Hawk
Summary: Thunder Hawk is the gentle and wise hero of the Thunderfoot Tribe in Mexico. He seeks revenge against Shadaloo and M. Bison, which are guilty of many crimes against his people, such as poisoning the land, kidnapping villagers, murdering their leader Arroyo Hawk (T. Hawk's father) and turning Noembelu and Julia (the latter being T. Hawk's fiancee) into mindless assassins.

Name: Tommy Oliver
Key: '''Civilian''' | '''Mighty Morphin Power Rangers: Season 1''' | '''Mighty Morphin Power Rangers: Season 2''' | '''Mighty Morphin Power Rangers: Season 3''' | '''Red Zeo Form''' | '''Dino Thunder Black''' | '''Super Dino Mode'''
Summary: Tommy Oliver is the Green Mighty Morphin Ranger, White Mighty Morphin Ranger, Red Zeo Ranger, Red Turbo Ranger I & the Black Dino Ranger. He is often considered the greatest Power Ranger of all time both in and out of the actual show for his many accomplishments on several different teams. He is a fan favorite, the most reoccurring ranger, and second most reoccurring character in the entire show next to Bulk. He is also one of the strongest rangers.

Name: Trent Fernandez-Mercer
Summary: Trent Fernandez-Mercer is the White Dino Thunder Ranger, who was initially corrupted by the White Dino Gem but then reformed when the evil was removed from him by his adopted father, Dr. Anton Mercer. When his biological parents were killed in an archaeological cave-in, Dr. Mercer took him in, though he still kept his original surname. He works at Hayley's Cyberspace as a waiter and draws in his spare time, though he keeps this secret because his father does not approve of his artistic endeavours.

Name: Trini Kwan
Summary: Trini Kwan is the original Yellow Ranger of the Power Rangers series. She was the caring and optimistic member of the team during the war against Rita and served as the tactics expert on-board the Dino Megazord. She would go on to become a world peace ambassador following her retirement as a Ranger.

Name: Tron (TRON)
Summary: Tron is one of the main protagonists of the TRON franchise. He is a security computer program written by Alan Bradley, and in 1982 was taken prisoner by the self-aware Master Control Program and forced to play on the Game Grid. His legendary skills and devotion to the users turned him into a formidable warrior and Disc Arena master.

Name: Truckasaurus
Summary: Truckasaurus is a giant mechanical truck/dinosaur first appearing in "Bart the Daredevil". It was inspired by the real life robotic dinosaur, Robosaurus.

Name: Tusk (Club Penguin)
Summary: Tusk, also known as the Supreme Master of Snow, is a walrus and the primary antagonist at the Card-Jitsu Party 2013, the true antagonist behind Card-Jitsu Snow, and the leader of the Snow Minions. He is the one who sent Scrap, Sly, and Tank out to defeat Sensei and destroy the Dojo. Tusk seems to have hatred for Sensei and his Ninjas. He used to train in the art of Card-Jitsu with Sensei, his childhood best friend, but Tusk turned on Sensei out of jealousy. Players could battle in his lair after receiving the Snow Gem.

Name: Twilight Sparkle (Sci-Twi)
Summary: Twilight Sparkle is one of the main protagonists in the My Little Pony: Equestria Girls series.

Name: Tyrant T-002
Summary: The Tyrant T-002 is, as its name implies, the second form of the Tyrant and the first successful product of the Tyrant Project, which sought to create the ultimate life form.

Name: Tyrant T-103
Summary: The Tyrant T-103 is the first successful Tyrant, no longer a prototype like previous models. With intelligence close to that of a human, the T-103 can follow orders and perform complex tasks, and it is for this reason that it is mass-produced, with models being used for hunting down and kill targets or acquire objects.

Name: U-8
Summary: U-8 is a B.O.W. created by Tricell from the combination of Plagas parasites with the DNA of several shelled organisms. It attacked BSAA agents Chris Redfield and Sheva Alomar as they explored the Tricell Africa facility.

Name: Ustanak
Summary: Ustanak is a B.O.W. employed by Carla Radames in order to capture Jake Muller and use his blood for an enhanced C-Virus.

Name: Utahime Iori
Summary: Respect! Your! Elders!

Name: Uumuu
Summary: Uumuu is a main boss in Hollow Knight. It guards Monomon the Teacher, one of the Dreamers. Uumuu is an intelligent yet Infected being similar to the Uomas and Oomas infesting Fog Canyon. It defends Monomon's chamber at the heart of the Teacher's Archives.

Name: Vega
Summary: Vega, known in Japan as Balrog, also known as Claw, is a fictional character from the Street Fighter fighting game series by Capcom. Vega is a mask-wearing, claw-wielding fighter from Spain who uses a personal fighting style combining Japanese ninjutsu and Spanish bullfighting, earning him the nickname of "Spanish Ninja".

Name: Velocidrome
Summary: Velocidromes are Bird Wyverns introduced in Monster Hunter.

Name: Vengefly
Summary: Vengeflies are enemies in Hollow Knight. They are flying predators who inhabit many areas in Hallownest, although the Vengefly King is native to Greenpath.

Name: Verdugo
Summary: Salazar: So, maybe you have nine lives. But it doesn't matter now, Mr. Kennedy! I have sent my right hand to dispose of you. Leon S. Kennedy: Your right hand comes off?

Name: Victor Quartermaine
Summary: Lady Tottington: Victor, hadn't we agreed? No more thoughtless killing! Victor Quartermaine: Quite right, my dear, so I thought this one through very carefully: [aims rifle at bunny] It's off to bunny heaven for you, big ears!

Name: Wallace (Wallace & Gromit)
Summary: Wallace is one of the titular protagonists of the stop-motion animated comedy franchise Wallace & Gromit, in which he is a kindhearted, simple-minded inventor, who often creates new contraptions alongside his anthropomorphic dog Gromit to make conveniences to his life, although usually these inventions tend to fail.

Name: Wandering Trader
