Summary: The Wandering Trader is a passive mob from Minecraft. They can spawn anywhere in the Overworld, and come with their llamas and a variety of wares to sell in exchange for emeralds.

Name: Wild Horn
Summary: Wild Horn, B-Class Rank 6, is a hero and member of the Hero Association. He was formerly a construction worker before becoming a hero, which helped influenced quite a lot of his current gear and motifs.

Name: William Birkin
Key: '''First and Second Form''' | '''Third and Fourth Form''' | '''Fifth Form'''
Summary: William Birkin was a researcher and virologist working for the Umbrella Corporation in Raccoon City, developing the T and G-Viruses among many other bioweapons. Bitter over Umbrella's refusal to give him a promotion, he slowly sabotaged his facilities and planned to betray them, but before he could do this, Umbrella intervened, and he was gunned down. Enraged, and barely alive, Birkin injected himself with the G-Virus, mutating into the monstrous G and causing the outbreak.

Name: Xero
Summary: Xero was a warrior of Hallownest who believed that strength would always allow him a bright future. When his mind was infected, he hoped to fight against the plague with violence. Fueled by the same hope, he turned against the Pale King, for which he was executed.

Name: Yasutora Sado (Chad)
Key: '''Substitute Shinigami Arc''' | '''Soul Society Arc''' | '''Arrancar Arc''' | '''Lost Agent Arc''' | '''Thousand Year Blood War Arc'''
Summary: Yasutora Sado (茶渡 泰虎, Sado Yasutora), also known as Chad (チャド, Chado) is a human teenager who lives in Karakura Town. He is a student at Karakura High School, where he is in the same class as Ichigo Kurosaki.

Name: Yawn (Resident Evil)
Summary: The Yawn was a snake-based B.O.W. that lurked around in the Spencer Mansion. It was nicknamed "Yawn" by the Arklay Laboratory team in reference to the way its mouth opens before attacking, which resembled a yawn.

Name: Zamtrios
Summary: Zamtrios are Amphibians introduced in Monster Hunter 4.

Name: Zangief
Summary: Zangief (Russian: Зангиев) also known as the "Red Cyclone", is a video game character created by Capcom. He is part of the Street Fighter series of fighting games, first starring in Street Fighter II. He is a national Russian hero who is always seen fighting for the glory of his country.

Name: Zhi (Dead Rising)
Summary: Prior to the zombie outbreak, Zhi already was on the verge of insanity. His wife left him, his kids didn't respect him and he lost his job at the pharmacy. With this sudden event, Zhi tries to become a monk and live in peace and harmony at the Zen Garden, and those who disturb him will meet their demise.

Name: Zombie (Dead Rising)
Summary: This page contains or depicts disturbing and/or graphic content that some may find upsetting, and that is only intended for mature audiences. Please proceed with caution.

Name: Zombie (Resident Evil)
Summary: Zombies are the result of humans succumbing to the effects of the T-Virus. They are distinguishable by their resemblance to corpses caused by the extensive necrosis on their skin and body. Originally created by Umbrella scientists as result of experimentation, they would rarely be seen in action up until 1998, the year the first viral outbreak was caused deliberately by former Umbrella scientist James Marcus, resulting in the infection of most of Umbrella's employees located in the Arklay Mountains. The actions of the now infected would lead to the intervention of S.T.A.R.S. police force which resulted in the Ecliptic Express and Mansion Incidents, where several members of the team would be brutally murdered by the infected.

Name: Zombie Elephant (Resident Evil)
Summary: A Zombie Elephant is the product of an elephant succumbing to t-Virus infection. Currently, only one Zombie Elephant has been known to have existed, that being a Raccoon Zoo attraction named Oscar.

Name: Zombie Lion (Resident Evil)
Summary: The Zombie Lions were big cats residing at the Raccoon Zoo during the Raccoon City Destruction Incident. There were three lionesses and one male lion named Max.

Name: Zote the Mighty
Summary: Zote the Mighty, referred to as Zote for short, is a character from the Metroidvania, Hollow Knight. As a traveller from another land, Zote travels to the fallen kingdom of Hallownest to fufill his goal and title. Throughout the game he is seen merely as an NPC and has a gag boss fight within the 1st trial of the Colosseum of Fools. After defeating Zote, the player is then allowed to fight Zote's dreamworld counterpart, Grey Prince Zote.

Name: Zoteling
Summary: Zotelings are enemies in Hollow Knight. Figments of Bretta's mind.

Name: Zuko
Summary: Even as the prince of the Fire Nation, Zuko has always struggled in life, particularly in matching his prodigy sister Azula and getting his father's acknowledgment. This came to a head when Ozai punished him for a perceived slight by horrifically burning his face and sending him into exile, refusing to let him return until he had captured the Avatar. (This was intended to be an impossible task, since Aang had been missing for a century). Determined to prove his worth to his father, Zuko hunted Aang across the world for the first season while trying to find his own destiny. Eventually, Zuko betrays Iroh and helps Azula take over Ba Sing Se. Granted amnesty for his actions, Zuko is finally allowed to come home. He has his honor restored, the adoration of a nation, the love of his life, and the respect of his father. And he finds himself lacking. After some soul-searching, Zuko finally realizes what Iroh had always tried to teach him. After calling out Ozai for controlling him, making him feel worthless, burning his face, banishing him for three years and generally being an evil, contemptible douchebag, Zuko defects to join the Gaang as Aang's Firebending teacher. Though initially mistrusted, grudges dissolve into friendships and Zuko soon becomes a core member of the group. At the end of the series, Zuko becomes the new Fire Lord and strives to rebuild the world into an era of peace. And hopefully find his mother.

Name: Ada Wong
Summary: Ada Wong is a secret agent appearing in the Resident Evil franchise. She was first introduced in Resident Evil 2 as a supporting character and reappeared in Resident Evil 4 and Resident Evil 6 as one of the main characters.

Name: Albert Wesker
Summary: Albert Wesker is the main antagonist in the Resident Evil series. He was the leader of S.T.A.R.S. while secretly working for Umbrella Corporation as a Researcher. Later working for The 3rd Organization, H.C.F. (Hive/Host Capture Force), TriCell, he shifts allegiances at will to further his own goals of world domination. Wesker has been directly or indirectly responsible for the events of every game, and always seems to come out on top. Eventually, he would go on to pursue his megalomaniacal desires for world domination with the Uroboros virus, but was stopped by his arch-nemesis Chris Redfield and the BSAA.

Name: Amber Freeman
Summary: Amber Freeman met her partner, Richie Kirsch over the Stab subreddit, where the two planned their own Ghostface killing spree. Amber, who lived in the house where the first Ghostface massacre ended, was all too eager to start her own, and proved herself to be a ruthless killer.

Name: Angry Dad
Summary: Angry Dad is a fictional character made by Bart Simpson from The Simpsons. It is about a father who has extremely bad anger issues, throwing fits over the smallest problems he runs into. This show being based on his father, Homer Simpson, and his anger problems.

Name: Annette Birkin
Summary: Annette Birkin was a scientist working at Umbrella. She was the wife of William Birkin and the mother of Sherry Birkin.

Name: Apple Bloom
Summary: Tier: At least 9-B, likely 8-A | Likely 6-B

Name: Atlas (RWBY)
Summary: Atlas is a kingdom located in Solitas, the far northern continent of Remnant. Formerly known as Mantle, Atlas was founded by settlers who traveled north to the barren, icy continent of Solitas. Where the people were forced to adapt quickly in order to survive the difficult climate, leading them to quickly learn to utilize Dust and other technologies. Following the end of the Great War, Atlas Academy was founded to the north of the original city of Mantle, soon growing to overshadow Mantle and eventually becoming the new capital and namesake of the kingdom.

Name: Austin Powers
Summary: Sir Austin Danger Powers is a fictional British secret agent and the main protagonist in the Austin Powers series. He was presumably born around 1940 or 1941, cryogenically frozen in the late 1960s, and resurrected in the late 1990s.

Name: B-127 (Transformers One)
Summary: B-127 is the Tritagonist of the film Transformers One. A worker in the lowest level of Waste Management, sub-level 50, Bee's isolation caused him to become extremely talkative, to the point of talking to himself and his imaginary friends, all to keep himself company. Upon meeting Orion Pax and D-16, who had both been banished to waste management, the trio would accidentally stumble upon a map leading to the lost Matrix of Leadership. Bee would then assist the two in finding the artifact, hoping to become good friends with the two.

Name: Beowolf
Summary: Beowolves are large werewolf-like Creatures of Grimm. They are the most basic and abundant type of Grimm on Remnant and are the first Grimm seen in the series.

Name: Billy Loomis
Summary: https://vsbattles.fandom.com/wiki/File:BillyMainQuote.mp3.ogg

Name: Boarbatusk
Summary: Boarbatusks are large, boar-like Creatures of Grimm. The first is seen in the episode "The Badge and The Burden" of RWBY Volume 1.

Name: Bora
Summary: Bora (ボラ) is a tall, muscular man who resides in the Sacred Land of Korin with his son Upa, in a tepee at the base of the Korin Tower.

Name: Boss Baby
Summary: Theodore Lindsay Templeton, better known as the Boss Baby, is the titular main protagonist of the Boss Baby franchise. Despite physically being an infant, the Boss Baby has the maturity and mentality of an experienced businessman. He works for Baby Corp, a company whose mission is to make sure babies remain the most loved creatures on Earth.

Name: Bruce Irvin
Summary: Bruce Irvin was born and raised in a rough neighborhood, one troubled by criminals and gangsters. While at a young age, Bruce was left with no family when his parents and older brother were attacked and killed by gangsters. With no other family to turn to, Bruce was forced to survive, alone, on the streets. This did not break him, however, and knowing that he had to be strong to survive, Bruce trained in the art of Muay Thai kickboxing. Forced to fight on a daily basis to survive on the mean streets, Bruce turned this to his advantage by competing in the underground fight scene to earn money, where he soon developed a fearsome reputation due to his vicious temperament and uncompromising technique. This led Bruce to compete in professional tournaments, where he soon became the undisputed heavyweight champion.

Name: Buzz Lightyear (Toy Story)
Summary: Buzz Lightyear is the deuteragonist of the Disney/Pixar Toy Story movies. He is a spaceman action figure originally belonging to Andy Davis. Buzz was created during a time where astronauts were especially popular amongst children. His arrival in the original Toy Story created conflict with Andy's favorite toy, Sheriff Woody, although this rivalry would eventually blossom into a lifelong friendship.

Name: Cade Yeager
Summary: All humans make mistakes. Sometimes, what comes from those mistakes comes the best thing that ever happened to them. That's what Cade Yeager believes when he looks at his daughter, to whom he and his girlfriend gave birth at the cost of their high school graduation. While Cade is not the most responsible father in the world, his most redeeming quality is that when it comes to keeping his daughter safe, he does not go back on his word, no matter what; a promise he made to his bride before she passed away. He does have a creative and optimistic mind, lending it to building all kinds of inventions to make a good business out of. Sadly, none of these inventions have brought in much profit for his family. Knowing all of the opportunities he lost, he has sworn not to let history repeat itself, which is probably why he disapproves of Tessa dating boys before she graduates from high school.

Name: Captain Magnum
Summary: Captain Magnum Longlegs is a pirate who, at the time of AHWM, was sailing through an unknown sea in search of treasure, though his crew is all dead. He encounters The Player in one of their many timelines, in which the Player's box is revealed to contain a map to treasure. The Player's choices determine whether or not Captain Magnum kills them and if they join the crew.

Name: Captain Mizuki
Summary: Captain Mizuki is the 71st ranked B-Class hero of One Punch Man. According to Hero Association executive Sekingar, Mizuki along with several other lower ranking heroes has S-Class potential, which is why he recruited them on the Monster Association raid. Before Mizuki became a professional hero, she was a world class track and field athlete. Her sports background can be seen in her fighting style and how she talks to others. Mizuki has a great respect for the S-Class heroes, especially Superalloy Darkshine and King, the former of which she has a student/mentor relationship with. Throughout raid she proves herself to be an incredibly capable hero and defeats numerous monsters, yet is helpless against Demon Level Rhino Wrestler, who Atomic Samurai dispatches of with ease. This shows that despite her great talent and potential she still has a long way to go before reaching the higher rankings of the Hero Association.

Name: Carla Radames
Summary: Carla Radames was a genius researcher who worked for Derek C. Simmons, doppleganger of Ada Wong and the main antagonist of Chris', Jake's and Ada's campaigns in Resident Evil 6, and is the secondary antagonist of Leon's campaign. Overall, Radames is the main antagonist of Resident Evil 6. Radames is one responsible for the discovery and creation of the C-Virus, and she is both the eventual founder and leader of an Umbrella Corporation-typed organization called Neo-Umbrella. Carla is initially portrayed as an uncharacteristically cruel Ada Wong. However, it is eventually revealed in Ada Wong's own campaign that she is in fact a clone Derek C. Simmons created using Carla Radames (without her consent), Ada Wong's DNA, and the C-Virus.

Name: Centinel
Summary: Centinels are Creatures of Grimm that resemble large centipedes. Centinels aren't so much dangerous as they are terrifying and annoying. For Huntsmen and Huntresses that get an eradication order, it takes them ages to locate every single one, while enduring pop out scares from the floor, walls, and ceilings. As a result their rewards tend to be disproportionately large compared to their difficulty ranking.

Name: Chad Meeks-Martin
Summary: Chad Meeks-Martin is the nephew of legacy character, Randy Meeks, and son of Martha Meeks. Although Chad doesn’t share many traits with his uncle unlike his twin sister, Mindy, who he is still close with. As a Woodsboro High football player, he dated Liv McKenzie. When a new Ghostface appears, Chad suspects Vince Schneider, Liv's ex, who has been stalking her online. After Vince's murder, Chad briefly becomes a suspect and is later attacked while searching for Liv at Wes Hicks' memorial party.

Name: Chainsaw Man (Resident Evil)
Summary: The Chainsaw Man is a class of Chainsaw Ganado. This Ganado wears a burlap potato sack as a mask over his head. the Chainsaw Man has been made exceptionally violent, and is compelled to relentlessly chase his enemies with his trademark chainsaw. Also, due to the Plaga's assimilation, he has been made exceptionally robust in comparison to regular villagers and can absorb small arms fire with ease.

Name: Charlie Walker
Summary: Charlie Walker is the secondary antagonist of Scream 4.

Name: Chase McCain
Summary: Chase McCain is a police man famous for arresting the notorious criminal Rex Fury. However, he was sent overseas after accidentally giving away the identity of his secret witness. Two years later, Rex escaped from the prison and Chase would have to, once again, put on his badge and bring him to justice.

Name: Chi-Chi (Dragon Ball)
Summary: Chi-Chi is the former princess of Fire Mountain and the daughter of the Ox-King who later marries Goku and becomes the loving mother of Gohan and Goten. She was first introduced as a shy and fearful girl, but later, as she gets older, develops a very tomboyish, tough and fierce personality, which sometimes causes her to have anger outbursts seen several times throughout the series. Despite this, she has shown her love for Goku and their sons many times throughout the series.

Name: Chica (Five Nights at Freddy's)
Summary: https://vsbattles.fandom.com/wiki/File:WItheredChicaFaceBreaker.ogg

Name: Choco Yuzuki
Summary: Choco Yuzuki is a demon who works as the school nurse of the Underworld Academy. Despite being a common demon, she's sometimes mistaken for a succubus due to having the beauty of one. Thanks to that, she's incredibly popular among the students, the boys in particular coming to get checked up all the time. Choco is polite, respectful and acts a lot more mature than other Hololive talents, with the wisdom and intelligence to back that up. Though she sometimes partakes in shenanigans with her coworkers, she sometimes also shows a no-nonsence attitude when things become too ridiculous. She likes to dote on and spoil Luna Himemori.

Name: Chris Redfield
Summary: Chris Redfield is one of the main protagonists of the Resident Evil series. He is a former member of the S.T.A.R.S. unit. He is now an American Special Operations Unit Captain of the BSAA (Bioterrorism Security Assessment Alliance), an anti-Bioterrorist group, of which he is a founding member along with his long-time partner, Jill Valentine. A senior member of an elite security force in Racoon City, S.T.A.R.S. Members of Team 1, they are the pride of S.T.A.R.S. for their competence in firearms and close combat. Chris is also the older brother of TerraSave member Claire Redfield. He appears in the original Resident Evil, Resident Evil - Code: Veronica, Resident Evil 5, Resident Evil 6, Resident Evil 7: Biohazard, and Resident Evil Village.

Name: Claire Redfield
Summary: Claire Redfield is a current member of the human rights organization, TerraSave. She is the younger sister of BSAA operative and former S.T.A.R.S. member Chris Redfield. Claire is a survivor of the Raccoon City Incident, which took place in September 1998 after she traveled to the city in search of her brother. After escaping the city with the help of Leon S. Kennedy, Claire ventured to Europe to resume her search for Chris. In December, she was captured by Umbrella after infiltrating their Paris Laboratory and transported to the Umbrella owned Rockfort Island and imprisoned. When Rockfort Island was attacked by a mysterious Special Forces group, Claire tried to escape with a fellow prisoner, Steve Burnside, leading to both of their involvements in the Antarctic outbreak. Her brother soon learned of her situation and rescued her. In 2005, Claire confronted the t-Virus again when she arrived at Harvardville Airport to meet some friends. While surviving in the airport, she was reunited with Leon, now a U.S. Government agent, who had been sent to deal with the outbreak. Later, in 2011, Claire would be kidnapped along with other TerraSave members by Alex Wesker's organization and left on Sushestvovanie Island, which made her try to escape with Moira Burton amid the outbreak taking place there. Having been the only one to be rescued, she would eventually support Barry Burton in the search for his daughter and in the process participated in the elimination of the last of the Wesker Children. As early as 2014, in the midst of her investigation into bioterrorist activities taking place in the Sonido de Tortuga Island region, Claire was eventually involved in the outbreak that occurred at the site.

Name: Colmillos (Resident Evil)
Summary: Colmillos (コルミロス) are Plaga-infested wolves encountered in Resident Evil 4. The name 'Colmillos' means 'Fangs' in Spanish.

Name: Convicts
Summary: The Convicts, consisting of Sam Franklin, Reginald Jenkins, and Miguel Sanchez, are psychopaths in Dead Rising who are involved in the mission Prisoners.

Name: Cool Cat (Warner Bros.)
Summary: Cool Cat is a Bengal tiger from the classic era of Looney Toons shorts. Due to his species, he is constantly chased around by Colonel Rimfire, a big game hunter who never succeeds in catching him, mainly due to Cool Cat's extremely good luck.

Name: Cotton Weary
Summary: Cotton Weary was a resident of Woodsboro, who had a secret affair with an older woman, Maureen Prescott, and was falsely accused and arrested of her rape and murder in late-September 1995. However, he was released a year later when it was revealed that Billy Loomis and Stu Macher were the ones that killed Maureen and framed Cotton. Opportunistic, he sought fame and fortune with Gale's help and finally achieved it after saving Sidney's life at Windsor College in 1998. He parlayed the media coverage into his own show in Hollywood, 100% Cotton, before finally falling prey to a new Ghostface whose quest was to locate Sidney.

Name: Cozy Glow
Summary: Cozy Glow is an evil Pegasus in the series, My Little Pony.

Name: Crablante
Summary: Crablante was a Tiger-level Threat who was created when a man ate too much crab and transformed.

Name: Creep (RWBY)
Summary: Creeps are subterranean Creatures of Grimm that resemble both lizards and birds. They were first encountered in "No Brakes".

Name: Creeper (Kingdom Hearts)
Summary: Creeper is the weakest of the Nobody species, often being found alongside Dusks.

Name: Crewmate (Among Us)
Summary: The Crewmates are one of the two roles in the murder mystery game, Among Us. Their role is to complete all of their assigned tasks or to deduce who the Impostor among them is so the Impostor can be ejected. Most locations they go to involve the theme of outer space adventure.

Name: Dan Hibiki
Summary: nan

Name: Daphne (Cartoon)
Summary: Daphne Blake is the fashion-loving member of Mystery Inc, Daphne's characteristic trait in the gang is her tendency to get into danger, hence earning the nickname "Danger-prone Daphne".

Name: Destoroyah
Summary: Destoroyah (デストロイア, Desutoroia?, lit. Destroyer) is a crustacean kaiju created by Toho that first appeared in the 1995 Godzilla film, Godzilla vs. Destoroyah. Originally a colony of microscopic Precambrian crustaceans that mutated from exposure to the Oxygen Destroyer used to kill the first Godzilla in 1954, it created a monster able to splinter itself and recombine at will. Named after the biological weapon that created it, Destoroyah is the final opponent of Burning Godzilla in his final moments.

Name: Dewey Riley
Summary: Dwight “Dewey” Riley is one of the main characters of the Scream series. He's a retired cop (and former sheriff) and the ex-husband of Gale Weathers, and a survivor of the first Woodsboro murders. During the first Ghostface's 1996 killing spree, he lost his sister to the killer, which served as his motivation to assist Sam during the 2022 killings. Since 1996, he’s had to face many more Ghostface killers, even being the one to kill Roman Bridger.

Name: Dick Gumshoe
Summary: Dick Gumshoe is a homicide detective from the Ace Attorney series. He used to work under characters such as Phoenix Wright, Franziska von Karma, and Godot. However, he now works under Miles Edgeworth. Gumshoe will usually take care of the initial investigation and is always willing to back Edgeworth up. He will even go behind a prosecutor's back for a case.

Name: DJ Music Man
Summary: https://vsbattles.fandom.com/wiki/File:GlamrockFreddylikesDJMM.ogg

Name: Drain Deimos
Summary: The Drain Deimos (ドレインディモス) are fleas which have been mutated by the t-Virus. Their only confirmed sighting was during the Raccoon City Destruction Incident, in which they were infected by feeding on blood from zombies. Like many other arthropods, the fleas responded to the virus by dramatically increasing in size, strength and aggression, as well as growing more humanoid anatomy, such as its arms and legs.

Name: Earl Devereaux
Origin: Cloudy with a Chance of Meatballs
Summary: Earl Devereaux is the police officer from the town of Swallow Falls island. He is one of the main characters and a secondary protagonist of Cloudy with a Chance of Meatballs and Cloudy with a Chance of Meatballs 2. He is portrayed as a tall and muscular cop with incredible athletic skills.

Name: Ed Wuncler III
Summary: Edward "Ed" Wuncler III is the grandson of Ed Wuncler I and son of Ed Wuncler II. He is a drunken, trigger-happy ex-soldier freshly discharged from active duty in Iraq.

Name: Edwin Murray
Summary: Edwin Murray is the loving husband of Fiona Murray and father of his son, David Murray. Despite his love for them, due to all of the commissions by Fazbear Entertainment, Edwin was so engrossed in his work that he didn't have enough time to spend. Before David's third birthday party however, Fiona decides to help out at Fall Fest, dying after a brief fire and leaving Edwin alone with David.

Name: Elita-1 (Transformers One)
Summary: Elita-1 is the Tritagonist of the film Transformers One. A no-nonsense bot, Elita-1 was the head of an Energon mining crew, maintaining a spotless record while harvesting large amounts of energon for the good of Cybertron. Up until a mining incident involving Orion Pax and D-16, which involved her demotion, leading to a disdain particularly towards the former.

Name: Ethan Landry
Summary: Ethan Kirsch, also known under the alias of Ethan Landry, is a secondary antagonist of Scream VI.

Name: Ethan Winters
Summary: Ethan Winters is a major character in the Resident Evil series. An American systems engineer who was happily married to his wife Mia Winters, Ethan's normal life changed when Mia suddenly disappeared without a trace while working away from home.

Name: FLDSMDFR
Origin: Cloudy with a Chance of Meatballs
Summary: The Flint Lockwood Diatonic Super Mutating Dynamic Food Replicator, or FLDSMDFR for short, is the machine which the two Cloudy With A Chance Of Meatballs movies revolve around.

Name: Fluttershy (Human World)
Summary: Fluttershy is one of the main characters of My Little Pony Equestria Girls, and represents the Element of Kindness.

Name: Forest Law
Summary: Forest Law is a character that appears in the Tekken series of fighting games, and he is the son of Marshall Law. He dons the same fighting style and moves as his father, and also shares a friendship with Paul Phoenix.

Name: Foxy (Five Nights at Freddy's)
Summary: https://vsbattles.fandom.com/wiki/File:PhoneGuyFoxy.ogg

Name: Fred (Cartoon)
Summary: Fred "Freddie/Freddy" Jones is the leader of the Mystery Inc. gang, and (more often than not) the driver of their van: The Mystery Machine, Fred is statuesque and brave; everything that the group's other male human member, Shaggy, isn't.

Name: Fredbear (Five Nights At Freddy's)
Summary: Fredbear is an animatronic mascot for Fredbear's Family Diner, and an important character withing the Five Nights at Freddy's franchise, though most notably Five Nights at Freddy's 4. He is one of two "spring-lock" suits, the other being Spring Bonnie. Both animatronics double as animatronics and suits. He would later be possessed by a Crying Child, becoming Golden Freddy, as well as being dreamed up as Nightmare Fredbear and Nightmare. Fredbear is also a secret animatronic in the game Ultimate Custom Night. Fredbear appears after the Death Token is used on Golden Freddy.

Name: Freddy & Friends
Summary: (Ragged moaning from animatronics can be heard) Oh no..." (Sound used by Golden Freddy during his jumpscare plays, call ends)

Name: Freddy Fazbear
Summary: https://vsbattles.fandom.com/wiki/File:PhoneGuyFreddy.ogg

Name: Gale Weathers
Summary: Gale Weathers (formerly Gale Riley) appears in the Scream films as an ambitious, strong-willed news reporter, journalist, and writer who ultimately joins forces with Sidney Prescott and Dewey Riley, the latter of whom she eventually falls in love with and marries, in order to investigate and stop the Ghostface murders.

Name: Gargwa
Summary: Gargwa are Bird Wyverns introduced in Monster Hunter Portable 3rd.

Name: Garrador
Summary: Garradors are hosts enhanced by the Plaga parasite, clad in armor and claws to enhance their killing efficiency, but chained in cells with their eyelids sewn shut to keep it controlled. They are encountered by Leon Kennedy during his mission to Spain.

Name: Gezzoora
Summary: Gezzoora is a kaiju and an antagonist in the manga, "SD Godzilla World: Godzilla Kun".

Name: Ghostface (1996)
Summary: The Ghostface killers of 1996 are a pair of high school seniors, Billy Loomis and Stu Macher, who terrorize the town of Woodsburo one year after killing Maureen Prescott. The two would call their victim’s phone, taunting them with a voice changer before attacking them while dressed in a mask and cloak. Together, they ended the lives of six people, all before being killed by their main target, Sidney Prescott.

Name: Ghostface (1998)
Summary: The Ghostface killers of 1998 are Nancy Loomis and Mickey Altieri, whom team up for a series of copycat murders based on the 1996 killers of the same alias. Together, they terrorize Windsor College in pursuit of Sidney Prescott.

Name: Ghostface (2011)
Summary: The Ghostface killers of 2011 are Jill Roberts and Charlie Walker, two high school students who seek to gain fame from their murders. Together, they massacred the town of Woodsboro, in hopes of going down in history as the survivors of their own tragedy. However, Jill would go on to betray Charlie, hoping to become the sole survivor of the incident. Jill's reign as the sole survivor would soon be thwarted by her cousin, Sidney Prescott, after she awoke in the ICU.

Name: Ghostface (2022)
Summary: The Ghostface killers of 2022 are Richie Kirsch and Amber Freeman. The couple met on Reddit after being disappointed by the release of Stab (2021), and so began to form a plan to give Hollywood new material for a proper Stab movie. Their scheme ended with several dead, until it was stopped by Sidney Prescott, Gale Weathers, Sam Carpenter, and Tara Carpenter.

Name: Ghostface (2023)
Summary: The Ghostface killers of 2023, Wayne Bailey, Ethan Landry, and Quinn Bailey were the culprits of the New York Murders. The trio are a family, seeking revenge for the death of Richie Kirsch, the brother of Ethan and Quinn and the son of Wayne. Together, they attempt to kill Samantha Carpenter and Tara Carpenter, going after Gale Weathers and many other victims along the way.

Name: Glamrock Chica
Summary: Glamrock Chica is a counterpart of Chica who appears as a primary antagonist in Five Nights at Freddy's: Security Breach.

Name: Glamrock Endo
Summary: https://vsbattles.fandom.com/wiki/File:GregoryFindsEndosCreepy.ogg

Name: Glamrock Freddy
Summary: https://vsbattles.fandom.com/wiki/File:GLAMFREDDYwayTogo.ogg

Name: Glasses (One-Punch Man)
Summary: Glasses is the B-Class Rank 20 professional hero of the Hero Association and one of the few people aware of Saitama's strength.

Name: Gloriosa Daisy
Summary: Gloriosa Daisy is a supporting character and later main antagonist of My Little Pony Equestria Girls: Legends of Everfree.

Name: Golden Ball
Summary: Golden Ball (黄金ボール, Ōgon Bōru) is an A-Class Superhero, rank 26. He was partnered with Spring Mustachio to investigate the monster rumor in Z-City.

Name: Golden Freddy (Five Nights at Freddy's)
Summary: Golden Freddy is a mysterious character that appears in the first and second games of the Five Nights at Freddy's franchise, appearing as a rare Easter Egg first made truly widespread to the masses by Markiplier during his playthrough of Five Nights at Freddy's 1.[1]

Name: Goro Gondo
Summary: Goro Gondo (権藤 吾郎) is a colonel in the JSDF and one of the leaders of the Defend Against Godzilla unit, along with his partner Sho Kuroki. He is a supporting character in the 1989 Godzilla film, Godzilla vs. Biollante, and is later referenced in the 1994 film, Godzilla vs. SpaceGodzilla.

Name: Gravedigger
Summary: The Grave Digger (グレイブディガ) is an irregular mutant that was created when an overload of waste transported out from the Raccoon City Underground Laboratory led to the P-12A incinerator facility leaking t-Virus into the soil, thus mutating the local millipedes.

Name: Great Girros
Summary: Great Girros (痺賊竜) is a Fanged Wyvern first introduced in Monster Hunter: World.

Name: Great Jaggi
Summary: Tier: 9-B | 8-C

Name: Great Jagras
Summary: Great Jagras is a monster introduced in Monster Hunter World.

Name: Griffon (RWBY)
Summary: Griffons are a species of Grimm with both feline and avian traits. They appeared en masse just prior to the Fall of Beacon, having responded to the distress created by the machinations of Cinder Fall.

Name: Haato Akai
Summary: Haato Akai is schoolgirl who loves all cute things, particularyl red ribbons and heart shapes, which she wears as accessories. She's sweet and attentionate, but tends to act like a tsundere. In spite of that, chaos seems to follow wherever she goes, as she frequently brushes aside common sense. She rides the line between purity and insanity, and is sometimes shown performing various odd jobs. Haato's chaotic nature is called Haachama, often treated like a different entity from Haato. She frequently says her catchphrase Haachama-chama~!. She's infamous for being a terrible cook.

Name: Henry Emily
Summary: nan

Name: Hero Association
Summary: The Hero Association is an organization founded by the multi-millionaire Agoni after his grandson was saved from a monster by a passerby. Operating independently of the government, the Hero Association recruits various individuals, ordinary and extraordinary alike, to fight for justice against the evil in the world. Those registered within the National Hero Registry database are tasked with protecting civilians from harm against monsters, villains, natural disasters, and other threats and are compensated for their efforts.

Name: Huey Freeman
Summary: Huey Freeman is the main protagonist of the Boondocks series. Politically sapient and borderline militant, he regularly reflects on current events as well as the plight of African Americans as it relates to greater society. Huey was named after Huey P. Newton, one of the founders of the Black Panther Party. Huey grew up with his younger brother Riley Freeman and granddad Robert Freeman, and it is strongly suggested that Huey and Riley's birth parents are deceased.

Name: HUNK
Summary: "HUNK" is the code-name of a Special Agent of the Umbrella Security Service, who was the leader of the ill-fated Alpha Team in the employment of Umbrella. Cold, silent, and devoid of emotion, he is a ruthless operative who puts the mission objective above all. Nicknamed "Mr. Death", he is infamous amongst Umbrella's ranks due to often being the only survivor after a mission.

Name: Illinois (AHWM)
Summary: Illinois is an adventurer and avid treasure hunter. Shortly before meeting the Player, he lost his assistant at the time to a boulder.

Name: Impostor (Among Us)
Summary: The Impostor is the antagonist/protagonist (Depending on the role you're given at the start of the game) of the murder mystery game, Among Us. Its mission is to kill every Crewmate before they can finish all of their tasks while also trying to avoid suspicious actions that can make the Crewmates realize that it is the Impostor among them.

Name: Jet Nice Guy
Summary: Jet Nice Guy is the B-Class Rank 50 hero from the Hero Association.

Name: Jill Roberts
Summary: Jill Roberts is the main antagonist of Scream 4.

Name: Jill Valentine
Summary: Jill Valentine is one of the main protagonists in the Resident Evil series. She appears in the first game, Resident Evil 3, the "End of Umbrella" scenario, Revelations, and the RE5 DLCs "Desperate Escape" and "Lost in Nightmares." She appears as a member of S.T.A.R.S. and then later fights zombies and bioterrorism. A senior member of S.T.A.R.S. belonging on the same team as Chris. Jill has also resigned from S.T.A.R.S. in Resident Evil 3 Nemesis and attempts to escape from the T-virus infested town, Raccoon City. She runs into Nemesis, a B.O.W. from Umbrella Corp. Nemesis relentlessly pursued Jill throughout the city. At some point, Nemesis managed to infect Jill with T-NE-virus. She also meets a member of the U.B.C.S. Carlos Olivera. In the end, Jill managed to kill Nemesis, and together with Carlos and Barry, escaped the city successfully.

Name: Josie Rizal
Summary: Having been a big cry baby since she was very young, her parents who were big fans of Martial Arts insisted that she train martial arts. Despite her reluctance at first, Josie Rizal later became accustomed to training kick-boxing to live up to her parent's expectations although it hasn't cured her from being a cry baby.

Name: Juniper Montage
Summary: Juniper Montage is the main antagonist in the first 3-parter of the Equestria Girls.

Name: Kairi (Kingdom Hearts)
Summary: Kairi is a longtime friend of both Sora and Riku and one of the Seven Princesses of Heart. She was raised by her grandmother in Radiant Garden but was sent to the Destiny Islands after Radiant Garden became shrouded in Darkness. As the Destiny Islands succumbed to the Darkness, her body vanished as she tried to meet up with Sora, leaving her heart behind in her friend, who set out on a journey to reunite with her and Riku.

Name: Koji Shinjo
Summary: Koji Shinjo (新城功二) is one of the main human protagonists in the 1994 Godzilla film, Godzilla vs. SpaceGodzilla. He is a lieutenant in G-Force and a co-pilot of MOGUERA.

Name: Kon
Summary: Kon (コン, Kon) is an Underpod (部下強化型 (アンダーポッド), Andāpoddo; Japanese for "Lower Part-Strengthened Form") Mod-Soul created during Project Spearhead. His name is short for Kaizō Konpaku (改造 魂魄, Modified soul). Kon typically inhabits a stuffed lion, but occasionally doubles as a Soul Candy pill for Ichigo Kurosaki, taking charge of Ichigo's Human body.

Name: Kool-Aid Man (Family Guy)
Summary: Kool-Aid Man is a gag character in the animated series, Family Guy.

Name: Kota Izumi
Summary: Kota Izumi is the nephew of Mandalay and the son of the deceased hero Water Hose. At first, he hated heroes and what they represent, but after having his life saved from Muscular by Deku, he learns the meaning of a true hero and begins to idolize him.

Name: Kurumu Kurono
Summary: Kurumu is a Succubus and a third-year student at Yōkai Academy. Kurumu initially planned to enslave all the boys at the academy, until she met Tsukune and Moka and the following incident, she became convinced that Tsukune was her "fateful mate", and planned to win his heart without the use of her powers. Kurumu later becomes one of the most prominent supporting characters and proactively involved in the adventures.

Name: Lancer (RWBY)
Summary: Lancers are large hornet-like Creatures of Grimm. There are two types: a smaller, more common version called a Warrior Drone and a larger variation known as a Queen Lancer.

Name: Launch (Dragon Ball)
Summary: Launch (ランチ, Ranchi; lit. "Lunch") is a woman with a strange disorder which causes her to switch between two different personalities each time she sneezes. Her first personality is a sweet, blue haired woman, who is pure-hearted. Her other personality is an angry, trigger-happy, blonde haired woman, who commits crimes for money and is quick to respond with gunfire when angered. Neither of Launch's personalities remembers the other's actions, or anything they said. Her blood type is AB.

Name: Leanbow
Summary: Leanbow is Udonna's husband, Bowen's father (AKA Nick Russel), and the mentor of Daggeron and Calindor. He was known for his honor and valor which Calindor resented. As a Mystic, he can assume "Ancient Mystic Mode", resembling a red/purple fiery demon wielding a sword and shield. Twenty years prior to the series, Leanbow led the other Mystics in the Great Battle against the Supreme Master of the Underworld, and his Forces of Darkness led by Morticon in order to prevent them entering the human realm. The forces of good magic eventually forced the Forces of Darkness through the Gate of the Underworld, with Leanbow personally taking on Morticon at one point. In order to keep the Forces of Darkness from escaping the Underworld, he held back the Darkness hordes from the Gate while Niella the Gatekeeper sealed both it and Leanbow into the Underworld.

Name: Leon S. Kennedy
Summary: Leon Scott Kennedy is one of the main characters in the Resident Evil horror media franchise by Capcom. He debuted as one of the two playable protagonists of the video game Resident Evil 2. Leon later returned as the main character of Resident Evil 4 and as one of the protagonists in Resident Evil Darkside Chronicles and Resident Evil 6.

Name: Lucas Lee
Summary: Tier: At least 9-B, likely higher

Name: Lucky Chloe
Summary: Ever since her parents brought her to an Expo and exposed her to Japanese culture when she was a child, Lucky Chloe always wanted to be a Pop Idol. With her good looks, she aimed at being the most famous Pop Idol in the world.

Name: M11
Summary: M11 is an android built by the Futurians in the 23rd century. His only appearance was in the 1991 Godzilla film, Godzilla vs. King Ghidorah.

Name: Maleficent (Kingdom Hearts V Cast)
Summary: Maleficent is the main antagonist of Kingdom Hearts V Cast.

Name: Manticore (RWBY)
Summary: Manticores are large, lion-like flying Creatures of Grimm first encountered in the episode "Argus Limited" of RWBY Volume 6.

Name: Master Control Program
Summary: The Master Control Program (or MCP) is the main antagonist in TRON. The MCP was a rogue computer program, created by Walter Gibbs and vastly improved by Ed Dillinger, that ruled over the world inside ENCOM's mainframe computer system. During the rule of the MCP, many programs were enslaved and pitted against the program's henchmen, led by Commander Sark.

Name: Matthew Patel
Summary: Tier: 9-B, likely higher with his Demon Hipster Chicks

Name: Max (Lightning Max)
Summary: Max, also known by his hero alias Lightning Max, is the Rank 19 A-Class Hero for the Hero Association. He fought against Deep Sea King but was easily defeated. After recovering from his injuries, he began to train so that he can one day overcome the Sea King's strength.

Name: Meganulon
Summary: In Rodan, the Meganulon were prehistoric dragonfly nymphs living underground in Kitamatsu, where they were awakened by mining operations. The Meganulon began to move to the surface, flooding the mines and brutally killing any miners they came across. Shigeru Kawamura and a team of JSDF soldiers attempted to exterminate the insects, but Shigeru fell into a deep underground cavern inhabited by countless Meganulon and a gigantic egg. The egg hatched into a baby Rodan, which ate the Meganulon before flying out of the cavern.

Name: Megatron (Transformers One)
Summary: Megatron is the Deuteragonist and eventual main Antagonist of Transformers One. Once a lowly miner named D-16, the young bot idolized the legendary Megatronus Prime and was a stickler for protocol, believing that following the rules and believing in the system would one day allow him to ascend up the hierarchy. He was also the best friend of the rebellious Orion Pax, often acting as the straight man to Orion's shenanigans, but willing to back Orion up no matter what.

Name: Messenger of the Seafolk
Summary: The Messenger of the Seafolk was a monster that appeared in J-City as a representative of the Seafolk.

Name: Mickey Altieri
Summary: Mickey Altieri was a college student who frequented an online forum for serial killers, where he met Nancy Loomis. After the two had met, Mickey began a new series of murders under the Ghostface moniker alongside his partner, hoping to get caught and go to trial in order to blame horror movies for his behavior.

Name: Ming Long-Dou
Summary: Ming Long-Dou (voiced by Tiffany Espensen) has so far only appeared in the episode, "The Red Ball" as the captain of the Chinese kickball team and Mr. Long-dou's granddaughter. Ming's training since age 3 has made her ruthlessly competitive. She cares only about proving herself better than anyone else.

Name: Mister Satan
Summary: Mr. Satan, real name Mark, is the reigning World Martial Arts Champion as of the Buu Saga, the World's Champion following the Cell Games, a superhero and crime fighter, and an actor, praised by oblivious Earthlings for defeating the likes of Cell and Majin Buu and saving the world, feats that, in truth, belong to the Z-Fighters. Among the Z-Fighters, he is a known liar, cheater, and a showboating blowhard.

Name: Mizore Shirayuki
Summary: Mizore was introduced as an antagonist to Tsukune and Moka. However, she eventually became a friend and an ally. She later fell in love with Tsukune, and even wanted to marry him. She was rescued from a forced marriage by him. She participated in the final battle against Fairy Tale.

Name: Moira Burton
Summary: Moira Burton Moira Burton is one of Barry and Kathy Burton's daughters, and Polly Burton's sister. She is a playable character in Resident Evil Revelations 2 along with Claire Redfield.

Name: Moka Akashiya
Summary: Moka Akashiya (Akashiya Moka, 赤夜 萌香) is a vampiress in Yōkai Academy and the main female protagonist of the series. She serves as the primary love interest to Tsukune Aono, who is the sole human enrolled in an academy of monsters. She has an enchanted rosary that gives her a split personality; her outer persona is gentle, compassionate, and seemingly weaker than average monsters. In contrast, the inner persona is a bold and domineering vampire lady; she is also a remarkably strong fighter, even among vampires.

Name: Monkey D. Luffy (Pre-Timeskip)
Key: '''Young''' | '''East Blue Saga''' | '''Alabasta Saga''' | '''Skypiea Arc''' | '''Water 7 Arc''' | '''Enies Lobby Arc''' - '''Paramount War Saga'''
Summary: Monkey D. Luffy (モンキー・Ｄディー・ルフィ, Monkī Dī Rufi?), known as "Straw Hat Luffy", is the main protagonist of the manga and anime, One Piece. He's the son of Monkey D. Dragon, a revolutionary considered “The World's Most Dangerous Criminal”; the grandson of Monkey D. Garp, a powerful Marine Vice-Admiral who had cornered the late Pirate King himself on several occasions; the sworn brother of late "Fire Fist" Portgas D. Ace and Revolutionary chief of staff Sabo; and the foster son of Curly Dadan. He seeks to find One Piece and become the Pirate King; to accomplish this, he founded the Straw Hat Pirates and set out on the high seas at age 17 in search of the elusive treasure, beginning a series of increasingly odd and dangerous adventures. He has eaten the Gomu Gomu no Mi, which gives him stretching powers that he has become quite a master of and he's quite creative with them as he has developed two unique techniques with them: Gear 2nd, which makes him much faster, and Gear 3rd, which allows him to inflate any body parts for a stronger attack.

Name: Montgomery Gator
Summary: https://vsbattles.fandom.com/wiki/File:MontySaysRockAndRoll.ogg

Name: Mr. Bean
Summary: Mr. Bean is the main character on the British comedy television programme, Mr. Bean, acted by Rowan Sebastian Atkinson. He is a slow-witted, sometimes ingenious, selfish and generally likeable buffoon who brings various unusual schemes and contrivances to everyday tasks.

Name: Musashi Goda
Summary: Musashi Goda (郷田武蕨, Gōda Musashi) is a student of Salt Middle School and the Body Improvement Club's President. He's a close friend of Mob.

Name: N'Doul
Origin: JoJo's Bizarre Adventure '''(Part III: Stardust Crusaders)'''
Summary: N'Doul is a minor antagonist in JoJo's Bizarre Adventure Part III: Stardust Crusaders. A blind man with no fear of death, he is hired by Dio Brando to eliminate the Joestars and allies. He assassinates helicopter pilots from the Speedwagon Foundation in an attempt to eliminate the group and fights them in an Egyptian desert.

Name: Nancy Loomis
Summary: Nancy Loomis is the mother of Billy Loomis, who left her family after her husband had an affair with Maureen Prescott. Years later, upon hearing of Billy’s death at the hands of Sidney Prescott, she pursues Sidney in hopes of killing her as an act of revenge. She recruits Mickey Altieri as her partner, the two having met on a forum for serial killers.

Name: Narcisstoic
Summary: Narcisstoic is an A-Class Rank 29 hero for the Hero Association.

Name: Needle Star
Summary: Needle Star is the B-Class Rank 60 hero in the Hero Association.

Name: Nobara Kugisaki
Key: '''Fearsome Womb Arc''' | '''Kyoto Goodwill Event Arc''' | '''Shibuya Incident Arc'''
Summary: I love the me that dresses up and looks beautiful! I love the me that's strong! I'm Nobara Kugisaki!

Name: Okayu Nekomata
Summary: Okayu Nekomata is a catgirl raised by her grandmother that runs an onigiri store. As a result, she loves onigiri. She shares traits with cats, as she's laid-back, free-spirited and likes to relax and sleep. In spite of those, she's also a prankster and a playboy, having captured the heart of Aqua Minato with seemingly no effort. She's often seen with Korone Inugami, who she's close friends with.

Name: One Shotter
Summary: One Shotter is an A-Class Rank 22 hero for the Hero Association.

Name: Optimus Prime (Transformers One)
Summary: Optimus Prime is the main protagonist of Transformers One. Once a low class Miner, Orion Pax sought out to find the Matrix of Leadership, in order to end the need for him and his fellow miners to stay in the dangerous mines, and to prove that cogless bots like him were so much more, often facing prejudice by Cybertronians born with Transformation cogs.

Name: Panpoot
Summary: Panpoot, also known as Pamput in the anime, is a multiple time Muay Thai champion who faces off against Kid Goku in the 22nd World Martial Arts tournament. Despite his great confidence in himself due to his past victories and Goku's unimposing demeanor, Pamput is swiftly defeated by the child. He is notable for having a considerable amount of strength despite not at all being able to utilize his ki.

Name: Personification Of A Light Pull Cord
Summary: Personification Of A Light Pull Cord is one of the various, terrifying beings Saitama faced during his 3 year journey to becoming a hero.
ID: Personification Of A Light Pull Cord-One-PunchMan-9-B

Name: Piggy Bancon
Summary: Piggy Bancon (豚の貯金バコン Buta No Chokin Bakon) was a Mysterious Being that appeared 13 years prior to the One-Punch Man series.

Name: Pinkie Pie (Human World)
Summary: Pinkie Pie is one of the main characters of My Little Pony Equestria Girls, and represents the Element of Laughter.

Name: Portgas D. Ace
Summary: Portgas D. Ace, also known as "Fire Fist" Ace, was the son of the late Gol D. Roger who was secretly adopted by Monkey D. Garp and given the surname of his dying mother Portgas D. Rouge. Placed under the care of Curly Dadan, Ace eventually met his guardian's grandson, Monkey D. Luffy and the two became sworn brothers along with Sabo. Ace later left Luffy at the age of 17 to take to piracy, acquiring the power of the Flame-Flame Fruit (Mera Mera no Mi), a Logia that allows him to create, control and transform into fire, and captaincy of the Spade Pirates along with a massive bounty of 550,000,000 berries. Ace later makes an attempt on the life of the pirate Whitebeard, and ends up joining the older pirate's crew.

Name: Precious (The Boss Baby)
Summary: Precious is a pony given to Tabitha Templeton by her uncle Theodore, the former Boss Baby. She strongly dislikes Tabitha's father Tim for no apparent reason, and regularly attacks him.

Name: Princess Cadance
Summary: Princess Cadance is a secondary character in My Little Pony: Friendship is Magic.

Name: Princess Celestia
Summary: Princess Celestia is a major character in My Little Pony: Friendship is Magic and is one of the many Alicorns seen in the series, so far. She is Twilight Sparkle's mentor and the one responsible for raising the sun, every day. Celestia rules over all of Equestria and is portrayed as a wise, kind, and beloved leader.

Name: Princess Luna
Key: '''Princess Luna/Nightmare Moon''' | '''Vice Principal Luna (Equestria Girls counterpart)'''
Summary: Princess Luna is a former antagonist and recurring character in My Little Pony: Friendship is Magic.

Name: Q (Street Fighter)
Summary: Q (キュ Kyu) is a character in the Street Fighter series. He first appeared in Street Fighter III: 3rd Strike, and is voiced by Len Carlson. While Q can be chosen as a playable character, he is also a "hidden" computer-controlled sub-boss in Arcade Mode that can only be battled after meeting specific requirements: the player must win the first eight matches without losing a round.

Name: Quinn Bailey
Summary: Quinn Kirsch, also known under the alias of Quinn Bailey, is a secondary antagonist of Scream VI.

Name: Rainbow Dash (Human World)
Summary: Rainbow Dash is one of the main characters in My Little Pony Equestria Girls.

Name: Ranfan
Summary: Ranfan is a character in Dragon Ball, a female martial artist who competes in the 21st World Martial Arts Tournament.

Name: Rarity (Human World)
Summary: Rarity is one of the main characters of My Little Pony Equestria Girls, and represents the Element of Generosity.

Name: Ravage (Michael Bay)
Summary: Ravage is a Decepticon scout and partner of Soundwave. He was sent down to Earth with a group of microcons to steal a shard of the Allspark. Following the completion of the mission, he journeyed to Egypt to aid in the Fallen's plan to harvest Earth's Sun but he was killed by Bumblebee in the process.

Name: Rebecca Chambers
Summary: Dr. Rebecca Chambers is a former member of S.T.A.R.S., a special forces unit of the Raccoon Police Department. Despite her sweet and seemingly fragile appearance, she is a medical expert and a capable fighter. She is currently a professor at a university in Chicago, USA.

Name: Regenerador
Summary: The Regenerador is a Plaga infected human that has been extensively experimented on and modified to create a monster that is nearly unkillable due to its regenerative abilities. Some versions of Regenerador have been altered further into spike-covered Iron Maidens.

Name: Reigen Arataka
Summary: Arataka Reigen is Mob's mentor and boss. He is the self-proclaimed "Greatest Psychic of the 21st Century" as well as owner and operator of the Spirits and Such Consultation Office.

Name: Rex Fury
Summary: Rex Fury was a notorious criminal since he was 6 years old. After being put behind bars by Chase McCain, the millionaire Forrest Blackwell helped him escape. In return, Rex would assist him in a plan to make a space colony on the Moon.

Name: Richie Kirsch
Summary: Richie Kirsch is a superfan of Stab movie franchise, and with the help of a girl he met on Reddit, Richie hoped to create his own set of Ghostface killings in order to inspire Hollywood to take the series back to its roots. During the planning of this murder spree, Richie formed a faux relationship with Sam Carpenter, the daughter of Billy Loomis, whom he used to get closer to Woodsboro in order to kickstart the 2022 Ghostface murders.

Name: Riku
Summary: Riku is Sora's rival and best friend, as well as deuteragonist of Kingdom Hearts. A cool-headed and confident youth, he nevertheless is determined to leave the Destiny Islands and see the worlds outside of them. However, on the day he vowed to leave with Sora and Kairi, a freak storm hit that engulfed his world in darkness. Separated from his friends, Maleficent discovers his potential power and manipulates him into believing that Sora had forgotten and replaced him, stoking the inner darkness within Riku and turning him into an unwitting pawn despite his suspicions. Riku is later able to break free of the evil fairy's influence and decides to atone for his mistakes by sealing off the door to Kingdom Hearts along with King Mickey. His story did not end there, as he soon finds himself in Castle Oblivion's basement, having been guided there by Sora's heart. He takes this opportunity to continue assisting Sora from the shadows, but struggles with the darkness in his heart in spite of his attempts to embrace the light.

Name: Riley Freeman
Summary: Riley Freeman is a main character of the Boondocks comic strip and cartoon series.

Name: Robert Freeman
Summary: Robert "Granddad" Freeman is one of the main characters of The Boondocks series, the grandfather of Huey and Riley Freeman, former WWII veteran, and former civil rights activist. He is known for being quite hot-blooded, and will never shy away from using his trusty belt.

Name: Roman Bridger
Summary: https://vsbattles.fandom.com/wiki/File:RomanMonolouge3.ogg

Name: Roxanne Wolf
Summary: Roxanne Wolf is a primary antagonist who appears in Five Nights at Freddy's: Security Breach

Name: S.T.A.F.F. Bot
Summary: https://vsbattles.fandom.com/wiki/File:S.TAFFbotSEZNoTampering.ogg

Name: Sabo
Summary: Sabo is Luffy and Ace's childhood friend and sworn "brother". His weapon of choice is a long pipe, and was the first of them to set out on their dream of becoming great pirates. He was believed to have been killed by the World Nobles, but is later revealed to have survived and has been taken in by Monkey D. Dragon, having lost his memory in the process and didn't remember his past until he hears the news of Ace's death. During his time with the revolutionaries, he eventually risen to the rank of Chief of Staff, making him Dragon's second-in-command. And this was before he ultimately found and ate the Flame-Flame Fruit (Mera Mera no Mi), inheriting Ace's power and will.

Name: Sabyr
Summary: Sabyrs are Creatures of Grimm that resemble saber-toothed cats. They made their first appearance in “The Greatest Kingdom”, attacking the city of Mantle after a wall was breached.

Name: Saitama
Summary: Saitama (サイタマ?) is a human from Z-City who; through rigorous (sort of) training broke through his human limiters and achieved unbelievable strength and abilities. Never breaking a sweat, the name One Punch Man is fitting for the effortless wins Saitama has achieved through the series. Never going beyond a simple brawl, his sheer strength, speed, and power have effortlessly mowed down anyone in his way.

Name: Saizou Komiya
Summary: Saizo Komiya (小宮 砕蔵, Komiya Saizo) was an antagonist to Tsukune Aono and Moka Akashiya and was the first enemy that was featured in the anime and manga adaptions of the series. In his first appearance, Saizo was portrayed as a typical school bully and in the manga was said to have been forced into Yōkai Academy because he molested women in the Human world.

Name: Samantha Carpenter
Summary: Having run from a troubled past, Samantha Carpenter returns to her haunted small California hometown to aid her younger sister and her group of friends against a new Ghostface entity. She is revealed to have been the daughter of Billy Loomis, who had cheated on Sidney with a girl named Christina Carpenter. Later, she and the Core Four (consisting of herself, her younger sister and the Meeks-Martin twins) are confronted with a series of Ghostface entities in New York City.

Name: Sark
Summary: Sark is the secondary antagonist in TRON. He was written by Ed Dillinger, and became the commander of the MCP's army and overseer of the games fought on the Game Grid. He was a merciless and evil program, willing to do anything that pleased the MCP. Sark was in charge of forcing the programs that believed in the users to play video game type gladiator games with personnel from Sark's Army as the opponents.

Name: Satoru (Mumen Rider)
Summary: Mumen Rider is a character from the Manga/Anime One Punch Man.

Name: Scooby Doo (Cartoon)
Summary: Scoobert "Scooby" Doo is the titular main protagonist of the animated franchise of the same name. He is a Great Dane, the mascot of Mystery Inc, and best friend of Shaggy Rogers.

Name: Scott Pilgrim
Summary: Scott William Pilgrim is the titular protagonist of the Scott Pilgrim media franchise.

Name: Shadow (Kingdom Hearts)
Summary: Shadow is the most common Heartless species usually found across nearly all worlds the main cast visits. While they may look cute, they are legitimately dangerous creatures one should watch out for.

Name: Shadow Ring
Summary: Shadow Ring is an A-Class Rank 32 hero for the Hero Association.

Name: Shelly De Killer
Summary: Shelly de Killer is the third heir to a line of assassins known as de Killer. De Killer is an assassin for hire, and after killing his victim, leaves behind a card with a pink shell on it as a signal that it was him who killed this person. This not to take credit for the kill, but take any blame or suspension off the person who hired him as a suspect. Authorities have been after him for years but he has always slipped away and kept from meeting any justice to his crimes.

Name: Sidney Prescott
Summary: Sidney Prescott is the main protagonist of the Scream film series.

Name: Sieg (Fate/Apocrypha)
Summary: nan

Name: Snow Golem (Minecraft)
Summary: The Snow Golem is a constructable entity. It mainly throws snowballs at the enemies, doing absolutely no damage to them.

Name: Sora (Kingdom Hearts V Cast)
Summary: Sora is the main protagonist of Kingdom Hearts V Cast. Sora is forced to sleep by Maleficent to traverse worlds to find the whereabouts of Donald Duck and Goofy, and save the universe from the darkness.

Name: Sora (Kingdom Hearts)
Summary: Sora is a cheerful, young boy hailing from the Destiny Islands and the main protagonist of the Kingdom Hearts series. Longing to see the worlds outside of his own, he and his friends Riku and Kairi pledged to build a raft and set out together. However, on their planned day of departure, a freak storm hit their home and their world was subsequently engulfed by the Darkness. It was at this time that Sora unlocked his ability to wield a Keyblade, a weapon of legend that is said to bring salvation or destruction but is thrown into a Corridor of Darkness despite his efforts to combat the shadows that were swarming his home. Awakening in Traverse Town, he soon sets out with Goofy and Donald Duck, attendants to King Mickey, to discover the mystery behind the darkness and reunite with his friends.

Name: Sora's Heartless
Summary: Sora's Heartless is the main antagonist of Kingdom Hearts coded and its remake, Kingdom Hearts Re:coded. He is the Heartless of the digital replica of Data-Sora that desires to consume the Datascape and the Real World.

Name: Spopovich
Summary: Spopovich was a martial artist who was mind controlled by Babidi.

Name: SSS9
Summary: SSS9 is the main antagonist of Godzilla vs Biollante. He was a spy and assassin.

Name: Starlight Glimmer
Key: '''From Season 5 to 8''' | '''Series Finale onward''' | '''Equestria Girls Human Self'''
Summary: Starlight Glimmer was the main antagonist of Season 5 of My Little Pony: Friendship is Magic, and later one of the show's main protagonists.

Name: Stinkmeaner
Summary: Colonel H. Stinkmeaner, simply known by all as Stinkmeaner, is the secondary antagonist in The Boondocks series. Stinkmeaner is described as one of the most evil human beings to ever walk the earth. He is sadistic, nihilistic and overall horrible to everyone he meets. He enjoys the pain and anguish of other people. He claims to hate everyone in general, but in truth, he simply loves being evil. He lived a long, terrible life. When he got killed by Robert Freeman, he is sent to hell, where he literally felt truly much more happy than he ever had been in life and considers it much better than jail.

Name: Stu Macher
Summary: Stu Macher aids Billy Loomis in the 1996 Woodsboro murders, donning a ghost mask and cloak that would later be known as the Ghostface costume. He is later killed by Sidney Prescott after she drops a television set over his head, electrocuting him.

Name: Suisei Hoshimachi
Summary: Suisei Hoshimachi is a hard-working, modest, multitalented singer and aspiring idol. As such, she focuses very heavily on singing, dancing and performing, having performed in multiple concerts. She's also a master of Tetris. While she's normally among the more level-headed members of Hololive, when Suisei is angry, she displays a different side of her, known of Suicopath, where she's violent, temperamental and unforgiving. At that stage, few dare oppose her. She has a friendly rivalry with Marine Houshou.

Name: Sung Jin-Woo (Novel)
Summary: nan

Key: '''Human''' | '''Unicorn Form''' | '''Element of Magic (Demon Form)''' | '''Pony-Up Form''' | '''Daydream Shimmer'''
Summary: Sunset Shimmer is a reformed villain from My Little Pony: Friendship is Magic.

Summary: Tier: At least 9-B, likely 8-A

Name: Tara Carpenter
Summary: https://vsbattles.fandom.com/wiki/File:TaraMainQuote.mp3.ogg

Name: Tenga Onigawara
Summary: Tenga Onigawara (鬼瓦天牙, Onigawara Tenga) is the banchou of Salt Middle School and an unofficial member of the Body Improvement Club.

Name: The Brute (Lego Fortnite)
Summary: The Brute from Lego Fortnite is by far the most powerful creature in the game. Lego Fortnite is chock-full of hostile creatures, hazards, and enemies, but none are as intimidating as the towering Brutes that roam the various Biomes in your World. Equipped with four devastating attacks and an impressive health pool, tracking down and defeating these aggressive beasts can seem near impossible without upgraded Weapons and Health Charms. But if you manage to take down a Brute, you'll be rewarded with Brute Scales which can be used to upgrade your crafting bench.

Name: The Daycare Attendant
Summary: The Daycare Attendant is a recurring antagonist in Five Nights At Freddy's: Security Breach.

Name: The Dazzlings
Summary: The Dazzlings are the villains of the My Little Pony: Friendship is Magic movie Rainbow Rocks.

Name: The Hateocracy
Summary: The Hateocracy are a gang of elderly, nasty, self-hating bigots and the major antagonists of the episode "Stinkmeaner 3: The Hateocracy".

Name: The Looper (Lego)
Summary: The Looper (Also simply known as The Player) is the unnamed protagonist of the sub-game Lego Fortnite. The focus of the game is on long-term survival, crafting and online cooperation with friends.

Name: The Mimic (Five Nights at Freddy's)
Summary: Now I will tell you a story about a mother and a little boy who lived alone in a cabin in the dark woods. There was a monster in the woods. But the mother caught it and kept it locked in the basement. The monster always made scary noises at night, but the mother would tell the boy not to worry because it could never get out. Then she would sing the boy a lullaby to sleep. One day, the monster stopped growling and instead, listened and learned the lullaby. The next day when the mother went out to find food, the monster sang the lullaby from the basement. The little boy heard the lullaby and opened the door.

Name: The Mooninites
Summary: - Ignignokt

Summary: nan

Name: The Phantom (Ace Attorney)
Summary: The Phantom is an international spy with no true identity to speak of. He is a human incapable of experiencing emotions the way humans do with his only drive being to accomplish the missions delivered to him. For the majority of Dual Destinies, he lies under the guise of detective Bobby Fullbright.

Name: The Player (A Heist With Markiplier)
Summary: [redacted] is the being through which the viewer sees the events of A Heist With Markiplier. Though they frequently showcase their shapeshifting capabilities, no one within the lore notices their changes.

Name: Twilight Sparkle (Pony World)
Key: '''Unicorn Form''' | '''Alicorn Form''' | '''The Ending of the End Alicorn Form''' | '''Elements of Harmony/Magic of Friendship''' | '''All Alicorn Magic''' | '''Post-Timeskip Alicorn Form''' | '''Rainbow Power''' | '''Equestria Girls Human form'''
Summary: Twilight Sparkle is the main protagonist of My Little Pony: Friendship is Magic.

Summary: Twilight Sparkle is one of the main protagonists in the My Little Pony: Equestria Girls series.

Name: Ty Lee
Summary: Ty Lee was a cheerful and energetic girl who hailed from the Fire Nation.

Name: Uncle Ruckus
Summary: Uncle Ruckus (born July 4, 1939) is a fictional character and the main antagonist of the American animated sitcom The Boondocks. Voiced by Gary Anthony Williams, he first appeared on television in the show's pilot, "The Garden Party", on November 6, 2005. Created and designed by cartoonist Aaron McGruder, Ruckus enjoyed great success after appearing in the comic strip of the same name.

Name: Ursa (RWBY)
Summary: Ursai are large, bear-like Creatures of Grimm that first appeared in "The Emerald Forest" in Volume 1. They have appeared in two varieties: the smaller, more common Ursa Minor, and the larger, better armored and more powerful Ursa Major.

Name: Vegapunk (One Piece)
Key: '''With Satellites''' | '''With Sea Beast Weapons or PX·III''' | '''With Seraphim'''
Summary: The Vegapunks are a group of seven individuals who collectively represent the genius mind of Dr. Vegapunk, the leading scientist of the World Government. Unable to balance his overwhelming intelligence and the physical limitations of a single human body, Vegapunk created six Satellites — Lilith, Shaka, Edison, Pythagoras, Atlas, and York — each embodying a distinct aspect of his personality. Together, they operate as the core of Egghead Island, a technologically advanced island said to be 500 years ahead of the rest of the world.

Name: Velma (Cartoon)
Summary: Velma is the bespectacled resident genius of Mystery Inc., often being the one to decipher the clues and solve the crimes.

Name: Videl
Summary: Videl is the daughter of Mr. Satan, who is very protective of her especially in respect to boys. She is a tough, tomboyish character raised with fame all around her. She grows up learning martial arts hoping to be as great as her father when in fact, unknown to herself, she is already better and stronger than him.

Name: Wakka (Kingdom Hearts)
Summary: Wakka is a minor character in the Kingdom Hearts series, originally from Final Fantasy X. He is one of the residents living in Destiny Islands and is part of a trio including Tidus and Selphie. In Sora's Dive to the Heart, he appears in the Destiny Islands area along with Selphie and Tidus. He asks Sora "What do you want outta life?"

Name: Wallflower Blush
Summary: Wallflower Blush is the hidden main antagonist of the My Little Pony: Equestria Girls special, Forgotten Friendship.

Name: Wayne Bailey
Summary: Wayne: There's a very special bond between a father and his first son. Which is why I helped him build this collection. Sam: This was, all his? Wayne: Yes, he was a very passioned collector and he inspired others. Ah, we had to kill those two wannabe film students because, well, we had to kill you first, Sam. I put the theater in their name, and good-old Detective Bailey would've just stumbled on it, but I didn’t have too because by golly, that Gale Weathers is one hell of a journalist. I built a tribute to my son, which is why this is where you have to die, Sam. Surrounded by all the things he loved the most.

Name: William Afton (Games)
Key: '''William Afton''' | '''Post-Springlock Failure''' | '''Post-Fazbear Frights Fire''' | '''Ultimate Custom Night'''
Summary: https://vsbattles.fandom.com/wiki/File:WilliamAftonDeception.ogg

Name: Woody (Toy Story)
Summary: Woody, sometimes titled Sheriff Woody, is one of the main protagonists of the Toy Story franchise. Woody is a 50s-era smart toy that uses a pull string to repeat a select few phrases; however, when Andy (or any other human) isn't watching, Woody and the other toys would "wake up;" that is, switch from being inanimate objects to living toys. Before Andy got Buzz Lightyear for his birthday, Woody was Andy's favorite toy. After an initial falling-out with Buzz Lightyear over his own jealousy, Woody and Buzz would become respectable friends with one another.

Name: Yancy (AHWM)
Summary: Yancy is one of the prisoners at Happy Trails Penitentiary. He was arrested after killing both of his parents, but discovered he enjoyed life in the prison.

Name: Yang Xiao Long (RWBY Chibi)
Summary: Yang Xiao Long is one of the characters of RWBY Chibi.

Name: Yellow Rabbit (Return To The Pit)
Summary: The Yellow Rabbit is the main antagonist of the interactive novel, Return To The Pit. It is a supernatural entity of unknown nature which stalks Oswald during his trips to the past and eventually follows him home, impersonating his father. It can meet various fates depending on the route taken in the book.

Name: Zombie (Resident Evil)
Summary: Zombies are the result of humans succumbing to the effects of the T-Virus. They are distinguishable by their resemblance to corpses caused by the extensive necrosis on their skin and body. Originally created by Umbrella scientists as result of experimentation, they would rarely be seen in action up until 1998, the year the first viral outbreak was caused deliberately by former Umbrella scientist James Marcus, resulting in the infection of most of Umbrella's employees located in the Arklay Mountains. The actions of the now infected would lead to the intervention of S.T.A.R.S. police force which resulted in the Ecliptic Express and Mansion Incidents, where several members of the team would be brutally murdered by the infected.

Name: Akira Yuki (Godzilla)
Summary: Major Akira Yuki (結城 晃) is a G-Force soldier and the main human protagonist in the 1994 Godzilla film Godzilla vs. SpaceGodzilla. He is committed to getting revenge on Godzilla for causing the death of his best friend, Colonel Goro Gondo, during the events of the film Godzilla vs Biollante.

Name: Amber Freeman
Summary: Amber Freeman met her partner, Richie Kirsch over the Stab subreddit, where the two planned their own Ghostface killing spree. Amber, who lived in the house where the first Ghostface massacre ended, was all too eager to start her own, and proved herself to be a ruthless killer.

Name: Angry Dad
Summary: Angry Dad is a fictional character made by Bart Simpson from The Simpsons. It is about a father who has extremely bad anger issues, throwing fits over the smallest problems he runs into. This show being based on his father, Homer Simpson, and his anger problems.

Name: Axeman (Resident Evil: Afterlife)
Summary: The Axeman, also known as The Executioner, is a major antagonist in the Resident Evil film series, appearing in Resident Evil: Afterlife (2010) and Resident Evil: Retribution (2012). It is a mutated Undead bio-weapon created by the Umbrella Corporation at their top-secret Umbrella Prime facility in Siberia. Designed as a recreation of the Executioner Majini from the video game Resident Evil 5, the Axemen were engineered for enhanced combat capabilities and released into the world by the Red Queen AI to exterminate remaining human survivors during the global T-virus pandemic.

Name: Banana Joe
Summary: Joseph A. Banana, better known by his nickname Banana Joe is a supporting character in The Amazing World of Gumball. He is a living banana and a student at Elmore Junior High. Banana Joe loves making jokes, jumping around and replacing song lyrics with the word "banana". He is moderately popular at school, but this is because people find it funny when he makes a fool out of himself.

Name: Billy Loomis
Summary: https://vsbattles.fandom.com/wiki/File:BillyMainQuote.mp3.ogg

Name: Bulma
Summary: Bulma (ブルマ, Buruma; lit. "Bloomers") is a brilliant scientist and the second daughter of Capsule Corporation's founder Dr. Brief and his wife Mrs. Brief. At the age of 16, she found the two-star Dragon Ball in her basement. She created the Dragon Radar to find the other Dragon Balls so she can wish for a lifetime supply of strawberries, but later decides she wants to wish for the perfect boyfriend instead. As she was heading to Mount Paozu to find the next Dragon Ball when she accidentally hit a young boy named Son Goku with her car. Bulma was the first girl Goku had ever seen and even more so, the second human Goku had ever seen, after his guardian, Grandpa Gohan, who had died. After Goku took Bulma to his house, she finds out that he has the four-star Dragon Ball, and explains the legend and power behind them. After failing to seduce Goku for it, she decides to become traveling partners with him to which he agrees, thus beginning their journey as well as the Dragon Ball saga as a whole.

Name: Buzz Lightyear (Toy Story)
Summary: Buzz Lightyear is the deuteragonist of the Disney/Pixar Toy Story movies. He is a spaceman action figure originally belonging to Andy Davis. Buzz was created during a time where astronauts were especially popular amongst children. His arrival in the original Toy Story created conflict with Andy's favorite toy, Sheriff Woody, although this rivalry would eventually blossom into a lifelong friendship.

Name: Chad Meeks-Martin
Summary: Chad Meeks-Martin is the nephew of legacy character, Randy Meeks, and son of Martha Meeks. Although Chad doesn’t share many traits with his uncle unlike his twin sister, Mindy, who he is still close with. As a Woodsboro High football player, he dated Liv McKenzie. When a new Ghostface appears, Chad suspects Vince Schneider, Liv's ex, who has been stalking her online. After Vince's murder, Chad briefly becomes a suspect and is later attacked while searching for Liv at Wes Hicks' memorial party.

Name: Charlie Walker
Summary: Charlie Walker is the secondary antagonist of Scream 4.

Name: Chica (Five Nights at Freddy's)
Summary: https://vsbattles.fandom.com/wiki/File:WItheredChicaFaceBreaker.ogg

Name: Convicts
Summary: The Convicts, consisting of Sam Franklin, Reginald Jenkins, and Miguel Sanchez, are psychopaths in Dead Rising who are involved in the mission Prisoners.

Name: Cotton Weary
Summary: Cotton Weary was a resident of Woodsboro, who had a secret affair with an older woman, Maureen Prescott, and was falsely accused and arrested of her rape and murder in late-September 1995. However, he was released a year later when it was revealed that Billy Loomis and Stu Macher were the ones that killed Maureen and framed Cotton. Opportunistic, he sought fame and fortune with Gale's help and finally achieved it after saving Sidney's life at Windsor College in 1998. He parlayed the media coverage into his own show in Hollywood, 100% Cotton, before finally falling prey to a new Ghostface whose quest was to locate Sidney.

Name: Dewey Riley
Summary: Dwight “Dewey” Riley is one of the main characters of the Scream series. He's a retired cop (and former sheriff) and the ex-husband of Gale Weathers, and a survivor of the first Woodsboro murders. During the first Ghostface's 1996 killing spree, he lost his sister to the killer, which served as his motivation to assist Sam during the 2022 killings. Since 1996, he’s had to face many more Ghostface killers, even being the one to kill Roman Bridger.

Name: Diamond Dogs
Summary: The Diamond Dogs were a PMC (Private Military Contractor) formed by Kazuhira Miller in the early 1980s, and commanded from 1984 onwards by Venom Snake, after recovering from his coma. Under his command, it would become an extremely powerful and highly influential player in the worldwide military-industrial complex, taking on jobs for all clients.
