The organization would end up at odds with XOF, the covert strike force of the shadow government known as The Patriots, due to the feud between Big Boss/Venom Snake and XOF's leader, Skull Face. Ultimately, Diamond Dogs would emerge victorious, with Venom Snake and Kazuhira Miller dealing the finishing blows to Skull Face and scattering XOF. The PMC would remain in operation for roughly a decade more, before being supplanted and its strength absorbed by Big Boss' military fortress nation, Outer Heaven.

Name: Douglas Gordon
Summary: Captain Douglas Gordon (ダグラス・ゴードン Dagurasu Gōdon) is the captain of the Gotengo in the 2004 Godzilla film, Godzilla: Final Wars. He is portrayed by UFC Hall of Famer Don Frye.

Name: Edwin Murray
Summary: Edwin Murray is the loving husband of Fiona Murray and father of his son, David Murray. Despite his love for them, due to all of the commissions by Fazbear Entertainment, Edwin was so engrossed in his work that he didn't have enough time to spend. Before David's third birthday party however, Fiona decides to help out at Fall Fest, dying after a brief fire and leaving Edwin alone with David.

Name: Ethan Landry
Summary: Ethan Kirsch, also known under the alias of Ethan Landry, is a secondary antagonist of Scream VI.

Name: Foxy (Five Nights at Freddy's)
Summary: https://vsbattles.fandom.com/wiki/File:PhoneGuyFoxy.ogg

Name: Franz Gutentag
Summary: Franz Gutentag, real name Franz Schlechtnacht, is a one-episode character in the animated series, Family Guy.

Name: Franziska von Karma
Summary: Franziska is the daughter of the legendary Prosecutor Manfred von Karma, from whom she adopted tactics and her obsession with perfection. She usually carries a whip, or a riding crop when she was younger, and she will not hesitate to use it against anyone who tries to bother her.

Name: Fredbear (Five Nights At Freddy's)
Summary: Fredbear is an animatronic mascot for Fredbear's Family Diner, and an important character withing the Five Nights at Freddy's franchise, though most notably Five Nights at Freddy's 4. He is one of two "spring-lock" suits, the other being Spring Bonnie. Both animatronics double as animatronics and suits. He would later be possessed by a Crying Child, becoming Golden Freddy, as well as being dreamed up as Nightmare Fredbear and Nightmare. Fredbear is also a secret animatronic in the game Ultimate Custom Night. Fredbear appears after the Death Token is used on Golden Freddy.

Name: Freddy & Friends
Summary: (Ragged moaning from animatronics can be heard) Oh no..." (Sound used by Golden Freddy during his jumpscare plays, call ends)

Name: Freddy Fazbear
Summary: https://vsbattles.fandom.com/wiki/File:PhoneGuyFreddy.ogg

Name: Gale Weathers
Summary: Gale Weathers (formerly Gale Riley) appears in the Scream films as an ambitious, strong-willed news reporter, journalist, and writer who ultimately joins forces with Sidney Prescott and Dewey Riley, the latter of whom she eventually falls in love with and marries, in order to investigate and stop the Ghostface murders.

Name: Garoga Spider
Summary: The Garoga Spider (ガロガスパイダー) is a kaiju created by Toho that first appeared in the ninth episode of Zone Fighter, Search for the Secret of the Red Spider!.

Name: Ghostface (1996)
Summary: The Ghostface killers of 1996 are a pair of high school seniors, Billy Loomis and Stu Macher, who terrorize the town of Woodsburo one year after killing Maureen Prescott. The two would call their victim’s phone, taunting them with a voice changer before attacking them while dressed in a mask and cloak. Together, they ended the lives of six people, all before being killed by their main target, Sidney Prescott.

Name: Ghostface (1998)
Summary: The Ghostface killers of 1998 are Nancy Loomis and Mickey Altieri, whom team up for a series of copycat murders based on the 1996 killers of the same alias. Together, they terrorize Windsor College in pursuit of Sidney Prescott.

Name: Ghostface (2011)
Summary: The Ghostface killers of 2011 are Jill Roberts and Charlie Walker, two high school students who seek to gain fame from their murders. Together, they massacred the town of Woodsboro, in hopes of going down in history as the survivors of their own tragedy. However, Jill would go on to betray Charlie, hoping to become the sole survivor of the incident. Jill's reign as the sole survivor would soon be thwarted by her cousin, Sidney Prescott, after she awoke in the ICU.

Name: Ghostface (2022)
Summary: The Ghostface killers of 2022 are Richie Kirsch and Amber Freeman. The couple met on Reddit after being disappointed by the release of Stab (2021), and so began to form a plan to give Hollywood new material for a proper Stab movie. Their scheme ended with several dead, until it was stopped by Sidney Prescott, Gale Weathers, Sam Carpenter, and Tara Carpenter.

Name: Ghostface (2023)
Summary: The Ghostface killers of 2023, Wayne Bailey, Ethan Landry, and Quinn Bailey were the culprits of the New York Murders. The trio are a family, seeking revenge for the death of Richie Kirsch, the brother of Ethan and Quinn and the son of Wayne. Together, they attempt to kill Samantha Carpenter and Tara Carpenter, going after Gale Weathers and many other victims along the way.

Name: Giant Rat (Godzilla)
Summary: The Giant Rats (大ネズミ) are Kaijus that first appeared in the 1969 Toho film Latitude Zero.

Name: Godzilla Jr.
Key: '''Baby Godzilla''' | '''Little Godzilla''' | '''Godzilla Jr.''' | '''Rebirth Godzilla''' | '''Post-Rebirth''' | '''Powered Up State'''
Summary: Godzilla Jr (ゴジラジュニア, Gojira Junia?), also known as Baby Godzilla (ベビーゴジラ, Bebī Gojira?) and Little Godzilla (リトルゴジラ, Ritoru Gojira?), is a young Godzillasaurus kaiju created by Toho that first appeared in the 1993 Godzilla film, Godzilla vs. Mechagodzilla II.

Name: Golden Freddy (Five Nights at Freddy's)
Summary: Golden Freddy is a mysterious character that appears in the first and second games of the Five Nights at Freddy's franchise, appearing as a rare Easter Egg first made truly widespread to the masses by Markiplier during his playthrough of Five Nights at Freddy's 1.[1]

Name: Happy Frog
Summary: Happy Frog is an animatronic first introduced in Freddy Fazbear's Pizzeria Simulator as a prop for your customizable pizzeria. Later, she was made an enemy in Ultimate Custom Night.

Name: Henry Emily
Summary: nan

Name: Herbert (Family Guy)
Summary: John Herbert is a recurring character from Family Guy

Name: Iggy
Origin: JoJo's Bizarre Adventure '''(Part III: Stardust Crusaders)'''
Summary: Iggy is a major character in the second half of JoJo's Bizarre Adventure Part III: Stardust Crusaders. Once a pure-breed champion who became a "king" of stray dogs in the slums of New York, he is captured by Muhammad Avdol and Joseph Joestar in order to aid them in their journey to Egypt to defeat Dio Brando.

Name: Jill Roberts
Summary: Jill Roberts is the main antagonist of Scream 4.

Name: Junpei Yoshino
Summary: Junpei Yoshino (吉よし野の順じゅん平ぺい, Yoshino Junpei?) is a supporting character in the Vs. Mahito Arc of the Jujutsu Kaisen series. He was a high school student in Satozakura High School who befriended Yuji Itadori, but turned into a curse user after meeting Mahito.

Name: Kairi Sisigou
Summary: Kairi Sisigou (獅子劫 界離, Shishigō Kairi) is the Master of Saber of Red in the Great Holy Grail War of Fate/Apocrypha.

Name: Kevin Flynn
Summary: Kevin Flynn: The Grid, A digital frontier. I tried to picture clusters of information as they moved through the computer. What did they look like? Ships? Motorcycles? Were the circuits like freeways? I kept dreaming of a world I thought I'd never see. And then, one day... Sam Flynn: You got in? Kevin Flynn: That's right man, I got in.

Name: Kilaak Queen
Summary: The Kilaak Queen (キラアク星人首領) is the leader of the Kilaaks and the main antagonist in the 1968 Godzilla film Destroy All Monsters.

Name: Kiyoshi Sato
Summary: Kiyoshi Sato (佐藤清志) is a G-Force lieutenant and a supporting character in the 1994 Godzilla film, Godzilla vs. SpaceGodzilla.

Name: Knack (Character)
Summary: Knack is the titular character in the game of the same name. He is a being made up of ancient relics that was brought to life by Doctor Vargas as a way to combat the Goblin threat.

Name: Kumasaka (Godzilla)
Summary: The second-in-command of the Xiliens, known as the Controller, shoots his Commander, tired of the slow plans of a peaceful takeover. Using his species' control over M Base, he takes control of the mutants, excluding Ozaki, and releases the monsters to resume their attacks on the cities. He also sends out an army of small fighter ships to assist in leveling and decimating human civilization. M-Unit commander Kumasaka holds off his former command while the others escape. However, their escape is hindered by Kazama, a fellow mutant, who Ozaki is able to subdue.

Name: Kuronuma
Summary: Kuronuma (黒沼) was the supreme commander of the first attempt by the Black Hole Planet 3 Aliens to conquer Earth using Mechagodzilla in the 1974 film Godzilla vs. Mechagodzilla. He was succeeded by the eerily identical-looking Mugal in the aliens' second attempt to invade the Earth.

Name: Mai (Dragon Ball)
Summary: Mai (マイ) is Emperor Pilaf's female minion. She always works with Shu and, although she is intelligent, the two of them always manage to fail their objectives. She is a beautiful, calculating enemy who always resorts to weaponry and technology; her serious tone is a foil to Shu's comic personality.

Name: Manfred Von Karma
Summary: Manfred Von Karma is the father of Franziska von Karma, and also the mentor of Miles Edgeworth. He was a renowned Prosecutor who had a 40-year record of no losses during his time as a prosecutor and earned the title "King of Prosecutors" until meeting Phoenix Wright, who put an end to this during the case of the DL-6 Incident and put him in jail for the murder of Gregory Edgeworth, a man he killed for causing him to get a penalty. He was taken to jail and and died shortly after.

Name: Mannequins
Summary: Created to be the perfect army, Mannequins are zombie-like beings created by Alchemy to protect Father and the top dogs of the Amestrian military. However, when they are finally awakened they run wild among its Central City, being a threat against almost all parties involved in a coup d'etat.

Name: Matango (Showa)
Summary: Matango (マタンゴ Matango) are mutant fungus kaiju that appeared in the 1963 Toho film, Matango.

Name: Meganula
Summary: In the Millennium era the Meganulon were prehistoric insects that were released into the modern world through a black hole experiment. A giant dragonfly flew through a black hole and laid an egg in the forest, which was discovered and taken home by a young boy. The boy dumped the egg into the sewers of Tokyo when it started to ooze. The egg hatched into several Meganulons, which flooded the city and attacked and killed several citizens before molting into Meganula.

Name: Michael Afton
Summary: Can you hear me? I don't know if you can hear me. ...I'm sorry.

Name: Mickey Altieri
Summary: Mickey Altieri was a college student who frequented an online forum for serial killers, where he met Nancy Loomis. After the two had met, Mickey began a new series of murders under the Ghostface moniker alongside his partner, hoping to get caught and go to trial in order to blame horror movies for his behavior.

Name: Miko Nakadai
Summary: Miko Nakadai is a teenage girl from Japan with a strong love of punk and metal. She's always searching for thrills and causing trouble. As the human partner to the Autobot Bulkhead, she's helped him get over his fear of his own strength by encouraging him to get in trouble with her. Her recklessness is actually a cover for her insecurity, leaping into danger to prove herself. Her fierce loyalty and sheer gall wound up impressing Wheeljack and even Ultra Magnus enough to let her join the Wreckers.

Name: Minilla (Godzilla Final Wars)
Summary: Minilla is an infant member of Godzilla's species. In Godzilla: Final Wars, Minilla appears near Mount Fuji without explaining his origins.

Name: Mr. Hippo
Summary: Mr. Hippo is an animatronic first introduced in Freddy Fazbear's Pizzeria Simulator as a prop for your customizable pizzeria. Later, he was made an enemy in Ultimate Custom Night. Mr. Hippo is arguably one of the most infamous antagonists in Ultimate Custom Night due to his long, droning ramblings after he kills the player.[1]

Name: Muhammad Avdol
Origin: JoJo's Bizarre Adventure '''(Part III: Stardust Crusaders)'''
Summary: Muhammad Avdol is a major character in JoJo's Bizarre Adventure Part III: Stardust Crusaders.

Name: Music Man
Summary: Music Man is a member of the "Posh Pizzeria" group, and first appears in Freddy Fazbear's Pizzeria Simulator.[2] He is classified as a "Heavy" animatronic, in "Very Good" condition within the Catalog.[2] Music Man also appears in Ultimate Custom Night, in which he is an antagonist capable of killing the player.[1] He starts behind the protagonist, and will slowly be triggered into attacking the opponent based on the amount of noise they make or allow to take place.[1]

Name: Mutants (Godzilla)
Summary: The Mutants are the genetic descendents of both humans and Xiliens. They were trained as a form of highly elite soldiers by the EDF under Commander Kumasaka. In Godzilla: Final Wars, all but Ozaki (and later Kazama) fell under the control of X. The most notable Mutant is Ozaki, who used his Keizer Energy to revive Godzilla.

Name: Nanbara (Godzilla)
Summary: Nanbara (南原) was an INTERPOL agent that appeared in the 1974 Toho film Godzilla vs. Mechagodzilla. He trailed Keisuke Shimizu and Saeko Kanagusuku from Okinawa to Tokyo, constantly shadowing them as well as Black Hole Alien agent Yanagawa.

Name: Nancy Loomis
Summary: Nancy Loomis is the mother of Billy Loomis, who left her family after her husband had an affair with Maureen Prescott. Years later, upon hearing of Billy’s death at the hands of Sidney Prescott, she pursues Sidney in hopes of killing her as an act of revenge. She recruits Mickey Altieri as her partner, the two having met on a forum for serial killers.

Name: Nedd Bear
Summary: Nedd Bear is an animatronic first introduced in Freddy Fazbear's Pizzeria Simulator as a prop for your customizable pizzeria. Later, he was made an enemy in Ultimate Custom Night.

Name: Nightmarionne (Five Nights At Freddy's)
Summary: https://vsbattles.fandom.com/wiki/File:YouCantWakeFromNightmarionne.ogg

Name: Nobara Kugisaki
Key: '''Fearsome Womb Arc''' | '''Kyoto Goodwill Event Arc''' | '''Shibuya Incident Arc'''
Summary: I love the me that dresses up and looks beautiful! I love the me that's strong! I'm Nobara Kugisaki!

Name: Orville Elephant
Summary: Orville Elephant is an animatronic first introduced in Freddy Fazbear's Pizzeria Simulator as a prop for your customizable pizzeria. Later, he was made an enemy in Ultimate Custom Night. Orville is frequently spoken about in Mr. Hippo's speeches.[1]

Name: Pet Shop
Origin: JoJo's Bizarre Adventure '''(Part III: Stardust Crusaders)'''
Summary: Pet Shop is a minor antagonist in JoJo's Bizarre Adventure Part III: Stardust Crusaders. He is a trusted pet of Dio Brando and the guardian of his mansion.

Name: Pigpatch
Summary: Pigpatch is an animatronic first introduced in Freddy Fazbear's Pizzeria Simulator as a prop for your customizable pizzeria. Later, he was made an enemy in Ultimate Custom Night.

Name: Quinn Bailey
Summary: Quinn Kirsch, also known under the alias of Quinn Bailey, is a secondary antagonist of Scream VI.

Name: Reedman
Summary: After Soundwave discovered the location of the AllSpark shard needed to resurrect Megatron, he deployed Ravage to the island of Diego Garcia where NEST was based. Ravage infiltrated the base's defenses and released the Microcons into the ventilation system of the chamber where the AllSpark fragment was held. The ball bearings coalesced into Reedman and proceeded to steal the fragment. Security was alerted but were quickly dealt with by the razor-sharp Decepticon while they made their escape. The drone then headed outside and met up with Ravage, who fended off more humans and retrieved the fragment from Reedman.

Name: Richie Kirsch
Summary: Richie Kirsch is a superfan of Stab movie franchise, and with the help of a girl he met on Reddit, Richie hoped to create his own set of Ghostface killings in order to inspire Hollywood to take the series back to its roots. During the planning of this murder spree, Richie formed a faux relationship with Sam Carpenter, the daughter of Billy Loomis, whom he used to get closer to Woodsboro in order to kickstart the 2022 Ghostface murders.

Name: Riza Hawkeye
Summary: Lieutenant Riza Hawkeye (リザ・ホークアイ, Riza Hōkuai) is an officer in the Amestrian State Military as well as the personal adjutant and bodyguard of Colonel Roy Mustang. A sharpshooter and firearms specialist, Lt. Hawkeye is an invaluable asset to the Colonel both in office and on the battlefield and serves as his closest and most supportive subordinate.

Name: Rockstar Bonnie
Summary: https://vsbattles.fandom.com/wiki/File:RockstarBonnieSinging2.ogg

Name: Rockstar Chica
Summary: Rockstar Chica is one of the Rockstar animatronics that first appears in Freddy Fazbear's Pizza Simulator, and later in Ultimate Custom Night. Her appearance bears resemblance to the original Chica. She has pinkish-magenta eyes with blue cheeks, eyelids and kneecaps. Rockstar Chica appears to have lipstick on her orange-colored beak and the text on her bib shows the words "LET'S ROCK!!!".

Name: Rockstar Foxy
Summary: Rockstar Foxy is one of the Rockstar animatronics that first appears in Freddy Fazbear's Pizzeria Simulator, and later in Ultimate Custom Night. He appears as a newer and unbroken version of the original Foxy, but with a yellow star in the middle of his torso, a peg leg, an accordion, and a small, green parrot on his shoulder, which can apparently act autonomously from Rockstar Foxy.

Name: Rockstar Freddy
Summary: Rockstar Freddy is one of the Rockstar animatronics that first appears in Freddy Fazbear's Pizzeria Simulator, and later in Ultimate Custom Night. Yet another interpretation of the original Freddy Fazbear, he differs by having red cheeks, much like Toy Freddy, a purple hat and bowtie rather than black, and a yellow star in the middle of his torso.

Name: Roman Bridger
Summary: https://vsbattles.fandom.com/wiki/File:RomanMonolouge3.ogg

Name: Ryoichi Shiraishi
Summary: Ryoichi Shiraishi (白石亮一) is an astrophysicist and one of the main characters in the 1957 Toho film, The Mysterians.

Name: Samantha Carpenter
Summary: Having run from a troubled past, Samantha Carpenter returns to her haunted small California hometown to aid her younger sister and her group of friends against a new Ghostface entity. She is revealed to have been the daughter of Billy Loomis, who had cheated on Sidney with a girl named Christina Carpenter. Later, she and the Core Four (consisting of herself, her younger sister and the Meeks-Martin twins) are confronted with a series of Ghostface entities in New York City.

Name: Sark
Summary: Sark is the secondary antagonist in TRON. He was written by Ed Dillinger, and became the commander of the MCP's army and overseer of the games fought on the Game Grid. He was a merciless and evil program, willing to do anything that pleased the MCP. Sark was in charge of forcing the programs that believed in the users to play video game type gladiator games with personnel from Sark's Army as the opponents.

Name: Shin Nemoto
Summary: Shin Nemoto (Nemoto Shin) is one of the Eight Bullets who works for Overhaul and the Shie Hassaikai. Shin appears cynical because he could never find anyone worthy of his trust and friendship, thanks to his Quirk. He states that emotions are unnecessary to carry out objectives, but it is unknown if he believes this or if it was just a way to demoralize Lemillion as he fought Overhaul.

Name: Shinichi Ozaki
Summary: Ensign Shinichi Ozaki (尾崎 真一) is a Mutant that was a member of M-Organization, which is part of the Earth Defense Force. He served under Captain Douglas Gordon aboard the Gotengo. He serves as the main protagonist of 2004 Godzilla film, Godzilla: Final Wars.

Name: Shockirus
Summary: Shockirus is a mutated sea louse kaiju created by Toho that first appeared in the 1984 Godzilla film, The Return of Godzilla.

Name: Sidney Prescott
Summary: Sidney Prescott is the main protagonist of the Scream film series.

Name: Solf J. Kimblee
Summary: Solf J. Kimblee (ゾルフ・J・キンブリー, Zorufu J Kinburī), the Crimson Lotus Alchemist (紅蓮の錬金術師, Guren no Renkinjutsushi), sometimes referred to as the Crimson Alchemist, is a recurring antagonist in the Fullmetal Alchemist series. He is a former State Alchemist and special agent working under the direct orders of Führer King Bradley. Admittedly sadistic and arguably psychopathic, Kimblee was imprisoned in Central City for several years after his official involvement in the Ishval Civil War for having infamously turned his unique brand of combustion-based combat alchemy on people who were not on his government-approved kill list. Due to conspiratorial acts at the top of government, Kimblee is officially exonerated of his crimes so as to serve as the Führer's hidden left hand in the secret battles to come.

Name: Stu Macher
Summary: Stu Macher aids Billy Loomis in the 1996 Woodsboro murders, donning a ghost mask and cloak that would later be known as the Ghostface costume. He is later killed by Sidney Prescott after she drops a television set over his head, electrocuting him.

Name: Tara Carpenter
Summary: https://vsbattles.fandom.com/wiki/File:TaraMainQuote.mp3.ogg

Name: The Judge (Ace Attorney)
Summary: There is not much known about The Judge. All that is known is The Judge is the one often presiding over the cases in Ace Attorney. While he is sometimes bumbling, and a little slow with details, he still stands for truth and justice. Even refusing to leave the courtroom despite the witness and killer threat of He courtroom with a bomb, until a verdict had been passed down. He does his best with his verdicts and has claimed he had never gotten a verdict wrong in his life many times before

Name: The Mimic (Five Nights at Freddy's)
Summary: Now I will tell you a story about a mother and a little boy who lived alone in a cabin in the dark woods. There was a monster in the woods. But the mother caught it and kept it locked in the basement. The monster always made scary noises at night, but the mother would tell the boy not to worry because it could never get out. Then she would sing the boy a lullaby to sleep. One day, the monster stopped growling and instead, listened and learned the lullaby. The next day when the mother went out to find food, the monster sang the lullaby from the basement. The little boy heard the lullaby and opened the door.

Name: The Mooninites
Summary: - Ignignokt

Name: The One You Shouldn't Have Killed
Summary: nan
ID: The One You Shouldn't Have Killed-FiveNightsAtFreddy's-9-C

Name: The Rainman
Summary: Jason Baker, known under the alias Caleb, otherwise known as the Rainman is the titular main antagonist of the 2023 indie-horror game, The Rainman.

Name: Tomomo
Summary: Tomomo is the self-made final boss of 100% Orange Juice. Tomomo is a magical girl who ascended to godhood via unknown means. Despite her so called super interesting backstory, Tomomo was left as a background character. Through her frustration as a background character, Tomomo recreated the Orange Juice verse to make her the overarching antagonist. However, this wouldn't last long.

Name: Tron (TRON)
Summary: Tron is one of the main protagonists of the TRON franchise. He is a security computer program written by Alan Bradley, and in 1982 was taken prisoner by the self-aware Master Control Program and forced to play on the Game Grid. His legendary skills and devotion to the users turned him into a formidable warrior and Disc Arena master.

Name: Vampire Plant
Summary: The Vampire Plant (吸血植物 lit. Bloodsucking Plant) is a mutated plant kaiju created by Toho that first appears in the 1961 Toho film, Mothra.

Name: Warfstache Automated Interview Automaton
Summary: The Warfstache Automated Interview Automaton is a robot being developed under Wilford Warfstache, modeled after him, to be able to conduct interviews on his behalf, and has currently reached its testing phase.

Name: Wayne Bailey
Summary: Wayne: There's a very special bond between a father and his first son. Which is why I helped him build this collection. Sam: This was, all his? Wayne: Yes, he was a very passioned collector and he inspired others. Ah, we had to kill those two wannabe film students because, well, we had to kill you first, Sam. I put the theater in their name, and good-old Detective Bailey would've just stumbled on it, but I didn’t have too because by golly, that Gale Weathers is one hell of a journalist. I built a tribute to my son, which is why this is where you have to die, Sam. Surrounded by all the things he loved the most.

Name: William Afton (Games)
Key: '''William Afton''' | '''Post-Springlock Failure''' | '''Post-Fazbear Frights Fire''' | '''Ultimate Custom Night'''
Summary: https://vsbattles.fandom.com/wiki/File:WilliamAftonDeception.ogg

Name: Woody (Toy Story)
Summary: Woody, sometimes titled Sheriff Woody, is one of the main protagonists of the Toy Story franchise. Woody is a 50s-era smart toy that uses a pull string to repeat a select few phrases; however, when Andy (or any other human) isn't watching, Woody and the other toys would "wake up;" that is, switch from being inanimate objects to living toys. Before Andy got Buzz Lightyear for his birthday, Woody was Andy's favorite toy. After an initial falling-out with Buzz Lightyear over his own jealousy, Woody and Buzz would become respectable friends with one another.

Name: Xiliens (Godzilla Final Wars)
Summary: The Xiliens returned as the villains in Godzilla Final Wars nearly four decades later. Intending to harvest the mitochondria from human cells for sustenance, they again posed as allies to humanity, unleashing an army of monsters under their control before teleporting them all away. When their plan was exposed by the Earth Defense Force, the Xilien Commander was assassinated and usurped by his subordinate who became the Controller of Planet X. The Controller unleashed all of the Xiliens' mind-controlled kaiju on Earth and tried to eliminate all resistance, but the surviving members of the EDF used the Gotengo to free Godzilla from his prison in Antarctica. Godzilla swiftly eliminated most of the Xiliens' monsters before the Controller summoned his ultimate weapon, Monster X, to stop him. The Gotengo breached the Xilien Mothership and its crew were able to defeat the Controller and his minions. In a final act, the Controller set the Mothership to self-destruct, but the Gotengo was able to escape in time and help Godzilla overcome Monster X's final form, Keizer Ghidorah.

Name: Yellow Rabbit (Return To The Pit)
Summary: The Yellow Rabbit is the main antagonist of the interactive novel, Return To The Pit. It is a supernatural entity of unknown nature which stalks Oswald during his trips to the past and eventually follows him home, impersonating his father. It can meet various fates depending on the route taken in the book.

Name: 170,000-Year-Old Cicada Nymph
Summary: 170,000-Year Cicada Nymph (17万年ゼミ幼虫, 17 Man-nen Zemi Yōchū) is a large Mysterious Being that attacked Z-City at some point during Saitama's training years.

Name: A.K.I.
Summary: A.K.I. is a character introduced in Street Fighter 6. She is F.A.N.G's protégé and assistant, as well as a sort of adoptive daughter. A.K.I. was a street child living of expedients and hoaxes, until the day she and her brother tried to extort money from F.A.N.G. The former Shadaloo responded by putting them before a deadly trial that would have killed them both regardless of the choice. However, A.K.I. unexpectedly asked to learn more about F.A.N.G. instead. Intrigued by the child's attitude, F.A.N.G. took her in and raised her in the ways of the Poison Hand.

Name: Aang
Summary: Aang was a male Air Nomad born in 12 BG and the Avatar during the Hundred Year War, succeeding Avatar Roku and preceding Avatar Korra. As the Avatar of his time, he was the only person capable of using all four Bending arts: Airbending, Waterbending, Earthbending, and Firebending. He was also one of a select few Avatars and one of the first in many cycles to learn the ancient art of Energybending and the first Avatar known to have actively used the technique.

Name: Abe Simpson
Summary: Abraham Jay "Abe" Simpson II, commonly known as Grampa Simpson or simply Grampa, is a major recurring character in The Simpsons and a supporting character in The Simpsons Movie. He is the elderly patriarch of the Simpson family, Abe was a World War II veteran who was later sent to the Springfield Retirement Castle by Homer. He is known for his long, rambling, and often inaccurate stories.

Name: Ada Wong
Summary: Ada Wong is a secret agent appearing in the Resident Evil franchise. She was first introduced in Resident Evil 2 as a supporting character and reappeared in Resident Evil 4 and Resident Evil 6 as one of the main characters.

Name: Adam Kane (Dead Rising)
Summary: This page contains or depicts disturbing and/or graphic content that some may find upsetting, and that is only intended for mature audiences. Please proceed with caution.

Name: Adam MacIntyre
Summary: Adam MacIntyre once was a popular clown before the zombie outbreak. He went mad after they ate his audience.

Name: Agnaktor
Summary: Agnaktor is a large Leviathan which was first introduced in Monster Hunter 3 or Monster Hunter Tri.

Name: Akira Yuki (Godzilla)
Summary: Major Akira Yuki (結城 晃) is a G-Force soldier and the main human protagonist in the 1994 Godzilla film Godzilla vs. SpaceGodzilla. He is committed to getting revenge on Godzilla for causing the death of his best friend, Colonel Goro Gondo, during the events of the film Godzilla vs Biollante.

Name: Albert Wesker
Summary: Albert Wesker is the main antagonist in the Resident Evil series. He was the leader of S.T.A.R.S. while secretly working for Umbrella Corporation as a Researcher. Later working for The 3rd Organization, H.C.F. (Hive/Host Capture Force), TriCell, he shifts allegiances at will to further his own goals of world domination. Wesker has been directly or indirectly responsible for the events of every game, and always seems to come out on top. Eventually, he would go on to pursue his megalomaniacal desires for world domination with the Uroboros virus, but was stopped by his arch-nemesis Chris Redfield and the BSAA.

Name: Alex (Street Fighter)
Summary: Alex is a playable character in the Street Fighter series, and the protagonist of the Street Fighter III games. He is a professional wrestler who lives day-by-day out of his trailer house in New York, which he never left and has no interest in doing so. His day is spent between construction jobs, wrestling events and training. Tom, Alex's mentor and a friend of his father, is worried about him, as he always keeps his emotions in check, isn't very talkative and lacks sensitivity, which makes it seem he lacks a true purpose in his life, although things apparently started to change after his meeting with Dhalsim.

Name: Alligator (Resident Evil)
Summary: The Alligator is an irregular mutant found in the sewer area of Raccoon City. For unknown reasons he was infected by the T-Virus, which greatly increased its size. It inhabits the waste area and its large size prevents it from moving freely through the sewer system. It is different from The Crocodiles that appear in Resident Evil 5.

Name: Amber Freeman
Summary: Amber Freeman met her partner, Richie Kirsch over the Stab subreddit, where the two planned their own Ghostface killing spree. Amber, who lived in the house where the first Ghostface massacre ended, was all too eager to start her own, and proved herself to be a ruthless killer.

Name: Angel Quijano (Dead Rising)
Summary: This page contains or depicts disturbing and/or graphic content that some may find upsetting, and that is only intended for mature audiences. Please proceed with caution.

Name: Angry Dad
Summary: Angry Dad is a fictional character made by Bart Simpson from The Simpsons. It is about a father who has extremely bad anger issues, throwing fits over the smallest problems he runs into. This show being based on his father, Homer Simpson, and his anger problems.

Name: Annette Birkin
Summary: Annette Birkin was a scientist working at Umbrella. She was the wife of William Birkin and the mother of Sherry Birkin.

Name: Apple Bloom
Summary: Tier: At least 9-B, likely 8-A | Likely 6-B

Name: Applejack (Human World)
Summary: Applejack is one of the main characters in My Little Pony Equestria Girls.

Name: Apu Nahasapeemapetilon
Summary: In the 1960s, Apu lived in India and spent some time as a student of the Maharishi Mahesh Yogi. He became a friend of Paul and Linda McCartney. He graduated from Calcutta Technical University and then got a scholarship in the United States at the Springfield Heights Institute of Technology. He achieved a doctorate in Computer Science by designing the world's first tic-tac-toe program that only the top human players could beat. After this, he took a job at the Kwik-E-Mart and continues to work there to this day. Due to his past, he is put in an arranged marriage with a woman named Manjula. After having 8 children (octuplets at that), he continues to raise his family and work his business in Springfield.

Name: Atlas (RWBY)
Summary: Atlas is a kingdom located in Solitas, the far northern continent of Remnant. Formerly known as Mantle, Atlas was founded by settlers who traveled north to the barren, icy continent of Solitas. Where the people were forced to adapt quickly in order to survive the difficult climate, leading them to quickly learn to utilize Dust and other technologies. Following the end of the Great War, Atlas Academy was founded to the north of the original city of Mantle, soon growing to overshadow Mantle and eventually becoming the new capital and namesake of the kingdom.

Name: Austin Powers
Summary: Sir Austin Danger Powers is a fictional British secret agent and the main protagonist in the Austin Powers series. He was presumably born around 1940 or 1941, cryogenically frozen in the late 1960s, and resurrected in the late 1990s.

Name: Axeman (Resident Evil: Afterlife)
Summary: The Axeman, also known as The Executioner, is a major antagonist in the Resident Evil film series, appearing in Resident Evil: Afterlife (2010) and Resident Evil: Retribution (2012). It is a mutated Undead bio-weapon created by the Umbrella Corporation at their top-secret Umbrella Prime facility in Siberia. Designed as a recreation of the Executioner Majini from the video game Resident Evil 5, the Axemen were engineered for enhanced combat capabilities and released into the world by the Red Queen AI to exterminate remaining human survivors during the global T-virus pandemic.

Name: Azula
Summary: Azula was the princess of the Fire Nation, daughter of Fire Lord Ozai and Princess Ursa, younger sister of Zuko, niece of Iroh, the older half-sister of Kiyi, the aunt of Izumi, and the grand aunt of Iroh II.

Name: B-127 (Transformers One)
Summary: B-127 is the Tritagonist of the film Transformers One. A worker in the lowest level of Waste Management, sub-level 50, Bee's isolation caused him to become extremely talkative, to the point of talking to himself and his imaginary friends, all to keep himself company. Upon meeting Orion Pax and D-16, who had both been banished to waste management, the trio would accidentally stumble upon a map leading to the lost Matrix of Leadership. Bee would then assist the two in finding the artifact, hoping to become good friends with the two.

Name: Balrog (Street Fighter)
Summary: Balrog, known as M. Bison (マイク・バイソン Maiku Baison) in Japan, is a character from the Street Fighter series. He first appeared as a boss character in Street Fighter II.

Name: Banana Joe
Summary: Joseph A. Banana, better known by his nickname Banana Joe is a supporting character in The Amazing World of Gumball. He is a living banana and a student at Elmore Junior High. Banana Joe loves making jokes, jumping around and replacing song lyrics with the word "banana". He is moderately popular at school, but this is because people find it funny when he makes a fool out of himself.

Name: Bart Simpson
Summary: Bartholomew JoJo "Bart" Simpson (born April 1, 1980) is a main character and the tritagonist of The Simpsons.

Name: Bear Thief
Summary: The Bear Thief (Sanzoku Kuma (山賊熊?, lit. "Bandit Bear")) is a minor antagonist encountered by Bulma and Son Goku on their search for the Dragon Balls.[1] He is a large anthropomorthic brown bear who lives near Mt. Paozu, attacking any passerby of their food and valuables.

Name: Beck (TRON)
Summary: Beck is a young program who adopts the persona of Tron to free his home and friends from the reign of the villainous CLU and his henchman General Tesler. With training from Tron, the greatest warrior the Grid has ever come to know, he not only teaches Beck the fighting and lightcycle skills he needs to challenge this brutal military occupation, but becomes a guide and mentor to him as he grows beyond his youthful, impulsive nature into a courageous, powerful, strong leader.

Name: Bee (Hollow Knight)
Summary: Bees are the residents of the Hive, below the Kingdom's Edge, are a species of sentient bees. These airborne warriors possess a hive mind which dictates their behaviour among the Hive. Hivelings carry out simple tasks, and can colonize husks to serve the Hive's purpose.

Name: Belfly
Summary: Belflies are enemies in Hollow Knight. They are quick, highly volatile flying creatures who dive at prey with no sense of self-preservation. The Belfly Hangs from a ceiling, emitting a high-pitched squeak. Listen carefully for this sound as it is usually found in dark or secluded places, where spotting it usually means that it is too late to avoid contact with it.

Name: Beowolf
Summary: Beowolves are large werewolf-like Creatures of Grimm. They are the most basic and abundant type of Grimm on Remnant and are the first Grimm seen in the series.

Name: Billy Loomis
Summary: https://vsbattles.fandom.com/wiki/File:BillyMainQuote.mp3.ogg

Name: Birdie (Street Fighter)
Key: '''Street Fighter''' | '''Street Fighter Alpha Series''' | '''Street Fighter V'''
Summary: Birdie is one of the characters who debuted in the first game of the series, and later returned with a drastic change in design and personality, most notably his loved hair and signature chains. He used to be a heel wrestler, until he grew unable to endure the laughter and contempt, and was expelled after having hospitalized several colleagues. He then alternated working as a bouncer in a bar to small illegal activities, becoming renowned in the underground for his great strength.[3]

Name: Bitores Mendez
Summary: Father Bitores Mendez is one of the many antagonists of Resident Evil 4. He was a Catholic priest that fell into the influence of Osmund Saddler and later led the initial hunt for Leon S. Kennedy, Dr. Luis Sera and Ada Wong, which were potential threats to the cult, though Leon ultimately killed him after a long fight.

Name: Blangonga
Summary: Blangonga is a Fanged Beast introduced in Monster Hunter 2.

Name: Blanka
Summary: Blanka (ブランカ, Buranka), also known by his birth name Jimmy (ジミー Jimī), is a video game character from the Street Fighter series. Blanka's first appearance in the series was in Street Fighter II as part of the starting lineup.

Name: Boarbatusk
Summary: Boarbatusks are large, boar-like Creatures of Grimm. The first is seen in the episode "The Badge and The Burden" of RWBY Volume 1.

Name: Bora
Summary: Bora (ボラ) is a tall, muscular man who resides in the Sacred Land of Korin with his son Upa, in a tepee at the base of the Korin Tower.

Name: Boss Baby
Summary: Theodore Lindsay Templeton, better known as the Boss Baby, is the titular main protagonist of the Boss Baby franchise. Despite physically being an infant, the Boss Baby has the maturity and mentality of an experienced businessman. He works for Baby Corp, a company whose mission is to make sure babies remain the most loved creatures on Earth.

Name: Brad Park (Dead Rising)
Summary: This page contains or depicts disturbing and/or graphic content that some may find upsetting, and that is only intended for mature audiences. Please proceed with caution.

Name: Brian Griffin
Summary: https://vsbattles.fandom.com/wiki/File:Family-Guy-Whose-leg-do-you-have-to-hump-YoutubeConvert.cc-_1_1.ogg

Name: Brock Mason
Summary: Brock Mason is the second main antagonist of Dead Rising as well as Dead Rising: Chop Till You Drop.

Name: Broken Vessel
Summary: Broken Vessel is one of the main bosses in Hollow Knight. It blocks the way to the Monarch Wings. Lost Kin is its dream variant. Broken Vessel is one of the many Vessels who escaped the Abyss like the Knight, but unlike the Knight, was met with a tragic death while still in Hallownest.

Name: Bruce Irvin
Summary: Bruce Irvin was born and raised in a rough neighborhood, one troubled by criminals and gangsters. While at a young age, Bruce was left with no family when his parents and older brother were attacked and killed by gangsters. With no other family to turn to, Bruce was forced to survive, alone, on the streets. This did not break him, however, and knowing that he had to be strong to survive, Bruce trained in the art of Muay Thai kickboxing. Forced to fight on a daily basis to survive on the mean streets, Bruce turned this to his advantage by competing in the underground fight scene to earn money, where he soon developed a fearsome reputation due to his vicious temperament and uncompromising technique. This led Bruce to compete in professional tournaments, where he soon became the undisputed heavyweight champion.

Name: Bulbous G
Summary: Bulbous G is the second Hollow which attacked Yasutora Sado, was eventually defeated after Sado unlocked his Fullbringer.

Name: Bullfango
Summary: Bullfango are Fanged Beasts (formerly Herbivores), introduced in the first Monster Hunter.

Name: Bulma
Summary: Bulma (ブルマ, Buruma; lit. "Bloomers") is a brilliant scientist and the second daughter of Capsule Corporation's founder Dr. Brief and his wife Mrs. Brief. At the age of 16, she found the two-star Dragon Ball in her basement. She created the Dragon Radar to find the other Dragon Balls so she can wish for a lifetime supply of strawberries, but later decides she wants to wish for the perfect boyfriend instead. As she was heading to Mount Paozu to find the next Dragon Ball when she accidentally hit a young boy named Son Goku with her car. Bulma was the first girl Goku had ever seen and even more so, the second human Goku had ever seen, after his guardian, Grandpa Gohan, who had died. After Goku took Bulma to his house, she finds out that he has the four-star Dragon Ball, and explains the legend and power behind them. After failing to seduce Goku for it, she decides to become traveling partners with him to which he agrees, thus beginning their journey as well as the Dragon Ball saga as a whole.

Name: Bushido Brown
Summary: Bushido Brown was a bodyguard for hire who charged exorbitant fees to protect clients with his martial arts skill.

Name: Buzz Lightyear (Toy Story)
Summary: Buzz Lightyear is the deuteragonist of the Disney/Pixar Toy Story movies. He is a spaceman action figure originally belonging to Andy Davis. Buzz was created during a time where astronauts were especially popular amongst children. His arrival in the original Toy Story created conflict with Andy's favorite toy, Sheriff Woody, although this rivalry would eventually blossom into a lifelong friendship.

Name: Cade Yeager
Summary: All humans make mistakes. Sometimes, what comes from those mistakes comes the best thing that ever happened to them. That's what Cade Yeager believes when he looks at his daughter, to whom he and his girlfriend gave birth at the cost of their high school graduation. While Cade is not the most responsible father in the world, his most redeeming quality is that when it comes to keeping his daughter safe, he does not go back on his word, no matter what; a promise he made to his bride before she passed away. He does have a creative and optimistic mind, lending it to building all kinds of inventions to make a good business out of. Sadly, none of these inventions have brought in much profit for his family. Knowing all of the opportunities he lost, he has sworn not to let history repeat itself, which is probably why he disapproves of Tessa dating boys before she graduates from high school.

Name: Cammy White
Summary: Cammy White, also known by the codename Killer Bee, is a video game character from the Street Fighter series, first appearing in Super Street Fighter II. She was once a deadly assassin working for Shadaloo before breaking free and becoming an MI6 operative for the British government.

Name: Captain Gutt
Summary: Captain Gutt was a Gigantopithecus who took to being a self-styled master and captain of the high seas, taking whatever food he could find by theft and hoarding it with the help of his crew. Gutt is the main antagonist of Ice Age 4.

Name: Captain Magnum
Summary: Captain Magnum Longlegs is a pirate who, at the time of AHWM, was sailing through an unknown sea in search of treasure, though his crew is all dead. He encounters The Player in one of their many timelines, in which the Player's box is revealed to contain a map to treasure. The Player's choices determine whether or not Captain Magnum kills them and if they join the crew.

Name: Captain Mizuki
Summary: Captain Mizuki is the 71st ranked B-Class hero of One Punch Man. According to Hero Association executive Sekingar, Mizuki along with several other lower ranking heroes has S-Class potential, which is why he recruited them on the Monster Association raid. Before Mizuki became a professional hero, she was a world class track and field athlete. Her sports background can be seen in her fighting style and how she talks to others. Mizuki has a great respect for the S-Class heroes, especially Superalloy Darkshine and King, the former of which she has a student/mentor relationship with. Throughout raid she proves herself to be an incredibly capable hero and defeats numerous monsters, yet is helpless against Demon Level Rhino Wrestler, who Atomic Samurai dispatches of with ease. This shows that despite her great talent and potential she still has a long way to go before reaching the higher rankings of the Hero Association.

Name: Carla Radames
Summary: Carla Radames was a genius researcher who worked for Derek C. Simmons, doppleganger of Ada Wong and the main antagonist of Chris', Jake's and Ada's campaigns in Resident Evil 6, and is the secondary antagonist of Leon's campaign. Overall, Radames is the main antagonist of Resident Evil 6. Radames is one responsible for the discovery and creation of the C-Virus, and she is both the eventual founder and leader of an Umbrella Corporation-typed organization called Neo-Umbrella. Carla is initially portrayed as an uncharacteristically cruel Ada Wong. However, it is eventually revealed in Ada Wong's own campaign that she is in fact a clone Derek C. Simmons created using Carla Radames (without her consent), Ada Wong's DNA, and the C-Virus.

Name: Casey Rhodes
Key: '''Casey Rhodes''' | '''Dai-Shi awakening Arc (1-10)''' | '''Overlords Arc (11-21)''' | '''Phantom Beast Arc (22-32)'''
Summary: Casey Rhodes is the Jungle Fury Red Ranger. He was a fairly new member to the Pai Zhua Academy and hence known as a cub and possessed the spirit of the tiger. He has the power to stand up for what he believes in and for others. He doesn't like other people to get picked on. When Casey stood up one day for a fellow cub who was being verbally abused by Jarrod, Master Mao (the leader of the Pai Zhua Academy) dismissed Jarrod. Master Mao saw the potential that Casey had in him and chose him instead of Jarrod, to guard Dai Shi's imprisonment box.

Name: Centinel
Summary: Centinels are Creatures of Grimm that resemble large centipedes. Centinels aren't so much dangerous as they are terrifying and annoying. For Huntsmen and Huntresses that get an eradication order, it takes them ages to locate every single one, while enduring pop out scares from the floor, walls, and ceilings. As a result their rewards tend to be disproportionately large compared to their difficulty ranking.

Name: Chad Meeks-Martin
Summary: Chad Meeks-Martin is the nephew of legacy character, Randy Meeks, and son of Martha Meeks. Although Chad doesn’t share many traits with his uncle unlike his twin sister, Mindy, who he is still close with. As a Woodsboro High football player, he dated Liv McKenzie. When a new Ghostface appears, Chad suspects Vince Schneider, Liv's ex, who has been stalking her online. After Vince's murder, Chad briefly becomes a suspect and is later attacked while searching for Liv at Wes Hicks' memorial party.

Name: Chain'n'Toad
Summary: Chain'n'Toad is an A-Class Rank 36 hero for the Hero Association.

Name: Chainsaw Man (Resident Evil)
Summary: The Chainsaw Man is a class of Chainsaw Ganado. This Ganado wears a burlap potato sack as a mask over his head. the Chainsaw Man has been made exceptionally violent, and is compelled to relentlessly chase his enemies with his trademark chainsaw. Also, due to the Plaga's assimilation, he has been made exceptionally robust in comparison to regular villagers and can absorb small arms fire with ease.

Name: Charlie Nash
Summary: Charlie Nash, known as Charlie or Nash dependent upon the game and region, is a character from Capcom's Street Fighter series of fighting games. He is a strong Captain in the United States Air Force and fighting injustice alongside his friend Guile.

Name: Charlie Walker
Summary: Charlie Walker is the secondary antagonist of Scream 4.

Name: Chase McCain
Summary: Chase McCain is a police man famous for arresting the notorious criminal Rex Fury. However, he was sent overseas after accidentally giving away the identity of his secret witness. Two years later, Rex escaped from the prison and Chase would have to, once again, put on his badge and bring him to justice.

Name: Chi-Chi (Dragon Ball)
Summary: Chi-Chi is the former princess of Fire Mountain and the daughter of the Ox-King who later marries Goku and becomes the loving mother of Gohan and Goten. She was first introduced as a shy and fearful girl, but later, as she gets older, develops a very tomboyish, tough and fierce personality, which sometimes causes her to have anger outbursts seen several times throughout the series. Despite this, she has shown her love for Goku and their sons many times throughout the series.

Name: Chica (Five Nights at Freddy's)
Summary: https://vsbattles.fandom.com/wiki/File:WItheredChicaFaceBreaker.ogg

Name: Choco Yuzuki
Summary: Choco Yuzuki is a demon who works as the school nurse of the Underworld Academy. Despite being a common demon, she's sometimes mistaken for a succubus due to having the beauty of one. Thanks to that, she's incredibly popular among the students, the boys in particular coming to get checked up all the time. Choco is polite, respectful and acts a lot more mature than other Hololive talents, with the wisdom and intelligence to back that up. Though she sometimes partakes in shenanigans with her coworkers, she sometimes also shows a no-nonsence attitude when things become too ridiculous. She likes to dote on and spoil Luna Himemori.

Name: Choze
Summary: Choze is a martial arts competitor from One Punch Man. He comes from a clan of eugenicists determined to create a "superior race." Due to years of selective breeding with the best of genes, Choze was born with naturally superhuman abilities, which he uses to brutally torture others for his pleasure.

Name: Chris Griffin
Summary: Chris Griffin is one of the main characters in the animated series, Family Guy.

Name: Chris Redfield
Summary: Chris Redfield is one of the main protagonists of the Resident Evil series. He is a former member of the S.T.A.R.S. unit. He is now an American Special Operations Unit Captain of the BSAA (Bioterrorism Security Assessment Alliance), an anti-Bioterrorist group, of which he is a founding member along with his long-time partner, Jill Valentine. A senior member of an elite security force in Racoon City, S.T.A.R.S. Members of Team 1, they are the pride of S.T.A.R.S. for their competence in firearms and close combat. Chris is also the older brother of TerraSave member Claire Redfield. He appears in the original Resident Evil, Resident Evil - Code: Veronica, Resident Evil 5, Resident Evil 6, Resident Evil 7: Biohazard, and Resident Evil Village.

Name: Chuck Greene
Summary: This page contains or depicts disturbing and/or graphic content that some may find upsetting, and that is only intended for mature audiences. Please proceed with caution.

Name: Chun-Li
Summary: Chun-Li is a character in the Street Fighter series. She is the first female player character that appears in the series, one of the series' major lead characters alongside Ryu and Ken and the first playable female character to appear in a 1-on-1 fighting game. Introduced in Street Fighter II, Chun-Li was the only female character in the game, as well as one of the youngest fighters, and while not as physically powerful as the other characters, she is by far the quickest. She is one of the most popular playable female characters in the series.

Name: Claire Redfield
Summary: Claire Redfield is a current member of the human rights organization, TerraSave. She is the younger sister of BSAA operative and former S.T.A.R.S. member Chris Redfield. Claire is a survivor of the Raccoon City Incident, which took place in September 1998 after she traveled to the city in search of her brother. After escaping the city with the help of Leon S. Kennedy, Claire ventured to Europe to resume her search for Chris. In December, she was captured by Umbrella after infiltrating their Paris Laboratory and transported to the Umbrella owned Rockfort Island and imprisoned. When Rockfort Island was attacked by a mysterious Special Forces group, Claire tried to escape with a fellow prisoner, Steve Burnside, leading to both of their involvements in the Antarctic outbreak. Her brother soon learned of her situation and rescued her. In 2005, Claire confronted the t-Virus again when she arrived at Harvardville Airport to meet some friends. While surviving in the airport, she was reunited with Leon, now a U.S. Government agent, who had been sent to deal with the outbreak. Later, in 2011, Claire would be kidnapped along with other TerraSave members by Alex Wesker's organization and left on Sushestvovanie Island, which made her try to escape with Moira Burton amid the outbreak taking place there. Having been the only one to be rescued, she would eventually support Barry Burton in the search for his daughter and in the process participated in the elimination of the last of the Wesker Children. As early as 2014, in the midst of her investigation into bioterrorist activities taking place in the Sonido de Tortuga Island region, Claire was eventually involved in the outbreak that occurred at the site.

Name: Cleveland Brown
Summary: https://vsbattles.fandom.com/wiki/File:ClevelandOHThatsNasty.ogg

Name: Cliff Hudson
Summary: Cliff Hudson is a psychopath appearing in Dead Rising.

Name: CLU
Summary: CLU is an artificial intelligence program that was written in 1983 by Kevin Flynn. CLU is the main antagonist of TRON: Legacy, the secondary antagonist of TRON: Evolution and the overarching antagonist of TRON: Uprising. As with most programs, CLU appears visually identical - albeit at a younger age - to his creator. He represents an evil digital doppelgänger of Kevin Flynn and a twisted embodiment of Flynn's youth.

Name: Cole Evans
Summary: Cole Evans is the Red Ranger Wild Force and the main character of Power Rangers Wild Force, leading his team of rangers against Master Org and other Orgs.

Name: Colmillos (Resident Evil)
Summary: Colmillos (コルミロス) are Plaga-infested wolves encountered in Resident Evil 4. The name 'Colmillos' means 'Fangs' in Spanish.

Name: Conner McKnight
Key: '''Civilian Form''' | '''Red Ranger''' | '''Super Dino Mode''' | '''Triassic Ranger, w/ Battlizers'''
Summary: Conner McKnight is the Dino Thunder Red Ranger and leader of the group. He is given the special power of super speed by his Red Dino Gem and fights alongside the other DT rangers in order to defeat Mesagog. Conner's enjoys soccer, playing at Reefside High School and on a namesake club, and he aspires to be a famous soccer star. At first, he appears to fit the stereotype of being a high school jock as he comes off as hot-headed, arrogant and being a bit of a flirt with woman but he is actually a very well-meaning and honest person who always does the right thing in the end.

Name: Convicts
Summary: The Convicts, consisting of Sam Franklin, Reginald Jenkins, and Miguel Sanchez, are psychopaths in Dead Rising who are involved in the mission Prisoners.

Name: Cool Cat (Warner Bros.)
Summary: Cool Cat is a Bengal tiger from the classic era of Looney Toons shorts. Due to his species, he is constantly chased around by Colonel Rimfire, a big game hunter who never succeeds in catching him, mainly due to Cool Cat's extremely good luck.

Name: Cotton Weary
Summary: Cotton Weary was a resident of Woodsboro, who had a secret affair with an older woman, Maureen Prescott, and was falsely accused and arrested of her rape and murder in late-September 1995. However, he was released a year later when it was revealed that Billy Loomis and Stu Macher were the ones that killed Maureen and framed Cotton. Opportunistic, he sought fame and fortune with Gale's help and finally achieved it after saving Sidney's life at Windsor College in 1998. He parlayed the media coverage into his own show in Hollywood, 100% Cotton, before finally falling prey to a new Ghostface whose quest was to locate Sidney.

Name: Cozy Glow
Summary: Cozy Glow is an evil Pegasus in the series, My Little Pony.

Name: Crablante
Summary: Crablante was a Tiger-level Threat who was created when a man ate too much crab and transformed.

Name: Creep (RWBY)
Summary: Creeps are subterranean Creatures of Grimm that resemble both lizards and birds. They were first encountered in "No Brakes".

Name: Creeper (Kingdom Hearts)
Summary: Creeper is the weakest of the Nobody species, often being found alongside Dusks.

Name: Cretaceous and Maelstrom
Summary: Cretaceous and Maelstrom are the primary antagonists of the film Ice Age: The Meltdown. Cretaceous is slender with traits of both a crocodile and a fish, while Maelstrom is stout with a broad snout and a short tail.

Name: Crewmate (Among Us)
Summary: The Crewmates are one of the two roles in the murder mystery game, Among Us. Their role is to complete all of their assigned tasks or to deduce who the Impostor among them is so the Impostor can be ejected. Most locations they go to involve the theme of outer space adventure.

Name: Crimson Viper
Summary: Crimson Viper, also known as either C. Viper or by her true name Maya, is a video game character from the Street Fighter series, first appearing in Street Fighter IV. She is an undercover CIA agent who fights using an assortment of gadgets hidden within her battle suit.

Name: Crystal Guardian
Summary: The Crystal Guardian is part of the miners of Crystal Peak who died from the Infection and were reanimated by it. It appears larger than the other husks, has crystal growing on its back and encasing both its arms and its head.

Name: Dan Hibiki
Summary: nan

Name: Daphne (Cartoon)
Summary: Daphne Blake is the fashion-loving member of Mystery Inc, Daphne's characteristic trait in the gang is her tendency to get into danger, hence earning the nickname "Danger-prone Daphne".

Name: Dave (One-Punch Man)
Summary: Dave, is a Martial Artist and user of the Giant Style Crushing that participated in the 22nd Super Fight Tournament.

Name: Death (Family Guy)
Summary: Death, also known as the Grim Reaper, is a recurring character on Family Guy.

Name: Dee Jay
Summary: Dee Jay is a fighter and musical artist from Jamaica. He made his way as a kickboxer representing his country in tournaments around the world, quickly becoming a world-class champion. His musical career started when a record company scout noticed his extremely charismatic, fun-loving and upbeat attitude during a competition, and offered him a contract. Dee Jay discovered his natural talent for music, scoring a musical success after another and with all of his albums having gone gold. Over time his love for music started waning, but the spark was reignited when he realized the "Rhythm of Attacks" during a fight, and that he could combine his love of music and martial arts into a single journey.

Name: Demoman (Team Fortress 2)
Summary: A fierce temper, a fascination with all things explosive, and a terrible plan to kill the Loch Ness Monster cost the six year old Demoman his original set of adoptive parents. Later, at the Crypt Grammar School for Orphans near Ullapool in the Scottish Highlands, the boy's bomb-making skills improved dramatically. His disposition and total number of intact eyeballs, however, did not.

Name: Destoroyah
Summary: Destoroyah (デストロイア, Desutoroia?, lit. Destroyer) is a crustacean kaiju created by Toho that first appeared in the 1995 Godzilla film, Godzilla vs. Destoroyah. Originally a colony of microscopic Precambrian crustaceans that mutated from exposure to the Oxygen Destroyer used to kill the first Godzilla in 1954, it created a monster able to splinter itself and recombine at will. Named after the biological weapon that created it, Destoroyah is the final opponent of Burning Godzilla in his final moments.

Name: Dewey Riley
Summary: Dwight “Dewey” Riley is one of the main characters of the Scream series. He's a retired cop (and former sheriff) and the ex-husband of Gale Weathers, and a survivor of the first Woodsboro murders. During the first Ghostface's 1996 killing spree, he lost his sister to the killer, which served as his motivation to assist Sam during the 2022 killings. Since 1996, he’s had to face many more Ghostface killers, even being the one to kill Roman Bridger.

Name: Diamond Dogs
Summary: The Diamond Dogs were a PMC (Private Military Contractor) formed by Kazuhira Miller in the early 1980s, and commanded from 1984 onwards by Venom Snake, after recovering from his coma. Under his command, it would become an extremely powerful and highly influential player in the worldwide military-industrial complex, taking on jobs for all clients. The organization would end up at odds with XOF, the covert strike force of the shadow government known as The Patriots, due to the feud between Big Boss/Venom Snake and XOF's leader, Skull Face. Ultimately, Diamond Dogs would emerge victorious, with Venom Snake and Kazuhira Miller dealing the finishing blows to Skull Face and scattering XOF. The PMC would remain in operation for roughly a decade more, before being supplanted and its strength absorbed by Big Boss' military fortress nation, Outer Heaven.

Name: Dick Gumshoe
Summary: Dick Gumshoe is a homicide detective from the Ace Attorney series. He used to work under characters such as Phoenix Wright, Franziska von Karma, and Godot. However, he now works under Miles Edgeworth. Gumshoe will usually take care of the initial investigation and is always willing to back Edgeworth up. He will even go behind a prosecutor's back for a case.

Name: DJ Music Man
Summary: https://vsbattles.fandom.com/wiki/File:GlamrockFreddylikesDJMM.ogg

Name: Don Kanonji
Summary: Don Kanonji (ドン・観音寺, Don Kanonji), real name Misaomaru Kanonji (観音寺 ミサオ丸, Kanonji Misaomaru) is the host of the Television show Casual Soul Realm Assault Trip, commonly shortened to Cazh Soul.

Name: Douglas Gordon
Summary: Captain Douglas Gordon (ダグラス・ゴードン Dagurasu Gōdon) is the captain of the Gotengo in the 2004 Godzilla film, Godzilla: Final Wars. He is portrayed by UFC Hall of Famer Don Frye.

Name: Dracula Duck
Summary: Count Dracula Duck (Or in some cases, referred as Drake Von Vladstone) is a Disney character and provides the role as the Final Boss in the game, Ducktales for NES, later to be the Final Boss once more for its Remastered version for the Wii U, Ducktales Remastered.

Name: Drain Deimos
Summary: The Drain Deimos (ドレインディモス) are fleas which have been mutated by the t-Virus. Their only confirmed sighting was during the Raccoon City Destruction Incident, in which they were infected by feeding on blood from zombies. Like many other arthropods, the fleas responded to the virus by dramatically increasing in size, strength and aggression, as well as growing more humanoid anatomy, such as its arms and legs.

Name: Dudley
Summary: Dudley is a character in the Street Fighter series. He is a professional boxer known for being quite the gentleman.

Name: Dung Defender
Summary: Ogrim, one of the King's most trusted Five Knights and a Boss in the Waterways. After being defeated, he gifts The Knight the Defender's Crest.

Name: E. Honda
Summary: Edmond Honda, better known as E. Honda, is a recurring character in the Street Fighter series. Having been around since The World Warrior, this practitioner of sumo wrestling is bent on proving the greatness of said art.

Name: Earl Devereaux
Origin: Cloudy with a Chance of Meatballs
Summary: Earl Devereaux is the police officer from the town of Swallow Falls island. He is one of the main characters and a secondary protagonist of Cloudy with a Chance of Meatballs and Cloudy with a Chance of Meatballs 2. He is portrayed as a tall and muscular cop with incredible athletic skills.

Name: Ed (Street Fighter)
Summary: Ed is a playable character introduced in Street Fighter V. Ed is one of Shadaloo's many victims, having been subjected to cruel experiments since childhood that enhanced his physical abilities and grented him control of Psycho Power. Ed's fate was to become a loyal soldier and future spare body for M. Bison, but following the collapse of the facility he was being kept in, Ed was found and taken away by Balrog, who planned to exploit his powers for potential future economical gain.

Name: Ed Wuncler III
Summary: Edward "Ed" Wuncler III is the grandson of Ed Wuncler I and son of Ed Wuncler II. He is a drunken, trigger-happy ex-soldier freshly discharged from active duty in Iraq.

Name: Edwin Murray
Summary: Edwin Murray is the loving husband of Fiona Murray and father of his son, David Murray. Despite his love for them, due to all of the commissions by Fazbear Entertainment, Edwin was so engrossed in his work that he didn't have enough time to spend. Before David's third birthday party however, Fiona decides to help out at Fall Fest, dying after a brief fire and leaving Edwin alone with David.

Name: El Fuerte
Summary: El Fuerte is a luchador and cook from Mexico. He wants to become the ultimate chef, and in order to accomplish such dream he enters the third world tournament with the aim to collect recipes from the strongest fighters around and prove his might as a warrior. His cooking skill is quite mediocre and he doesn't realize how terrible his dishes are, reason why he often yelled at by his colleagues. Competing in the tournament hasn't helped him a bit in that regard, but his cheerful personality and burning passion granted him lots of friends, especially fellow wrestlers such as Zangief and E. Honda.

Name: Elder Hu
Summary: Elder Hu was a travelling sage who sought to purify the borderlands of Hallownest from the Infection. He reached the Mantis Village, but his own Infected mind made him see the Mantis Lords and the Tribe as afflicted by the plague.

Name: Elena (Street Fighter)
Summary: Elena is a princess from Kenya and fighter in the World Championship Tournament who specializes in Capoeira. Her social, cheery and energetic personality has let her make several friends while studying overseas, primarily in France and Japan.

Name: Elita-1 (Transformers One)
Summary: Elita-1 is the Tritagonist of the film Transformers One. A no-nonsense bot, Elita-1 was the head of an Energon mining crew, maintaining a spotless record while harvesting large amounts of energon for the good of Cybertron. Up until a mining incident involving Orion Pax and D-16, which involved her demotion, leading to a disdain particularly towards the former.

Name: Eminem (Fortnite)
Summary: Eminem is a former Boss/Event Character in Fortnite. He appears Spaghetti Grotto as a Boss, which sports Grenades and RG's Minigun and is a tough foe.[1] He also appears as a character in a Live Event as a large version of Marshall Never More that sings his song Godzilla.

Name: Endermite
Summary: The Endermite is a mysterious creature that appears from Ender Pearls.

Name: Engineer
Summary: This amiable, soft-spoken good ol' boy from tiny Bee Cave, Texas loves barbecues, guns, and higher education. Natural curiosity, ten years as a roughneck in the west Texas oilfields, and eleven hard science PhDs have trained him to design, build and repair a variety of deadly contraptions.

Name: Ernie The Giant Chicken
Summary: Ernie the Giant Chicken is a minor character that appears a few times in the adult television comedy series Family Guy. He is the arch nemesis of Peter Griffin, all because Peter tried to kill him over giving him an expired coupon, further resulting to them beating up each other in incredibly brutal brawls.

Name: Ethan Landry
Summary: Ethan Kirsch, also known under the alias of Ethan Landry, is a secondary antagonist of Scream VI.

Name: Ethan Winters
Summary: Ethan Winters is a major character in the Resident Evil series. An American systems engineer who was happily married to his wife Mia Winters, Ethan's normal life changed when Mia suddenly disappeared without a trace while working away from home.

Name: F.A.N.G
Summary: F.A.N.G (ファン Fan), known as the "Great F.A.N.G" or F.A.N.G-sama in Japanese, is a character in the Street Fighter series who first appeared in Street Fighter V. He was the fourth and last of the first new fighters confirmed for Street Fighter V and he is one of the game's bosses.

Name: Fairies (Touhou)
Summary: A fairy (妖精 yousei) is a small, simple, humanoid creature of magic that represents some aspect of nature. Many of them are also simple-minded. They tend to have short lives, but they will regenerate immediately after dying. In the games themselves, the fairies are by far the most common general stage enemy in the Touhou Project. The way they shoot danmaku all depends on what difficulty the player chooses and what stage they appear in. They can come in different kinds of colored dresses and hair, and can appear bigger than usual at times, such as the Sunflower Fairy.

Name: False Knight
Summary: The False Knight is one of the first bosses The Knight encounters within Hallownest. While appearing large and intimidating, in actuality, the False Knight is actually a small maggot who has taken on the shell of the great knight Hegemol. If the Knight enters the maggot's dream, it can encounter the False Knight's dream form, the Failed Champion, who is a far stronger and faster version of its real-world counterpart.

Name: Fei Long
Summary: Fei Long is a character from the Street Fighter series of fighting games. He makes his first appearance in Street Fighter II. He is an action movie star in Hong Kong, who spends hs free time testing his skills at martial arts tournaments.

Name: Finn the Human
Key: '''Seasons 1-Dungeon Train''' | '''Dungeon Train - Dad's Dungeon''' | '''Dad's Dungeon - Apple Wedding''' | '''Blade of Grass - Reboot''' | '''Two Swords - Elementals Arc''' | '''Season 10''' | '''Deceased'''
Summary: Finn the Human, real name Finn Mertens is the main character of Adventure Time. He, along with his adoptive brother Jake the Dog are the loyal champions of the Candy Kingdom. Finn vowed to keep the Kingdom and its residence safe at all cost. Finn is a very loyal and kind person, always giving a helping hand to those who need it.

Name: FLDSMDFR
Origin: Cloudy with a Chance of Meatballs
Summary: The Flint Lockwood Diatonic Super Mutating Dynamic Food Replicator, or FLDSMDFR for short, is the machine which the two Cloudy With A Chance Of Meatballs movies revolve around.

Name: Flintheart Glomgold
Summary: Flintheart Glomgold is a Disney character, the rival of Scrooge McDuck, and is one of the main antagonists of the Disney cartoon Ducktales. He is the world's 2nd richest duck, and plans to put Scrooge out of his league, even if it means engineering his rival's death. However, Scrooge tends to outplay Glomgold throughout any plot that he devises.

Name: Fluttershy (Human World)
Summary: Fluttershy is one of the main characters of My Little Pony Equestria Girls, and represents the Element of Kindness.

Name: Forest Law
Summary: Forest Law is a character that appears in the Tekken series of fighting games, and he is the son of Marshall Law. He dons the same fighting style and moves as his father, and also shares a friendship with Paul Phoenix.

Name: Fox (Minecraft)
Summary: Foxes are nocturnal neutral mobs that spawn commonly in taiga and snowy taiga biomes.

Name: Foxy (Five Nights at Freddy's)
Summary: https://vsbattles.fandom.com/wiki/File:PhoneGuyFoxy.ogg

Name: Frank West
Summary: This page contains or depicts disturbing and/or graphic content that some may find upsetting, and that is only intended for mature audiences. Please proceed with caution.

Name: Franz Gutentag
Summary: Franz Gutentag, real name Franz Schlechtnacht, is a one-episode character in the animated series, Family Guy.

Name: Franziska von Karma
Summary: Franziska is the daughter of the legendary Prosecutor Manfred von Karma, from whom she adopted tactics and her obsession with perfection. She usually carries a whip, or a riding crop when she was younger, and she will not hesitate to use it against anyone who tries to bother her.

Name: Fred (Cartoon)
Summary: Fred "Freddie/Freddy" Jones is the leader of the Mystery Inc. gang, and (more often than not) the driver of their van: The Mystery Machine, Fred is statuesque and brave; everything that the group's other male human member, Shaggy, isn't.

Name: Fredbear (Five Nights At Freddy's)
Summary: Fredbear is an animatronic mascot for Fredbear's Family Diner, and an important character withing the Five Nights at Freddy's franchise, though most notably Five Nights at Freddy's 4. He is one of two "spring-lock" suits, the other being Spring Bonnie. Both animatronics double as animatronics and suits. He would later be possessed by a Crying Child, becoming Golden Freddy, as well as being dreamed up as Nightmare Fredbear and Nightmare. Fredbear is also a secret animatronic in the game Ultimate Custom Night. Fredbear appears after the Death Token is used on Golden Freddy.

Name: Freddy & Friends
Summary: (Ragged moaning from animatronics can be heard) Oh no..." (Sound used by Golden Freddy during his jumpscare plays, call ends)

Name: Freddy Fazbear
Summary: https://vsbattles.fandom.com/wiki/File:PhoneGuyFreddy.ogg

Name: Frylock
Summary: Frylock is one of the four main characters in Aqua Teen Hunger Force. He is the most rational and intelligent member of the Aqua Teens. He is also considered to be a scientist; although, some of his motives and means of doing scientific research are a bit shady at times.

Name: Gale Weathers
Summary: Gale Weathers (formerly Gale Riley) appears in the Scream films as an ambitious, strong-willed news reporter, journalist, and writer who ultimately joins forces with Sidney Prescott and Dewey Riley, the latter of whom she eventually falls in love with and marries, in order to investigate and stop the Ghostface murders.

Name: Galien
Summary: Galien was a brave and undefeated warrior who claimed to be the strongest in Hallownest and desired to prove his valour to the Pale King as a Knight. He travelled to Deepnest in order to test his strength, but eventually found death instead.

Name: Gargwa
Summary: Gargwa are Bird Wyverns introduced in Monster Hunter Portable 3rd.

Name: Garoga Spider
Summary: The Garoga Spider (ガロガスパイダー) is a kaiju created by Toho that first appeared in the ninth episode of Zone Fighter, Search for the Secret of the Red Spider!.

Name: Garrador
Summary: Garradors are hosts enhanced by the Plaga parasite, clad in armor and claws to enhance their killing efficiency, but chained in cells with their eyelids sewn shut to keep it controlled. They are encountered by Leon Kennedy during his mission to Spain.

Name: Gendrome
Summary: Gendrome are Bird Wyverns introduced in Monster Hunter.

Name: General Tesler
Summary: General Tesler is the main antagonist of TRON: Uprising. He is one of CLU's generals and is both extremely ambitious and a coldly calculating sadist. Tesler rules over Argon City from his command ship.

Name: Gezzoora
Summary: Gezzoora is a kaiju and an antagonist in the manga, "SD Godzilla World: Godzilla Kun".

Name: Ghostface (1996)
Summary: The Ghostface killers of 1996 are a pair of high school seniors, Billy Loomis and Stu Macher, who terrorize the town of Woodsburo one year after killing Maureen Prescott. The two would call their victim’s phone, taunting them with a voice changer before attacking them while dressed in a mask and cloak. Together, they ended the lives of six people, all before being killed by their main target, Sidney Prescott.

Name: Ghostface (1998)
Summary: The Ghostface killers of 1998 are Nancy Loomis and Mickey Altieri, whom team up for a series of copycat murders based on the 1996 killers of the same alias. Together, they terrorize Windsor College in pursuit of Sidney Prescott.

Name: Ghostface (2011)
Summary: The Ghostface killers of 2011 are Jill Roberts and Charlie Walker, two high school students who seek to gain fame from their murders. Together, they massacred the town of Woodsboro, in hopes of going down in history as the survivors of their own tragedy. However, Jill would go on to betray Charlie, hoping to become the sole survivor of the incident. Jill's reign as the sole survivor would soon be thwarted by her cousin, Sidney Prescott, after she awoke in the ICU.

Name: Ghostface (2022)
Summary: The Ghostface killers of 2022 are Richie Kirsch and Amber Freeman. The couple met on Reddit after being disappointed by the release of Stab (2021), and so began to form a plan to give Hollywood new material for a proper Stab movie. Their scheme ended with several dead, until it was stopped by Sidney Prescott, Gale Weathers, Sam Carpenter, and Tara Carpenter.

Name: Ghostface (2023)
Summary: The Ghostface killers of 2023, Wayne Bailey, Ethan Landry, and Quinn Bailey were the culprits of the New York Murders. The trio are a family, seeking revenge for the death of Richie Kirsch, the brother of Ethan and Quinn and the son of Wayne. Together, they attempt to kill Samantha Carpenter and Tara Carpenter, going after Gale Weathers and many other victims along the way.

Name: Giadrome
Summary: Giadrome is a Bird Wyvern introduced in Monster Hunter Freedom 2. It is physically very similar to the Velocidrome, the only key difference being the pale blue colouration and the presence of a frost sac.

Name: Giant Medic
