Name: Saitama
Summary: Saitama (サイタマ?) is a human from Z-City who; through rigorous (sort of) training broke through his human limiters and achieved unbelievable strength and abilities. Never breaking a sweat, the name One Punch Man is fitting for the effortless wins Saitama has achieved through the series. Never going beyond a simple brawl, his sheer strength, speed, and power have effortlessly mowed down anyone in his way.

Name: Saizou Komiya
Summary: Saizo Komiya (小宮 砕蔵, Komiya Saizo) was an antagonist to Tsukune Aono and Moka Akashiya and was the first enemy that was featured in the anime and manga adaptions of the series. In his first appearance, Saizo was portrayed as a typical school bully and in the manga was said to have been forced into Yōkai Academy because he molested women in the Human world.

Name: Sakura Kasugano
Summary: Sakura Kasugano (春日野 さくら, Kasugano Sakura) is a character in the Street Fighter series who made her debut in Street Fighter Alpha 2. She is a seemingly normal Japanese high school girl. Sakura decided to take on street fighting after witnessing her idol Ryu in battle. She has managed to copy and learn some of Ryu's techniques but really wants him to train her personally. She uses a self-taught imitation of Ryu's martial art with her own versions of his special techniques.

Name: Sam Flynn
Summary: Sam Flynn: Your boss works for the CEO, and the CEO works for the shareholders. Now, do you know who the biggest shareholder is? Security Guard: I don't know some kid?... You're Mr. Flynn? Why? This is your fathers company! Sam Flynn: Not anymore.

Name: Samantha Carpenter
Summary: Having run from a troubled past, Samantha Carpenter returns to her haunted small California hometown to aid her younger sister and her group of friends against a new Ghostface entity. She is revealed to have been the daughter of Billy Loomis, who had cheated on Sidney with a girl named Christina Carpenter. Later, she and the Core Four (consisting of herself, her younger sister and the Meeks-Martin twins) are confronted with a series of Ghostface entities in New York City.

Name: Santa’s Little Helper
Summary: Santa’s Little Helper is the family dog in The Simpsons.

Name: Sark
Summary: Sark is the secondary antagonist in TRON. He was written by Ed Dillinger, and became the commander of the MCP's army and overseer of the games fought on the Game Grid. He was a merciless and evil program, willing to do anything that pleased the MCP. Sark was in charge of forcing the programs that believed in the users to play video game type gladiator games with personnel from Sark's Army as the opponents.

Name: Satoru (Mumen Rider)
Summary: Mumen Rider is a character from the Manga/Anime One Punch Man.

Name: Scooby Doo (Cartoon)
Summary: Scoobert "Scooby" Doo is the titular main protagonist of the animated franchise of the same name. He is a Great Dane, the mascot of Mystery Inc, and best friend of Shaggy Rogers.

Name: Scott Pilgrim
Summary: Scott William Pilgrim is the titular protagonist of the Scott Pilgrim media franchise.

Name: Scout
Summary: https://vsbattles.fandom.com/wiki/File:Meet_The_Scout_%22Grass_grows%22.wav

Name: Scrooge McDuck
Summary: Scrooge McDuck was born in Glasgow, Scotland in 1867 to a poor family and was the oldest of three siblings. At the age of 10, Scrooge became a shoe polisher to earn more money for his family, but his first client scammed him by paying with an American dime, unusable in Scotland. Nevertheless, Scrooge keeps the dime and, recognizing it as the start of something big, moves to the U.S. at age 13 to work as a river-boater with his uncle.

Name: Sean Keanan
Summary: Sean Keanan is a psychopath appearing in Dead Rising and Dead Rising: Chop Till You Drop. As the leader of the True Eye cult, Sean is obsessed with "purifying" survivors by killing them to cleanse their "tainted" blood. His cult members roam the mall until Frank West discovers their hideout in Colby's Movieland and defeats Sean.

Name: Sensei (Club Penguin)
Summary: Sensei (labeled ?????? before his identity was revealed) is a character in Club Penguin. A long-lived ninja master, he resides in the Dojo he built where he teaches penguins, who he refers to as his students, about the ancient art of Card-Jitsu.

Name: Shadow (Kingdom Hearts)
Summary: Shadow is the most common Heartless species usually found across nearly all worlds the main cast visits. While they may look cute, they are legitimately dangerous creatures one should watch out for.

Name: Shadow Ring
Summary: Shadow Ring is an A-Class Rank 32 hero for the Hero Association.

Name: Shaggy Rogers (Cartoon)
Summary: Norville "Shaggy" Rogers is a member of Mystery Inc., and the owner and best friend of their team's mascot: Scooby Doo, a talking Great Dane.

Name: Shelly De Killer
Summary: Shelly de Killer is the third heir to a line of assassins known as de Killer. De Killer is an assassin for hire, and after killing his victim, leaves behind a card with a pink shell on it as a signal that it was him who killed this person. This not to take credit for the kill, but take any blame or suspension off the person who hired him as a suspect. Authorities have been after him for years but he has always slipped away and kept from meeting any justice to his crimes.

Name: Sherry Birkin
Summary: Sherry Birkin is one of the main characters in the Resident Evil series. She was born around 1986 to the Umbrella virologist, William Birkin, and his research colleague and new wife, Annette, when the two were both working at the Arklay Laboratory. She is one of the survivors of the Raccoon City incident, thanks to Claire Redfield and Leon S. Kennedy, who came to her aid. They eventually escaped the fallen city together.

Name: Sheva Alomar
Summary: Sheva Alomar (シェバ・アローマ Sheba Arōma) is a fictional character in the Resident Evil horror video series by Capcom. She first appeared in Resident Evil 5 as one of the main characters. She was introduced in the E3 trailer and later on in E3 demo videos where she was a playable character that assists Chris Redfield throughout the game. She was introduced in 2009's Resident Evil 5 as a native African operative of the Bioterrorism Security Assessment Alliance (BSAA) and a new partner of the series' veteran Chris Redfield. The character was met with mostly positive reception, but has yet not returned for any further installment of the series. Operating as part of its West African branch. She was assigned to the current mission to assist Chris Redfield, who was unfamiliar with the area. A versatile fighter with extensive experience, her ability to use firearms is on par with Chris. She is much smaller and more flexible than Chris, enabling her to perform certain maneuvers that Chris cannot. In turn, this allows Chris to throw her up to high ledges, or over large gaps in order to reach areas or objectives that a lone operative couldn't reach.

Name: Shin Nemoto
Summary: Shin Nemoto (Nemoto Shin) is one of the Eight Bullets who works for Overhaul and the Shie Hassaikai. Shin appears cynical because he could never find anyone worthy of his trust and friendship, thanks to his Quirk. He states that emotions are unnecessary to carry out objectives, but it is unknown if he believes this or if it was just a way to demoralize Lemillion as he fought Overhaul.

Name: Shinichi Ozaki
Summary: Ensign Shinichi Ozaki (尾崎 真一) is a Mutant that was a member of M-Organization, which is part of the Earth Defense Force. He served under Captain Douglas Gordon aboard the Gotengo. He serves as the main protagonist of 2004 Godzilla film, Godzilla: Final Wars.

Name: Shockirus
Summary: Shockirus is a mutated sea louse kaiju created by Toho that first appeared in the 1984 Godzilla film, The Return of Godzilla.

Name: Shrieker
Summary: Shrieker is an extremely cruel and evil Hollow, previously a serial killer in his human life, he hunts down and torments his victims, was eventually killed and sent to hell for his heinous crimes while alive by Ichigo Kurosaki.

Name: Sid (Ice Age)
Summary: Sidney, known more commonly as Sid, is one of the main protagonists of the Ice Age franchise. He is a ground sloth who was part of a herd of different animals after a number of adventures and experiences brought them all together.

Name: Sidney Prescott
Summary: Sidney Prescott is the main protagonist of the Scream film series.

Name: Sieg (Fate/Apocrypha)
Summary: nan

Name: Silverfish (Minecraft)
Summary: The Silverfish is a rare kind of monster found either high up in the mountains or in the strongholds near the End. They are quite weak individually, though they often come in very large groups.

Name: Slime (Minecraft)
Summary: A Slime is a hostile mob that spawns in caves underground or in swamps. It is squishy and can vary in sizes. The smallest of the slimes are harmless and deal no damage. However, the bigger the slime is, the more capable it is to harm a player.

Name: Sludge Jellyfish
Summary: Sludge Jellyfish is a member of the Monster Association, and like Phoenix Man, he is one of the few rational monsters who aren't prompt to attack humans on sight, and by his own accord a monster who bears grudges. Sludge Jellyfish's body is comprised of liquids, giving him a natural resistance to physical attacks and the ability to absorb other liquids into his body.

Name: Snake Jailbird
Summary: Chester Turley, better known as Snake Jailbird, is a recurring antagonist in the animated TV series The Simpsons and a minor antagonist in the 2007 theatrical film The Simpsons Movie. He is a recidivist criminal, always getting arrested, but rarely being kept locked up for long. He speaks with a "Valley Boy" accent and has a tattoo of a snake on his arm, which is presumably the source of his nickname.

Name: Sneed
Summary: Sneed is a farmer that appears in the episode E-I-E-I-(Annoyed Grunt). He is the owner of the convenience store Sneed's Feed and Seed (Formerly Chuck's).

Name: Sniper
Summary: The Sniper is one of the support classes in Team Fortress 2. His job is to defend the base while also attacking enemy targets from afar. Half rugged outdoorsman, half alien observer, this taciturn strip of beef jerky has spent the better part of his life alone in the bush, slow baking under the Australian sun.

Name: Snow Golem (Minecraft)
Summary: The Snow Golem is a constructable entity. It mainly throws snowballs at the enemies, doing absolutely no damage to them.

Name: Snowball 2
Summary: Snowball 2 is the black cat that The Simpsons family took in after their original cat, Snowball 1, was killed. Snowball 2 is often portrayed as fairly intelligent for an animal, understanding human english, and pulling off human activities such as dancing. Aside from her decent intelligence shown every now and then, she is your typical stereotypical cat. She lived as the Simpsons family cat for many years until being ran over and killed by Dr. Herbert in season 15.

Name: Snowball V
Summary: nan

Name: Sokka
Summary: Sokka was a Water Tribe warrior of the Southern Water Tribe and the son of Chief Hakoda and Kya.

Name: Soldier
Summary: I have personally killed 6,578 men in cold blood while looking them in the eye; jumped on 1,336 live grenades; and stuffed fourteen feet of my own intestine back into my stomach. If that doesn't scare you out of your frilly pink leotards, guess what: You are an idiot and you hate America.

Name: Solf J. Kimblee
Summary: Solf J. Kimblee (ゾルフ・J・キンブリー, Zorufu J Kinburī), the Crimson Lotus Alchemist (紅蓮の錬金術師, Guren no Renkinjutsushi), sometimes referred to as the Crimson Alchemist, is a recurring antagonist in the Fullmetal Alchemist series. He is a former State Alchemist and special agent working under the direct orders of Führer King Bradley. Admittedly sadistic and arguably psychopathic, Kimblee was imprisoned in Central City for several years after his official involvement in the Ishval Civil War for having infamously turned his unique brand of combustion-based combat alchemy on people who were not on his government-approved kill list. Due to conspiratorial acts at the top of government, Kimblee is officially exonerated of his crimes so as to serve as the Führer's hidden left hand in the secret battles to come.

Name: Sora (Kingdom Hearts V Cast)
Summary: Sora is the main protagonist of Kingdom Hearts V Cast. Sora is forced to sleep by Maleficent to traverse worlds to find the whereabouts of Donald Duck and Goofy, and save the universe from the darkness.

Name: Sora (Kingdom Hearts)
Summary: Sora is a cheerful, young boy hailing from the Destiny Islands and the main protagonist of the Kingdom Hearts series. Longing to see the worlds outside of his own, he and his friends Riku and Kairi pledged to build a raft and set out together. However, on their planned day of departure, a freak storm hit their home and their world was subsequently engulfed by the Darkness. It was at this time that Sora unlocked his ability to wield a Keyblade, a weapon of legend that is said to bring salvation or destruction but is thrown into a Corridor of Darkness despite his efforts to combat the shadows that were swarming his home. Awakening in Traverse Town, he soon sets out with Goofy and Donald Duck, attendants to King Mickey, to discover the mystery behind the darkness and reunite with his friends.

Name: Sora's Heartless
Summary: Sora's Heartless is the main antagonist of Kingdom Hearts coded and its remake, Kingdom Hearts Re:coded. He is the Heartless of the digital replica of Data-Sora that desires to consume the Datascape and the Real World.

Name: Soul Master
Summary: Soul Master is a main boss in Hollow Knight. Defeating him grants the Desolate Dive Spell. The Soul Tyrant is his dream variant. Soul Master is the leader of the Soul Sanctum of Hallownest, which searched for ways to expand the minds of bugs and attain pure focus.

Name: Spider (Minecraft)
Summary: The Spider is a common Minecraft monster from the Overworld. They're larger than usual monsters and are capable of climbing walls.

Name: Spopovich
Summary: Spopovich was a martial artist who was mind controlled by Babidi.

Name: Spot Master 6000
Summary: The Spot Master 6000 was a device used in the episode "The Krusty Plate" after SpongeBob had unsuccessfully tried to clean a spot off a plate via other means.

Name: Spring Mustachio
Key: '''Beginning of Series''' | '''Monster Raid Arc and Onwards'''
Summary: Spring Mustache (バネヒゲ, Banehige) is an A-Class Superhero, rank 28. He was partnered up with Golden Ball to investigate the monster rumor in Z-City.

Name: Spy
Summary: This Spy has already breached our defenses... You've seen what he's done to our colleagues! And worst of all: He could be any one of us.

Name: SSS9
Summary: SSS9 is the main antagonist of Godzilla vs Biollante. He was a spy and assassin.

Name: Starlight Glimmer
Key: '''From Season 5 to 8''' | '''Series Finale onward''' | '''Equestria Girls Human Self'''
Summary: Starlight Glimmer was the main antagonist of Season 5 of My Little Pony: Friendship is Magic, and later one of the show's main protagonists.

Name: Steven Chapman
Summary: Steven Chapman is a psychopath appearing in Dead Rising.

Name: Stewie Griffin
Summary: Stewie Griffin is one of the main characters in the animated series, Family Guy.

Name: Stinkmeaner
Summary: Colonel H. Stinkmeaner, simply known by all as Stinkmeaner, is the secondary antagonist in The Boondocks series. Stinkmeaner is described as one of the most evil human beings to ever walk the earth. He is sadistic, nihilistic and overall horrible to everyone he meets. He enjoys the pain and anguish of other people. He claims to hate everyone in general, but in truth, he simply loves being evil. He lived a long, terrible life. When he got killed by Robert Freeman, he is sent to hell, where he literally felt truly much more happy than he ever had been in life and considers it much better than jail.

Name: Stu Macher
Summary: Stu Macher aids Billy Loomis in the 1996 Woodsboro murders, donning a ghost mask and cloak that would later be known as the Ghostface costume. He is later killed by Sidney Prescott after she drops a television set over his head, electrocuting him.

Name: Suisei Hoshimachi
Summary: Suisei Hoshimachi is a hard-working, modest, multitalented singer and aspiring idol. As such, she focuses very heavily on singing, dancing and performing, having performed in multiple concerts. She's also a master of Tetris. While she's normally among the more level-headed members of Hololive, when Suisei is angry, she displays a different side of her, known of Suicopath, where she's violent, temperamental and unforgiving. At that stage, few dare oppose her. She has a friendly rivalry with Marine Houshou.

Name: Suki
Summary: Suki is a major character in the animated series, Avatar: The Last Airbender.

Name: Sung Jin-Woo (Novel)
Summary: nan

Name: Sunset Shimmer
Key: '''Human''' | '''Unicorn Form''' | '''Element of Magic (Demon Form)''' | '''Pony-Up Form''' | '''Daydream Shimmer'''
Summary: Sunset Shimmer is a reformed villain from My Little Pony: Friendship is Magic.

Name: SWATbot (Archie Comics)
Summary: SWATbots are military robots in the Sonic the Hedgehog comic series and its spin-offs published by Archie Comics.

Name: Sweetie Belle
Summary: Tier: At least 9-B, likely 8-A

Name: T-A.L.O.S.
Summary: T-A.L.O.S. was created to be a superior and controllable version of the Tyrant, and Umbrella North America's response to Umbrella Europe's Nemesis project.

Name: Tara Carpenter
Summary: https://vsbattles.fandom.com/wiki/File:TaraMainQuote.mp3.ogg

Name: Tenga Onigawara
Summary: Tenga Onigawara (鬼瓦天牙, Onigawara Tenga) is the banchou of Salt Middle School and an unofficial member of the Body Improvement Club.

Name: Terry Bogard (Street Fighter)
Summary: Terry: You and I walk down different paths. And maybe the strength we're both after takes a different form, but...

Name: Terry Bogard (The King of Fighters)
Key: '''Prologue Chapter (KOF '94) ''' | '''Chapter of Orochi Saga (KOF '95 to KOF '97)''' | '''Chapter of NESTS Saga (KOF '99 to KOF 2001)''' | '''KOF Sky Stage''' | '''Chapter of Ash Saga (KOF 2003 to KOF XIII)'''
Summary: nan

Name: The Brute (Lego Fortnite)
Summary: The Brute from Lego Fortnite is by far the most powerful creature in the game. Lego Fortnite is chock-full of hostile creatures, hazards, and enemies, but none are as intimidating as the towering Brutes that roam the various Biomes in your World. Equipped with four devastating attacks and an impressive health pool, tracking down and defeating these aggressive beasts can seem near impossible without upgraded Weapons and Health Charms. But if you manage to take down a Brute, you'll be rewarded with Brute Scales which can be used to upgrade your crafting bench.

Name: The Collector (Hollow Knight)
Summary: The Collector is a hidden boss in Hollow Knight. The Collector is a Void creature. It lives hidden away in the locked Tower of Love along with a large collection of bugs from throughout Hallownest that are preserved, both dead and alive, in glass jars.

Name: The Daycare Attendant
Summary: The Daycare Attendant is a recurring antagonist in Five Nights At Freddy's: Security Breach.

Name: The Dazzlings
Summary: The Dazzlings are the villains of the My Little Pony: Friendship is Magic movie Rainbow Rocks.

Name: The Hateocracy
Summary: The Hateocracy are a gang of elderly, nasty, self-hating bigots and the major antagonists of the episode "Stinkmeaner 3: The Hateocracy".

Name: The Hunter (Hollow Knight)
Summary: A true Hunter has no home, no kingdom and I'm eager for new prey. You bear the mark now, but that's only the beginning. That mark will become a part of you, will engrave itself deep within, and that yearning to hunt... It will never leave.

Name: The Judge (Ace Attorney)
Summary: There is not much known about The Judge. All that is known is The Judge is the one often presiding over the cases in Ace Attorney. While he is sometimes bumbling, and a little slow with details, he still stands for truth and justice. Even refusing to leave the courtroom despite the witness and killer threat of He courtroom with a bomb, until a verdict had been passed down. He does his best with his verdicts and has claimed he had never gotten a verdict wrong in his life many times before

Name: The Knight (Hollow Knight)
Summary: The Knight is the playable character of Team Cherry's hit Indie Metroidvania game, Hollow Knight. Their species was created as vessels by the Pale King to carry the Infection spread by the Radiance. Many details about the character, including their name, are left ambiguous; though it is likely that they do not have one, as all vessels except for one were considered impure by the King, and left to rot in the Abyss. However, the Knight and some of its other siblings managed to escape.

Name: The Looper (Fortnite Battle Royale)
Summary: The Looper (Also simply known as The Player) is the unnamed protagonist of the third-person shooter Fortnite (Battle Royale). The objective of the game is to be the last one standing (or be the last team standing) in a map of 100 other people, finding loot such as guns while avoiding the dangerous storm.

Name: The Looper (Lego)
Summary: The Looper (Also simply known as The Player) is the unnamed protagonist of the sub-game Lego Fortnite. The focus of the game is on long-term survival, crafting and online cooperation with friends.

Name: The Mimic (Five Nights at Freddy's)
Summary: Now I will tell you a story about a mother and a little boy who lived alone in a cabin in the dark woods. There was a monster in the woods. But the mother caught it and kept it locked in the basement. The monster always made scary noises at night, but the mother would tell the boy not to worry because it could never get out. Then she would sing the boy a lullaby to sleep. One day, the monster stopped growling and instead, listened and learned the lullaby. The next day when the mother went out to find food, the monster sang the lullaby from the basement. The little boy heard the lullaby and opened the door.

Name: The Mooninites
Summary: - Ignignokt

Name: The One You Shouldn't Have Killed
Summary: nan
ID: The One You Shouldn't Have Killed-FiveNightsAtFreddy's-9

Name: The Phantom (Ace Attorney)
Summary: The Phantom is an international spy with no true identity to speak of. He is a human incapable of experiencing emotions the way humans do with his only drive being to accomplish the missions delivered to him. For the majority of Dual Destinies, he lies under the guise of detective Bobby Fullbright.

Name: The Player (A Heist With Markiplier)
Summary: [redacted] is the being through which the viewer sees the events of A Heist With Markiplier. Though they frequently showcase their shapeshifting capabilities, no one within the lore notices their changes.

Name: The Player (Club Penguin)
Summary: The Player was the playable character of Club Penguin, a game that took place in an island inhabited by penguins. The Penguin's name depended on the player.

Name: The Player (Minecraft)
Summary: The Player is the protagonist of Minecraft. Known as either Steve or Alex depending on the player's choice, they are a lone miner in an endless blocky world, trying their best to survive.

Name: The Radiance
Summary: The Radiance is the forgotten goddess of Light of the Moth Tribe and source of the Infection plaguing Hollownest. She is the final boss of both the main game and the Godmaster DLC. When the Pale King took over the lands of Hollownest, he attempted to destroy her by erasing all evidence of her existence and allowing her to fade out of memory.

Name: The Rainman
Summary: Jason Baker, known under the alias Caleb, otherwise known as the Rainman is the titular main antagonist of the 2023 indie-horror game, The Rainman.

Name: The Visitor (Fortnite)
Summary: The Visitor is a mysterious entity who had arrived to the planet via a meteorite in Season 3 of Fortnite: Battle Royale, responsible for having launched the rocket during Season 4 as well. Though nothing is known about their original intentions, it was through the launching of this rocket that a multitude of spatial and temporal rifts were opened up within the atmosphere, leading to the events in Seasons 4 - 6.

Name: Thunder Hawk
Summary: Thunder Hawk is the gentle and wise hero of the Thunderfoot Tribe in Mexico. He seeks revenge against Shadaloo and M. Bison, which are guilty of many crimes against his people, such as poisoning the land, kidnapping villagers, murdering their leader Arroyo Hawk (T. Hawk's father) and turning Noembelu and Julia (the latter being T. Hawk's fiancee) into mindless assassins.

Name: Tommy Oliver
Key: '''Civilian''' | '''Mighty Morphin Power Rangers: Season 1''' | '''Mighty Morphin Power Rangers: Season 2''' | '''Mighty Morphin Power Rangers: Season 3''' | '''Red Zeo Form''' | '''Dino Thunder Black''' | '''Super Dino Mode'''
Summary: Tommy Oliver is the Green Mighty Morphin Ranger, White Mighty Morphin Ranger, Red Zeo Ranger, Red Turbo Ranger I & the Black Dino Ranger. He is often considered the greatest Power Ranger of all time both in and out of the actual show for his many accomplishments on several different teams. He is a fan favorite, the most reoccurring ranger, and second most reoccurring character in the entire show next to Bulk. He is also one of the strongest rangers.

Name: Tomomo
Summary: Tomomo is the self-made final boss of 100% Orange Juice. Tomomo is a magical girl who ascended to godhood via unknown means. Despite her so called super interesting backstory, Tomomo was left as a background character. Through her frustration as a background character, Tomomo recreated the Orange Juice verse to make her the overarching antagonist. However, this wouldn't last long.

Name: Trent Fernandez-Mercer
Summary: Trent Fernandez-Mercer is the White Dino Thunder Ranger, who was initially corrupted by the White Dino Gem but then reformed when the evil was removed from him by his adopted father, Dr. Anton Mercer. When his biological parents were killed in an archaeological cave-in, Dr. Mercer took him in, though he still kept his original surname. He works at Hayley's Cyberspace as a waiter and draws in his spare time, though he keeps this secret because his father does not approve of his artistic endeavours.

Name: Trini Kwan
Summary: Trini Kwan is the original Yellow Ranger of the Power Rangers series. She was the caring and optimistic member of the team during the war against Rita and served as the tactics expert on-board the Dino Megazord. She would go on to become a world peace ambassador following her retirement as a Ranger.

Name: Tron (TRON)
Summary: Tron is one of the main protagonists of the TRON franchise. He is a security computer program written by Alan Bradley, and in 1982 was taken prisoner by the self-aware Master Control Program and forced to play on the Game Grid. His legendary skills and devotion to the users turned him into a formidable warrior and Disc Arena master.

Name: Truckasaurus
Summary: Truckasaurus is a giant mechanical truck/dinosaur first appearing in "Bart the Daredevil". It was inspired by the real life robotic dinosaur, Robosaurus.

Name: Tusk (Club Penguin)
Summary: Tusk, also known as the Supreme Master of Snow, is a walrus and the primary antagonist at the Card-Jitsu Party 2013, the true antagonist behind Card-Jitsu Snow, and the leader of the Snow Minions. He is the one who sent Scrap, Sly, and Tank out to defeat Sensei and destroy the Dojo. Tusk seems to have hatred for Sensei and his Ninjas. He used to train in the art of Card-Jitsu with Sensei, his childhood best friend, but Tusk turned on Sensei out of jealousy. Players could battle in his lair after receiving the Snow Gem.

Name: Twilight Sparkle (Pony World)
Key: '''Unicorn Form''' | '''Alicorn Form''' | '''The Ending of the End Alicorn Form''' | '''Elements of Harmony/Magic of Friendship''' | '''All Alicorn Magic''' | '''Post-Timeskip Alicorn Form''' | '''Rainbow Power''' | '''Equestria Girls Human form'''
Summary: Twilight Sparkle is the main protagonist of My Little Pony: Friendship is Magic.

Name: Twilight Sparkle (Sci-Twi)
Summary: Twilight Sparkle is one of the main protagonists in the My Little Pony: Equestria Girls series.

Name: Ty Lee
Summary: Ty Lee was a cheerful and energetic girl who hailed from the Fire Nation.

Name: Tyrant T-002
Summary: The Tyrant T-002 is, as its name implies, the second form of the Tyrant and the first successful product of the Tyrant Project, which sought to create the ultimate life form.

Name: Tyrant T-103
Summary: The Tyrant T-103 is the first successful Tyrant, no longer a prototype like previous models. With intelligence close to that of a human, the T-103 can follow orders and perform complex tasks, and it is for this reason that it is mass-produced, with models being used for hunting down and kill targets or acquire objects.

Name: U-8
Summary: U-8 is a B.O.W. created by Tricell from the combination of Plagas parasites with the DNA of several shelled organisms. It attacked BSAA agents Chris Redfield and Sheva Alomar as they explored the Tricell Africa facility.

Name: Uncle Ruckus
Summary: Uncle Ruckus (born July 4, 1939) is a fictional character and the main antagonist of the American animated sitcom The Boondocks. Voiced by Gary Anthony Williams, he first appeared on television in the show's pilot, "The Garden Party", on November 6, 2005. Created and designed by cartoonist Aaron McGruder, Ruckus enjoyed great success after appearing in the comic strip of the same name.

Name: Ursa (RWBY)
Summary: Ursai are large, bear-like Creatures of Grimm that first appeared in "The Emerald Forest" in Volume 1. They have appeared in two varieties: the smaller, more common Ursa Minor, and the larger, better armored and more powerful Ursa Major.

Name: Ustanak
Summary: Ustanak is a B.O.W. employed by Carla Radames in order to capture Jake Muller and use his blood for an enhanced C-Virus.

Name: Utahime Iori
Summary: Respect! Your! Elders!

Name: Uumuu
Summary: Uumuu is a main boss in Hollow Knight. It guards Monomon the Teacher, one of the Dreamers. Uumuu is an intelligent yet Infected being similar to the Uomas and Oomas infesting Fog Canyon. It defends Monomon's chamber at the heart of the Teacher's Archives.

Name: Vampire Plant
Summary: The Vampire Plant (吸血植物 lit. Bloodsucking Plant) is a mutated plant kaiju created by Toho that first appears in the 1961 Toho film, Mothra.

Name: Vega
Summary: Vega, known in Japan as Balrog, also known as Claw, is a fictional character from the Street Fighter fighting game series by Capcom. Vega is a mask-wearing, claw-wielding fighter from Spain who uses a personal fighting style combining Japanese ninjutsu and Spanish bullfighting, earning him the nickname of "Spanish Ninja".

Name: Vegapunk (One Piece)
Key: '''With Satellites''' | '''With Sea Beast Weapons or PX·III''' | '''With Seraphim'''
Summary: The Vegapunks are a group of seven individuals who collectively represent the genius mind of Dr. Vegapunk, the leading scientist of the World Government. Unable to balance his overwhelming intelligence and the physical limitations of a single human body, Vegapunk created six Satellites — Lilith, Shaka, Edison, Pythagoras, Atlas, and York — each embodying a distinct aspect of his personality. Together, they operate as the core of Egghead Island, a technologically advanced island said to be 500 years ahead of the rest of the world.

Name: Velma (Cartoon)
Summary: Velma is the bespectacled resident genius of Mystery Inc., often being the one to decipher the clues and solve the crimes.

Name: Velocidrome
Summary: Velocidromes are Bird Wyverns introduced in Monster Hunter.

Name: Vengefly
Summary: Vengeflies are enemies in Hollow Knight. They are flying predators who inhabit many areas in Hallownest, although the Vengefly King is native to Greenpath.

Name: Verdugo
Summary: Salazar: So, maybe you have nine lives. But it doesn't matter now, Mr. Kennedy! I have sent my right hand to dispose of you. Leon S. Kennedy: Your right hand comes off?

Name: Victor Quartermaine
Summary: Lady Tottington: Victor, hadn't we agreed? No more thoughtless killing! Victor Quartermaine: Quite right, my dear, so I thought this one through very carefully: [aims rifle at bunny] It's off to bunny heaven for you, big ears!

Name: Videl
Summary: Videl is the daughter of Mr. Satan, who is very protective of her especially in respect to boys. She is a tough, tomboyish character raised with fame all around her. She grows up learning martial arts hoping to be as great as her father when in fact, unknown to herself, she is already better and stronger than him.

Name: Wakka (Kingdom Hearts)
Summary: Wakka is a minor character in the Kingdom Hearts series, originally from Final Fantasy X. He is one of the residents living in Destiny Islands and is part of a trio including Tidus and Selphie. In Sora's Dive to the Heart, he appears in the Destiny Islands area along with Selphie and Tidus. He asks Sora "What do you want outta life?"

Name: Wallace (Wallace & Gromit)
Summary: Wallace is one of the titular protagonists of the stop-motion animated comedy franchise Wallace & Gromit, in which he is a kindhearted, simple-minded inventor, who often creates new contraptions alongside his anthropomorphic dog Gromit to make conveniences to his life, although usually these inventions tend to fail.

Name: Wallflower Blush
Summary: Wallflower Blush is the hidden main antagonist of the My Little Pony: Equestria Girls special, Forgotten Friendship.

Name: Wandering Trader
Summary: The Wandering Trader is a passive mob from Minecraft. They can spawn anywhere in the Overworld, and come with their llamas and a variety of wares to sell in exchange for emeralds.

Name: Warfstache Automated Interview Automaton
Summary: The Warfstache Automated Interview Automaton is a robot being developed under Wilford Warfstache, modeled after him, to be able to conduct interviews on his behalf, and has currently reached its testing phase.

Name: Wayne Bailey
Summary: Wayne: There's a very special bond between a father and his first son. Which is why I helped him build this collection. Sam: This was, all his? Wayne: Yes, he was a very passioned collector and he inspired others. Ah, we had to kill those two wannabe film students because, well, we had to kill you first, Sam. I put the theater in their name, and good-old Detective Bailey would've just stumbled on it, but I didn’t have too because by golly, that Gale Weathers is one hell of a journalist. I built a tribute to my son, which is why this is where you have to die, Sam. Surrounded by all the things he loved the most.

Name: Wild Horn
Summary: Wild Horn, B-Class Rank 6, is a hero and member of the Hero Association. He was formerly a construction worker before becoming a hero, which helped influenced quite a lot of his current gear and motifs.

Name: William Afton (Games)
Key: '''William Afton''' | '''Post-Springlock Failure''' | '''Post-Fazbear Frights Fire''' | '''Ultimate Custom Night'''
Summary: https://vsbattles.fandom.com/wiki/File:WilliamAftonDeception.ogg

Name: William Birkin
Key: '''First and Second Form''' | '''Third and Fourth Form''' | '''Fifth Form'''
Summary: William Birkin was a researcher and virologist working for the Umbrella Corporation in Raccoon City, developing the T and G-Viruses among many other bioweapons. Bitter over Umbrella's refusal to give him a promotion, he slowly sabotaged his facilities and planned to betray them, but before he could do this, Umbrella intervened, and he was gunned down. Enraged, and barely alive, Birkin injected himself with the G-Virus, mutating into the monstrous G and causing the outbreak.

Name: Woody (Toy Story)
Summary: Woody, sometimes titled Sheriff Woody, is one of the main protagonists of the Toy Story franchise. Woody is a 50s-era smart toy that uses a pull string to repeat a select few phrases; however, when Andy (or any other human) isn't watching, Woody and the other toys would "wake up;" that is, switch from being inanimate objects to living toys. Before Andy got Buzz Lightyear for his birthday, Woody was Andy's favorite toy. After an initial falling-out with Buzz Lightyear over his own jealousy, Woody and Buzz would become respectable friends with one another.

Name: Xero
Summary: Xero was a warrior of Hallownest who believed that strength would always allow him a bright future. When his mind was infected, he hoped to fight against the plague with violence. Fueled by the same hope, he turned against the Pale King, for which he was executed.

Name: Xiliens (Godzilla Final Wars)
Summary: The Xiliens returned as the villains in Godzilla Final Wars nearly four decades later. Intending to harvest the mitochondria from human cells for sustenance, they again posed as allies to humanity, unleashing an army of monsters under their control before teleporting them all away. When their plan was exposed by the Earth Defense Force, the Xilien Commander was assassinated and usurped by his subordinate who became the Controller of Planet X. The Controller unleashed all of the Xiliens' mind-controlled kaiju on Earth and tried to eliminate all resistance, but the surviving members of the EDF used the Gotengo to free Godzilla from his prison in Antarctica. Godzilla swiftly eliminated most of the Xiliens' monsters before the Controller summoned his ultimate weapon, Monster X, to stop him. The Gotengo breached the Xilien Mothership and its crew were able to defeat the Controller and his minions. In a final act, the Controller set the Mothership to self-destruct, but the Gotengo was able to escape in time and help Godzilla overcome Monster X's final form, Keizer Ghidorah.

Name: Yancy (AHWM)
Summary: Yancy is one of the prisoners at Happy Trails Penitentiary. He was arrested after killing both of his parents, but discovered he enjoyed life in the prison.

Name: Yang Xiao Long (RWBY Chibi)
Summary: Yang Xiao Long is one of the characters of RWBY Chibi.

Name: Yasutora Sado (Chad)
Key: '''Substitute Shinigami Arc''' | '''Soul Society Arc''' | '''Arrancar Arc''' | '''Lost Agent Arc''' | '''Thousand Year Blood War Arc'''
Summary: Yasutora Sado (茶渡 泰虎, Sado Yasutora), also known as Chad (チャド, Chado) is a human teenager who lives in Karakura Town. He is a student at Karakura High School, where he is in the same class as Ichigo Kurosaki.

Name: Yawn (Resident Evil)
Summary: The Yawn was a snake-based B.O.W. that lurked around in the Spencer Mansion. It was nicknamed "Yawn" by the Arklay Laboratory team in reference to the way its mouth opens before attacking, which resembled a yawn.

Name: Yellow Rabbit (Return To The Pit)
Summary: The Yellow Rabbit is the main antagonist of the interactive novel, Return To The Pit. It is a supernatural entity of unknown nature which stalks Oswald during his trips to the past and eventually follows him home, impersonating his father. It can meet various fates depending on the route taken in the book.

Name: Zamtrios
Summary: Zamtrios are Amphibians introduced in Monster Hunter 4.

Name: Zangief
Summary: Zangief (Russian: Зангиев) also known as the "Red Cyclone", is a video game character created by Capcom. He is part of the Street Fighter series of fighting games, first starring in Street Fighter II. He is a national Russian hero who is always seen fighting for the glory of his country.

Name: Zhi (Dead Rising)
Summary: Prior to the zombie outbreak, Zhi already was on the verge of insanity. His wife left him, his kids didn't respect him and he lost his job at the pharmacy. With this sudden event, Zhi tries to become a monk and live in peace and harmony at the Zen Garden, and those who disturb him will meet their demise.

Name: Zombie (Dead Rising)

Name: Zombie (Resident Evil)
Summary: Zombies are the result of humans succumbing to the effects of the T-Virus. They are distinguishable by their resemblance to corpses caused by the extensive necrosis on their skin and body. Originally created by Umbrella scientists as result of experimentation, they would rarely be seen in action up until 1998, the year the first viral outbreak was caused deliberately by former Umbrella scientist James Marcus, resulting in the infection of most of Umbrella's employees located in the Arklay Mountains. The actions of the now infected would lead to the intervention of S.T.A.R.S. police force which resulted in the Ecliptic Express and Mansion Incidents, where several members of the team would be brutally murdered by the infected.

Name: Zombie Elephant (Resident Evil)
Summary: A Zombie Elephant is the product of an elephant succumbing to t-Virus infection. Currently, only one Zombie Elephant has been known to have existed, that being a Raccoon Zoo attraction named Oscar.

Name: Zombie Lion (Resident Evil)
Summary: The Zombie Lions were big cats residing at the Raccoon Zoo during the Raccoon City Destruction Incident. There were three lionesses and one male lion named Max.

Name: Zote the Mighty
Summary: Zote the Mighty, referred to as Zote for short, is a character from the Metroidvania, Hollow Knight. As a traveller from another land, Zote travels to the fallen kingdom of Hallownest to fufill his goal and title. Throughout the game he is seen merely as an NPC and has a gag boss fight within the 1st trial of the Colosseum of Fools. After defeating Zote, the player is then allowed to fight Zote's dreamworld counterpart, Grey Prince Zote.

Name: Zoteling
Summary: Zotelings are enemies in Hollow Knight. Figments of Bretta's mind.

Name: Zuko
Summary: Even as the prince of the Fire Nation, Zuko has always struggled in life, particularly in matching his prodigy sister Azula and getting his father's acknowledgment. This came to a head when Ozai punished him for a perceived slight by horrifically burning his face and sending him into exile, refusing to let him return until he had captured the Avatar. (This was intended to be an impossible task, since Aang had been missing for a century). Determined to prove his worth to his father, Zuko hunted Aang across the world for the first season while trying to find his own destiny. Eventually, Zuko betrays Iroh and helps Azula take over Ba Sing Se. Granted amnesty for his actions, Zuko is finally allowed to come home. He has his honor restored, the adoration of a nation, the love of his life, and the respect of his father. And he finds himself lacking. After some soul-searching, Zuko finally realizes what Iroh had always tried to teach him. After calling out Ozai for controlling him, making him feel worthless, burning his face, banishing him for three years and generally being an evil, contemptible douchebag, Zuko defects to join the Gaang as Aang's Firebending teacher. Though initially mistrusted, grudges dissolve into friendships and Zuko soon becomes a core member of the group. At the end of the series, Zuko becomes the new Fire Lord and strives to rebuild the world into an era of peace. And hopefully find his mother.
